)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,TIDE$ @[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@3TIDEX$ - TERMINATE SCANJK
)@@G@@NING MODE   @F@@@@ THE X-REGISTERS ARE RESTORED TO THEIR PREVIOUS VALUESJL
)@@G@@, THE PACKET@C@@@@ IS CLOSED, AND SCANNING MODE IS TERMINATED.    @[@@@@JM
)@@G@@SPACE @ @@@@       LMJ       X11,TIDEX$   @[@@@@SPACE @^@@@@            JN
)@@G@@     OR:    @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@       T$IDEX     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      JO
)@@G@@           UPON TERMINATION, A0 CONTAINS THE PACKET ADDRESS.@[@@@@SPACE JP
)@@G@@@A@@@@3TIDER$ - REINITIALIZE SCANNING MODE@F@@@@ THE X-REGISTERS ARE SAVJQ
)@@G@@ED, AND THE COLUMN POINTER IS SET TO ITS  @C@@@@ POSITION AT THE LAST CAJR
)@@G@@LL TO     TIDEX$     .  @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@       LA,XU     A0,ADDRESS-OFJS
)@@G@@-PACKET     @ @@@@       LMJ       X11,TIDER$   @[@@@@SPACE @^@@@@      JT
)@@G@@           OR:    @[@@@@SPACE @^@@@@       T$IDER    ADDRESS@[@@@@SPACE JU
)@@G@@@ @@@@3TCLR$ - CLEAR INPUT IMAGE    @F@@@@ RESETS THE COLUMN POINTER TO JV
)@@G@@ZERO IN ORDER TO READ THE NEXT CARD @F@@@@ IMAGE. IT'S EQUIVALENT TO CALJW
)@@G@@LING TIDEX$, THEN TIDE$, BUT FASTER.@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       LA,XU     AJX

)@@G@@. IF A0 IS  @B@@@@ NEGATIVE, THE COLUMN POINTER BACKS UP.   @[@@@@SPACE KC
)@@G@@@C@@@@          LA,XU     A0,#-OF-COLUMNS-TO-SKIP     @ @@@@          LMKD
)@@G@@J       X11,TSKIP$@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PRKE
)@@G@@OC:   @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@          T$SKIP    SKIPCOUNT @A@@@@3TCOL$ - MOVKF
)@@G@@E TO A SPECIFIED COLUMN @F@@@@ THE COLUMN POINTER IS SET TO THE NUMBER IKG
)@@G@@N A0.  THE FIRST COLUMN @]@@@@ IS ZERO.   @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       LA,XUKH
)@@G@@     A0,COLUMNUMBER     @ @@@@       LMJ       X11,TCOL$    @[@@@@SPACE KI
)@@G@@@]@@@@ THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@       T$COL     COLUMNUMBER  @B@@@@KJ
)@@G@@3TCOLN$ - OBTAIN CURRENT COLUMN POSITION  @C@@@@ A0 RETURNS WITH THE CURKK

)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@          T$COLN  @#@@@@KM
)@@G@@4NUMERIC ROUTINES @F@@@@ THERE ARE 4 TYPES OF NUMERIC ROUTINES - OCTAL, KN
)@@G@@DECIMAL, INTEGER, @E@@@@ AND FLOATING POINT. SINGLE AND DOUBLE PRECISIONKO
)@@G@@ FOR EACH IS@G@@@@ ALLOWED, AS WELL AS VARIABLE (FREE) AND FIXED FORMAT KP
)@@G@@(FIXED FORMAT     @F@@@@ SPECIFIES A MAXIMUM NUMBER OF COLUMNS TO SCAN, KQ
)@@G@@FREE FORMAT DOES  @E@@@@ NOT). THE RESPECTIVE SUBROUTINE NAMES ARE FORMEKR
)@@G@@D THUSLY:   @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@       1) START WITH A 'T'    @B@@@@      KS
)@@G@@ 2) ADD 'OCT' FOR OCTAL INTEGER     @B@@@@              'DEC' FOR DECIMAKT
)@@G@@L INTEGER   @B@@@@              'INT' FOR GENERAL INTEGER   @B@@@@      KU
)@@G@@        'FLO' FOR FLOATING POINT    @G@@@@       3) ADD 'V' OR 'F' FOR VKV
)@@G@@ARIABLE OR FIXED FORMAT, RESPECTIVELY     @C@@@@       4) ADD 'D' IF DOUKW
)@@G@@BLE PRECISION IS DESIRED@ @@@@       5) ADD '$' (AT LAST)   @[@@@@SPACE KX
)@@G@@@F@@@@ FOR EXAMPLE, TINTVD$ IS THE VARIABLE FORMAT DOUBLE PRECISION     KY
)@@G@@@F@@@@ INTEGER ROUTINE, AND TOCTF$ IS THE FIXED FORMAT SINGLE PRECISION KZ
)@@G@@@#@@@@ OCTAL ROUTINE.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ THE CORRESPONDING PROC NAMES LA
)@@G@@ARE FORMED BY REMOVING THE '$' AND  @G@@@@ INSERTING IT AFTER THE LEADINLB
)@@G@@G 'T'. FOR EXAMPLE,    T$IDE    CALLS     @]@@@@ TIDE$.     @[@@@@SPACE LC
)@@G@@@E@@@@ CALLING SEQUENCE - WHERE     TRTN$     STANDS FOR THE TIDE$@G@@@@LD
)@@G@@ ROUTINE BEING CALLED, AND     T$RTN     IS THE CORRESPONDING PROC:     LE
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@    1) FREE FORMAT (VARIABLE FORMAT) SEQUENCE   @[@@@@LF
)@@G@@SPACE @B@@@@       LA,XU     A0,ADDRESS-OF -VARIABLE  @ @@@@       LMJ  LG
)@@G@@     X11,TRTN$    @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PRLH
)@@G@@OC:   @[@@@@SPACE @^@@@@       T$RTN    ADDRESS @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE LI
)@@G@@@^@@@@    2) FIXED FORMAT CALL@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@       LA,XU     A0,ADDRLJ

)@@G@@       LMJ       X11,TRTN$    @[@@@@SPACE @^@@@@                 OR:    LL
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       T$RTN    ADDRESS   COL-COUNT @[@@@@EJECT @F@@@@LM
)@@G@@ AS AN EXAMPLE, THE FOLLOWING SEQUENCE SIMULATES THE FORTRAN INPUT@]@@@@LN

)@@G@@    R$EAD     (EOF,CARD)        . READ A CARD   @E@@@@          T$IDE   LR
)@@G@@  PACKET  0,A0      . OPEN TIDE$ PACKET   @E@@@@          T$DECF    II  LS
)@@G@@10            . I10 FORMAT INTO II  @E@@@@          T$FLOF    A   16    LT
)@@G@@        . READ FLOATING POINT @F@@@@          T$FLOFD   X   10          LU
)@@G@@  . DOUBLE PRECISION FLOATING @D@@@@          T$IDEX                    LV
)@@G@@  . CLOSE PACKET  @^@@@@3NUMERIC TERMINATION    @F@@@@ TIDE$ NUMERIC ROULW
)@@G@@TINES SCAN THE CARD IMAGE, TERMINATING WHEN:    @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMNLX
)@@G@@ 11   @F@@@@       1) AN END-OF-FIELD IS ENCOUNTERED. THIS APPLIES ONLY LY
)@@G@@TO    @F@@@@          FIXED FIELD ROUTINES, AND SIGNIFIES THAT THE ROUTILZ
)@@G@@NE HAS@G@@@@          SCANNED THE NUMBER OF COLUMNS ORIGINALLY SPECIFIEDMA
)@@G@@ IN A1.     @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@       2) A BREAKARACTER IS ENCOUNTERED. TMB
)@@G@@HE USER PROVIDES A 2-WORD     @F@@@@          MASK IN THE PACKET, AND SEMC
)@@G@@TS THE BITS CORRESPONDING TO  @F@@@@          THE CHARACTERS HE WISHES SMD
)@@G@@CANNING TO STOP ON. BIT 0     @F@@@@          (RT.-MOST) CORRESPONDS TO ME
)@@G@@'@', BIT 1 TO '[', ETC. UNLESS@F@@@@          SPECIFIED, ONLY BIT 56 IS MF
)@@G@@SET, INSTRUCTING TIDE$ TO STOP@F@@@@          SCANNING IF A COMMA (CHARAMG
)@@G@@CTER 56) IS ENCOUNTERED, SINCE@D@@@@          COMMAS ARE USUALLY USED TOMH
)@@G@@ SEPARATE FIELDS. @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@       3) THE END OF THE CARD IS REAMI
)@@G@@CHED. @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@       4) AN ERROR OCCURS     @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@MJ
)@@G@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ UPON TERMINATION, REGISTERS ARE RETURNED WITH INTERESMK
)@@G@@TING DATA:  @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@      A1 - ERROR CODE (0-9). IF NO ERROR, ML
)@@G@@A1 IS ZERO. @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@      A2 - TERMINATION CODE (END-OF-CARD, MM
)@@G@@ETC.) @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@      A3 - LAST CHARACTER SCANNED. A3=-1 IF END-MN
)@@G@@OF-CARD.    @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@ A COMPLETE LIST OF THESMO
)@@G@@E RETURN CODES, AND OTHERS, IS FOUND IN   @F@@@@ SECTION 15.1.1 . THE STMP
)@@G@@ATUS INFORMATION RETURNED BY TIDE$ NUMERIC@F@@@@ ROUTINES, BOTH IN REGISMQ
)@@G@@TERS (SECTION 15.1.1) AND IN PACKET FLAGS @F@@@@ (SECTION 10.1.1) IS EXTMR
)@@G@@ENSIVE, BUT WILL NOT BE NECESSARY FOR ALL @]@@@@ USERS.     @[@@@@EJECT MS
)@@G@@@#@@@@2PRESET RETURNS   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ IN THE EVENT OF A NON-NORMAL MT
)@@G@@RETURN (ERROR RETURN, END-OF-CARD   @F@@@@ RETURN, ETC.), TIDE$ HAS THE MU
)@@G@@CAPABILITY OF RETURNING CONTROL TO  @E@@@@ USER-SPECIFIED LOCATIONS. FORMV
)@@G@@ EXAMPLE, RATHER THAN TEST THE@F@@@@ CONTENTS OF A1 UPON EVERY TERMINATIMW
)@@G@@ON, THE USER MAY DEFINE AN    @F@@@@ 'ERRORETURN'    IN THE PACKET TO WHMX
)@@G@@ICH TIDE$ WILL RETURN IN THE  @F@@@@ EVENT OF AN ERROR. THIS OPTION IS EMY
)@@G@@XPLAINED MORE COMPLETELY IN   @]@@@@ SECTION 13.@[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3OCTALMZ
)@@G@@ INTEGER ROUTINES @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @C@@@@       TOCTV$  - SINGLE PRECISNA
)@@G@@ION FREE FORMAT   @C@@@@       TOCTF$  - SINGLE PRECISION FIXED FORMAT  NB

)@@G@@D$ - DOUBLE PRECISION FIXED FORMAT  @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ OCTAL NUMBERS AREND
)@@G@@ STRINGS OF OCTAL DIGITS.  THESE DIGITS ('0'-'7')     @F@@@@ ARE OPTIONANE
)@@G@@LLY PRECEEDED BY A '+' OR '-', POSSIBLY FOLLOWED BY AN@G@@@@ EXPONENT SINF

)@@G@@0D9   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ NOTE THAT 77+10 IS EQUIVALENT TO 77K+10. SINCE NP

)@@G@@GAL.  @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ DOUBLE PRECISION OCTAL NUMBERS MAY RANGE FROM 0NR

)@@G@@ 9K3 (=9000)   1957   1492   021   678   -9E9   @#@@@@ (=-9000000000)   OA

)@@G@@NITUDE FROM 0     @#@@@@ TO (10**20)-1.   @[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@3GENERAL INTOC
)@@G@@EGER (GENINT) ROUTINES  @C@@@@       TINTV$  - SINGLE PRECISION FREE FOROD
)@@G@@MAT   @C@@@@       TINTF$  - SINGLE PRECISION FIXED FORMAT  @C@@@@      OE
)@@G@@ TINTVD$ - DOUBLE PRECISION FREE FORMAT   @C@@@@       TINTFD$ - DOUBLE OF
)@@G@@PRECISION FIXED FORMAT  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ GENINT ROUTINES WILL READ OCTOG
)@@G@@AL AND DECIMAL INTEGER NUMBERS, AND @G@@@@ ALPHANUMERIC STRINGS. THESE ROH
)@@G@@OUTINES SCAN THE FIELD, DETERMINE THE     @E@@@@ TYPE, AND INPUT THE DATOI
)@@G@@A IN THE APPROPRIATE MANNER. GENINT @F@@@@ ROUTINES ARE USEFUL FOR SCANNOJ
)@@G@@ING CARDS THAT HAVE AN ARBITRARILY  @E@@@@ MIXED ASSORTMENT OF OCTAL, DEOK
)@@G@@CIMAL, AND ALPHANUMERIC ITEMS.@^@@@@2GENINT NUMERIC INPUT   @D@@@@ 1) OCOL
)@@G@@TAL NUMBERS ARE SPECIFIED BY LEADING ZEROES.    @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@    EXOM
)@@G@@.   010   077K10  -015  0     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ 2) DECIMAL NUMBERS ARE ON
)@@G@@THOSE NUMBERS THAT LACK LEADING ZEROES.   @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@    EX.   10OO
)@@G@@   77K5   -15   8 @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ IF THE PACKET FLAG     OP
)@@G@@GOC     (GENINT OCTAL FLAG) IS 0 (WHICH IS@F@@@@ THE NORMAL CASE), GENINOQ
)@@G@@T BEHAVES AS DESCRIBED ABOVE. IF, HOWEVER,@F@@@@ GOC   IS NON-ZERO, THENOR
)@@G@@ GENINT WILL EXPECT ONLY OCTAL NUMBERS    @G@@@@ (WITH NO LEADING ZEROESOS
)@@G@@ NECESSARY) OR ALPHANUMERIC. THIS OPTION IS     @F@@@@ USEFUL FOR DIAGNOOT
)@@G@@STIC PROGRAMS THAT EXPECT ONLY OCTAL ADDRESSES  @F@@@@ (WITHOUT LEADING OU
)@@G@@ZEROES) AND/OR ALPHANUMERIC ITEMS (FOR SEARCHING@]@@@@ PURPOSES). @[@@@@OV
)@@G@@SPACE @F@@@@ NOTE: WITH    GOC    SET NON-ZERO, IT IS THEN IMPOSSIBLE, OOW
)@@G@@F     @E@@@@ COURSE, TO INPUT DECIMAL NUMBERS WITH GENINT ROUTINES.     OX
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ UPON RETURN, THE REGISTERS CONTAIN THE NORMAL NUMERICOY
)@@G@@-RETURN FLAGS     @C@@@@ DISCUSSED IN SECTION 15.1.1 OF THE APPENDIX.   OZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@EJECT @ @@@@2GENINT ALPHANUMERIC SCANNING @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@PA
)@@G@@ GENERAL INTEGER HAS THE ABILITY TO READ ALPHANUMERIC STRINGS;    @E@@@@PB
)@@G@@ STRINGS OF CHARACTERS PRECEEDED AND FOLLOWED BY A SPECIAL  @F@@@@ CHARAPC
)@@G@@CTER CALLED THE DELIMITER.  THE USER IS ALLOWED TO SPECIFY  @F@@@@ TWO APD
)@@G@@LPHANUMERIC DELIMITERS IN THE PACKET.  WHEN EITHER SUCH     @F@@@@ CHARAPE
)@@G@@CTER (USUALLY A QUOTE OR A '$') IS ENCOUNTERED AS THE FIRST @G@@@@ NON-BPF
)@@G@@LANK CHARACTER TO APPEAR IN A GENINT FIELD, ALPHANUMERIC MODE     @F@@@@PG
)@@G@@ IS INITIATED: THE ADDRESS SPECIFIED IN A0 OF THE CALLING SEQUENCE@F@@@@PH
)@@G@@ IS BLANKED OUT, AND THE CHARACTERS BETWEEN THE DELIMITERS ARE    @F@@@@PI
)@@G@@ TRANSFERRED TO THAT ADDRESS.  THE CHARACTERS ARE STORED IN A     @^@@@@PJ
)@@G@@ LEFT-JUSTIFIED FASHION.@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@ SEVERAL CONDITIONS TERMINATE PK
)@@G@@ALPHANUMERIC SCANNING:  @]@@@@COLUMN 11   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@      1)  ENPL
)@@G@@D OF CARD ENCOUNTERED. TIDE$ STOPS TRANSFERRING @E@@@@          CHARACTEPM
)@@G@@RS, AND CONSIDERS THE ALPHANUMERIC STRING @^@@@@          TERMINATED.   PN
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@      2)  TRAILING DELIMITER (MATCHING THE INITIAL ONEPO
)@@G@@)     @F@@@@          ENCOUNTERED.  THIS SIGNALS THE END OF THE STRING, PP
)@@G@@AND   @F@@@@          ALPHANUMERIC MODE IS TERMINATED.  CONSECUTIVE DELIPQ
)@@G@@MITERS@E@@@@          WITHIN THE STRING ARE STORED AS ONE CHARACTER. FORPR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          EXAMPLE, WITH THE QUOTE AS A DELIMITER, THE STRING@D@@@@PS
)@@G@@          'AB''CD'    IS STORED AS    AB'CD     .     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@PT
)@@G@@      3)  ONE WORD (6 CHARACTERS) TRANSFERRED. TIDE$ TRANSFERS A  @F@@@@PU
)@@G@@          MAXIMUM OF 6 CHARACTERS AT A TIME, AND THEN RETURNS TO  @E@@@@PV
)@@G@@          THE USER.  BECAUSE THE END OF THE STRING WAS NOT  @F@@@@      PW
)@@G@@    ENCOUNTERED (INDICATING MORE CHARACTERS TO COME), TIDE$ @F@@@@      PX
)@@G@@    IS PLACED IN CONTINUED ALPHANUMERIC MODE. THE NEXT CALL @F@@@@      PY
)@@G@@    TO A GENINT ROUTINE WILL RETURN THE NEXT SIX CHARACTERS @F@@@@      PZ
)@@G@@    (OR UP TO THE FINAL DELIMITER), AND SO ON, EACH ROUTINE @G@@@@      QA
)@@G@@    CALL RETURNING ANOTHER WORD. IN THIS MANNER, ALPHANUMERIC     @F@@@@QB
)@@G@@          STRINGS CONTAINING MORE THAN 6 CHARACTERS MAY BE READ.  @G@@@@QC
)@@G@@          CONTINUED ALPHANUMERIC MODE IS DISCUSSED IN SECTION 15.2.     QD
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ WITH THE PACKET DELIMITERS SPECIFIEQE
)@@G@@D AS A QUOTE AND '$', SOME    @B@@@@ EXAMPLES OF ALPHANUMERIC STRINGS ARQF
)@@G@@E:    @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@     'HERE''S A STRING'     'ANOTHER ONE'     $GQG
)@@G@@ACK!$ @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@ UPON RETURN, REGISTERS CONTAIQH
)@@G@@N FLAGS INDICATING THE TERMINATION  @F@@@@ STATUS (ERROR CODES, ETC.). TQI
)@@G@@HESE FLAGS ARE DISCUSSED IN SECTION @^@@@@ 15.1.2 OF THE APPENDIX.@[@@@@QJ
)@@G@@EJECT @[@@@@EJECT @[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@2FURTHER CONSIDERATIONS @ @@@@1DOUBLQK
)@@G@@E PRECISION ALPHANUMERIC@[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ IF PACKET FLAG   DAL   IS SETQL
)@@G@@ NON-ZERO, THEN TIDE$ SCANS A MAXIMUM     @G@@@@ OF 12 CHARACTERS (2 WORQM
)@@G@@DS) AT A TIME, AND WILL INITIALLY BLANK OUT     @F@@@@ 2 WORDS. THIS DOUQN
)@@G@@BLE PRECISION CAPABILITY IS DEPENDENT ONLY ON   @F@@@@ DAL   AND NOT ON QO
)@@G@@THE MODE (SINGLE OR DOUBLE PRECISION) OF THE    @F@@@@ ROUTINE THAT WAS QP
)@@G@@CALLED.  THIS FEATURE IS PARTICULARLY USEFUL FOR@^@@@@ SCANNING FILENAMEQQ
)@@G@@S.    @[@@@@SPACE @^@@@@1ILLEGAL DELIMITERS     @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@ THE FQR
)@@G@@OLLOWING CHARACTERS ARE ILLEGAL AS DELIMITERS:  @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@     DQS
)@@G@@IGITS (0-9) , + , - , . , E , K , D , BLANK     @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ IF SUQT
)@@G@@CH CHARACTERS ARE SPECIFIED IN THE PACKET AS DELIMITERS, THEY     @E@@@@QU
)@@G@@ WILL BE IGNORED (WHICH PROVIDES A METHOD OF DISABLING THE  @C@@@@ ALPHAQV
)@@G@@NUMERIC CAPABILITY OF GENINT ROUTINES) .  @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@1FREE FORMATQW
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ ALPHANUMERIC SCANNING IS STRICTLY A FREE FORMAT OPERAQX
)@@G@@TION: IF A  @F@@@@ FIXED FORMAT GENINT ROUTINE (TINTF$ OR TINTFD$) IS CAQY
)@@G@@LLED, AND AN@E@@@@ ALPHANUMERIC STRING IS ENCOUNTERED, THEN THE FIELD WIQZ
)@@G@@DTH AS@ @@@@ SPECIFIED IN A1 IS IGNORED.  @[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3FLOATING PORA
)@@G@@INT ROUTINES@C@@@@       TFLOV$  - SINGLE PRECISION FREE FORMAT   @C@@@@RB
)@@G@@       TFLOF$  - SINGLE PRECISION FIXED FORMAT  @C@@@@       TFLOVD$ - DRC
)@@G@@OUBLE PRECISION FREE FORMAT   @C@@@@       TFLOFD$ - DOUBLE PRECISION FIRD
)@@G@@XED FORMAT  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ FLOATING POINT FORMAT IS SIMILAR TO DECIMRE
)@@G@@AL, BUT DECIMAL POINTS  @A@@@@ AND NEGATIVE EXPONENTS ARE ALLOWED.@[@@@@RF
)@@G@@SPACE @D@@@@ 10**-39  <  SINGLE PRECISION MAGNITUDE  <  10**38    @[@@@@RG
)@@G@@SPACE @]@@@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@ ANY SIGNIFICANCE PAST 8 DIGITS IS IGNOREDRH
)@@G@@.  SOME EXAMPLES OF     @E@@@@ FLOATING POINT NUMBERS (SUCH AS THESE ROURI
)@@G@@TINES EXPECT) ARE:@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@    517  98.6  077K10 (=77.0E+10 = 7RJ
)@@G@@7+10)  -559.1957  @D@@@@       +454.2573E4        15D3 (=15000.0)   0123RK
)@@G@@4567  @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@ 10**-309  <  DOUBLE PRECISION MAGNITUDE  <  10*RL
)@@G@@*308  @]@@@@SPACE 0     @C@@@@ ANY SIGNIFICANCE PAST 19 DIGITS IS IGNORERM
)@@G@@D.    @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ EX.    2  -100D5 (=10000000.)   56.   91K200  3RN
)@@G@@3.33333-5   @#@@@@ (=.0003333333)   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ NOTICE: DECIMAL PRO
)@@G@@OINTS ARE NOT MANDATORY;   5   IS INTERPRETED THE     @^@@@@ SAME AS    RP
)@@G@@5.0    .    @[@@@@EJECT @ @@@@2FIXED POINT REPRESENTATION   @H@@@@0     RQ
)@@G@@A FIXED POINT FRACTIONAL NUMBER CONSISTS OF A STRING OF BINARY BITS     RR
)@@G@@@ @@@@ SEPARATED BY A BINARY POINT  @D@@@@ INTO AN INTEGER PART (GREATERRS
)@@G@@ THAN OR EQUAL TO 1) AND@G@@@@ A FRACTIONAL PART (LESS THAN 1). THE SIZERT
)@@G@@ OF THE FRACTIONAL PART IS    @F@@@@ SPECIFIED BY THE NUMBER OF BITS TO RU
)@@G@@THE RIGHT OF THE BINARY POINT @F@@@@ (WHICH SERVES THE SAME PURPOSE AS ARV
)@@G@@ BASE TEN DECIMAL POINT).     @G@@@@ THIS REPRESENTATION ALLOWS LIMITED RW
)@@G@@PRECISION FRACTIONAL NUMBERS TO BE  @G@@@@ SPECIFIED WITH FEWER BITS THARX
)@@G@@N NEEDED FOR THE FLOATING POINT FORMAT.   @#@@@@ FOR EXAMPLE,     @[@@@@RY
)@@G@@0     @E@@@@0     0201400000000     0201600000000     0200600000000     RZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@0     @F@@@@0     ARE THE FLOATING POINT REPRESENTATIONS FOR 1.0, SA
)@@G@@1.5, AND .75@F@@@@ RESPECTIVELY. WITH A FRACTIONAL PART OF 6 BITS (6 BITSB
)@@G@@S TO THE    @E@@@@ RIGHT OF THE BINARY POINT), THE PRECEEDING NUMBERS MASC
)@@G@@Y BE  @D@@@@ REPRESENTED AS THE FOLLOWING FIXED POINT FRACTIONS:  @[@@@@SD
)@@G@@0     @A@@@@0         0140      0160      060   @[@@@@0     @F@@@@0IF PASE
)@@G@@CKET FLAG    INTFRC    IS NON-ZERO, FLOATING POINT NUMBERS  @F@@@@ ARE SSF
)@@G@@CANNED AS FIXED POINT FRACTIONS, WITH    INTFRC-1   BITS TO @E@@@@ THE RSG
)@@G@@IGHT OF THE BINARY POINT. IF    INTFRC    IS ZERO (THE@E@@@@ USUAL CASE)SH
)@@G@@, THEN THE FLOATING POINT ROUTINES INTERPRET    @ @@@@ NUMBERS AS FLOATISI
)@@G@@NG POINT.   @A@@@@ INTFRC MAY BE A MAXIMUM OF 63.     @[@@@@EJECT @ @@@@SJ
)@@G@@3GENERAL SCANNING ROUTINES    @A@@@@       TGENV$ - FREE FORMAT ROUTINE SK
)@@G@@@A@@@@       TGENF$ - FIXED FORMAT ROUTINE@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ GENERAL SCASL
)@@G@@NNING IS USED WHEN THE MODE (OCTAL, FLOATING POINT,   @G@@@@ ETC.) OF THSM
)@@G@@E NEXT FIELD TO BE SCANNED IS UNKNOWN. EVERY ATTEMPT IS     @F@@@@ MADE SN
)@@G@@TO DETERMINE THIS MODE, WHICH IS THEN PLACED IN THE PACKET  @D@@@@ FLAG SO
)@@G@@     MODE     , DESCRIBED IN SECTION 10.1.1 .   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ GENERSP
)@@G@@AL MODE INITIALLY SCANS AS SINGLE PRECISION GENERAL INTEGER,@F@@@@ WITH SQ
)@@G@@GENINT FLAGS 'DAL' AND 'GOC' SET AS DESIRED BY THE USER. THE@F@@@@ FOLLOSR
)@@G@@WING RULES ARE IN EFFECT, HOWEVER, AND DETERMINE THE MODE   @]@@@@ CHOICSS
)@@G@@E:    @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 11   @F@@@@       1) AN '8' OR '9' FORCE ST
)@@G@@DECIMAL MODE, EVEN IF A LEADING ZERO@F@@@@          HAD ORIGINALLY INDICSU
)@@G@@ATED OCTAL MODE. THIS DIFFERS FROM  @F@@@@          STANDARD GENINT, WHESV
)@@G@@RE AN ERROCT (ILLEGAL OCTAL DIGIT   @B@@@@          ERROR) WOULD HAVE RESW
)@@G@@SULTED.     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       2) AN EXPONENTIAL 'D' FORCES DOUBLESX
)@@G@@ PRECISION (INTEGER OR  @^@@@@          FLOATING).    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@SY
)@@G@@       3) A '.', OR EXPONENTIAL 'E', '+', OR '-' FORCE FLOATING   @F@@@@SZ
)@@G@@          POINT MODE.  A NEGATIVE EXPONENT ALWAYS FORCES FLOATING @^@@@@TA
)@@G@@          POINT MODE.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       4) TOO MUCH SIGNIFICANCTB
)@@G@@E FOR SINGLE PRECISION FORCES DOUBLE@^@@@@          PRECISION     @[@@@@TC
)@@G@@SPACE @F@@@@       5) SINGLE PRECISION INTEGER OVERFLOW FORCES D. P. INTTD
)@@G@@EGER. @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       6) DOUBLE PRECISION INTEGER OVERFLOW FORCTE
)@@G@@ES D. P. FLOATING @#@@@@          POINT.  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       7) SITF
)@@G@@NGLE PRECISION FLOATING POINT OVER/UNDERFLOW FORCES   @B@@@@          DOTG
)@@G@@UBLE PRECISION FLOATING POINT.@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @[@@@@EJECT TH
)@@G@@@D@@@@1EXAMPLES OF GENERAL SCANNING MODE DETERMINATION.     @[@@@@SPACE TI

)@@G@@2E  1234567890123456789012345 @[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@2NAME SCANNING VIA GENERUA
)@@G@@AL MODE     @F@@@@ GENERAL MODE CAN SCAN FOR NAMES AND LABELS BY SETTINGUB
)@@G@@ THE PACKET @E@@@@ FLAG      NLG      (NAME-LENGTH) WITH THE MAXIMUM NUMUC
)@@G@@BER OF@F@@@@ CHARACTERS ALLOWED PER NAME. IF NLG = 0, NO NAME SCANNING IUD
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@ ALLOWED. THE 2-WORD PACKET BIT MASK      MK1      IS SET TOUE
)@@G@@@F@@@@ INDICATE WHICH CHARACTERS ARE ACCEPTABLE AS FIRST CHARACTERS OF  UF
)@@G@@@F@@@@ THE NAME, WITH MK1 USUALLY SET TO ALLOW ONLY LETTERS AS FIRST    UG
)@@G@@@F@@@@ CHARS.  THE 2-WORD MASK      MK2      INDICATES WHICH CHARACTERS UH
)@@G@@@F@@@@ MAY FOLLOW THE FIRST. MK2 IS USUALLY SET TO LETTERS, DIGITS, AND UI
)@@G@@@F@@@@ '$'.  BOTH MASKS ARE EASILY GENERATED USING THE PROC    T$MASKR  UJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DESCRIBED IN SECTION 9.1 .  NAME SCANNING MODE IS INITIATED WHEN UK
)@@G@@@G@@@@ ONE OF THE CHARACTERS SPECIFIED IN    MK1   IS THE FIRST CHARACTEUL
)@@G@@R     @^@@@@ ENCOUNTERED IN A FIELD.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ GENERAL ROUTINES UM
)@@G@@ARE CALLED IN A MANNER SIMILAR TO THE GENINT    @F@@@@ ROUTINES, WITH THUN
)@@G@@E OPTIONAL PARTWORD INDICATOR (DESCRIBED IN     @F@@@@ SECTION 15.2) LOAUO
)@@G@@DED IN H1 OF A0 (FOR ALPHANUMERIC AND NAME-LABEL@]@@@@ PURPOSES). @[@@@@UP
)@@G@@SPACE @D@@@@       LA,XU     A0,ADDRESS        . WHERE TO PUT IT  @E@@@@UQ
)@@G@@       LXI,U     A0,PTWD           . OPTIONAL. IF 0, OMIT.  @D@@@@      UR
)@@G@@ LA,XU     A1,COUNT          . ONLY FOR TGENF$  @B@@@@       LMJ       XUS
)@@G@@11,TGENV$-OR-TGENF$ .   @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY UT
)@@G@@THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@       T$GEN[V-OR-F],PTWD   ADDRESS   COUNUU
)@@G@@T  . THE PROC     @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ UPON TERMINATION UV
)@@G@@FROM GENERAL MODE NAME SCANNING, THE REGISTERS  @F@@@@ ARE SET AS DESCRIUW
)@@G@@BED IN SECTION 15.1.2 (GENINT ALPHA), WITH THE  @^@@@@ FOLLOWING EXCEPTIUX
)@@G@@ONS:  @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@       A1 - ERROR CODE - ALWAYS ZERO WHEN NAME SUY
)@@G@@CANNING     @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@       A2 - TERMINATION CODE  @[@@@@SPACE UZ
)@@G@@@]@@@@COLUMN 14   @F@@@@         0 - END-OF-FIELD. 1) ROUTINE HAS SCANNEVA
)@@G@@D THE # OF COLUMNS@F@@@@             ORIGINALLY SPECIFIED IN A1 (FOR FIXVB
)@@G@@ED FIELD TGENF$)  @G@@@@             OR, 2) NUMBER OF CHARACTERS STORED VC

)@@G@@T ALLOWED BY MASK 'MK2' @^@@@@             WAS FOUND. @^@@@@         2 -VE
)@@G@@ END OF CARD@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ NOTE:  UPON TERMINATIONVF

)@@G@@@ @@@@1EXAMPLE OF GENERAL SCANNING  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ WITH    NLG    = VI
)@@G@@12, WE READ THE FORTRAN CARD IMAGE USING TGENV$:@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ 100  VJ
)@@G@@ DO 500 I = 10,20,2     @]@@@@SPACE 2     @ @@@@ FIRST CALL TO TGENV$ REVK
)@@G@@TURNS:@A@@@@       MODE: SP-DECIMAL   VALUE: 100@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ 2ND CVL

)@@G@@$ RETURNS:  @E@@@@       MODE: NAME-LABEL   VALUE: I     CHARACTER COUNTVP
)@@G@@: 1   @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ 5TH CALL TO TGENV$ RETURNS:  @C@@@@       MODE:VQ
)@@G@@ ERRCHAR      VALUE: (A3 = '=')     @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ 6TH CALL TO TGENVVR
)@@G@@$ RETURNS:  @A@@@@       MODE: SP-DECIMAL   VALUE: 10 @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@VS
)@@G@@ 7TH CALL TO TGENV$ RETURNS:  @A@@@@       MODE: SP-DECIMAL   VALUE: 20 VT
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ 8TH CALL TO TGENV$ RETURNS:  @A@@@@       MODE: SP-DEVU
)@@G@@CIMAL   VALUE: 2  @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ IN THVV
)@@G@@E ABOVE EXAMPLE, TIDE$ WAS SET TO IGNORE LEADING BLANKS AND @F@@@@ TREATVW
)@@G@@ TRAILING BLANKS AS BREAKARACTERS BY SETTING THE PACKET FLAG@F@@@@ BLK  VX
)@@G@@   PROPERLY.    BLK (BLANK-FLAG) IS DISCUSSED IN SECTION    @]@@@@ 10.1.VY
)@@G@@1 .   @[@@@@EJECT @B@@@@3RESTRICTED GENERAL SCANNING ROUTINES     @[@@@@VZ
)@@G@@SPACE @ @@@@       TGNRV$ - FREE FORMAT   @ @@@@       TGNRF$ - FIXED FOWA
)@@G@@RMAT  @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ RESTRICTED GENERAL SCANNING IS SIMILAR IN ACTIOWB
)@@G@@N TO REGULAR@G@@@@ GENERAL SCANNING, BUT SEVERAL SYNTACTIC LIMITATIONS AWC
)@@G@@RE IN EFFECT.     @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 11   @B@@@@       1) NO IMPLIWD
)@@G@@ED MANTISSAS ARE ALLOWED@E@@@@              E10   IS NOT READ IN AS EQUIWE
)@@G@@VALENT TO   1E10  @E@@@@            BUT GETS AN ERRCHAR (POINTING TO 'E'WF
)@@G@@). MANTISSAS@B@@@@            MUST CONTAIN AT LEAST 1 DIGIT.@[@@@@SPACE WG
)@@G@@@C@@@@       2) NO INTEGER EXPONENT SIGNS ARE ALLOWED.@F@@@@            WH
)@@G@@  1K10  IS FINE,  1K+10  IS NOT. THE '+' IS RETURNED  @C@@@@            WI
)@@G@@AS A BREAKARACTER (NOT ERRCHAR).    @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       3) NO IMPLIWJ
)@@G@@ED EXPONENT CHARACTERS ARE ALLOWED. @D@@@@              1E+20  IS FINE ,WK
)@@G@@ BUT   1.+20 IS ILLEGAL @D@@@@            AND RETURNS WITH '+' AS A BREAWL
)@@G@@KARACTER.   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@       4) INTEGERS ARE NEVER CONVERTED TO WM
)@@G@@FLOATING POINT    @D@@@@            MERELY BECAUSE OF OVERFLOW. YOU NEEDWN
)@@G@@ A    @E@@@@            '.' OR AN EXPONENTIAL 'E' TO FORCE CONVERSION.  WO
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ SOME EXAMPLES OF NUMBERS AND THEIR DECIPHERED MODES UWP
)@@G@@NDER  @#@@@@ THIS SCHEME:     @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@                 1     SWQ
)@@G@@P DECIMAL   @A@@@@                 01D   DP OCTAL     @A@@@@            WR
)@@G@@     1.    SP FLOATING  @A@@@@                 1E5   SP FLOATING  @A@@@@WS

)@@G@@MAL   @ @@@@                 1K25  ERRINT @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    WU
)@@G@@@E@@@@ WHILE GENERAL MODE IS DESIGNED TO READ DATA (TYPE UNKNOWN),@F@@@@WV
)@@G@@ RESTRICTED GENERAL IS DESIGNED TO FACILITATE THE SCANNING OF     @^@@@@WW
)@@G@@ ALGEBRAIC EXPRESSIONS. @ @@@@4CHARACTER COPYING ROUTINES   @F@@@@ THESEWX
)@@G@@ ROUTINES ARE USED FOR SCANNING AND/OR TRANSFERRING STRINGS @F@@@@ OF CHWY
)@@G@@ARACTERS, AND ARE THE SAME ROUTINES USED BY GENERAL MODE    @B@@@@ ROUTIWZ
)@@G@@NES WHEN INTERPRETING NAME-LABELS.  @]@@@@SPACE 1     @E@@@@    TSCANV$ XA
)@@G@@- FREE FIELD, LOOK FOR FIRST BREAK CHARACTER    @E@@@@    TSCANF$ - SAMEXB
)@@G@@ AS TSCANV$, BUT LOOK AT MAX OF A1 COLUMNS@F@@@@    TNBRKV$ - SAME AS TSXC
)@@G@@CANV$, BUT LOOK FOR 1ST NON - BREAKARACTER@E@@@@    TNBRKF$ - SAME AS TNXD
)@@G@@BRKV$, BUT LOOK AT MAX OF A1 COLUMNS@]@@@@SPACE 1     @F@@@@ THESE ROUTIXE
)@@G@@NES STOP SCANNING/TRANSFERRING WHEN AN END-OF-FIELD   @F@@@@ (FOR TSCANFXF
)@@G@@$ OF TNBRKF$) OR A BREAKARACTER (FOR TSCANV$/TSCANF$) @F@@@@ OR A NON-BRXG
)@@G@@EAKARACTER (FOR TNBRKV$/TNBRKF$) IS ENCOUNTERED, WITH @E@@@@ THE BREAKARXH
)@@G@@ACTERS DEFINED BY A USER-SUPPLIED 2-WORD MASK.  @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ AS ANXI
)@@G@@ EXAMPLE OF USE, TSCANV$ MIGHT BE USED TO FIND THE NEXT BLANK     @F@@@@XJ
)@@G@@ CHARACTER, WHILE TNBRKV$ WOULD BE USED TO FIND THE NEXT NON-BLANK@F@@@@XK
)@@G@@ CHARACTER, BOTH WITH THE SAME MASK.  THE MASKS ARE GENERATED WITH@D@@@@XL
)@@G@@ THE PROC     T$MASKR     DESCRIBED IN SECTION 9.1 .  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@XM
)@@G@@ THE USER LOADS A0 WITH THE ADDRESS OF WHERE THE CHARACTERS ARE TO@G@@@@XN
)@@G@@ BE TRANSFERRED (THE TARGET ADDRESS IS NOT INITIALLY BLANKED OUT BY     XO
)@@G@@@E@@@@ THESE ROUTINES). THE INCREMENT PORTION OF A0 MAY OPTIONALLY@F@@@@XP
)@@G@@ SPECIFY A PARTWORD INDEX AS IN GENINT ALPHANUMERIC ROUTINES.  IF @E@@@@XQ
)@@G@@ A0 IS 0, THE ROUTINES SCAN THE IMAGES, LOOKING FOR BREAK OR@E@@@@ NON-BXR
)@@G@@REAK CHARACTERS, BUT NO CHARACTERS ARE TRANSFERRED.   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@XS
)@@G@@       LA,XU     A0,ADDRESS        . WHERE TO PUT CHARACTERS@E@@@@      XT
)@@G@@ LXI,U     A0,PARTWORD       . IF 0, OMIT INSTRUCTION @F@@@@       LA,XUXU
)@@G@@     A1,FIELD-WIDTH    . ONLY FOR TSCANF$/TNBRKF$     @E@@@@       DL   XV
)@@G@@     A2,MASK           . THE BREAKARACTER MASK  @F@@@@       LMJ       XXW
)@@G@@11,TRTN$         . ONE OF THE ABOVE ROUTINES    @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESEXX
)@@G@@ LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       T$RTN,PARTWXY
)@@G@@ORD   ADDRESS   MASK   FIELD-WIDTH   . PROC CALL@]@@@@SPACE 1     @F@@@@XZ
)@@G@@ AFTER RETURNING TO THE USER, REGISTERS A1-A4, X11 ARE SET AS FROM@G@@@@YA
)@@G@@ A GENERAL MODE NAME SCANNING, WITH A0 READY FOR IMMEDIATE RE-ENTRY     YB
)@@G@@@E@@@@ AS IN GENINT ALPHA.  A4 CONTAINS THE NUMBER OF CHARACTERS  @G@@@@YC
)@@G@@ TRANSFERRED OR, IF ONLY SCANNING HAD BEEN PERFORMED, THE NUMBER OF     YD
)@@G@@@C@@@@ CHARACTERS THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN TRANSFERRED.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@YE
)@@G@@ EXAMPLE - THE SEQUENCE TO FIND THE NEXT NON-BLANK CHARACTER IS:  @[@@@@YF
)@@G@@SPACE @E@@@@          T$NBRKV    0    (T$MASKR  ' ')   . FREE FIELD     YG
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 1     @G@@@@ EXAMPLE - TO TRANSFER A MAXIMUM OF 10 CHARACTERYH
)@@G@@S INTO THE LOCATION     @G@@@@ BEGINNING WITH S4 OF 'STUFF', OR UNTIL THYI
)@@G@@E CHARACTER 'A' OR 'F' IS     @#@@@@ ENCOUNTERED:     @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@YJ
)@@G@@          T$SCAN,3    STUFF    (T$MASKR  'A'  'F')  10@B@@@@3CHARACTER MYK
)@@G@@ANIPULATION ROUTINES - REENTRY@F@@@@ UPON EXIT FROM ONE OF THE ABOVE ALPYL
)@@G@@HANUMERIC ROUTINES (TSCANV$,  @E@@@@ ETC.), A0 IS SET UP IN THE IMMEDIATYM
)@@G@@E REENTRY CONVENTION    @E@@@@ (PTWD,ADDR)    AS SPECIFIED IN SECTION 15YN
)@@G@@.2. IF THE NEXT   @F@@@@ ALPHANUMERIC ROUTINE CALLED USES THE SAME MASK,YO
)@@G@@ REENTRY IS QUITE @F@@@@ EASY, AS THE MASK STILL RESIDES THE PACKET WHERYP
)@@G@@E THE PREVIOUS    @A@@@@ ALPHANUMERIC ROUTINE PLACED IT.    @[@@@@SPACE YQ
)@@G@@@A@@@@ 1) IF THE REENTRY IS FREE-FORMAT:  @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       LMJ  YR
)@@G@@     X11,TSCNRV$       . OR THE PROC:     @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       T$SCNYS
)@@G@@RV                     .@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ 2) FOR FIXED-FORMAT REENTRY: YT
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       LA,XU     A1,FIELD-WIDTH    .@C@@@@       LMJ  YU
)@@G@@     X11,TSCNRF$       . THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       T$SCNRF   FYV
)@@G@@IELD-WIDTH       .@[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ NOTE: A0 RETURNS FROM A REENTRY CALYW
)@@G@@L IN THE USUAL FORMAT, THAT IS,     @ @@@@ READY FOR ANOTHER REENTRY.   YX
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ NOTE: IT IS IMPORTANT NOT TO CALL TIDE$ NUMERIC ROUTIYY
)@@G@@NES (TDECV$,@E@@@@ ETC.) BETWEEN ALPHANUMERIC AND REENTRY CALLS, OR BETWYZ
)@@G@@EEN   @F@@@@ CONSECUTIVE REENTRY CALLS, AS THESE ROUTINES WRITE INTO (ANZA
)@@G@@D THUS@F@@@@ DESTROY) THE PACKET AREA WHERE THE MASK IS STORED. EXAMPLESZB
)@@G@@:     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       T$SCANF   BORG (0D) 6    . NEXT 6 CHARS (ZC
)@@G@@NO MASK) INTO BORG@C@@@@       T$SKIP    3              . SKIP 3 COLUMNSZD
)@@G@@@E@@@@       T$SCNRF   5              . NEXT 5 CHARS INTO BORG+1  @C@@@@ZE
)@@G@@       T$COL     33             . SKIP SOME MORE@F@@@@       T$SCNRF   1ZF
)@@G@@1             . NEXT CHAR INTO S6 OF BORG+1     @F@@@@                  ZG
)@@G@@              . REMAINDER INTO BORG+2, BORG+3   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ OR YOZH
)@@G@@U CAN CHANGE FROM FREE TO FIXED FORMAT (OR VICE-VERSA):     @[@@@@SPACE ZI
)@@G@@@F@@@@       T$NBRKV   0  (T$MASKR ' ')  . SKIP UP TO 1ST NON-BLANK     ZJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@                                   . CHARACTER  @E@@@@       T$SCNZK
)@@G@@RF   3                 . AGAIN (MAX OF 3 CHARS) @ @@@@4INDIVIDUAL CHARACZL
)@@G@@TER FETCHING@F@@@@      THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES LOAD THE NEXT CHARACTER IZM
)@@G@@NTO A3.     @ @@@@3T$CHAR - INCREMENT POINTER   @F@@@@ IF IN SCANNING MOZN
)@@G@@DE, TO GET THE NEXT CHARACTER AND INCREMENT THE @#@@@@ COLUMN POINTER:  ZO
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@       T$CHAR                      . NOT A SUBROUTINE ZP
)@@G@@CALL  @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@ THIS GENERATES:  @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@       EX   ZQ
)@@G@@     0,*X5             . GRABS CHAR DIRECTLY.   @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@ THE CZR
)@@G@@HARACTER RETURNS IN A3. IF END-OF-CARD, A3 = -1.@[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE ZS
)@@G@@@E@@@@ IF THE OPTIONAL EOC (END-OF-CARD) RETURN IS SPECIFIED:     @[@@@@ZT
)@@G@@SPACE @C@@@@       T$CHAR    EOC-RETURN        . FOR EXAMPLE@[@@@@SPACE ZU
)@@G@@@A@@@@ THEN THE FOLLOWING IS GENERATED:   @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       EX   ZV
)@@G@@     0,*X5             . GET CHARACTER    @E@@@@       JN        A3,EOC-ZW
)@@G@@RETURN     . IF END-OF-CARD, JUMP   @ @@@@3T$CHARN - DON'T INCREMENT    ZX
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ TO OBTAIN THE NEXT CHARACTER WITHOUT MOVING THE POINTZY
)@@G@@ER ( TO LOOK@#@@@@ AHEAD), CALL:    @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@          T$CHARN ZZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@ THIS GENERATES:  @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@       EX        TAA
)@@G@@$CHARNL$,X5      . DON'T INCREMENT POINTER@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ THE T$CHARNAB
)@@G@@ EOC FORM IS EQUIVALENT TO THE T$CHAR VERSION:  @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@      AC
)@@G@@    T$CHARN   EOC-RETURN@ @@@@4INLINE CHARACTER SEARCHING   @E@@@@ IT ISAD
)@@G@@ SOMETIMES DESIRABLE TO FIND THE NEXT OCCURRENCE (OR  @F@@@@ NON-OCCURREAE
)@@G@@NCE) OF A PARTICULAR CHARACTER. THIS CAN BE DONE BY   @F@@@@ USING THE TAF
)@@G@@SCANV$ ROUTINES. HOWEVER, FOR ONE-CHARACTER SEARCHES, @^@@@@ THERE IS A AG
)@@G@@FASTER WAY: @A@@@@3T$FIND - SEEK SPECIFIED CHARACTER  @D@@@@ TO FIND THEAH
)@@G@@ NEXT OCCURRENCE OF A CERTAIN CHARACTER:  @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       T$FINAI
)@@G@@D    CHAR  EOC-RETURN  .@[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@ THIS GENERATES:  @[@@@@SPACE AJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@       EX        0,*X5             . GET NEXT CHARACTER (OR -1)   AK
)@@G@@@E@@@@       JN        A3,EOC-RETURN     . END-OF-CARD RETURN     @D@@@@AL
)@@G@@       TE,U      A3,CHAR           . 'U' BY DEFAULT.  @E@@@@            AM
)@@G@@                       . OTHERS MAY BE SPECIFIED@E@@@@       J         $AN
)@@G@@-3               . NO LUCK, TRY AGAIN     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ THE OMISSIOAO
)@@G@@N OF THE END-OF-CARD RETURN GENERATES THE FOLLOWING:  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@AP
)@@G@@       LX        X11,ENDXIT        . END-OF-CARD EXIT FROM PACKET @D@@@@AQ
)@@G@@       EX        0,*X5             . T$CHAR DOES THIS @F@@@@       JN   AR
)@@G@@     A3,,X11           . NO INFINITE-LOOP ALLOWED     @D@@@@       TE,U AS
)@@G@@     A3,CHAR           . WELL, IS IT?     @B@@@@       J         $-3    AT
)@@G@@           . GADS!@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ ENDXIT (AUTOMATIC END-OF-CARD RETURAU
)@@G@@N) IS DESCRIBED LATER IN@#@@@@ SECTION 13 .     @B@@@@3T$NFIND - SEEK SPAV
)@@G@@ECIFIED NON-CHARACTER   @F@@@@ TO FIND THE NEXT NON-OCCURRENCE OF A PARTAW
)@@G@@ICULAR CHARACTER, CALL: @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@       T$NFIND   CHAR  EOC-RETAX
)@@G@@URN  .@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ THE CODE GENERATED DUPLICATES THAT OF T$FIND, WAY
)@@G@@ITH A 'TNE' @G@@@@ GENERATED INSTEAD OF A 'TE'.  EXAMPLE:  TO FIND THE NAZ
)@@G@@EXT NON-BLANK     @]@@@@ CHARACTER: @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       T$NFIND   'BA
)@@G@@ '   EOC-RETURN   . CHARACTER IN A3 @#@@@@4MASK GENERATION  @#@@@@3T$MASBB
)@@G@@KR - PROC   @F@@@@ THIS PROC GENERATES A RIGHT JUSTIFIED BIT MASK CORRESBC
)@@G@@PONDING TO  @G@@@@ THE FIELDATA CODE.  BIT 0 (THE RIGHT-MOST) CORRESPONDBD
)@@G@@S TO '@', BIT     @A@@@@ 56 TO A COMMA, ETC.  THE CALL IS:  @[@@@@SPACE BE
)@@G@@@D@@@@       T$MASKR   THINGS TO SET     . (RIGHT JUSTIFIES)@[@@@@SPACE BF
)@@G@@@D@@@@ THINGS TO SET ARE 'A' 'B' ETC. ONE MAY ALSO SPECIFY: @[@@@@SPACE BG
)@@G@@@ @@@@       'NUM' SETS ALL DIGITS  @ @@@@       'LET' SETS ALL LETTERS BH
)@@G@@@A@@@@       'SP'  SETS EVERYTHING ELSE   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ IF A FIELD BI
)@@G@@IS PRECEEDED BY A * , THAT BIT IS CLEARED. THUS,@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@      BJ
)@@G@@ T$MASKR   'LET'  *'Q'  *'Z'  @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ SETS BK
)@@G@@ALL LETTERS EXCEPT Q AND Z.  AS AN EXAMPLE OF USE, TO SEARCH@B@@@@ FOR TBL
)@@G@@HE NEXT BLANK OR '/' CHARACTER, DO: @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@       T$SCANV   0BM
)@@G@@  (T$MASKR ' ' '/')  .  @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ NOTE: FOR REASONS OF SYMMETRYBN
)@@G@@, THE PROC    T$MASKL     IS  @F@@@@ AVAILABLE TO GENERATE LEFT-JUSTIFIEBO
)@@G@@D BIT MASKS. TIDE$ ROUTINES,  @C@@@@ HOWEVER, USE      T$MASKR     EXCLUBP
)@@G@@SIVELY.     @ @@@@3TMASK$ - DYNAMIC ROUTINE     @F@@@@ THIS IS A DYMANICBQ
)@@G@@ BITMASK CREATING ROUTINE.  WHEN FED UP TO 12   @E@@@@ CHARACTERS IN A0,BR
)@@G@@A1 (RJZF) THIS ROUTINE WILL RETURN THE    @C@@@@ CORRESPONDING DOUBLE WOBS
)@@G@@RD BITMASK IN A0,A1.    @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@          DL        A0,CHARACTBT
)@@G@@ERS   @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,TMASK$@[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ THIS CALLINBU
)@@G@@G SEQUENCE MAY BE GENERATED USING : @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@       T$MASK    CBV
)@@G@@HARACTERS   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE IN SCANNING MODE TO BW
)@@G@@USE THIS ROUTINE. @#@@@@4THE TIDE$ PACKET @F@@@@ STARRED ITEMS ARE USER-BX
)@@G@@SET; OTHERS ARE INTERNAL TIDE$ FLAGS.  3  @G@@@@ PACKETS ARE AVAILABLE, BY
)@@G@@DEPENDING ON WHAT CAPABILITIES ARE DESIRED.     @#@@@@3NORMAL PACKET    BZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@    ............................................................. CA
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@ 0  :TEST&SET :  *BLK   : *BUFLNG :           *BCB
)@@G@@UFADR           : @F@@@@    ............................................CC

)@@G@@2FIELDEFINITIONS - NORMAL PACKET    @]@@@@SPACE 3     @]@@@@COLUMN 18   DS
)@@G@@@F@@@@       BLK       BLANK FLAG - HOW TO TREAT BLANKS IN NUMERIC SCANSDT
)@@G@@@A@@@@                 - USUALLY SET TO 1 @G@@@@                   0 - IDU
)@@G@@GNORE LEADING BLANKS, TREAT TRAILING BLANKS     @B@@@@                  DV
)@@G@@     AS BREAKARACTERS   @F@@@@                   1 - IGNORE ALL BLANKS (DW
)@@G@@EXCEPT IN ALPHA STRINGS)@E@@@@                   2 - TREAT ALL BLANKS ASDX
)@@G@@ BREAKARACTERS    @F@@@@                   3 - TREAT BLANKS AS '0' (OCTADY
)@@G@@L 060 - ZEROES)   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       BUFLNG    DEFAULT LENGTH OF CDZ
)@@G@@ARD IMAGE. IF A1=0 IN CALLING @G@@@@                 SEQUENCE, TIDE$ GETEA
)@@G@@S LENGTH HERE. BUFLNG IS MAX OF     @F@@@@                 63 (1 SIXTH-WEB
)@@G@@ORD), BUT LENGTH SPECIFIED IN A1 MAY@B@@@@                 BE GREATER (1EC

)@@G@@EAKARACTER MASK FOR     @F@@@@                 NUMERIC ROUTINES. USUALLYEF
)@@G@@ SET TO 1D*/56 IN ORDER @E@@@@                 TO STOP ON COMMAS. ALL TIEG
)@@G@@DE$ MASKS ARE     @F@@@@                 RIGHT-JUSTIFIED, WITH THE LOW OEH

)@@G@@NG TO THE CHARACTER     @^@@@@                 '@'.   @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@EJ

)@@G@@GE LENGTH - @^@@@@                 1)     @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@EM

)@@G@@ERED  @C@@@@       SIGNIF    1 - SEEN A SIGNIFICANT DIGIT,  @]@@@@SPACE ET

)@@G@@ERAL INTEGER MODE, ELSE ZERO  @D@@@@       INTEGER   IF 2 - IN INTEGER MEY

)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       EXPOCTAL  OCTAL MODE OF MANTISSA WHEN EXPONENT FS

)@@G@@ MODE. DL1 IS USUALLY SET     @C@@@@                 TO A QUOTE, AND DL2FV

)@@G@@@A@@@@                 IN EXPONENT MODE.  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@       INTFRGI

)@@G@@THE OFFICIAL DESCRIPTION OF UOM ASCII:    @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @[@@@@SPACE JZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@      A FACILITY FOR TRANSMITTING ALL 128 ASCII CHARACTERS BETWEENKA
)@@G@@@F@@@@ TELETYPE-COMPATIBLE DEMAND TERMINALS AND USER PROGRAMS OPERATING KB
)@@G@@@F@@@@ UNDER EXEC 8 HAS BEEN DEVELOPED AT THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND.   KC
)@@G@@@C@@@@ THIS FACILITY ALLOWS USER PROGRAMS TO CONTROL A@F@@@@ TELETYPE-COKD
)@@G@@MPATIBLE GRAPHICS DEVICE OR TO MAKE USE OF THE UPPER  @C@@@@ AND LOWER CKE
)@@G@@ASE CAPABILITIES OF OF SOME DEVICES.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      USERS DIAL TKF
)@@G@@HE 1108 AND INITIATE A RUN IN THE USUAL MANNER. @F@@@@ ONCE A RUN IS ACTKG
)@@G@@IVE, A USER MAY AT ANY TIME MAKE HIS TERMINAL   @E@@@@ ELIGIBLE FOR ASCIKH
)@@G@@I INPUT AND OUTPUT BY ENTERING THE CONTROL@F@@@@ STATEMENT '@TABSET,A'. KI
)@@G@@ ELIGIBILITY IS TERMINATED BY THE CONTROL @F@@@@ STATEMENT '@TABSET,F'. KJ
)@@G@@ IF EITHER THE A- OR F-OPTION APPEARS ON  @F@@@@ THE @TABSET CARD, THE RKK
)@@G@@EMAINING FIELDS WILL BE IGNORED AND TAB   @F@@@@ SETTINGS WILL BE UNCHANKL
)@@G@@GED.  IF BOTH OPTIONS ARE PRESENT, F ONLY @F@@@@ WILL BE USED.  WHILE A KM
)@@G@@TERMINAL IS ELIGIBLE FOR ASCII INPUT AND  @E@@@@ OUTPUT, PROGRAMS MAY INKN
)@@G@@PUT AND OUTPUT ASCII AS FOLLOWS:    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      ASCII INPUT:KO
)@@G@@  WHEN THE SYSTEM RECEIVES ONE OF THE 128 ASCII @F@@@@ CHARACTERS, IT NOKP
)@@G@@RMALLY TRANSLATES IT TO ONE OF THE 64 FIELDATA  @F@@@@ CHARACTERS AND STKQ
)@@G@@ORES IT AS A SIXTH-WORD IN A READ$ IMAGE.  IN   @F@@@@ ORDER TO BYPASS TKR
)@@G@@HE TRANSLATION, THE DEMAND TERMINAL USER MUST   @G@@@@ TRANSMIT AN ASCIIKS
)@@G@@ SO (SHIFT OUT).  THE SO IS TRANSLATED TO 077 AND     @E@@@@ STORED AS TKT
)@@G@@HE NEXT SIXTH-WORD OF THE CURRENT READ$ IMAGE.  @F@@@@ TRANSLATION IS THKU
)@@G@@EN SUSPENDED UNTIL AN ASCII SI (SHIFT IN) IS    @F@@@@ RECEIVED.  THE FIKV
)@@G@@RST CHARACTER RECEIVED AFTER THE SO IS STORED IN@E@@@@ THE FIRST AVAILABKW
)@@G@@LE QUARTER-WORD AFTER THE 077.  SUBSEQUENT@F@@@@ CHARACTERS ARE STORED IKX
)@@G@@N CONSECUTIVE QUARTER-WORDS.  WHEN THE 14 @E@@@@ WORD READ$ IMAGE IS COMKY
)@@G@@PLETE, IT IS SENT TO THE USER.  IN  @G@@@@ SUBSEQUENT IMAGES, THE SYSTEMKZ
)@@G@@ WILL STORE 077 IN THE FIRST SIXTH OF     @G@@@@ THE FIRST WORD TO INDICLA
)@@G@@ATE THAT NO TRANSLATION IS BEING PERFORMED.     @F@@@@ UNTRANSLATED INPULB
)@@G@@T CHARACTERS ARE THEN STORED IN CONSECUTIVE     @G@@@@ QUARTER-WORDS BEGLC
)@@G@@INNING WITH THE SECOND QUARTER OF THE FIRST WORD.     @F@@@@ THE CURRENTLD
)@@G@@ READ$ IMAGE IS SENT TO THE USER WHENEVER AN ASCII CR @F@@@@ (CARRIAGE RLE
)@@G@@ETURN) IS STORED IN IT.  AFTER AN SI IS RECEIVED AND  @F@@@@ STORED IN TLF
)@@G@@HE CURRENT READ$ IMAGE, THE IMAGE IS SENT TO THE USER @F@@@@ AND NORMAL LG
)@@G@@TRANSLATION RESUMES.  AN ASCII NUL (BREAK KEY) WILL   @F@@@@ TERMINATE ULH
)@@G@@NTRANSLATED INPUT AND WILL BE PROCESSED NORMALLY.  AN @F@@@@ ASCII XOFF LI
)@@G@@(023) ACTS LIKE A CARRIAGE RETURN, BUT DOES NOT MOVE  @B@@@@ THE CURSOR LJ
)@@G@@TO THE BEGINNING OF THE LINE. @[@@@@EJECT @E@@@@     ASCII OUTPUT:  WHENLK
)@@G@@ SENDING A PRINT$ IMAGE TO A DEMAND @F@@@@ TERMINAL, THE SYSTEM ASSUMES LL
)@@G@@THAT THE IMAGE CONSISTS OF FIELDATA @F@@@@ CHARACTERS STORED IN SIXTH-WOLM
)@@G@@RDS.  THE SYSTEM TRANSLATES THESE   @G@@@@ FIELDATA CHARACTERS TO THE APLN
)@@G@@PROPRIATE ASCII CHARACTERS, ADDS SOME     @G@@@@ CONTROL CHARACTERS AND LO
)@@G@@TRANSMITS THE RESULT TO THE TERMINAL.  AS A     @F@@@@ RESULT, A USER PRLP
)@@G@@OGRAM CAN NORMALLY SEND ONLY 64 OF THE 128 ASCII@F@@@@ CHARACTERS TO A TLQ
)@@G@@ERMINAL.  IF A TERMINAL IS ELIGIBLE FOR ASCII   @F@@@@ OUTPUT, AND IF THLR
)@@G@@E FIRST SIXTH-WORD OF A PRINT$ IMAGE CONTAINS   @G@@@@ 077, THEN SUCCESSLS
)@@G@@IVE QUARTER-WORDS OF THE IMAGE BEGINNING WITH THE     @F@@@@ SECOND QUARLT
)@@G@@TER OF THE FIRST WORD ARE ASSUMED TO CONTAIN ASCII    @F@@@@ CHARACTERS LU
)@@G@@WHICH ARE TO BE TRANSMITTED TO THE TERMINAL WITHOUT   @G@@@@ TRANSLATIONLV
)@@G@@ OTHER THAN THE ADDITION OF AN EIGHTH BIT TO FORCE EVEN     @F@@@@ PARITLW
)@@G@@Y.  NO CONTROL CHARACTERS ARE ADDED TO THE IMAGE BY THE     @#@@@@ OPERALX
)@@G@@TING SYSTEM.@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@3TIDE$ RESPONSE TO UOM ASCII  @F@@@@ IT WALY
)@@G@@S IMMEDIATELY OBVIOUS THAT ALLOWING IMAGES TO SHIFT MODE IN @E@@@@ MID-SLZ
)@@G@@TREAM PLACED AN INTOLERABLE BURDEN ON THE POINTER     @C@@@@ MANIPULATIOMA
)@@G@@N ROUTINES: TCOL$, TCOLN$, TSKIP$.  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ THEREFORE, IF AN MB
)@@G@@077 IS ENCOUNTERED (INDICATING A MODE SHIFT FROM@F@@@@ FIELDATA TO ASCIIMC
)@@G@@), THE TERMINATION CODE (IN A2) IS RETURNED WITH@F@@@@ A VALUE OF 3. THIMD
)@@G@@S DOES NOT APPLY TO THE 077 IN S1 OF THE FIRST  @A@@@@ WORD OF AN INITIAME
)@@G@@LLY ASCII IMAGE.  @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ THIS TERMINATION (A2=3) APPLIES ONLMF
)@@G@@Y TO NUMERIC ROUTINES CURRENTLY     @F@@@@ IN FIELDATA MODE. OTHER SCANNMG
)@@G@@ING ROUTINES (TSCANV$, ETC.) WILL   @G@@@@ SCAN THE 077 AND PROBABLY JUSMH
)@@G@@T RETURN WITH A BREAKARACTER TERMCODE     @]@@@@ OF ONE.    @^@@@@4ASCIIMI
)@@G@@ INPUT UNDER TIDE$@]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@ ALTHOUGH DESIGNED PRIMARILY FMJ
)@@G@@OR NUMERIC SCANNING, TIDE$ WILL     @F@@@@ ACCEPT AND TRANSMIT ASCII INPMK
)@@G@@UT. THERE IS, HOWEVER, NO REASON WHY@F@@@@ TIDE$ SHOULD CONCERN ITSELF WML
)@@G@@ITH THE MULTITUDINOUS ASCII CONTROL @]@@@@ CHARACTERS.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@MM
)@@G@@ TIDE$ THEREFORE REQUIRES THAT, IN ADDITION TO THE ASCII CHARACTER@E@@@@MN
)@@G@@ IT FETCHES FROM THE CARD IMAGE, IT BE GIVEN THE EQUIVALENT @G@@@@ FIELDMO
)@@G@@ATA CHARACTER. THE ONLY TIME TIDE$ DIRECTLY MANIPULATES ASCII     @F@@@@MP
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS IS WHEN TRANSFERRING ALPHANUMERIC STRINGS (EITHER     @E@@@@MQ
)@@G@@ GENINT DELIMITED ALPHANUMERIC, OR THE NON-DELIMITED TSCANV$@F@@@@ STRINMR
)@@G@@GS).  ALPHANUMERIC STRINGS READ IN AS FIELDATA ARE ALWAYS   @F@@@@ TRANSMS
)@@G@@MITTED AS SUCH, WHILE ASCII STRINGS MAY BE STORED AS EITHER @^@@@@ ASCIIMT
)@@G@@ OR FIELDATA.     @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ TO SATISFY THIS REQUIREMENT, THE USMU
)@@G@@ER SUPPLIES A 32-WORD   @F@@@@ ASCII-FIELDATA QUARTER-WORD TRANSLATION TMV
)@@G@@ABLE, WITH EACH ASCII   @F@@@@ CHARACTER MAPPED TO IT'S FIELDATA EQUIVALMW
)@@G@@ENT. IN ADDITION TO THE @G@@@@ STANDARD FIELDATA CHARACTERS (0-63), THE MX
)@@G@@VALUES 64-71 ARE ALLOWED.     @G@@@@ SETTING ASCII CHARACTERS TO THESE VMY
)@@G@@ALUES HAS THE FOLLOWING MEANING     @ @@@@ TO TIDE$ NUMERIC ROUTINES:   MZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 13   @E@@@@       64 - NULL CHARACTER. IGNORED NA
)@@G@@COMPLETELY (UNLESS IN   @ @@@@            ALPHANUMERIC MODE)@ @@@@      NB
)@@G@@ 65 - ERROR CHARACTER.  @B@@@@       66 - BREAKARACTER. TERMINATE FIELD.NC
)@@G@@@E@@@@       67 - ASCII ALPHA DELIMITER. TRANSFER ASCII CHARACTERS@E@@@@ND
)@@G@@       68 - SUPER BREAKARACTER. TERMINATE FIELD AND LINE    @E@@@@      NE
)@@G@@      (EX.CARRIAGE RETURN), RETURNS WITH END-OF-CARD  @A@@@@            NF
)@@G@@TERMINATION CODE (A2=2).@F@@@@       69-71 - TREATED AS ERROR CHARACTERSNG
)@@G@@, BUT CAN BE TURNED INTO@F@@@@            BREAK BY SETTING THE APPROPRIANH
)@@G@@TE BITS IN THE MASK     @#@@@@            'MSK'.@[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@3ASCIINI
)@@G@@-FIELDATA CONVERSION TABLE    @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @C@@@@ THE TABLE IS GENENJ
)@@G@@RATED BY THE FOLLOWING PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       T$ATBL    A(1),A(NK
)@@G@@2),A(3),F(1)  A(4),F(2)  ETC. @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@ A(I) IS ASCII,   F(J) INL
)@@G@@S THE FIELDATA COUNTERPART    @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ DEFAULT CONNM

)@@G@@ERS TO LETTERS, DIGITS TO DIGITS, ETC), AND ALL ASCII SPECIAL     @G@@@@NO
)@@G@@ CHARS (0-037) MAP TO '?', WITH THE EXCEPTIONS OF 015(CR), 017(SI),     NP
)@@G@@@F@@@@ AND 023(XOFF), WHICH GO TO 68 (SUPERBREAK).  016(SO) AND 000(NUL)NQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@ ARE SET TO 64 (IGNORE).@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ EXAMPLE    @[@@@@SPACE NR
)@@G@@@ @@@@       T$ATBL    '$','"',67   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ THIS TURNS '$' ANNS

)@@G@@EJECT @^@@@@3ASCII UTILITY ROUTINES @F@@@@ A FEW ROUTINES HAVE BEEN PROVPT

)@@G@@@#@@@@1ESCAPE RETURN    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ THE 'ESCAPE' CHAR (USUALLY SESQ
)@@G@@T TO 033 (ESC)) ALLOWS MODIFICATION @F@@@@ OF THE CHAR AFTER THE ESCAPE,SR

)@@G@@E ESCAPE CHAR. THIS ALLOWS INPUT OF @F@@@@ QUESTION MARKS, FOR EXAMPLE. SZ

)@@G@@G CHARACTER @F@@@@ (CARRIAGE RETURN, SHIFT IN, XOFF) WAS ENCOUNTERED. ITTC

)@@G@@@F@@@@ RATHER THAN TEST NUMEROUS REGISTERS TO DETERMINE THE TERMINATION TQ

)@@G@@@B@@@@ THERE ARE FOUR ADDRESS FIELDS AVAILABLE: @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMNTV
)@@G@@ 18   @F@@@@ 1) ERRXIT       TIDE$ RETURNS TO THIS ADDRESS IN THE EVENT TW
)@@G@@OF AN @F@@@@                 ERRORETURN (NON-ZERO A1). THIS RETURN IS ALTX

)@@G@@NES.  TCOL$, TSKIP$, ETC. ARE NOT AFFECTED.     @#@@@@4INTERRUPT-REENTRYUP
)@@G@@@F@@@@ WITH THE EXCEPTION OF NUMERIC ERRORS, TIDE$ NUMERIC ROUTINES     UQ

)@@G@@@G@@@@ BY PROPERLY SETTING THE 6-BIT PACKET MASK 'REN', THE USER MAY GAIUV
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@ CONTROL IMMEDIATELY, ALLOWING HIM TO TERMINATE NORMALLY, ORUW

)@@G@@,XU     A0,NARG   @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,TINTV$@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@BG
)@@G@@ THE FIRST CALL TO TINTV$ BLANKS OUT GLOM AND STORES 'A' IN S1. A0@G@@@@BH
)@@G@@ RETURNS EQUAL TO  (1,GLOM) INDICATING THAT THE NEXT CHARACTER WILL     BI
)@@G@@@#@@@@ GO IN S2 OF GLOM.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ BECAUSE THE INCREMENT PORTIONBJ
)@@G@@ OF A0 IS NON-ZERO, GLOM IS NOT     @F@@@@ BLANKED OUT BY THE SECOND CALBK
)@@G@@L (WHICH IS FORTUNATE), AND THE FIVE@F@@@@ CHARACTERS    'Y$BC    ARE STBL
)@@G@@ORED IN S2 TO S5 OF GLOM. AN ENTIRE @F@@@@ WORD HAS BEEN FILLED, SO A0 RBM
)@@G@@ETURNS EQUAL TO  (0,GLOM+1), IN     @^@@@@ CONTINUED ALPHA MODE.  @[@@@@BN
)@@G@@SPACE @F@@@@ GLOM+1 IS BLANKED BY THE THIRD CALL, AND THE 3 CHARACTERS DBO
)@@G@@EF    @F@@@@ ARE INSERTED IN S1 THROUGH S3 OF GLOM+1. A TRAILING DELIMITBP
)@@G@@ER IS @C@@@@ DETECTED, AND CONTINUED ALPHA MODE IS STOPPED. @[@@@@SPACE BQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@ A0 RETURNS EQUAL TO (3,GLOM+1), BUT IS IMMEDIATELY LOADED WITH THBR
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@ ADDRESS OF NARG, WHICH IS BLANKED. 'X' IS PLACED IN S1.    BS
)@@G@@@[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3FUTURE IMPLEMENTATION  @F@@@@ TIDE$ WAS ORIGINALLY DEBT
)@@G@@SIGNED AS A FIELDATA PACKAGE, THEN LATER  @F@@@@ MODIFIED TO ACCEPT UOM BU
)@@G@@ASCII. FULL ASCII IMPLEMENTATION IS THE   @F@@@@ OBVIOUS NEXT STEP; INCLBV
)@@G@@UDING FIELDATA TO ASCII TRANSLATION, AND A@F@@@@ MORE COMPLETE SET OF INBW
)@@G@@TERFACE ROUTINES TO PROCESS ASCII INPUT.  @F@@@@ THE PACKET FLAGS 'ASC' BX
)@@G@@AND 'ASO' WILL PROBABLY BE PROMOTED TO    @F@@@@ GENERAL INPUT AND OUTPUBY
)@@G@@T ASCII FLAGS. IN THE FINAL STAGES, TIDE$ @E@@@@ WILL BE TRULY EQUIVALENBZ
)@@G@@T IN EITHER FIELDATA OR ASCII MODE. @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@CA
)@@G@@ MOST OF TIDE$ WAS FORMULATED BY THE AUTHOR WHILE DEVISING VARIOUS@G@@@@CB
)@@G@@ INPUT SCANNERS: ANY TASK MORE EASILY ACCOMPLISHED BY TIDE$ THAN BY     CC
)@@G@@@F@@@@ THE CALLING PROGRAM WAS IMMEDIATELY IMPLEMENTED; A LUXURY THAT   CD
)@@G@@@G@@@@ SOON SPAWNED AUTOMATIC RETURNS, REENTRY, ETC. OTHERS WHO HAVE USECE
)@@G@@D     @F@@@@ TIDE$ HAVE BEEN DISHEARTENINGLY COMPLIMENTARY: FEW SUGGESTICF
)@@G@@ONS   @F@@@@ HAVE BEEN FORTHCOMING. RECOMMENDATIONS OR REQUESTS ARE, HOWCG
)@@G@@EVER, @^@@@@ EAGERLY SOLICITED.     @[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3EXAMPLES OF TIDE$CH
)@@G@@ USE  @]@@@@2FREE FORMAT@A@@@@ SIMULATE THE FORTRAN SEQUENCE:     @[@@@@CI
)@@G@@SPACE @B@@@@      READ (5,10) A,B,I,(J(L),L=1,I),K    @]@@@@SPACE 0     CJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@ 10   FORMAT ()   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ IT'S EASILY DONE. FIRST SET UCK
)@@G@@P THE PACKET TO PROVIDE FOR AUTOMATIC     @A@@@@ END-OF-CARD AND ERROR RCL
)@@G@@ETURNS.     @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@         T$FIELDS  T                    TOCM
)@@G@@ GET TIDE$ LABELS @]@@@@SPACE 0     @D@@@@ BUF     RES       14         CN
)@@G@@       . CARD BUFFER    @]@@@@SPACE 0     @D@@@@ T       T$PKT     14,BUCO
)@@G@@F  'END',READ  'ERR',ERROR    @]@@@@SPACE 0     @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ THE ICP
)@@G@@NSTRUCTION SEQUENCE IS: @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@       T$IDE     T   0        CQ
)@@G@@     . OPEN PACKET@E@@@@       LMJ       X11,READ          . READ A CARDCR
)@@G@@ (SEE BELOW)@E@@@@       T$FLOV    A                 . FREE FORMAT FLOATCS
)@@G@@ING   @E@@@@       T$FLOV    B                 . NEXT NUMBER (FLOATING) CT
)@@G@@@D@@@@       T$INTV    I                 . INTEGER IS NEXT  @E@@@@      CU
)@@G@@ LR        R4,I              . TIDE$ USES R1,R2,R3    @C@@@@       LX   CV
)@@G@@     X8,(1,0)          . INDEX FOR J@D@@@@       JGD       R4,$+1       CW
)@@G@@     . DECREMENT FIRST  @]@@@@SPACE 0     @E@@@@ BLIP  T$INTV    J,*X8  CX
)@@G@@           . GET NEXT J (INTEGER)   @D@@@@       JGD       R4,BLIP      CY
)@@G@@     . BACK FOR MORE    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ AT THIS POINT WE DON'T CARE ICZ
)@@G@@F WE HIT AN END OF CARD, BECAUSE    @F@@@@ WE'RE GETTING THE LAST NUMBERDA
)@@G@@. SO TURN OFF THE AUTOMATIC RETURN, @C@@@@ AND FORCE THE TIDE$ ROUTINE TDB
)@@G@@O RETURN TO 0,X11.@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@       SZ        ENDXIT            .DC
)@@G@@ NO MORE ADDRESS  @D@@@@       T$INTV    K                 . LAST INTEGEDD
)@@G@@R     @D@@@@       T$IDEX                      . CLOSE PACKET     @]@@@@DE
)@@G@@          . @]@@@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@ END OF CARD RETURN. READ A NEW CARDDF
)@@G@@, AND RETURN TO 0,X11 (THE    @C@@@@ INSTRUCTION AFTER THE LAST TIDE$-RODG
)@@G@@UTINE CALL).@[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ READ  R$EAD     (EOF,BUF)         . READ DH
)@@G@@A CARD@D@@@@       LA,XU     A1,,A0            . GET WORD COUNT   @E@@@@DI
)@@G@@       JZ        A1,READ           . BLANKARD. READ ANOTHER @E@@@@      DJ
)@@G@@ J         TCLR$             . TCLR$ RETURNS TO 0,X11 @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@DK
)@@G@@ ERRORETURN:  ERROR P$RINT    (0101,('ERROR!')) . TELL HAPLESS USER     DL
)@@G@@@E@@@@       ER        ABORT$            . WE'RE ROUGH ON ERRORS  @[@@@@DM
)@@G@@EJECT @#@@@@2FIXED FORMAT     @A@@@@ CONSIDER THE FORTRAN SEQUENCE:     DN
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@      READ (5,10) A,I,(J(K),K=1,4),M,N    @]@@@@SPACE DO
)@@G@@0     @C@@@@ 10   FORMAT (3X,F10.8,T27,I6,3A6,A5,A6/1X,I10) @[@@@@SPACE DP
)@@G@@@F@@@@ FIRST, DEFINE THE PACKET TO TREAT ALL BLANKS IN NUMERIC FIELDS ASDQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ ZEROES, WHICH IS WHAT FIXED-FORMAT FORTRAN WANTS.  PROVIDE FOR   DR
)@@G@@@F@@@@ AUTOMATIC ERROR AND BREAKARACTER RETURNS, AS WE INTEND TO BE     DS
)@@G@@@B@@@@ FIXED-FORMAT, WITH NO USE FOR COMMAS.    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ T    DT
)@@G@@   T$PKT     14,BUF  'ERR',ERROR  'BLK',0  'BRX',BREAK .    @]@@@@SPACE DU
)@@G@@0     @^@@@@ BUF     RES       14   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ START. WE'LL ASSUDV
)@@G@@ME THAT THE DATA CONFORMS EXACTLY TO FORMAT     @F@@@@ SPECIFICATIONS, WDW
)@@G@@HICH ASSUMES THAT ALL RETURNS ARE END-OF-FIELD. @E@@@@ IF THE OCCURRENCEDX
)@@G@@ OF A BREAKARACTER TERMINATES SCANNING    @E@@@@ PREMATURELY, WE GO TO ADY
)@@G@@ LITTLE ROUTINE THAT SKIPS OVER THE @^@@@@ REMAINDER OF THE FIELD.@[@@@@DZ
)@@G@@SPACE @D@@@@       R$EAD     (EOF,BUF)         . READ A CARD IMAGE@E@@@@EA
)@@G@@       T$IDE     T  0,A0           . OPEN PACKET, BEGIN     @B@@@@      EB
)@@G@@ T$SKIP    3                 . 3X   @B@@@@       T$FLOF    A  10        EC
)@@G@@     . F10.8@F@@@@       T$COL     26                . OUR COL 26 IS THEED
)@@G@@IR COL 27   @B@@@@       T$DECF    I  6              . I6   @F@@@@      EE
)@@G@@ T$SCANF   J (0D) 18         . 3A6 (NO MASK) J(1),J(2),J(3) @E@@@@      EF
)@@G@@ LA        A2,('      ')     . DON'TOUCH A0! BLANK OUT@F@@@@       SA   EG
)@@G@@     A2,J+3            . J(4) BECAUSE TSCANV$ WON'T.  @F@@@@       T$SCNEH
)@@G@@RF   5                 . REENTER. SAME A0 AND MASK.   @D@@@@            EI
)@@G@@                       . 1A5 INTO J(4)    @F@@@@       T$SCANF   M (0D) EJ
)@@G@@6          . NEW VARIABLE (OR NEW MASK)   @E@@@@                        EK
)@@G@@           . GETS NEW ROUTINE CALL  @E@@@@       R$EAD     (EOF,BUF)    EL
)@@G@@     . NEW CARD IS READ IN    @E@@@@       T$CLR     0,A0              .EM
)@@G@@ WITH NEW WORD COUNT. . @B@@@@       T$SKIP    1                 . 1X   EN
)@@G@@@C@@@@       T$DECF    N  10             . I10 FORMAT @#@@@@       T$IDEEO
)@@G@@X     @]@@@@          . @]@@@@SPACE 0     @G@@@@ BREAKARACTER RETURN. THEP
)@@G@@IS INDICATES THAT THE OCCURRENCE OF A COMMA     @F@@@@ HAS SUSPENDED SCAEQ
)@@G@@NNING.  THIS ROUTINE SKIPS OVER THE REMAINS OF  @#@@@@ DEAD FIELDS.     ER
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ BREAK LA        A0,R1             . GET # TO SKIP, GOES
)@@G@@TO TSKIP$   @G@@@@       J         TSKIP$            . WITH IT, THEN RETET
)@@G@@URN TO 0,X11.     @[@@@@EJECT @]@@@@2ASCII INPUT@E@@@@ FINALLY, LET'S REEU
)@@G@@AD (POSSIBLY ASCII) CARDS OF THE FORM:    @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@EV
)@@G@@ COMMAND   NUMBER1  NUMBER2/NAME    @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ COMMAEW
)@@G@@ND AND NAME ARE STRINGS OF UP TO 10 CHARACTERS. THE FIRST   @F@@@@ CHARAEX
)@@G@@CTER MUST BE A LETTER, AND THE FOLLOWING CHARACTERS MUST BE @F@@@@ DIGITEY
)@@G@@S. NUMBER1 AND NUMBER2 ARE NUMBERS OF UNKNOWN TYPE.  IN     @G@@@@ ADDITEZ
)@@G@@ION, THE OCCURRENCE OF A ';' ANYWHERE (EXCEPT IN A NAME) SETS     @B@@@@FA
)@@G@@ A FLAG. ALL THIS GOES INTO THE PACKET.   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@         T$FFB
)@@G@@IELDS  T                    TO GET TIDE$ LABELS @]@@@@SPACE 0     @D@@@@FC
)@@G@@ BUF     RES       20                . ROOM FOR ASCII @]@@@@SPACE 0     FD
)@@G@@@E@@@@ ASCTBL  T$ATBL                      . CONVERSION TABLE     @]@@@@FE
)@@G@@SPACE 0     @F@@@@ T       T$PKTGN   20,BUF  'END',ERROR  'ERR',ERROR  'FF
)@@G@@BLK',0  ;   @E@@@@        'FDA',ASCTBL  'MSK',+(T$MASKR '/')  'REN',1*/4FG
)@@G@@  ;   @E@@@@         'RNX',REENTRY 'NLG',10  'MK2',+(T$MASKR 'NUM') .   FH
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 0     @[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ NOTICE THAT END-OF-CARDFI
)@@G@@S AND ERROR TERMINATIONS GO TO ERROR, '/' @F@@@@ IS A BREAKARACTER, ASCTFJ
)@@G@@BL IS THE ASCII TO FIELDATA CONVERSION    @F@@@@ TABLE, ERROR CHARACTERSFK
)@@G@@ TAKE THE REENTRY RETURN (WHERE WE CAN SEE@F@@@@ IF THE OFFENDING CHARACFL
)@@G@@TER IS A SEMI-COLON), AND LEADING BLANKS  @F@@@@ ARE IGNORED, WHILE TRAIFM
)@@G@@LING BLANKS ARE BREAKARACTERS. ALSO, THE  @F@@@@ MAXIMUM NAME SIZE HAS BFN
)@@G@@EEN SET AT 10 CHARACTERS (DEFAULT WAS 12) @F@@@@ AND THE 2ND NAME MASK (FO
)@@G@@ANY CHARACTERS AFTER THE FIRST) WAS SET TO@D@@@@ ALLOW DIGITS (NO DOLLARFP
)@@G@@ SIGNS OR LETTERS, PLEASE).   @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ START BY READING A CARDFQ
)@@G@@. SEE IF WE'RE ASCII:   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ READ  T$RD      (EOF,BUF)  T FR
)@@G@@     . READ DATA, SET 'ASC' FLAG    @C@@@@                              FS
)@@G@@     . AND A2     @D@@@@       LA,XU     A1,,A0            . GET WORD COFT
)@@G@@UNT   @C@@@@       JZ        A1,READ           . BLANKARD?  @C@@@@      FU
)@@G@@ JZ        A2,NORMAL         . ASCII?     @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@ IT'S AN ASCFV
)@@G@@II IMAGE, SO CLEAN IT UP, PUT IT BACK INTO BUF. @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@      FW
)@@G@@ T$CLN     BUF BUF A1,,W 0137 077 033  . CLEAN UP ASCII IMAGE     @F@@@@FX
)@@G@@       J         READ              . QUESTION-MARK. READ AGAIN.   @E@@@@FY
)@@G@@       ER        ABORT$            . FULL BUFFER. GIVE UP.  @E@@@@      FZ
)@@G@@ T$CLNESC                    . ESCAPE. TAKE AS IT.    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@GA
)@@G@@ NORMAL RETURN FROM TCLN$. ADD A LINEFEED SO WE CAN PRINT IMAGE   @^@@@@GB
)@@G@@ LATER, AND CONTINUE.   @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@       T$CLNADD  012          GC
)@@G@@     . LINEFEED   @F@@@@       LA,XU     A1,4,X7           . CHARACTER CGD
)@@G@@OUNT (INCLUDES    @C@@@@                                   .  LINEFEED) GE
)@@G@@@D@@@@                                   . ADD 3 FOR ROUNDUP@E@@@@      GF
)@@G@@ SSL       A1,2              . THIS IS THE WORD COUNT @D@@@@            GG
)@@G@@                       . (ROUNDED-UP)     @]@@@@SPACE 0     @G@@@@ NORMAGH
)@@G@@L  T$IDE   T                 . OPEN PACKET. A1 HAS WORD COUNT     @E@@@@GI
)@@G@@       DL        A0,('            ') . BLANK OUT NAMES,     @D@@@@      GJ
)@@G@@ DS        A0,COMMAND        . BECAUSE TGENV$   @C@@@@       DS        AGK
)@@G@@0,NAME           . WON'T DO IT@C@@@@       T$GENV    COMMAND           .GL
)@@G@@ FIRST NAME @G@@@@       T$GENV    NUMBER1           . T$FIELDS DEFINED GM
)@@G@@THE PACKET FLAG   @F@@@@       LA        A0,MODE           . 'MODE' FOR GN
)@@G@@US. IT'S THE MODE @F@@@@       SA        A0,MODENUM1       . OF NUMBER1.GO
)@@G@@ SAVE IT SOMEWHERE@D@@@@       T$GENV    NUMBER2           . DO THE SAMEGP
)@@G@@ FOR  @C@@@@       LA        A0,MODE           . NUMBER2    @C@@@@      GQ
)@@G@@ SA        A0,MODENUM2       . LIKE THIS  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ HAVE WE HITGR
)@@G@@ THE '/' YET, OR DID WE STOP AFTER READING NUMBER2    @F@@@@ BECAUSE WE GS
)@@G@@HIT A BLANK BEFORE THE '/'?  FIND OUT. FIND THE '/'.  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@GT
)@@G@@       TNE,U     A3,'/'            . A3 IS LAST CHARACTER (BREAK) @F@@@@GU
)@@G@@       J         LAST              . IT WAS THE '/' AFTER ALL.    @F@@@@GV
)@@G@@       T$FINDA   '/'  ERROR        . FIND SLASH. POSSIBLY ASCII   @[@@@@GW
)@@G@@SPACE @E@@@@ WE ARE AT LAST READY TO READ THE LAST NAME, SO ALLOW THE   GX
)@@G@@@D@@@@ END-OF-CARD TERMINATION. CLEAR THE PACKET ADDRESS.   @[@@@@SPACE GY
)@@G@@@C@@@@ LAST  SZ        ENDXIT            . CLEARED    @C@@@@       T$GENGZ
)@@G@@V    NAME              . LAST THING @#@@@@       T$IDEX     @]@@@@      HA
)@@G@@    . @F@@@@          .  COME HERE IF WE ERROR OR ENCOUNTER AN END-OF-CAHB
)@@G@@RD.   @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ ERROR   ER        ERR$              .    @[@@@@HC
)@@G@@SPACE @G@@@@ COME HERE IF WE HIT AN ERROR CHARACTER. IF IT (A7) IS A SEMHD
)@@G@@ICOLON,     @E@@@@ SET THE FLAG AND SKIP OVER THE CONTINGENCY. IF IT'S NHE
)@@G@@OT A  @C@@@@ SEMICOLON, RETURN TO DIE (EVENTUAL ERRCHAR).   @[@@@@SPACE HF
)@@G@@@E@@@@ REENTRY LA,XU     A3,,A3            . GET FIELDATA PART    @D@@@@HG
)@@G@@         TE,U      A3,';'            . WELL, IS IT?   @D@@@@         J  HH
)@@G@@       0,X7              . NO, SO DIE     @F@@@@         SR        R3,SEHI
)@@G@@MICOLONFLAG  . R3=1, SO USE IT TO SET FLAG@C@@@@         J         TREN$HJ
)@@G@@             . CONTINUE ___0 F@F@@@@         SR        R3,SEMICOLONFLAG HK
)@@G@@ . R3=1, SO USE IT TO SET FLAG@C@@@@         J  *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     HL
)@@G@@@D@@@@. PROCEDURES TO CALL FIASG$ AND FIFREE$ ROUTINES.     @A@@@@. FIBIHM
)@@G@@TS WRITTEN BY MIKE MCAMIS     @A@@@@. FIASG  WRITTEN BY ALAN STEBBENS   HN
)@@G@@@A@@@@. FIFREE WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @A@@@@. FIPFIL WRITTEN BY BEN HO
)@@G@@CRANSTON    @A@@@@. FIPELT WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@HP
)@@G@@. FIASG UPDATED TO WORK IN ASCII OR FIELDATA - 2/11/76, AKS.@[@@@@.     HQ
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         DEFINE BITS FOR FIASG$    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          DEHR
)@@G@@F                         .   @D@@@@FBIT      EQU       001             HS
)@@G@@  . FORCE USE NAME@D@@@@UBIT      EQU       002               . USE NAMEHT
)@@G@@ GIVEN@D@@@@XBIT      EQU       004               . GET ASG,AX    @E@@@@HU
)@@G@@RBIT      EQU       010               . GET READ PERMISSION @E@@@@WBIT  HV
)@@G@@    EQU       020               . GET WRITE PERMISSION@D@@@@OBIT      EQHW
)@@G@@U       040               . OPTIONS IN A3 @B@@@@FIBITS*   PROC      0,0 HX
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@HY
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. TO ASSIGN A FILE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         FIASG,'OPTS' PHZ
)@@G@@ACKET,BITS NAME   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *2              IA
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@FIASG*    NAME                        .   @E@@@@N         EQIB
)@@G@@U       6+3*(' '=040)     . # OF BITS PER CHAR  @E@@@@C         EQU     IC
)@@G@@  077+0700*(N=9)    . SET PROPER MASK     @D@@@@          ON        P(1)ID
)@@G@@>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. FUNCTION TO GET BIT FOIE
)@@G@@R 'BITS' LETTER.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@F         FUNC      *               IF
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@PBIT*     NAME                        .   @E@@@@I         DOIG
)@@G@@      6 , DO M(0)*/(N-N*I)**C=F(1) , END F(2)   @D@@@@          END     IH
)@@G@@  +0                . STRANGE BITS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@M(0)      EQU     II
)@@G@@  P(1,2)+0D         . PICK UP MODE LETTERS@F@@@@B(0)      EQU       PBITIJ
)@@G@@('F',1)+PBIT('U',2)+PBIT('X',4)+; F,U,X   @F@@@@                    PBITIK
)@@G@@('R',8)+PBIT('W',16)+PBIT('O',32)++; R,W,O@G@@@@                    2*(PIL
)@@G@@(2)>0)+32*(P(0)>1) . FORCE BITS IF NECESSARY    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. NOW IM
)@@G@@GENERATE CODE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          LA,U      A0,P(1,1)       IN
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          DO (B(0)=0)=0 , LXI,U A0,B(0) . @D@@@@          OFIO
)@@G@@F       P(1)>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(2)>0 ,IP
)@@G@@ DL A1,P(2,1),P(2,2)      . GET FILENAME  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          ONIQ
)@@G@@        P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @E@@@@          ON        P(0,IR
)@@G@@1)=0=0        . SOMETHING THERE?    @E@@@@          ON        N=9       IS
)@@G@@        . ASCII CHARACTERSET? @G@@@@F         FUNC      *               IT
)@@G@@  . ASCII TO FIELDATA MAPPING FUNC  @B@@@@ATOF*     NAME                IU
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@        DO (F(1)=' ')++(F(1)=0) , END +0 . ABLANK     IV
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO        (F(1)<'A')++(F(1)>'Z') , END +09) . BAD NEWS  IW
)@@G@@@F@@@@          END       F(1)-'A'+6        . CHANGE TO FIELDATA   A    IX
)@@G@@@E@@@@I         DO        6 ,;                MAXIMUM OF 6 CHARS  @I@@@@IY
)@@G@@P(0,1)    EQU       (P(0,1)**-(C*/(I*9-9)))+ATOF(P(0,1)*/(9-9*I)**C)*/(IIZ
)@@G@@*6-6) .     @E@@@@          OFF       N=9               . ASCII CHARACTEJA
)@@G@@RSET? @G@@@@I DO 6 , DO P(0,1)**C*/30=0 ,P(0,1) EQU P(0,1)*/6+5 . FILL TJB
)@@G@@HE FIELDATA @F@@@@G         FORM      36                . WE WANT ONLY OJC
)@@G@@NE WORD     @D@@@@          L         A3,(G P(0,1))       . LOAD LITERALJD
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OFF       P(0,1)=0=0        .   @F@@@@          DO      JE
)@@G@@  P(0,1)=0 , LA,U   A3,0 . CLEAR OPTIONS REG    @D@@@@          OFF     JF
)@@G@@  P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. FINALLY, CALL SUJG
)@@G@@BROUTINE    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,FIASG$        . ASJH
)@@G@@SIGN FILE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   JI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS USED TO CALL THE DIAGNOSTIC ROUTINJJ
)@@G@@E FIDIAG$   @F@@@@. IF A CSF$ ERROR IS DETECTED THE ERROR$ REP IS CALLEDJK
)@@G@@.  IF THE   @D@@@@. ERROR IS PERMISSIONS FIDIAG PRINTS THE MESSAGE.     JL
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *0,1              .   @B@@@@FIDIAGJM
)@@G@@*   NAME      FIDIAG$           .   @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,P(0,0)JN
)@@G@@        . CALL ROUTINE  @B@@@@          END                         .   JO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO FREE A FILE WHICH HAS BEJP
)@@G@@EN ASSIGNED @ @@@@. VIA FIASG$. THE CALL IS:    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     JQ
)@@G@@    FIFREE    NAME FREECODE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *2  JR
)@@G@@              .   @D@@@@FIFREE*   NAME      FIFREE$           . NORMAL FJS
)@@G@@REE   @E@@@@FIFRIM*   NAME      FIFRIM$           . RETURN FREE IMAGE   JT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , DL A1,P(1,1),P(1,2)      . GET FILE NAME JU
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO P(2)>0 , L  A0,P(2,1),P(2,2),P(2,3) . GET FREE CODE     @F@@@@JV
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,P(0,0)        . CALL SELECTED ROUTINE     @[@@@@JW
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@JX
)@@G@@. GENERATE FIASG$ PACKET.  THE CALLS ARE: @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.         FIJY
)@@G@@PFIL    'Q','QUAL' 'F','FILE' ....  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE FIRST SUBFIEJZ
)@@G@@LD OF EACH FIELD IS A CODE LETTER, IN QUOTES :  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.     KA
)@@G@@    'Q' - QUALIFIER     @^@@@@.         'F' - FILENAME@^@@@@.         'RKB
)@@G@@' - READKEY @^@@@@.         'W' - WRITEKEY@ @@@@.         'C' - FILECYCLKC
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF THE PROCEDURE FIPELT IS CALLED THE FULL 14 KD
)@@G@@WORD ELT$ PACKET  @F@@@@. IS GENERATED AND THE FOLLOWING ADDITION FIELDSKE
)@@G@@ ARE ALLOWED.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         'E' - ELEMENT NAME  @ @@@@KF
)@@G@@.         'V' - VERSION NAME  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE SECOND SUBFIELD OFKG
)@@G@@ EACH FIELD IS A STRING OF NOT MORE THAN  @F@@@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENKH
)@@G@@DING ON THE NORMAL LENGTH OF THAT FIELD)  @ @@@@. ENCLOSED IN QUOTATION KI
)@@G@@MARKS.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *8                .   @E@@@@KJ
)@@G@@FIPFIL*   NAME      0                 . ONLY FILE PORTION   @G@@@@FIPELTKK
)@@G@@*   NAME      1                 . BOTH FILE AND ELEMENT PORTIONS  @[@@@@KL
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@B(1)      EQU       0D                . PRESENCE BITS (2 WORKM
)@@G@@DS)   @D@@@@Q(1)      EQU       0D                . QUALIFIER (2) @D@@@@KN
)@@G@@F(1)      EQU       0D                . FILENAME (2)  @D@@@@R(1)      EQKO
)@@G@@U       0                 . READKEY (1)   @D@@@@W(1)      EQU       0   KP
)@@G@@              . WRITEKEY (1)  @D@@@@C(1)      EQU       0               KQ
)@@G@@  . CYCLE (1)     @E@@@@E(1)      EQU       0D                . ELEMENT KR
)@@G@@NAME (2)    @E@@@@V(1)      EQU       0D                . VERSION NAME(2KS
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@I DO P-1 , FISCAN   .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@      KT
)@@G@@    +         B(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         Q(1)      KU
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         F(1)              .   @B@@@@      KV
)@@G@@    +         C(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         R(1)      KW
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         W(1)              .   @B@@@@      KX
)@@G@@    ON        P(0,0)            .   @B@@@@          +         E(1)      KY
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         V(1)              .   @B@@@@      KZ
)@@G@@    +         0                 .   @B@@@@          OFF       P(0,0)    LA
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          END       .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@LB
)@@G@@. PROCEDURE TO PROCESS EACH FIELD.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@FISCAN*   PROC    LC
)@@G@@  *0,0              . SECOND GLOBAL PASS ONLY   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@ DO P(LD
)@@G@@I,1)='Q' ,Q*(1) FIW2 66 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='F' ,F*(1) FIW2 60 .     LE
)@@G@@@A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='C' ,C*(1) FIW1 54 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='R' ,R*(1) FILF
)@@G@@W1 48 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='W' ,W*(1) FIW1 42 .     @B@@@@          ONLG
)@@G@@        P(0,0)            .   @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='E' ,E*(1) FIW2 30 .     LH
)@@G@@@A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='V' ,V*(1) FIW2 24 .     @B@@@@          OFF       P(0,LI
)@@G@@0)            .   @B@@@@ DO FOUND(1)=0 , +09                  .   @B@@@@LJ
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURE LK
)@@G@@TO LEFT JUSTIFY AND STORE THE COMPONENT.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Z         PRLL
)@@G@@OC      *1,0              .   @B@@@@FIW2*     NAME                      LM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@P**(I,2)  EQU       P(I,2)++0D        .   @F@@@@ DO 12 , DO LN
)@@G@@(P(I,2)*/-66)**077=0 ,P**(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 .     @B@@@@FIW1*     NALO
)@@G@@ME                        .   @F@@@@ DO 06 , DO (P(I,2)*/-30)**077=0 ,P*LP
)@@G@@*(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 .     @B@@@@*         EQU       P(I,2)          LQ
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@B**(1)    EQU       B(1)++1D*/Z(1,1)   .  @B@@@@FOUND*(1) EQLR
)@@G@@U       1                 .   @^@@@@          END       .   ___N  @F@@@[LS
)@@G@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENDING ON THE NORMAL LENGT*[S@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@      LT
)@@G@@  SAXR$                         . STRUCTURED AXR$, DEFINES U-PROC @B@@@@LU
)@@G@@OP      EQU     '@OLD PROGRAM'        .   @G@@@@        STRUC$          LV
)@@G@@              . DEFINE STRUCTURED PROCEDURES    @D@@@@        E$DEF   **LW
)@@G@@*   EDIT$ EDITING PACKAGE   ***     @]@@@@$(1)    LIT.@F@@@@ .          LX
)@@G@@                   EDIT$ DESIGNED AND IMPLEMENTED BY  @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@LY
)@@G@@ .                             DEREK A ZAVE  (MARCH 1968)   @[@@@@ .    LZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@VERSION EQU     E$VER$$               . DISPLAY EDIT$ VERSION     MA
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .              EDIT$ IS A UNIFIED COLLECTION OF EDITIMB
)@@G@@NG ROUTINES @F@@@@ .         WHICH ALLOWS THE USER TO EASILY COMPOSE COMMC
)@@G@@PLEX STRINGS@F@@@@ .         OF FIELDATA CHARACTERS FOR MANY APPLICATIONMD
)@@G@@S, SUCH AS  @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .                1. PRINTED OUTPUT.@[@@@@ME
)@@G@@ .    @A@@@@ .                2. PUNCHED OUTPUT.@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .    MF
)@@G@@            3. IMAGES FOR CSF$ AND OTHER EXECUTIVE REQUESTS.@[@@@@ .    MG
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .         ALL COMMUNICATION BETWEEN EDIT$ AND THE USER IS DONE   MH
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .         THROUGH THE REGISTERS A0 AND A1. INFORMATION IS SAVED  MI
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .         IN A SIX WORD PACKET SUPPLIED BY THE USER. EDIT$ IS    MJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .         REENTRANT BUT MUST BE USED IN THE USER'S REGISTER SET. MK
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .         THE REGISTERS X11, A0, A1, A2, A3, AND R1 ARE THE ONLY ML
)@@G@@@B@@@@ .         REGISTERS DESTROYED BY EDIT$.  @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .    MM
)@@G@@          TO USE EDIT$ THE USER MUST FIRST ESTABLISH HIMSELF@F@@@@ .    MN
)@@G@@     IN EDIT MODE BY CALLING EDIT$ WITH A0 CONTAINING THE   @F@@@@ .    MO
)@@G@@     LOCATION OF HIS PACKET. HE MUST SUPPLY THE FOLLOWING   @D@@@@ .    MP
)@@G@@     INFORMATION IN THE FIRST WORD OF THE PACKET@[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .    MQ
)@@G@@           S2: SIGNAL CHARACTER FOR EMSG$ @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .          MR
)@@G@@     S3: LENGTH OF THE IMAGE IN WORDS     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .          MS
)@@G@@     H2: LOCATION OF THE IMAGE@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .         THE REST OF TMT
)@@G@@HE PACKET IS FILLED BY EDIT$ EXCEPT FOR   @F@@@@ .         THE S1-FIELD MU
)@@G@@OF THE FIRST WORD WHICH MAY BE USED AS    @F@@@@ .         A TEST-AND-SEMV
)@@G@@T FLAG. EDIT$ SAVES X1,X2, AND X3 IN THE  @F@@@@ .         PACKET AND INMW
)@@G@@ITIALIZES THESE REGISTERS. THE IMAGE IS   @F@@@@ .         THEN SET TO BMX
)@@G@@LANKS AND RETURN IS MADE TO THE USER.     @F@@@@ .             THE USER MY
)@@G@@IS NOW IN EDIT MODE AND HE MAY FREELY     @F@@@@ .         CALL THE VARIMZ
)@@G@@OUS EDITING FUNCTIONS WHICH ARE AVAILABLE @F@@@@ .         TO HIM. HE MUNA
)@@G@@ST, HOWEVER, LEAVE X1,X2, AND X3 INTACT.  @F@@@@ .             TO LEAVE NB
)@@G@@EDIT MODE THE USER CALLS EDITX$. THIS     @F@@@@ .         ROUTINE SAVESNC
)@@G@@ HIS POINTERS, RESTORES X1,X2, AND X3 FROM@F@@@@ .         THE PACKET ANND
)@@G@@D RETURNS TO HIM WITH A0 CONTAINING THE   @E@@@@ .         PACKET ADDRESNE
)@@G@@S. HE IS NO LONGER IN EDIT MODE.    @G@@@@ .             IF THE USER HASNF
)@@G@@ NOT COMPLETED COMPOSING HIS IMAGE HE     @G@@@@ .         MAY CALL EDITNG
)@@G@@R$ WITH A0 CONTAINING THE PACKET ADDRESS TO     @G@@@@ .         RE-ENTENH
)@@G@@R EDIT MODE AND PICK UP EXACTLY WHERE HE LEFT OFF.    @C@@@@/.        RENI
)@@G@@PUTEDLY OPTIMIZED, ASCIIFIED BY     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .         JEFF JENJ
)@@G@@WETT  (JAN 1973)  UOM   @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         ZAVING THE BEST FORNK
)@@G@@ LAST @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .         EDIT$ ROUTINES - THE ENDLNL
)@@G@@ESS SUMMARY @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .         ALL ROUTINES USE X11,A0,A1,A2,ANM
)@@G@@3, AND R1 UNLESS SPECIFIED    @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         INITIALIZATIONN
)@@G@@N ROUTINES  @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .                   EDIT$  -  INITIAL ENTNO
)@@G@@RY    @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .                   EDITX$ -  EXIT @[@@@@ .    NP
)@@G@@@B@@@@ .                   EDITR$ -  RE-ENTRY   @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .    NQ
)@@G@@               ECLR$  -  CLEAR BUFFER, RESET COLUMN POINTER @[@@@@ .    NR
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .         COLUMN MANIPULATION ROUTINES   @[@@@@ .    NS
)@@G@@@E@@@@ .                   ECOL$  -  POSITION TO A FIXED COLUMN   @[@@@@NT
)@@G@@ .    @C@@@@ .                   ESKIP$ -  SKIP AN AREA     @[@@@@ .    NU
)@@G@@@E@@@@ .                   ECOLN$ -  COMPUTE THE COLUMN NUMBER    @[@@@@NV
)@@G@@ .    @D@@@@ .                   EWRDN$ -  COMPUTE WORD COUNT     @[@@@@NW
)@@G@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         ALPHANUMERIC ROUTINES    @[@@@@ .    NX
)@@G@@@C@@@@ .                   ECHAR$ -  EDIT A CHARACTER @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@NY
)@@G@@ .                   EPAD$  -  INSERT CHARACTER A0 TIMES    @[@@@@ .    NZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .                   EFD1$   - INSERT FIELDATA OR ASCII (ONE WORD)OA
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .                   EFD2$   - INSERT FIELDATA OR ASCIOB
)@@G@@I (TWO WORDS)     @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .                   EFD3$   - INSEROC
)@@G@@T FIELDATA OR ASCII (THREE WORD)    @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .                OD
)@@G@@   ECOPY$  - COPY A STRING    @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   EPAOE
)@@G@@CK$  - COPY A STRING (EXCEPT '@')   @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .                OF
)@@G@@   EPACKC$ - COPY A STRING (EXCEPT THE CHAR IN A2)    @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@OG
)@@G@@ .                   EMSG$   - MESSAGE EDITOR (INITIAL ENTRY)     @[@@@@OH
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   EMSGR$  - MESSAGE EDITOR (RE-ENTRY)    OI
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .                   EMSKP$  - MESSAGE FIELD SKIP     OJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @ @@@@ .         INTEGER ROUTINES   @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .    OK
)@@G@@               EOCTV$  - EDIT OCTAL (VARIABLE LENGTH FIELD) @[@@@@ .    OL
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .                   EOCTF$  - EDIT OCTAL (FIXED LENGTH FIELD)    OM
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .                   EDECV$  - EDIT DECIMAL (VARIABLE ON
)@@G@@LENGTH FIELD)     @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                   EDECF$  - EDIT OO
)@@G@@DECIMAL (FIXED LENGTH FIELD)  @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   EDEOP
)@@G@@CFZ$ - EDIT DECIMAL (LEADING ZEROES)@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                OQ
)@@G@@   EDECFL$ - EDIT DECIMAL (LEADING CHARACTERS)  @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    OR
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         INTEGER FORM ROUTINES    @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@OS
)@@G@@ .                 OCTAL ROUTINES USE X11,A0,A1,A2,A3,A4,A5,R1    @[@@@@OT
)@@G@@ .    @G@@@@ .                 DECIMAL ROUTINES USE X11,A0,A1,A2,A3,A4,AOU
)@@G@@5,R1,R2,R3  @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .                   EFORM$  - OCTAL FORM OV
)@@G@@- BLANKS SEPARATE SUBFIELDS   @[@@@@ .    @H@@@@ .                   EFOOW
)@@G@@RMC$ - OCTAL FORM - CHARACTERS SEPARATE SUBFIELDS     @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@OX
)@@G@@ .                   EFDECV$ - FREE FORMAT DECIMAL FORM     @[@@@@ .    OY
)@@G@@@E@@@@ .                   EFDECF$ - FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL FORM    @[@@@@OZ
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   EFDECFZ$- LEADING ZEROES - DECIMAL FORMPA
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                   EFDECFL$- LEADING CHARACTERS - DEPB
)@@G@@CIMAL FORM  @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         FLOATINPC
)@@G@@G POINT ROUTINES  @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                    EFLS1$ - SINGLPD
)@@G@@E PRECISION SCIENTIFIC FORMAT @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                    EFPE
)@@G@@LS2$ - DOUBLE PRECISION SCIENTIFIC FORMAT @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .          PF
)@@G@@          EFLG1$ - SINGLE PRECISION GENERALIZED FORMAT@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@PG
)@@G@@ .                    EFLG2$ - DOUBLE PRECISION GENERALIZED FORMAT@[@@@@PH
)@@G@@ .    @F@@@@ .                    EFLF1$ - SINGLE PRECISION FIXED POINT PI
)@@G@@FORMAT@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                    EFLF2$ - DOUBLE PRECISION PJ
)@@G@@FIXED POINT FORMAT@[@@@@/.    @ @@@@ .         OUTPUT ROUTINES    @[@@@@PK
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   EPRT$   - PRINT$ IMAGE, CLEAR IMAGE    PL
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .                   ECSF$   - SHIP IMAGE TO CSF$     PM
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         TIME AND DATE ROUTINES   @[@@@@PN
)@@G@@ .    @D@@@@ .                   ETIME$  - EDIT TIME - HH:MM:SS   @[@@@@PO
)@@G@@ .    @D@@@@ .                   EDAY1$  - EDIT DATE - MM/DD/YY   @[@@@@PP
)@@G@@ .    @D@@@@ .                   EDAY2$  - EDIT DATE - DD MMM YY  @[@@@@PQ
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   EDAY3$  - EDIT DATE - MONTH DD, YEAR   PR
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .              EACH OF THESE ROUTINES IS PS
)@@G@@CALLED BY   @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .                             LMJ X11,<ROPT
)@@G@@UTINE NAME> @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .         AND RETURNS IMMEDIATLY FOLLOWINPU
)@@G@@G THE CALL. @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@/.    @A@@@@ .         ROUTINE DESCRIPTIONPV
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .              IN MOST OF THE EDITING ROUTINES PW
)@@G@@THE IMAGE IS@F@@@@ .         BUILT FROM FROM LEFT TO RIGHT. THE POINTER PX
)@@G@@IS ADVANCED @E@@@@ .         BY EITHER A PARAMETER FURNISHED TO THE ROUTPY
)@@G@@INE OR@F@@@@ .         SIMPLY BY THE SIZE OF THE EDITED FIELD. THE ROUTIPZ
)@@G@@NES   @F@@@@ .         ECOL$ AND ESKIP$ CAN BE USED TO CHANGE THE POINTEQA
)@@G@@R     @C@@@@ .         AND ECOLN$ RETRIEVES THE POINTER.    @[@@@@ .    QB
)@@G@@@H@@@@ .         EDIT$  -  INITIATE EDITING MODE, SAVE X1,X2,X3, BLANK TQC
)@@G@@HE IMAGE.   @H@@@@ .                   SET THE COLUMN POINTER TO ZERO. IQD
)@@G@@F IN ASCII INPUT OR     @H@@@@ .                   OUTPUT MODE (EASC[IN]QE
)@@G@@=1), AND CURRENTLY IN THIRD-WORD MO @H@@@@ .                   QUARTER-WQF
)@@G@@ORD MODE IS INITIATED VIA PSR$. OLD CONTENTS    @E@@@@ .                QG
)@@G@@   OF PSR IN A1. (IF NO PSR$ DONE, A1=0). @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .          QH
)@@G@@         LA,U     A0,PACKET-ADDR    @B@@@@ .                   LMJ      QI
)@@G@@X11,EDIT$   @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   THESE LINES ARE GENERQJ
)@@G@@ATED BY THE PROC: @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                   E$DIT    PACKETQK
)@@G@@-ADDR @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .         EDITX$ -  TERMINATE EDITING MODE, RESQL
)@@G@@TORE X1,X2,X3, SAVE THE @G@@@@ .                   COLUMN POINTER FOR POQM
)@@G@@SSIBLE REENTRY VIA EDITR$. A0 @E@@@@ .                   CONTAINS THE PAQN
)@@G@@CKET ADDRESS AT EXIT.   @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                   LMJ      QO
)@@G@@X11,EDIT$   @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@ .                   THE PROC:@[@@@@ .    QP
)@@G@@@ @@@@ .                   E$DITX   @[@@@@/.    @G@@@@ .         EDITR$ QQ
)@@G@@-  REESTABLISH EDITING MODE TO THE STATUS OF THE LAST @G@@@@ .          QR
)@@G@@         CALL TO EDITX$. RESAVE X1,X2,X3. RESTORE POINTERS. @[@@@@ .    QS
)@@G@@@C@@@@ .                   LA,U     A0,PACKET-ADDR    @B@@@@ .          QT
)@@G@@         LMJ      X11,EDITR$  @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@ .                   THEQU
)@@G@@ PROC:@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                   E$DITR   PACKET-ADDR @[@@@@QV
)@@G@@ .    @G@@@@ .         ECLEAR$ - BLANK OUT THE IMAGE BUFFER , SET COLUMNQW
)@@G@@ POINTER TO @ @@@@ .                   ZERO.    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .    QX
)@@G@@               LMJ      X11,ECLEAR$ @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@ .                QY
)@@G@@   THE PROC:@[@@@@ .    @#@@@@ .         ECLEAR$@[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    QZ
