)@@G@@DAY, MONTH, @C@@@@ .                   AND YEAR RESPECTIVELY.     @[@@@@CN
)@@G@@ .    @F@@@@ .         EDAY2$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FCO
)@@G@@ORMAT @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                             DD MMM YY  @[@@@@CP
)@@G@@ .    @G@@@@ .                   AND ADVANCES THE POINTER 9 POSITIONS. DCQ
)@@G@@D AND YY    @E@@@@ .                   ARE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE DAY ANDCR
)@@G@@ YEAR,@F@@@@ .                   RESPECTIVELY AND MMM IS A THREE-CHARACTCS
)@@G@@ER    @C@@@@ .                   ABBREVIATION FOR THE MONTH.@[@@@@ .    CT
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .         EDAY3$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FORMAT CU
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .                             MONTH DD, YEAR   @[@@@@CV
)@@G@@ .    @F@@@@ .                   WHERE MONTH IS THE NAME OF THE MONTH (UCW
)@@G@@P TO  @G@@@@ .                   9 CHARACTERS) DD IS THE DAY (ONE OR TWOCX
)@@G@@ DIGITS)    @D@@@@ .                   AND YEAR IS THE FOUR DIGIT YEAR. CY
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .         EDAY4$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTOCZ
)@@G@@ THE FORMAT @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                             YYYYMMDD   DA
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .                   AND ADVANCES THE POINTER 8 POSITIDB
)@@G@@ONS. DD, MM,@F@@@@ .                   AND YY ARE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE DC
)@@G@@DAY, MONTH, @C@@@@ .                   AND YEAR RESPECTIVELY.     @[@@@@DD
)@@G@@ .    @F@@@@ .         EDAY5$ -  EDITS THE DATE PORTION OF A0 INTO THE FDE
)@@G@@ORMAT @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                             YYMMDD     @[@@@@DF
)@@G@@ .    @F@@@@ .                   AND ADVANCES THE POINTER 6 POSITIONS. DDG
)@@G@@D, MM,@F@@@@ .                   AND YY ARE THE TWO DIGITS OF THE DAY, MDH
)@@G@@ONTH, @C@@@@ .                   AND YEAR RESPECTIVELY.     @[@@@@ .    DI
)@@G@@@B@@@@ .                   CALLING SEQUENCE:    @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .    DJ
)@@G@@               LA       A0,TDATE$-WORD    @B@@@@ .                   LMJDK
)@@G@@      X11,ERTN$   @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .                   THE PROC IS:   DL
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .                   E$RTN    TDATE$-WORD @[@@@@ .    DM
)@@G@@@G@@@@ .                   THE PROCS E$TD, E$DAT1, E$DAT2, E$DAT3 GENERADN
)@@G@@TE:   @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .                                     ER TDATE$DO
)@@G@@@E@@@@ .                                     LMJ X11,EROUTINE$    @[@@@@DP
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ .                   WHERE EROUTINE$ IS ETIME$, EDAY1$,     DQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@ .                   EDAY2$, OR EDAY3$ RESPECTIVELY.  @[@@@@/.    DR
)@@G@@@A@@@@ .         EDIT A TIME (HH:MM:SS)   @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ETIME$*     DS
)@@G@@                          .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EDEC3                DT
)@@G@@  .   @I@@@@   LA,U    A3,,A0                     . A3 IS TIME (SECS SINDU
)@@G@@CE MIDNITE) OF TDATE    @F@@@@   LA      A0,EASC                    . OUDV
)@@G@@TPUT ASCII MODE TO A0   @G@@@@   DSL     A1,72                      . A1DW
)@@G@@=A2=0, PREPARE TO DIVIDE SECS.@G@@@@   DI,U    A2,60                    DX
)@@G@@  . A2=MINS SINCE MIDNITE, A3=SECS  @F@@@@   DI,U    A1,60              DY
)@@G@@        . A1=HOURS, A2=MINS, A3=SECS@F@@@@   LR      R1,COLON,A0        DZ
)@@G@@        . COLON IS FIELD SEPARATOR  @G@@@@ ENDBEG                       EA
)@@G@@        . END OF ETIME$. XFER TO EDEC3.   @H@@@@        RES     -1      EB
)@@G@@              . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO EDEC3     @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@EC
)@@G@@ . OUTPUT 'XXCYYCZZ' (E.G. 'HH:MM:SS', 'MM/DD/YY') .  @H@@@@ . ENTER WITED
)@@G@@H A1=XX,A2=YY,A3=ZZ, R1='C'. IF C IS ZERO, IT IS NOT INSERTED.    @ @@@@EE
)@@G@@ . RETURN TO USER VIA X11.    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EDEC3                   EF
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              . X11 IS REG
)@@G@@ETURN LINK  @E@@@@   LSSL    A3,36-9                    . A2=YY, A3=(ZZ,EH
)@@G@@0,0,0)@F@@@@   LDSL    A2,36-9                    . A1=XX, A2=(YY,ZZ,0,0EI
)@@G@@)     @F@@@@   LDSL    A1,36-9                    . BEGIN WITH A1=(XX,YYEJ
)@@G@@,ZZ,0)@F@@@@   REPEAT JGD,A0 FOR,U(3)             . FOR 3 GROUPS: XX,YY,EK
)@@G@@ZZ    @F@@@@      LA,U    A2,0                    . CLEAR A2 IN PREPARATEL
)@@G@@ION   @F@@@@      LDSC    A1,9                    . MOVE NEXT GROUP TO AEM
)@@G@@2     @H@@@@      CALL,A1 EDEC                    . INSERT 2-DIGIT GROUPEN
)@@G@@. H1(A1) UNCHNGED.@G@@@@   ESCAPE WHEN A0,IS,ZERO             . ON LAST EO
)@@G@@LOOP, NO SEPARATION CHAR@H@@@@   OTHERWISE                          . NOEP
)@@G@@T LAST LOOP, POSSIBLE INSERTION     @F@@@@      LA      A2,R1           EQ
)@@G@@        . FETCH SEPARATION CHARACTER@E@@@@      IF A2,IS,NONZ THEN      ER
)@@G@@        . STASH IS ALLOWED.   @E@@@@         EX      STORE              ES
)@@G@@  . INSERT THE CHARACTER@G@@@@      ENDIF                           . ENET
)@@G@@D OF NONZERO SEP-CHAR TEST    @E@@@@   ENDREP                           EU
)@@G@@  . NEXT GROUP, PLEASE  @G@@@@ ENDBEG                               . WEEV
)@@G@@'RE OFF TO SEE THE WIZARD.    @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .         INSERT TWO DEEW
)@@G@@CIMAL DIGITS@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EDEC                                  .   EX
)@@G@@@ @@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,A1,NOSAVE   @F@@@@   DSL     A2,36              EY
)@@G@@        . SET UP DIVIDE. A3=A2,A2=0 @G@@@@   DI,U    A2,10              EZ
)@@G@@        . DIVIDE BY 10. REMAINDER TO A3.  @F@@@@   AA,U    A2,'0'       FA
)@@G@@              . A2 = FIRST FIELDATA DIGIT @C@@@@   EX      STORE        FB
)@@G@@              . STORE IT@F@@@@   LA,U    A2,'0',A3                  . A2FC
)@@G@@ = SECOND FIELDATA DIGIT@C@@@@   EX      STORE                      . STFD
)@@G@@ORE IT@E@@@@   LA      A3,EASC                    . RESTORE ASCII INDEX FE
)@@G@@@D@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF EDEC   @[@@@@/.    FF
)@@G@@@B@@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT MM/DD/YY)  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EDAY1$FG
)@@G@@*                               .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EDEC3          FH
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@   DSL     A0,72-18                   . A0=0, A1=(0,MMFI
)@@G@@DDYY) @F@@@@   LA      A0,EASC                    . OUTPUT ASCII MODE TOFJ
)@@G@@ A0   @E@@@@   DSL     A1,6+6                     . A1=MM, A2=(DDYY,0,0)FK
)@@G@@@F@@@@   DSL     A2,36-6                    . A2=DD, A3=(YY,0,0,0,0,0)  FL
)@@G@@@G@@@@   SSL     A3,36-6                    . A3 IS YY (YEAR REL TO 1964FM
)@@G@@)     @F@@@@   AA,U    A3,64                      . A3 IS NOW 2 DIGIT YEFN
)@@G@@AR    @E@@@@   LR      R1,SLASH,A0                . '/' IS THE DELIMITERFO
)@@G@@@G@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF EDAY1$. XFER TO EDEFP
)@@G@@C3.   @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT DD MMM YY) @[@@@@FQ
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@@EDAY2$*                               .   @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROFR
)@@G@@UTINE,NOSAVE              .   @E@@@@   SSL     A0,18                    FS
)@@G@@  . GET RID OF THE TIME @D@@@@   AND,U   A0,07700                   . GEFT
)@@G@@T THE DAY   @C@@@@   DSL     A1,42                      . A2 = DAY@E@@@@FU
)@@G@@   CALL,A1 EDEC                       . EDIT IT TO DECIMAL  @D@@@@   LA FV
)@@G@@     A2,BLANK,A3                . INSERT SPACE  @B@@@@   EX      STORE  FW
)@@G@@                    .   @G@@@@   LR,U    R1,3                       . INFX
)@@G@@SERT THREE LETTERS FOR MONTH  @H@@@@   LX,U    X11,,X11                 FY
)@@G@@  . H1(X11)=0 SIGNIFYING NO SPECIAL ACTION@H@@@@   CALL,A2 EFDMON       FZ
)@@G@@              . INSERT 'MMM '. A1 RTNS WITH DATE.     @G@@@@   AND,U   AGA
)@@G@@1,077                     . A2 = YEAR (RELATIVE TO 1964)    @D@@@@   AA,GB
)@@G@@U    A2,64                      . A2 = YEAR     @E@@@@   CALL,A1 EDEC   GC
)@@G@@                    . EDIT IT TO DECIMAL  @G@@@@ ENDBEG                 GD
)@@G@@              . END OF EDAY1$. RETURN TO USER.  @[@@@@ .    @H@@@@ . OUTGE
)@@G@@PUT MONTH (AND BLANK). ON ENTRY R1 IS # OF CHARACTERS TO INSERT (MAX 9) GF
)@@G@@@H@@@@ . AND A0 IS DATE PART OF TDATE$. IF ASCII OUTPUT, LINK TO SIMILARGG
)@@G@@ ROUTINE    @H@@@@ . IN ELEMENT EDIT$ASC VIA XFER PACKET CELL  'ADRASCX'GH
)@@G@@ . A3 RETURNS WITH MODE @B@@@@ . AND A1 WITH DATE PART OF TDATE$ WORD.  GI
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EFDMON                                .   @B@@@@ BEGINGJ
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE,A2,NOSAVE           .   @E@@@@   SA      A2,SAV1H1          GK
)@@G@@        . SAVE RETURN LINK    @G@@@@   SA      A0,SAV1H2                GL
)@@G@@  . SAVE DATE PART OF TDATE$ WORD   @E@@@@   DSL     A0,36+12           GM
)@@G@@        . A1 IS MONTH INDEX   @G@@@@   LSSL    A1,1                     GN
)@@G@@  . A1 IS MONTH INDEX (TIMES 2)     @H@@@@   LA      A2,ADRASC          GO
)@@G@@        . FETCH BASE LINK TO ASCII ROUTINE.     @F@@@@   IF        A3,ISGP
)@@G@@,NONZ THEN          . OUTPUT MODE IS ASCII.     @G@@@@      CALL,A2 EADAGQ
)@@G@@Y3,A2               . XFER TO ASCII MONTH ROUTINE.    @F@@@@   ELSE     GR
)@@G@@                          . OUTPUT MODE IS FIELDATA.  @F@@@@      DL    GS
)@@G@@  A0,MTAB,A1              . FIELDATA MONTH IN A0,A1   @G@@@@      REPEATGT
)@@G@@ JGD,R1                   . FOR EACH CHARACTER OF THE MONTH.@F@@@@      GU
)@@G@@   LDSC    A0,6                 . MOVE NEXT CHAR TO A1.     @E@@@@      GV
)@@G@@   AND,U   A1,077               . MOVE CHAR TO A2     @F@@@@      ESCAPEGW
)@@G@@ WHEN A2,IS,ZERO          . WHEN NO MORE TO INSERT.   @F@@@@      OTHERWGX
)@@G@@ISE                       . CHARACTER IS STILL GOOD.  @E@@@@         EX GY
)@@G@@     STORE                . STASH CHARACTER     @E@@@@      ENDREP      GZ
)@@G@@                    . LOOP FOR NEXT CHAR. @G@@@@   ENDIF                HA
)@@G@@              . END OF FIELDATA PROCESSING.     @D@@@@   LA      A2,BLANHB
)@@G@@K,A3                . LOAD BLANK.   @E@@@@   EX      STORE              HC
)@@G@@        . STASH A FINAL BLANK.@E@@@@   LA      A2,SAV1H1                HD
)@@G@@  . FETCH RETURN LINK.  @G@@@@   LA      A1,SAV1H2                  . FEHE
)@@G@@TCH DATE PART OF TDATE$ WORD. @D@@@@ ENDBEG                             HF
)@@G@@  . END OF EFDMON.@[@@@@/.    @C@@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT MONTHHG
)@@G@@ DD, YEAR)  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EDAY3$*                               .   HH
)@@G@@@B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              .   @F@@@@   LA      A3,EASCHI
)@@G@@                    . ASCII OUTPUT MODE TO A3   @G@@@@   LXI,XU  X11,-1 HJ
)@@G@@                    . SPECIAL ACTION IF ASCII OUTPUT  @G@@@@   LR,U    RHK
)@@G@@1,9                       . MAX MONTH LENGTH IS 9 CHARS     @G@@@@   SSLHL
)@@G@@     A0,18                      . MOVE DATE$ PART OF TDATE$ TO H2 @H@@@@HM
)@@G@@   CALL,A2 EFDMON                     . INSERT MONTH. RETURN WITH DATE IHN
)@@G@@N A1. @D@@@@   AND,U   A1,07700                   . GET THE DAY   @F@@@@HO
)@@G@@   LA      A0,A3                      . A0 IS ASCII OUTPUT FLAG   @E@@@@HP
)@@G@@   DSL     A2,42                      . SET UP THE DIVIDE   @E@@@@   DI,HQ
)@@G@@U    A2,10                      . GET THE TWO DIGITS  @E@@@@   IF A2,IS,HR
)@@G@@NONZ THEN                 . TWO DIGITS NEEDED   @E@@@@      AA,U    A2,'HS
)@@G@@0'                  . A2 = FIRST DIGIT    @C@@@@      EX      STORE     HT
)@@G@@              . STORE IT@G@@@@   ENDIF                              . ENHU
)@@G@@D OF 1ST-DIGIT PROCESSING     @E@@@@   LA,U    A2,'0',A3                HV
)@@G@@  . A2 = SECOND DIGIT   @G@@@@   LA      A3,EDAY3TAB,A0             . FEHW
)@@G@@TCH ', 19' (ASCII OR FIELDATA)@H@@@@   LA      A0,SHFT,A0               HX
)@@G@@  . FETCH CHAR SHFT-CNT (6=FD,9=ASCII)    @H@@@@   REPEAT JGD,R1 FOR,U(5HY
)@@G@@)             . INSERT 5 CHARS: 'D, 19' (D=DIGIT)     @F@@@@      EX    HZ
)@@G@@  STORE                   . STASH CHARACTER IN A2     @G@@@@      DSC   IA
)@@G@@  A2,,A0                  . SHIFT NEXT CHAR (ASCII/FD) TO A2@F@@@@   ENDIB
)@@G@@REP                             . AND STASH THAT CHARACTER  @G@@@@   ANDIC
)@@G@@,U   A1,077                     . MOVE YEAR (REL TO 1964) TO A2   @F@@@@ID
)@@G@@   AA,U    A2,64                      . LOAD A2 WITH 2-DIGIT YEAR.@F@@@@IE
)@@G@@   CALL,A1 EDEC                       . INSERT 2-DIGITS OF YEAR.  @H@@@@IF
)@@G@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF EDAY3$. RETURN TO USER VIIG
)@@G@@A X11.@[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ . EDAY3$ TABLE OF ', 19' IN ASCII AND FIELDATA.IH
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EDAY3TAB                               .  @F@@@@      II
)@@G@@  FIELDATA                       . JUST FOR THE RECORD.     @B@@@@      IJ
)@@G@@  ', 19  '                      .   @E@@@@        ASCII                 IK
)@@G@@        . AND THE OTHER GUY.  @#@@@@        ', 19'  . @D@@@@        FIELIL
)@@G@@DATA                       . AND BACK     @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ .         MIM
)@@G@@ONTH TABLE  @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@MTAB    EQU     $-2     @^@@@@        'JANIN
)@@G@@UARY@  '    @^@@@@        'FEBRUARY@ '    @^@@@@        'MARCH@    '    IO
)@@G@@@^@@@@        'APRIL@    '    @^@@@@        'MAY@      '    @^@@@@      IP
)@@G@@  'JUNE@     '    @^@@@@        'JULY@     '    @^@@@@        'AUGUST@  IQ
)@@G@@ '    @^@@@@        'SEPTEMBER@'    @^@@@@        'OCTOBER@  '    @^@@@@IR
)@@G@@        'NOVEMBER@ '    @^@@@@        'DECEMBER@ '    @[@@@@/.    @A@@@@IS
)@@G@@ . EDIT A DATE (FORMAT YYYYMMDD)    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EDAY4$*           IT
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EDAY5$                 .   IU
)@@G@@@E@@@@   LA,U    A2,19                      . ASSUME 20TH CENTURY @E@@@@IV
)@@G@@   CALL,A1 EDEC                       . INSERT 2 CHARS: '19'@G@@@@ ENDBEIW
)@@G@@G                               . END OF EDAY4$. XFER TO EDAY5$.  @H@@@@IX
)@@G@@        RES     -1                    . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO EDAYIY
)@@G@@5$    @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@ . EDIT A DATE (FORMAT YYMMDD)@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@IZ
)@@G@@EDAY5$*                               .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EDEC3    JA
)@@G@@              .   @G@@@@   SA      A0,SAV1W                   . STASH MMJB
)@@G@@DDYY IN H1 OF SAV1W.    @C@@@@   LA,S3   A1,SAV1W                   . A1JC
)@@G@@ IS YY@E@@@@   AA,U    A1,64                      . BIAS YEAR BY 1964   JD
)@@G@@@C@@@@   LA,S1   A2,SAV1W                   . A2 IS MM@C@@@@   LA,S2   AJE
)@@G@@3,SAV1W                   . A3 IS DD@G@@@@   LR,U    R1,0               JF
)@@G@@        . THERE IS NO FIELD SEPARATOR.    @G@@@@ ENDBEG                 JG
)@@G@@              . END OF EDAY5$. XFER TO EDEC3.   @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ . TYPJH
)@@G@@ICAL SLIPSHOD UNIVAC CODE BY NAMELESS HACK INCLUDED   @A@@@@ . ONLY FOR JI
)@@G@@THE SAKE OF COMPARISON  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMATJJ
)@@G@@ YYYYMMDD)  @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ . EDAY4$*   SSL       A0,18             GJK
)@@G@@ET RID OF THE TIME@G@@@@ .           AND,U     A0,077            GET THEJL
)@@G@@ YEAR (RELATIVE TO 1964)@D@@@@ .           LA,U      A2,1964,A1        AJM
)@@G@@2 = YEAR    @E@@@@ .           DSL       A2,36             SET UP FOR DIJN
)@@G@@VIDE  @G@@@@ .           DI,U      A2,100            A2 = FIRST TWO DIGIJO
)@@G@@TS OF YEAR  @G@@@@ .           LR        R1,A3             SAVE SECOND DJP
)@@G@@WO DIGITS OF YEAR @E@@@@ .           LMJ       A1,EDEC           EDIT TOJQ
)@@G@@ DECIMAL    @G@@@@ .           LA        A2,R1             A2 = SECOND TJR
)@@G@@WO DIGITS OF YEAR @E@@@@ . EDAY41    LMJ       A1,EDEC           EDIT TOJS
)@@G@@ DECIMAL    @D@@@@ .           AND,U     A0,0770000        GET THE MONTHJT
)@@G@@@D@@@@ .           DSL       A1,48             A2 = MONTH   @E@@@@ .    JU
)@@G@@       LMJ       A1,EDEC           EDIT TO DECIMAL    @D@@@@ .          JV
)@@G@@ AND,U     A0,07700          GET THE DAY  @D@@@@ .           DSL       AJW
)@@G@@1,42             A2 = DAY     @E@@@@ .           LMJ       A1,EDEC      JX
)@@G@@     EDIT TO DECIMAL    @C@@@@ .           J         0,X11             RJY
)@@G@@ETURN @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .         EDIT A DATE (FORMAT YYMMDD)    @[@@@@JZ
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ . EDAY5$*   SSL       A0,18             GET RID OF THE TIMEKA
)@@G@@@G@@@@ .           AND,U     A0,077            GET THE YEAR (RELATIVE TOKB
)@@G@@ 1964)@D@@@@ .           LA,U      A2,64,A1          A2 = YEAR    @D@@@@KC
)@@G@@ .           TG,U      A2,100            3 DIGIT YEAR?@F@@@@ .          KD
)@@G@@ ANA,U     A2,100            YES--REDUCE TO 2 DIGITS  @E@@@@ .          KE
)@@G@@ J         EDAY41            FINISH EDITING     @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    KF
)@@G@@@^@@@@ .   SIMULATE AEDIT$    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@        ON      A$EDIT$ KG
)@@G@@              .   @C@@@@AETIME$*        EQU                   ETIME$  . KH
)@@G@@@C@@@@AEDAY1$*        EQU                   EDAY1$  . @C@@@@AEDAY2$*    KI
)@@G@@    EQU                   EDAY2$  . @C@@@@AEDAY3$*        EQU           KJ
)@@G@@        EDAY3$  . @C@@@@AEDAY4$*        EQU                   EDAY4$  . KK
)@@G@@@C@@@@AEDAY5$*        EQU                   EDAY5$  . @B@@@@        OFF KL
)@@G@@                          .   @]@@@@        END ___  AACTION IF ASCII OUKM
)@@G@@TPUT  @G@&@>   LR,U    R1,9                       . MAX MONTH LENGTH IS KN
)@@G@@9 CHARS     @G@>@<   SSL*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@          AXR$    @^@@@@      KO
)@@G@@    EDIT$PROC     @G@@@@          E$DEF     ***   EDIT$ FIELDATA-ASCII CKP
)@@G@@ONVERSION TABLE ***     @#@@@@$(1)      LIT.    @F@@@@.                 KQ
)@@G@@            EDIT$ DESIGNED AND IMPLEMENTED BY   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     KR
)@@G@@                        DEREK A ZAVE  (MARCH 1968)    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@KS
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.         OPTIMIZED, MODIFIED FOR ASCII USE BY  @[@@@@.     KT
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                   JEFF JEWETT  UOM  JANUARY 1973    @[@@@@.     KU
)@@G@@@F@@@@VERSION   EQU       E$VER$$           . DISPLAY EDIT$ VERSION     KV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@E$DTBL$*                              .   @B@@@@      KW
)@@G@@    E$TBLX                       .  @B@@@@          END                 KX
)@@G@@        .   ___V           .  @B@@@@          END                       KY
)@@G@@  .   ___V  @^@^@[   68 DO 71 J = 1,NFDC  @^@@@^      DO 71 J = 1,NFDC  KZ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@        SAXR$                         . STRUCTURED AXRLA
)@@G@@$, DEFINES U-PROC @B@@@@OP      EQU     '@OLD PROGRAM'        .   @G@@@@LB
)@@G@@        STRUC$                        . DEFINE STRUCTURED PROCEDURES    LC
)@@G@@@#@@@@        EDIT$PROC @D@@@@        E$DEF   ***   EDIT$ UOM EDITING PALD
)@@G@@CKAGE   *** @]@@@@$(1)    LIT.@F@@@@ .                             EDIT$LE
)@@G@@ DESIGNED AND IMPLEMENTED BY  @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .                      LF
)@@G@@       DEREK A ZAVE  (MARCH 1968)   @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .    LG
)@@G@@     OPTIMIZED, MODIFIED FOR ASCII USE BY @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .          LH
)@@G@@         JEFF JEWETT  UOM  JANUARY 1973   @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@VERSION EQU LI
)@@G@@    E$VER$$               . DISPLAY EDIT$ VERSION     @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@LJ
)@@G@@LOAD    EQUF    0,*A0                 . FETCH CHARACTER INTO A2   @[@@@@LK
)@@G@@ .    @A@@@@ .   PAD OUT DESIRED CHARACTERS     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EPAD$*LL
)@@G@@                                .   @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE      LM
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@   XLATE   A1                         . SAVE INSERT-CHLN
)@@G@@ARACTER IN A2     @E@@@@   SA      A0,SAV1H2                  . SAVE COULO
)@@G@@NT IN PACKET@D@@@@   SX      X11,SAV1H1                 . SAVE RETURN   LP
)@@G@@@E@@@@   IF A0,IS,NEG THEN                  . MOVE BACKWARDS, SO  @F@@@@LQ
)@@G@@      CALL    ESKIP$                  . BACK UP TO START OF STRING@G@@@@LR
)@@G@@      DL      A0,CX                   . SAVE POINTERS TO START OF STRINGLS
)@@G@@@F@@@@   ENDIF                              . AND BEGIN FORWARD INSERT  LT
)@@G@@@F@@@@   LM      A3,SAV1H2                  . A3 HAS MAGNITUDE OF COUNT LU
)@@G@@@F@@@@   REPEAT JGD,R1 FOR,A3               . REPEAT FOR EACH CHARACTER LV
)@@G@@@E@@@@      EX      STORE                   . INSERT LIKE THIS    @E@@@@LW
)@@G@@   ENDREP                             . LOOP FOR NEXT CHAR  @E@@@@   IF LX
)@@G@@NEG,IN,SAV1H2 THEN              . STASH WAS BACKWARDS,@H@@@@      SA    LY
)@@G@@  A0,CX                   . RESTORE POINTERS TO START OF STRING   @E@@@@LZ
)@@G@@      LXM     WX,A1                   . RESTORE WORD POINTER@D@@@@   ENDMA
)@@G@@IF                              . AND PROCEED   @D@@@@   LX      X11,SAVMB
)@@G@@1H1                 . GET RETURN    @F@@@@ ENDBEG                       MC
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO USER VIA X11    @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ .   COMPUTE WORD MD
)@@G@@COUNT @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EWRDN$*                               .   @B@@@@ME
)@@G@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              .   @D@@@@   LA,U    A0,1,WX      MF
)@@G@@              . GET WORD INDEX@E@@@@   LA      A3,EASC                  MG
)@@G@@  . OUTPUT ASCII MODE   @E@@@@   LA,U    A1,,CX                     . OVMH
)@@G@@ER A BOUNDARY?    @G@@@@   IF A1,EQ,E$PTRS$,A3 THEN           . WE ARE PMI
)@@G@@OINTING TO S1 OR Q1     @G@@@@      AN,U    A0,1                    . ROMJ
)@@G@@UND DOWN FOR WORD BOUNDARY    @B@@@@   ENDIF                            MK
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@@   AN      A0,ILOC                    . SUBTRACT BASE @F@@@@ML
)@@G@@ ENDBEG                               . RETURN TO USER VIA X11    @[@@@@MM
)@@G@@ .    @C@@@@ .   CLEAR BUFFER - THIS IS GOING AWAY ******** @[@@@@ .    MN
)@@G@@@B@@@@ERASE$*                               .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,ECLMO
)@@G@@R$$                 .   @E@@@@   LR,U    R1,0                       . ASMP
)@@G@@SUME NO BLANKING  @F@@@@   IF A1,IS,POS THEN                  . SOME BLAMQ
)@@G@@NKING DESIRED     @E@@@@      LR      R1,IL                   . ASSUME FMR
)@@G@@ULL BUFFER  @F@@@@      IF A1,IS,ZERO THEN              . ONLY AS MUCH AMS
)@@G@@S IS NEEDED @E@@@@         AN      WX,ILOC              . MINUS BASE ADDMT
)@@G@@RESS  @E@@@@         LR,U    R1,1,WX              . LOAD WORDS TO BLANK MU
)@@G@@@E@@@@      ENDIF                           . END OF ZERO-POS IF  @E@@@@MV
)@@G@@   ENDIF                              . END OF POS-NEG IF   @G@@@@ ENDBEMW
)@@G@@G                               . END OF ERASE$, RTN VIA ECLR     @[@@@@MX
)@@G@@/.    @^@@@@ .   MESSAGE FIELD SKIP @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@EMSKP$*           MY
)@@G@@                    . SKIP COUNT IN A0    @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVEMZ
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@   SR      R2,SAV1W                   . SAVE R2 NA
)@@G@@IN PACKET   @F@@@@   LA      A3,EASCIN                  . A3 HAS INPUT ANB
)@@G@@SCII MODE   @F@@@@   EX      GETMSGC,A3                 . R1 HAS SIGNAL NC
)@@G@@CHARACTER   @E@@@@   SM      A0,R2                      . R2 HAS FIELD CND
)@@G@@OUNT  @E@@@@   LA      A1,WIM                     . A1 HAS WORD INDEX   NE
)@@G@@@G@@@@   LA,U    A2,E$PTRL$,A3              . FETCH FORWRD LOAD TABLE ADNF
)@@G@@DR    @F@@@@   IF A0,IS,NEG THEN                  . WE HAVE REVERSE MOVENG
)@@G@@MENT  @G@@@@      LA,U    A2,EDITML$,A3           . FETCH BAKWRD LOAD TANH
)@@G@@BLE ADDR    @F@@@@      AN,U    A1,1                    . SUBTRACT WORD NI
)@@G@@INDEX BY 1  @F@@@@   ENDIF                              . END OF FRONT/BNJ
)@@G@@ACK TEST    @E@@@@   LA      A0,CIM                     . A0 HAS CHAR INNK
)@@G@@DEX   @G@@@@   AH      A0,,A2                     . BIAS A0 WITH XQTABLENL
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @F@@@@   LXI,H1  A1,,A2                     . SET WIM INCR WNM
)@@G@@ITH +1 OR -1@G@@@@   REPEAT JGD,R2                      . FOR EACH FIELDNN
)@@G@@ TO BE SKIPPED    @F@@@@      REPEAT                          . FOR EACHNO
)@@G@@ CHARACTER SCANNED@G@@@@         EX      LOAD                 . FETCH NENP
)@@G@@XT MSG CHAR INTO A2     @G@@@@EMSKP(1)                              . RTNQ
)@@G@@N HERE FROM XQT TBL BRKOUT    @G@@@@      ESCAPE WHEN A2,EQ,R1          NR
)@@G@@  . WHEN CHAR IS A SIGNAL CHAR.     @F@@@@      ENDREP                  NS
)@@G@@        . END OF CHAR FETCH LOOP    @F@@@@   ENDREP                     NT
)@@G@@        . END OF MSG FIELD LOOP     @[@@@@   .  @ @@@@   .   ALL DONE, SNU
)@@G@@AVE POINTERS@[@@@@   .  @D@@@@   LR      R2,SAV1W                   . RENV
)@@G@@STORE R2    @F@@@@   IF A0,IS,NEG THEN                  . WE WERE GOING NW
)@@G@@BACKWARDS   @H@@@@      AA,U    A1,1                    . SO BUMP WIM BYNX
)@@G@@ ONE (TO COMPENSATE)    @E@@@@   ENDIF                              . ENNY
)@@G@@D OF BAKWRDS TEST @E@@@@   SA      A1,WIM                     . SAVE THENZ
)@@G@@ WORD INDEX @F@@@@   IF A1,IS,POS THEN                  . WE WERE MOVINGOA
)@@G@@ FORWRD,    @E@@@@      ANH     A0,E$PTRL$,A3           . GET CHARACTER OB
)@@G@@INDEX @E@@@@   ENDIF                              . END OF FRWRD TEST   OC
)@@G@@@F@@@@   IF A1,IS,NEG THEN                  . WE WERE MOVING BAKWRD,    OD
)@@G@@@E@@@@      ANH     A0,EDITML$,A3           . GET CHARACTER INDEX @E@@@@OE
)@@G@@   ENDIF                              . END OF BKWRDS TEST  @D@@@@   SA OF
)@@G@@     A0,CIM                     . SAVE IN PACKET@F@@@@ ENDBEG           OG
)@@G@@                    . RETURN TO USER VIA X11    @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .   BOH
)@@G@@ACKWARDS MOVING LOAD TABLES FOR MESSAGE SKIPPING@[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ .   EOI
)@@G@@MSKP FD TABLE     @[@@@@ .    @H@@@@EDITML  JMGI    A1,EDITML3          OJ
)@@G@@  . INCR. A1, BREAK OUT OF XQTABLE LOOP   @B@@@@        LA,S6   A2,,A1  OK
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@        LA,S1   A2,1,A1               .   @B@@@@OL
)@@G@@        LA,S2   A2,1,A1               .   @B@@@@        LA,S3   A2,1,A1 OM
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@        LA,S4   A2,1,A1               .   @B@@@@ON
)@@G@@EDITML3 LA,S5   A2,1,A1               .   @E@@@@        LXM,U   A0,$-2  OO
)@@G@@              . NEXT TIME, GET S3   @E@@@@        J       EMSKP(1)      OP
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO SEQUENCE  @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ .   EMSKP ASCII TABLE  OQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @H@@@@EDITMLA JMGI    A1,EDITMLA3           . INCR. A1, BREAOR
)@@G@@K OUT OF XQTABLE LOOP   @B@@@@        LA,Q4   A2,,A1                .   OS
)@@G@@@B@@@@        LA,Q1   A2,1,A1               .   @B@@@@        LA,Q2   A2OT
)@@G@@,1,A1               .   @B@@@@EDITMLA3                               .  OU
)@@G@@@B@@@@        LA,Q3   A2,1,A1               .   @E@@@@        LXM,U   A0OV
)@@G@@,$-2                . NEXT TIME, GET Q1   @E@@@@        J       EMSKP(1)OW
)@@G@@              . RETURN TO SEQUENCE  @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@GETMSGOX
)@@G@@C LR      R1,EMSGC              . FIELDATA@C@@@@        LR      R1,EMSGCOY
)@@G@@A             . ASCII   @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@EDITML$           OZ
)@@G@@                    . BACKWARDS FETCH INDICES   @E@@@@        +       -1PA
)@@G@@,EDITML             . EMSKP$ FD TABLE     @E@@@@        +       -1,EDITMPB
)@@G@@LA            . EMSKP$ ASCII TABLE  @B@@@@        END                   PC
)@@G@@        .   ___   COUNT *[S@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@        SAXR$                 PD

)@@G@@OGRAM'        .   @G@@@@        STRUC$                        . DEFINE SPF

)@@G@@SPLAY EDIT$ VERSION     @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@ .   ASCII - FIELDPL
)@@G@@ATA EQUIVALENCES, BIT MASKS   @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ACBS    EQUF    010,,U  PM
)@@G@@              . ASCII BACKSPACE     @D@@@@ACAT    EQUF    0100,,U       PN
)@@G@@        . ASCII '@'     @E@@@@ACUL    EQUF    0137,,U               . ASPO
)@@G@@CII UNDERLINE     @D@@@@ACBEL   EQUF    07,,U                 . ASCII BEPP
)@@G@@LL    @F@@@@FCBS    EQUF    '!',,U                . FD BACKSPACE INDICATPQ
)@@G@@OR    @D@@@@FCMLTI  EQUF    '#',,U                . MULTI-SHIFT   @D@@@@PR
)@@G@@FCUL    EQUF    '%',,U                . FD UNDERLINE  @D@@@@FCSNGL  EQUFPS
)@@G@@    '&',,U                . SINGLE SHIFT  @G@@@@FCPFX   EQUF    '''',,U PT
)@@G@@              . PREFIX - DISABLES CTL CHARS     @E@@@@FCCTL   EQUF    '?PU
)@@G@@',,U                . FD CONTROL CHAR     @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ACTLMK  +   PV
)@@G@@    0020000000352         . ASCII CONTROL CHARACTERS  @G@@@@ALPMK   +   PW
)@@G@@    000777777776          . ASCII ALPHABETIC CHARACTERS     @G@@@@FCNTMKPX
)@@G@@  T$MASKR '!' '#' '%' '&' '''' '?'  . FIELDATA CONTROL CHARACTERS @H@@@@PY
)@@G@@FSDMK   T$MASKR 'LET' '@' '[' '\' ']' '^' 077  . SHIFT-DEPENDENT CHARACTPZ
)@@G@@ER    @[[@@@ .    @E@@@@BIAS    EQUF    $,,S1                 . XLATION QA
)@@G@@TABLE BIAS  @F@@@@AJUMP                                 . ASCII TO FD JUQB
)@@G@@MP TABLE    @G@@@@        +       0,ACTL                . ASCII CONTROL QC
)@@G@@CHARACTERS (0-037)@F@@@@        +       0400000,ANUM          . NUMERIC/QD
)@@G@@SPECIAL (040-077) @F@@@@        +       0400000,AUC           . UPPER CAQE
)@@G@@SE (0100-0137)    @F@@@@        +       0,ALC                 . LOWER CAQF
)@@G@@SE (0140-0177)    @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@ .   FETCH NEXT CHARACTER     @[@@@@QG
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@@FETCH*  PROC    *0,2                  .   @B@@@@        LMJ QH
)@@G@@    A2,GET                .   @E@@@@        LA      A3,A5               QI
)@@G@@  . RESTORE LINE MODE   @B@@@@        END                           .   QJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @E@@@@ .   ENTER FROM ECNVT$. FOLDING NOT DESIRED AS INDICATQK
)@@G@@ED BY @H@@@@ .   PACKET FLAG XAF=1. RETAIN SHIFTING INFORMATION IN XLATIQL
)@@G@@NG FROM ASCII TO  @B@@@@ .   ON ENTRY, A2 CONTAINS THE CHARACTER. @[@@@@QM
)@@G@@ .    @A@@@@ . WE MAY USE X11-A5,R1,R2,R3 .     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@E$XALFQN
)@@G@@$*                               .  @B@@@@RTN(1)  EQUF    *AJUMP,A2     QO
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,RTN(1)                 .   @D@@@@   LXMQP
)@@G@@     X11,IMGMD                  . GET LINE MODE @E@@@@   LA,U    A3,,X11QQ
)@@G@@                    . GET TEMP LINE MODE  @F@@@@   IF NONZ,IN,EASC THEN QR
)@@G@@              . XLATE IS FIELDATA TO ASCII@F@@@@      J       FDAT      QS
)@@G@@              . SO XFER TO CORRECT SECTION@F@@@@   ENDIF                QT
)@@G@@              . ELSE, XLATE IS ASCII TO FD@[@@@@   .  @A@@@@   .   ASCIIQU
)@@G@@ TO FIELDATA CONVERSION @[@@@@   .  @F@@@@   AND,U   A2,037             QV
)@@G@@        . LOWER ORDER 5 BITS TO A3  @E@@@@   LSSL    A2,36-7            QW
)@@G@@        . SHIFT OFF PARITY    @G@@@@   SSL     A2,36-2                  QX
)@@G@@  . UPPER 2 BITS (0,1,2,3) TO A2    @G@@@@ ENDBEG                       QY
)@@G@@        . XFER TO APPROPRIATE SECTION     @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .   ASCII CQZ
)@@G@@ONTROL CHARACTER (0-037)@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ACTL                          RA
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,E$ARTN$                . RETURN TO EDITRB
)@@G@@$ASC  @G@@@@   LA      A2,FCCTL                   . ASSUME UNTRANSLATABLRC
)@@G@@E CNTRL CHAR@F@@@@   IF A3,EQ,ACBS THEN                 . CHAR IS ASCII RD
)@@G@@BACKSPACE   @E@@@@      LA      A2,FCBS                 . THEN SIGNIFY WRE
)@@G@@ITH " @F@@@@   ENDIF                              . END OF BACKSPACE TESRF
)@@G@@T     @D@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF ACTL   @[@@@@RG
)@@G@@ .    @E@@@@ .   NUMERIC/SPECIAL (040-077) . TEST FOR FLAG CHARACTERS   RH
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ANUM                                  .   @E@@@@ BEGINRI
)@@G@@ EXECSUB,E$ARTN$                . RETURN TO EDIT$ASC  @G@@@@   LA      ARJ
)@@G@@4,ACTLMK                  . GET MASK DEFINING FLAG CHARS    @F@@@@   SSLRK
)@@G@@     A4,,A3                     . SHIFT BIT INTO POSITION   @H@@@@   AM RL
)@@G@@     A3,ETBL                    . ADD XLATION TABLE ADDRESS TO CHAR     RM
)@@G@@@F@@@@   LA,S1   A2,32,A3                   . GET FD EQUIVALENT FROM TBLRN
)@@G@@@F@@@@   IF A4,IS,ODD THEN                  . WE HAVE A FLAG CHARACTER  RO
)@@G@@@F@@@@      LA      A3,FCPFX                . GET FLAG INDICATOR PREFIX RP
)@@G@@@G@@@@      J       FPUT2                   . INSERT FLAG, THEN CHARACTERQ
)@@G@@R     @F@@@@   ENDIF                              . ELSE RETURN TO E$ARTRR
)@@G@@N$    @D@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF ANUM   @[@@@@RS
)@@G@@ .    @ @@@@ .   UPPER CASE (0100-0137)   @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@AUC         RT
)@@G@@                          .   @E@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,AUCLC                RU
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO EDIT$ASC  @H@@@@   LA      A2,FCUL                    . LORV
)@@G@@AD FIELDATA UNDERLINE CHARACTER     @F@@@@   IF A3,EQ,ACUL-0100 THEN    RW
)@@G@@        . CHAR IS ASCII UNDERLINE   @H@@@@      J       E$ARTN$         RX
)@@G@@        . *ESCAPE*, INSERT FIELDATA INDICATOR,  @F@@@@   ENDIF          RY
)@@G@@                    . ELSE, CONTINUE PROCESSING @F@@@@   LA      A4,ALPMRZ
)@@G@@K                   . GET MASK DEFINING ALPHAS  @D@@@@ ENDBEG           SA
)@@G@@                    . END OF AUC    @[@@@@/.    @ @@@@ .   LOWER CASE (0SB
)@@G@@140-0177)   @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ALC                                   .   SC
)@@G@@@E@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,AUCLC                  . RETURN TO EDIT$ASC  @D@@@@SD
)@@G@@   LN      A4,ALPMK                   . NON-ALPHA MASK@D@@@@ ENDBEG     SE
)@@G@@                          . END OF ALC    @H@@@@        RES     -1      SF
)@@G@@              . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO AUCLC     @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@SG
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@@AUCLC                                 .   @E@@@@ BEGIN EXECSSH
)@@G@@UB,E$ARTN$                . RETURN TO EDIT$ASC  @F@@@@   SSL     A4,,A3 SI
)@@G@@                    . JUSTIFY BIT FOR THIS CHAR @G@@@@   AM      A3,ETBLSJ
)@@G@@                    . ADD TRANSLATION TBL ADDRESS     @F@@@@   LA,S1   ASK
)@@G@@2,64,A3                   . A2 = FD EQUIVALENT CHAR   @I@@@@   XOR     ASL
)@@G@@4,X11                     . IS SHIFT THE SAME AS CURRENT IMAGE MODE     SM
)@@G@@@E@@@@   IF A5,IS,ODD THEN                  . SHIFT HAS CHANGED   @]@@@@SN
)@@G@@      .     @G@@@@      .   CHAR HAS DIFFERENT SHIFT MODE FROM PREVIOUS SO
)@@G@@PART OF IMAGE     @]@@@@      .     @E@@@@      IF ZERO,IN,LAHEAD(CX) THSP
)@@G@@EN      . LOOKAHEAD IS OFF    @F@@@@         SX      CX,LAHEAD(CX)      SQ
)@@G@@  . SAVE CURRENT POSITION OF  @F@@@@         LA      A3,FCSNGL          SR
)@@G@@  . GET SINGLE SHIFT INDICATOR@F@@@@         SX      WX,LAHEAD(WX)      SS
)@@G@@  . SINGLE SHIFT INDICATOR    @H@@@@         J       FPUT2              ST
)@@G@@  . *ESCAPE* INSERT SHIFT, THEN FD CHAR   @F@@@@      ENDIF             SU
)@@G@@              . END OF LOOKAHEAD-OFF CODE @]@@@@      .     @H@@@@      SV
)@@G@@.   SHIFT CHANGE DETECTED WITH LOOKAHEAD ON. CHANGE PREVIOUS SINGLE     SW
)@@G@@@D@@@@      .   SHIFT INDICATOR TO MULTI SHIFT INDICATOR.   @]@@@@      SX
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@      DL      A4,CX                   . SAVE OUR LOCATION   SY
)@@G@@@E@@@@      LA      A3,A2                   . SAVE CURRENT FD CHAR@G@@@@SZ
)@@G@@      LXM     CX,LAHEAD(CX)           . OBTAIN POSITION OF PREVIOUS     TA
)@@G@@@H@@@@      LXM     WX,LAHEAD(WX)           . SNGL SHIFT CHARACTER, REPLTB
)@@G@@ACE WITH    @F@@@@      LA      A2,FCMLTI               . MULTI SHIFT INTC
)@@G@@DICATOR     @D@@@@      SX      WX,BLNKADR              . SAVE LOCATION TD
)@@G@@@G@@@@      JGD     R2,$+1                  . INCREMENT STORED CHAR COUNTE
)@@G@@T     @E@@@@      EX      STORE                   . INSERT MULTI SHIFT  TF
)@@G@@@F@@@@      LXM     X11,MODINV,X11          . INVERT IMAGE SHIFT MODE   TG
)@@G@@@F@@@@      SA      A4,CX                   . RESTORE CHARACTER POINTER TH
)@@G@@@E@@@@      LXM     WX,A5                   . RESTORE WORD POINTER@E@@@@TI
)@@G@@      LA      A2,A3                   . RETRIEVE CHARACTER  @F@@@@   ENDTJ
)@@G@@IF                              . END OF SHIFT-CHANGE CODE  @[@@@@   .  TK
)@@G@@@C@@@@   .   CLEAR LOOKAHEAD, INSERT FD CHARACTER     @[@@@@   .  @E@@@@TL
)@@G@@   SZ      LAHEAD(CX)                 . CLEAR LOOKAHEAD     @G@@@@ ENDBETM
)@@G@@G                               . END OF ASCII TO FIELDATA STUFF  @[@@@@TN
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@@ .   ENTER FROM ASCII TO FIELDATA SECTION.@F@@@@ .   INSERT TO
)@@G@@FD CHAR IN A3, THEN THE ONE IN A2 (VIA E$ARTN$) .     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@TP
)@@G@@FPUT2                                 .   @E@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,E$ARTN$  TQ
)@@G@@              . RETURN TO EDIT$ASC  @D@@@@   DSC     A2,36              TR
)@@G@@        . SWITCH A2,A3  @D@@@@   SX      WX,BLNKADR                 . SATS
)@@G@@VE LOCATION @G@@@@   JGD     R2,$+1                     . INCREMENT STORTT
)@@G@@ED CHAR COUNT     @C@@@@   EX      STORE                      . INSERT  TU
)@@G@@@F@@@@   LA      A2,A3                      . RETRIEVE NEXT CHARACTER   TV
)@@G@@@B@@@@ ENDBEG                               .   @[@@@@/.    @A@@@@ .   FTW
)@@G@@IELDATA TO ASCII TRANSLATION  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@FDAT                    TX
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,E$ARTN$                .   @G@@@@TY
)@@G@@   LA,U    A4,0                       . SKIP TOP OF LOOP ON 1ST PASS    TZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@   REPEAT UNTIL A4,IS,ZERO            . UNTIL CHAR IS NON-SHIFT CNUA
)@@G@@TRL   @H@@@@      IF A4,IS,NONZ THEN              . NOT THE 1ST ITERATIOUB
)@@G@@N, CHAR WAS SHFT  @H@@@@         LA      A3,MODINV,A3         . ASSUME SUC
)@@G@@INGLE SHIFT. INVERT MODE.     @F@@@@         IF A4,IS,ODD THEN          UD
)@@G@@  . LAST CHAR WAS MULTI-SHIFT.@F@@@@            LXM     X11,MODINV,X11  UE
)@@G@@  . INVERT GLOBAL SHIFT MODE  @G@@@@            LA,U    A3,,X11         UF
)@@G@@  . A3 HAS SHIFT MODE FOR NEXT CHAR @F@@@@         ENDIF                UG
)@@G@@        . END OF MULTI-SHIFT CODE   @I@@@@         FETCH                UH
)@@G@@        . IF MULTI/SNGL SHFT, FETCH NXT FD CHAR IN    @G@@@@      ENDIF UI
)@@G@@                          . END OF SHIFT-CHAR PROCESSING    @G@@@@      UJ
)@@G@@DL      A4,FCNTMK               . GET MASK DEFINING CONTROL FLAGS @G@@@@UK
)@@G@@      DSL     A4,,A2                  . JUSTIFY WITH CURRENT CHAR IN A2 UL
)@@G@@@G@@@@   ESCAPE WHEN A5,IS,EVEN             . WHEN A2 IS NOT A CONTROL FUM
)@@G@@LAG   @G@@@@      DL      A4,FSDMK                . FETCH SHIFT DEPENDENUN
)@@G@@CE MASK     @F@@@@      DSL     A4,,A2                  . JUSTIFY WITH CUO
)@@G@@URRENT CHAR @E@@@@   OTHERWISE                          . A2 IS A CONTROUP
)@@G@@L FLAG@H@@@@      LA,U    A4,0                    . ASSUME A2 IS NOT A CUQ
)@@G@@HG-SHIFT FLAG     @F@@@@      IF A2,EQ,FCSNGL THEN            . A2 IS SIUR
)@@G@@NGLE-SHIFT FLAG   @H@@@@         LA,U    A4,2                 . SET INDEUS
)@@G@@X TO SPECIFY SINGLE SHIFT     @F@@@@      ENDIF                         UT
)@@G@@  . END OF SINGLE SHIFT TEST  @F@@@@      IF A2,EQ,FCMLTI THEN          UU
)@@G@@  . A2 IS MULTI-SHIFT FLAG    @G@@@@         LA,U    A4,1               UV
)@@G@@  . SET INDEX TO SPECIFY MULTI SHIFT@F@@@@      ENDIF                   UW
)@@G@@        . END OF MULTI SHIFT TEST   @G@@@@   ATEND                      UX
)@@G@@        . A2 WAS NON-SHIFT CONTROL FLAG   @F@@@@      IF A2,NE,FCPFX THEUY
)@@G@@N             . A2 IS NON-PREFIX CONTROL  @G@@@@         LA      A3,ACBSUZ
)@@G@@              . ASSUME WE WANT ASCII BACKSPACE  @G@@@@         IF A2,EQ,VA
)@@G@@FCCTL THEN          . A2 IS STANDARD CONTROL CHAR     @H@@@@            VB
)@@G@@LA      A3,ACBEL          . SO LOAD ASCII BELL (TO ALERT USER)    @E@@@@VC
)@@G@@         ENDIF                        . END OF CONTROL/BELL @F@@@@      VD
)@@G@@   IF A2,EQ,FCUL THEN           . ASCII UNDERLINE DESIRED   @F@@@@      VE
)@@G@@      LA      A3,ACUL           . SO FETCH ASCII UNDERLINE  @E@@@@      VF
)@@G@@   ENDIF                        . END OF UNDERLINE    @F@@@@         LA VG
)@@G@@     A2,A3                . MOVE ASCII CHAR TO A2     @I@@@@         J  VH
)@@G@@     E$ARTN$              . *ESCAPE* TO CHARACTER INSERTION ROUTINE     VI
)@@G@@@F@@@@      ENDIF                           . END OF NON-PREFIX CODE    VJ
)@@G@@@]@@@@      .     @E@@@@      . CHAR IS PREFIX. FETCH NEXT CHARACTER ANDVK
)@@G@@ INSERT.    @]@@@@      .     @E@@@@      FETCH                         VL
)@@G@@  . NEXT FD CHAR TO A2  @H@@@@      SZ      A5                      . SEVM
)@@G@@T KLUDGE MASK TO SHFT-INDEPENDENT   @E@@@@   ENDREP                     VN
)@@G@@        . END OF FETCH LOOP   @[@@@@/.    @F@@@@   .   FD CHAR IS NOT A VO
)@@G@@CONTROL CHAR. CHECK FOR SHIFT DEPENDENCE  @[@@@@   .  @F@@@@   AM      AVP
)@@G@@2,ETBL                    . ADD XLATION TABLE ADDRESS @E@@@@   LA,QT   AVQ
)@@G@@2,,A2                     . GET ASCII CHARACTER @G@@@@   IF A5,IS,ODD THVR
)@@G@@EN                  . CHARACTER IS SHIFT-DEPENDENT    @]@@@@      .     VS
)@@G@@@I@@@@      .   SHIFT DEPENDENT FD CHAR. A3 HAS SHIFT MODE OF ASCII CHARVT
)@@G@@ IN A2 (0100-0    @]@@@@      .     @E@@@@      LA,U    A3,2,A3         VU
)@@G@@        . ASSUME UPPER SHIFT  @E@@@@      IF A2,GE,0133,,U ;            VV
)@@G@@  . CHAR IS NOT A LETTER@D@[@@          OR A2,EQ,U(ACAT) THEN       . ORVW
)@@G@@ CHAR IS '@'@D@@@[          OR A2,EQ,ACAT    THEN       . OR CHAR IS '@'VX
)@@G@@@E[@@@         AN,U    A3,2                 . SO IT'S LOWER CASE  @F@@@@VY
)@@G@@      ENDIF                           . END OF LOWER CASE TEST    @C@@@@VZ
)@@G@@      AA      A2,BIAS,A3              . ADD BIAS@]@@@@      .     @A@@@@WA
)@@G@@      .   INSERT ASCII CHARACTERS   @]@@@@      .     @G@@@@   ENDIF    WB
)@@G@@                          . IF SHIFT DEP, INSERT AT ONCE    @F@@@@ ENDBEWC
)@@G@@G                               . END OF FD TO ASCII XLATION@[@@@@ .    WD
)@@G@@@G@@@@ .   FETCH NEXT CHARACTER. IF E$APROC FLAG EFDFG = 0, EX 0,*A0 DOEWE
)@@G@@S IT. @G@@@@ .   IF EFDFG NON-ZERO (INDICATING EFD[1,2,3]$) SHIFT NEXT CWF
)@@G@@HAR FROM A0.@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@GET                                   .   WG
)@@G@@@ @@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,A3,NOSAVE   @E@@@@   JGD     R1,$+2             WH
)@@G@@        . DECREMENT LOAD COUNT@F@@@@   J       E$ARTN$                  WI
)@@G@@  . *ESCAPE* WHEN ALL DONE    @F@@@@   DS      A2,A4                    WJ
)@@G@@  . RETURN ADDRESS, LINE MODE @F@@@@   IF ZERO,IN,EFDFG THEN            WK
)@@G@@  . NOT EFD[1/2/3] ROUTINE.   @G@@@@      EX      0,*A0                 WL
)@@G@@  . EXECUTE LOAD TO FETCH CHARACTER @E@@@@   ELSE                       WM
)@@G@@        . PROCESSING EFDX$    @E@@@@      LA      A3,EASCIN             WN
)@@G@@  . INPUT ASCII MODE    @E@@@@      LA      A2,SHFT,A3              . GEWO
)@@G@@T SHIFT COUNT     @E@@@@      DSC     A0,,A2                  . SHIFT OFWP
)@@G@@F CHARACTER @D@@@@      AND     A1,MASK,A3              . AND PROPERLY  WQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@   ENDIF                              . WE NOW HAVE FD CHAR IN A2 WR
)@@G@@@D@@@@   LA      A3,A4                      . GET RETURN    @F@@@@ ENDBEWS
)@@G@@G                               . RETURN TO FD-ASCII SECTION@B@@@@      WT
)@@G@@  END                           .   ___                       .   @B@@@@WU
)@@G@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,E$ARTN$                .   @G@@@@   LA,U    A4,0         WV
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@        SAXR$                         . STRUCTURED AXRWW
)@@G@@$, DEFINES U-PROC @B@@@@OP      EQU     '@OLD PROGRAM'        .   @G@@@@WX
)@@G@@        STRUC$                        . DEFINE STRUCTURED PROCEDURES    WY
)@@G@@@#@@@@        EDIT$PROC @F@@@@        E$DEF   ***   EDIT$ ALPHANUMERIC EWZ
)@@G@@DITING PACKAGE   ***    @]@@@@$(1)    LIT.@F@@@@ .                      XA
)@@G@@       EDIT$ DESIGNED AND IMPLEMENTED BY  @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .          XB
)@@G@@                   DEREK A ZAVE  (MARCH 1968)   @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    XC
)@@G@@@C@@@@ .         OPTIMIZED, MODIFIED FOR ASCII USE BY @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@XD
)@@G@@ .                   JEFF JEWETT  UOM  JANUARY 1973   @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@XE
)@@G@@VERSION EQU     E$VER$$               . DISPLAY EDIT$ VERSION     @[@@@@XF
)@@G@@ .    @F@@@@LOAD    EQUF    0,*A0                 . FETCH CHARACTER INTOXG
)@@G@@ A2   @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ .   STORE THREE WORDS  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EFD3$*XH
)@@G@@                                .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EFD(1)         XI
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@   LXI,XU  X11,-1                     . WE ARE EFD3$  XJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@   SA      A2,SAV1W                   . SAVE THIRD WORD     @D@@@@XK
)@@G@@ ENDBEG                               . RETURN VIA EFD@[@@@@ .    @ @@@@XL
)@@G@@ .         STORE ONE WORD     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EFD1$*                  XM
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EFD(1)                 .   @D@@@@XN
)@@G@@   LX,U    X11,,X11                   . WE ARE EFD1$  @F@@@@ ENDBEG     XO
)@@G@@                          . RETURN TO USER VIA EFD    @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@XP
)@@G@@ .         STORE TWO WORDS    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EFD2$*                  XQ
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EFD(1)                 .   @D@@@@XR
)@@G@@   LXI,U   X11,1                      . WE ARE EFD2$  @G@@@@ ENDBEG     XS
)@@G@@                          . END OF EFD2$. RTN VIA EFD(1)    @H@@@@      XT
)@@G@@  RES     -1                    . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO EFD(1).   XU
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EFD(1)                        XV
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              .   @D@@@@   LA XW
)@@G@@     A3,EASCIN                  . ASCII FLAG    @E@@@@   LA,U    A2,,X11XX
)@@G@@                    . A2 HAS MOD(X11)     @G@@@@   LR      R1,DCNT,A3   XY
)@@G@@              . ASSUME 2 WRDS: 12(FD) OR 8(ASC) @G@@@@   IF A2,EQ,X11 THXZ
)@@G@@EN                  . INCR(X11)=0: EFD1$: ONE WORD    @F@@@@      LR    YA
)@@G@@  R1,SCNT,A3              . LOAD 6(FD) OR 4(ASCII)    @F@@@@   ENDIF    YB
)@@G@@                          . R1 NOW HAS CHARACTER COUNT@E@@@@   LA      AYC
)@@G@@2,ONEZERO                 . SET EFD[1,2,3]$ FLAG@E@@@@   CALL,A2 SETUP(2YD
)@@G@@)                   . SETUPOSSIBLE XLATION@E@@@@   REPEAT               YE
)@@G@@              . EFD3/NON-EFD3 LOOP  @G@@@@      REPEAT JGD,R1           YF
)@@G@@        . FOR # OF CHARACTERS DESIRED     @E@@@@         LA      A2,SHFTYG
)@@G@@,A3           . GET SHIFT COUNT     @G@@@@         DSC     A0,,A2       YH
)@@G@@        . POSITION THE NEXT CHARACTER     @E@@@@         AND     A1,MASKYI
)@@G@@,A3           . ISOLATE IT IN A2    @G@@@@         IF A2,IS,NONZ THEN   YJ
)@@G@@        . IF CHARACTER IS NON-ZERO, AND. .@F@@@@            IF A2,NE,BLAYK
)@@G@@NK,A3 THEN    . IF CHAR IS NON-BLANK,     @C@@@@               EX      SYL
)@@G@@TORE          . STORE IT@F@@@@            ENDIF                     . ENYM
)@@G@@D OF NON-BLANK TEST     @E@@@@         ENDIF                        . ENYN
)@@G@@D OF NON-ZERO TEST@F@@@@      ENDREP                          . LOOP FORYO
)@@G@@ NEXT CHARACTER   @F@@@@   ESCAPE WHEN POS,IN,X11             . IF NOT PYP
)@@G@@HASE1 OF EFD3$    @G@@@@   OTHERWISE                          . BEGIN 3RYQ
)@@G@@D-WORD STASH FOR EFD3$  @E@@@@      LA      A2,EASCIN               . GEYR
)@@G@@T INPUT ASCII MODE@E@@@@      LR      R1,SCNT,A2              . GET ONE YS
)@@G@@WORD COUNT  @E@@@@      LA      A0,SAV1W                . RESTORE 3RD WOYT
)@@G@@RD    @E@@@@      LX,U    X11,,X11                . NO MORE OF THIS     YU
)@@G@@@E@@@@   ENDREP                             . END OF EFD3$ LOOP   @F@@@@YV
)@@G@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF EFD. RTN VIA X11   @[@@@@YW
)@@G@@/.    @C@@@@ .         COPY A STRING WITH OR WITHOUT PACKING@[@@@@ .    YX
)@@G@@@E@@@@EPACK$*                               . STANDARD PACK...    @F@@@@YY
)@@G@@        SZ      A2                    . EXCLUDE ZERO CHARACTERS   @[@@@@YZ
)@@G@@ .    @G@@@@EPACKC$*                               . UOM PACK, EXCLUDE CZA
)@@G@@HAR IN A2   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,ECOPY(1)               .   @F@@@@   SA ZB
)@@G@@     A2,SAV1H1                  . SAVE EXCLUSION CHARACTER  @E@@@@   LXIZC
)@@G@@,XU  X11,-1                     . INDICATE PACKING    @I@@@@ ENDBEG     ZD
)@@G@@                          . END OF EPACK[C]. RTN TO USER VIA ECOPY(1    ZE
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ECOPY$*                               .   @B@@@@ BEGINZF
)@@G@@ EXECSUB,ECOPY(1)               .   @E@@@@   LX,U    X11,,X11           ZG
)@@G@@        . SPECIFY NO PACKING  @H@@@@ ENDBEG                             ZH
)@@G@@  . END OF ECOPY. RTN TO USER VIA ECOPY(1)@H@@@@        RES     -1      ZI
)@@G@@              . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO ECOPY(1)  @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ZJ
)@@G@@ECOPY(1)                               . COMMON ROUTINE FOR EPACK, ECOPYZK
)@@G@@@F@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              . RETURN TO USER VIA X11    ZL
)@@G@@@H@@@@   IF A1,IS,NEG THEN                  . A1 IS WORD COUNT, NOT CHARZM
)@@G@@ACTER COUNT @F@@@@      LM      A1,A1                   . IF NEG, A1 IS ZN
)@@G@@WORD COUNT  @E@@@@      LA      A3,EASCIN               . INPUT ASCII FLZO
)@@G@@AG    @E@@@@      MSI     A1,SCNT,A3              . CONVERT TO CHARS    ZP
)@@G@@@G@@@@   ENDIF                              . END OF WORD/CHAR COUNT TESZQ
)@@G@@T     @E@@@@   LR,U    R1,,A1                     . R1 = CHARACTER COUNTZR
)@@G@@@D@@@@   CALL,A2 SETUP(0)                   . SETUPOINTERS  @F@@@@   REPZS
)@@G@@EAT JGD,R1                      . LOOP FOR EACH CHARACTER   @F@@@@      ZT
)@@G@@EX      LOAD                    . GET THE NEXT CHARACTER    @F@@@@      ZU
)@@G@@IF POS,IN,X11 ;                 . THEN ECOPY, NOT EPACK...  @G@@@@      ZV
)@@G@@   OR      A2,NE,SAV1H1 THEN    . A2 IS NOT EXCLUDE-CHARACTER     @D@@@@ZW
)@@G@@         EX      STORE                . SO STORE IT   @E@@@@      ENDIF ZX
)@@G@@                          . END OF EXCLUDE TEST @D@@@@   ENDREP         ZY
)@@G@@                    . LOOP ON R1    @F@@@@ ENDBEG                       ZZ
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO USER VIA X11    @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ .     ASCII LOAD AA
)@@G@@TABLE @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@XTB(1)                                . COME HERAB
)@@G@@E WHEN EXECUTING LA,Q4  @G@@@@        LA,Q4   A2,,*A1               . LOAC
)@@G@@AD Q4, INCREMENT WORD POINTER @H@@@@        CALL,A0 0,A0                AD
)@@G@@  . A0 POINTS TO EDITLA, RTN TO MAIN SEQ  @D@@@@EDITLA                  AE
)@@G@@              . BEGIN HERE    @F@@@@        LA,Q1   A2,,A1              AF
)@@G@@  . EXECUTE VIA   EX 0,*A0    @B@@@@        LA,Q2   A2,,A1              AG
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@        LA,Q3   A2,,A1                .   @F@@@@        CALLAH
)@@G@@,A0 XTB(1)                . ON LA,Q4, XFER TO LOOP TOP@[@@@@ .    @^@@@@AI
)@@G@@ .   FIELDATA LOAD TABLE@[@@@@ .    @G@@@@XTB(2)                        AJ
)@@G@@        . COME HERE WHEN EXECUTING LA,S6  @G@@@@        LA,S6   A2,,*A1 AK
)@@G@@              . LOAD S6, INCREMENT WORD POINTER @H@@@@        CALL,A0 0,AL
)@@G@@A0                  . A0 POINTS TO EDITL, RTN TO MAIN SEQ   @D@@@@EDITL AM
)@@G@@                                . BEGIN HERE    @F@@@@        LA,S1   A2AN
)@@G@@,,A1                . EXECUTE VIA   EX 0,*A0    @B@@@@        LA,S2   A2AO
)@@G@@,,A1                .   @B@@@@        LA,S3   A2,,A1                .   AP
)@@G@@@B@@@@        LA,S4   A2,,A1                .   @B@@@@        LA,S5   A2AQ
)@@G@@,,A1                .   @F@@@@        CALL,A0 XTB(2)                . ONAR
)@@G@@ LA,S6, XFER TO LOOP TOP@[@@@@ .    @#@@@@ .   LOAD POINTERS@[@@@@ .    AS
)@@G@@@F@@@@E$PTRL$*                               . GENERAL LOAD POINTERS    AT
)@@G@@@C@@@@        +       1,EDITL               . FIELDATA@C@@@@        +   AU
)@@G@@    1,EDITLA              . ASCII   @[@@@@/.    @F@@@@ . GENERALIZED MESAV
)@@G@@SAGE EDITOR. ENTER WITH 1ST CHAR IN A2, INPUT   @F@@@@ . ASCII MODE IN AAW
)@@G@@3, LOAD POINTERS IN A0,A1 , AND RETURN IN X11.  @F@@@@ . NOTE THAT ENTRYAX
)@@G@@ IS 1ST MADE TO EMSG(1), WHICH MUST BE DEFINED  @^@@@@ . PRIOR TO FIRST AY
)@@G@@USE.  @[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              . RETURN TAZ
)@@G@@O USER VIA X11    @F@@@@   REPEAT                             . UNTIL STBA
)@@G@@OP-CHAR DETECTED. @F@@@@      EX      STORE                   . STORE CHBB
)@@G@@ARACTER IN A2     @H@[@@EMSG(1)                               . INITIAL BC
)@@G@@ENTRY HERE. A2 ALREADY LOADED @H@@@[EMSG(1)  EQU   $                    BD
)@@G@@  . INITIAL ENTRY HERE. A2 ALREADY LOADED @G@@@@      EX      LOAD      BE
)@@G@@              . FETCH NEXT CHARACTER IN A2.     @H@@@@      EX      MSGTBF
)@@G@@EST,A3              . TEST A2 AGAINST ASCII/FD STOP CHAR    @G@@@@   ENDBG
)@@G@@REP                             . REPEAT IF STOP CHAR NOT FOUND   @E@@@@BH
)@@G@@   . STOP CHARACTER FOUND, SAVE LOCATION OF MSG POINTERS    @E@@@@   SA BI
)@@G@@     A1,WIM                     . SAVE THE WORD INDEX @E@@@@   ANH     ABJ
)@@G@@0,E$PTRL$,A3              . GET CHARACTER INDEX @D@@@@   SA      A0,CIM BK
)@@G@@                    . SAVE IN PACKET@H@@@@ ENDBEG                       BL
)@@G@@        . END OF EMSG[R]$. RTN TO USER VIA X11  @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@ . RE-BM
)@@G@@ENTER MSG EDITOR. @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EMSGR$*                             BN
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EMSG(2)                .   @F@@@@   LA      ABO
)@@G@@1,WIM                     . RESTORE THE WORD INDEX    @G@@@@   LA      ABP
)@@G@@0,CIM                     . RESTORE THE CHARACTER INDEX     @F@@@@   CALBQ
)@@G@@L,A2 SETUP(1)                   . SETUP POINTERS AND SUCH.  @G@@@@ ENDBEBR
)@@G@@G                               . END OF EMSGR$, XFER TO EMSG(2)  @[@@@@BS
)@@G@@ .    @C@@@@ . ENTER MSG EDITOR. MSG BUFFER ADDRESS IN A0.  @[@@@@ .    BT
)@@G@@@B@@@@EMSG$*                                .   @F@@@@   CALL,A2 SETUP(0BU
)@@G@@)                   . SETUP POINTERS AND SUCH.  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EMSG(2BV
)@@G@@)                               .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,EMSG(1)        BW
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@@   LR,U    R1,1000                    . BIG FOR XALF (BX
)@@G@@IF NEEDED)  @G@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF EMSG(2)BY
)@@G@@. XFER TO EMSG(1) @[@@@@ .    @A@@@@ .   GET THAT MESSAGE CHARACTER     BZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .   TEST CHAR IN A2 AGAINST APPROPRIATE STOP CHAR IN PACKET.     CA
)@@G@@@B@@@@ .   IF A MATCH, ESCAPE FROM MSG LOOP.    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@MSGTESCB
)@@G@@T                               .   @C@@@@        TE      A2,EMSGC      CC
)@@G@@        . FIELDATA@C@@@@        TE      A2,EMSGCA             . ASCII   CD
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@ .   SET UP WORD AND CHARACTER POINTERS. IF XLATION RECE
)@@G@@QUIRED,     @E@@@@ .   GO TO ASCII ELEMENT (USING ADDR IN PACKET - ADRASCF
)@@G@@CX) . @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@SETUP(0)                               . ENTER FCG
)@@G@@ROM EMSG, ECOPY, EPACK  @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,SETUP(1)               .   CH
)@@G@@@F@@@@   LA,U    A1,,A0                     . POSITION THE WORD INDEX   CI
)@@G@@@G@@@@   SSL     A0,18                      . POSITION THE CHARACTER INDCJ
)@@G@@EX    @G@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF SETUP, RTN VICK
)@@G@@A SETUP(1)  @H@@@@        RES     -1                    . BACKUP OVER EXCL
)@@G@@ECSUB JUMP TO SETUP(1). @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@SETUP(1)                      CM
)@@G@@         . ENTER FROM EMSGR   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,SETUP(2)             CN
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@   LA      A3,EASCIN                  . GET ASCII INPUT MODECO
)@@G@@@D@@@@   AH      A0,E$PTRL$,A3              . LOAD POINTERS @F@@@@   LA,CP
)@@G@@U    A2,,A2                     . SET NON-EFD[1,2,3]$ FLAG  @D@@@@   AH CQ
)@@G@@     A1,ONEZERO                 . ADD INCREMENT @H@@@@ ENDBEG           CR
)@@G@@                    . END OF SETUP(1). RTN VIA SETUP(2)     @H@@@@      CS
)@@G@@  RES     -1                    . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO SETUP(2). CT
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @F@@@@SETUP(2)                               . ENTER FROM EMCU
)@@G@@SG, EFDX    @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROUTINE,A2,NOSAVE           .   @H@@@@   IF CV
)@@G@@A3,NE,EASC THEN                 . ASCII FLAGS UNEQUAL: XLATIONEEDED     CW
)@@G@@@G@@@@      SZ      PKT+11,,S3              . CLEAR FOR POSSIBLE INDIRECCX
)@@G@@T     @G@@@@      CALL,A3 *ADRASCX                . XFER TO EDITXALF VIACY
)@@G@@ PKT ADDR   @B@@@@   ENDIF                              .   @E@@@@ ENDBECZ
)@@G@@G                               . END OF SETUP RTNS   @[@@@@ .    @^@@@@DA
)@@G@@ .   SIMULATE AEDIT$    @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@        ON      A$EDIT$       DB
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@AEFD1$* EQU     EFD1$                 .   @B@@@@AEFD2$DC
)@@G@@* EQU     EFD2$                 .   @C@@@@AEPACK$*        EQU           DD
)@@G@@        EPACK$  . @C@@@@AECOPY$*        EQU                   ECOPY$  . DE
)@@G@@@B@@@@AEMSG$* EQU     EMSG$                 .   @C@@@@AEMSGR$*        EQDF
)@@G@@U                   EMSGR$  . @B@@@@        OFF                         DG
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@        END                           .   ___     . LOAD S6,DH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@        SAXR$                         . STRUCTURED AXRDI

)@@G@@SS FIELDATA USERS, THIS ELEMENT     @F@@@@ .   CONTAINS AS MUCH OF THE ADR
)@@G@@SCII PROCESSING CODE AS POSSIBLE.   @[@@@@ .    @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .   JDS
)@@G@@UMP/EXECUTE TABLE INDEXED OFF PACKET FLAG EDITASC     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@DT
)@@G@@E$ASCII$*                              .  @D@@@@        J       ECNVT$  DU
)@@G@@              . SET UP XLATION@E@@@@        J       E$ASC$+1            DV
)@@G@@  . EDAY3$ ASCII CODE   @F@@@@        J       E$ASC$+2              . CHDW
)@@G@@ECK QUARTERWORD MODE    @F@@@@        +       0                     . NODX
)@@G@@ LONGER ACTIVE. TRAP.   @F@@@@ .         J         EXLATE$           . TDY
)@@G@@RANSLATE ONE CHARACTER  @[@@@@ .    @ @@@@ .   TRANSLATE CHARACTER IN A2DZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @B@@@@EXLATE$                               .   @B@@@@ BEGINEA
)@@G@@ EXECSUB,EXLAT(1)               .   @E@@@@   LA,XU   A2,,A2             EB
)@@G@@        . NO INCREMENT, PLEASE@G@@@@   JN      A2,,A3                   EC
)@@G@@  . *ESCAPE* IF NEGATIVE, NO XLATION@I@@@@ ENDBEG                       ED
)@@G@@        . END OF EXLATE$, RETURN TO USER VIA EXLAT    @H@@@@        RES EE
)@@G@@    -1                    . BACKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO EXLAT(1)  @[@@@@EF
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@@EXLAT(1)                               .  @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROEG
)@@G@@UTINE,A3,NOSAVE           .   @D@@@@   SA      A3,SAV12W                EH
)@@G@@  . SAVE RETURN   @F@@@@   LA      A3,EASCIN                  . FETCH INEI
)@@G@@PUT ASCII FLAG    @E@@@@   IF A3,NE,EASC THEN                 . TRANSLATEJ
)@@G@@ION DESIRED @E@@@@      IF POS,IN,ETBL ;                . IF 64-WORD TABEK
)@@G@@LE... @E@@@@         AND     A2,GE,0100,,U THEN   . AND CHAR TOO BIG,   EL
)@@G@@@F@@@@         LA,U    A3,2                 . SET INDEX FOR ASCII TO FD EM
)@@G@@@G@@@@         AN,U    A2,0100              . BRING INTO 64-WORD TABLE REN
)@@G@@ANGE  @E@@@@      ENDIF                           . END OF TABLE FARBLE EO
)@@G@@@E@@@@      AM      A2,ETBL                 . ADD TABLE ADDRESS   @G@@@@EP
)@@G@@      EX      ECTBL,A3                . A3=(0,1,2), A2 HAS NEW CHARACTEREQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@   ENDIF                              . END OF XLATION TEST @D@@@@ER
)@@G@@   LA      A3,SAV12W                  . FETCH RETURN  @C@@@@ ENDBEG     ES
)@@G@@                          . RETURN  @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ .   EXECUTABLE TOET
)@@G@@ FETCH CONVERTED CHAR   @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ECTBL                         EU
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@        LA,QT   A2,,A2                . FIELDATA TO ASEV
)@@G@@CII   @F@@@@        LA,S1   A2,,A2                . ASCII TO FIELDATA (0EW
)@@G@@-077) @G@@@@        LA,S2   A2,,A2                . ASCII TO FIELDATA (0EX
)@@G@@100-0177)   @[@@@@/.    @D@@@@ .   ASCII TO FIELDATA (AND VICE VERSA) SEEY
)@@G@@CTION FOR:  @E@@@@ .   EFD[1-2-3]$, EPACK$, ECOPY$, AND THE EMSG$ THINGIEZ
)@@G@@ES.   @E@@@@ .   SAVE POINTERS AND TABLE ADDRESS FOR MODE CONVERSION    FA
)@@G@@@F@@@@ .   TEST FOR FOLDED OR NON-FOLDED (EXTENDED ALPHA) TRANSLATION.  FB
)@@G@@@[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .   CX NORMALLY POINTS TO A STORE TABLE (ASCII OR FD)FC
)@@G@@. FOR TRANSLATION,@G@@@@ .   CX IS MODIFIED SO THAT AN ATTEMPTED STORE (FD
)@@G@@EX 0,*CX) BY ONE OF THE @G@@@@ .   ALPHANUMERIC ROUTINES WILL RESULT IN FE
)@@G@@AN LMJ TO THE FOLLOWING CODE. @[@@@@ .    @G@@@@ .   IF EXTENDED ALPHA, FF
)@@G@@GET ADDRESS OF E$XALF$ FROM PACKET FLAG EXALF,  @F@@@@ .   AND JUMP TO TFG
)@@G@@HE EXTENDED ALPHA CODE IN ELEMENT EDIT$XALF.    @[@@@@ .    @D@@@@ .   WFH
)@@G@@E ARE ALLOWED TO USE X11-A5,R1, R2, AND R3.     @[@@@@ .    @B@@@@ECNVT$FI
)@@G@@                                .   @B@@@@ BEGIN EXECSUB,RETURN         FJ
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@   LR,U    R2,0                       . CHAR STORE COUFK
)@@G@@NT    @E@@@@   SA      A3,CXRET                   . SAVE OUR RETURN     FL
)@@G@@@E@@@@   SX      X11,FINRET                 . SAVE ORIGINAL RETURN@F@@@@FM
)@@G@@   SZ      PKT+7                      . CLEAR BLNKADR, LAHEAD(CX) @E@@@@FN
)@@G@@   LA      A3,A2                      . GET EFD[1,2,3]$ FLAG@F@@@@   SSLFO
)@@G@@     A3,18                      . JUSTIFY EFD[1,2,3] FLAG   @F@@@@   LXMFP
)@@G@@,U   X11,0                      . ASSUME LOWER CASE (IF XAF)@D@@@@   SA FQ
)@@G@@     A3,EFDFG                   . SAVE EFD FLAG @[@@@@   .  @F@@@@   .  FR
)@@G@@ SAVE CX (CHAR POINTER), LOAD CX WITH POINTER TO FOLLOWING  @A@@@@   .  FS
)@@G@@ CODE     -     ( LMJ  CX,,CX)@[@@@@   .  @G@@@@   REPEAT               FT
)@@G@@              . FOR AS MANY CHARS AS NEEDED     @D@@@@      SX      CX,CFU
)@@G@@HARPT               . SAVE POINTER  @E@@@@      LA      A3,EASCIN       FV
)@@G@@        . INPUT ASCII FLAG    @F@@@@      SX      X11,IMGMD             FW
)@@G@@  . SAVE LINE MODE (IF XAF)   @E@@@@      LXM     CX,CXRET              FX
)@@G@@  . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @G@@@@      LXM,U   X11,RETURN              . REFY
)@@G@@TURN TO CONVERSION ROUTINE    @]@@@@      .     @G@@@@      .   EX 0,*CXFZ
)@@G@@ - GRABS CHARACTER, TRANSLATES, STORES, AND RETURNS.  @I@@@@      .   IFGA
)@@G@@ PACKET FLAG XAF = 0 , LOWER CASE ASCII MAPS TO UPPER CASE FIELDATA.    GB
)@@G@@@G@@@@      .   IF XAF IS NON-ZERO, JUMP TO EXTENDED ALPHA ROUTINE VIA EGC
)@@G@@NTRY  @B@@@@      .   ADDRESS IN PACKET FLAG  E$XALF$ @]@@@@      .     GD
)@@G@@@H@@@@      LMJ     CX,,CX                  . RETURN WITH ADDR OF INSTR GE
)@@G@@TO EXECUTE  @G@@@@      LMJ     CX,$+1                  . EXECUTE THIS, GF
)@@G@@START CONVERSION  @E@@@@      SX      CX,CXRET                . SAVE RETGG
)@@G@@URN ADDRESS @F@@@@      LXM     CX,CHARPT               . OBTAIN CHARACTGH
)@@G@@ER POINTER  @F@@@@      LA,U    A3,EXLAT(1)             . ASSUME NORMAL GI
)@@G@@TRANSLATION @G@@@@      IF NONZ,IN,XAF THEN             . CASE-PRESERVINGJ
)@@G@@G ALFA XLATION    @H@@@@         LA      A3,ADRXALF           . SO FETCHGK
)@@G@@ XAF-ADDRESS FROM PACKET CELL @H@@@@      ENDIF                         GL
)@@G@@  . ELSE, NORMAL XLATION WILL SUFFICE,    @F@@@@      CALL,A3 0,A3      GM
)@@G@@              . SO PROCESS IN THIS FASHION@B@@@@      . RETURN HERE FROMGN
)@@G@@ XALPHA, ALSO.    @B@[@@EARTN(1)                               .  @B@@@[GO
)@@G@@EARTN(1) EQU   $                       .  @F@@@@      LA      A3,EASC   GP
)@@G@@              . GET ASCII OUTPUT MODE     @G@@@@      JGD     R2,$+1    GQ
)@@G@@              . INCREMENT STORED CHAR COUNT     @E@@@@      IF A2,NE,BLAGR
)@@G@@NK,A3 THEN          . CHAR WAS NOT A BLANK@G@@@@         SX      WX,BLNKGS
)@@G@@ADR           . SAVE LOC OF LAST NON-BLANK CHAR @B@@@@      ENDIF       GT
)@@G@@                    .   @E@@@@      EX      STORE                   . INGU
)@@G@@SERT NEW CHARACTER@F@@@@   ENDREP                             . LOOP FORGV
)@@G@@ NEXT CHARACTER   @G@@@@ ENDBEG                               . END OF CGW
)@@G@@HARACTER PROCESSING     @H@@@@        RES     -1                    . BAGX
)@@G@@CKUP OVER EXECSUB JUMP TO RETURN    @F@@@@        DO      PASS(2) ,E$ARTGY
)@@G@@N$* EQU EARTN(1)  . EXTERNALIZE     @D@@@@PASS(2) EQU     1             GZ
)@@G@@        . NOW IN PASS 2 @[@@@@ .    @E@@@@ .   TERMINATE, UNDO DAMAGE TOHA
)@@G@@ POINTERS. A0 RETURNS WITH    @E@@@@ .   ADDR OF WHERE LAST NON-BLANK CHHB
)@@G@@ARACTER WAS STORED,     @E@@@@ .   A1 WITH # OF CHARACTERS STORED. IF NOHC
)@@G@@ CHARS STORED     @B@@@@ .   (NULL LINE) THEN A0 RETURNS WITH 0.  @[@@@@HD
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@@RETURN                                .   @B@@@@ BEGIN SUBROHE
)@@G@@UTINE,NOSAVE              .   @E@@@@   LXM     X11,FINRET               HF
)@@G@@  . GET ORIGINAL RETURN @F@@@@   LN      A1,R2                      . REHG
)@@G@@TRIEVE STORED CHAR COUNT@E@@@@   LXM     CX,CHARPT                  . REHH
)@@G@@STORE CHAR POINTER@F@@@@   LA      A0,BLNKADR                 . GET NON-HI
)@@G@@BLANK ADDRESS     @C@@@@ ENDBEG                               . GO BACK HJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@        END                           .   ___E  @E@@@@      ENDIF HK
)@@G@@                        *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROC DOES AHL
)@@G@@ PCT$, AND RETURNS A0=CPU TIME, A1=MEM TIME.    @F@@@@. PLACE ACCESS WORHM
)@@G@@D FOR PCT$ IN A0, WHICH MUST BE AT LEAST THE    @D@@@@. SIZE DESCRIBED BHN
)@@G@@ELOW.  TRASHES A0,A1,A3, AND A4 .   @F@@@@. NOTE- CALLING ROUTINES RELY HO
)@@G@@ON THE FACT THAT A2 IS PRESERVED    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE FIRST PARAMEHP
)@@G@@TER FIELD INDICATES UNDER WHICH LEVEL OF EXEC 8 @F@@@@. THIS PROC SHOULDHQ
)@@G@@ WORK.  MORE THAN ONE LEVEL MAY BE SPECIFIED    @E@@@@. (I.E. M$TIME 27,HR
)@@G@@31), IN WHICH CASE THE GENERATED CODE WILL@E@@@@. DETERMINE AT EXECUTIONHS
)@@G@@ TIME WHICH LEVEL OF THE EXEC IT IS @F@@@@. ACTUALLY RUNNING UNDER.  IF HT
)@@G@@NO LEVEL IS SPECIFIED, THE CURRENT  @F@@@@. EXEC LEVEL IS ASSUMED. (31 AHU
)@@G@@T THE TIME, BUT THAT MAY CHANGE).   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ENTRY 'M$TIMHV
)@@G@@X' GENERATES ABBREVIATED CODE FOR PEOPLE WHO    @F@@@@. HAVE ALREADY GOTHW
)@@G@@TEN THE PCT.  REGISTER CONTENTS MUST BE: A0=PCT @F@@@@. ADDR, A1=RESULT HX
)@@G@@OF TIME$ DONE JUST BEFORE ER PCT$ (27 AND 27/31 @F@@@@. ONLY), A4=POSITIHY
)@@G@@VE FOR LEVEL 27, NEGATIVE FOR LEVEL 31 (27/31   @#@@@@. VERSION ONLY).  HZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ARRAY MTIMESIZE STATES HOW LARGE THE PCT BUFFER IA
)@@G@@HAS TO BE   @E@@@@. FOR THE VARIOUS LEVELS, MTIMESIZE(0) CONTAINS THE PCIB
)@@G@@T SIZE@B@@@@. NECESSARY FOR THE CURRENT EXEC LEVEL.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@IC
)@@G@@. THE FOLLOWING LEVELS AND COMBINATIONS ARE CURRENTLY IMPLEMENTED:@^@@@@ID
)@@G@@. 27, 31, 27/31, 32, 33 @A@@@@. LEVEL 32 IS SUPPORTED AS LEVEL31  @[@@@@IE
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@          DEF     @^@@@@MTIMESIZE(0)  EQU   027 @^@@@@MTIMESIF
)@@G@@IZE(27) EQU   0110@^@@@@MTIMESIZE(31) EQU   027 @B@@@@MTIMESIZE(32) EQU IG
)@@G@@  MTIMESIZE(31)     .   @B@@@@MTIMESIZE(33) EQU   MTIMESIZE(31)     .   IH
)@@G@@@^@[@@P         PROC      *1  @^@@@[P         PROC      1   @^@@@@M$TIMEII
)@@G@@*   NAME      1   @D@@@@M$TIMX*   NAME      0          . ABBREVIATED ENTIJ
)@@G@@RY    @F@@@@PCT       EQUF      0,A0       . PCT ACCESS WD IS USED AS INIK
)@@G@@DEX   @D@@@@  DO  P(1)=0  ,P(1,1)  EQU  33  . ASSUMED EXEC LEVEL  @A@@@@IL
)@@G@@I DO P(1) ,GENFLG(P(1,I)) EQU 1     @ @@@@   DO  P(0,0)=0  ,  GO M$TIMY IM
)@@G@@@D@@@@      ON        GENFLG(27)        . LEVEL 27 CODE     @E@@@@      IN
)@@G@@LA        A1,A0             . PRESERVE PCT ACCESS WORD@E@@@@         ON IO
)@@G@@       GENFLG(31)        . LEVEL 27/31 ONLY     @G@@@@         SZ       IP
)@@G@@ 0,A0              . CLEAR 1ST WORD OF PCT BUFFER     @G@@@@         ER IQ
)@@G@@       MSCON$            . DO MSCON$ WITH INVALID FUNCT (0) @G@@@@      IR
)@@G@@   LSSL      A0,1              . ALIGN STATUS TO SEE IF S1=020    @E@@@@IS
)@@G@@         SA        A0,A4             . AND STASH THE P1 BIT @ @@@@      IT
)@@G@@   OFF       GENFLG(31) @F@@@@      ER        TIME$             . FIND OIU
)@@G@@UT WHAT TIME IT IS NOW  @F@@@@      LDSC      A0,36             . RECOVEIV
)@@G@@R PCT ACW, HIDE TIME$   @ @@@@      OFF       GENFLG(27)    @E@@@@      IW

)@@G@@NFLG(33)      . END OF NON-33 CODE  @^@@@@M$TIMY    NAME      .   @D@@@@IZ

)@@G@@@E@@@@      AND,U     A3,07777          . ACTUAL SIZE IS IN T3    @G@@@@JG

)@@G@@EVEL 33     @F@@@@   LA        A1,PCT+014        . PLUS RUN ACCUMULATIONJO
)@@G@@ SO FAR     @D@@@@      ON        GENFLG(27)        . LEVEL 27 CODE     JP

)@@G@@T RESULT RIGHT 6 BITS (DIV BY 64)   @E@@@@   LA        A0,PCT+026       JT
)@@G@@ . FOR GOOD LUCK, GET CPU TIME@E@@@@          OFF       1-GENFLG(33)    JU
)@@G@@  . END OF NON-33 CODE  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. FOR LEVEL 33, WE TEST FOR OPJV
)@@G@@ERATION ON 1110-TYPE MACHINE  @E@@@@. VIA THE HIGHLY USEFUL TSS INSTRUCTJW
)@@G@@ION AND COMPUTE THE CPU @E@@@@. TIME FROM THE SRC'S. ELSE WE FETCH CPU TJX
)@@G@@IME FROM PCT+026. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          ON        GENFLG(33)      JY
)@@G@@  . BEGIN LEVEL 33 CODE @F@@@@          SZ        A3                . SEJZ
)@@G@@T MACHINE FLAG (1=>1108)@H@@@@          SZ        PCT               . CLKA

)@@G@@        . IF 1110, SKIP NEXT INSTRUCTION  @F@@@@          J         A(11KC
)@@G@@08)           . IF HERE, WE ARE ON 1108   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. BEGIN 1140KD
)@@G@@/1110 CODE. @G@@@@. CPU TIME IS COMPUTED DIRECTLY FROM THE SRC'S BY THE KE
)@@G@@FOLLOWING FORMULA:@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         CPU (200 USECS) = (TOTAL SKF
)@@G@@RC'S)*(AVE. INSTRUCTION/1.6 SRC)    @G@@@@.                            *KG
)@@G@@(700NS/AVE.INSTRUCTION)*(SUP/200USECS)    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.           KH
)@@G@@              = (TOTAL SRC'S)*(7/3200)    @[@@@].     @G@@@]. UOM MOD EFKI
)@@G@@FECTIVE 7/1/78. TO EQUALIZE CPU TIME (AND HENCE CB-SUBS)    @E@@@]. ON OKJ
)@@G@@UR 1108 AND 1140 (WELL, AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE), WE HAVE @D@@@]. DOUBLED THKK
)@@G@@E CPU CALCULATION. E.G. CPU=SRC(14/3200)  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          LAKL
)@@G@@        A3,A0             . WE ARE 1110. SAVE USERS PCT ACW @F@@@@      KM

)@@G@@  . BUT IF A3 IS NONZ, THEN   @F@@@@          LA        A0,A3           LC
)@@G@@  . IT CONTAINS 1140 CPU TIME @E@@@@          OFF       GENFLG(33)      LD

)@@G@@ HAGERTY, UOM     @#@@@@ CHIEF OF SYSTEMS.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@            LS
)@@G@@                          JEFF JEWETT  SEPTEMBER 1973 @#@@@@4INTRODUCTIOLT
)@@G@@N     @]@@@@3PURPOSE    @F@@@@      THE EDIT$ PACKAGE IS A COLLECTION OFLU
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINES DESIGNED TO@E@@@@ FACILITATE THE COMPOSITION OF STRINGS OF LV
)@@G@@FIELDATA OR ASCII @F@@@@ CHARACTERS; STRINGS WHICH MAY THEN BE USED BY ELW
)@@G@@R PRINT$, ER CSF$,@#@@@@ ER PUNCH$, ETC.  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      THE EDLX
)@@G@@IT$ ROUTINES ARE ACTIVITY REENTRANT; EDIT$ STORES ITS @F@@@@ FLAGS IN A LY
)@@G@@PACKET SUPPLIED BY THE USER. IN FIELDATA MODE, THESE  @F@@@@ ROUTINES ARLZ
)@@G@@E THIRDWORD-QUARTERWORD INSENSITIVE, BUT THEY MUST BE @D@@@@ IN QUARTERWMA
)@@G@@ORD MODE TO PROCESS ASCII CHARACTERS.     @ @@@@3USE OF THE EDIT$ ROUTINMB
)@@G@@ES    @F@@@@      ALL COMMUNICATION BETWEEN THE USER AND THE EDIT$ ROUTIMC
)@@G@@NES IS@F@@@@ CONDUCTED THROUGH PARAMETERS EITHER SET IN THE PACKET OR LOMD
)@@G@@ADED  @E@@@@ INTO A-REGISTERS PRIOR TO CALLING THE INDIVIDUAL ROUTINES. ME
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      THE USER FIRST CALLS THE ROUTINE     EDIT$     WMF
)@@G@@ITH THE     @F@@@@ ADDRESS OF THE PACKET IN A0.      EDIT$     INITIATESMG
)@@G@@ EDITING    @F@@@@ MODE: THE OUTPUT IMAGE IS BLANKED, THE CONTENTS OF REMH
)@@G@@GISTERS X1, @F@@@@ X2, AND X3 (WHICH ARE USED INTERNALLY AS POINTERS BY MI
)@@G@@EDIT$) ARE  @F@@@@ SAVED, AND THE COLUMN POINTER IS SET TO COLUMN ZERO (MJ
)@@G@@THE FIRST   @]@@@@ COLUMN).   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@     THE USER IS NOW IN MK
)@@G@@EDITING MODE AND, BY CALLING THE    @E@@@@ APPROPRIATE EDIT$ ROUTINES, CML
)@@G@@AN COMPOSE HIS DESIRED STRING:@F@@@@ INSERTING STRINGS OF CHARACTERS, OCMM
)@@G@@TAL AND DECIMAL INTEGERS,     @F@@@@ FLOATING POINT NUMBERS, ETC. INTO HMN
)@@G@@IS OUTPUT IMAGE. THE USER MUST@D@@@@ NOT, HOWEVER, ALTER THE CONTENTS OFMO
)@@G@@ X1, X2, OR X3.   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@     TO LEAVE EDITING MODE, THE ROUTMP
)@@G@@INE      EDITX$      IS CALLED,     @F@@@@ WHICH SAVES THE COLUMN POINTEMQ
)@@G@@R (FOR POSSIBLE REENTRY INTO EDIT   @E@@@@ MODE), AND RESTORES THE CONTEMR
)@@G@@NTS OF X1, X2, X3.  TO REENTER@F@@@@ EDITING MODE TO THE STATUS OF THE LMS
)@@G@@AST CALL TO     EDITX$     ,  @F@@@@ THE USER LOADS THE PACKET ADDRESS IMT
)@@G@@N A0 AND CALLS THE ROUTINE    @F@@@@ EDITR$   . HE CAN NOW BEGIN EDITINGMU
)@@G@@ WHERE HE LEFT OFF WHEN EDITX$@#@@@@ WAS LAST CALLED. @^@@@@4THE EDIT$ RMV
)@@G@@OUTINES     @G@@@@     THE EDIT$ ROUTINES ESTABLISH OR TERMINATE EDITINGMW
)@@G@@ MODE, INSERT     @F@@@@ CHARACTER STRINGS INTO THE OUTPUT IMAGE, OR ADJMX
)@@G@@UST THE COLUMN    @G@@@@ POINTER. CHARACTERS ARE INSERTED INTO THE IMAGEMY
)@@G@@ FROM LEFT TO RIGHT     @F@@@@ BEGINNING WITH THE COLUMN SPECIFIED BY THMZ
)@@G@@E COLUMN POINTER. THE   @F@@@@ COLUMN POINTER ALWAYS SPECIFIES THE COLUMNA
)@@G@@N SUCCEEDING THE LAST   @F@@@@ CHARACTER INSERTED.  THE EDIT$ ROUTINES, NB
)@@G@@UNLESS SPECIFIED, USE   @F@@@@ (BUT DO NOT SAVE OR RESTORE) X11, A0-A3, NC
)@@G@@AND R1.  THE APPENDIX   @A@@@@ CONTAINS A LIST OF THESE ROUTINES. @[@@@@ND
)@@G@@SPACE @G@@@@      THE MODE OF THE GENERATED OUTPUT IMAGE IS SPECIFIED BYNE

)@@G@@@B@@@@                    LMJ      X11,ECOPY$   @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ THE PSB
)@@G@@ROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@                    E$COPY   COUNT,ADDRESS@[@@@@SC
)@@G@@SPACE @ @@@@1ALTERNATE CALLING SEQUENCE   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@      ECOPY$SD
)@@G@@, EPACK$, AND EPACKC$ NORMALLY EXPECT A1 TO CONTAIN THE     @F@@@@ CHARASE
)@@G@@CTER COUNT. IF A1 IS NEGATIVE, HOWEVER, ITS MAGNITUDE IS    @G@@@@ TREATSF
)@@G@@ED AS A WORD COUNT. FOR EXAMPLE, TO COPY 4 WORDS (24 FIELDATA     @D@@@@SG

)@@G@@TRING SELECTIVELY @E@@@@      THIS ROUTINE IS SIMILAR TO ECOPY$, BUT ZERSJ
)@@G@@O-CHARACTERS@F@@@@ (FIELDATA '@' OR ASCII NULL CHARACTERS), ALTHOUGH INCSK
)@@G@@LUDED IN THE@B@@@@ INPUT CHARACTER COUNT, ARE NOT COPIED.   @[@@@@SPACE SL

)@@G@@11,EPACK$   @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@            SO
)@@G@@        E$PACK   COUNT,ADDRESS@A@@@@2EPACKC$ - COPY A STRING SELECTIVELYSP
)@@G@@@F@@@@      SIMILAR TO EPACK$, WITH THE RIGHT-JUSTIFIED CHARACTER IN A2 SQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@ EXCLUDED INSTEAD OF ZERO-CHARACTERS.     @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@      SR

)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@                    E$PACKC  COUNT,ADDRESS    CHAR    SV
)@@G@@@B@@@@2EMSG$ - INITIALIZE THE MESSAGE EDITOR    @E@@@@      A0 CONTAINS SW
)@@G@@THE LOCATION OF THE EMSG$ INPUT STRING.   @F@@@@ CHARACTERS FROM THIS STSX
)@@G@@RING ARE COPIED TO THE OUTPUT IMAGE UNTIL @G@@@@ THE SENTINEL CHARACTER SY
)@@G@@IN PACKET FLAG      EMSGC     (FOR FIELDATA     @G@@@@ STRINGS) OR     ESZ
)@@G@@MSGCA     (FOR ASCII STRINGS) IS ENCOUNTERED. THE     @F@@@@ POINTER TO TA
)@@G@@THE NEXT CHARACTER IN THE EMSG$ STRING TO BE COPIED IS@F@@@@ SAVED IN THTB
)@@G@@E PACKET FOR POSSIBLE FUTURE USE BY      EMSGR$     OR@F@@@@ EMSKP$ . ANTC
)@@G@@ EXAMPLE OF MESSAGE EDITING USING    EMSG$    IS GIVEN@#@@@@ IN SECTION TD
)@@G@@6.4  .@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@                    LA,U     A0,ADDR-OF-MSGSTRINTE
)@@G@@G     @B@@@@                    LMJ      X11,EMSG$    @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@TF
)@@G@@ THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@                    E$MSG    ADDR-OF-MSGSTTG
)@@G@@RING  @[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@2EMSGR$ - REENTER THE MESSAGE EDITOR@F@@@@     TTH
)@@G@@HE EMSG$ STRING POINTER IS RETRIEVED FROM THE PACKET, AND   @E@@@@ COPYITI
)@@G@@NG FROM THE STRING BEGINS AT THE POINT WHERE IT WAS   @G@@@@ PREVIOUSLY TJ
)@@G@@INTERRUPTED.  EACH CALL TO  EMSGR$  INSERTS THE CURRENT     @F@@@@ EMSG$TK
)@@G@@ FIELD (THE CHARACTERS BETWEEN THE SENTINELS) AND ADVANCES  @F@@@@ THE ETL
)@@G@@MSG$ POINTER TO THE BEGINNING OF THE NEXT FIELD.  EMSG$ AND @F@@@@ EMSGRTM
)@@G@@$ PERMIT THE USER TO SELECTIVELY COPY THE EMSG$ STRING,     @F@@@@ OCCASTN
)@@G@@IONALLY INTERRUPTING THE PROCESS TO INSERT OTHER FIELDS     @#@@@@ (NUMBTO
)@@G@@ERS, ETC.). @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@                    LMJ      X11,EMSGR$   TP
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@                    E$MSTQ
)@@G@@GR    @ @@@@2EMSKP$ - SKIP MESSAGE FIELDS @F@@@@     THE EMSG$ STRING POTR
)@@G@@INTER IS MOVED PAST THE NUMBER OF FIELDS  @F@@@@ SPECIFIED BY A0. IF THETS
)@@G@@ NUMBER IS NEGATIVE, THE POINTER WILL BACK@ @@@@ UP OVER PREVIOUS FIELDSTT
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@                    LA,XU    A0,NUMBER-OF-FIELDSTU

)@@G@@NT    @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ TO SKIP TO A CERTAIN FIELD, AND THEN COPY IT:  TX

)@@G@@                    E$MSGR    @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ TO GENERATE THESE LINESTZ
)@@G@@:     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@                    E$MSKPR           SKIPCOUNT UA
)@@G@@@[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3FLOATING POINT ROUTINES@F@@@@      THESE ROUTINES EDIUB
)@@G@@T THE SINGLE PRECISION FLOATING POINT     @F@@@@ NUMBER IN A1 OR THE DOUUC
)@@G@@BLE PRECISION NUMBER IN A1 AND A2 TO A    @E@@@@ DECIMAL REPRESENTATION UD
)@@G@@PRECEEDED BY A '-' IF THE NUMBER IS @]@@@@ NEGATIVE.  @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@UE
)@@G@@       A0 IS EXPECTED TO CONTAIN A PARAMETER OF THE FORM     X*/6+Y     UF
)@@G@@@E@@@@ WHERE X IS THE DESIRED FIELD WIDTH, AND Y IS THE NUMBER OF @E@@@@UG
)@@G@@ SIGNIFICANT DIGITS, OR DIGITS FOLLOWING THE DECIMAL POINT, @A@@@@ DEPENUH
)@@G@@DING ON THE ROUTINE CALLED.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      THE RESULT IS RIGHUI
)@@G@@T-JUSTIFIED IN A FIELD OF BLANKS, UNLESS  @F@@@@ THE FIELD IS TOO SMALL,UJ
)@@G@@ FORCING THE RESULT TO OVERFLOW TO THE    @]@@@@ RIGHT.     @[@@@@SPACE UK
)@@G@@@E@@@@      WITH X AND Y AS DESCRIBED, THE SCIENTIFIC FORMAT IS   @E@@@@UL
)@@G@@ EQUIVALENT TO THE FORTRAN  'E'  OR  'D'  FORMAT (EX.Y), THE@F@@@@ GENERUM
)@@G@@AL FORMAT IS SIMILAR TO THE FORTRAN  'G'  FORMAT, AND THE   @F@@@@ FIXEDUN
)@@G@@ FORMAT IS SIMILAR TO THE FORTRAN  'F'  FORMAT.  WITH THE   @F@@@@ EDIT$UO
)@@G@@ ROUTINES, HOWEVER, THE RESULTS ARE PERMITTED TO EXCEED THE @^@@@@ SPECIUP
)@@G@@FIED FIELD WIDTH. @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      BECAUSE THE RESULTS OVERFLOW TUQ
)@@G@@O THE RIGHT WHEN NECESSARY, A @G@@@@ FIELD WIDTH (SPECIFIED BY X) OF ZERUR
)@@G@@O GENERATES FREE FORMAT OUTPUT,     @B@@@@ USING ONLY AS MANY COLUMNS ASUS
)@@G@@ NECESSARY. @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@     WHEN PACKET FLAG    FPR   IS SET NON-UT
)@@G@@ZERO, FLOATING POINT    @G@@@@ NUMBERS ARE ROUNDED UP BY ADDING 5 TO THEUU
)@@G@@ EIGHTH SIGNIFICANT DIGIT     @F@@@@ FOR SINGLE PRECISION, OR THE EIGHTEUV
)@@G@@ENTH SIGNIFICANT DIGIT FOR    @#@@@@ DOUBLE PRECISION.@[@@@@EJECT @C@@@@UW
)@@G@@2EFLS1$ - SINGLE PRECISION SCIENTIFIC FORMAT    @F@@@@      THE SINGLE PUX
)@@G@@RECISION FLOATING POINT NUMBER IN A1 IS EDITED  @E@@@@ INTO THE FOLLOWINUY
)@@G@@G FORMAT: A LEADING '-' (IF THE NUMBER IS @F@@@@ NEGATIVE), FOLLOWED BY UZ

)@@G@@ELDATA) OR     SPCA     (IF ASCII), @F@@@@ FOLLOWED BY A    '+'     OR  VD
)@@G@@   '-'     TO DENOTE THE SIGN OF THE@F@@@@ CHARACTERISTIC (POWER OF 10) VE

)@@G@@SPACE @ @@@@          LA,U      A0,X*/6+Y @B@@@@          LA        A1,AVG

)@@G@@ION   @F@@@@      A FIXED POINT FRACTIONAL NUMBER CONSISTS OF A STRING OXH
)@@G@@F     @F@@@@ BINARY BITS SEPARATED BY A BINARY POINT INTO AN INTEGER PARXI
)@@G@@T     @F@@@@ (GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO 1) AND A FRACTIONAL PART (LESS THXJ

)@@G@@OF BITS     @G@@@@ TO THE RIGHT OF THE BINARY POINT (WHICH SERVES THE SAXL

)@@G@@0000000     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ ARE THE FLOATING POINT REPRESENTATIONS FOXQ
)@@G@@R 1.0, 1.5, AND .75     @F@@@@ RESPECTIVELY. WITH A FRACTIONAL PART OF 6XR

)@@G@@E     @^@@@@ BINARY POINT PLUS 1.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      AN EXAMPLE: XZ
)@@G@@TO DISPLAY A DOUBLE PRECISION INTEGER (INTEGERS @G@@@@ HAVE 0 BITS TO THYA
)@@G@@E RIGHT OF THE BINARY POINT, SO Z = 1), ONE MIGHT     @[@@@@ DO:  @[@@@@YB
)@@G@@SPACE @C@@@@          E$FLF2    1*/12+24*/6+0,INT-ADDRESS   @[@@@@EJECT YC

)@@G@@2351  @[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3INTEGER FORM ROUTINES  @F@@@@     OCTAL FORM EDAL
)@@G@@ITING - THESE ROUTINES ARE ANALOGOUS TO THE     @F@@@@ ASSEMBLER FORM DIAM
)@@G@@RECTIVE, AND USE REGISTERS  X11, A0-A5, AND R1. @F@@@@ A0 IS EDITED INTOAN
