)@@G@@ ZERO IS EQUIVALENT TO SPECIFYING THE ENTIRE WORD     (E$FW 36)  .@[@@@@AT
)@@G@@SPACE @F@@@@ EXAMPLE:  TO EDIT H1 AND H2 (2 18-BIT SUBFIELDS) OF A WORD,AU
)@@G@@ THE  @B@@@@ FORM WORD WOULD BE    (E$FW   18,18)    .@]@@@@SPACE 3     AV
)@@G@@@F@@@@    DECIMAL FORM EDITING - THE ENTIRE MINOR REGISTER SET (X11,    AW
)@@G@@@F@@@@ A0-A5, R1-R3) IS USED.  A0 IS EDITED DECIMALLY INTO SUBFIELDS    AX
)@@G@@@F@@@@ (WHOSE WIDTH IS SPECIFIED BY H1 OF A2) SEPARATED BY THE CHARACTERAY
)@@G@@@F@@@@ FOUND IN H2 OF A2.  A '-' PRECEEDS THE FIRST SUBFIELD IF A0 IS   AZ
)@@G@@@]@@@@ NEGATIVE.  @]@@@@SPACE 2     @G@@@@      IF DESIRED, THE USER-SUPBA
)@@G@@PLIED SEPARATION OR LEADING CHARACTER     @G@@@@ WILL BE TRANSLATED (ASCBB
)@@G@@II-FIELDATA OR FIELDATA-ASCII) AS EXPLAINED     @#@@@@ IN SECTION 5.    BC
)@@G@@@[@@@@EJECT @B@@@@2EFORM$ - OCTAL FORM (BLANK SEPARATED)    @E@@@@      BD
)@@G@@EDITS A0 INTO OCTAL SUBFIELDS SEPARATED BY BLANKS.    @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@BE
)@@G@@                    LA       A1,(E$FW F1,...,FN)@C@@@@                  BF
)@@G@@  LA       A0,ADDR-OF-NUMBER  @B@@@@                    LMJ      X11,EFOBG
)@@G@@RM$   @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@BH
)@@G@@SPACE @E@@@@                    E$FORM   (E$FW F1,...,FN),ADDR-OF-NUMBERBI
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 2     @ @@@@ AS AN EXAMPLE, THE CALL:     @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@BJ
)@@G@@          E$FORM    (E$FW 9,9,9,9),(-1)   @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ PRODUCES:  BK
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@          777 777 777 776     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@2EFORMBL
)@@G@@C$ - OCTAL FORM (CHARACTER SEPARATED)     @F@@@@      SAME AS EFORM$, WIBM
)@@G@@TH THE CHARACTER IN A2 SEPARATING THE     @ @@@@ FIELDS INSTEAD OF BLANKBN
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@                    LA,U     A2,CHAR@C@@@@      BO
)@@G@@              LA       A1,(E$FW F1,...,FN)@C@@@@                    LA  BP
)@@G@@     A0,ADDR-OF-NUMBER  @B@@@@                    LMJ      X11,EFORMC$  BQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE BR
)@@G@@@F@@@@                    E$FORMC  (E$FW F1,...,FN),ADDR-OF-NUMBER  CHARBS
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 2     @ @@@@ AS AN EXAMPLE, THE CALL:     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@BT
)@@G@@          E$FORMC   (E$FW 9,9,9,6,3),(-1)   ',' @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@ PRODUBU
)@@G@@CES:  @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@          777,777,777,77,6    @[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@BV
)@@G@@2EFDECV$ - FREE FORMAT DECIMAL FORM @F@@@@      CORRESPONDS TO EDECV$ - BW
)@@G@@FREE FORMAT.  A0 IS EDITED INTO     @G@@@@ DECIMAL SUBFIELDS (WHOSE WIDTBX
)@@G@@H IS SPECIFIED IN H1 OF A2) SEPARATED     @ @@@@ BY THE CHARACTER IN H2 BY
)@@G@@OF A2.@[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@                    LA       A0,ADDR-OF-NUMBER  BZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@                    LA,U     A2,CHAR@B@@@@                    LXI,CA
)@@G@@U    A2,WIDTH     @B@@@@                    LMJ      X11,EFDECV$  @[@@@@CB
)@@G@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@CC
)@@G@@                    E$FDECV  ADDR-OF-NUMBER  WIDTH,CHAR     @]@@@@SPACE CD
)@@G@@2     @^@@@@ EXAMPLE: WITH THE CALL:@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@          E$FDECV CE
)@@G@@  NUMBER  3,','   @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@ SOME EXAMPLES OF OUTPUT ARE: @[@@@@CF
)@@G@@SPACE @E@@@@   1   -12   123   -1,234   12,345   -123,456   1,234,567   CG
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 2     @A@@@@2EFDECF$ - FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL FORM@F@@@@      CH
)@@G@@CORRESPONDS TO EDECF$ - FIXED FORMAT VERSION OF EFDECV$     @[@@@@SPACE CI
)@@G@@@C@@@@                    LA       A0,ADDR-OF-NUMBER  @C@@@@            CJ
)@@G@@        LA,U     A1,FIELD-WIDTH     @A@@@@                    LA,U     ACK
)@@G@@2,CHAR@B@@@@                    LXI,U    A2,WIDTH     @B@@@@            CL
)@@G@@        LMJ      X11,EFDECF$  @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATCM
)@@G@@ED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@                    E$FDECF  FIELD-WCN
)@@G@@IDTH,ADDR-OF-NUMBER  WIDTH,CHAR     @[@@@@EJECT @D@@@@2EFDECFZ$ - FIXED CO
)@@G@@FORMAT DECIMAL FORM (LEADING ZEROES)@F@@@@      CORRESPONDS TO EDECFZ$, CP
)@@G@@WITH LEADING ZEROES INSERTED INSTEAD@F@@@@ OF LEADING BLANKS. IF A0 IS NCQ
)@@G@@EGATIVE, THE MINUS SIGN PRECEEDS THE@]@@@@ ZEROES.    @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@CR
)@@G@@                    LA       A0,ADDR-OF-NUMBER  @C@@@@                  CS
)@@G@@  LA,U     A1,FIELD-WIDTH     @A@@@@                    LA,U     A2,CHARCT
)@@G@@@B@@@@                    LXI,U    A2,WIDTH     @B@@@@                  CU
)@@G@@  LMJ      X11,EFDECFZ$ @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY CV
)@@G@@THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@                    E$FDECFZ FIELD-WIDTH,ACW
)@@G@@DDR-OF-NUMBER  WIDTH,CHAR     @]@@@@SPACE 2     @^@@@@ EXAMPLE: WITH THECX
)@@G@@ CALL:@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@          E$FDECFZ  5,NUMBER   3,','@[@@@@SPACE CY
)@@G@@@ @@@@ SOME EXAMPLES OF OUTPUT ARE: @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@    00001   -0012 CZ
)@@G@@  00123   -1,234   12,345   -123,456@[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@2EFDECFL$ - FIXED DA
)@@G@@FORMAT DECIMAL FORM - LEADING CHARACTERS  @F@@@@      SAME AS EFDECFZ$, DB
)@@G@@WITH THE CHARACTER IN A3 USED INSTEAD OF  @A@@@@ ZEROES AS THE LEADING CDC
)@@G@@HARACTERS.  @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@                    LA       A0,ADDR-OF-NUDD
)@@G@@MBER  @C@@@@                    LA,U     A1,FIELD-WIDTH     @A@@@@      DE
)@@G@@              LA,U     A2,CHAR@B@@@@                    LXI,U    A2,WIDTDF
)@@G@@H     @C@@@@                    LA,U     A3,LEADING-CHAR    @B@@@@      DG
)@@G@@              LMJ      X11,EFDECFL$ @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GDH
)@@G@@ENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@        E$FDECFL FIELD-WIDTH,ADI
)@@G@@DDR  WIDTH,CHAR LEADING-CHAR  @]@@@@SPACE 2     @^@@@@ EXAMPLE: WITH THEDJ
)@@G@@ CALL:@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@          E$FDECFL  5,NUMBER   3,','  '&' @[@@@@DK
)@@G@@SPACE @ @@@@ SOME EXAMPLES OF OUTPUT ARE: @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@    &&&&1   DL
)@@G@@-&&12   &&123   -1,234   12,345   -123,456@[@@@@SPACE @[@@@@EJECT @#@@@@DM
)@@G@@3OUTPUT ROUTINES  @F@@@@      THESE ROUTINES EITHER PRINT THE IMAGE (VIADN
)@@G@@     PRINT$    OR @F@@@@ APRINT$   ) OR SEND THE IMAGE TO    CSF$    . TDO
)@@G@@HE IMAGE IS THEN  @A@@@@ REINITIALIZED ACCORDING TO A1:     @[@@@@SPACE DP
)@@G@@@]@@@@COLUMN 21   @C@@@@          A1 < 0    SET COLUMN POINTER TO ZERO. DQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          A1 = 0    BLANK ONLY AS MUCH OF THE BUFFER ADR
)@@G@@S WAS USED  @F@@@@                    (UP TO WORD POINTER), SET COLUMN PDS
)@@G@@OINTER TO   @G@@@@                    ZERO. THIS IS SOMEWHAT FASTER THANDT
)@@G@@ CLEARING THE     @A@@@@                    ENTIRE BUFFER.  @[@@@@SPACE DU
)@@G@@@F@@@@          A1 > 0    BLANK ENTIRE BUFFER, SET POINTER TO ZERO.     DV
)@@G@@@^@@@@2EDIT$ PRINTING ROUTINES@]@@@@COLUMN 2    @G@@@@     DEPENDING ON DW
)@@G@@THE ROUTINE CALLED, A0 IS EXPECTED TO CONTAIN THE     @F@@@@ NUMBER OF LDX
)@@G@@INES TO SKIP BEFORE PRINTING, OR THE PRINT CONTROL    @B@@@@ WORD.  CALLDY
)@@G@@ED. THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS : @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@          LA,XU     A1,CDZ
)@@G@@LEARBUFFERFLAG    @B@@@@          LA,XU     A0,LINE-SKIP-COUNT    @A@@@@EA
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,EROUTINE$   @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@     OR:    @[@@@@EB
)@@G@@SPACE @B@@@@          LA,XU     A1,CLEAR-BUFFER-FLAG  @B@@@@          LAEC
)@@G@@        A0,(CONTROL-WORD)     @A@@@@          LMJ       X11,EROUTINE$   ED
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@  THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:  @[@@@@SPACE EE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$ROUTINE BUFFER-FLAG,LINESKIP-OR-CONTROLWORD     @[@@@@EF
)@@G@@SPACE @E@@@@    WHERE     EROUTINE$    IS THE APPROPRIATE EDIT$ PRINTINGEG
)@@G@@@D@@@@ ROUTINE (DESCRIBED BELOW), AND    E$ROUTINE    IS THE@ @@@@ CORREEH
)@@G@@SPONDING PROC CALL.     @[@@@@EJECT @C@@@@ THE PRINTING ROUTINES AND THEEI
)@@G@@IR ACTIONS ARE:   @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 21   @G@@@@          EPRT$   EJ
)@@G@@- SKIP A0 LINES, PRINT THE CONTENTS OF THE ENTIRE     @E@@@@            EK
)@@G@@        OUTPUT IMAGE USING PRINT$ (FIELDATA).   @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@      EL
)@@G@@    EPRTI$  - USES A0 AS PRINT$ CONTROL WORD    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      EM
)@@G@@    EAPRT$  - SAME AS EPRT$, BUT DOES AN APRINT$ (ASCII)    @[@@@@SPACE EN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          EAPRTI$ - USES A0 AS AN APRINT$ CONTROL WORD@[@@@@SPACE EO
)@@G@@@F@@@@          EPRTA$  - UOM ASCII PRINTING. INSERTS A CARRIAGE RETURN EP
)@@G@@@E@@@@                    (015), THEN A LINE FEED (012), AND THEN @B@@@@EQ
)@@G@@                    TRANSFERS TO EPRT$.   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@          EPER
)@@G@@RTG$  - IF EASC (PACKET OUTPUT ASCII FLAG) = 0  @F@@@@                  ES
)@@G@@  (INDICATING FIELDATA) , CONTROL IS PASSED TO  @F@@@@                  ET
)@@G@@  EPRT$, IF EASC IS NOT 0, CONTROL PASSES TO    @ @@@@                  EU
)@@G@@  EAPRT$.   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@          EPRTGA$ - IF EASC = 0, CONTROL PEV
)@@G@@ASSES TO EPRT$, OTHERWISE     @ @@@@                    TO EPRTA$.@[@@@@EW
)@@G@@SPACE @ @@@@2ECSF$ - EDIT$ CSF$ ROUTINE   @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @G@@@@      EX
)@@G@@THE FIELDATA OUTPUT IMAGE IS SUBMITTED TO EXEC 8 AS IF IT HAD     @F@@@@EY
)@@G@@ BEEN ENTERED AS A CONTROL STATEMENT.  A0 RETURNS CONTAINING THE  @ @@@@EZ
)@@G@@ STATUS FROM      CSF$    .   @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@          LA,XU     A1,CFA
)@@G@@LEAR-IMAGE-FLAG   @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,ECSF$ @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@FB
)@@G@@ THIS CODE IS GENERATED BY THE PROC:@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@          E$CSF   FC
)@@G@@  CLEAR-IMAGE-FLAG@[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3TIME AND DATE ROUTINES @G@@@@     TFD
)@@G@@HE EDIT$ TIME AND DATE ROUTINES EXPECT A0 TO CONTAIN THE TIME     @G@@@@FE
)@@G@@ AND DATE IN THE FORMAT ONE OBTAINS FROM DOING AN    ER TDATE$    :     FF
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@    ..................................................FG
)@@G@@........... @F@@@@    :  MONTH  :   DAY   :   YEAR  :            TIME   FH
)@@G@@          : @F@@@@    ..................................................FI
)@@G@@........... @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 21   @F@@@@          MONTH -   S1 OFJ
)@@G@@F A0 CONTAINS THE MONTH OF THE YEAR (1-12)@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          DAFK
)@@G@@Y  -    S2 OF A0 CONTAINS THE DAY OF THE MONTH (1-31) @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@FL
)@@G@@          YEAR  -   S3 OF A0 CONTAINS THE NUMBER OF YEARS PASSED  @ @@@@FM
)@@G@@                    SINCE 1964@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          TIME  -   H1 OFN
)@@G@@F A0 CONTAINS THE TIME IN SECONDS SINCE   @ @@@@                    MIDNFO
)@@G@@IGHT  @A@@@@2ETIME$ - TIME EDITING - HH:MM:SS   @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @E@@@@FP
)@@G@@      THE TIME PORTION OF A0 IS INSERTED INTO THE IMAGE AS: @[@@@@SPACE FQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@                    HH:MM:SS  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ WHERE HH,MM, AND FR
)@@G@@SS ARE THE HOURS, MINUTES, AND SECONDS OF THE   @[@@@@ TIME.@[@@@@SPACE FS
)@@G@@@A@@@@          LA        A0,TDATE$-WORD  @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,FT
)@@G@@ETIME$@[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ THESE TWO WORDS ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:     FU
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@          E$TIME    TDATE$-WORD     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@FV
)@@G@@ TO INSERT THE CURRENT TIME INTO THE IMAGE:     @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@      FW
)@@G@@    ER        TDATE$    @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,ETIME$@[@@@@SPACE FX
)@@G@@@B@@@@ THESE LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@      FY
)@@G@@    E$TD    @[@@@@EJECT @A@@@@2EDAY1$ - DATE EDITING - MM/DD/YY   @E@@@@FZ
)@@G@@      THE DATE PORTION OF A0 IS INSERTED INTO THE IMAGE AS: @[@@@@SPACE GA
)@@G@@@ @@@@                    MM/DD/YY  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ WHERE MM,DD, AND GB
)@@G@@YY ARE THE MONTH, DAY, AND YEAR OF THE DATE.    @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@      GC
)@@G@@    LA        A0,TDATE$-WORD  @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,EDAY1$@[@@@@GD
)@@G@@SPACE @C@@@@ THESE TWO WORDS ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:     @[@@@@SPACE GE
)@@G@@@A@@@@          E$DAY1    TDATE$-WORD     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ TO INSERT TGF
)@@G@@HE CURRENT DATE INTO THE IMAGE:     @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@          ER      GG
)@@G@@  TDATE$    @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,EDAY1$@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESEGH
)@@G@@ LINES ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@          E$DAT1  GI
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 2     @A@@@@2EDAY2$ - DATE EDITING - DD MMM YY  @E@@@@      GJ
)@@G@@THE DATE PORTION OF A0 IS INSERTED INTO THE IMAGE AS: @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@GK
)@@G@@                    DD MMM YY @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@ WHERE MMM, DD, AND YY AGL
)@@G@@RE THE MONTH, DAY, AND YEAR OF THE DATE.  @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@          LAGM
)@@G@@        A0,TDATE$-WORD  @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,EDAY2$@[@@@@SPACE GN

)@@G@@          E$DAY2    TDATE$-WORD     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ TO INSERT THE CURGP
)@@G@@RENT DATE INTO THE IMAGE:     @[@@@@SPACE @ @@@@          ER        TDATGQ
)@@G@@E$    @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,EDAY2$@[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@ THESE LINESGR
)@@G@@ ARE GENERATED BY THE PROC:   @[@@@@SPACE @#@@@@          E$DAT2  @[@@@@GS
)@@G@@EJECT @B@@@@2EDAY3$ - DATE EDITING - MONTH DD, YEAR   @E@@@@      THE DAGT
)@@G@@TE PORTION OF A0 IS INSERTED INTO THE IMAGE AS: @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@      GU
)@@G@@              MONTH DD,YEAR   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ WHERE MONTH,DD, AND YEAGV
)@@G@@R ARE THE MONTH, DAY, AND YEAR OF THE DATE.     @[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@      GW

)@@G@@@A@@@@          E$DAY3    TDATE$-WORD     @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ TO INSERT TGZ

)@@G@@@#@@@@4THE EDIT$ PACKET @F@@@@     THE SIX TO FOURTEEN WORD EDIT$ PACKETHD
)@@G@@ CONTAINS USER-DEFINED  @E@@@@ PARAMETERS, AND INTERNAL FLAGS USED BY THHE
)@@G@@E EDIT$ ROUTINES. @#@@@@3PACKET STRUCTURE @G@@@@      EDIT$ USES THE FOLHF
)@@G@@LOWING PACKET. WORDS 6 THROUGH 9 ARE NEEDED     @F@@@@ BY THE FLOATING PHG
)@@G@@OINT ROUTINES, WORDS 6 THROUGH 12 ARE REQUIRED  @E@@@@ FOR ASCII CAPABILHH
)@@G@@ITIES, AND EXTENDED ASCII DEMANDS WORD 13.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@    ........HI
)@@G@@..................................................... @]@@@@SPACE 0     HJ

)@@G@@EJECT @ @@@@3PACKET FIELD DEFINITIONS     @D@@@@          S1 0F WORD 0  IR

)@@G@@    EMSGC     FIELDATA EMSG$  STOP-CHARACTER. EMSG$ AND     @F@@@@      IT
)@@G@@              EMSGR$ STOP TRANSFERRING FIELDATA CHARACTERS  @G@@@@      IU
)@@G@@              FROM THE EMSG$ INPUT STRING TO THE OUTPUT IMAGE     @G@@@@IV
)@@G@@                    BUFFER WHEN THIS CHARACTER IS ENCOUNTERED. THIS     IW
)@@G@@@F@@@@                    ALLOWS OTHER STRINGS (NUMBERS, ETC.) TO BE    IX
)@@G@@@D@@@@                    INSERTED WITHIN THE EMSG$ IMAGE.  @[@@@@SPACE IY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          IL        LENGTH OF OUTPUT IMAGE BUFFER. THIS IS USUALLYIZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@                    22 FOR FIELDATA IMAGES AND 32 FOR ASCII IMAGESJA
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@          ILOC      ADDRESS OF OUTPUT IMAGE BUFFJB
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@          RETRN     INTERNAL EDIT$ SAVE AREA    JC
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@          FPS       NUMBER OF DIGITS PRIOR TO THE DECIJD
)@@G@@MAL POINT FOR     @F@@@@                    SCIENTIFIC FLOATING POINT EDJE
)@@G@@ITING. THIS ALSO  @G@@@@                    DESIGNATES THE NUMBER OF ZERJF
)@@G@@OES PLACED PRIOR TO     @D@@@@                    THE DECIMAL POINT FOR JG
)@@G@@FIXED POINT @G@@@@                    REPRESENTATION OF NUMBERS WHOSE MAJH
)@@G@@GNITUDE < 1.0     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          FPR       FLOATING POINT RJI
)@@G@@OUNDING. IF NONZERO (THE USUAL@F@@@@                    CASE), 5 IS ADDEJJ
)@@G@@D TO THE EIGHTH SIGNIFICANT   @F@@@@                    DIGIT FOR SINGLEJK
)@@G@@ PRECISION OR TO THE 18TH     @E@@@@                    SIGNIFICANT DIGIJL
)@@G@@T FOR DOUBLE PRECISION. @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@          CIM       EMSG$ CHARJM
)@@G@@ACTER INDEX @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          EASC      OUTPUT MODE FLAG. THE JN
)@@G@@OUTPUT IMAGE IS FIELDATA@F@@@@                    IF EASC IS ZERO, ASCIIJO
)@@G@@ IF EASC IS NON-ZERO.   @[@@@@SPACE @E@@@@          EASCIN    INPUT MODEJP
)@@G@@ FLAG FOR EFD1$, EFD2$, EFD3$,@F@@@@                    ECOPY$, EPACK$, JQ
)@@G@@EPACKC, EMSG$, AND EMSGR$.    @F@@@@                    THESE ROUTINES TJR
)@@G@@RANSFER CHARACTERS FROM INPUT @F@@@@                    CHARACTER STRINGJS
)@@G@@S OR REGISTERS TO THE OUTPUT  @G@@@@                    IMAGE BUFFER. IFJT
)@@G@@ EASCIN=0, THEY EXPECT FIELDATA     @F@@@@                    CHARACTERSJU
)@@G@@, IF EASCIN=1, THEY EXPECT TO READ  @B@@@@                    ASCII CHARJV
)@@G@@ACTERS.     @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@          QWM       IF 1, THEN QUARTERWORDJW
)@@G@@ MODE WAS SET VIA PSR$ BY     @F@@@@                    EDIT$, ERASE$, OJX
)@@G@@R EDITR$. IF 0, NO PSR$ WAS   @ @@@@                    PERFORMED.@[@@@@JY
)@@G@@SPACE @A@@@@          WIM       E$MSG WORD INDEX@[@@@@EJECT @E@@@@      JZ
)@@G@@    SAVE1     SAVE OF X1 (PACKET POINTER) MODIFIER    @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@KA
)@@G@@          SAVE2     SAVE OF X2 OR CHARACTER POINTER   @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@KB
)@@G@@          SAVE3     SAVE OF X3 OR WORD POINTER  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      KC
)@@G@@    DPC       FIELDATA EXPONENT CHARACTER FOR D.P. FLOATING @E@@@@      KD
)@@G@@              POINT, TO SEPARATE THE MANTISSA AND     @F@@@@            KE
)@@G@@        CHARACTERISTIC PARTS OF THE FIELD. IF 0, NO   @B@@@@            KF
)@@G@@        CHARACTER IS USED.    @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@          SPC       FIELKG
)@@G@@DATA CHARACTER FOR S.P. FLOATING POINT. DPC     @F@@@@                  KH
)@@G@@  AND SPC ALLOW COMPATIBILITY WITH EXISTING     @F@@@@                  KI
)@@G@@  FORMATS (SUCH AS THE FORTRAN    'E'    OR 'D' @ @@@@                  KJ

)@@G@@ERIC TRANSLATION  @E@@@@     AS EXPLAINED IN THE SECTION ON THE ALPHANUMMN
)@@G@@ERIC EDIT$  @F@@@@ ROUTINES, EDIT$ HAS THE CAPABILITY TO TRANSLATE ASCIIMO
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS @F@@@@ TO FIELDATA (EASCIN=1, EASC=0) OR FIELDATA TO ASCII (MP

)@@G@@ 11   @F@@@@     1)   ASCII CONTROL CHARACTERS (000-037). THESE ARE SPECMT
)@@G@@IAL   @E@@@@          FORMATTING AND COMMUNICATIONS CHARACTERS, AND ARE MU
)@@G@@@C@@@@          NORMALLY OF NO CONCERN TO THE USER.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@MV

)@@G@@          COMMAS. @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      3)  UPPER CASE (0100-0137). THMY

)@@G@@E ASCII UNDERLINE CHARACTER.  @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@      4)  LOWER CASE (01NA
)@@G@@40-0177). THESE ARE THE LOWER CASE LETTERS,     @F@@@@          LEFT ANDNB
)@@G@@ RIGHT BRACES, VERTICAL LINE, TILDE, ACCENT, AND@B@@@@          THE ASCINC
)@@G@@I DELETE CHARACTER.     @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 2    @F@@@@     THE FIEND
)@@G@@LDATA COMPLEMENT OF 64 CHARACTERS CONSISTS OF THE     @F@@@@ NUMERIC/SPENE
)@@G@@CIAL AND UPPER CASE CHARACTERS. IT CAN BE SEEN THAT IN@F@@@@ TRANSLATINGNF
)@@G@@ FROM 128 CHARACTER ASCII TO 64 CHARACTER FIELDATA,   @F@@@@ EITHER LOWENG
)@@G@@R CASE MAY BE FORSAKEN, OR CERTAIN FIELDATA CHARACTERS@F@@@@ MAY BE SACRNH
)@@G@@IFICED AND DESIGNATED AS CONTROL FLAGS TO RETAIN THE  @F@@@@ SHIFTING INNI
)@@G@@FORMATION. THESE TWO METHODS OF TRANSLATION ARE BOTH  @D@@@@ AVAILABLE, NJ
)@@G@@AND ARE SPECIFIED WITH THE FLAG    XAF   .@]@@@@SPACE 2     @E@@@@      NK
)@@G@@NOTE: THIS TRANSLATION IS ONLY NECESSARY WHEN THE USER@F@@@@ SUPPLIES CHNL
)@@G@@ARACTERS OF ONE MODE TO EDIT$ ROUTINES AND WISHES THEM@C@@@@ INSERTED INNM
)@@G@@TO THE IMAGE IN THE OTHER MODE.     @[@@@@EJECT @^@@@@3NORMAL TRANSLATIONN
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@     IF    XAF    EQUALS ZERO, EACH ASCII CHARACTER HAS ONE NO
)@@G@@@F@@@@ FIELDATA EQUIVALENT CHARACTER IN THE TRANSLATION TABLE, AND VICE NP
)@@G@@@G@@@@ VERSA.  GENERALLY, THE ASCII CONTROL CHARACTERS ARE EQUATED TO THNQ
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@ FIELDATA '?', THE ASCII NUMERIC/SPECIAL CHARACTERS ARE MAPPNR
)@@G@@ED TO @G@@@@ THEIR CORRESPONDING FIELDATA EQUIVALENTS, AND BOTH UPPER ANNS
)@@G@@D LOWER     @E@@@@ CASE CHARACTERS ARE EQUATED TO THEIR FIELDATA UPPER CNT
)@@G@@ASE   @F@@@@ EQUIVALENTS.  THERE ARE THREE EXCEPTIONS: THE ASCII CIRCUMFNU
)@@G@@LEX IS@G@@@@ EQUIVALENT TO THE FIELDATA DELTA (UP-ARROW), THE DOUBLE QUONV
)@@G@@TE IS A     @F@@@@ FIELDATA LOZENGE (SOFT PILLOW), AND THE ASCII UNDERLINW
)@@G@@NE BECOMES A@ @@@@ FIELDATA NOT-EQUAL SIGN.     @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@     INX
)@@G@@N TRANSLATING FROM ASCII TO FIELDATA THIS SCHEME  PROHIBITS @G@@@@ LOWERNY
)@@G@@ CASE CAPABILITIES (TRANSLATING THE FIELDATA STRING BACK INTO     @F@@@@NZ
)@@G@@ ASCII DOES NOT RESTORE THE SHIFTING INFORMATION) , BUT FOR MOST  @F@@@@OA
)@@G@@ APPLICATIONS, WHERE LOWER CASE IS NEITHER USEFUL NOR NECESSARY,  @ @@@@OB
)@@G@@ THIS METHOD SHOULD SUFFICE.  @A@@@@3SHIFT-CODED (EXTENDED) TRANSLATION OC
)@@G@@@F@@@@      BY DESIGNATING CERTAIN FIELDATA CHARACTERS AS CONTROL FLAGS,OD
)@@G@@@F@@@@ THE SHIFTING INFORMATION IN TRANSLATING FROM ASCII TO FIELDATA ISOE
)@@G@@@F@@@@ RETAINED.  THE FIELDATA IMAGE MAY LATER BE RETRANSLATED TO ASCII,OF
)@@G@@@F@@@@ WITH THE SHIFTING INTACT, ALLOWING ASCII MESSAGES TO BE STORED   OG
)@@G@@@F@@@@ INTERNALLY IN THE MORE COMPACT FIELDATA MODE, AND THEN TRANSLATEDOH
)@@G@@@F@@@@ AND PRINTED AS REASONABLY FULL ASCII.  THIS SCHEME IS IMPLEMENTEDOI
)@@G@@@C@@@@ WHEN PACKET FLAG   XAF   IS SET EQUAL TO 1.    @[@@@@SPACE @B@@@@OJ
)@@G@@      THE CONVENTIONS ARE AS FOLLOWS:     @[@@@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 11   OK
)@@G@@@F@@@@     1)   ASCII CONTROL CHARACTERS (EXCEPT FOR THE BACKSPACE) MAP OL
)@@G@@@A@@@@          INTO THE FIELDATA '?'.    @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@     2)   NUOM
)@@G@@MERIC/SPECIAL ASCII CHARACTERS ARE SHIFT-INDEPENDENT  @C@@@@          ANON
)@@G@@D MAP TO THEIR FIELDATA EQUIVALENTS.@[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@     3)   ACCENT, OO
)@@G@@UPPER CASE LETTERS, BRACES, VERTICAL LINE, AND  @E@@@@          THE TILDOP
)@@G@@E ARE CONSIDERED SHIFTED (UPPER CASE).    @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@     4)   @,OQ
)@@G@@ LOWER CASE LETTERS, [, \, ] AND THE CIRCUMFLEX (^) ARE     @A@@@@      OR
)@@G@@    UNSHIFTED (LOWER CASE).   @[@@@@EJECT @F@@@@     5)   EACH LINE IS IOS
)@@G@@NITIALLY CONSIDERED TO BE UNSHIFTED. THE  @F@@@@          SPECIAL FIELDAOT
)@@G@@TA CONTROL CHARACTERS AND THEIR FUNCTIONS @#@@@@          ARE:    @[@@@@OU
)@@G@@SPACE @]@@@@COLUMN 21   @E@@@@          &         SHIFT THE MODE OF THE OV

)@@G@@REST OF THE LINE  @ @@@@                    ALONE.    @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@OX
)@@G@@          #         SHIFT THE MODE FOR THE REST OF THE IMAGE (UNTIL     OY
)@@G@@@A@@@@                    THE NEXT #)     @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@          ! OZ
)@@G@@        TRANSLATES TO AN ASCII BACKSPACE  @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          ? PA
)@@G@@        NON-BACKSPACE ASCII CONTROL CHARACTERS ARE    @F@@@@            PB

)@@G@@        FIELDATA TO ASCII, THIS CHARACTER BECOMES AN  @F@@@@            PD
)@@G@@        ASCII BELL, AUDIBLY ALERTING THE USER TO THE  @E@@@@            PE
)@@G@@        PRESENCE OF POSSIBLE TRASH IN HIS IMAGE.@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@      PF
)@@G@@    %         ASCII UNDERLINE @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@          '         THE PG
)@@G@@NEXT CHARACTER IS INTERPRETED AS ITSELF,  @F@@@@                    INSTPH

)@@G@@RSAND, '' IS A SINGLE QUOTE, ETC.   @]@@@@SPACE 2     @]@@@@COLUMN 2    PJ

)@@G@@FTED. @[@@@@EJECT @B@@@@3ALPHANUMERIC ROUTINES - MODIFICATIONS    @F@@@@PV

)@@G@@ $123,456.78@[@@@@EJECT @B@@@@3UOM EDIT$ VERSUS UNIVAC EDIT$-AEDIT$     YP
)@@G@@@G@@@@      RATHER THAN MAINTAIN ONE PACKAGE WITH BOTH FIELDATA AND ASCIYQ
)@@G@@I     @F@@@@ CAPABILITIES, UNIVAC HAS CHOSEN TO SUPPORT TWO NEARLY IDENTYR
)@@G@@ICAL  @G@@@@ PACKAGES: STANDARD FIELDATA     EDIT$    , AND THE ASCII   YS
)@@G@@ AEDIT$     @F@@@@ PACKAGE AS DEFINED IN PROGRAMMERS REFERENCE MANUAL (UYT
)@@G@@P-4144 REV. @F@[@@ 3).  THE STRUCTURE OF AEDIT$ APPEARS TO DELIBERATLY MYU
)@@G@@IMIC EDIT$, @E@@@[ 3).  THE STRUCTURE OF AEDIT$ WAS DESIGNED TO MIMIC EDYV
)@@G@@IT$,  @F@@@@ WITH CORRESPONDING PROC AND SUBROUTINE CALLS: ONE OPENS WITYW
)@@G@@H     @F@[@@ AEDIT$ AND CLOSES WITH AEDITX$, ETC.  WE HAVE NOT SEEN AN AYX
)@@G@@EDIT$ @B@@@[ AEDIT$ AND CLOSES WITH AEDITX$, ETC.     @F@[@@ LISTING, BUYY
)@@G@@T SIMILARITIES WITH EDIT$ CAN BE EXPECTED. THE CODE IS@C@[@@ PROBABLY EQYZ
)@@G@@UIVALENT, AND POSSIBLY REDUNDANT.   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      WHILE THE FIZA
)@@G@@ELDATA-ASCII TRANSLATION CAPABILITIES OF UOM    @F@@@@ EDIT$ ARE EXTENSIZB
)@@G@@VE AND EXPANDABLE, THE UNIVAC SCHEME DOES NOT   @F@@@@ SUPPORT TRANSLATIZC
)@@G@@ON, AND IN FACT DISCOURAGES SIMULTANEOUS OR     @F@@@@ DYNAMIC USE OF BOZD
)@@G@@TH FIELDATA AND ASCII EDITING. THIS RESTRICTION @F@@@@ STEMS FROM THE FAZE
)@@G@@CT THAT UNIVAC EDIT$ AND AEDIT$ BOTH USE X1, X2,@F@@@@ AND X3 AS POINTERZF
)@@G@@S TO SEPARATE AND DISIMILAR PACKETS, AND OPERATE@G@@@@ THROUGH ENTIRELY ZG
)@@G@@DIFFERENT ROUTINES. IF A PROGRAM IS DESIRED WHICH     @G@@@@ DYNAMICALLYZH
)@@G@@ SWITCHES FROM FIELDATA TO ASCII EDITING MODE, THEN TWO     @G@@@@ NEARLZI
)@@G@@Y IDENTICAL INSTRUCTION SEQUENCES MUST BE SET UP; ONE CALLING     @F@[@@ZJ
)@@G@@ THE FIELDATA EDIT$ ROUTINES, THE OTHER USING ASCII AEDIT$. THIS  @E@@@[ZK
)@@G@@ THE FIELDATA EDIT$ ROUTINES, THE OTHER USING ASCII AEDIT$. @F@[@@ (TOGEZL
)@@G@@THER WITH THE LOADING OF BOTH SETS OF SUBROUTINES) LEADS TO @G@[@@ DISTUZM
)@@G@@RBING AND INEVITABLE DUPLICATION OF CODE. UOM EDIT$ ,HOWEVER,     @]@@@[ZN
)@@G@@ UOM EDIT$  @F@@@@ OPERATES IN A MODE DESIGNATED BY A PACKET FLAG, AND IZO
)@@G@@S EASILY    @F@@@@ ALTERED; THE SAME SEQUENCE OF CODE IS SUFFICIENT FOR ZP
)@@G@@PRODUCING   @E@@@@ FIELDATA OR ASCII OUTPUT, AND REDUNDANT CODE IS REDUCZQ
)@@G@@ED.   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@      THE STANDARD UOM EDIT$ PACKAGE, WHICH INCLZR
)@@G@@UDES THOSE ROUTINES     @G@@@@ COMMON TO UNIVAC EDIT$, AS WELL AS ERASE$ZS
)@@G@@, EFD3$, EMSKP$, EDECFZ$,     @F@@@@ EDECFL$, AND EPAD$, AND EXCLUDES THZT
)@@G@@E PRINTING, TRANSLATION, AND  @F@@@@ INTEGER FORM ROUTINES (WHICH RESIDEZU
)@@G@@ IN SEPARATE ELEMENTS), IS    @F@@@@ SLIGHTLY LARGER THAN UNIVAC EDIT$: ZV
)@@G@@ 650 WORDS TO 508. WE HAVE NO @F@@@@ INDICATION OF THE SIZE OF AEDIT$; AZW
)@@G@@SSUMING EQUIVALENCE, WE EXPECT@F@@@@ IT TO BE APPROXIMATELY 520 WORDS INZX
)@@G@@ LENGTH. BECAUSE UOM EDIT$    @E@@@@ RESIDES IN SEVERAL SUBROUTINES, USEZY
)@@G@@RS MAY FIND  THEIR CORE @G@@@@ REQUIREMENTS ACTUALLY REDUCED FROM THAT RZZ
)@@G@@EQUIRED FOR UNIVAC EDIT$.     @[@@@@EJECT @F@@@@      DEPENDING ON THE NAA
)@@G@@UMBER OF DIGITS PER NUMBER, UOM EDIT$     @E@@@@ APPROACHES BEING TWICE AB
)@@G@@AS FAST AS UNIVAC EDIT$ IN PRODUCING@F@@@@ DECIMAL INTEGER NUMBERS, AND AC
)@@G@@IS ALMOST TWICE AS FAST FOR FLOATING@F@@@@ POINT.  DEPENDING ON THE NUMBAD
)@@G@@ER OF CHARACTERS TRANSFERRED, THE   @F@@@@ COPYING (ECOPY$, ETC.) AND EMAE
)@@G@@SG$ ROUTINES MAY RUN SLIGHTLY FASTER@E@@@@ USING UOM EDIT$ THAN THE UNIVAF
)@@G@@AC VERSION. OTHERWISE, THE TWO@B@@@@ VERSIONS ARE APPROXIMATELY EQUIVALEAG
)@@G@@NT.   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@      A LARGER REPERTOIRE OF ROUTINES IS PROVIDEAH
)@@G@@D BY UOM EDIT$ THAN     @G@@@@ UNIVAC. DESPITE UNIVAC'S PENCHANT FOR REPAI
)@@G@@LICATION, WE ARE SOMEWHAT     @F@@@@ SURPRISED THAT THEIR AEDIT$ IMPLEMEAJ
)@@G@@NTATION OMITS AN EQUIVALENT TO@F@@@@ EFD3$. THE INSERTION OF TWELVE-CHARAK
)@@G@@ACTER ASCII FILENAMES WOULD   @A@@@@ SEEM TO ENCOURAGE SUCH A ROUTINE.  AL
)@@G@@@[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@      FINALLY, THE STRUCTURE OF UOM EDIT$ IS COMPATABLAM
)@@G@@E WITH UNIVAC     @F@@@@ EDIT$. THE PROC AND ROUTINE CALLS ARE EQUIVALENAN
)@@G@@T, THE STANDARD   @F@@@@ USER-DEFINED PACKET FLAGS ('SPC', FPS', ETC.) OAO
)@@G@@CCUPY THE SAME    @F@@@@ POSITIONS IN THE UOM EDIT$ PACKET AS IN THE UNIAP
)@@G@@VAC VERSION, AND  @F@@@@ THE STANDARD EDIT$ ROUTINES (THOSE COMMON TO BOAQ
)@@G@@TH UOM AND UNIVAC @F@@@@ EDIT$) ADHERE TO THE CONVENTION OF USING ONLY XAR
)@@G@@11,A0-A3, AND R1. @F@@@@ IN GENERAL, PROGRAMS USING THE EXISTING UNIVAC AS
)@@G@@EDIT$ CAN CONVERT @A@@@@ TO UOM EDIT$ WITH NO MODIFICATION. @[@@@@EJECT AT
)@@G@@@^@@@@3THE FUTURE OF UOM EDIT$@E@@@@      THE PESTILENT (AND LAMENTABLE)AU
)@@G@@ FECUNDITY OF THE USER  @F@@@@ COMMUNITY DEMANDS THAT THE FOLLOWING FEATAV

)@@G@@E LISTED IN NO PARTICULAR     @]@@@@ ORDER.     @]@@@@SPACE 2     @]@@@@AX
)@@G@@COLUMN 11   @[@@@@SPACE @F@@@@      1)  END OF BUFFER INDICATION. IF EDIAY

)@@G@@@E@@@@/. PROC DEFINITION, FLAG RESET FOR STRUCTURED PROC PACKAGE  @[@@@@JG
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@G$LCTR(1) EQU  2                      . DEFAULT LOCN CTR FORJH

)@@G@@  . FORM FOR MASKING OFF ALL BUT JX IMMEDIAT    @H@@@@G$JMSK  EQUF   0,0JK
)@@G@@,016                . FORM FOR TESTING IMMEDIATE J-VALUES   @H@@@@G$UMSKJL
)@@G@@  EQUF   *0177777,*0            . FORM TO MASK OFF ALL BUT IMMEDIATE U  JM
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$NOFO  FORM   36                     . FORM TO GET RID OF OTHER FJN
)@@G@@ORMS  @I@@@@G$$FJA  FORM   6,8,4,2,16             . FORM FOR INSTRS USINJO
)@@G@@G JA FIELD (E.G. JGD    @F@@@@G$$IMU    FORM    6,4,4,4,18          . FOJP
)@@G@@RM FOR IMMEDIATE U-SPECS@[@@@@.     @H@@@@STRUC$DEF* PROC     *0,0      JQ
)@@G@@        . IF @ASM, DEFINE THESE BY XPLICIT CALL @B@@@@          END     JR
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@P       PROC   *2             JS
)@@G@@        . PF'S : DBANK-LOCNCTR,DISPLAY-OCTAL-FLAG     @E@@@@STRUC$* NAMEJT
)@@G@@                          . NORMAL ENTRY POINT  @G@@@@ DO 0=0=0 , STRUC$JU
)@@G@@OMN                 . IF MASM, INCLUDE OMN IF NEEDED  @F@@@@ DO 0=0=1 , JV
)@@G@@STRUC$DEF                 . IF @ASM, READ IN HUGE DEF @E@@@@ DO P(1)>0 ,JW
)@@G@@G$LCTR*(1) EQU P(1,1)     . SET DATA LOCN CTR   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. USAGJX
)@@G@@E OF OVERALL COUNTER ARRAY G$CTR:   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.       1 = COUNT JY
)@@G@@OF TOTAL NO BLOX (ALL KINDS EXCEPT BEGIN) @A@@@@.       2 = GLOBAL ADDREJZ
)@@G@@SS FLOAT    @A@@@@.       3 = ARG PUSHDOWN COUNTER    @C@@@@.       4 = KA
)@@G@@COUNTER OF TOTAL NO CALLS TO G$$TST @B@@@@.       5 = GLOBAL NESTING DEPKB
)@@G@@TH COUNTER  @D@@@@.       6 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASS 1   KC
)@@G@@@D@@@@.       7 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASS 2   @[@@@@.     KD
)@@G@@@D@@@@K DO     5 ,G$CTR*(K) EQU 0           . CLEAR COUNTERS@[@@@@.     KE
)@@G@@@G@@@@. NOW DEFINE SPECIAL THINGS DEPENDENT UPON WHICH ASSEMBLER PASS THKF
)@@G@@IS IS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*(6) EQU 1-G$CTR(6)            . SET FLAG: KG
)@@G@@ON IF ASSEMBLER PASS 1  @D@@@@G$CTR*(7) EQU      1-G$CTR(6)       . ON IKH
)@@G@@F PASS 2    @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , BRIEF                  . ON PASS 2, CLEKI
)@@G@@AN UP THE LISTING @D@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END                    . THEN GETKJ
)@@G@@ OUT  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. -------- PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND THIS POINT -------KK
)@@G@@-     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$MASM*   EQU       0=0=0           KL
)@@G@@  . 0=>@ASM, 1=>@MASM   @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,G$AMPR*    EQU      &(5)=-2 KM
)@@G@@. TRUE IF RELOCATION FUNC AVAILABLE @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,G$AMPR*   EQU   KN
)@@G@@    1     . IF MASM, WE HAVE A RELOCATION FUNCTION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@KO
)@@G@@          G$$CLD                      . DECLARE OUR 'CALL' PROC   @F@@@@KP
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM , $INSERT ;                . IF @MASM, FORGET ABOUT... @E@@@@KQ
)@@G@@   'G$$CLD* $DELETE','STRUC$DEF* $DELETE' . SOME OLD PROCS  @E@@@@ DO G$KR
)@@G@@UOM=1 , END    . STOP HERE IF NO NEED FOR DUMMY PROCS @F@@[@ DO (G$MASM=KS
)@@G@@0)**(G$AMPR=1) , END      . IF UOM ASM, FORGET PROCS  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@KT
)@@G@@P         PROC      *0,0              . DUMMY PROCS   @#@@@@RESUME** NAMKU
)@@G@@E     @#@@@@BRIEF**  NAME     @G@@@@         END                        KV
)@@G@@  . END OF DUMMY INTERNAL PROC DEFN @[@@@@.     @G@@@@          END     KW
)@@G@@                    . END DEFN OF MASTER MAGIC PROC   @ @@@@/. ***** DIAKX
)@@G@@GNOSTICS *****    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. FIELDS IN ERROR MESSAGKY
)@@G@@E FORM ARE: @C@@@@.    FIELD 1: TYPE OF CURRENTLY ACTIVE BLOCK    @E@@@@KZ
)@@G@@.             TYPES ARE 1=>BEGIN, 2=>IF, 3=>CASE, 4=>REPEAT @A@@@@.     LA
)@@G@@     2: CURRENT NESTING DEPTH @F@@@@.          3: MESSAGE CLASS (0=LOCN LB
)@@G@@CTR, 1=SYNTAX, 2=STRUCTURE)   @^@@@@.          4: ERROR TYPE@ @@@@.     LC
)@@G@@     5: ERROR SUBTYPE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LOCATION COUNTER ERRORS (MESLD
)@@G@@SAGE CLASS=0) ARE SIGNALLED WHEN    @E@@@@. SOME CODE PREVIOUS TO THE POLE
)@@G@@INT OF THE MESSAGE GENERATES  @F@@@@. A DIFFERENT NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONSLF
)@@G@@ ON ASSEMBLER PASSES ONE AND  @F@@@@. TWO (ASSEMBLER D-FLAG). AT THE POILG
)@@G@@NT OF DETECTION, STRUC$ WILL  @F@@@@. ATTEMPT TO FORESTALL SPURIOUS ERROLH
)@@G@@RS OF THIS TYPE IN THE CODE   @G@@@@. WHICH FOLLOWS BY FORCING THE LOCATLI
)@@G@@ION COUNTER TO WHAT IT BELIEVES     @F@@@@. THE CORRECT VALUE SHOULD BE.LJ
)@@G@@ THE ERROR TYPE AND SUBTYPE FIELDS  @F@@@@. ARE INTERNAL SERIAL NUMBERS,LK
)@@G@@ AND HAVE NO SPECIAL SIGNIFICANCE.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR SYNTAX ERRORLL
)@@G@@S (MESSAGE CLASS=1), ERROR TYPES AND SUBTYPES ARE:    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@LM
)@@G@@.    1,X => ERROR IN SPECIFICATION OF TEST@C@@@@.     ,01      UNRECOGNILN
)@@G@@ZEABLE TYPE OF TEST     @B@@@@.     ,02      UNRECOGNIZEABLE KEYWORD    LO
)@@G@@@B@@@@.    2,X => ERROR IN <VARY> SPECIFICATION @C@@@@.     ,01      OFFLP
)@@G@@SET REQUIRES IMMEDIATE 'BY'   @E@@@@.     ,02      LOOKFOR FORMAT REQUIRLQ
)@@G@@ES 'BY' SPECIFICATION   @D@@@@.     ,03      REQUIRED FROM, TO, OR BY SPLR
)@@G@@EC MISSING  @E@@@@.     ,04      LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE PASSES THROUGH ZELS
)@@G@@RO    @E@@@@.     ,05      SIGN OF BY CONFLICTS WITH SIGN OF TO-FROM    LT
)@@G@@@F@@@@.     ,06      EXPLICIT SENSE (UP/DOWN) CONFLICTS WITH BY, TO-FROMLU
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     ,07      REQUIRED 'BY' SPECIFICATION NOT GIVEN  @C@@@@.     LV
)@@G@@,010     BAD KEYWORD FOLLOWING 'LOOKFOR'  @G@@@@.     ,011     SPECIFIC LW
)@@G@@LOOP INSTR CONFLICTS WITH TO/FROM/BY/FOR SPEC   @ @@@@.    3,X => PARAMELX
)@@G@@TER ERROR   @D@@@@.     ,01      CASEREGISTER NOT OVERLAPPED (A0-A3)    LY
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     ,02      REQUIRED REGISTER SPECIFICATION MISSING@D@@@@.     LZ
)@@G@@,03      INCORRECT NUMBER OF FIELDS ON 'IF'     @D@@@@.     ,04      MISMA
)@@G@@SING 'WHEN' ON ESCAPE STATEMENT     @F@@@@.     ,05      MINIMUM SPECIFIMB
)@@G@@ED CASE NOT ZERO (CALLING OPTION)   @F@@@@.     ,06      ALL CASE VALUESMC
)@@G@@ NOT SPECIFIED (CALLING OPTION)     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FOR STRUCTURE ERMD
)@@G@@RORS (MESSAGE CLASS=2) , TYPES AND SUBTYPES ARE:@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.    1ME
)@@G@@,X => NESTING ERROR     @F@@@@.     ,01      TOO MANY OR TOO FEW END STAMF
)@@G@@TMENTS IN PREVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@@.     ,02      MISSING END IN PREVIOUS BLOMG
)@@G@@CK MAY CAUSE D-FLAGS    @E@@@@.     ,03      STATEMENT CANNOT APPEAR IN MH
)@@G@@CURRENT BLOCK TYPE@F@@@@.              EITHER THE END STATEMENT FOR THE MI
)@@G@@PREVIOUS BLOCK OR @G@@@@.              THE START STATEMENT FOR THE CURREMJ
)@@G@@NT BLOCK IS MISSING     @D@@@@.    2,X => INCONSISTENT LOGIC (STATEMENTSMK
)@@G@@ OR FIELDS) @G@@@@.     ,01      ESCAPE INVALID IF BOTH WHILE/LOOKFOR ANML
)@@G@@D UNTIL ARE GIVEN @E@@@@.     ,02      OTHERWISE STMNT MEANINGLESS, NO EMM
)@@G@@SCAPE GIVEN @F@@@@.     ,03      ATEND UNREACHABLE, NO TESTS APPEARED ONMN
)@@G@@ REPEAT     @F@@@@.     ,05      NOFIND CODE ILLEGAL WITH CALLING OPTIONMO
)@@G@@ (CASE)     @C@@@@.     ,06      REMOTE CALL TO NON-REMOTE BLOCK  @ @@@@MP
)@@G@@.    3,X => MISCELLANEOUS     @E@@@@.     ,01      ATTEMPT TO CHANGE LOCMQ
)@@G@@ATION COUNTERS WITHIN   @F@@@@.              A BLOCK. BLOCKS MUST BE WHOMR
)@@G@@LLY CONTAINED WITHIN    @F@@@@.              A SINGLE BANK. SWITCHING BEMS
)@@G@@TWEEN BANKS MUST BE     @D@@@@.              ACCOMPLISHED VIA A SUBROUTIMT
)@@G@@NE CALL     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          DEF     @H@@@@G$ERFO    FORM    MU
)@@G@@  3,6,3,12,12     . A DISTINCTIVE FORM FOR ERROR MESSAGES   @#@@@@P     MV
)@@G@@  PROC   *2 @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$GFL*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@MW
)@@G@@. FORCE DEFINITION OF PROC NEEDED TO FORCE G-FLAGS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@MX
)@@G@@          PROC    @#@@@@G$$FRG**  NAME    @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @#@@@@      MY
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. NOW G-FLAG GENERATOR ACTUALLY DOES ITS TMZ
)@@G@@HING  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ GO G$$FRG          . LEAP TO OTHER PROC, WHICH NA
)@@G@@LEAPS TO G$$DIA   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$IFL*  NAME       3   NB
)@@G@@              . THIS ENTRY FOR TRULY INVALID INSTRUCTION    @H@@@@      NC
)@@G@@    RES       1                 . WHICH ACTUALLY TAKES SPACE IN THE CODEND
)@@G@@@C@@@@ GO G$$DIA          . GO DISPLAY THE MESSAGE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@NE
)@@G@@G$$EFL*  NAME       1                 . GENERATE AN E-FLAG  @#@@@@A     NF
)@@G@@  EQU    +) @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$DFL*  NAME       0   NG
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$DFLG****                      . GENERATE A GLOBAL D-FLAG  @B@@@@NH
)@@G@@G$DFLG****          EQU               0 . @G@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , RES P(1,1)-NI
)@@G@@$             . THEN FORCE LC BACK INTO PHASE   @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@NJ
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@G$$TFL*  NAME       4                 . GENERATE A T-FLAG   NK
)@@G@@@A@@@@A       EQU    + (I$ 0,0,0,0,077,0) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOW WE GENNL
)@@G@@ERATE THE MESSAGES. TO AVOID EXTRANEOUS D-FLAGS ON    @E@@@@. THE USER'SNM
)@@G@@ LISTING, NEGATIVE RES'S ARE USED TO INSURE THAT@F@@@@. THE MESSAGES DO NN
)@@G@@NOT OCCUPY ANY SPACE IN THE PROGRAM'S ADDRESS   @F@@@@. SPACE. TO INSURENO
)@@G@@ THAT THE MESSAGE DOES NOT GO UNNOTICED, WE     @G@@@@. TRASH ON THE LASNP
)@@G@@T WORD OF GENERATED USER CODE, MAKING IT AN IOPR.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@NQ
)@@G@@. TO AVOID SURPRESSION IF BRIEF MODE IS ON, THE DIAGNOSTIC  @D@@@@. MESSNR
)@@G@@AGE SENTINAL WORD IS THE 1ST ONE GENERATED.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$DIANS
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . DIAGNOSTIC PRINTOUT STARTS HERE @H@@@@NT
)@@G@@          RES       -1                . GET RID OF USER'S LAST INSTRUCTINU
)@@G@@ON    @F@@@@K         EQU       1+(P(0,0)=0)      . SPEC TO FIND FLAGS INV
)@@G@@N     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . CURRENT NESTING LEVENW
)@@G@@L     @D@@@@          G$ERFO    G$TYPE(M),M,P(0,0),P(K,1),P(K,2)  @#@@@@NX
)@@G@@          UNLIST  @F@@@@          G$$IFLAG                    . MARK THINY
)@@G@@S ELEMENT IN ERROR@G@@@@          RES       -2                . PURGE SENZ
)@@G@@NTINAL AND IFLAG WORD   @H@@@@          +0                          . FOOA
)@@G@@RCE PROG TO IOPR IF ITS EXECUTED    @#@@@@          LIST    @E@@@@      OB
)@@G@@    END                         . OF DIAGNOSTIC PROCS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@OC
)@@G@@. THIS PROC DISPLAYS DEBUGGING INFORMATION WITHOUT AFFECTING@F@@@@. THE OD
)@@G@@GENERATED CODE. IT IS USED FOR DEBUGGING STRUC$ ITSELF.     @[@@@@.     OE
)@@G@@@ @@@@P          PROC     *999,0    @#@@@@G$DBUG*    NAME   @B@@@@I(1)  OF
)@@G@@     EQU      I(1)+1            .   @^@@@@ DO P(I(1))=0 , END     @ @@@@OG
)@@G@@ DO P(I(1))=1 , +P(I(1),1)    @A@@@@ DO P(I(1))=2 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2)OH
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO P(I(1))=3 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3)  @E@@@@ DO P(I(1))=OI
)@@G@@4 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3),P(I(1),4)    @H@@@@ DO P(I(1))>4 , +POJ
)@@G@@(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3),P(I(1),4),P(I(1),5),P(I(1),6)  @^@@@@      OK
)@@G@@     RES      -1  @B@@@@ DO I(1)<P , GO G$DBUG                  . @#@@@@OL
)@@G@@           END    @C@@@@/.    ******** PROGRAM DEFINITION GROUP ********OM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ARRAY USAGE BY BEGIN BLOCKS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    GON
)@@G@@$LABL(K,1) ENTRY POINT TO BLOCK (=PKT ADDR IF CONTINGENCY)  @B@@@@.     OO
)@@G@@        2) EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK    @E@@@@.             3) ADDR OF GENEROP
)@@G@@ATED REG SAVE AREA (IF ANY)   @E@@@@.             4) ADDR OF SIGNAL CELLOQ
)@@G@@ OR RETURN TARGET ADDR  @G@@@@.             5) ADDR OF BLOK EXIT INSTR (OR
)@@G@@AFTER REG RESTORE INSTRS)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    G$FLAG(K,1) XREG USOS
)@@G@@ED FOR SIGNALLING, ZERO IF NONE     @B@@@@.             2) NUMBER OF SAVOT
)@@G@@ED REGISTERS@C@@@@.             2,N) AXR$ VALUE OF N'TH SAVED REG @C@@@@OU
)@@G@@.             3) BLOCK TYPE (MAINPROG, ETC.)    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    GOV
)@@G@@$BSEQ(<X>) BLOK SEQ NO (I.E., K) WHERE <X> IS START ADDR    @[@@@@.     OW
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           OX
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *           BEOY
)@@G@@GIN             * @C@@@@.               *                             * OZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@PA
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@           DEF    @H@@@@F          FUNC         PB
)@@G@@              . ----- UTILITY FUNC USED IN SORTING    @#@@@@G$$INC*    NPC
)@@G@@AME   @D@@@@III*(1)    EQU              III(1)+1  . BUMP COUNTER  @E@@@@PD
)@@G@@           END              III(1)    . RETURN NEW VALUE    @[@@@@.     PE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *3 @]@@@@BEGIN*  NAME@G@@@@ DO (G$CTR(5PF
)@@G@@)=0)=0 , G$$GFL 1,1             . REQUIRE NESTING DEPTH ZERO@F@@@@M     PG
)@@G@@    EQU       1                 . FORCE NEW NESTING DEPTH   @D@@@@G$CTR*PH
)@@G@@(5) EQU  M                      . THEN SAVE IT  @F@@@@ DO (G$CTR(2)=0)=0PI
)@@G@@ , G$$GFL 1,2             . REQUIRE NO FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@K     PJ
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SERIAL NUMBER   @D@@@@G$CTR*PK
)@@G@@(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @D@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU    PL
)@@G@@  1                 . SET BLOCK TYPE@E@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K         PM
)@@G@@        . SAVE SERIAL NUMBER  @F@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,G$BSEQ*($) EQU      K PN
)@@G@@  . SERIAL # INDEXED BY STARTA@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,G$BSEQ*($AP($)) EQU K PO
)@@G@@  . SERIAL # INDEXED BY STARTADR    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@T         EQU  P(1PP
)@@G@@,1)+(P(1)=0)*MAINPROGRAM . GET PROG TYPE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU T      PQ
)@@G@@               . AND REMEMBER IT    @E@@@@ISSUB      EQU      (T=SUBROUTPR
)@@G@@INE)++(T=LIJSUB)++(T=LDJSUB)  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ALLOW 'NOSAVE' TO DEFAPS
)@@G@@ULT TO SUBFIELD 2 @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NOSDEF    EQU       ISSUB**(P(1)=2)*PT
)@@G@@*(P(1,2)=NOSAVE) . NOSAVE DEFAULT   @E@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE PU
)@@G@@        . FORCE THIRD FIELD   @D@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,2) EQU 0            PV
)@@G@@  . CLEAR REGISTER@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO NOSDEF ,P(1)   EQU 3 . NOW NOTPW
)@@G@@E THERE ARE 3 SUBFIELDS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,1)PX
)@@G@@=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $           . SAPY
)@@G@@VE ENTRY POINT TO BLOK  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       G$CTR(6)  PZ
)@@G@@        . ALLOW ZERO AS A FLAG@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0-G$CTR(7)      QA
)@@G@@  . SET GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO T=CYCLIC , END            QB
)@@G@@     . SINCE CYCLICS NEVER EXIT, WE'RE DONE     @G@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY QC
)@@G@@, +0D               . IF CONTING, GENERATE PACKET     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@QD
)@@G@@.              HANDLE EXITS WHICH SIGNAL THE EXEC (MAIN/CONTINGENCY)    QE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@GI      EQU    (P(1,1)=SIGNAL)+2*(P(2,1)=SIGNAL)+3*(P(QF
)@@G@@3,1)=SIGNAL)@F@@@@. SIGNAL XREG IS FLAG, IF NONE (<0), THEN EXIT WILL BEQG
)@@G@@ 'NORMAL'   @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU (GI>0)*(P(1,2)+(P(1)<2)*A0)-(GI=0) . QH
)@@G@@SET SIGNAL XREG   @F@@@@ DO (T=REMOTESUB)=0                     ; IF NOTQI
)@@G@@ A REMOTE SUB     @F@@@@   ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU                  ; DEFAULT QJ
)@@G@@RETURN JUMPTARGET @G@@@@      (T=CONTINGENCY)*G$LABL(K,1)-ISSUB . TO PACQK
)@@G@@KET OR -1 FLAG VALUE    @G@@@@ DO (T=EXECSUB)**(P(1)=1)             ; IFQL
)@@G@@ EXECSUB BUT NO RETURN ADDR   @F@@@@   ,P(1,2) EQU DISP                 QM
)@@G@@  . FORCE STD RETURN ADDR     @G@@@@ DO T=EXECSUB ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU P(1,QN
)@@G@@2) . JUMPTARGET FOR EXEC ROUTINES   @G@@@@ DO GI>0 , DO P(GI)>1 ,G$LABL*QO
)@@G@@(K,4) EQU ;  UNLESS USER PROVIDED A USPEC @G@@@@        +      (I$ 0,P(GQP
)@@G@@I,4),,P(GI,3),2*P(GI,*3)+P(GI,*2),P(GI,2) )     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.     QQ
)@@G@@         HANDLE REGISTER SAVE REQUESTS    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO ISSUB**(QR
)@@G@@P(1,2)=0) ,P(1,2) EQU X11 . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11    @H@@@@SII     EQU QS
)@@G@@   ((P(1,1)=STACK)++(P(1,1)=SAVE))+; FIND REG SAVE CONTROL FIELD  @G@@@@QT
)@@G@@2*((P(2,1)=STACK)++(P(2,1)=SAVE))+3*((P(3,1)=STACK)++(P(3,1)=SAVE))     QU
)@@G@@@F@@@@SI      EQU    SII+(SII=0)*ISSUB      . IF NONE**SUBROUTINE, SET 1QV
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO SI=0 ,  END                       . IF NONE, WE'RE DONE @[@@@@QW
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@ST      EQU    P(SI,1)                . ELSE GET TYPE (SAVE/QX
)@@G@@STACK/SUBRTNE)    @H@@@@ DO ISSUB=0                           ; IF NOT AQY
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE TO START WITH     @G@@@@    ,P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE              QZ
)@@G@@  . OBVIOUSLY NO LINKREG TO BE SAVED@D@@@@I DO 3 ,Q(I) EQU P(I)         RA
)@@G@@        . COPY LEAVES   @G@@@@NOLINK    EQU       P(1,3)=NOSAVE     . ONRB
)@@G@@=> INHIBIT SAVE OF LINKREG    @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,P(1,2) EQU -P(1,2)      RC
)@@G@@  . IF NOT SAVING, JUST REMEMBER IT @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,Q(1) EQU +2       RD
)@@G@@        . AND FORCE THE NOSAVE SPEC AWAY  @H@@@@KLX     EQU    Q(SI)-2*(RE
)@@G@@ST=STACK)     . INDEX OF LAST REG TO EXPLICITLY SAVE  @H@@@@I DO KLX ,RSRF
)@@G@@AV(P(SI,I+1)**0777777) EQU 1 . MARK ALL REGS REQUESTED EXPLICITLY @H@@@@RG
)@@G@@III(1)     EQU      1       . INIT INCREMENTATION CTR: 1ST SUBFIELD WILLRH
)@@G@@ BE 2 @F@@@@I DO 128 , DO RSAV(I) ,P(SI,G$$INC(1)) EQU I . SORT EXPLICITRI
)@@G@@ REGS @H@@@@ DO KLX<Q(SI) , DO (P(SI,KLX+1)=POINTER)=0 , G$$EFL 3,2 . RERJ
)@@G@@QUIRE REG SPEC    @H@@@@SEX        EQU      (ST=SUBROUTINE)++(ST=LIJSUB)RK
)@@G@@++(ST=LDJSUB)=0 . ON IF SAVE G@H@@@@SLI        EQU      ISSUB           RL
)@@G@@  . ON IF LINKREG SHOULD BE REMEMBERED    @G@@@@ DO SEX**SLI ,P(SI,KLX+1RM
)@@G@@) EQU P(1,2)  . FORCE LINKREG INTO SAVE LIST    @G@@@@KLR     EQU    KLXRN
)@@G@@+(SEX**SLI)         . INDEX OF LAST REG TO REMEMBER   @H@@@@I DO     KLRRO
)@@G@@-1 ,G$FLAG*(K,2,I) EQU +P(SI,I+1) . REMEMBER WHATS BEING SAVED    @I@@@@RP
)@@G@@KL        EQU       KLR-(NOLINK*(1-(T=EXECSUB))) . NUMBER TO ACTUALLY PURQ
)@@G@@T IN COR    @I@@@@I DO KL-1 ,FNC(I) EQU 1+5*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+3*(G$FLAGRR
)@@G@@(K,2,I)>A15) . SA, SX, SR     @G@@@@I DO KL-1 ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-RS
)@@G@@A0*(FNC(I)=1)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=4)     @H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)=1 ,FNC(IRT
)@@G@@) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE STORE A'S    @F@@@@  (070*(AFL(I+1)=ARU
)@@G@@FL(I)+1)+1) . DOUBLE STORE CONTIGUOUS AREGS     @G@@@@ DO ST=STACK , GO RV
)@@G@@G$$B10              . IF STACKING, GO DO SPECIAL STUFF@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0RW
)@@G@@ ,IC      EQU    &        . PRESERVE USER'S LOCATION COUNTER@G@@@@ DO G$RX
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,IC      EQU    $LCN     . IC IS CURRENT LOCATION COUNTER  @F@@@@RY
)@@G@@$(G$LCTR(1))                          . AND ESTABLISH OUR OWN     @G@@@@RZ
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&=IC)**(KL>1) , J $+KL    . IF =, LEAP AROUND THE RESSA
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($LCN=IC)**(KL>1) , J $+KL . IF =, LEAP AROUND TSB
)@@G@@HE RES@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU    $                 . START OF REG SAVE ARSC
)@@G@@EA (IF ANY) @E@@@@             RES    KL-1              . SET ASIDE SAVESD
)@@G@@ SPACE@E@@@@$(IC)                                 . RESTORE USER'S IC   SE
)@@G@@@H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)>0 , I$ FNC(I),012*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LASF
)@@G@@BL(K,3)+I-1 @G@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . IF NOT STACKINSG
)@@G@@G, WE'RE DONE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$$B10* NAME                        SH
)@@G@@  . HANDLE STACKING HERE@F@@@@OI      EQU    P(SI+1,1)=OFFSET       . ONSI
)@@G@@ IF OFFSET SPECIFIED    @H@@@@AI      EQU    P(SI,*KLX+2)           . ONSJ
)@@G@@ TO AUTO-INCREMENT STACK POINTER    @G@@@@OSV     EQU    + (I$ 0,OI*P(SISK
)@@G@@+1,3),0,P(SI,KLX+2),2*AI,OI*P(SI+1,2))    @C@@@@I DO  KL-1 , S G$FLAG(K,SL
)@@G@@2,I),OSV+(1-AI)*(I-1)   @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU 0-OSV                  . SM
)@@G@@REMEMBER OFFSET FLAGS   @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@SN
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * SO
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *          ENDBEG   SP
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@SQ
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     SR
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@ENDBEG*  NAME     @G@@@@M         EQU     SS
)@@G@@  G$CTR(5)          . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @H@@@@K         EQST
)@@G@@U       G$SEQN(M)         . GET OVERALL BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER     @F@@@@SU
)@@G@@ DO (M=1)=0 , G$$GFL 1,1         . BE SURE NESTING LEVEL IS OK    @D@@@@SV
)@@G@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=1)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . AND BLOCK TYPE     @I@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQSW
)@@G@@U       0                 . FORCE NESTING LEVEL FOR SUBSEQUENT CODE     SX
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO (G$CTR(2)=(0-G$CTR(7)))=0 , G$$GFL 1,2 . DIAGNOSE BAD FLOAT   SY
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0                 . AND FORCE IT CORRECT@E@@@@SZ
)@@G@@T         EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)       . GET BEGIN BLOCK TYPE@[@@@@.     TA
)@@G@@@E@@@@          RES       0-G$CTR(6)        . FIXUP FOR FLAGS     @E@@@@TB
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,2)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,2)    @D@@@@G$LABLTC
)@@G@@*(K,2)  EQU   $           . MARK END OF BLOCK   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO T=TD
)@@G@@CYCLIC , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . IF CYCLIC, LOOP BACK    @D@@@@ DO T=TE
)@@G@@CYCLIC , END                 . AND THAT'S ALL   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. IF ATF
)@@G@@NY REGS WERE SAVED, RESTORE THEM    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)=0 TG
)@@G@@, GO G$$X01 @H@@@@NRR     EQU    +G$FLAG(K,2)              . GET NO OF RTH
)@@G@@EGISTERS REMEMBERED     @G@@@@LINK(1)   EQU       G$FLAG(K,2,NRR)   . LITI
)@@G@@NK IS ALWAYS THE LAST ONE     @H@@@@NR        EQU       NRR-(LINK(1)<0) TJ
)@@G@@  . FUDGE IN CASE WE DIDN'T SAVE LINK     @G@@@@ DO NRR>NR ,LINK(1) EQU TK
)@@G@@-LINK(1)      . THEN GET REAL VALUE OF LINK     @G@@@@I DO NR ,FNC(I) EQTL
)@@G@@U 010+017*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+013*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)>A15)  @G@@@@I DO NR ,AFLTM
)@@G@@(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=010)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=023)   @H@@@@I DO NTN
)@@G@@R , DO FNC(I)=010 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE LOAD A'S     TO
)@@G@@@F@@@@  (061*(AFL(I+1)=AFL(I)+1)+010) . DOUBLE LOAD CONTIGUOUS AREGS    TP
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,SR      EQU    0-G$LABL(K,3) . GET STACKREG/SAVE FLATQ
)@@G@@G     @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,SR      EQU    $AP(0-G$LABL(K,3)) . GET STACKRTR
)@@G@@EG/SAVE FLAG@ @@@@ DO (SR>0)=0 ,I DO NR , ;     @G@@@@  DO FNC(I)>0 , I$TS
)@@G@@ FNC(I),013*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-1     @F@@@@ DO (SR>0)=0TT
)@@G@@ , GO G$$X01              . IF NOT STACKED, WE'RE DONE@#@@@@. HANDLE STATU
)@@G@@CKING @F@@@@INC     EQU    SR**0400000            . ISOLATE AUTO-INCREMETV
)@@G@@NT BIT@F@@@@XSR     EQU    (017000000**SR)*/4     . MOVE XREG INTO AREG TW
)@@G@@FIELD @F@@@@ DO INC>0 , ANX,U 0,NR+(017000000**SR)*/4 . BACK UP STACK POTX
)@@G@@INTER @F@@@@I DO     NR , L G$FLAG(K,2,I),(SR**007777177777)+I-1 . AND UTY
)@@G@@NSTACK@F@@@@G$$X01* NAME                          . END OF REG RESTORATITZ
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $                 . MARK POSUA
)@@G@@N OF EXIT INSTR   @F@@@@ DO T=LIJSUB , I$ 07,013,LINK(1),LINK(1),,0 . LIUB
)@@G@@J LINK,0,LINK     @F@@@@ DO T=LDJSUB , I$ 07,012,LINK(1),LINK(1),,0 . LDUC
)@@G@@J LINK,0,LINK     @ @@@@ DO T=SUBROUTINE , J 0,LINK(1)@C@@@@ DO (T=EXECSUD
)@@G@@UB)++(T=REMOTESUB) , J G$LABL(K,4)  @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,5) , END       UE
)@@G@@        . QUIT IF ANY OF THE ABOVE  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. PROCESS MAINPROGUF
)@@G@@S AND CONTINGENCIES     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@XREG    EQU    G$FLAG(K,1)    UG
)@@G@@        . GET EXIT TYPE (NORMAL OR SIGNAL)@G@@@@ DO XREG>0 , GO G$$X02  UH
)@@G@@              . IF EXCEPTION, GO PROCESS IT     @G@@@@ DO T=MAINPROGRAM UI
)@@G@@, ER EXIT$          . NORMAL MAINPROGRAM EXIT IS EXIT$@E@@@@ DO T=CONTINUJ
)@@G@@GENCY , SZ,H1 G$LABL(K,4) . CLEAR PACKET UPPER  @F@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY UK
)@@G@@, I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . AND JUMP THRU PKT @G@@@@ DO 1 , END       UL
)@@G@@                    . THAT'S ALL FOR NORMAL EXITS     @H@@@@G$$X02* NAMEUM
)@@G@@                          . HERE TO HANDLE EXITS WITH SIGNALLING  @F@@@@UN
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 051,H1,,,,G$LABL(K,4) . IS UPPER (H1) ZERO @G@@@@UO
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . YES, EXIT THRU PACKET   UP
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (G$LABL(K,4)<0)=0 , LX XREG,G$LABL(K,4) . LOAD FUQ
)@@G@@ROM SIGNALLOC     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM , DO $AP(G$LABL(K,4))>=0 , LX XREG,G$UR
)@@G@@LABL(K,4) . LOAD FROM SIGNALLOC     @F@@@@        I$     074,04,,XREG,,$US
)@@G@@+1      . JUMP INTO FOLLOWING TABLE @C@@@@        ER     011            UT
)@@G@@        . 0=EXIT$ @C@@@@        ER     040                    . 1=ERR$  UU
)@@G@@@C@@@@        ER     026                    . 2=EABT$ @C@@@@        ER  UV
)@@G@@   012                    . 3=ABORT$@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@UW
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     UX
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       UY
)@@G@@  SWITCHTO            * @C@@@@.               *                         UZ
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     VA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@SWITCHTO*  NAME   @[@@@@.     VB
)@@G@@@D@@@@. NOTE: THIS FEATURE IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE BECAUSE OF@E@@@@. OPTIVC
)@@G@@MIZATION TECHNIQUES FOR THE OBJECT CODE. ANY BLOCK    @E@@@@. MUST BE WHVD
)@@G@@OLLY GENERATED UNDER A SINGLE LOCATION COUNTER. @F@@@@. CONTINGENCY PROCVE
)@@G@@ESSING IN A SEPERATE BANK MUST BE ACCOMPLISHED  @D@@@@. BY MEANS OF A SUVF
)@@G@@BROUTINE CALL TO THE OTHER BANK.    @[@@@@.     @I@@@@          RES     VG
)@@G@@  1                 . SPACE SO DIAGNOSTIC DOESN'T CREAM OLD US    @D@@@@VH
)@@G@@          G$$GFL    3,1               . GIVE A WARNING@H@@@@          REVI
)@@G@@S       -1                . ZAP THE IOPR SO THE PROGRAM WORKS     @G@@@@VJ
)@@G@@. NOTE THAT WE SIMPLY IGNORE THE REQUEST FOR A LOCATION COUNTER CHANGE  VK
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********VL
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         VM
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           BASE              * @C@@@@.     VN
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********VO
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@P          PROC   VP
)@@G@@  *1                .  SPECS:  IBANK\DBANK(,<USPEC FOR BDI>)@E@@@@BASE* VQ
)@@G@@     NAME                       . MAKE A BANK VISIBLE @F@@@@XREG       EVR
)@@G@@QU      P(0,1)+X11*(P(0,1)=0) . XREG USED FOR LINKAGE @E@@@@. THE FOLLOWVS
)@@G@@ING THREE LINES ARE COURTESY OF ISAAC BORNSTEIN.@E@@@@. THEY FIX A BUG IVT
)@@G@@NVOLVING THE LOAD OF THE BDI (LXI,LDJ)    @F@@@@          DO P(1)<2 , GOVU
)@@G@@ NOLXI . IF ONLY 1 PARAM, NO LXI IS NEEDED@H@@@@ DO P(1,4)<016 , I$ 046,VV
)@@G@@P(1,4),XREG,P(1,3),2*P(1,*3)+P(1,*2),P(1,2) . LXI BDI @G@@@@ DO P(1,4)>0VW
)@@G@@15 , G$$IMU 046,P(1,4),XREG,P(1,3),P(1,2) . LXI,U/XU BDI    @^@@@@NOLXI VX
)@@G@@    NAME      .   @F@@@@           I$       07,012+(P(1,1)=IBANK),XREG,,VY
)@@G@@,$+1 . DO LIJ/LDJ @#@@@@           END    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@VZ
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * WA
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *            CALL   WB
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@WC
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     WD
)@@G@@@G@@@@          PROC      *0                . PROC TO DECLARE THE 'CALL'WE
)@@G@@ PROC @E@@@@. PREVENTS RLIB$ ENTRY POINT CONFLICTS WITH COBOL'S 'CALL'  WF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@G$$CLD*   NAME                        .   @[@@@@.     WG
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @B@@@@CALL*** NAME                          .   WH
)@@G@@@G@@@@RAD(1)    EQU       +(0,-1)           . ASSUME NOT CALLING RMT BLOWI
)@@G@@K     @F@@@@P11       EQU       P(1,1)            . P11 IS ADDRESS OF TAWJ
)@@G@@RGET  @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P11 EQU $AP(P11)        . IF MASM, USE ONLY ABWK
)@@G@@SOLUTE PART @E@@@@ DO P(1)=1                            ; IF ONLY ONE FIWL
)@@G@@ELD   @E@@@@   , DO P11<0400000                   ; AND IT ISN'T EQUF'D WM
)@@G@@@E@@@@      ,RAD(1) EQU P11                 . GET ITS ACTUAL ADDR @F@@@@WN
)@@G@@K          EQU      G$BSEQ(RAD(1))    . GET SEQUENCE NO OF BLOK   @G@@@@WO
)@@G@@ DO K>0                               ; IF BLOCK HAS BEEN PROCESSED...  WP
)@@G@@@E@@@@   , DO G$FLAG(K,3)=REMOTESUB         ; AND IT'S REMOTE     @F@@@@WQ
)@@G@@      , GO G$$CL1                     . GO TREAT IT SPECIALLY     @[@@@@WR
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@XREG    EQU    P(0,1)+(P(0,1)=0)*X11  . DEFAULT LINKREG TO XWS
)@@G@@11    @G@@@@BANKSW     EQU      P(2,1)=BASING     . ON IF WE SHOULD SWITWT
)@@G@@CH BANKS    @G@@@@K DO P(2)*(1-BANKSW) , SZ P(2,K) . CLEAR ALT EXIT SENTWU
)@@G@@INALS, IF ANY     @E@@@@. THE FOLLOWING THREE LINES ARE COURTESY OF ISAAWV
)@@G@@C BORNSTEIN.@E@@@@. THEY FIX A BUG INVOLVING THE LOAD OF THE BDI (LXI,LDWW
)@@G@@J)    @I@@@@          DO 1-(BANKSW**(P(2)>2)) , GO NOLXI . IF ONLY 1 PARWX
)@@G@@AM, NO LXI IS NEEDED    @H@@@@ DO P(2,5)<016 , I$ 046,P(2,5),XREG,P(2,4)WY
)@@G@@,2*P(2,*4)+P(2,*3),P(2,3) . LXI BDI @G@@@@ DO P(2,5)>015 , G$$IMU 046,P(WZ
)@@G@@2,5),XREG,P(2,4),P(2,3) . LXI,U/XU BDI    @^@@@@NOLXI     NAME      .   XA
)@@G@@@D@@@@FUN        EQU      074-BANKSW*065    . LMJ OR LIJ/LDJ@H@@@@JAY   XB
)@@G@@     EQU      013-BANKSW*(P(2,2)=DBANK) . 013 UNLESS LDJ (THEN 012)     XC
)@@G@@@F@@@@           I$       FUN,JAY,XREG,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) .XD
)@@G@@@I@@@@K DO     P(2)*(1-BANKSW) , SX XREG,P(2,K)        . SET ALT EXIT SEXE
)@@G@@NTINALS, IF ANY   @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$CL1***  NAME   XF
)@@G@@                    . HERE FOR CALLS TO REMOTE BLOX   @F@@@@           JXG
)@@G@@        P(1,1)            . FLYING LEAP TO THE BLOCK  @F@@@@           GXH
)@@G@@$$PRB   K,$               . PATCH ITS RETURN ADDR     @H@@@@          ENXI
)@@G@@D                         . END OF THE ACTUAL 'CALL' PROC DEFN    @G@@@@XJ
)@@G@@          END                         . END OF PROC WHICH DEFINES 'CALL'XK
)@@G@@@C@@@@/.           ******    IF   GROUP    *******    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@XL
)@@G@@. USE OF LABELS AND FLAGS --  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.       G$FLXM
)@@G@@AG(K,1) EXPLICIT NOT FLAG     @E@@@@.                2) SIDE EFFECT AND XN
)@@G@@'IF' TEST INVERSION FLAG@B@@@@.                3) IMPLIED LINEITEM FLAG XO
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                4) FLOAT ADJUSTMENT CAUSED BY 'ELSE' @F@@@@.     XP
)@@G@@           5) FLOAT CAUSED BY OPTIMIZATION OF 'IF' TEST     @B@@@@.     XQ
)@@G@@           6) COMPLEX CONDITION FLAG@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1XR
)@@G@@) START ADDR OF TESTS AT 'IF' @E@@@@.                2) START ADDR OF USXS
)@@G@@ER CODE IN 'IF' BLOCK   @D@@@@.                3) END ADDR OF CODE IN 'IXT
)@@G@@F' BLOCK    @D@@@@.                4) START ADDR OF CODE IN 'ELSE' BLOCKXU
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                5) TARGET ADDR FOR EXIT FROM BLOCK   @[@@@@.     XV
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           XW
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *            IXX
)@@G@@F               * @C@@@@.               *                             * XY
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@XZ
)@@G@@P       PROC   *6 @]@@@@IF*     NAME@[@@@@.     @H@@@@LOOF      EQU     YA
)@@G@@  (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=LOOKFOR) . CHECK FOR TABLE SEARCH FORMAT@^@@@@ DO LOYB
)@@G@@OF , GO G$$I05    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ANALYZE SYNTAX SO WE KNOW IF THIS YC
)@@G@@IS LINEITEM OR A BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@L       EQU    P-1@B@@@@L1    YD
)@@G@@  EQU    (P(L)=1)**(P(L,1)=THEN)    @B@@@@L2      EQU    (P(L-1)=1)**(P(YE
)@@G@@L-1,1)=THEN)@E@@@@FLT     EQU    L1*L+L2*(L-1)  . FIELD OF 'THEN' OR ZERYF
)@@G@@O     @E@@@@THF     EQU    FLT+(FLT=0)*P  . IF NOT GIVEN, ASSUME IT     YG
)@@G@@@F@@@@IFNOT     EQU       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=NOT) . SET EXPLICIT NOT FLAGYH
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO (THF=IFNOT+2)++(THF=IFNOT+4)=0 , G$$EFL 3,3 . CHECK NO OF FIELYI
)@@G@@DS    @F@@@@CXF       EQU       THF=IFNOT+4     . SET COMPLEX CONDITION YJ
)@@G@@FLAG  @E@@@@ DO P<THF+2 , GO G$$I05               . GO DO NORMAL FORMAT YK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. LINEITEM FORMAT DOES NOT UPDATE NESTING ARRAYS- GETSYL
)@@G@@ SPECIAL HANDLING @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$TST    1+IFNOT,CXF,IFNOYM
)@@G@@T . GENERATE THE TEST   @E@@@@          +P(THF+1,1)                 . THYN
)@@G@@EN THE LINEITEM   @A@@@@   DO 1 , END       . AND THEN QUIT @[@@@@.     YO
)@@G@@@B@@@@. PROCESS NORMAL (NOT LINEITEM) IF --     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I05YP
)@@G@@*   NAME    @H@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUYQ
)@@G@@ENCE NO FOR THIS BLOCK  @F@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . ANYR
)@@G@@D UPDATE BLOCK COUNTER  @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUYS
)@@G@@MP CURRENT BLOCK NESTING LEVEL@G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        YT
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@G$TYPE*(M)          EQU       YU
)@@G@@        2 . SET CURRENT BLOCKTYPE TO IF   @H@@@@G$SEQN*(M)          EQU YV
)@@G@@              K . AND REMEMBER ITS SEQUENCE NUMBER    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@YW
)@@G@@. ADJUST ALL LABELS FOR FLOAT @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,1) EQU G$LABL(YX
)@@G@@K,1)+G$CTR(2) . GLOBAL FLOAT  @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(YY
)@@G@@K,5) . APPLY 'IF' FLOAT @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+GYZ
)@@G@@$CTR(2) . GLOBAL+IF     @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+3) EQU G$LABL(K,N+3)+GZA
)@@G@@$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,4)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@  DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,1ZB
)@@G@@)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)   @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $        . REMEMZC
)@@G@@BER START ADDR FOR OPTIMIZATION     @H@@@@ DO LOOF , GO G$$I10          ZD
)@@G@@        . LOOKFOR TESTS GET SPECIAL HANDLING    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NOGEN ZE
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(7)*(G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,1)) . ON TO SURPRESS ALL   ZF
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU G$CTR(4)+NOGEN           . KEEP G$$TST'S COUNTER IN ZG
)@@G@@PHASE @A@@@@ DO NOGEN , END     . STOP IF NO MO @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAGZH
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU IFNOT            . SAVE NOT FLAG FOR OPTIMIZER   @E@@@@G$FLAGZI
)@@G@@*(K,6) EQU CXF              . AND ALSO COMPLEX FLAG   @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)ZJ
)@@G@@ , G$$SVA              . PASS 1: SAVE ARGS FOR RECALL AT ENDIF    @[@@@@ZK
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSAZL
)@@G@@L FLAG@F@@@@LIG       EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     . SET IMPLIED LINEITEM FZM
)@@G@@LAG   @G@@@@ DO 1-LIG ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF G$LABL(K,4)  . GENERATEZN
)@@G@@ THE TEST   @H@@@@ DO LIG  ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      . GENERATE LIZO
)@@G@@NE ITEM FORMAT TEST(S)  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU SIDE(1)               . RZP
)@@G@@EMEMBER IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         ZQ
)@@G@@. REMEMBER START OF USER CODE FOR OPTIMIZA@#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@ZR
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE 'LOOKFOR' TESTS, WHICH GENERATE 1100 SERIES SEARCH ZS
)@@G@@INSTRUCTIONS@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I10*   NAME    @A@@@@ DO (P(3,1)=VARY)=ZT
)@@G@@0 , G$$EFL 2,010 .@I@@@@VI        EQU       3                 . 'VARY' SZU
)@@G@@PECIFICATION MUST FOLLOW 'LOOKFO    @E@@@@P(3,1)    EQU       LOOKFOR   ZV
)@@G@@        . FORCE THE KEYWORD   @G@@@@KW(1)     EQU       LOOKFOR         ZW
)@@G@@  . IN ALL PLACES ITS EXPECTED TO BE@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         ZX
)@@G@@         . GUARANTEE NON-EMPTY 'IF' CLAUSE@H@@@@          G$$LAN        ZY
)@@G@@              . ANALYZE SPECS, LOAD REGS IF NECESSARY @G@@@@          G$ZZ
)@@G@@$LGE    3,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,4),1 . GEN CODE FOR SEARCH   @F@@@@G$CTR*AA
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)+G$CTR(6)       . PRETEND WE SAVED THE ARGS @[@@@@.     AB
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********AC
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         AD
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           ELSE              * @C@@@@.     AE
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********AF
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@        PROC   *0 @]@@@@ELSE* AG
)@@G@@  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING AH
)@@G@@LEVEL @F@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQ NUM FOR THISAI
)@@G@@ BLOCK@F@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=2)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3        . CATCH NESTING ERROAJ
)@@G@@RS    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,3)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LAK
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) .  @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU   $                       . MARK ENDAL
)@@G@@ OF 'IF' CLAUSE   @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)=$ , END . EMPTY 'IF' => IGNORE EAM
)@@G@@LSE COMPLETELY    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@     DO G$FLAG(K,4)=0 , I$     074,0AN
)@@G@@4,,,,G$LABL(K,5) . LEAP TO ENDI     @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(AO
)@@G@@K,4) . SET ELSE FLOAT FOR CODE BELOW@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)  EQU   $ . MARK SAP
)@@G@@TART OF 'ELSE' USER CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@AQ
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * AR
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           ENDIF   AS
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@AT
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@      AU
)@@G@@  PROC   *0 @]@@@@ENDIF*  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        AV
)@@G@@  . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)       AW
)@@G@@  . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @F@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=2)=0 , G$$GFL 1AX
)@@G@@,3          . CATCH NESTING ERRORS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO AY
)@@G@@(G$LABL(K,5)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,5)    @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $   AZ
)@@G@@      . MARK END OF BLOCK     @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1             BA
)@@G@@  . STEP NESTING BACK ONE LEVEL     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. RESTORE GLOBAL FBB
)@@G@@LOAT FOR FOLLOWING BLOX (EFFECTIVE ON PASS 2 ONLY)    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BC
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(7)*(G$CTR(2)-G$FLAG(K,5)-G$FLAG(K,4)) . @E@@@@ DO G$BD
)@@G@@CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE AT THIS POINT    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@BE
)@@G@@.   ***** PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND THIS POINT *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*BF
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)-1              . ADJUST ARGSAVE STACK POINTER    @[@@@@BG
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. TABULATE FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED ELSE, IF ANY    @[@@@@.     BH
)@@G@@@H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU 0-((G$LABL(K,3)>0)**(G$LABL(K,4)=$)) . 'ELSE' FLOBI
)@@G@@AT (NO -0!!)@G@@@@          RES       G$FLAG(K,4)     . APPLY ELSFLOAT FBJ
)@@G@@OR SUCCEEDING CODE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CHECK FOR SURPRESSION OF EVERYTHINBK
)@@G@@G (NO CODE AND NO SIDE EFFECTS)     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO ($>G$LABL(K,2)BL
)@@G@@)++G$FLAG(K,2) , GO G$$I20 . IF NOT, GO CHECK OPTIMIZATION  @E@@@@G$FLAGBM
)@@G@@*(K,5) EQU G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2) . TURN OFF 'IF'    @F@@@@          REBN
)@@G@@S       G$LABL(K,1)-$   . ADJUST L.C. APPROPRIATELY   @C@@@@  DO 1 , ENDBO
)@@G@@        . AND TERMINATE GRACEFULLY  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CHECK FOR POSSIBBP
)@@G@@LE OPTIMIZATION OF THE INITIAL TEST @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I20*   NAME    BQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU $ . IF NO ELSE, PUT IT HERE   BR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU G$LABL(K,3)=G$LABL(K,2) . NO 'IF' CLABS
)@@G@@USE =>INVERT@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU    $-G$LABL(K,2)=1   . IMPLIED LINEITBT
)@@G@@EM    @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)++G$FLAG(K,3)=0 , END . DONE IF NO OPTIMIZATIBU
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WE'RE GOING TO OPTIMIZE THE JUMP WHEN WE GET BBV
)@@G@@ACK THERE ON PASS 2     @F@@@@. TO INSURE THAT LABELS BELOW THIS POINT ABW
)@@G@@RE OK, WE MUST PERFORCE @E@@@@. DO A TRIAL GENERATION OF THE MODIFIED TEBX
)@@G@@ST SO WE KNOW     @G@@@@. HOW MANY INSTRUCTIONS IT WILL TAKE WHEN WE GENBY
)@@G@@ IT BACK AT THE TOP     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@KK        EQU       G$CTR(3)+1BZ
)@@G@@        . GET ARGSAVE INDEX OF MATCHING 'IF'    @F@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,JCA
)@@G@@ DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J)    @E@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,JCB
)@@G@@ DO G$ARGS(KK,I)    ; FOR ALL SUBFIELDS   @F@@@@  , DO G$ARGS(KK,I,*J) ,CC
)@@G@@P(I,J) EQU *P(I,J) . PRESERVE ASTERISKS   @A@@@@IFNOT     EQU       G$FLCD
)@@G@@AG(K,1)     @F@@@@CXF       EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)   . RETRIEVE COMPLEX CCE
)@@G@@ONDN FLAG   @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL RCF
)@@G@@EVERSAL FLAG@E@@@@START                 . REMEMBER WHERE BEGINNING OF TECG
)@@G@@ST WAS@D@@@@ DO 1-G$FLAG(K,3) , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF $+10 .     @D@@@@CH
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)   , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      .     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQCI
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(4)-1        . RESTORE INTERNAL CTR USED BY G$$TST   @[@@@@CJ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. NOW SET ADDRESS ADJUSTMENT FLAGS SO PASS 2 WILL GEN PROPERCK
)@@G@@ CODE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SIZE      EQU       G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . SICL
)@@G@@ZE OF ORIGINAL TEST     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU $-START-SIZE       . COMPCM
)@@G@@UTE PASS 2 FLOAT  @H@@@@          RES      0-SIZE            . COMPENSATCN
)@@G@@E L.C. FOR CODE WHICH FOLLOWS @]@@@@        END @B@@@@/.          ******CO
)@@G@@** CASE GROUP  *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. ARRAY USAGE IS -CP
)@@G@@-     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$FLAG(K,1) TOTAL NUMBER OF CASE VALUES CQ
)@@G@@GIVEN @G@@@@.         ...    2) RUNNING TALLY: NUMBER OF VALUES ON PREVICR
)@@G@@OUS CASE    @C@@@@.         ...    3) INHIBIT/CALL OPTION FLAG    @E@@@@CS
)@@G@@.         ...    4,X) VALUE OF X'TH SPECIFIED CASEVALUE     @C@@@@.     CT
)@@G@@    ...    5) # OF REMOTE CASES PROCESSED @D@@@@.         ...    6) FLAGCU
)@@G@@ SET 1 IF NOCHECKING IS ON    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1) STARCV
)@@G@@T ADDR OF USER NOFIND CODE    @C@@@@.         ...    2) END ADDR OF USERCW
)@@G@@ NOFIND CODE@D@@@@.         ...    3) ULTIMATE EXIT ADDR FROM BLOCK     CX
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         ...    4,X) JUMPTARGET ADDR FOR X'TH CASEVALUE    @E@@@@CY
)@@G@@.         ...    5) RUNNING LABEL: LAST JUMP TO CLOSE A CASE@E@@@@.     CZ
)@@G@@    ...    6) BASE ADDR FOR OFFSET INTO JUMP TABLE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@DA
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     DB
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       DC
)@@G@@   CASENTRY           * @C@@@@.               *                         DD
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     DE
)@@G@@@B@@@@. SYNTAX--     CASENTRY <AXREG>    OR...  @D@@@@.              CASDF
)@@G@@ENTRY CALLING(,<LINK>) NAME(,<TAG>) @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P     DG
)@@G@@  PROC   *6 @B@@@@CASENTRY*  NAME                       .   @F@@@@K     DH
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUENCE NUM    @D@@@@G$CTR*DI
)@@G@@(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @G@@@@M         EQU     DJ
)@@G@@  G$CTR(5)+1        . NESTING LEVEL FOR THIS BLOCK    @E@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQDK
)@@G@@U       M                 . UPDATE THAT, TOO    @G@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU    DL
)@@G@@  K                 . REMEMBER BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER  @F@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EDM
)@@G@@QU      3                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO CASE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@DN
)@@G@@. DO PRELIMINARY PARSING@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CALOPT     EQU      P(1,1)=CALDO
)@@G@@LING    . ON TO CALL SUBROUTINE     @G@@@@N DO (P-2)*(P>2)              DP
)@@G@@        ; SEARCH ALL BUT 0TH AND 1ST FIELD@F@@@@  , DO P(N+1)=1         DQ
)@@G@@              ; IF ONLY ONE SUBFIELD...   @G@@@@    , DO P(N+1,1)=NOCHECDR
)@@G@@KING          ; AND ITS THE NOCHECKING KEYWORD  @H@@@@       ,G$FLAG*(K,DS
)@@G@@6) EQU 1            . SET GLOBAL FLAG FOR ENDCASE FLOAT     @G@@@@N DO (DT
)@@G@@P-2)*(P>2)                      ; SEARCH ALL BUT 0TH AND 1ST FIELD@G@@@@DU
)@@G@@  , DO P(N+1,1)=NOFINDEXIT            ; AND ITS THE NOFIND EXIT SPEC    DV
)@@G@@@F@@@@     ,NFI(1) EQU N+1                  . REMEMBER WHERE IT APPEAREDDW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO CALOPT=0 , GO G$$C05              . SKIP THIS IF NDX
)@@G@@ORMAL CASENTRY    @G@@@@BANKSW     EQU      P(3,1)=BASING     . ON IF WEDY
)@@G@@ SHOULD SWITCH BANKS    @G@@@@XREG       EQU      P(1,2)+X11*(P(1,2)=0) DZ
)@@G@@. LINK REG, DEFAULT => X11    @I@@@@ DO BANKSW**(P(3)>2) , I$ 046,P(3,5)EA
)@@G@@,XREG,P(3,4),3*P(3,*4)+P(3,*3),P(3,3) . LXI     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C05EB
)@@G@@*    NAME   @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,0) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY GLOBAEC
)@@G@@L FLOAT     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,0)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,ED
)@@G@@0)    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,0)  EQU   $                 . MARK START IN CASE WEE
)@@G@@E'LL INHIBIT@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       CALOPT*G$CTR(6) . ACCOEF
)@@G@@UNT FOR THE LMJ   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C10*   NAME    @F@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)EG
)@@G@@ , GO G$$C40           . ON PASS 1, SKIP THIS STUFF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@EH
)@@G@@. ***** PASS 2 ONLY-- GENERATE CHECKING AND THE JUMPTABLE   @[@@@@.     EI
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO 1-CALOPT , ; IF NOT A SUBROUTINE CALL BLOCK @F@@@@ DO (P(1,1)<EJ
)@@G@@A0)++(P(1,1)>A3) , G$$EFL 3,1 . DIE IF NOT OVERLAP REG@[@@@@.     @B@@@@EK
)@@G@@. COMPUTE CHARACTERISTICS OF THE TABLE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NUMCA     EQEL
)@@G@@U       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@CMAX(1)   EQEM
)@@G@@U       -34359738367      . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@@EN
)@@G@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MEO
)@@G@@AX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MIN TO LARGEST EP
)@@G@@POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) EEQ
)@@G@@QU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @D@@@@OFF     EQU    1-CMIN(1)            ER
)@@G@@  . SET OFFSET    @G@@@@JTSIZ   EQU    CMAX(1)+OFF            . SET TOT ES
)@@G@@TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL @F@@@@JTL       EQU       JTSIZ-(G$FLAG(K,3)=-1)ET
)@@G@@*(G$FLAG(K,4,1)=CMAX(1))@F@@@@ DO CALOPT , DO (CMIN(1)=0)=0 , G$$EFL 3,5EU
)@@G@@ . MIN VAL NOT ZERO     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS BELONEV
)@@G@@GING TO THIS BLOCK, SET GLOBAL FLOAT@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU  EW
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,3)+G$CTR(2) . LAST LBL GETS ONLY GLOBAL FLOAT    @G@@@@PRSIZ EX
)@@G@@    EQU       (CALOPT=0)*(4-3*G$FLAG(K,6)) . SIZE OF PREAMBLE     @G@@@@EY
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+(G$FLAG(K,3)<1)*(PRSIZ+JTL)  . SET FLOAT   EZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY IT    @G@@@@FA
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END                 . IF OPTIMIZED AWAY, QUIT HERE  FB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE CROSS REFERENCES NEEDED TO GENERATE THE JUMPFC
)@@G@@ TABLE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ISNF      EQU       G$LABL(K,2)>G$LABL(K,1) . ONFD
)@@G@@=> USER GAVE NOFIND CODE@H@@@@ DO (NFI(1)>0)**ISNF , G$$EFL 3,07    . NOFE
)@@G@@FIND EXIT FORBIDS NOFIND USER CODE  @G@@@@NFA(1)    EQU       G$LABL(K,3FF
)@@G@@-2*ISNF) . NOFIND ADDR <= ENDCASE/USERCODE@G@@@@ DO NFI(1)>0            FG
)@@G@@              ; IF EXPLICIT NOFIND TARGET GIVEN @E@@@@  ,NFA(1) EQU P(NFFH
)@@G@@I(1),2)             . SET JUMPTARGET TO IT@F@@@@ DO CALOPT              FI
)@@G@@              ; IF WE'RE CALLING A SUBRTNE@G@@@@  ,NFA(1) EQU -1        FJ
)@@G@@              . SET MISSING CASE DETECTION FLAG @F@@@@N DO JTSIZ        FK
)@@G@@                    ; FOR ALL JUMPTABLE ENTRIES @G@@@@  ,JT(N) EQU NFA(1FL
)@@G@@)                   . INITIALIZE TARGET ADDR TO NOFIND@F@@@@N DO NUMCA  FM
)@@G@@                          ; FOR ALL CASEVALUES GIVEN  @G@@@@  ,JT(G$FLAGFN
)@@G@@(K,4,N)+OFF)              ; SET JMPTBL ADDR FOR N'TH VALUE  @G@@@@     EFO
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,4,N)+G$CTR(2)       . TO FLOATED ADDR OF TARGET BLOK  @E@@@@FP
)@@G@@N DO JTSIZ                            ; FOR ALL CASE VALUES @F@@@@  , DOFQ
)@@G@@ JT(N)=G$CTR(2)                 ; IF TARGET BLOCK IS EMPTY  @G@@@@     ,FR
)@@G@@JT(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3)           . JUMP DIRECTLY TO THE ENDCASE    @G@@@@FS
)@@G@@N DO CALOPT*JTSIZ                     ; FOR ALL CASEVALS OF CALL OPTION FT
)@@G@@@G@@@@  , DO JT(N)=-1                       ; IF NO ACTION GIVEN FOR N'TFU
)@@G@@H EXIT@G@@@@     , G$$EFL 3,6                     . GIVE MISSING CASE DIFV
)@@G@@AGNOSTIC    @G@@@@. NOW FIXUP FOR LAST CASE OPTIMIZED OUT FROM UNDER EMPFW
)@@G@@TY CASES BEFORE IT@F@@@@OSADR     EQU       G$LABL(K,3)+1     . OVERSHOOFX
)@@G@@T TARGET ADDR     @F@@@@N DO JTSIZ                            ; FOR ALL FY
)@@G@@CASE VALUES GIVEN @G@@@@  , DO JT(N)=OSADR                    ; IF EMPTYFZ
)@@G@@ CASE CAUSED OVERSHOOT  @H@@@@    ,JT(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3)            . PAGA
)@@G@@TCH UP EXIT TO REAL ENDBEG LOCN     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GEN PREAMBLE TO GB
)@@G@@JUMP TABLE, I.E., CHECKING CODE AND JUMP OR CALL@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO CAGC
)@@G@@LOPT , GO G$$C26                . CALLING OPTION GETS NO PREAMBLE @G@@@@GD
)@@G@@    DO G$FLAG(K,6)>0 , GO G$$C25      . CHECKS INHIBITED GETS ONLY JUMP GE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TLE,XU    P(1,1),CMAX(1)+1  . TEST AGAINST MAX RANGE    GF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TLE,XU    P(1,1),CMIN(1)    . AND AGAINST THE MIN @G@@@@GG
)@@G@@          J         NFA(1)            . NOFIND EXIT IF OUT AT EITHER ENDGH
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$C25*   NAME    @E@@@@          J         $+OFF,P(1,1)      . JUGI
)@@G@@MP THRU TABLE     @#@@@@    GO G$$C29     @E@@@@G$$C26*   NAME          GJ
)@@G@@              . HERE FOR CALLING    @F@@@@FUN       EQU       074-BANKSWGK
)@@G@@*065    . FUNC CODE, LMJ/LIJ/LDJ    @G@@@@JAY       EQU       013-BANKSWGL
)@@G@@*(P(3,2)=DBANK) . J-DES IS PART OF OPCODE @B@@@@HI        EQU       2*P(GM
)@@G@@2,*2)+P(2,*1)     @D@@@@          I$        FUN,JAY,XREG,P(2,2),HI,P(2,1GN
)@@G@@) .   @F@@@@G$$C29*   NAME                        . END OF PREAMBLE GENEGO
)@@G@@RATION@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. NOW ACTUALLY GENERATE THE JUMP TABLE    @[@@@@GP
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,6) EQU    $-CMIN(1)         . ESTABLISH ANCHOR ADDGQ
)@@G@@R FOR JMPTBL@G@@@@N DO JTL                              ; FOR ALL ENTRIEGR
)@@G@@S IN THE TABLE    @G@@@@  , J JT(N)                           . TAKE PROGS
)@@G@@VERBIAL FLYING LEAP     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. ***** PASS 1 LEAPS DIRECTLY GT
)@@G@@HERE  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C40*   NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU 0-CALOPGU
)@@G@@T             . REMEMBER CALL OPTION, IF ANY    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU GV
)@@G@@  $                 . MARK START OF NOFIND CODE, IF ANY     @F@@@@G$FLAGGW
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU 0                    . NO CASE STMNTS SEEN YET   @G@@@@G$LABLGX
)@@G@@*(K,4,0) EQU  $                 . INITIALIZE LOCAL OPTIMIZATION   @I@@@@GY
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU 0                    . NO VALUES ON NON-EXISTENT PREVIOGZ
)@@G@@US CASE     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@HA
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * HB
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           CASE    HC
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@HD
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     HE
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @F@@@@CASE*   NAME                          . SPHF
)@@G@@ECS--  <VALUE-LIST>     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GEHG
)@@G@@T CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GEHH
)@@G@@T SEQUENCE NUM OF THIS BLOCK  @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=3)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3    HI
)@@G@@  . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END                 . HJ
)@@G@@DONE IF OPTIMIZED AWAY  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@JJ      EQU    +G$FLAG(K,1)   HK
)@@G@@        . GET # OF CASEVALS SO FAR IN THIS GRP  @G@@@@ DO JJ=0 ,G$LABL*(HL
)@@G@@K,2)  EQU   $       . MARK END OF USER NOFIND CODE    @B@@@@ DO (JJ>0)++HM
)@@G@@(G$FLAG(K,3)>-1) , GO G$$C60 .@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. SPECIAL STUFF FOR 1ST HN
)@@G@@CASE WITH CALLING OPTION@G@@@@.    THE MAX VAL IS MOVED TO THE 1ST POSN HO
)@@G@@SO THAT WE CAN EASILY CHECK   @G@@@@. LATER WHETHER IT IS THE GLOBAL MAXHP
)@@G@@.  IF SO, AND IF THE 1ST BLOCK HAS  @G@@@@. CODE, THEN THE LAST JUMPTBL HQ
)@@G@@ENTRY CAN BE OMITTED AND WE CAN INSTEAD   @B@@@@. SIMPLY FALL INTO THE CHR
)@@G@@ODE FOR THIS CASE.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,1) , G$$GFL 2,5 . NO HS
)@@G@@NOFIND ALLOWED FOR CALL OPTION@E@@@@MAX(1)    EQU       P(1,1)          HT
