)@@G@@    . INITIALIZE MAX    @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)>MAX(1) ,MAX(1) EQU PHU
)@@G@@(1,N) . FIND MAX VALUE  @F@@@@IMAX(1)   EQU       1                 . INHV
)@@G@@ITIALIZE POSN OF MAXVAL @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)=MAX(1) ,IMAX(1) EQU HW
)@@G@@N . FIND POSN OF MAXVAL @E@@@@MTEMP     EQU       P(1,1)            . TEHX
)@@G@@MP SAVE 1ST VALUE @E@@@@P(1,1)    EQU       MAX(1)            . FORCE ITHY
)@@G@@ TO MAX     @G@@@@P(1,IMAX(1)) EQU    MTEMP             . EXCHANGE WITH HZ
)@@G@@PREVIOUS VALUE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CLOSE PREVIOUS CASE   @[@@@@.     IA
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$C60*   NAME    @H@@@@REDUN     EQU       $=G$LABL(K,3)     . ONIB
)@@G@@=> CLOSURE HERE WOULD BE REDUNDANT  @G@@@@GOTSOM EQU $>G$LABL(K,4,JJ)   IC
)@@G@@        . ON IF PRECEDING CASE HAD CODE   @G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,3)<0)**(JJID
)@@G@@=1)           ; IF 2ND CASE OF CALLING OPTION...@F@@@@    ,G$FLAG*(K,3) IE
)@@G@@EQU GOTSOM-2        . SET FLAG IF 1ST CASE EMPTY@F@@@@ DO GOTSOM**1-REDUIF
)@@G@@N , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,3) . CLOSE LAST CASE  @H@@@@ DO GOTSOM ,G$LABLIG
)@@G@@*(K,5)   EQU  $     . MARK START USERCODE FOR THIS CASE     @G@@@@G$CTR*IH
)@@G@@(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-REDUN*GOTSOM    . IF SURPRESSED, NOTE FLOAT@D@@@@II
)@@G@@N DO (1-GOTSOM)*G$FLAG(K,2) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+1-N) EQU 0@[@@@@.     @B@@@@IJ
)@@G@@. TABULATE PARAMETERS FOR THE PRESENT CASE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1)IK
)@@G@@ EQU JJ+P(1)              . UPDATE CASEVAL COUNT@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU +IL
)@@G@@P(1)                . REMEMBER HOW MANY TBL ENTRIES WE'RE USI     @F@@@@IM
)@@G@@N DO P(1) ,G$FLAG*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU +(P(1,N)) . SAVE CASE VALUE(S)   @G@@@@IN
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)=0)=0 , ; IF NOT OPTIMIZED AWAY ...  IO
)@@G@@@G@@@@  DO (G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CTR(2)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CIP
)@@G@@TR(2) @H@@@@N DO     P(1) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU $ . SET OUR OWN JUMPTARIQ
)@@G@@GET ADDRESSES     @G@@@@ DO (P(2,1)=REMOTESUB)=0 , END          . QUIT UIR
)@@G@@NLESS REMOTESUB CALL    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    G$FLAG(K,5IS
)@@G@@)+G$CTR(6) . ON PASS 1,  COUNT REMOTE CALLS     @D@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) , ENDIT
)@@G@@                    . AND THAT'S ALL@F@@@@          G$$PRA    P(2,2),G$LIU
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) . PATCH UP BLOCK EXIT INSTR@E@@@@ DO P(2,3)=VIA ,P(2,2) EQU P(2IV
)@@G@@,4)     . SET XFER TARGET ADDR@F@@@@HERE                                IW
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WHERE WE ARE     @G@@@@N DO P(1)                           IX
)@@G@@  ; FOR ALL VALUES IN THIS CASE     @G@@@@  , G$$PJT G$LABL(K,6)+P(1,N),IY
)@@G@@P(2,2)  . MAKE JMPTBL POINT TO TARGET     @E@@@@          RES       HEREIZ
)@@G@@-$            . RESTORE THE L.C.    @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @E@@@@JA
)@@G@@P         PROC      *1,0              . DO NOTHING ON PASS 1@E@@@@G$$PJTJB
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . PATCH UP JUMP TABLE @F@@@@          REJC
)@@G@@S       P(1,1)-$          . GO BACK TO JUMPTBL ENTRY  @G@@@@          J JD
)@@G@@        P(1,2)            . AND OVERLAY IT WITH NEW TARGET  @#@@@@      JE
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **JF
)@@G@@***************************** @C@@@@.               *                   JG
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *          ENDCASE            * @C@@@@JH
)@@G@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.               **JI
)@@G@@***************************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROCJJ
)@@G@@   *0 @#@@@@ENDCASE*  NAME    @G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        JK
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M) JL
)@@G@@        . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=3)=0 , G$JM
)@@G@@$GFL 1,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE TABLE SIJN
)@@G@@ZE SO WE KNOW HOW MUCH FLOAT TO APPLY     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@CALOPT    EQJO
)@@G@@U       G$FLAG(K,3)<0     . SET IF CASENTRY WITH CALLING OPTION   @F@@@@JP
)@@G@@NUMCA     EQU       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@JQ
)@@G@@CMAX(1)   EQU       -34359738367      . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUJR
)@@G@@MBER  @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,JS
)@@G@@4,L) . GET MAX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MINJT
)@@G@@ TO LARGEST POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1JU
)@@G@@) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @G@@@@JTS(1)   EQU    CMAX(1)-JV
)@@G@@CMIN(1)+1      . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)=-1JW
)@@G@@ ,JTS(1) EQU JTS(1)-(CMAX(1)=G$FLAG(K,4,1))     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$JX
)@@G@@LABL(K,0)=$                     ; IF NO CODE IN ANY CASE BLOK     @G@@@@JY
)@@G@@  , DO G$FLAG(K,5)=0                  ; AND NO REMOTE BLOX EITHER...    JZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@    ,G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU 1               . TURN OFF CODE GENERATION  KA
)@@G@@@G@@@@REDUN     EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=$     . ON=> LAST CASE CLOSURE REDKB
)@@G@@UNDANT@G@@@@PRSIZ     EQU       (CALOPT=0)*(4-3*G$FLAG(K,6)) . GET PREAMKC
)@@G@@BLE SIZE    @H@@@@FLOAT     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,3)<1)*(PRSIZ+JTS(1)-REDUKD
)@@G@@N) . FLOAT FOR TABL     @G@@@@          RES       FLOAT*G$CTR(6)    . ONKE
)@@G@@ PASS 1, APPLY FLOAT TO L.C.  @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-FLOAT*GKF
)@@G@@$CTR(7) . ON P2, APPLY TO GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7)KG
)@@G@@ , DO (G$LABL(K,3)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU KH
)@@G@@  $                 . MARK ULTIMATE EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK   @G@@@@G$CTR*KI
)@@G@@(5) EQU       M-1               . UPDATE GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL     @[@@@@KJ
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@        END @B@@@@/.       ********* REPEAT GROUP ********* KK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$FLAG(K,X) IS USED TO KEEPKL
)@@G@@ FLAGS THROUGOUT  @E@@@@.    THE SCOPE OF THE REPEAT BLOCK. FOR EACH X, KM
)@@G@@THE FLAG IS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.       1      INDEX OF 'VARY' FIELD ON SOKN
)@@G@@URCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE     @F@@@@.       2      ON IF THERE IS <LOOP CTL> CKO
)@@G@@ODE WHICH MUST APPEAR   @D@@@@.              AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF TKP
)@@G@@HE LOOP     @E@@@@.       3      INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD IN SOURCE 'REPEAT' KQ
)@@G@@IMAGE @F@@@@.       4      INDEX OF 'WHILE' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT IMAGKR
)@@G@@E     @B@@@@.       5      FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL @C@@@@.       6   KS
)@@G@@   INDEX OF 'UNTIL' ON SOURCE IMAGE @B@@@@.       7      SURPRESS EVERYTKT
)@@G@@HING FLAG   @A@@@@.       8      ON=> 'LOOKFOR' FORMAT@C@@@@.       9   KU
)@@G@@   ON=> BOTTOM OF LOOP CHECKING DONE@E@@@@.       .      FLAGS USED TO CKV
)@@G@@ONTROL POSITIONING AND FLOAT: @D@@@@.      10      ON=> ENTRY CONDITION KW
)@@G@@IS JUMP TO WHILE  @B@@@@.      11      ON => SURPRESS WHILE AT TOP@B@@@@KX
)@@G@@.      12      ON=> INVERT ESCAPE TEST    @E@@@@.      13      ON=> CLOSKY
)@@G@@E ESCAPE CLAUSE (WITH JUMP TO EXIT) @G@@@@.      14      ON=> CLOSE OTHEKZ
)@@G@@RWISE/UNTIL CLAUSE (WITH JUMP TO LOOP)    @C@@@@.      15      ON=> SURPLA
)@@G@@RESS WHILE AT BOTTOM    @C@@@@.      16      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED LB
)@@G@@AT TOP@B@@@@.      17      FLOAT FOR INVERTED ESCAPE  @D@@@@.      18   LC
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED AT BOTTOM   @E@@@@.      19      ON=> CODELD
)@@G@@ IN LOOP WILL APPEAR BELOW ESCAPE   @C@@@@.      20      GLOBAL FLOAT ATLE
)@@G@@ ENTRY TO BLOCK   @E@@@@.      21      1+FLOAT FOR INITIAL JUMP FALLTHRULF
)@@G@@ (0=>NONE)  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$LABL(K,X) IS USED TO LABELG
)@@G@@L VARIOUS CONTROL @D@@@@.    POINTS IN THE GENERATED CODE.  VALUES OF X LH
)@@G@@ARE:  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       1      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP WHILE TESLI
)@@G@@T     @D@@@@.       2      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE    @F@@@@LJ
)@@G@@.       3      START USER-SPECIFIED REPEATED CODE (TOP OF LOOP)   @G@@@@LK
)@@G@@.       4      LOCATION OF CONDITION TEST AT ESCAPE (0=>NO ESCAPE STMNT)LL
)@@G@@@D@@@@.       5      START USER-SPECIFIED ESCAPE CLAUSE     @D@@@@.     LM
)@@G@@  6      START USER-SPECIFIED OTHERWISE CODE    @D@@@@.       7      LOCLN
)@@G@@ATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE TEST  @D@@@@.       8      LOCATION OF BOTLO
)@@G@@TOM-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE @C@@@@.       9      START USER-SPECIFIED ATEND LP
)@@G@@CODE  @C@@@@.      10      ULTIMATE BLOCK EXIT TARGET ADDR  @[@@@@.     LQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE FOLLOWING ARCANE RULES ARE FOLLOWED IN POSITIONILR
)@@G@@NG THE VARIOUS    @ @@@@. CODE GENERATED FOR A LOOP:  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@LS
)@@G@@. 1) <UNTIL> CODE ALWAYS APPEARS AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     LT
)@@G@@@F@@@@.            SO WE CAN AVOID JUMPING AROUND IT AT LOOP ENTRY.     LU
)@@G@@@B@@@@. 2) <VARY>  CODE MOVES AROUND AS FOLLOWS:@G@@@@.        A)  IF THLV
)@@G@@E SENSE (UP/DOWN) IS KNOWN, THEN THE CODE IS PLACED   @G@@@@.           LW
)@@G@@ ACCORDING TO THE PREFERENCE OF THE LOOP INSTRUCTION, E.G.  @D@@@@.     LX
)@@G@@       JGD AT THE BOTTOM, SEARCHES AT THE TOP.  @G@@@@.        B)  IF THLY
)@@G@@E SENSE IS UNKNOWN, THE CODE APPEARS AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@.           LZ
)@@G@@ BOTTOM, WITH THE BRANCH SENSE APPROPRIATELY INVERTED.@G@@@@.           MA
)@@G@@ IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE PRIMARY CODE (BOTTOM), A SIGN TEST  @G@@@@.     MB
)@@G@@       IS INSERTED WHICH DETERMINES WHICH OF THE TWO VARIATIONS   @ @@@@MC
)@@G@@.            WILL BE EXECUTED.@G@@@@. 3) <WHILE> CODE ALSO MOVES AROUND.MD
)@@G@@ WE DEFINE A <WHILE> TEST WHICH IS  @G@@@@.            PERFORMED IN A SIME
)@@G@@NGLE INSTRUCTION WHICH HAS AN INVERSE     @G@@@@.            (I.E. A CONMF
)@@G@@DITIONAL JUMP) AS 'OPTIMIZEABLE'. POSITIONING   @E@@@@.            THEN MG
)@@G@@DEPENDS UPON OTHER CONDITIONS AS FOLLOWS- @G@@@@.            NORMAL POSIMH
)@@G@@TIONING IS AT THE BOTTOM, WITH A (ONE TIME) JUMP@H@@@@.            TO THMI
)@@G@@E WHILE TEST INSERTED AT THE TOP. IF THERE IS AN ESCAPE     @G@@@@.     MJ
)@@G@@       CONDITION WHICH WOULD OTHERWISE FALL THROUGH, HOWEVER, THE @H@@@@MK
)@@G@@.            JUMP AROUND THE WHILE IS AVOIDED BY PUTTING IT AT THE TOP AML
)@@G@@ND    @H@@@@.            INVERTING THE ESCAPE TEST ACCORDINGLY. IF THEREMM
)@@G@@ IS NO <VARY>     @G@@@@.            CODE AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE MN
)@@G@@LOOP, AND THE WHILE     @G@@@@.            TEST IS OPTIMIZEABLE, THEN THMO
)@@G@@E INITIAL JUMP TO THE WHILE   @G@@@@.            TEST IS REPLACED BY THEMP
)@@G@@ TEST ITSELF. IN THIS CASE, THE     @G@@@@.            TEST WILL APPEAR MQ
)@@G@@AT BOTH THE TOP AND BOTTOM OF THE LOOP.   @E@@@@. 4) ESCAPE  AN ESCAPE TMR
)@@G@@EST CAN BE MODIFIED BOTH BECAUSE OF @G@@@@.            THE ABOVE, OR BECMS
)@@G@@AUSE THE CLAUSE IS EMPTY. IF THE CODE     @F@@@@.            FOLLOWING TMT
)@@G@@HE TEST IS NOT IN THE LOOP (I.E. IS A NON-@F@@@@.            VACUOUS ESCMU
)@@G@@APE CLAUSE OR IS THE END OF THE LOOP),    @F@@@@.            THE ESCAPE MV
)@@G@@TEST BRANCHES TO STAY IN THE LOOP. IF     @G@@@@.            THE FOLLOWIMW
)@@G@@NG CODE IS IN THE LOOP (I.E. VACUOUS ESCAPE     @G@@@@.            AND NMX
)@@G@@ON-VACUOUS OTHERWISE), THEN THE SENSE IS REVERSED     @F@@@@.           MY
)@@G@@ SO THAT THE BRANCH CONDITION GOES COMPLETELY OUT OF  @^@@@@.           MZ
)@@G@@ THE BLOCK. @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **************************NA
)@@G@@***** @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.     NB
)@@G@@          *           REPEAT            * @C@@@@.               *       NC
)@@G@@                      * @C@@@@.               **************************ND
)@@G@@***** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *12@]@@@@REPEAT* NAME@[@@@@.     NE
)@@G@@@E@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . BUMP BLOCK COUNTER  @F@@@@NF
)@@G@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . SAVE UPDATED BLOCK COUNT  @F@@@@NG
)@@G@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUMP GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL @F@@@@NH
)@@G@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M                 . SAVE NEW NESTING LEVEL    @F@@@@NI
)@@G@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K                 . SAVE SEQ NO OF THIS BLOCK @F@@@@NJ
)@@G@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU      4                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO REPEAT  @[@@@@NK
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS IN THIS BLOCK    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NL
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(6) , GO G$$R10           . ON PASS 1, FLOAT MEANS NOTHING     NM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,20) EQU   G$CTR(2)          . SAVE INITIAL FNN
)@@G@@LOAT  @H@@@@ESCF      EQU       G$LABL(K,4)       . REMEMBER ENTRY VALUENO
)@@G@@ OF ESCAPE FLAG   @H@@@@FALLF     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,21)>0)*(1-G$FLAG(KNP
)@@G@@,21)) . GET FALLTHRU FLOAT    @H@@@@N DO 10 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,NNQ
)@@G@@)+G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . GLOBAL, JUMPENTR@I@@@@N DO 9 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) ENR
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,N+1)+G$FLAG(K,16)+FALLF . SURPRESS TOP WHILE    @G@@@@N DO 6NS
)@@G@@ ,G$LABL*(K,N+4) EQU G$LABL(K,N+4)+G$FLAG(K,17) . ESCAPE INVERSION@G@@@@NT
)@@G@@N DO 5 ,G$LABL*(K,N+5) EQU G$LABL(K,N+5)+G$FLAG(K,13) . ESCAPE CLOSURE  NU
)@@G@@@I@@@@N DO 4 ,G$LABL*(K,N+6) EQU G$LABL(K,N+6)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,5) NV
)@@G@@. OTHER/UNTIL     @G@@@@N DO 3 ,G$LABL*(K,N+7) EQU G$LABL(K,N+7)+G$FLAG(NW
)@@G@@K,18) . BOTTOM WHILE    @E@@@@ DO ESCF=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU 0 . IF NO ESCNX
)@@G@@APE, RESTORE FLAG @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ***** SYNTAX ANALYSIS ***** @[@@@@NY
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$R10*   NAME    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@C(1)      EQNZ
)@@G@@U  1                      . INITIALIZE CURRENT FIELD COUNTER@G@@@@KW(1) OA
)@@G@@    EQU  P(1,1)                 . AND CURRENT LEADING KEYWORD     @[@@@@OB
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.               EXAMINE 'WHILE' FIELD     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@OC
)@@G@@G$$R50* NAME                          . MARK START OF WHILE TEST  @G@@@@OD
)@@G@@WI      EQU    KW(1)=WHILE            . FIELD INDEX OF 'WHILE' OR ZERO  OE
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU WI                 . REMEMBER INDEX IN CASE DEFEROF
)@@G@@RED   @C@@@@ DO WI=0 , GO G$$R59 . IF NO 'WHILE', WE'RE DONE@C@@@@WYNOT OG
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) .    @H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(OH
)@@G@@3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @F@@@@C(1)    EQU OI
)@@G@@   3+WYNOT+2*WC                 . UPDATE FIELD POINTER@F@@@@KW(1)   EQU OJ
)@@G@@   P(C(1),1)              . KEYWORD FOR NEXT FIELD    @H@@@@G$$R59* NAMEOK
)@@G@@                          . END PROCESSING OF 'WHILE' CONDITION   @[@@@@OL
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.       EXAMINE <LOOP CTL> FIELD, LOADING REGS IF NECESSARY OM
)@@G@@@D@@@@. NOTE: THE <LOOP CONTROL> ANALYSIS SUBROUTINE G$$LAN @E@@@@. SETSON
)@@G@@ THE FLAGS FI(X) USED BELOW.  FOR THEIR DEFINITIONS,  @ @@@@. SEE THE COOO
)@@G@@DE FOR G$$LAN     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       SEE IF THIS IS A HARDWARE SEOP
)@@G@@ARCH SPEC   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$R60* NAME                          . MAOQ
)@@G@@RK START PROCESSING OF <LOOP CNTRL> SP    @F@@@@ DO (KW(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , OR
)@@G@@GO G$$R61 . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO TRY 'VARY' @I@@@@VI      EQU    C(1)+2   OS
)@@G@@              . IN THIS FMT, 'VARY' FOLLOWS LOOKFOR AND     @F@@@@ DO (POT
)@@G@@(VI,1)>VARY)++(P(VI,1)<LOOKFOR) , G$$EFL 2,010 . CHECK IT   @G@@@@P(VI,1OU
)@@G@@) EQU    LOOKFOR                . FORCE KEYWORD FOR USE BY G$$LAN @H@@@@OV
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU 1                 . SET FLAG ALLOWING UNCONDITIONAL ESCOW
)@@G@@APE   @A@@@@ GO G$$R62 . THEN GO PROCESS IT     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$$R61OX
)@@G@@* NAME                          . TRY A NORMAL 'VARY' FIELD @F@@@@VI    OY
)@@G@@  EQU    C(1)*((KW(1)>JMGI-1)**(KW(1)<VARY+1)) . FIELD INDEX@D@@@@ DO VIOZ
)@@G@@=0 , GO G$$R69 . SKIP THIS IF FIELD NOT GIVEN   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R62PA
)@@G@@* NAME@E@@@@        G$$LAN                . ANALYZE THE LOOP CTL FIELD  PB
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU FI(5)              . REMEMBER IF IT HAS DEFERRED PC
)@@G@@CODE  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU FI(3)              . NOTE FIELD IN WHICH 'TPD
)@@G@@O' SPEC APPEARS   @H@@@@C(1)    EQU    FI(7)+1                . SET FIELPE
)@@G@@D OF NEXT (I.E. UNTIL) GROUP  @F@@@@KW(1)   EQU    P(C(1),1)            PF
)@@G@@  . AND ITS FUNCT FLAG WORD   @]@@@@G$$R69* NAME@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU VPG
)@@G@@I                 . SAVE INDEX OF VARY FIELD, IF ANY  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@PH
)@@G@@.              SCAN 'UNTIL' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,6) EQU  PI
)@@G@@  C(1)*(KW(1)=UNTIL). EXTERNALIZE SO WE KNOW IT WAS GIVEN   @[@@@@.     PJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@.     ***** CODE GENERATION *****   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R80* NAMEPK
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,10) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,7) . ENTER WITH JUMP TO WPL
)@@G@@HILE/VARY   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . APPLY FLOAPM
)@@G@@T, IF ANY   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $        . MARK START PN
)@@G@@OF WHILE TEST     @H@@@@ DO (WI>0)**1-G$FLAG(K,11) , G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,WPO
)@@G@@YNOT G$LABL(K,9) . GEN IT     @D@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+((WI>0)PP
)@@G@@**G$FLAG(K,11)) . @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,16) . AND PQ
)@@G@@APPLY THE FLOAT   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. GENERATE LOOP <VARY> CODE, IF ANY PR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF 2NDARY LPS
)@@G@@OOP CHECK   @C@@@@ DO VI>0 , ; IF THERE IS LOOP VARIATION CODE    @G@@@@PT
)@@G@@ DO (P(VI,1)=LOOKFOR)++((FI(5)=FI(6))=0) , ; AND SOME OR ALL IS HERE    PU
)@@G@@@E@@@@        G$$LGE VI,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,9),1 . GENERATE IT   @F@@@@PV
)@@G@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)<$ ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0 . IF ANY, CAN'T FALL THRU  @[@@@@PW
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. FINAL CLEANUP   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$SVA        PX
)@@G@@              . SAVE ARGS FOR LATER @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 0            PY
)@@G@@     . CLEAR ENDCHECK DONE FLAG     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,3)PZ
)@@G@@=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU   $         . MARKQA
)@@G@@ START OF USER'S CODE   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@QB
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* QC
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.           QD
)@@G@@    *           ESCAPE            * @C@@@@.               *             QE
)@@G@@                * @C@@@@.               ******************************* QF
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *4 @#@@@@ESCAPE*  NAME     QG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NEQH
)@@G@@STING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NQI
)@@G@@O OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=4)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTINGQJ
)@@G@@ ERRORS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,4)=$)=0 , G$$DQK
)@@G@@FL G$LABL(K,4)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)  EQU   $        . MARK START OF ESCQL
)@@G@@APE TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@TBOT      EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)>0     . ONQM
)@@G@@ => TEST AT LOGICAL BOTTOM (UNTIL)  @H@@@@TTOP      EQU       (G$FLAG(K,QN
)@@G@@1)>0)++(G$FLAG(K,4)>0) . ON => TESTS AT LGL TOP @H@@@@ DO TTOP**TBOT , GQO
)@@G@@$$GFL 2,1               . CAN'T HAVE CAKE AND EAT IT TOO    @G@@@@G$FLAGQP
)@@G@@*(K,8) EQU G$FLAG(K,8)**(P(1)=0) . UNCONDITIONAL (LOOKFOR) FLAG   @G@@@@QQ
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . UNCONDITIONAL => LEAP OUT QR
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , GO G$$E10 . THEN GO CLEAN UP  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@QS
)@@G@@ DO (P(1,1)=WHEN)=0 , G$$EFL 3,4 . SYNTAX ERROR IF NO 'WHEN'@F@@@@WHENOTQT
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) . ON FOR NOT CONDITION @H@@@@CFLG  QU
)@@G@@  EQU    P>3+WHENOT                      . ON FOR COMPOUND CONDITION    QV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ON PASS 1, BOTH SENSES OF THE TEST ARE GENERATED, SOQW
)@@G@@ WE CAN     @F@@@@. DETERMINE THE FLOAT TO USE IF REVERSAL OCCURS. ON PAQX
)@@G@@SS 2, ONLY  @A@@@@. THE DESIRED SENSE IS GENERATED    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@QY
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(6)++G$FLAG(K,12) , ; PASS 1 ALWAYS, PASS 2 IF REVERSED  @I@@@@QZ
)@@G@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,WHENOT G$LABL(K,1+5*G$FLAG(K,19)) . JUMP=> KEEPRA
)@@G@@ LOOPIN     @F@@@@SIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . LENGTH OF REVERB
)@@G@@RSED TEST   @E@@@@          RES      0-G$CTR(6)*SIZE . THEN RES TEST AWARC
)@@G@@Y     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$CTR(7)+G$FLAG(K,7) . KEEP G$$RD
)@@G@@TST CTR IN PHASE  @H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,12)++G$FLAG(K,7)=0 , ; PASS1 ALWAYSRE
)@@G@@, 2 IF NOT REVERSED/SURPRESSED@G@@@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,1-WHENOT G$RF
)@@G@@LABL(K,10) . JUMP=> EXIT FROM LOOP  @E@@@@WIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(KRG
)@@G@@,4)     . SIZE OF 2ND TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,RH
)@@G@@7) EQU    SIDE(1)           . PASS 1: SET SIDE EFFECT @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQRI
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,17) . PASS2: APPLY FLOAT FOR ENCLOSED BL@E@@@@RJ
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU  SIZE-WIZE . PASS 1: GET FLOAT, 2=>NOISE  @[@@@@.     RK
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$E10*   NAME    @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $           . MARK STARL
)@@G@@RT OF USER'S ESCAPE CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@RM
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * RN
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *         OTHERWISE RO
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@RP
)@@G@@.               *           ATEND             * @C@@@@.               * RQ
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           ENDREP  RR
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@RS
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     RT
)@@G@@@#@@@@Y       PROC   *1 @^@@@@OTHERWISE* NAME     0   @^@@@@ATEND*    NARU
)@@G@@ME      1   @^@@@@ENDREP*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQRV
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQRW
)@@G@@U       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (GRX
)@@G@@$TYPE(M)=4)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(KRY
)@@G@@,5)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,5) EQU $ . FIXUP FOR MISSING ESCAPE  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@RZ
)@@G@@. CLOSE DANGLING ESCAPE, IF REQUIRED@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,13) ,SA
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . PASS2: LEAP OUT    @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU     SB
)@@G@@  G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,13) . APPLY CLOSURE FLOAT   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU SC
)@@G@@  0                 . REMEMBER WE'VE DONE THIS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. ****SD
)@@G@@ OTHERWISE GETS OFF THE TRAIN HERE ...    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO Y(0,0)>0SE
)@@G@@ , GO G$$Z10              . IF ATEND OR ENDREP, KEEP MOVING @H@@@@ DO G$SF
)@@G@@LABL(K,4)=0 , G$$GFL 2,2            . OTHERWISE INVALID IF NO ESCAPE    SG
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,6)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,6) 1  @F@@@@SH
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,6)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF 'OTHERWISE' CODE    @B@@@@SI
)@@G@@ DO 1 , END         . THAT'S ALL FOLKS    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. **** ATENDSJ
)@@G@@/ENDREP LUMBER ONWARD...@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         CLOSE LOOP: GEN CTL SK
)@@G@@CODE WHICH PREFERS PHYSICAL BOTTOM  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z10*   NAME    SL
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,9) , GO G$$Z50          . IF ITS TUESDAY, THIS MUST BSM
)@@G@@E ENDREP    @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 1                 . REMEMBER WE'VE BESN
)@@G@@EN HERE     @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,6)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,6) EQU $ . DEFAULT START SO
)@@G@@OF OTHERWISE@G@@@@KK        EQU       G$CTR(3)          . GET POINTER INSP
)@@G@@TO ARGSAVE STACK  @H@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +SQ
)@@G@@G$ARGS(KK,I,J) . GET ARGS     @E@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I)  SR
)@@G@@  ; FOR ALL SUBFIELDS   @F@@@@  , DO G$ARGS(KK,I,*J) ,P(I,J) EQU *P(I,J)SS
)@@G@@ . PRESERVE ASTERISKS   @G@@@@G$CTR*(3) EQU       KK-1              . THST
)@@G@@EN MOVE STACK POINTER BACK    @I@@@@ DO (Y(0,0)=1)**(G$ARGS(KK)=0) , G$$SU
)@@G@@GFL 2,3        . ATEND UNREACHABLE IF NO ARG    @G@@@@LL      EQU    G$FSV
)@@G@@LAG(K,2)          . ON IF ANY <VARY> CODE WAS DEFERRED@H@@@@DFER      EQSW
)@@G@@U       LL++(G$FLAG(K,4)>0) . ON IF DEFFERED CODE OF ANY TYPE     @[@@@@SX
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE UNTIL CONDITIONS. THEY CAN HAVE EITHER BRANCH SENSESY
)@@G@@:     @G@@@@.   A) IF WHILE/VARY CODE WILL FOLLOW, UNTIL SUCCESS LEAPS TSZ
)@@G@@O ATEND     @E@@@@.   B) IF NOT (A), THEN UNTIL FAILURE LEAPS TO TOP OF TA
)@@G@@LOOP  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@UNORG                                 . MARK ORITB
)@@G@@GIN OF UNTIL TESTS, IF ANY    @G@@@@UN        EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)     TC
)@@G@@. GET INDEX INTO P OF UNTIL SPECS   @B@@@@ DO UN=0 , GO G$$Z30          TD
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@KILL      EQU       G$CTR(7)**G$FLAG(K,7) . ON IF SURPTE
)@@G@@RESSING ALL CODE  @G@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,5) . APPLYTF
)@@G@@ UNTIL SURPRESS FLOAT   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+KILL     . COTG
)@@G@@UNT SURPRESSED UNTIL    @E@@@@ DO KILL , GO G$$Z30                   . ATH
)@@G@@ND FORGET THE REST@F@@@@UNN       EQU       (P(UN+1)=1)**(P(UN+1,1)=NOT)TI
)@@G@@ . SET NOT FLAG   @I@@@@UNC       EQU       (P(UN+UNN+2)=1)**((P(UN+UNN+TJ
)@@G@@2,1)=OR)++(P(UN+UNN+2,1)=AND)) .    @D@@@@  G$$TST UN+UNN+1,UNC,DFER--UNTK
)@@G@@N G$LABL(K,1+9*DFER)    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CLOSE DANGLING OTHERWISE/UNTTL
)@@G@@IL    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z30*   NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    UNORTM
)@@G@@G-$           . GET FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL  @E@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,14) ,TN
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . JUMP TO TOP   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTTO
)@@G@@R(2)+G$FLAG(K,14) . FLOAT FOLLOWING CODE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   0   TP
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER WE DID THIS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE WHILE CONTQ
)@@G@@DITIONS.  THESE CAN BE SURPRESSED OR CAN BRANCH TWO   @F@@@@. WAYS; FORTTR
)@@G@@UNATELY, THE BRANCH SENSE IS KNOWN ON PASS 1 (LL):    @F@@@@.  A) IF <VATS
)@@G@@RY> CODE FOLLOWS, THEN WHILE FAILURE JUMPS TO ATEND   @D@@@@.  B) IF NOTTT
)@@G@@ (A), WHILE SUCCESS JUMPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,7)TU
)@@G@@  EQU   $        . MARK START OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE @B@@@@. NOTE: IF WTV
)@@G@@HILE EXISTS, ITS ALWAYS SPEC 1@B@@@@WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1TW
)@@G@@)=NOT)@H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))*TX
)@@G@@*(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,4)>0)**1-G$FLAG(K,15) , ; IF EXISTTY
)@@G@@S AND NOT SURPRESSED-   @D@@@@        G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,LL=WYNOT G$LABL(TZ
)@@G@@K,2+7*LL)   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$FLAG(K,15) . COUNT SURPUA
)@@G@@RESSED WHILE@H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,18) . APPLY WHILUB
)@@G@@E SURPRESSION FLOAT     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. GENERATE <VARY> CODE  @[@@@@UC
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,8)  EQU   $        . MARK START OF BOTTOM OF LOOP UD
)@@G@@VARY  @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++(G$FLAG(K,1)>0) UE
)@@G@@. NOTE SIDE EFFEC @D@@@@ DO LL , G$$LGE G$FLAG(K,1),G$FLAG(K,3) G$LABL(KUF
)@@G@@,3)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++SIDEUG
)@@G@@(1) . NOTE SIDE EFFECTS @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,9)=$)=0 , G$$DUH
)@@G@@FL G$LABL(K,9) 2  @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,9)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF USUI
)@@G@@ER ATEND CODE     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. END PROCESSING OF LOOP TERMINATIONUJ
)@@G@@ CONDITIONS @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO Y(0,0)=1 , END  . ATEND STATEMENT FINIUK
)@@G@@SHES UP HERE@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CLEANUP FOR ENDREP STATEMENT@[@@@@.     UL
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$Z50*   NAME    @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,10)=$)=0 , G$$UM
)@@G@@DFL G$LABL(K,10) 3@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,10) EQU   $          . SET BLOCK EXIT UN
)@@G@@LABEL @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$FLAG(K,20)      . RESTORE GLOBAL FLOATUO
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU  M-1                    . DECREMENT GLOBAL NESTING LUP
)@@G@@EVEL  @C@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE HERE @[@@@@.     UQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@. ***** PASS 1 ONLY: DETERMINE POSITIONING AND OPTIMIZATIONS@[@@@@UR
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAGS INDICATING WHETHER USER PUT ANY CODEUS
)@@G@@ IN SPECIFIC CLAUSES    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ESCAPP    EQU       G$LABL(K,4UT
)@@G@@)>0     . ON=>ESCAPE STMNT APPEARED @H@@@@RVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,3UU
)@@G@@)=G$LABL(K,5-ESCAPP) . ON=> NOTHING AFTER REPEAT@H@@@@EVAC      EQU     UV
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,6) . ON=> USER ESCAPE CLAUSE VACUOUS @H@@@@UOVAC UW
)@@G@@    EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7)+G$FLAG(K,5) . ON=> NO USER 'OTHER UX
)@@G@@@I@@@@OVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7) . ON=> EMPTY OTHERWISEUY
)@@G@@/UNTIL CLAUSE     @H@@@@AVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,9)=G$LABL(K,10) . OUZ
)@@G@@N=> USER ATEND CLAUSE VACUOUS @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NOKILL    EQU       G$FLVA
)@@G@@AG(K,7)++1-(RVAC**EVAC**UOVAC**AVAC) .    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@VATBOT    EQVB
)@@G@@U       G$FLAG(K,2)       . ON=> SOME (OR ALL) <VARY> AT BOTTOM   @H@@@@VC
)@@G@@LOOBOT    EQU       VATBOT++1-OVAC  . ON=> SOME LOOP CODE WILL BE AT BOTVD
)@@G@@TOM   @G@@@@EFOLLO    EQU       LOOBOT++1-AVAC  . ON=> SOMETHING WILL FOVE
)@@G@@LLOW ESCAPE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. COMPUTE OPTIMUM POSITIONING OF WHILE (CAVF
)@@G@@N BE TOP, BOTTOM, OR BOTH)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@WHSPEC    EQU       G$FLVG
)@@G@@AG(K,4)>0     . ON IF WHILE SPECIFICATION GIVEN @H@@@@WONET     EQU     VH
)@@G@@  1=G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . ON => WHILE IS ONE INST AT T  @G@@@@WONEB VI
)@@G@@    EQU       1=G$LABL(K,8)-G$LABL(K,7) . ON => ONE INSTR AT BOT  @[@@@@VJ
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@WHIBOT    EQU       (EFOLLO++1-ESCAPP)**NOKILL . ON=> IF WHIVK
)@@G@@LE, ALLOW AT BOTTO@I@@@@WHISBO    EQU       WHSPEC**WHIBOT    . ON => WHVL
)@@G@@ILE WILL REALLY APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @H@@@@WHITOP    EQU       (WONET**WOVM
)@@G@@NEB**1-VATBOT++1-WHIBOT)**NOKILL . 0N=>ALLOW    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SET VN
)@@G@@GLOBAL SURPRESS FLAGS AND FLOATS FOR WHILE OPTIMIZATION     @[@@@@.     VO
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,11) EQU   WHSPEC**1-WHITOP . ON => SURPRESS AT TOP@H@@@@VP
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,16) EQU   (G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2))*G$FLAG(K,11) . TOP SURPRESVQ
)@@G@@S FLOA@F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,15) EQU   WHSPEC**1-WHIBOT . ON=> SURPRESS AT BOTTVR
)@@G@@OM    @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,18) EQU   (G$LABL(K,7)-G$LABL(K,8))*G$FLAG(K,15) .VS
)@@G@@ BOT SURPRESS FLOA@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE VARIOUS FLAGS FOR ESCAPE OVT
)@@G@@PTIMIZATION AND CLOSURE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,19) EQU   LOOBOT++WHVU
)@@G@@ISBO    . ON=>LOOP CODE FOLLOWS     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,12) EQU   (G$FLAG(K,VV
)@@G@@19)**EVAC=0)**NOKILL . ON=>JUMP TO KEEP GOING   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU VW
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,17)*G$FLAG(K,12) . SET FLOAT TO USE  @F@@@@ DO 1-NOKILL ,G$FLVX
)@@G@@AG*(K,17) EQU ESCAPP*(G$LABL(K,4)-G$LABL(K,5)) .@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU VY
)@@G@@  NOKILL**ESCAPP**G$FLAG(K,12)**(EFOLLO++WHISBO) . CLOSURE FLAG   @[@@@@VZ
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAG FOR GENERATION OF JUMP TO WHILE/VARY AT TOP (INITWA
)@@G@@IAL ENTRY)  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU   (VATBOT++1-WHITOP**WHSWB
)@@G@@PEC)**NOKILL . ON=> GEN ENTRY JUMP  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR IMMEDIATE JGWC
)@@G@@D LOOPS WE WON'T JUMP. FOR NOW, WE WON'T CHECK FOR    @G@@@@. PRESENCE OWD
)@@G@@F WHILE AT TOP, BUT WILL TURN OFF THIS OPTIMIZATION IF THERE@G@@@@. IS AWE
)@@G@@NY WHILE AT ALL. IN ADDITION, ONLY JGD'S NOW SET THE OPTIMIZATION @G@@@@WF
)@@G@@. FLAG, SO THERE WILL BE NO FLOATING. WHEN TLEM'S AND JMGI'S ARE DONE,  WG
)@@G@@@G@@@@. SURPRESSION OF SOME REGISTER LOAD CODE WILL CAUSE FLOAT WHICH WIWH
)@@G@@LL    @C@@@@. NEED TO BE COMPENSATED FOR AT THIS POINT.     @[@@@@.     WI
)@@G@@@G@@@@CANFAL    EQU       1-WHSPEC**(G$FLAG(K,21)>0) . ON => WE CAN FALLWJ
)@@G@@ THRU @H@@@@ DO CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU 0       . SO FORGET ABOUT JUMPWK
)@@G@@ING TO BOTTOM     @G@@@@ DO 1-CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0     . CLEAR FLWL
)@@G@@AG IF WE CAN'T FALL THRU@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CLOSE OTHERWISE/UNTIL WITH JWM
)@@G@@UMP IF NOT FOLLOWED BY TESTS WHICH DO IT  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@UNTOP     EQWN
)@@G@@U       (G$FLAG(K,6)>0)**(VATBOT++WHSPEC=0) . UNTIL JUMPS TO TOP  @G@@@@WO
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   (OVAC**ESCAPP++WHISBO++VATBOT++UNTOP=0)**NOKILL .   WP
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$FLAG(K,5)*(1-NOKILL) . ADJUST UNTIL SURPRESSIONWQ
)@@G@@ FLOAT@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET LC TO REFLECT WHAT IT WILL BE ON PASS 2 BYWR
)@@G@@ APPLYING FLOATS TO IT  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU    1-NOKILL  WS
)@@G@@        . SET FLAG TO KILL ALL CODE @H@@@@          RES       G$FLAG(K,5WT
)@@G@@)+G$FLAG(K,10)+G$FLAG(K,16)+G$FLAG(K,17)+ ;     @E@@@@                  WU
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,13)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,18)  @]@@@@        END @C@@@@/.    WV
)@@G@@     ******** EXEC REQUEST GROUP *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@WW
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * WX
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *          -READ-$  WY
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@WZ
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     XA
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@READ$*  NAME   015@#@@@@READA$*  NAME  042XB
)@@G@@@^@@@@TREAD$*  NAME  0102     @^@@@@AREAD$*  NAME  0166     @^@@@@AREADAXC
)@@G@@$*  NAME 0167     @^@@@@ATREAD$*  NAME 0170     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (PXD
)@@G@@(0,0)=015)++(P(0,0)=0166) , GO G$$D20 . NO PKT IF READ$,AREAD$    @G@@@@XE
)@@G@@PKTOFF  EQU    (P(0,0)=0102)++(P(0,0)=0170) . OFFSET FOR TREAD$ PACKETS XF
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO P(1)=0 , GO G$$D10                . IF PKT ADDR NOT GIVEN, GO XG
)@@G@@KLUDGE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GENERATE CODE FOR CASE WHERE PACKET ADDR EXPLIXH
)@@G@@CITLY GIVEN---    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@        LA,U   A0,$+5               XI
)@@G@@  . GET EOF ADDR (SKIP AFTER READ$) @H@@@@        I$     06,H1,A0,P(1,2)XJ
)@@G@@,P(1,*1),P(1,1)+PKTOFF . STASH IN PACKET (FIELD @G@@@@        I$     026XK
)@@G@@,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM PKT ADR   @E@@@@ GO G$$D99  XL
)@@G@@                          . GO GENERATE THE READ@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF PXM
)@@G@@ACKET ADDR CAN VARY AT XQT TIME, WE MUST FARBLE A BIT @[@@@@.     @]@@@@XN
)@@G@@G$$D10* NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,0,A1                . TEMP SAVE A1 LXO
)@@G@@OWER IN A0 UPPER  @F@@@@        LXM,U  A1,$+7                 . GET ADDRXP
)@@G@@ OF EOF RETURN    @E@@@@        SA,H1  A1,PKTOFF,A0           . EOF ADDRXQ
)@@G@@ TO PACKET  @G@@@@        LSSC   A0,18                  . ALIGN OLD A1 LXR
)@@G@@OWER IN A0 LOWER  @E@@@@        LXM,U  A1,0,A0                . RESTORE XS
)@@G@@A1 LOWER    @E@@@@        SSL    A0,18                  . REALIGN PACKETXT
)@@G@@ ADDR @E@@@@ GO G$$D99                            . THEN GO DO THE ER   XU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. GENERATE CALL FOR IO FUNCTS WHICH DO NOT USE PACKETSXV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D20* NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,$+(P(1)>0)+3      XW
)@@G@@  . SET EOF TO SKIP AFTER READ$     @H@@@@ DO P(1)>0 ,         I$     02XX
)@@G@@6,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM BUF@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D99XY
)@@G@@* NAME@D@@@@        ER     P(0,0)                 . DO THE FUNC   @E@@@@XZ
)@@G@@        I$     074,04,,,,$+2          . NORMAL EXIT HERE    @G@@@@      YA
)@@G@@  AA,U   A0,0400000             . IF EOF, SET LOWORDER SIGN BIT   @]@@@@YB
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @D@@@@/.   ****** UTILITIES FOR CONDITION TESTINYC
)@@G@@G *******   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************************YD
)@@G@@********************    @F@@@@.     *                                   YE
)@@G@@                   *    @F@@@@.     *       G$$CAN : ANALYZE A SIMPLE COYF
)@@G@@NDITION FIELD      *    @F@@@@.     *                                   YG
)@@G@@                   *    @F@@@@.     ************************************YH
)@@G@@********************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. DEFINE ARRAYS FOYI
)@@G@@R OPTIMIZATION OF TYPE 1 TESTS ON REGISTERS INTO TYPE 3     @[@@@@.     YJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@          DEF     @F@@@@G$ALTT(NE)  EQU     NONZ              . NOYK
)@@G@@T EQUAL ZERO IS NONZERO @E@@@@G$ALTT(EQ)  EQU     ZERO              . EQYL
)@@G@@UAL ZERO IS ZERO  @ @@@@G$ALTT(DNE) EQU     DNONZ     @ @@@@G$ALTT(DEQ) YM
)@@G@@EQU     DZERO     @F@@@@G$ALTT(LT)  EQU     NEG               . LESS THAYN
)@@G@@N ZERO IS NEGATIVE@G@@@@G$ALTT(GE)  EQU     POS               . GTR OR EYO
)@@G@@QUAL ZERO IS POSITIVE   @#@@@@Z       PROC   *1 @#@@@@G$$CAN*  NAME     YP
)@@G@@@H@@@@I       EQU    Z(1,1)                 . GET INDEX TO FIELD BEING AYQ
)@@G@@NALYZED     @F@@@@K       EQU    Z(1,2)                 . GET ITS ORDER YR
)@@G@@IN THE TEST @ @@@@. DETERMINE TYPE OF CONDITION @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)>0  ,N(1YS
)@@G@@) EQU 1     @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)=IN ,N(1) EQU 2     @A@@@@ DO P(I,2)=IS ,N(1YT
)@@G@@) EQU 3+2*(P(I)=4)@ @@@@ DO P(I)=1    ,N(1) EQU 4     @ @@@@ DO P(I,1)=CYU
)@@G@@HANNEL ,N(1) EQU 6@F@@@@ DO N(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,1               . E-FLAG IYV
)@@G@@F UNKNOWN TYPE    @F@@@@ DO N(1)<3 , G$$DCU,2 I,3             . DECODE EYW
)@@G@@QUF'D U-SPECS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. TRY TO CHANGE TEST TO A MORE OPTIMYX
)@@G@@AL ONE THAN SPECIFIED   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (N(1)=2)**G$AMPR , GO G$$AYY
)@@G@@10      . REG STATUS NEEDS RELOCATION FUNC &(X) @E@@@@U16     EQU     (PYZ
)@@G@@(I,5)<016)++(P(I,4)>0)++P(I,*3)++P(I,*4)  @E@@@@ DO (N(1)>1)++U16 , GO GZA
)@@G@@$$A30 . VALUE TESTS NEED IMMEDIATES @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. IMMEDIATE LE OR ZB
)@@G@@GT CAN BE ALTERED TO LT OR GE...    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PI3       EQU     ZC
)@@G@@  P(I,3)            . PI3 IS UFIELD @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,PI3 EQU $AP(PI3)ZD
)@@G@@        . IF MASM, REMOVE RELOCATABLE PART@C@@@@NEGEQU    EQU       (P(IZE
)@@G@@,5)=017)**(PI3>0377777) @E@@@@OFVAL     EQU       0377777+0400000*((P(I,ZF
)@@G@@5)=016)++NEGEQU)  @F@@@@FUDGE     EQU       ((LT-LE)*(P(I,2)=LE)+(GE-GT)ZG
)@@G@@*(P(I,2)=GT))* ;  @F@@@@                    (PI3<OFVAL) . DON'T OVERFLOWZH
)@@G@@ OR CHANGE SIGN   @D@@@@P**(I,2) EQU        P(I,2)+FUDGE      . ADJUST KZI
)@@G@@EYWORD@F@@@@P**(I,3) EQU        P(I,3)+1-(FUDGE=0) . ADJUST IMMEDIATE VAZJ
)@@G@@LUE   @F@@@@ DO ((P(I,3)=0)**(P(I,4)=0)=0)++(G$ALTT(P(I,2))=0) , GO G$$AZK
)@@G@@30 .  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. REGISTER TESTS AGAINST IMMEDIATE ZEROES CAN BEZL
)@@G@@COME CONDITIONAL JUMPS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. BE CAREFUL NOT TO OVEROPTIMIZM
)@@G@@ZE IMMEDIATES     @F@@@@ DO 1-G$AMPR , GO G$$A30 . CANNOT OPTIMIZE WITHOZN
)@@G@@UT & FUNCTION     @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&(P(I,3))=-2)=0 , GO G$$A30 .ZO
)@@G@@ ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE  @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($BA(P(I,3))=0)=0 , GO GZP
)@@G@@$$A30 . ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE @F@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       G$ALTT(P(I,2))  ZQ
)@@G@@  . GET ALTERNATE KEYWORD     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,P**(I) EQU 3          ZR
)@@G@@    . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWAY ,,U)     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P**(ZS
)@@G@@I,4) $DELETE          . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWAY ,,U)     @I@@@@ZT
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P**(I,5) $DELETE          . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWZU
)@@G@@AY ,,U)     @C@@@@ GO G$$A20          . GO FINISH UP THE FARBLING @[@@@@ZV
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. TYPE 2 CONDITION TESTS ON A-REGS CAN BECOME CONDITIONAL JUZW
)@@G@@MPS, TOO.   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$A10*   NAME    @G@@@@ DO P(I)>3 , GO G$ZX
)@@G@@$A30                . DON'T OPTIMIZE EQUF'D CORE LOCNS@I@@@@REG       EQZY
)@@G@@U       P(I,3)            . GET REG FROM  <KEYWORD>,IN,<REG> FORMAT     ZZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($BA(REG)=0)=0 , GO G$$A30 . MUST BE AN ABSOLUTEAA
)@@G@@ VALUE@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&(REG)=-2)=0 , GO G$$A30  . MUST BE AN ABAB
)@@G@@SOLUTE VALUE@G@@@@ DO (REG<A0)++(REG>A15) , GO G$$A30   . MAKE SURE ITS AC
)@@G@@WITHIN AREG RANGE @H@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       P(I,1)            . FORCE COAD
)@@G@@NDITION KEYWORD INTO SPEC3    @F@@@@P**(I,1)  EQU       REG             AE
)@@G@@  . THEN MOVE REG INTO SPEC1  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$A20*   NAME          AF
)@@G@@              . FINISH FUDGING  <AREG>,IS,<KEYWORD> TEST    @E@@@@P**(I,AG
)@@G@@2)  EQU       IS                . CRAM IN THE KEYWORD @G@@@@N(1)      EQAH
)@@G@@U       3                 . AND MARK THIS AS A TYPE 3 TEST  @[@@@@.     AI
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$A30*   NAME    @F@@@@J(1)    EQU    P(I,G$KSF(N(1)))       . GEAJ
)@@G@@T FUNC KEYWORD VALUE    @H@@@@ DO DTH ,J(1) EQU G$IV(N(1),J(1))     . FLAK
)@@G@@IP IF DEMORGAN'S THEOREM IN EFFECT  @F@@@@ DO J(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,2       AL
)@@G@@        . E-FLAG IF UNKNOWN KEYWORD @F@@@@NI$*(K) EQU    G$FJ(N(1),J(1))AM
)@@G@@        . NO OF INSTRS GENERATED    @D@@@@WA$*(K) EQU    G$WS(N(1),J(1))AN
)@@G@@        . WAITING STATUS@G@@@@KE$*(K) EQU    J(1)                   . EXAO
)@@G@@TERNALIZE FUNC KEYWORD VAL    @F@@@@TP$*(K) EQU    N(1)                 AP
)@@G@@  . EXTERNALIZE TYPE OF TEST  @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     AQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************************************AR
)@@G@@********    @F@@@@.     *                                               AS
)@@G@@       *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$COD : GENERATE CODE FOR A SIMPLE CONDITIONAT
)@@G@@ TEST  *    @F@@@@.     *                                               AU
)@@G@@       *    @F@@@@.     ************************************************AV
)@@G@@********    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@Q       PROC   *2 @I@@@@G$$CODAW
)@@G@@*  NAME                         . PF'S: FIELD-INDEX,TEST-INDEX,WAIT-VAL AX
)@@G@@FA    @F@@@@I       EQU    Q(1,1)                 . GET FIELD WE'RE SCANAY
)@@G@@NING  @F@@@@NN      EQU    Q(1,2)                 . GET DECODED DATA INDAZ
)@@G@@EX    @E@@@@N       EQU    TP$(NN)                . GET CONDITION TYPE  BA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@CGISF   EQU    G$FCF(N)=0             . TRUE IF G$FJ=FBB
)@@G@@UNC CODE (ELSE J-S@E@@@@JI(1)   EQU    KE$(NN)                . GET KEYWBC
)@@G@@ORD FUNCTION@F@@@@JI(2)   EQU    G$IV(N,JI(1))          . AND KEYWORD OFBD
)@@G@@ THE INVERSE@F@@@@WOK     EQU    Q(1,3)=G$WS(N,JI(1))   . ON IF WAITING BE
)@@G@@STATUS OK   @A@@@@.     ---- DECODE OPERAND FIELDS    @G@@@@AAA     EQU BF
)@@G@@   0+(G$ASF(N)>0)*(P(I,G$ASF(N))-A0) . WATCH OUT FOR -0!!!!!@D@@@@JJJ   BG
)@@G@@  EQU     CGISF*P(I,5)          . J DESIGNATOR  @ @@@@XXX     EQU     CGBH
)@@G@@ISF*P(I,4)  @C@@@@HI      EQU     CGISF*(2*P(I,*4)+P(I,*3)) .     @G@@@@BI
)@@G@@U18     EQU     (JJJ>015)**(XXX=0)**(N<3)**(HI=0) . ON=>18 BIT U-FIELD  BJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@UUU     EQU    CGISF*P(I,3)+(1-CGISF)*Q(2,1)    @G@@@@SIDE**(1) EQBK
)@@G@@U SIDE(1)++(N=5)++(HI>0)  . ON IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS     @G@@@@ DO G$BL
)@@G@@FJ(N,JI(1),1)>077 , GO G$$G10   . CHECK FOR ASYMMETRIC INSTRUCTION@[@@@@BM
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. PROCESS SYMMETRIC TESTS (FOR WHICH AN INVERSE MACHINE INSTBN
)@@G@@R EXISTS)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@JIU     EQU    JI(2-WOK)              . GEBO
)@@G@@T INDEX OF OPCODE WE'LL USE   @G@@@@NUMINS  EQU    G$FJ(N,JIU)          BP
)@@G@@  . GET NO OF INSTRS TO GENERATE    @E@@@@K DO     NUMINS ,FUN(K) EQU G$BQ
)@@G@@FCF(N)+CGISF*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)    @E@@@@K DO     NUMINS ,JAY(K) EQU JJJ+(1-CBR
)@@G@@GISF)*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)     @G@@@@K DO     NUMINS*(1-U18) , I$ FUN(K),JAY(K)BS
)@@G@@,AAA,XXX,HI,UUU . GENERATE    @F@@@@K DO     NUMINS*U18 , G$$IMU FUN(K),BT
)@@G@@JAY(K),AAA,XXX,UUU . IMMEDIAT @F@@@@REVER**(1) EQU G$FJ(N,JI(1))*G$FJ(N,BU
)@@G@@JI(2))=1 . SET REVERSIBLE FLAG@G@@@@ DO REVER(1)++WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,$BV
)@@G@@+2 . WATCHOUT FOR NON-REVERSIBLES   @H@@@@ DO 1 , END                   BW
)@@G@@        . FOR STANDARD INSTRS, ITS ALL OVER HERE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. PROCBX
)@@G@@ESS ASYMMETRIC INSTRS (FOR WHICH NO SINGLE INVERSE EXISTS)  @[@@@@.     BY
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$G10* NAME@F@@@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(N,JI(1),1)        . GET FUNCBZ
)@@G@@T-JDESIG VALUE    @E@@@@ DO FUN=01637 , GO G$$G20             . TEST FORCA
)@@G@@ DTE INSTR  @D@@@@. IF NOT A DTE, THEN INSTRUCTION IS A JUMP OF SORTS   CB
)@@G@@@B@@@@. (EITHER DJZ OR AN I/O CHANNEL TEST)     @H@@@@AREG    EQU    AAACC
)@@G@@+A0*(FUN>01700)     . FOR CHANNEL INSTRS, USE GIVEN AVALUE  @G@@@@      CD
)@@G@@     I$       FUN*/-4,FUN**017,AREG,,,WOK*UUU+(WOK=0)*($+2) .     @ @@@@CE
)@@G@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,UUU  @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @B@@@@. HERE WE HANDLE TCF
)@@G@@HE DOUBLE TEST EQUAL -  @]@@@@G$$G20* NAME@D@@@@           I$       FUN*CG
)@@G@@/-4,FUN**017,AAA,XXX,HI,UUU . @ @@@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,$+2  @]@@@@CH
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************CI
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       CJ
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$TST : DRIVER FOR SCK
)@@G@@IMPLE AND COMPOUND COND TESTS  *    @F@@@@.     *                       CL
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     ************************CM
)@@G@@********************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@R     CN
)@@G@@  PROC   *2 @H@@@@G$$TST*  NAME                         . PF'S: FIELD-INCO
)@@G@@-P,COMPOUND-FLAG,INVERT @I@@@@                              . IF NO JUMPCP
)@@G@@-EXIT GIVEN, G$TLBL(TTL)+1 IS USED (LINE I@H@@@@TTL     EQU    G$CTR(4)+CQ
)@@G@@1             . COUNT THIS REFERENCE TO THIS PROCEDURE@F@@@@ORIG        CR
)@@G@@                          . REMEMBER WHERE WE STARTED @G@@@@G$CTR**(4) ECS
)@@G@@QU  TTL                   . BUMP NO OF CALLS TO THIS PROC   @D@@@@G$TLBLCT
)@@G@@**(TTL) EQU G$TLBL(TTL)+G$CTR(2) . FOLD IN FLOAT@F@@@@LIF     EQU    R(2CU
)@@G@@)=0                 . ON IF LINEITEM FORMAT     @E@@@@FA(1)   EQU    R(2CV
)@@G@@,1)+LIF*(G$TLBL(TTL)+1) . SET FALSE EXIT  @G@@@@DTH     EQU    R(1,3)   CW
)@@G@@              . ON => USE DEMORGAN'S THEOREM FOR@I@@@@                  CX
)@@G@@                    . WHICH CAUSES G$$CAN TO INVERT THE SENSE     @[@@@@CY
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@ DO R(1,2) , GO G$$T10                . GO DO COMPOUND CONDICZ
)@@G@@TION  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CODE GENERATION FOR SIMPLE CONDITIONS   @[@@@@DA
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@        G$$CAN R(1,1),1               . ANALYZE THE (SINGLE)DB
)@@G@@ FIELD@H@@@@ DO WA$(1)>1 , GO G$$T01              . CHECK FOR TEST INSTRDC
)@@G@@ TO GE GENN'D     @D@@@@        G$$COD R(1,1),1,0 FA(1)       . JUMP TO DD
)@@G@@FALSE @C@@@@ GO G$$T99                            . AND QUIT@[@@@@.     DE
)@@G@@@H@@@@G$$T01* NAME                          . HERE IF SIMPLE CONDITION IDF
)@@G@@S A TEST    @I@@@@        G$$COD R(1,1),1,2+LIF         . SKIP IF: TRUE DG
)@@G@@(IF-ELSE) FALSE (LINEITEM)    @F@@@@ DO 1-LIF , I$ 074,04,,,,FA(1)      DH
)@@G@@  . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     DI
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$T10* NAME                          . COMPOUND CONDITIONS COME HDJ
)@@G@@ERE   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@K DO     2 ,II(K) EQU R(1,1)+2*(K=2)  . SET FIELDK
)@@G@@D INDICES FOR SIMPLE CONDS    @E@@@@K DO     2 , G$$CAN II(K),K         DL
)@@G@@  . ANALYZE BOTH FIELDS @H@@@@K DO     2 ,IX(K) EQU K+(WA$(2)<WA$(1))*(3DM
)@@G@@-2*K) . ORDER SO 2ND IS HIGHER WAIT @H@@@@.  DO WA$(1)=WA$(2) ,K DO 2 ,IDN
)@@G@@X(K) EQU K+(NI$(2)>NI$(1))*(3-2*K) . NOT NOW    @G@@@@WOVR    EQU    (WADO
)@@G@@$(1)>1)+(WA$(2)>1)  . DETERMINE OVERALL WAIT TYPE     @G@@@@ DO (P(R(1,1DP
)@@G@@)+1,1)=AND)=1-DTH , GO G$$T20 . IF AND-CONDITION, GO DO IT  @[@@@@.     DQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@. GENERATE OPTIMIZED CODE FOR OR-CONDITIONS     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@DR
)@@G@@ DO WOVR>0 , GO G$$T11  @ @@@@. COME HERE FOR JUMP-JUMP     @E@@@@      DS
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),1 G$TLBL(TTL) . JUMP IF TRUE @D@@@@        G$$CDT
)@@G@@OD II(IX(2)),IX(2),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSE@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@G$$T11DU
)@@G@@* NAME@^@@@@ DO WOVR>1 , GO G$$T13  @ @@@@. COME HERE FOR TEST-JUMP     DV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOTE THAT THIS IS THE ONLY CASE IN WHICH WE GENERATEDW
)@@G@@ A TEST     @E@@@@. OVER A JUMP, AND IS THUS THE ONLY PLACE WE NEED TO CDX
)@@G@@HECK  @F@@@@. WHETHER THE JUMP INSTRUCTION HAS A SINGLE-INSTRUCTION INVEDY
)@@G@@RSE   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (WA$(IX(1))=0)++(G$FJ(TP$(IX(1)),KE$(IX(1)),DZ
)@@G@@1)<0100) , GO G$$T12    @ @@@@. OOPS, WE'RE IN HOT WATER--  @E@@@@      EA
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),1 G$TLBL(TTL) . JUMP IF TRUE @I@@@@        G$$CEB
)@@G@@OD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2+LIF  . SKIP IF: TRUE (IF-ELSE) FALSE (LINEITEM     EC
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO 1-LIF , I$ 074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   ED
)@@G@@@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @ @@@@. TEST OVER JUMP IS LEGAL --  @]@@@@G$$T12* NAMEEE
)@@G@@@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@      EF
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSE@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@EG
)@@G@@G$$T13* NAME@ @@@@. COME HERE TO DO TEST-TEST   @H@@@@ DO LIF , GO G$$T1EH
)@@G@@4                   . DIFFERENT STUFF IF LINE ITEM FORMAT   @D@@@@      EI
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @D@@@@        I$     074EJ
)@@G@@,04,,,,G$TLBL(TTL)  . JUMP TO TRUE  @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2)EK
)@@G@@,2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUEL
)@@G@@MP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$T14* NAME            EM
)@@G@@              . THIS IS TEST-TEST IN LINE ITEM FORMAT @ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(1EN
)@@G@@))>1 , GO G$$T15  @ @@@@. HERE IF TEST 1 IS 1 INSTR   @D@@@@        G$$CEO
)@@G@@OD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1))EP
)@@G@@,IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$T15EQ
)@@G@@* NAME@ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(2))>1 , GO G$$T16  @C@@@@. HERE IF 1ST TEST IS MOER
)@@G@@RE THAN ONE INSTRUCTION @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2      . SKES
)@@G@@IP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKIP IF FALSE ET
)@@G@@@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@G$$T16* NAME@B@@@@. HERE IF BOTH TESTS ARE MULTIEU
)@@G@@-INSTRUCTION@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE EV
)@@G@@@D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,G$TLBL(TTL)  . JUMP TO TRUE  @D@@@@      EW
)@@G@@  G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@EX
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. GENERATE TESTS FOR AND-CONDITIONS @[@@@@.     EY
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$T20* NAME@[@@@@.     @^@@@@ DO WOVR>0 , GO G$$T21  @ @@@@. GENEEZ
)@@G@@RATE CODE FOR JUMP-JUMP @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),0 FA(1) . JFA
)@@G@@UMP IF FALSE@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSEFB
)@@G@@@]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$T21* NAME@^@@@@ DO WOVR>1 , GO G$FC
)@@G@@$T23  @ @@@@. COME HERE FOR TEST-JUMP     @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1))FD
)@@G@@,IX(1),0 FA(1) . JUMP IF FALSE@I@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2+LIFFE
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF: TRUE (IF-ELSE) FALSE (LINEITEM     @F@@@@ DO 1-LIF , I$ 074FF
)@@G@@,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@FG
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@G$$T23* NAME                          . THIS PLACE FOR TEST-FH
)@@G@@TEST  @I@@@@ DO LIF , GO G$$T26                   . SPECIAL EASIER STUFFFI
)@@G@@ IN LINEITEM FORMAT     @ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(1))>1 , GO G$$T24  @ @@@@. HEREFJ
)@@G@@ IF TEST 1 IS 1 INSTR   @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKFK
)@@G@@IP IF FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  FL
)@@G@@@D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$FM
)@@G@@$T99  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$T24* NAME@ @@@@ DO NI$(IX(2))>1 , GO G$$T25  FN
)@@G@@@C@@@@. HERE IF 1ST TEST IS MORE THAN ONE INSTRUCTION @D@@@@        G$$CFO
)@@G@@OD II(IX(1)),IX(1),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2))FP
)@@G@@,IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)      FQ
)@@G@@  . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @]@@@@G$$T25* NAME@B@@@@. HERE IF BOFR
)@@G@@TH TESTS ARE MULTI-INSTRUCTION@D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2    FS
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FT
)@@G@@FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),2      . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@FU
)@@G@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FALSE @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  FV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$T26* NAME                          . TEST-TEST IN LFW
)@@G@@INE ITEM FORMAT (MUCH SIMP    @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(1)),IX(1),2    FX
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF TRUE  @D@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,FA(1)        . JUMP TO FY
)@@G@@FALSE @D@@@@        G$$COD II(IX(2)),IX(2),3      . SKIP IF FALSE @[@@@@FZ
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@G$$T99* NAME@F@@@@ DO $=ORIG , G$$EFL 1,1               . BOGA
)@@G@@MBOUT IF NOTHING DONE   @F@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$TLBL(TTL)=$)=0 ,  G$$GB
)@@G@@DFL G$TLBL(TTL) 0,0777  @F@@@@G$TLBL**(TTL) EQU   $           . RELEVANTGC
)@@G@@ ON GLOBAL PASS 1 ONLY  @]@@@@        END @E@@@@/.  ******* UTILITIES FOGD
)@@G@@R GENERATION OF LOOP CONTROLS ******@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SELEGE
)@@G@@CTION OF THE INSTRUCTION TO BE USED TO CONTROL THE LOOP IS: @E@@@@.    1GF
)@@G@@) JGD    IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS -1, OR   @E@@@@.           GG
)@@G@@   LOOP IS FOR A SPECIFIED NUMBER OF TIMES.     @E@@@@.    2) JMGI   IF GH
)@@G@@LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS NOT -1.  @D@@@@.    3) TLEM   IF LOOP TGI
)@@G@@ERMINATES AT OTHER THAN ZERO. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. POSITIONING OF THE LOOGJ
)@@G@@P CONTROL INSTRUCTION IS:     @A@@@@.    1) JGD    ALWAYS AT THE BOTTOM GK
)@@G@@@F@@@@.    2) JMGI   AT BOTTOM (SO JUMP DESTINATION CONTINUES IN THE    GL
)@@G@@@F@@@@.              LOOP), IF INCREMENT NEGATIVE (LOOP SENSE DOWN),    GM
)@@G@@@E@@@@.              I.E. VALUES OF LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE ARE >0 .@A@@@@GN
)@@G@@.              AT TOP OTHERWISE     @F@@@@.    3) TLEM   AT BOTTOM (SO SGO
)@@G@@KIP CAUSES EXIT FROM LOOP) WHEN     @E@@@@.              INCREMENT IS POGP
)@@G@@SITIVE (LOOP SENSE UP), I.E.  @F@@@@.              TERMINATION CONDITIONGQ
)@@G@@ IS APPROACHED FROM BELOW.    @F@@@@.              BECAUSE OF LACK OF SIGR
)@@G@@GN EXTENSION, THIS HOLDS RE-  @F@@@@.              GARDLESS OF THE SIGN GS
)@@G@@OF THE LOOP VARIABLE ITSELF.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE: IF THE SIGN OF TGT
)@@G@@HE INCREMENT IS UNKNOWN (JMGI/TLEM), THE CODE   @G@@@@. TO VARY THE LOOPGU
)@@G@@ CONTROL VARIABLE WILL BE DUPLICATED AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@. BOTTOM, WIGV
)@@G@@TH AN EXECUTE-TIME TEST (SIGN JUMP) AT THE BOTTOM TO  @A@@@@. DETERMINE GW
)@@G@@WHICH IS TO BE USED.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. TO ENFORCE THE REQUIREMENT TGX
)@@G@@HAT THE LOOP CONTROL REGISTER CONTAIN     @F@@@@. THE FROM/TO VALUES ON GY
)@@G@@THE FIRST AND LAST TIMES THROUGH THE LOOP,@D@@@@. TLEM TESTS AT THE TOP GZ
)@@G@@ARE SURROUNDED BY AX AND ANX  @F@@@@. OF THE INCREMENT. IN THE GENERAL CHA
)@@G@@ASE, THERE IS NO WAY TO AVOID @G@@@@. THIS. IN THE FUTURE, WE WILL ALLOWHB
)@@G@@ THE USER TO SURPRESS IT, AND/OR    @G@@@@. IN THE CASE WHERE THE CONTROHC
)@@G@@L FIELDS ARE IMMEDIATE, GENERATE SLIGHTLY @C@@@@. DIFFERENT CODE WHICH WHD
)@@G@@ILL MAKE IT UNNECESSARY.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************HE
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       HF
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LAN : ANALYZE A <HG
)@@G@@LOOP CONTROL> SPECIFICATION    *    @F@@@@.     *                       HH
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     ************************HI
)@@G@@********************************    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.    FLAGS SET BY HJ
)@@G@@THIS SUBROUTINE ARE USED BY CALLING ROUTINE (REPEAT)  @^@@@@.    THEIR MHK
)@@G@@EANINGS ARE:@D@@@@.       FI(1)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FOR' SPECIFICATION  HL
)@@G@@@C@@@@.       FI(2)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FROM' SPEC    @G@@@@.       FI(3HM
)@@G@@)  INDEX OF 'TO' SPEC ('VARY'), OR 'MASKED' SPEC ('LOOKFOR')@G@@@@.     HN
)@@G@@  FI(4)  INDEX OF 'BY' SPEC. NOTE THAT IF USER DIDN'T GIVE ONE,   @C@@@@HO
)@@G@@.              WE FORCE IT BY STORING IN P(X,Y) @G@@@@.       FI(5)  ON HP
)@@G@@IF ANY LOOP CONTROL CODE IS TO APPEAR AT THE PHYSICAL @B@@@@.           HQ
)@@G@@   BOTTOM OF THE LOOP CODE    @F@@@@.       FI(6)  ON IF SENSE OF LOOP CHR
)@@G@@TL VARIABLE (UP\DOWN) IS KNOWN@D@@@@.              ('VARY'), OR OFFSET VHS
)@@G@@ALUE ('LOOKFOR')  @F@@@@.       FI(7)  INDEX IN P OF LAST FIELD SCANNED HT
)@@G@@BY THIS ROUTINE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ARRAYS IM(K) AND IV(K) ARE USEHU
)@@G@@D INTERNALLY FOR THE ANALYZED @H@@@@. PARAMETERS OF THE LOOP SPECIFICATIHV
)@@G@@ON. IM IS ON IF THE VALUE IS IMMEDIATE,   @G@@@@. AND IV IS THE VALUE ITHW
)@@G@@SELF. K=1,2,3,4=> FORVAL, FROMVAL, TOVAL, BYVAL.@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     HX
)@@G@@@H@@@@        PROC   *0                     . NOTE: ONE-PASS PROC FLAG RHY
)@@G@@EQUIRED     @#@@@@G$$LAN*  NAME     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@W(1)    EQU    KW(HZ
)@@G@@1)                  . GET KEYWORD WHICH DESCRIBES FIELD     @[@@@@.     IA
)@@G@@@E@@@@.       ***** BREAK DOWN SOURCE IMAGE, SET DEFAULTS *****   @[@@@@IB
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. SCAN ALL FIELDS FOR DEFINING KEYWORDS   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@IC
)@@G@@K3      EQU    MASKED*(W(1)=LOOKFOR)+TO*((W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0)  @G@@@@FI*(1)ID
)@@G@@  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FOR)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FOR)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FOR)   @G@@@@IE
)@@G@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FROM)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FROM)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FROM)IF
)@@G@@@D@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=K3)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=K3)+;   @B@@@@      IG
)@@G@@  3*(P(VI+3,1)=K3)+4*(P(VI+4,1)=K3) @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=BIH
)@@G@@Y)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=BY)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=BY)@G@@@@FI*(7)  EQU    FI(4)          II
)@@G@@        . INITIALIZE LAST FIELD POINTER   @H@@@@I DO     3 , DO FI(I)>FIIJ
)@@G@@(7) ,FI*(7) EQU FI(I) . FIND LAST FIELD USER GAVE US  @I@@@@LF(1)   EQU IK
)@@G@@   0+P                    . SET INDEX OF LAST FIELD + 1 IN CASE OF D    IL
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'TO' SPECIFICATION TO ZERO  @[@@@@IM
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@ DO (K3=MASKED)++(FI(3)>VI) , GO G$$L01 . IF 'TO' EXPLICIT, IN
)@@G@@SKIP THIS   @H@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    LF(1)                  . FORCE IT INTO IO
)@@G@@THE NEXT AVAIL SUBFIELD @E@@@@P*(FI(3),1) EQU TO                    . SEIP
)@@G@@T ITS KEYWORD     @F@@@@P*(FI(3),4) EQU XU                    . MAKE IT IQ
)@@G@@AN IMMEDIATE ZERO @G@@@@LF(1)   EQU    LF(1)+1                . BUMP NEXIR
)@@G@@T USABLE FIELD POINTER  @G@@@@G$$L01* NAME                          . ENIS
)@@G@@D OF DEFAULT FOR 'TO' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. 'BY' FIELD (IF GIVEN) IT
)@@G@@IS VARIABLE LENGTH. FORCE TO FIXED FORMAT @C@@@@. BY MOVING UP/DOWN/OFFSIU
)@@G@@ET TO THE FIFTH SUBFIELD@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , GO G$$L02      IV
)@@G@@        . IF 'BY' OMITTED, SKIP THIS@E@@@@ DO P(FI(4),4)=U ,P*(FI(4),4) IW
)@@G@@EQU XU . FORCE SIGN EXTENSION @F@@@@NB      EQU    0+P(FI(4))           IX
)@@G@@  . NO OF SPECS IN 'BY' FIELD @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (P(FI(4),NB)>0)++(IY
)@@G@@NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST     @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($AP(PIZ
)@@G@@(FI(4),NB))>0)++(NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST@G@@@@P*(FI(4),5) JA
)@@G@@EQU P(FI(4),NB)           . FORCE UP DOWN OFFSET TO FIELD 5 @F@@@@P*(FI(JB
)@@G@@4),NB) EQU 0                    . AND RESET WHEREVER IT WAS @H@@@@G$$L02JC
)@@G@@* NAME                          . END KEYWORD FARBLING FOR 'BY' FIELD   JD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE:  THE CODE BELOW WILL GENERATE (USUALLY) SPURIOJE
)@@G@@US R-FLAGS IF     @F@@@@. THE FIELDS BEING EXAMINED ARE EXTERNAL (I.E. UJF
)@@G@@-FLAGGED) EVEN    @F@@@@. THOUGH WE ARE STRIPPING OFF FIELDS WHICH HAVE JG
)@@G@@NO RELOCATION (THE@E@@@@. X AND J FIELDS), AND EVEN THOUGH THE PORTION OJH
)@@G@@F UV WHICH  @F@@@@. MAY CARRY RELOCATION (THE U-FIELD) IS NOT MASKED AT JI
)@@G@@THE POINT   @A@@@@. OF ITS USE. <EXPLETIVE DELETED>   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@JJ
)@@G@@          ON        G$MASM=0          . BEGIN ASM CODE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@JK
)@@G@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@JL
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ JM
)@@G@@0,P(FI(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @[@@@@JN
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)>0777777 ; IF THE USER EQUF'D THE JO
)@@G@@SYMBOL@E@@@@        ,IM(I) EQU 07017000000**(G$NOFO UV(I))=07000000000  JP
)@@G@@@F@@@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)<01000000 ; IF HE DIDN'T EQUF IT ..     JQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@        ,IM(I) EQU (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=P(FI(I),4)**016) . CHECK FJR
)@@G@@OR EXPLICI  @E@@@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)<01000000) ; IF NOT JS
)@@G@@EQUF'D@F@@@@        ,IV(I) EQU P(FI(I),2)         . USE THE VALUE HE GAVJT
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)>0777777) ; BUT IF HE EQUFJU
)@@G@@'D IT @G@@@@        ,IV(I) EQU + (G$NOFO UV(I)**G$UMSK) . PRAY ITS NOT EJV
)@@G@@XTERNAL     @H@@@@I DO     4 , DO IV(I)>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU IV(I)++077777JW
)@@G@@7000000 . SIGN EXTEND   @I@@@@I DO 2 ,APIV(I+1) EQU IV(I+1)         . FUJX
)@@G@@DGE ABSOLUTE PART FOR LATER MASM TESTS    @E@@@@          OFF           JY
)@@G@@              . END OF ASM CODE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          ON      JZ
)@@G@@  G$MASM=1          . BEGIN MASM CODE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@I         $RKA
)@@G@@EPEAT   4                 . DO ALL THIS FOR I=1,2,3,4 @G@@@@APU       EQKB
)@@G@@U       $AP(P(FI(I),2))   . STRIP U-FIELD OF RELOCATION     @[@@@@.     KC
)@@G@@@D@@@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     KD
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ 0,P(FIKE
)@@G@@(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @G@@@@APUV  KF
)@@G@@    EQU       $AP(UV(I))        . APUV IS ABSOLUTE PART OF UV(I)  @[@@@@KG
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@IM(I) EQU APU>0777777-> ; . IF THE USER EQUF'D THE SYMBOL   KH
)@@G@@@H@@@@ 07017000000**(G$NOFO APUV)=07000000000! ; THEN SET TRUE IF 'U' ANKI
)@@G@@D NO XDESIG @I@@@@ (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=P(FI(I),4)**016) . ELSE SET TRUEKJ
)@@G@@ IF EXPLICIT 'U', NO XREG     @D@@@@IV(I) EQU IM(I)**(APU<01000000)-> ; KK
)@@G@@  . IF NOT EQUF'D @F@@@@       P(FI(I),2)! ;      . USE THE VALUE HE GAVKL
)@@G@@E IN SUBFIELD 2   @F@@@@    + (G$NOFO APUV**G$UMSK)           . ELSE PRAKM
)@@G@@Y ITS NOT EXTERNAL@H@@@@ DO $AP(IV(I))>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU -(0777777-IV(IKN
)@@G@@)) . SIGN EXTEND (IF NEEDED)  @G@@@@APIV(I)   EQU       $AP(IV(I))      KO
)@@G@@  . NO RELOCATION FOR LATER TESTS.  @F@@@@          $ENDR               KP
)@@G@@        . END OF $REPEAT STRUCTURE  @E@@@@          OFF                 KQ
)@@G@@        . END OF MASM CODE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. APIV(2) AND APIV(3) ARKR
)@@G@@E NON-RELOCATABLE EQUIVALENTS OF    @D@@@@. IV(2...3) FOR USE BY MASM INKS
)@@G@@ COMPARISONS OF THE FORM@C@@@@. IV(2)>IV(3). WHEN USING @ASM, APIV(I)=IVKT
)@@G@@(I).  @E@@@@. ***NOTE*** WE ASSUME THAT IV(I) WILL NOT BE UPDATED PRIOR KU
)@@G@@@A@@@@. TO THE USE OF APIV(I), FOR I=2,3  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@KV
)@@G@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'BY' SPECIFICATION TO +-1, DEPENDING UPON     @F@@@@KW
)@@G@@. THE SIGN OF TO-FROM, AND/OR THE USER'S UP/DOWN/OFFSET SPEC.     @[@@@@KX
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO FI(4)>VI , GO G$$L03              . SKIP THIKY
)@@G@@S IF USER GAVE THIS FIELD     @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    LF(1)                KZ
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WHERE ITS GOING  @H@@@@ DO (W(1)=VARY)++(W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , LA
)@@G@@GO G$$L03 . SKIP FOR SPECIFIC LOOP TYPE   @F@@@@IV(4)   EQU    1        LB
)@@G@@              . INITIAL ASSUMPTION IS +1  @G@@@@ DO ((W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0)**LC
)@@G@@IM(2)**IM(3)  ; UNLESS WE KNOW TO-FROM VALUES   @F@@@@        ,IV(4) EQULD
)@@G@@ 1-2*(APIV(2)>APIV(3))  . THEN USE SIGN OF DIFF @G@@@@ DO (IV(4)=1)**(P(LE
)@@G@@FI(4),5)=DOWN) ,IV(4) EQU -1 . MAKE IMPLICIT EXPLICIT @F@@@@P*(FI(4),2) LF
)@@G@@EQU     IV(4)             . SAVE FOR USE BY GENERATOR @D@@@@P*(FI(4),4) LG
)@@G@@EQU XU  . MAKE SURE HE KNOWS ITS IMMEDIATE@E@@@@UV(4)   EQUF   IV(4),,XULH
)@@G@@              . MARK IT AS IMMEDIATE@G@@@@IM(4)   EQU    1              LI
)@@G@@        . AND TURN ON THE IMMEDIATE FLAG  @G@@@@G$$L03* NAME            LJ
)@@G@@              . END DEFAULT PROCESSING OF 'BY'  @G@@@@ DO P(FI(4),5)=0 ,LK
)@@G@@P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(VI,3) . SET USER'S SIGN, IF ANY     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@LL
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@ DO (W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , GO G$$L30      . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO DLM
)@@G@@O VARY@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.       ***** PROCESS 'LOOKFOR' LOOPLN
)@@G@@ (I.E. SEARCH, MASKED SEARCH) ***** @[@@@@.     @H@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    0  LO
)@@G@@                    . FLAG NO CODE APPEARS AT THE BOTTOM    @[@@@@.     LP
)@@G@@@A@@@@. LOAD MASK AND REPEAT REGISTERS    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (FI(3)>VLQ
)@@G@@I)**(P(FI(3))>1) , I$ 023,,2,,,UV(3) . LOAD MASK REG (R2)   @F@@@@ DO FILR
)@@G@@(1)>VI , I$ 023,,1,,,UV(1)      . AND REPEAT COUNT (R1)     @[@@@@.     LS
)@@G@@@A@@@@. INITIALIZE REG USED AS TABLE INDEX@[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (P(FI(4)LT
)@@G@@,5)=OFFSET)**1-IM(4) , G$$EFL 2,1 . OFFSET NEEDS IMMEDIATE BY     @F@@@@LU
)@@G@@OFV     EQU    IM(4)*(P(FI(4),5)=OFFSET)*IV(4) . SET OFFSET VALUE @H@@@@LV
)@@G@@FI*(6)  EQU    OFV                    . AND SAVE FOR USE BY CODE GENERATLW
)@@G@@OR    @E@@@@ DO FI(2)=VI , END                    . IF NO 'FROM', QUIT  LX
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,2                 . REQUIRE THAT A 'BY' SPLY
)@@G@@EC APPEARED @H@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(4) , GO G$$L21          . IF BOTH IMMEDILZ
)@@G@@ATE, GO USE CONSTANT    @D@@@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2)   . LXMA
)@@G@@ XN,FROM    @F@@@@ DO OFV=0 , I$ 046,,P(VI,2),,,UV(4)   . IF NO OFFSET, MB
)@@G@@LXI XN,BY   @C@@@@ DO OFV=0 , END                       . AND QUIT@G@@@@MC
)@@G@@ DO P(VI,2)>X11 , AH P(VI,2),(+OFV,-OFV) . IF OVERLAPPED, ADD OFFSET IN MD
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , ANX,U P(VI,2),OFV    . IF NONOVERLAPPED, USE BRUTME
)@@G@@E FORCE     @B@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , LXI,U P(VI,2),OFV    .   @D@@@@ DO 1 MF
)@@G@@, END                           . THEN GET OUT  @I@@@@G$$L21* NAME      MG
)@@G@@                    . COME HERE IF FROM AND BY BOTH IMMEDIATE     @G@@@@MH
)@@G@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4),IV(2)-OFV) . LOAD XREG FROM CONS  MI
)@@G@@@]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.       ****** PROCESS 'VARY' (NORMAMJ
)@@G@@L LOOP) SPECIFICATION *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$L30* NAME            MK
)@@G@@              . MARK START OF VARY CHECKING     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ORIGOPML
)@@G@@     EQU      +W(1)             . REMEMBER ORIGINAL OPCODE  @[@@@@.     MM
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO FI(1)>VI , GO G$$L34              . IF 'FOR', ASSUME JGD IMMEDMN
)@@G@@IATELY@F@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4)=0 , GO G$$L35 . NO FUDGE IF ALL NOT MO
)@@G@@KNOWN @D@@@@ DO (APIV(2)>0)**(IV(3)=0)**(IV(4)=-1)=0 , GO G$$L35  @G@@@@MP
)@@G@@FI*(1)  EQU    FI(2)                  . PUT 'FOR' IN P WHERE 'FROM' WAS MQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI                     . AND INVALIDATE THE 'FROM' MR
)@@G@@@G@@@@IV(1)   EQU    IV(2)+1                . FORVAL IS ONE MORE THAN FRMS
)@@G@@OMVAL @G@@@@IM(1)   EQU    1                      . TURN ON IMMEDIATE 'FMT
)@@G@@OR' FLAG    @D@@@@UV(1)   EQUF   IV(1),,XU              . AND SET U-SPECMU
)@@G@@@D@@@@G$$L34* NAME                          . SET OPCODE JGD@G@@@@W(1)  MV
)@@G@@  EQU    0+JGD                  . ADD ZERO TO OVERRIDE OPCODE EQU @G@@@@MW
)@@G@@ GO G$$L39                            . THEN GO GLOBALIZE THE OPCODE    MX
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                             OP CAN'T BE JGD, MUST BE TLEM\JMGI  MY
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$L35* NAME@G@@@@ DO (VARY=ORIGOP)=0 , GO G$$L40       . SKIP IF MZ
)@@G@@OPCODE EXPLICITLY GIVEN @G@@@@ DO (FI(2)=VI)++(FI(3)=VI)++(FI(4)=VI) , GNA
)@@G@@$$EFL 2,3 . REQUIRE ALL SPECS @D@@@@W(1)    EQU    0+TLEM               NB
)@@G@@  . ASSUME TLEM   @F@@@@ DO IM(3)**(IV(3)=0) ,W(1) EQU 0+JMGI . UNLESS TNC
)@@G@@O IMMEDIATE ZERO  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$L39* NAME                        ND
)@@G@@  . END DETERMINATION OF INSTR SPECIFICATION    @F@@@@P*(VI,1) EQU   W(1NE
)@@G@@)                   . FORCE OPCODE SPEC FIELD   @G@@@@ DO (VARY=ORIGOP)+NF
)@@G@@+(W(1)=ORIGOP)=0 , G$$EFL 2,011 . OPCODE MISMATCH     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NG
)@@G@@.        SET LOOP SENSE AND FLAG IF CODE AT BOTTOM OF LOOP REQUIRED     NH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L40* NAME@F@@@@ DO (W(1)=JGD)=0 , GO G$$L41        NI
)@@G@@  . IF NOT JGD, WE MUST FARBLE@F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    1                    NJ
)@@G@@  . ELSE MARK SENSE KNOWN     @I@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    1                    NK
)@@G@@  . SET FLAG THAT CODE WILL APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @D@@@@ GO G$$L49        NL
)@@G@@                    . AND WE'RE DONE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPUTE SIGN/SENNM
)@@G@@SE FOR JMGI, TLEM LOOPS, AND CHECK TERMINATION  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L41NN
)@@G@@* NAME                          . NOT JGD, DETERMINE SENSE THE HARD WAY NO
)@@G@@@H@@@@USS     EQU    (P(FI(4),5)=UP)-(P(FI(4),5)=DOWN) . SET USER SUPPLINP
)@@G@@ED SIGN     @D@@@@BYS     EQU    IM(4)*(1-2*(IV(4)<0))  . SIGN FROM 'BY'NQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@FTS     EQU    (IM(2)**IM(3))*(1-2*(APIV(2)>APIV(3))) . FROMTO SIGNR
)@@G@@N     @G@@@@ DO FTS*BYS=-1 , G$$EFL 2,5               . N.G. IF SIGNS DONS
)@@G@@N'T AGREE   @E@@@@MYS     EQU    FTS+BYS                . GET MY OWN SIGNT
)@@G@@N FLAG@F@@@@ DO MYS*USS=-1 , G$$EFL 2,6               . BETTER AGREE WITNU
)@@G@@H HIS @F@@@@SIGN    EQU    MYS+USS                . GET THE SIGN WE'LL UNV
)@@G@@SE    @F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    (SIGN=0)=0             . ON IF WE KNOW LOOP SNW
)@@G@@ENSE  @H@@@@P*(VI,3) EQU   SIGN                   . REMEMBER FOR BOTTOM NX
)@@G@@OF LOOP USAGE     @F@@@@FI*(5) EQU (SIGN=0)++(W(1)=TLEM)**(SIGN>0)++(W(1NY
)@@G@@)=JMGI)**(SIGN<0) @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WATCH OUT FOR AX/ANX: TERMINATION NZ
)@@G@@CONDITION MAY NOT PASS THRU ZERO    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO 1-((W(1)=TLEM)OA
)@@G@@**IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4)) ; UNLESS TLEM AND IMMEDIATE... @E@@@@    , GO G$$OB
)@@G@@L49                       . DON'T DO THIS TEST  @E@@@@VV(1)      EQU    OC
)@@G@@  IV(2)             . SET UP START VAL    @E@@@@VV(2)      EQU      IV(3OD
)@@G@@)+IV(4)       . AND TERMINATION VAL @D@@@@          ON        G$MASM=0  OE
)@@G@@        . BEGIN ASM CODE@G@@@@  DO G$AMPR                           ; IFOF
)@@G@@ RELOCATION CAN BE DETERMINED @F@@@@    ,VK DO 2                        OG
)@@G@@  ; THEN FOR BOTH FROM AND TO @F@@@@      , DO 1-(&(VV(VK))=-2)         OH
)@@G@@  ; IF VALUE NOT ABSOLUTE     @F@@@@        ,VV(VK) EQU VV(VK)+01000    OI
)@@G@@  . FUDGE FOR ITS RELOCATION  @E@@@@VK DO 2                             OJ
)@@G@@  ; FOR BOTH LIMITS...  @G@@@@  ,VV(VK) EQU (1-(VV(VK)=0))*(1-2*(VV(VK)<OK
)@@G@@0)) . SIGN FLAG => -1, 0, +1  @F@@@@ DO VV(1)*VV(2)<1 , G$$EFL 2,4      OL
)@@G@@  . LOOP PASSES TO/THRU ZERO  @E@@@@          OFF                       OM
)@@G@@  . END OF ASM CODE     @E@@@@          ON        G$MASM=1          . BEON
)@@G@@GIN MASM CODE     @G@@@@  DO G$AMPR                           ; IF RELOCOO
)@@G@@ATION CAN BE DETERMINED @F@@@@    ,VK DO 2                          ; THOP
)@@G@@EN FOR BOTH FROM AND TO @F@@@@      , DO 1-($BA(VV(VK))=0)          ; IFOQ
)@@G@@ VALUE NOT ABSOLUTE     @F@@@@        ,VV(VK) EQU VV(VK)+01000      . FUOR
)@@G@@DGE FOR ITS RELOCATION  @E@@@@VK DO 2                               ; FOOS
)@@G@@R BOTH LIMITS...  @H@@@@  ,VV(VK) EQU (1-(VV(VK)=0))*(1-2*($AP(VV(VK))<0OT
)@@G@@)) . SIGN FLAG => -1, 0, +1   @G@@@@ DO $AP(VV(1))*$AP(VV(2))<1 , G$$EFLOU
)@@G@@ 2,4 . LOOP PASSES TO/THRU ZERO     @E@@@@          OFF                 OV
)@@G@@        . END OF MASM CODE    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L49*    NAME         OW
)@@G@@              . END SENSE/PREFERENCE DETERMINATION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@OX
)@@G@@. SIGN EXTEND NEGATIVE EQUFS TO GET 18-BIT NEGATIVE IMMEDIATES.   @[@@@@OY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@I DO 3 , DO (IM(I+1)=1)**(IV(I+1)<0) ; . FOR 2,3,4    @G@@@@OZ
)@@G@@ ,UV(I+1)   EQUF      *IV(I+1),*0,XU  . IF NEG IMMED, SET HI BITS=1     PA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. GENERATE REGISTER INITIAL LOAD CODE, IF ANY   @[@@@@PB
)@@G@@.     @I@@@@IMOP      EQU       G$FLAG(K,21)>0    . IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZE FPC
)@@G@@LAG (ZERO ON PASS 1)    @H@@@@ DO FI(1)=VI , GO G$$L51              . IFPD
)@@G@@ 'FOR' NOT GIVEN, GO DO FROM/BY     @G@@@@RR      EQU    027*(P(VI,2)<A4PE
)@@G@@)+023*(P(VI,2)>R1-1) . OPCODE IF X/R REG  @B@@@@RA      EQU    077**(0+PPF
)@@G@@(VI,2)-(RR=0)*A0) @G@@@@        I$     RR+010*(RR=0),,RA,,,UV(1)-IMOP . PG
)@@G@@LOAD COUNT REGISTER     @G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,21) EQU IM(1)              . SEPH
)@@G@@T IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZATION FLAG @F@@@@ DO 1 , END                         PI
)@@G@@  . END OF REG LOAD GENERATION@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L51* NAME            PJ
)@@G@@              . HERE TO LOAD REG USING FROM/BY SPECS  @G@@@@ DO FI(2)=VIPK
)@@G@@ , END                    . NO LOAD IF 'FROM' FIELD ABSENT  @G@@@@ DO FIPL
)@@G@@(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,7                 . ERROR IF 'FROM' BUT NO 'BY' @[@@@@PM
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. IF 'BY' NOT IMMEDIATE, GEN 3 INSTRUCTIONS:    @C@@@@.   LXPN
)@@G@@ XR,FROM  ;  ANX XR,(BY)  ;  LXI XR,(BY)  @E@@@@. IF 'BY' AND 'FROM' AREPO
)@@G@@ IMMED, GEN:  LX XR,(BY,FROM-BY)    @D@@@@. IF 'BY' AND LOOP CNTRL REG IPP
)@@G@@S OVERLAPPED AREG, GEN: @F@@@@.   LX AR,(BY,BY)  ;  AH AR,(FROM)    . IFPQ
)@@G@@ 'FROM' NOT IMMEDIATE   @H@@@@. NOTE: IF LOOP REG IS NON-OVERLAPPED REG PR
)@@G@@WE MUST GEN BRUTE FORCE (3 INSTRS)  @G@@@@. WE CANNOT GEN (AX XR,(FROM) PS
)@@G@@) BECAUSE OF OVERFLOW INTO INCREMENT,     @E@@@@. E.G. (1,-1) + (2) = (2PT
)@@G@@,0) , NOT (1,1). SURPRISE, CHIEF!   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@ DO IM(4)=0 , GO GPU
)@@G@@$$L52               . IF 'BY' NOT IMMEDIATE, CANT USE LITERAL     @H@@@@PV
)@@G@@ DO (W(1)=JMGI)**IM(2)**1-G$FLAG(K,4) ; IF IMMEDIATE JMGI WITHOUT 'WHILEPW
)@@G@@'     @G@@@@ , DO IV(4)<0 , GO G$$L53             . AND DECREASING, GO OPX
)@@G@@PTIMIZE     @G@@@@ DO IM(2) , LX P(VI,2),(+IV(4),0+IV(2)-IV(4)) . LX XR,PY
)@@G@@(STEP,FROM-STEP)  @H@@@@ DO IM(2) , END                       . IF 'FROMPZ
)@@G@@' AND 'BY' ARE IMMED, DONE    @G@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , GO G$$L52          QA
)@@G@@  . IF NOT OVERLAP, BRUTE FORCE     @F@@@@        LX     P(VI,2),(+IV(4)QB
)@@G@@,0-IV(4)) . LX XR,(STEP,FROM-STEP)  @G@@@@        AH     P(VI,2),UV(2)  QC
)@@G@@        . AH FROMVAL (OVERLAP ONLY!!!)    @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @D@@@@G$$L52QD
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . BRUTE FORCE.  @E@@@@        LX     P(VQE
)@@G@@I,2),UV(2)          . LX WITH FROMVAL     @H@@@@        ANX    P(VI,2),UQF
)@@G@@V(4)          . ANX STEP TO COMPENSATE FOR INCR AT TOP@G@@@@        LXI QG
)@@G@@   P(VI,2),UV(4)          . LXI STEP TO SET UP INCREMENT    @F@@@@ DO 1 QH
)@@G@@, END                           . END OF REG INITIALIZATION @[@@@@.     QI
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$L53* NAME                          . OPTIMIZE IMMEDIATE JMGI LOQJ
)@@G@@OPS   @E@@@@        LX      P(VI,2),(+IV(4),IV(2)) . LOAD (+BY,FROM)    QK
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,21) EQU  1                   . TURN ON OPTIMIZATION FLAQL
)@@G@@G     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************QM
)@@G@@********************************************    @F@@@@.     *           QN
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LGE :QO
)@@G@@ GENERATE CODE FOR <LOOP CONTROL> FIELDS   *    @F@@@@.     *           QP
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     ************QQ
)@@G@@********************************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     QR
)@@G@@@I@@@@Q       PROC   *2                     . PF'S: 'VARY','TO','BY'  JUQS
)@@G@@MPTARG,TOP/BOT    @#@@@@G$$LGE*  NAME     @G@@@@VI      EQU    Q(1,1)   QT
)@@G@@              . INDEX IN P OF VARY SPEC FIELD   @E@@@@TI      EQU    Q(1QU
)@@G@@,2)                 . INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD @E@@@@BI      EQU    Q(1,3)   QV
)@@G@@              . INDEX OF 'BY' FIELD @E@@@@F       EQU    P(VI,1)        QW
)@@G@@        . FUNCTION REQUESTED  @H@@@@ATTOP     EQU       Q(2,2)          QX
)@@G@@  . ON IF BEING CALLED AT TOP OF LOOP     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO F=LOOKFOQY
)@@G@@R , GO G$$L80             . SPECIAL HANDLING FOR SEARCHING  @F@@@@ DO F=QZ
)@@G@@JGD , G$$FJA 070,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . JUMP TO KEEP LOOPING    @G@@@@ DO F=RA
)@@G@@JGD , END                       . FOR JGD, THAT'S ALL THERE IS    @[@@@@RB
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. TLEM/JMGI ---   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@JMF     EQU    F=JMGI   RC
)@@G@@              . TRUE IF FUNC IS JMGI@G@@@@OLAP    EQU    P(VI,2)>X11    RD
)@@G@@        . ON IF LOOP CTL REG IS OVERLAPPED@G@@@@SENU    EQU    (P(VI,3)=RE
)@@G@@0)**(ATTOP=0) . ON AT BOTTOM AND UNKNOWN SENSE  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO SERF
)@@G@@NU**1-OLAP , I$ 060+JMF,,,,,P(VI,2) . TP(TLEM) TN(JMGI) ON REG    @H@@@@RG
)@@G@@ DO SENU , I$ 074,04-OLAP*(JMF+1),0+OLAP*(P(VI,2)-A0),,,G$LABL(K,2) . J RH
)@@G@@JN JP @[@@@@.     @C@@@@ DO JMF , GO G$$L70 . JMGI LOOPS ARE SIMPLE     RI
)@@G@@@E@@@@PTI2      EQU       P(TI,2)           . 'TO' FIELD UFIELD   @E@@@@RJ
)@@G@@PBI2      EQU       P(BI,2)           . 'BY' FIELD UFIELD   @F@@@@ DO G$RK
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,PTI2 EQU $AP(PTI2)      . JUST THE ABSOLUTE PART    @F@@@@ DO G$RL
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,PBI2 EQU $AP(PBI2)      . JUST THE ABSOLUTE PART    @G@@@@TUHI  RM
)@@G@@  EQU    3*(PTI2<0)+2*P(TI,*3)+P(TI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON    @D@@@@RN
)@@G@@TU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(TI,4),,P(TI,3),TUHI,P(TI,2)) @G@@@@BUHI    EQU RO
)@@G@@   3*(PBI2<0)+2*P(BI,*3)+P(BI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON    @D@@@@BU    RP
)@@G@@  EQU    + (I$ 0,P(BI,4),,P(BI,3),BUHI,P(BI,2)) @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 074RQ
)@@G@@,06,0,P(VI,2),2,0   . AT TOP AX INCR WITH A NOP @E@@@@          I$      RR
)@@G@@  047,,P(VI,2),,,TU . TLEM ON 'TO' FIELD  @B@@@@        I$     074,04,,,RS
)@@G@@,Q(2,1) . JUMP    @G@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 025,,P(VI,2),,,BU      . UNDO FUDRT
)@@G@@GE WITH ANX OF INCR     @E@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . THRU
)@@G@@AT'S ALL FOR TLEM @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. HANDLE JMGI LOOPS (WHICH TERMINATERV
)@@G@@ AT ZERO)   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$L70*   NAME    @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 051RW
)@@G@@,017,0,P(VI,2),,0 . TNZ REG (LAST TIME CHECK)   @B@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 074RX
)@@G@@,04,,,,Q(2,1)       .   @C@@@@        I$     074,012,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . RY
)@@G@@JMGI  @#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE SEARCH/MASKED SRZ
)@@G@@EARCH. NOTE: SINCE THIS IS ALWAYS CALLED  @E@@@@. AT THE PHYSICAL TOP OFSA
)@@G@@ THE LOOP BY REPEAT, THE VALUES OF  @B@@@@. THE ARRAY FI(N) ARE ALWAYS ASB
)@@G@@VAILABLE    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L80* NAME@H@@@@IC      EQU    VI-1     SC
)@@G@@              . INDEX IN P OF CONDITION TEST FIELD    @H@@@@KWD     EQU SD
)@@G@@   P(IC,2)                . GET KEYWORD FROM CONDITION SPEC FIELD @F@@@@SE
)@@G@@MSF     EQU    FI(3)>VI               . ON IF SEARCH IS MASKED    @G@@@@SF
)@@G@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(1,KWD,1)+010*(1-MSF)-052*MSF . MODIFY TO A SEARCH   SG
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO   MSF , I$ 071,FUN,P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(IC,3)+FI(6)SH
)@@G@@ . MS-@H@@@@ DO 1-MSF , I$ FUN,P(IC,5),P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(ISI
)@@G@@C,3)+FI(6) . S-   @E@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,Q(2,1)  . AT NOFIND,  JSJ
)@@G@@UMP TO ATEND@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @ @@@@/. *** MISCELLANEOUS UTISK
)@@G@@LITIES@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. PROCS TO CONSERVE TABLE SPACE BY SAVING ARGUMESL
)@@G@@NTS IN RE-USABLE ARRAY SPACE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          PROC      *0  SM
)@@G@@@I@@@@G$$SVA* NAME                          . SAVE ARRAY P IN STANDARD ASN
)@@G@@RGUMENT ARRAY     @F@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(3)+1        . BUMP ARGSO
)@@G@@ PUSHDOWN LEVEL   @D@@@@G$CTR**(3) EQU K                      . SAVE THESP
)@@G@@ LEVEL@^@@@@G$ARGS**(K) EQU +P-1    @A@@@@N DO P-1 ,G$ARGS**(K,N) EQU +0SQ
)@@G@@+P(N) @C@@@@N DO P-1 ,M DO P(N) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU +P(N,M)@F@@@@N DO PSR
)@@G@@-1 ,M DO P(N) , DO P(N,*M) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU *0+P(N,M) . @#@@@@      SS
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DECODE A U-FIELD INTO ITS COST
)@@G@@NSTITUENT ELEMENTS. THIS PROC USES  @G@@@@. SUBTRACTION TO AVOID SPURIOUSU
)@@G@@S R-FLAGS WHICH MIGHT OTHERWISE ARISE.    @F@@@@. IN ADDITION, IT DOES NSV
)@@G@@OT ALTER THE FORM OF THE ORIGINAL U-FIELD,@F@@@@. SINCE IT IS UNKNOWN WHSW
)@@G@@ETHER THE U FIELD ALREADY HAS FORM OR NOT.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        DEF SX
)@@G@@@^@@@@G$JBIT(1) EQU 1*/29     @^@@@@G$JBIT(2) EQU 1*/28     @^@@@@G$JBITSY
)@@G@@(3) EQU 1*/27     @^@@@@G$JBIT(4) EQU 1*/26     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$XBITSZ
)@@G@@(1) EQU 1*/21     @^@@@@G$XBIT(2) EQU 1*/20     @^@@@@G$XBIT(3) EQU 1*/1TA
)@@G@@9     @^@@@@G$XBIT(4) EQU 1*/18     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$HIBI(1) EQU 1*/1TB
)@@G@@7     @^@@@@G$HIBI(2) EQU 1*/16     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$JBITS EQU +(I$ 0TC
)@@G@@,017,,,,0)       . MASK FOR J-DESEG @D@@@@G$XBITS EQU +(I$ 0,,,017,,0)  TD
)@@G@@     . MASK FOR X-DESEG @D@@@@G$HBITS EQU +(I$ 0,,,,2,0)         . MASK TE
)@@G@@FOR H-DESEG @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Q       PROC        *2                .   TF
)@@G@@@B@@@@G$$DCU* NAME                          .   @E@@@@I       EQU     Q(TG
