)@@G@@              . DATE    @B@@@H   E$SKIP  2                          .   OM
)@@G@@@C@@@H   E$DAT5                             . DATE    @C@@@H   E$PRTG  1ON
)@@G@@,2                        . PRINT IT@D@@@H ENDBEG                       OO
)@@G@@        . END OF ASCTEST@[@@@H/.    @C@@@H .   XAF (CASE-PRESERVING TRANOP
)@@G@@SLATION) TEST     @[@@@H .    @G@@@H . ALTERNATE: ASCII TO FIELDATA, THEOQ
)@@G@@N FIELDATA TO ASCII, FOR EACH FCN.  @[@@@H .    @ @@@H . PHASE 1: ASCII OR
)@@G@@TO FIELDATA @G@@@H .   OUTPUT BUFFER IS EBUF. INPUT BUFFER IS XAFBUF (INOS
)@@G@@ITIAL STRING)     @E@@@H .   OR ASCII STRING IN EBUF1 FROM LAST FD-TO-ASOT
)@@G@@CII PHASE.  @[@@@H .    @ @@@H . PHASE 2: FIELDATA TO ASCII @G@@@H .   OOU
)@@G@@UTPUT BUFFER IS EBUF1. INPUT BUFFER (IF ANY) IS FIELDATA STRING   @C@@@HOV
)@@G@@ .   IN EBUF FROM LAST ASCII TO FIELDATA PHASE. @[@@@H .    @F@@@H . ON OW
)@@G@@RETURN FROM ANY ALFA ROUTINE (EFDX$,ECOPY$,EPACK$,EMSG$,ETC)@G@@@H . WHEOX
)@@G@@RE MODE TRANSLATION HAS TAKEN PLACE, A0 IS ADDRESS OF LOCATION    @G@@@HOY
)@@G@@ . WHERE LAST NON-BLANK CHARACTER WAS STORED (OR ZERO IF NONE STORED)   OZ
)@@G@@@B@@@H . AND A1 IS NUMBER OF CHARACTERS STORED. @[@@@H .    @B@@@HXAFTESPA
)@@G@@T                               .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE             PB
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@H   P$RINT  (0102,('ASCII STRING'))    .   @E@@@H   LA PC
)@@G@@     A0,(0212,XAFBUF)           . DISPLAY XAF-BUFFER  @B@@@H   ER      APD
)@@G@@PRINT$                    .   @D@@@H   LX      X9,(1,0)                 PE
)@@G@@  . FUNCTION INDEX@F@@@H   LA,U    A13,0                      . BEGIN WIPF
)@@G@@TH FIELDATA OUTPUT@I@@@H   SNZ     XAF                        . SET EXTEPG
)@@G@@NDED (CASE-PRESERVING) XLATE FLA    @B@@@H   REPEAT                     PH
)@@G@@        .   @G@I@H      IF A13,IS,ZERO THEN             . XLATION IS ASCPI
)@@G@@II-TO-FIELDATA    @G@@@I      IF ZERO,IN,A13 THEN             . XLATION PJ
)@@G@@IS ASCII-TO-FIELDATA    @E@@@H         LX,U    X7,1                 . INPK
)@@G@@PUT MODE IS ASCII @G@@@H         LA,U    A0,EBUF              . EBUF IS PL
)@@G@@FIELDATA OUTPUT BUFFER  @G@@@H      ELSE                            . XLPM
)@@G@@ATION IS FIELDATA-TO-ASCII    @F@@@H         LX,U    X7,0               PN
)@@G@@  . INPUT MODE IS FIELDATA    @G@@@H         LA,U    A0,EBUF1           PO
)@@G@@  . ASCII OUTPUT BUFFER IS EBUF1    @E@@@H      ENDIF                   PP
)@@G@@        . END OF FD/ASCII TEST@E@@@H      LX      X8,A13                PQ
)@@G@@  . X8 IS OUTPUT MODE   @E@@@H      SX      X7,EASCIN               . STPR
)@@G@@ASH INPUT MODE    @E@@@H      SX      X8,EASC                 . STASH OUPS
)@@G@@TPUT MODE   @H@@@H      SA      A0,ILOC                 . STASH OUTPUT BPT
)@@G@@UFFER ADDRESS IN PACKET @G@@@H      CALL    ECLOSNP                 . CLPU
)@@G@@OSE, REOPEN EDIT$. CHECK REGS.@B@@@H      E$CLEAR                       PV
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@H      CALL    MUSTBEQW                . WE MUST BE IN QUARTEPW
)@@G@@RWORD MODE  @G@@@H      CALL    XJUMP                   . PERFORM SPECIFPX
)@@G@@IED ALFA FUNCTION @F@@@H   ESCAPE WHEN A0,IS,NEG              . AS RETURPY
)@@G@@NED FROM XJUMP    @D@@@H   OTHERWISE                          . NOT DONEPZ
)@@G@@ YET  @G@@@H      CALL    XAFSUB                  . DISPLAY A0,A1 FROM AQA
)@@G@@LFA RTNS    @E@@@H      LA      A0,XAFLIT,X8            . FETCH PRINT$ LQB
)@@G@@ITERAL@G@@@H      ER      PRINT$                  . 'ASCII STRING' OR 'FQC
)@@G@@D STRING'   @C@@@H      E$PRTG  -1,2                    . PRINT IT@E@I@HQD
)@@G@@      IF A13,IS,ZERO THEN             . OUTPUT WAS FIELDATA @E@@@I      QE
)@@G@@IF A13,EQ,(0)  THEN             . OUTPUT WAS FIELDATA @E@@@H         LA,QF
)@@G@@U    A13,1                . SWITCH TO ASCII     @E@@@H      ELSE        QG
)@@G@@                    . OUTPUT WAS ASCII,   @F@@@H         LA,U    A13,0  QH
)@@G@@              . SO SWITCH TO FIELDATA     @E@@@H      ENDIF             QI
)@@G@@              . END OF A13 INVERSION@C@@@H   ENDREP                     QJ
)@@G@@        . AGAIN   @D@@@H ENDBEG                               . END OF XQK
)@@G@@AFTEST@[@@@H .    @B@@@H        CONSTS                        .   @B@@@HQL
)@@G@@XAFLIT                                .   @B@@@H        +       0102,('FQM
)@@G@@D STRING   ')  .  @B@@@H        +       0102,('ASCII STRING')  .  @[@@@HQN
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@H        INSTRS                        .   @[@@@H/.    @#@@@HQO
)@@G@@ .   AEDIT$ TEST  @[@@@H .    @B@@@HAEDITEST                            QP
)@@G@@   .  @B@I@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE                     .   @B@@@I BEGIN SUBROQQ
)@@G@@UTINE SAVE,X9,X10         .   @F@@@H   ASCII                            QR
)@@G@@  . DEFINE ASCII CHARACTER SET@D@@@H   CALL    STAT                     QS
)@@G@@  . DISPLAY STATUS@G@@@H   A$EMSG  AMSG                       . INSERT 'QT
)@@G@@COL,CHAR,SKIP,COLN'     @C@I@H   REPEAT VARY,R10 FOR,U(4)           . 4 QU
)@@G@@GROUPS@H@@@I   REPEAT VARY,X10 FROM,(4,1),,H1 TO,(4,1),,H2 BY,(-10,-1),,QV
)@@G@@XH2 . 4 GROUPS    @F@@@H      REPEAT VARY,R11 FOR,U(10)       . 10 STARSQW
)@@G@@ FOR EACH GROUP   @C@@@H         A$ECHAR '*'                  . 10 STARSQX
)@@G@@@B@@@H      ENDREP                          .   @D@@@H      A$ECOLN     QY
)@@G@@                    . COL # IN A0   @F@@@H      A$ECOL  10,A0           QZ
)@@G@@        . ADD 10 (SKIP 10 COLS.)    @F@@@H   ENDREP                     RA
)@@G@@        .                 . AGAIN   @E@@@H   ACLOSE                     RB
)@@G@@        . CLOSE, PRINT, OPEN  @B@J@I          SLJ       TON$            RC
)@@G@@  .   @C@I@H   REPEAT VARY,R10 FOR,U(4)           . 4 GROUPS@I@@@I   REPRD
)@@G@@EAT VARY,X10,DOWN FROM,(4,1),,H1 TO,(4,1),,H2 BY,(-10,-1),,XH2 . 4 GROUPRE
)@@G@@S     @#@J@I          FIELDATA@B@J@I          SX        X10,('X10   '),,RF
)@@G@@H2    @B@J@I          P$RINT    (0101,('X10   ')) .   @#@J@I          ASRG
)@@G@@CII   @D@@@H      A$ESKIP 10                      . SKIP 10 SPACES@C@I@HRH
)@@G@@      REPEAT VARY,R11 FOR,U(10)       . 10 STARS@F@@@I      REPEAT VARY,RI
)@@G@@X9,UP FROM,(2,11),,H1 TO,(2,11),,H2 . 10 STARS  @#@J@I          FIELDATARJ
)@@G@@@B@J@I          SX        X9,('X9    '),,H2     @B@J@I          P$RINT  RK
)@@G@@  (0101,('X9    ')) .   @ @J@I.         .$SNAP    'XREGS ',4@#@J@I      RL
)@@G@@    ASCII   @C@@@H         A$ECHAR '*'                  . 10 STARS@D@@@HRM
)@@G@@      ENDREP                          . LIKE THIS     @C@@@H   ENDREP   RN
)@@G@@                          . AGAIN   @E@@@H   ACLOSE                     RO
)@@G@@        . CLOSE, PRINT, OPEN  @^@K@I          SLJ TOFF$     @B@@@H   A$ERP
)@@G@@FD1  ('12345')                  .   @B@@@H   A$ESKIP 1                  RQ
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@H   A$EFD2  ('12345')                  . HAH     @C@@@HRR
)@@G@@   A$ESKIP 1                          . 1 SPACE @D@@@H   A$ECHAR '*'    RS
)@@G@@                    . INSERT '*'    @G@@@H   P$RINT  (0214,EBUF)        RT
)@@G@@        . FD PRINT. JUST FOR THE RECORD.  @B@@@H   ACLOSE               RU
)@@G@@              .   @D@@@H   A$ECOPY LACOPY,ACOPY               . BEGIN CORV
)@@G@@PY    @B@@@H   ACLOSE                             .   @D@@@H   A$EPACK LRW
)@@G@@ACOPY,ACOPY               . BEGIN PACK    @B@@@H   ACLOSE               RX
)@@G@@              .   @C@@@H   A$ETD                              . TIME    RY
)@@G@@@C@@@H   A$ESKIP 3                          . SKIP    @B@@@H   A$EDAT1  RZ
)@@G@@                          .   @C@@@H   A$EDITX                          SA
)@@G@@  . OUT     @C@@@H   A$EDITR                            . BACK IN @C@@@HSB
)@@G@@   A$ESKIP 3                          . SKIP    @B@@@H   A$EDAT2        SC
)@@G@@                    .   @C@@@H   A$ESKIP 3                          . SKSD
)@@G@@IP    @B@@@H   A$EDAT3                            .   @C@@@H   A$ESKIP 3SE
)@@G@@                          . SKIP    @B@@@H   A$EDAT4                    SF
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@H   A$ESKIP 3                          . SKIP    @B@@@HSG
)@@G@@   A$EDAT5                            .   @C@@@H   A$ESKIP 3            SH
)@@G@@              . SKIP    @B@@@H   ACLOSE  1                          .   SI
)@@G@@@[@@@H   .  @D@@@H   AOCT    1,10,1,,U                  . FREE FORMAT   SJ
)@@G@@@C@@@H   AOCT    2,8,1,,U                   . FIXED   @C@@@H   AOCT    2SK
)@@G@@,8,(0123456765432)        . DITTO   @D@@@HI       DO      2 , ADEC I    SL
)@@G@@        . DECIMAL STUFF @D@@@H   ACLOSE  1                          . PRSM
)@@G@@INT IT.     @D@@@H   A$EDITX                            . CLOSE AEDIT$. SN
)@@G@@@G@@@H   LA,U    15,1                       . SWITCH TO MINOR REGISTER SSO
)@@G@@ET    @G@@@H   A$EDIT  AEPKTF                     . OPEN WITH FLOATING PSP
)@@G@@OINT PACKET @F@@@H   A$EMSG  AMSGF                      . FIRE UP THE MSSQ
)@@G@@G STREAM.   @D@@@HI       DO      6 , AFLO I-1          . FLOATING POINTSR
)@@G@@@B@@@H   FIELDATA                            .  @E@@@H ENDBEG           SS
)@@G@@                    . END OF AEDITEST     @[@@@H/.    @D@@@H . DISPLAY SST
)@@G@@TATUS DATA. RETURN WITH A0 = QW MODE.     @[@@@H .    @B@@@HSTAT        SU
)@@G@@                          .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE SAVE,X8           SV
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@H   LA,U    A0,STATUS                  . ASSUME FIELDATA     SW
)@@G@@@E@@@H   IF NONZ,IN,EASCIN THEN             . WE ARE IN ASCII MODE@C@@@HSX
)@@G@@      LA,U    A0,ASTATUS              . ASCII   @E@@@H   ENDIF          SY
)@@G@@                    . END OF FD/ASCII TEST@D@@@H   E$MSG                SZ
)@@G@@              . DISPLAY STATUS@B@@@H   E$OCTV  FPS                      TA
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@H   E$MSGR                             .   @B@@@H   E$OCTV  FTB
)@@G@@PR                        .   @B@@@H   E$MSGR                           TC
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@H   E$OCTV  EASC                       .   @B@@@H   E$MSGR   TD
)@@G@@                          .   @B@@@H   E$OCTV  EASCIN                   TE
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@H   E$MSGR                             .   @C@@@H   E$OCTV  2TF
)@@G@@,X1,S6                    . QWM     @B@@@H   E$MSGR                     TG
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@H   E$CHAR  SPC                        .   @B@@@H   E$MTH
)@@G@@SGR                             .   @B@@@H   E$CHAR  DPC                TI
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@H   E$MSGR                             .   @B@@@H   E$OTJ
)@@G@@CTV  SPCA                       .   @B@@@H   E$MSGR                     TK
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@H   E$OCTV  DPCA                       .   @E@@@H   E$PTL
)@@G@@RTG  1,2                        . PRINT, CLEAR BUFFER @E@@@H   CALL    RTM
)@@G@@EGCHK                     . CHECK MODE IN PACKET@D@@@H ENDBEG           TN
)@@G@@                    . END OF STAT   @[@@@H .    @B@@@H . DISPLAY WORD COTO
)@@G@@UNT OF CURRENT IMAGE    @[@@@H .    @B@@@HCNTSUB                        TP
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE SAVE,A10            .   @G@@@H   SA TQ
)@@G@@     A1,A10                     . SAVE CHAR STORED COUNT (IF ANY) @D@@@HTR
)@@G@@   E$WRDN                             . GET WORD COUNT@D@@@H   E$DECF  8TS
)@@G@@                          . DISPLAY IT    @C@@@H   LA,U    A1,8         TT
)@@G@@              . 8 SPACES@D@@@H   LA      A0,A10                     . GETU
)@@G@@T CHAR COUNT@E@@@H   LA      A3,EASC                    . OUTPUT ASCII FTV
)@@G@@LAG   @E@@@H   IF A3,NE,EASCIN THEN               . XLATION IN PROGRESS TW
)@@G@@@D@@@H      E$DECF                          . DISPLAY IT    @B@@@H   ENDTX
)@@G@@IF                              .   @B@@@H ENDBEG                       TY
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@H .    @G@@@H . PRESET UNCHANGABLE REGS (X4-X6,A6-A8,R4TZ
)@@G@@-R9) WITH THE WORD 'SECRET',  @ @@@H . FOR LATER CHECKS BY REGCHK.@[@@@HUA
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@H . RETURN WITH A0=PACKET, A1=PACKET TYPE  @[@@@H .    @B@@@HUB
)@@G@@REGSET                                .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE       UC
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@H   DL      A4,('SECRETSECRET')        . A4,A5 HAUD
)@@G@@VE 'SECRET' @G@@@H   CALL    GETPKTTYPE                 . RETURN W/ PACKUE
)@@G@@ET TYPE IN A1     @G@@@H   IF A1,IS,ZERO THEN                 . NOT CURRUF
)@@G@@ENTLY IN EDIT MODE,     @D@@@H      DS      A4,X1                   . STUG
)@@G@@ASH IN X1,X2@D@@@H      SA      A4,X3                   . STASH IN X3   UH
)@@G@@@E@@@H   ENDIF                              . END OF X1-X3 STASH  @C@@@HUI
)@@G@@   SA      A4,X4                      . AND X4  @D@@@H   DS      A4,X5  UJ
)@@G@@                    . AND X5,X6     @D@@@H   DL      A6,A4              UK
)@@G@@        . AND A6,A7     @C@@@H   LA      A8,A4                      . ANUL
)@@G@@D A8  @D@@@H   DS      A4,R2                      . AND R2,R3     @D@@@HUM
)@@G@@   DS      A4,R4                      . AND R4,R5     @D@@@H   DS      AUN
)@@G@@4,R6                      . AND R6,R7     @D@@@H   DS      A4,R8        UO
)@@G@@              . AND R8,R9     @D@@@H ENDBEG                             UP
)@@G@@  . END OF REGSET.@[@@@H/.    @ @@@H . XAF TEST - DISPLAY A0,A1   @[@@@HUQ
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@HXAFSUB                                .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUR
)@@G@@UTINE   SAVE,A9,A10       .   @D@@@H   DS      A0,A9                    US
)@@G@@  . SAVE A0,A1    @C@@@H   E$SKIP  5                          . OVER    UT
)@@G@@@B@@@H   E$OCTV  A9                         . A0@B@@@H   E$SKIP  5      UU
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@H   E$OCTV  A10                        .   UV
)@@G@@@E@@@H   CALL    REGCHK                     . CHECK MODE IN PACKET@C@@@HUW
)@@G@@ ENDBEG                               . RETURN  @[@@@H .    @ @@@H . RETUX
)@@G@@URN PACKET INDEX IN A0: @ @@@H .        0 - NOT IN EDIT MODE@#@@@H .    UY
)@@G@@    1 - EPKT@^@@@H .        2 - AEPKT     @^@@@H .        3 - EPKTF     UZ
)@@G@@@^@@@H .        4 - AEPKTF    @^@@@H .        5 - EPKTA1    @^@@@H .    VA
)@@G@@    6 - EPKTA2    @^@@@H .        7 - EPKTA3    @^@@@H .        8 - EPKTVB
)@@G@@XA    @[@@@H .    @A@@@H . RETURN PAKET TYPE INDEX IN A1:   @ @@@H .    VC
)@@G@@    0 - NOT IN EDIT MODE@E@@@H .        1 - E$PKT (FD,NON-FLOATING POINTVD
)@@G@@, NON-TRANSLATION)@F@@@H .        2 - A$EPKT (ASCII,NON-FLOATING POINT, VE
)@@G@@NON-TRANSLATION)  @E@@@H .        3 - E$PKTF (FD,FLOATING POINT, NON-TRAVF
)@@G@@NSLATION)   @F@@@H .        4 - A$EPKTF (ASCII,FLOATING POINT, NON-TRANSVG
)@@G@@LATION)     @G@@@H .        5 - E$PKTA (FD/ASCII,FLOATING POINT, FOLDINGVH
)@@G@@ TRANSLATION)     @H@@@H .        6 - E$PKTXA (FD/ASCII,FLOATING POINT, VI
)@@G@@CASE-PRESERVING TRANSLATION)  @[@@@H .    @B@@@HGETPKTTYPE              VJ
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              .   @F@@@HVK
)@@G@@   LA,U    A0,,X1                     . FETCH PKT ADDRESS OR TRASH@F@@@HVL
)@@G@@   IF LOOKFOR A0,EQ,PKTTAB,,H2 VARY,A1 FROM,U(0) FOR,U(NPKTTAB) . @G@@@HVM
)@@G@@      LA      A0,PKTTAB-1,A1,S3       . SUCCESS, FETCH PACKET TYPE IN A0VN
)@@G@@@F@@@H      LA,U    A1,,A1                  . CLEAR INCREMENT IN A1     VO
)@@G@@@D@@@H      DSC     A0,36                   . SWITCH A0,A1  @I@@@H   ELSVP
)@@G@@E                               . SEARCH FAILED, X1 IS TRASH, NOT IN EDIVQ
)@@G@@T     @D@@@H      DSL     A0,72                   . CLEAR A0,A1   @E@@@HVR
)@@G@@   ENDIF                              . END OF TABLE LOOKUP @E@@@H ENDBEVS
)@@G@@G                               . END OF GETPKTTYPE   @[@@@H/.    @^@@@HVT
)@@G@@ .   XAF TEST SEQUENCE  @[@@@H .    @B@@@HATEN    EQUF    A10,,H2       VU
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@H .    @B@@@HXJUMP                                 .   VV
)@@G@@@B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE                     .   @D@@@H   LA,U    A0,,*X9VW
)@@G@@                    . FETCH INDEX   @D@@@H   CASENTRY    A0             VX
)@@G@@        . BRANCH ON TYPE@B@@@H      P$RINT  (0302,('END OF EDIT$'))  .  VY
)@@G@@@D@@@H      LN,U    A0,1                    . SIGNAL END    @B@@@H   CASVZ
)@@G@@E        0                      .   @]@@@H      .     @C@@@H      P$RINTWA
)@@G@@  (0301,('COPY  '))       . DISPLAY @B@@@H      E$COPY  LXAF,XAFBUF     WB
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@H   CASE        1                      .   @B@@@H      WC
)@@G@@E$COPY  ATEN,EBUF               .   @B@@@H   CASE        2              WD
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@H      P$RINT  (0301,('PACK  '))       . DISPLAY @B@@@HWE
)@@G@@      ASCII                           .   @B@@@H      E$PACKC LXAF,XAFBUWF
)@@G@@F   ' '       .   @B@@@H   CASE         3                     .   @B@@@HWG
)@@G@@      FIELDATA                         .  @B@@@H      E$PACKC ATEN,EBUF WH
)@@G@@  ' '         .   @B@@@H   CASE        4                      .   @C@@@HWI
)@@G@@      P$RINT  (0301,('FD3   '))       . DISPLAY @B@@@H      E$FD3   XAFBWJ
)@@G@@UF                  .   @B@@@H   CASE        5                      .   WK
)@@G@@@B@@@H      E$FD3   EBUF                    .   @B@@@H   CASE        6  WL
)@@G@@                    .   @C@@@H      P$RINT  (0301,('MSG   '))       . DIWM
)@@G@@SPLAY @C@K@H      .         SLJ       TON$              .   @B@@@H      WN
)@@G@@ASCII                           .   @C@@@H      LA,U    A0,' '          WO
)@@G@@        . A BLANK @E@@@H      SA      A0,EMSGCA               . NEW SENTWP
)@@G@@INEL CHAR   @B@@@H      E$MSG   XAFBUF                  .   @C@@@H      WQ
)@@G@@DS      A0,A9                   . SAVE IT @B@@@H      E$CHAR  '*'       WR
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@H      E$MSGR                          .   @D@@@HWS
)@@G@@      AA      A10,A1                  . ADD CHAR COUNT@E@@@H      IF A0,WT
)@@G@@IS,NONZ THEN              . NON-BLANK UPDATE    @D@@@H         LA      AWU
)@@G@@9,A0                . LAST TIME     @F@@@H      ENDIF                   WV
)@@G@@        . END OF NON-BLANK UPDATE   @B@@@H      E$CHAR  '*'             WW
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@H      DL      A0,A9                   . RESTORE @B@@@HWX
)@@G@@   CASE        7                      .   @B@@@H      FIELDATA          WY
)@@G@@               .  @C@@@H      LA,U    A0,'*'                  . FD BLANKWZ
)@@G@@@B@@@H      SA      A0,EMSGC                .   @B@@@H      E$MSG   EBUFXA
)@@G@@                    .   @C@@@H      DS      A0,A9                   . SAXB
)@@G@@V     @B@@@H      E$CHAR  '@'                     .   @B@@@H      E$MSGRXC
)@@G@@                          .   @D@@@H      AA      A10,A1                XD
)@@G@@  . ADD CHAR COUNT@E@@@H      IF A0,IS,NONZ THEN              . NON-BLANXE
)@@G@@K UPDATE    @D@@@H         LA      A9,A0                . LAST TIME     XF
)@@G@@@F@@@H      ENDIF                           . END OF NON-BLANK UPDATE   XG
)@@G@@@B@@@H      E$CHAR  '@'                     .   @C@@@H      DL      A0,AXH
)@@G@@9                   . RESTORE @B@@@H   ENDCASE                          XI
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@H   DL      A9,A0                      . SAVE A0,A1 IN A9,A10XJ
)@@G@@@B@@@H ENDBEG                               .   @[@@@H/.    @F@@@H . OPEXK
)@@G@@N, CLOSE ASCII EDIT$. ALTERNATE PSR$ MODE AS GIVEN BY A13.  @B@@@H . PERXL
)@@G@@FORM QW/TW MODE VALIDITY CHECKS.    @[@@@H .    @B@@@HACLOS             XM
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE   SAVE,A12          .   XN
)@@G@@@E@@@H   A$PRINT (0240,EBUF)                . PRINT CURRENT BUFFER@G@@@HXO
)@@G@@   CALL    MUSTBEQW                   . WE MUST BE IN QUARTERWORD MODE  XP
)@@G@@@H@@@H   CALL    REGCHK                     . CHECK REGS, RTN W/ A1 = PAXQ
)@@G@@CKET TYPE   @G@@@H   IF A1,NE,U(2) ;                    . PACKET WAS NOTXR
)@@G@@ A$EPKT TYPE.     @H@@@H      AND     A1,NE,U(4) THEN         . PACKET WXS
)@@G@@ASN'T A$EPKTF TYPE EITHER.    @G@@@H      ER      ERR$                  XT
)@@G@@  . BUT SHOULD BE ONE, SO ERROR     @F@@@H   ENDIF                      XU
)@@G@@        . END OF AEDIT$ PACKET TEST @G@@@H   A$EDITX                    XV
)@@G@@        . CLOSE ASCII EDIT$, SAVE POINTERS@G@@@H   LA      A12,A0       XW
)@@G@@              . SAVE A0 (PACKET ADDR FROM EDITX)@F@@@H   SPD     A0     XX
)@@G@@                    . STASH GOOD PSR BITS IN A0 @G@@@H   IF A14,IS,ZERO XY
)@@G@@THEN                . ORIGINAL MODE WAS THIRDWORD     @G@@@H      CALL  XZ
)@@G@@  MUSTBETW                . WE MUST BE IN THIRDWORD MODE    @E@@@H      YA
)@@G@@LA,U    A14,1                   . SET NEW MODE TO QW  @H@@@H      AA,U  YB
)@@G@@  A0,1*/3                 . ADD QUARTERWORD MODE BIT TO PSR BITS  @G@@@HYC
)@@G@@   ELSE                               . ORIGINAL MODE WAS QUARTERWORD   YD
)@@G@@@G@@@H      CALL    MUSTBEQW                . WE MUST BE IN QUARTERWORD YE
)@@G@@MODE  @F@@@H      LA,U    A14,0                   . SET NEW MODE TO THIRYF
)@@G@@DWORD @H@@@H      AN,U    A0,1*/3                 . CLR QUARTERWORD MODEYG
)@@G@@ BIT FROM PSR BITS@E@@@H   ENDIF                              . END OF QYH
)@@G@@WM CHECK    @G@@@H   LPD     0,A0                       . RESET PSR BITSYI
)@@G@@ WITH QW/TW MODE  @H@@@H   CALL    REGCHK                     . CHECK REYJ
)@@G@@GS, RETURN W/ A1=PACKET TYPE  @F@@@H   IF A1,IS,NONZ THEN               YK
)@@G@@  . WE ARE STILL IN EDIT MODE.@H@@@H      ER      ERR$                  YL
)@@G@@  . WHICH MEANS AEDITX$ FAILED, SO DIE.   @E@@@H   ENDIF                YM
)@@G@@              . END OF AEDITX$ TEST @E@@@H   A$EDIT  A12,,W             YN
)@@G@@        . REOPEN ASCII EDIT$  @G@@@H   CALL    MUSTBEQW                 YO
)@@G@@  . WE MUST BE IN QUARTERWORD MODE  @E@@@H   CALL    REGCHK             YP
)@@G@@        . CHECK PACKET, REGS. @D@@@H ENDBEG                             YQ
)@@G@@  . END OF ACLOS  @[@@@H .    @A@@@H . ERROR IF NOT IN THIRDWORD MODE   YR
)@@G@@@[@@@H .    @B@@@HMUSTBETW                               .  @B@@@H BEGINYS
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              .   @G@@@H   IF ZERO,IN,(1,0),,T2 THEN  YT
)@@G@@        . T2 IS Q3: MODE IS QUARTERWORD   @F@@@H      ER      ERR$      YU
)@@G@@              . WHICH IS THE WRONG MODE.  @C@@@H   ENDIF                YV
)@@G@@              . SO ERROR@E@@@H ENDBEG                               . ENYW
)@@G@@D OF MUSTBETW     @[@@@H .    @A@@@H . ERROR IF NOT IN QUARTERWORD MODE YX
)@@G@@@[@@@H .    @B@@@HMUSTBEQW                               .  @B@@@H BEGINYY
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE,NOSAVE              .   @G@@@H   IF NONZ,IN,(1,0),,Q3 THEN  YZ
)@@G@@        . Q3 IS T2: MODE IS THIRDWORD     @F@@@H      ER      ERR$      ZA
)@@G@@              . WHICH IS THE WRONG MODE.  @C@@@H   ENDIF                ZB
)@@G@@              . SO ERROR@E@@@H ENDBEG                               . ENZC
)@@G@@D OF MUSTBETW     @[@@@H/.    @ @@@H . OPEN, CLOSE FIELDATA EDIT$.@B@@@HZD
)@@G@@ . PERFORM QW/TW MODE VALIDITY CHECKS.    @[@@@H .    @ @@@H . DON'T CLEZE
)@@G@@AR, DON'T PRINT.  @[@@@H .    @F@@@HECLOSNP                             ZF
)@@G@@  . CLEAR BUT DON'T PRINT     @F@@@H BEGIN EXECSUB,ECLOS                ZG
)@@G@@  . XFER TO ECLOS WHEN DONE.  @G@@@H   LN,XU   A0,1                     ZH
)@@G@@  . NEG SKIP COUNT SEZ DON'T PRINT. @F@@@H   LA      A1,A0              ZI
)@@G@@        . AND DON'T CLEAR THE BUFFER@G@@@H ENDBEG                       ZJ
)@@G@@        . END OF ECLOSNP. XFER TO ECLOS . @[@@@H .    @E@@@H . PRINT BUFZK
)@@G@@FER, CLEAR BUFFER, CLOSE, VALIDATE, AND REOPEN. @[@@@H .    @C@@@H . A0 ZL
)@@G@@ - LINE SKIP COUNT. IF NEG, DON'T PRINT.  @A@@@H . A1  - IF NEG, DON'T CZM
)@@G@@LEAR BUFFER.@C@@@H . A13 - OUTPUT MODE: 0 (FIELDATA) , 1 (ASCII)  @C@@@HZN
)@@G@@ . A15 - REGISTER SET: 0 (SUB-MINOR) , 1 (MINOR)@[@@@H .    @ @@@H . *MUZO
)@@G@@ST* BE IN EDIT MODE.    @[@@@H .    @B@@@HECLOS                         ZP
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE   SAVE,A11,A12      . RETURN ON X11 ZQ
)@@G@@@D@@@H   IF A0,IS,POS THEN                  . PRINT IT.     @F@@@H      ZR
)@@G@@LSSL    A0,6                    . MAKE ROOM FOR LINE COUNT. @H@@@H      ZS
)@@G@@LA      A2,IL                   . FETCH BUFFER WORD LENGTH FROM PACKET  ZT
)@@G@@@G@@@H      IF A13,IS,ZERO ;                . OUTPUT IS FIELDATA, SO PRIZU
)@@G@@NT$   @G@@@H         AND     A2,GT,U(22) THEN     . TOO MANY WORDS FOR FZV
)@@G@@D PRINT$,   @H@@@H         LA,U    A2,22                . SO SET WORD LEZW
)@@G@@NGTH TO PRINT$ MAXIMUM  @G@@@H      ENDIF                           . ENZX
)@@G@@D OF PRINT$ WORD MAX TEST     @E@@@H      AA      A0,A2                 ZY
)@@G@@  . ADD BUFFER LENGTH   @G@@@H      LSSL    A0,18                   . MAZZ
)@@G@@KE ROOM FOR BUFFER ADDRESS.   @E@@@H      AA      A0,ILOC               AA
)@@G@@  . A0 IS PRINT$ ACW    @E@@@H      IF A13,IS,ZERO THEN             . FIAB
)@@G@@ELDATA OUTPUT     @B@@@H         ER      PRINT$               .   @D@@@HAC
)@@G@@      ELSE                            . ASCII OUTPUT  @B@@@H         ER AD
)@@G@@     APRINT$              .   @B@@@H      ENDIF                         AE
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@H   ENDIF                              . END OF PRINT-AT-ALL AF
)@@G@@TEST  @D@@@H   IF A1,IS,POS THEN                  . CLEAR BUFFER. @E@@@HAG
)@@G@@      IF A1,IS,NONZ THEN              . CLEAR ENTIRE BUFFER.@E@@@H      AH
)@@G@@   E$CLEAR                      . CALL EDIT$ ROUTINE  @F@@@H      ELSE  AI
)@@G@@                          . CLEAR AS MUCH AS NEEDED.  @F@@@H         E$CAJ
)@@G@@OLN                       . OBTAIN COL NUMBER IN A0   @F@@@H         LA,AK
)@@G@@U    A11,1,A0             . PLUS 1 TO JGD COUNTER A11 @G@@@H         LA,AL
)@@G@@U    A12,' '              . LOAD A12 WITH FIELDATA BLANK.   @G@@@H      AM
)@@G@@   IF NONZ,IN,EASCIN THEN       . WE ARE IN ASCII INPUT MODE,     @F@@@HAN
)@@G@@            ASCII                     . SO DEFINE ASCII CHAR SET, @F@@@HAO
)@@G@@            LA,U    A12,' '           . LOAD A12 WITH ASCII BLANK,@H@@@HAP
)@@G@@            FIELDATA                   . AND REVERT TO FIELDATA CHAR SETAQ
)@@G@@.     @E@@@H         ENDIF                        . A12 HAS PROPER BLANKAR
)@@G@@@D@@@H         E$COL   0                    . SET TO COL. 0 @G@@@H      AS
)@@G@@   REPEAT JGD,A11               . FOR AS MANY COLS AS NEEDED,     @G@@@HAT
)@@G@@            E$CHAR  A12,,W            . INSERT A BLANK (FD OR ASCII)    AU
)@@G@@@D@@@H         ENDREP                       . LOOP ON R1    @E@@@H      AV
)@@G@@   E$COL   0                    . REPOSITION COUNTER. @B@@@H      ENDIF AW
)@@G@@                          .   @E@@@H   ENDIF                            AX
)@@G@@  . END OF BUFFER CLEAR @I@@@H   CALL    REGCHK                     . CHAY
)@@G@@ECK REGISTERS. RETRN: A0 IS PACKET TYP    @F@@@H   IF A0,IS,ZERO THEN   AZ
)@@G@@              . WE ARE NOT IN EDIT MODE.  @E@@@H      ER      ERR$      BA
)@@G@@              . HORRIBLY WRONG.     @C@@@H   ENDIF                      BB
)@@G@@        . DIE.    @D@@@H   E$DITX                             . CLOSE EDBC
)@@G@@IT$   @E@@@H   LA      A12,A0                     . SAVE PKT ADDR IN A12BD
)@@G@@@I@@@H   CALL    REGCHK                     . CHECK REGISTERS. RETRN: A0BE
)@@G@@ IS PACKET TYP    @F@@@H   IF A0,IS,NONZ THEN                 . WE ARE SBF
)@@G@@TILL IN EDIT MODE.@E@@@H      ER      ERR$                    . HORRIBLYBG
)@@G@@ WRONG.     @C@@@H   ENDIF                              . DIE.    @G@@@HBH
)@@G@@   CALL    MUSTBETW                   . WE MUST BE IN THIRDWORD MODE.   BI
)@@G@@@G@@@H   E$DITR  A12,,W                     . REOPEN EDIT$ WITH A0 FROM BJ
)@@G@@EDITX$@F@@@H   CALL    REGCHK                     . CHECK PACKET PARAMETBK
)@@G@@ERS   @D@@@H ENDBEG                               . END OF ECLOS. @[@@@HBL
)@@G@@/.    @F@@@H . VALIDATE THE CONTENTS OF VARIOUS REGISTERS TO INSURE THATBM
)@@G@@ EDIT$@G@@@H . HASN'T TRASHED ANYTHING. STOCK UNIVAC EDIT$ FUNCTIONS OPEBN
)@@G@@RATE IN     @G@@@H . SUB-MINOR REGISTER MODE, WHICH MEANS THEY MAY USE ABO
)@@G@@0-A3, AND R1.     @F@@@H . NON-STANDARD FUNCTIONS (SOME, NOT ALL) AND ALBP
)@@G@@L FUNCTIONS WHICH @G@@@H . ARE TRANSLATING(FD TO ASCII OR ASCII TO FD) ABQ
)@@G@@RE IN MINOR REGISTER    @G@@@H . MODE, AND MAY USE A0-A5, R1-R3. IN EDITBR
)@@G@@ING MODE, H2(X1),X2,X3 ARE    @#@@@H . ALSO USED.     @[@@@H .    @D@@@HBS
)@@G@@ . RETURN WITH A0=PACKET INDEX, A1=PACKET TYPE INDEX. @[@@@H .    @B@@@HBT
)@@G@@        RESUME                        .   @B@@@HREGCHK                  BU
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROUTINE                     .   @I@@@HBV
)@@G@@   CALL    GETPKTTYPE                 . FETCH PKT INDEX, OR ZERO IF NOT BW
)@@G@@EDIT MOD    @D@@@H   IF A6,DNE,('SECRETSECRET') ;       . A6,A7 TRASHED BX
)@@G@@@D@@@H      OR      A8,NE,('SECRET') THEN   . A8 IS TRASHED.@F@@@H      BY
)@@G@@ER      ERR$                    . EITHER WAY, IT'S AN ERROR @F@@@H   ENDBZ
)@@G@@IF                              . END OF A6-A8 VALIDATION   @G@@@H   . NCA
)@@G@@OTE THAT WE KNOW AT THIS POINT THAT A6,A7 CONTAIN ('SECRETSECRET')@F@@@HCB
)@@G@@   IF A0,IS,ZERO THEN                 . WE ARE NOT IN EDIT MODE   @H@@@HCC
)@@G@@      IF LOOKFOR A6,NE,X1 VARY,A1 FROM,U(0) FOR,U(X6-X1+1) ; . TEST X1-XCD
)@@G@@6     @H@@@H         THEN                         . THE SEARCH FAILED SOCE
)@@G@@MEWHERE ON X1-X6  @C@@@H         ER      ERR$                 . SO DIE  CF
)@@G@@@F@@@H      ENDIF                           . END OF X1-X6 VALIDATION   CG
)@@G@@@G@@@H   ELSE                               . EDIT MODE ON, TEST H1(X1),CH
)@@G@@X4-X6 @D@@@H      LA      A1,X1                   . MOVE X1 TO A1 @D@@@HCI
)@@G@@      SSL     A1,18                   . RIGHT JUSTIFY @D@@@H      LA    CJ
)@@G@@  A3,X3                   . MOVE X3 TO A3 @D@@@H      SSL     A3,18     CK
)@@G@@              . RIGHT JUSTIFY @H@@@H      IF A1,NE,U('SEC') OR A3,NE,U('CL
)@@G@@SEC') THEN . H1(X1) OR H1(X3) IS TRASH    @C@@@H         ER      ERR$   CM
)@@G@@              . SO DIE  @E@@@H      ENDIF                           . ENCN
)@@G@@D OF H1(X1) TEST  @D@@@H      IF A6,DNE,X4 ;                  . X4,X5 TRCO
)@@G@@ASHED @D@@@H         OR      A6,NE,X6 THEN        . X6 TRASHED    @F@@@HCP
)@@G@@         ER      ERR$                 . EITHER WAY, IT'S WRONG    @F@@@HCQ
)@@G@@      ENDIF                           . END OF EDIT MODE XREG TEST@F@@@HCR
)@@G@@   ENDIF                              . END OF ALL XREG VALIDATION@F@@@HCS
)@@G@@   IF A15,IS,NONZ THEN                . MINOR REG SET IS USED     @H@@@HCT
)@@G@@      IF LOOKFOR A6,NE,R4 VARY,A1 FROM,U(0) FOR,U(R9-R4+1) ; . TEST R4-RCU
)@@G@@9     @H@@@H         THEN                         . THE SEARCH FAILED SOCV
)@@G@@MEWHERE ON R4-R9  @C@@@H         ER      ERR$                 . SO DIE  CW
)@@G@@@F@@@H      ENDIF                           . END OF X1-X6 VALIDATION   CX
)@@G@@@H@@@H   ELSE                               . SUB-MINOR SET USED, R2,R3 CY
)@@G@@MUST BE GOOD@H@@@H      IF LOOKFOR A6,NE,R2 VARY,A1 FROM,U(0) FOR,U(R9-RCZ
)@@G@@2+1) ; . TEST R2-R9     @H@@@H         THEN                         . THDA
)@@G@@E SEARCH FAILED SOMEWHERE ON R2-R9  @C@@@H         ER      ERR$         DB
)@@G@@        . SO DIE  @F@@@H      ENDIF                           . END OF RDC
)@@G@@2-R9 VALIDATION   @G@@@H      IF A6,DNE,A4 THEN               . A4,A5 TRDD
)@@G@@ASHED IN SUB-MINOR MODE,@C@@@H         ER      ERR$                 . SODE
)@@G@@ DIE  @F@@@H      ENDIF                           . END OF R-REG,A4,A5 TDF
)@@G@@EST   @D@@@H   ENDIF                              . END OF TEST   @G@@@HDG
)@@G@@   IF A0,IS,NONZ THEN                 . IN EDIT MODE, X1 POINTS TO PKT  DH
)@@G@@@F@@@H      LX,U    X11,,X1                 . MOVE PKT POINTER TO X11   DI
)@@G@@@E@@@H      AX      X11,PKTTAB-1,A0,S2      . ADD LENGTH OF PACKET@F@@@HDJ
)@@G@@      LXI,U   X11,1                   . TABLE HAS I-WORD ENTRIES  @H@@@HDK
)@@G@@      IF LOOKFOR A6,NE,0 VARY,X11 FOR,U(5) THEN . WORD AFTER PKT NOT 'SEDL
)@@G@@CRET' @H@@@H         ER      ERR$                 . SO ERROR CAUSE POST-DM
)@@G@@PKT AREA TRASHED  @]@@@H      ENDIF @G@@@H   ENDIF                      DN
)@@G@@        . END OF POST-PACKET AREA TEST    @F@@@H   LA,U    A2,NGAP      DO
)@@G@@              . LOAD # OF PKTGAP GROUPS   @D@@@H   REPEAT JGD,A2        DP
)@@G@@              . FOR EACH GROUP@E@@@H      IF LOOKFOR A6,NE,0 VARY,A3 FRODQ
)@@G@@M,GAPTAB,A2 FOR,U(5) ; .@G@@@H         THEN                         . ONDR
)@@G@@E WORD IN PKTGAP .NE. 'SECRET'@G@@@H         ER      ERR$               DS
)@@G@@  . BUT ALL 5 WRDS SHOULD BE, SO DIE@E@@@H      ENDIF                   DT
)@@G@@        . END OF PKTGAP CHECK @H@@@H   ENDREP                           DU
)@@G@@  . LOOP FOR NEXT PKTGAP GROUP TO EXAMINE @G@@@H   CALL    PKTMODECHK   DV
)@@G@@              . CHECK PACKET FLAGS VERSUS A14   @E@@@H   CALL    REGSET DW
)@@G@@                    . RESET ALL REGS,     @D@@@H ENDBEG                 DX
)@@G@@              . END OF REGCHK @B@K@H        BRIEF                       DY
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@H/.    @D@@@H . VALIDATE SOFTWARE/HARDWARE ASCII/FIELDATA FLADZ
)@@G@@GS    @E@@@H . CALLED BY REGCHK. ON ENTRY, A14 IS ORIGINAL MODE FLAG :  EA
)@@G@@@[@@@H .    @D@@@H . A14 = 0 - MODE WAS THIRDWORD PRIOR TO OPENING EDIT$EB
)@@G@@@E@@@H . A14 = 1 - MODE WAS QUARTERWORD PRIOR TO OPENING EDIT$    @[@@@HEC
)@@G@@ .    @B@@@HPKTMODECHK                             .  @B@@@H BEGIN SUBROED
)@@G@@UTINE SAVE,A0,A1,A11,A12  .   @G@@@H   CALL    GETPKTTYPE               EE
)@@G@@  . RETURN WITH PACKET TYPE IN A1   @F@@@H   CASENTRY A1                EF
)@@G@@        . BRANCH ON PACKET TYPE     @F@@@H      ER      ERR$            EG
)@@G@@        . BOGUS TYPE DRAWS ERROR    @G@@@H   CASE      0                EH
)@@G@@        . NO PACKET, NOT IN EDIT MODE.    @G@@@H      LA,U    A12,0     EI
)@@G@@              . SET FLAG TO FD-FD, NO XLATE.    @G@@@H   CASE      1,3  EJ
)@@G@@                    . 1 (E$PKT), 2(E$PKTF), NO XLATE. @G@@@H      LA,U  EK
)@@G@@  A12,0                   . SET FLAG TO FD-FD, NO XLATE     @G@@@H      EL
)@@G@@IF NONZ,IN,EASCII THEN          . EASC OR EASCIN OR QWM IS NONZ   @H@@@HEM
)@@G@@         ER      ERR$                 . WHICH IS WRONG. NO ASCII PROCESSEN
)@@G@@ING.  @F@@@H      ENDIF                           . END OF E$PKT(F) ASCIEO
)@@G@@I TEST@I@@@H   CASE      2,4                      . 2(A$EPKT), 4(A$EPKTFEP
)@@G@@), AS-AS, NO XLATE.     @G@@@H      LA,U    A12,1                   . SEEQ
)@@G@@T FLAG TO ASCII PROCESSING    @G@@@H      IF ZERO,IN,EASC OR ZERO,IN,EASER
)@@G@@CIN THEN . INPUT OR OUTPUT IS FD    @H@@@H         ER      ERR$         ES
)@@G@@        . WHICH IS WRON, ALL MUST BE ASCII.     @G@@@H      ENDIF       ET
)@@G@@                    . END OF FD INPUT/OUTPUT TEST     @F@@@H   CASE     EU
)@@G@@ 5,6                      . 5(E$PKTA), 6(E$PKTXA)     @E@@@H      LA,U  EV
)@@G@@  A12,0                   . ASSUME FD TO FD MODE@F@@@H      IF NONZ,IN,EEW
)@@G@@ASC OR NONZ,IN,EASCIN THEN . SOME ASCII STUFF   @F@@@H         LA,U    AEX
)@@G@@12,1                . SO SET FLAG NOT FD-FD     @F@@@H      ENDIF       EY
)@@G@@                    . END OF FD-FD FLAG TEST    @G@@@H      IF A1,EQ,U(6EZ
)@@G@@)                   . PACKET IS EXTENDED (XAF) XLATION@E@@@H      ENDIF FA
)@@G@@                          . **** NO TEST YET****@E@@@H   ENDCASE        FB
)@@G@@                    . END OF PACKET BRANCH@[@@@H   .  @F@@@H   IF A12,ISFC
)@@G@@,ZERO THEN                . NO PACKET OR FD-FD PACKET @F@@@H      IF A14FD
)@@G@@,IS,NONZ THEN             . ORIGINAL MODE WAS QW.     @F@@@H         CALFE
)@@G@@L    MUSTBEQW             . WE SHOULD STILL BE IN QWM @G@@@H      ELSE  FF
)@@G@@                          . ORIG MODE WAS THIRDWORD MODE,   @F@@@H      FG
)@@G@@   CALL    MUSTBETW             . WE MUST STILL BE THAT WAY.@E@@@H      FH
)@@G@@ENDIF                           . END OF TW/QW TEST   @E@@@H      IF A1,FI
)@@G@@IS,NONZ ;                 . WE ARE IN EDIT MODE.@G@@@H         AND     NFJ
)@@G@@ONZ,IN,QWM THEN     . EDIT$ DID UNNECESSARY PSR$.     @D@@@H         ER FK
)@@G@@     ERR$                 . SO DIE AT ONCE@F@@@H      ENDIF             FL
)@@G@@              . END OF UNNEEDED PSR$ TEST @H@@@H   ELSE                 FM
)@@G@@              . A12>0, SOME ASCII PROCESSING HERE.    @G@@@H      CALL  FN
)@@G@@  MUSTBEQW                . WE MUST BE IN QUARTERWORD MODE  @F@@@H      FO
)@@G@@IF A14,IS,NONZ THEN             . ORIG MODE WAS QUARTERWORD.@H@@@H      FP
)@@G@@   IF NONZ,IN,QWM THEN          . EDIT$ DID UNNEEDED PSR$ TO GET QWM.   FQ
)@@G@@@C@@@H            ER      ERR$              . SO DIE  @F@@@H         ENDFR
)@@G@@IF                        . END OF UNNEEDED PSR$ TEST @G@@@H      ELSE  FS
)@@G@@                          . A14=0, ORIG MODE WAS THIRDWORD. @H@@@H      FT
)@@G@@   IF ZERO,IN,QWM THEN          . EDIT$ DID NOT PERFORM PSR$ TO GET QWM,FU
)@@G@@@C@@@H            ER      ERR$              . SO DIE  @F@@@H         ENDFV
)@@G@@IF                        . END OF NNEEDED PSR$ TEST  @F@@@H      ENDIF FW
)@@G@@                          . END OF ORIGINAL MODE TEST @H@@@H      IF A1,FX
)@@G@@IS,NONZ THEN              . WE ARE IN EDIT$ MODE. X1 IS PKT PTR   @H@@@HFY
)@@G@@         DL      A11,X7               . LOAD A11,A12 WITH MODE REGS X7,XFZ
)@@G@@8     @F@@@H         IF A11,NE,EASCIN OR A12,NE,EASC THEN . X7,X8 NOT PRGA
)@@G@@OPER  @G@@@H            ER      ERR$              . SOMEONE BLEW THE X7,GB
)@@G@@X8 LOAD     @F@@@H         ENDIF                        . END OF X7,X8 VGC
)@@G@@ALIDATION   @F@@@H         IF A12,NE,A13 THEN           . A13 NOT PROPERGD
)@@G@@LY SET.     @C@@@H            ER      ERR$              . SO DIE. @F@@@HGE
)@@G@@         ENDIF                        . END OF A13 VALIDATION TEST@E@@@HGF
)@@G@@      ENDIF                           . END OF REGISTER TEST@E@@@H   ENDGG
)@@G@@IF                              . END OF A12 SWITCH   @E@@@H ENDBEG     GH
)@@G@@                          . END OF PKTMODECHK   @[@@@H/.    @]@@@H .   PGI
)@@G@@ACKETS@[@@@H .    @B@@@H        VARBLS                        .   @F@@@HGJ
)@@G@@        RESUME                        . LETS LOOK AT THE RECODRD  @E@@@HGK
)@@G@@EBUF    RES     40                    . EDIT$ OUTPUT BUFFER.@B@@@HPKTGAPGL
)@@G@@(1)                              .  @B@@@HI       DO      5 , + 'SECRET'GM
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@HEBUF1   RES     40                    . XAF TEST EDIT$GN
)@@G@@ BUFFER     @B@@@HPKTGAP(2)                              .  @B@@@HI     GO

)@@G@@        .   @E@@@HEPKT    E$PKT   22,EBUF               . STANDARD PACKEGQ

)@@G@@  . FLOATING POINT PACKET     @B@@@HPKTGAP(4)                           GT

)@@G@@I                         . DEFINE ASCII CHAR SET.    @G@@@HMGACHR  EQU GV
)@@G@@    '%'                   . ASCII MESSAGE STOP CHARACTER    @G@@@H      GW
)@@G@@  FIELDATA                       . RESET TO FIELDATA CHAR SET.    @I@@@HGX
)@@G@@EPKTA1  E$PKTA  32,EBUF 'MGA',MGACHR 'TBL',-FTABL128 ;  . XLATION PKT 12GY

)@@G@@ODE TO ASCII@B@@@HPKTGAP(7)                              .  @B@@@HI     HG

)@@G@@TS                        .   @B@@@HPSTUFF  'ASCII TO ASCII    '        HM
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@HEXCLAIM EQUF    $,,S1                 . ! @B@@@HSTAR    EQUFHN

)@@G@@  +       '!','*',',',' ',0,0   . FD@B@@@H        ASCII                 HQ

)@@G@@FPR & ASC & ASCIN & QWM & SPC & DPC &';   @B@@@H        ' SPCA & DPCA &'HT

)@@G@@W &THE &&&';@E@@@H        'WAH-DA-DOO-DAH &BY &GOOD &FOR &DOWN &ALL &&&'HY

)@@G@@    +         5                 .   @[@@@H/.    @F@@@HMSGBUF  'COPY: &PAIA
)@@G@@CK: &PACKC: &FD1: & FD2 :& FD3: &PAD: &COL: &'; @A@@@H        'OCTV: &OCIB
)@@G@@TF: &OCTF: &';    @F@@@H        'HEXV: &HEXF: &HEXF: &FORM TEST: [18,18]IC

)@@G@@ .    @C@@@HECOPY   'THIS@IS A TEST OF @@@CO@PY AND PA@CK' .@B@@@HLECOPYIH

)@@G@@@A@@@H .   ASCII-FIELDAT CONVERSION TABLE @[@@@H .    @D@@@HFTABL64     JD

)@@G@@%%%' .@D@@@HXAFBUF                                . XAF ASCII TEST@B@@@HJN
)@@G@@        +       0116,0157,0167,040    .   @B@@@H        +       0151,016JO

)@@G@@BUF)          . CHARACTER COUNT     @[@@@H .    @#@@@H .   AEDIT$ PACKETJV

)@@G@@  FIELDATA                       .  @B@@@HFF      FORM    6,6,6,18      KK
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@HPKTTAB                                . 0,LENGTH,PKT TKL
)@@G@@YPE,ADDRESS @C@@@H        FF      0,6,1,EPKT            . E$PKT   @C@@@HKM
)@@G@@        FF      0,13,2,AEPKT          . A$EPKT  @C@@@H        FF      0,KN
)@@G@@10,3,EPKTF          . E$PKTF  @C@@@H        FF      0,13,4,AEPKTF       KO
)@@G@@  . A$EPKTF @C@@@H        FF      0,13,5,EPKTA1         . E$PKTA  @C@@@HKP

)@@G@@  . E$PKTXA @D@@@HNPKTTAB EQU     $-PKTTAB              . TABLE SIZE.   KS
)@@G@@@[@@@H .    @A@@@H . TABLE OF PACKET-GAP ADDRESSES    @[@@@H .    @D@@@HKT

)@@G@@        .   @[@@@H/.    @F@@@HMSGBUF  'COPY: &PACK: &PACKC: &FD1: & FD2 KX
)@@G@@:& FD3: &PAD: &COL: &'; @A@@@H        'OCTV: &OCTF: &OCTF: &';    @F@@@HKY
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. PROGRAM TO CATCH AN PRINT ENGLISH MESSAGKZ
)@@G@@ES FOR ERRORS     @A@@@@. INTERFACES WITH THE ERROR$ REP    @[@@@@.     LA
)@@G@@@C@@@@.   CONCEIVED OF AND WRITTEN BY KERN E. SIBBALD @[@@@@.     @[@@@@LB
)@@G@@$(1). @B@@@@          AXR$                        .   @B@@@@          LILC
)@@G@@T                         .   @G@]@@          TYPE      TYPE$REP        LD
)@@G@@  . OUR GUARANTEE: NO IBANK STORES  @G@@@]          $INFO     9 1,3     LE
)@@G@@        . OUR GUARANTEE: NO IBANK STORES  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THIS ROUTILF
)@@G@@NE SETS UP AND HANDLES IALL CONTINGENCIES @]@@@@. CALLED    @ @@@@.     LG
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,I$ALL @A@@@@.         +SPEAK,MASK,ERROR ADDRESS @#@@@@LH
)@@G@@.         <RETURN>@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. WHERE SPEAK IS S1 AND IS THE MAXIMLI
)@@G@@UM NUMBER OF@ @@@@.   DIAGNOSTIC LINES TO PRINT @E@@@@. MASK IS THE CONTLJ
)@@G@@INGENCY MASK  I.E. -0 TO GET ALL TYPES    @D@@@@. ERROR ADDRESS IF NON-ZLK
)@@G@@ERO IS THE ADDRESS TO RETURN  @B@@@@. AFTER THE ERROR MESSAGES ARE PRINTLL
)@@G@@ED    @A@@@@. IF ZERO AN ER EABT$ WILL BE TAKEN @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     LM
)@@G@@@C@@@@.     TECHNICAL DOCUMENTATION FOR CALLING ERROR$@[@@@@.     @[@@@@LN
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.          .................................................LO
)@@G@@............@G@@@@.    0     : TS      :  0      : DUMP    : TALK    : RLP
)@@G@@ETURN  : ERROR   :@G@@@@.          :         :         : BITS    : LEVELLQ
)@@G@@   :         : TYPE    :@G@@@@.          ...............................LR
)@@G@@..............................@G@@@@.    1     :   SETC  : 0       : DESLS
)@@G@@TROY :  LANG   :      SETC         :@G@@@@.          :REG MASK :        LT
)@@G@@ : DBANK   :         :      VALUE        :@G@@@@.          .............LU
)@@G@@................................................@E@@@@.    2     : A0 BELV
)@@G@@FORE CSF$ CALL,  OR IALL WORD       :     @G@@@@.          :            LW
)@@G@@                                               :@G@@@@.          .......LX
)@@G@@......................................................@G@@@@.    3     :LY
)@@G@@ A0 AFTER CSF$ CALL OR SECOND WORD OF IALL CONTINGENCY     :@G@@@@.     LZ
)@@G@@     :         OR A0 RETURNED FROM MSCON$                        :@G@@@@MA
)@@G@@.          .............................................................MB
)@@G@@@G@@@@.    4     :            A0 TO BE RESTORED UPON RETURN             MC
)@@G@@     :@G@@@@.          :                                                MD
)@@G@@           :@G@@@@.          ...........................................ME
)@@G@@..................@G@@@@.    5     :            A1 TO BE RESTORED UPON RMF
)@@G@@ETURN                  :@G@@@@.          :                              MG
)@@G@@                             :@G@@@@.          .........................MH
)@@G@@....................................@G@@@@.    6     :         +0  OR YOMI
)@@G@@UR NAME FROM ER NAME$                    :@G@@@@.          :    IF +0   MJ
)@@G@@NEW NAME RETURNED FROM ER NAME$                :@G@@@@.          .......MK
)@@G@@......................................................@G@@@@.    7     :ML
)@@G@@       LENGTH OF IBANK       :    IBANK START ADDRESS      :@G@@@@.     MM
)@@G@@     :                             :                             :@G@@@@MN
)@@G@@.          .............................................................MO
)@@G@@@G@@@@.    8     :       LENGTH OF DBANK       :    DBANK START ADDRESS MP
)@@G@@     :@G@@@@.          :                             :                  MQ
)@@G@@           :@G@@@@.          ...........................................MR
)@@G@@..................@G@@@@.    9     :     STARTING DRUM ADDRESS OF IBANK MS
)@@G@@SAVED IN DIAG$         :@G@@@@.          :         (NOT YET USED) NEGATIMT
)@@G@@VE IF NO IBANK IN DIAG$      :@G@@@@.          .........................MU
)@@G@@....................................@G@@@@.    10    :                  MV
)@@G@@           : ADDRESS OF ADDITIONAL       :@G@@@@.          :            MW
)@@G@@                 : 50 WORDS IN D-BANK          :@G@@@@.          .......MX
)@@G@@......................................................@[@@@@.     @[@@@@MY
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@.    ERROR TYPE   @^@@@@.    1=IALL$ CONTINGENCY@H@@@@.    2MZ
)@@G@@=A0 RETURNED FROM CSF$  (DETERMINE TYPE, IF CAN'T ASSUME FACILITIES)    NA
)@@G@@@G@@@@.    3=A0 RETURNED FROM CSF$ (FACILITIES, FREE,ASG,CAT,USE,MODE,QUNB
)@@G@@AL)   @B@@@@.    4=A0 RETURNED FROM CSF$  (SYM,BRKPT) @C@@@@.    5=A0 RENC
)@@G@@TURNED FROM CSF$  (CKPT OR CKPAR)   @B@@@@.    6=A0 RETURNED FROM CSF$  ND
)@@G@@(START)     @A@@@@.    7=A0 RETURNED FROM CSF$  (LOG) @D@@@@.    8=A0 RENE
)@@G@@TURNED FROM CSF$  (RSPAR, RSTRT, ADD)     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.   15=A0 RENF
)@@G@@TURNED FROM MSCON$ (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED)  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@NG
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@.    RETURN TYPE  @[@@@@.     @]@@@@.    1=EXIT$@]@@@@.    2NH
)@@G@@=ERR$ @]@@@@.    3=EABT$@#@@@@.    4=ABORT$     @#@@@@.    5=UNLNK$     NI
)@@G@@@#@@@@.    6=EXLNK$     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    SPEAK LEVEL =NJ
)@@G@@ ROUGHLY THE NUMBER OF LINES ALLOWED TO PRINT   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.    DNK
)@@G@@UMP BITS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.   BIT   MEANING @A@@@@.    1=DETERMINE RNL
)@@G@@ELATIVE ADDRESS   @D@@@@.    2=GIVE MAP OF ELEMENT IN WHICH ERROR OCCURENM
)@@G@@D     @A@@@@.    3=GIVE MAP OF ALL USER ELEMENTS@A@@@@.    4=GIVE MAP OFNN
)@@G@@ LIBRARY ROUTINES @C@@@@.    5=GIVE ASM LISTING AROUND LOCATION OF ERRORNO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @]@@@@FIALL*.     @]@@@@I$ALL*.     @E@@@@      NP
)@@G@@    LA,H1     A0,0,X11          . GET SPEAK AND MASK  @D@@@@          LSNQ
)@@G@@SL      A0,24             . SHIFT INTO H1 @F@@@@          LXM,U     A0,INR
)@@G@@$PKT          . GET CONTINGENCY ADDRESS   @B@@@@          SA        A0,INS
)@@G@@$MASK         .   @B@@@@          ER        IALL$             .   @E@@@@NT
)@@G@@          LA,H2     A0,,X11           . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @F@@@@      NU
)@@G@@    SA        A0,RETURN         . CONTINGENCY RETURN ADDRESS@E@@@@      NV
)@@G@@    LA,S1     A0,,X11           . GET SPEAK LEVEL     @C@@@@          SANW
)@@G@@        A0,SPEAK          . SAVE IT @C@@@@          J         1,X11     NX
)@@G@@        . RETURN  @[@@@@/$(6).@B@@@@IALL      EQU       01              NY
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@CSF       EQU       02                .   @B@@@@EXIT      EQNZ
)@@G@@U       0100              .   @^@@@@UNLNK     EQU       0500@B@@@@EXLNK OA
)@@G@@    EQU       0600              .   @B@@@@EABT      EQU       0300      OB
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@EXLNK     EQU       0600              .   @B@@@@I$PKT*OC
)@@G@@    RES       2                 .   @]@@@@I$CAL*.     @D@@@@          DSOD
)@@G@@        A0,A0A1$          . SAVE A0 AND A1@C@@@@          SZ        A0  OE
)@@G@@              . CLEAR A0@F@@@@          ER        IALL$             . TUOF
)@@G@@RN OFF CONTINGENCIES    @E@@@@          DL        A0,I$PKT          . GEOG
)@@G@@T CONTINGENCY CODE@F@@@@          DS        A0,I$CONT         . PUT IN TOH
)@@G@@O ERROR$ PACKET   @C@@@@          L,U       A0,0200000+UNLNK+IALL .     OI
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A0,ERR$PKT        . STORE IN PACKET     @E@@@@OJ
)@@G@@          LA        A0,SPEAK          . GET SPEAK LEVEL     @D@@@@      OK
)@@G@@    SA,S4     A0,ERR$PKT        . YES PUT IT    @G@@@@          L       OL
)@@G@@  A0,(1*/33+LNKERR) . PICK UP ERRORS DURING LINK$     @H@@@@          EROM
)@@G@@        IALL$             . PICKUP CONTINGENCIES DURING LINK$     @C@@@@ON
)@@G@@          TE,U      A0,077            . MAX?    @D@@@@          J       OO
)@@G@@  CON50             . NO, CONTINUE  @E@@@@          S,S3      A0,ERR$PKTOP
)@@G@@        . YES, SET MAP BITS   @F@@@@          L,U       A0,DIAGADD      OQ
)@@G@@  . GET ADDRESS TO WRITE IBANK@D@@@@          S         A0,ERR$PKT+9    OR
)@@G@@  . SET IN PACKET @F@@@@          L,U       A0,IOPKT          . ADDRESS OS
)@@G@@OF I/O PACKET     @F@@@@          L         A1,ERR$PKT+7      . GET IBANOT
)@@G@@K ACCESS WORD     @E@@@@          S         A1,4,A0           . SET IN IOU
)@@G@@/O PACKET   @C@@@@          ER        IOW$              . DO I/O  @D@@@@OV
)@@G@@          TZ,S1     3,A0              . CHECK STATUS  @C@@@@          EROW
)@@G@@        ERR$              . SORRY   @E@@@@CON50     L,U       A1,ERR$PKTOX
)@@G@@        . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @D@@@@          LA        A0,('ERROR$')   OY
)@@G@@  . GET REP NAME  @B@@@@          ER        LINK$             .   @F@@@@OZ
)@@G@@          TNZ,H2    RETURN            . DID HE GIVE A RETURN?     @C@@@@PA
)@@G@@          ER        EABT$             . DUMP HIM@G@@@@          L,U     PB
)@@G@@  A0,020212         . = SYMB 02 = 2ND READ PAST EOF   @D@@@@          TNPC
)@@G@@E,H1    A0,I$PKT          . FATAL ERROR?  @G@@@@          SZ,H2     RETUPD
)@@G@@RN            . YES, MUST RESET TO CONTINUE     @E@@@@          LA      PE
)@@G@@  A0,I$MASK         . GET CONTINGENCY MASK@F@@@@          ER        IALLPF
)@@G@@$             . TURN ON CONTINGENCIES     @D@@@@          LA        A0,APG
)@@G@@0A1$          . RESTORE A0    @C@@@@          J         *RETURN         PH
)@@G@@  . RETURN  @[@@@@/$(2).@]@@@@I$RTN*.     @D@@@@RETURN    +         0   PI
)@@G@@              . RETURN POINT  @E@@@@SPEAK     EQUF      RETURN,,S1      PJ
)@@G@@  . SAVE FOR SPEAK LEVEL@[@@@@.     @D@@@@DIAGADD   EQU       1000      PK
)@@G@@        . SECTOR 1000   @B@@@@IOPKT     'DIAG$       '              .   PL
)@@G@@@B@@@@          +         0                 .   @C@@@@          +       PM
)@@G@@  W$,0,0            . FUNCTION@F@@@@          +         0               PN
)@@G@@  . ACCESS WORD MUST BE SET   @D@@@@          +         DIAGADD         PO
)@@G@@  . DRUM ADDRESS  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@$(4). @E@@@@I$MASK*   +         0   PP
)@@G@@              . CONTINGENCY MASK    @B@@@@ERR$PKT*  +         0         PQ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         0                 .   @]@@@@I$CONTPR
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@B$CSFA0*  +         0                 .   @B@@@@A$CSFA0*  + PS
)@@G@@        0                 .   @B@@@@A0A1$*    +         0               PT
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          +         0                 .   @B@@@@NAME      + PU
)@@G@@        0                 .   @C@@@@          +         LASTI$-FRSTI$+1,PV
)@@G@@FRSTI$ .    @C@@@@          +         LASTD$-FRSTD$+1,FRSTD$ .    @B@@@@PW
)@@G@@          -         0                 .   @B@@@@          RES       50  PX
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@/$(1).@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. THIS ROUTINE SUBMITS TPY
)@@G@@HE CSF IMAGE AND THEN CALLS THE     @A@@@@. ERROR REP TO PRINT OUT ANY BPZ
)@@G@@ITS   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. CALLED    @C@@@@.         LMJ X11,C$SF   OR   QA
)@@G@@AC$SF   FOR ASCII @ @@@@.         +BITS TO IGNORE     @#@@@@.         <RQB
)@@G@@ETURN>@]@@@@AC$SF*.     @E@@@@          S         A0,B$CSFA0        . SAQC
)@@G@@VE A0 BEFORE CSF  @C@@@@          ER        ACSF$             . DO CSF$ QD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          JZ        A0,1,X11          . RETURN IF OK  @E@@@@      QE
)@@G@@    J         C$SFERR           . NO, CHECK FOR ERRORS@[@@@@.     @[@@@@QF
)@@G@@C$SF*.@E@@@@          SA        A0,B$CSFA0        . SAVE A0 BEFORE CSF$ QG
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ER        CSF$              . SUBMIT REQUEST@F@@@@      QH
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,1,X11          . RETURN ON ZERO STATUS     @[@@@@.     QI
)@@G@@@B@@@@. ENTRY POINT TO PRINT ERROR MESSAGE ONLY @[@@@@.     @D@@@@C$SFERQJ
)@@G@@R*  DS        A0,A0A1$          . SAVE REGISTERS@D@@@@          LN      QK
)@@G@@  A0,0,X11          . GET HIS MASK  @F@@@@          AND       A0,A0A1$  QL
)@@G@@        . MASK OUT UNWANTED BITS    @F@@@@          JZ        A1,C$SF5  QM
)@@G@@        . RETURN IF NOTHING TO PRINT@D@@@@          SA        A1,A$CSFA0QN
)@@G@@        . PUT IN PACKET @B@@@@          L,U       A0,EXLNK+CSF      .   QO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SA        A0,ERR$PKT        . SAVE IT IN PACKET   @E@@@@QP
)@@G@@          L         A0,SPEAK          . GET SPEAK LEVEL     @F@@@@      QQ
)@@G@@    S,S4      A0,ERR$PKT        . STORE IN ERROR$ PACKET    @E@@@@LINK  QR
)@@G@@    L,U       A1,ERR$PKT        . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @G@@@@          L QS
)@@G@@        A0,(1*/33+LNKERR) . PICK UP REP ERRORS DURING LINK$ @E@@@@      QT
)@@G@@    ER        IALL$             . SET CONTINGENCY     @D@@@@          LAQU
)@@G@@        A0,('ERROR$')     . GET REP NAME  @C@@@@          ER        LINKQV
)@@G@@$             . LINK    @E@@@@          LA        A0,I$MASK         . GEQW
)@@G@@T CONTINGENCY MASK@F@@@@          ER        IALL$             . TURN ON QX
)@@G@@CONTINGENCIES     @D@@@@C$SF5     DL        A0,A0A1$          . RESTORE QY
)@@G@@A0    @D@@@@          J         1,X11             . RETURN TO USER@[@@@@QZ
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@$(2). @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF WE COME HERE IT IS BECAUSE OF CRA
)@@G@@ONTINGENCY DURING ER LINK$    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LNKERR    RES       2   RB
)@@G@@              . CONTINGENCY PACKET  @D@@@@          L,S1      A0,LNKERR RC
)@@G@@        . GET ERROR TYPE@D@@@@          TE,U      A0,010            . RERD
)@@G@@P ERROR?    @G@@@@          ER        EABT$             . NO, DIE UNKNOWRE
)@@G@@N DEATH SORRY     @G@@@@          L         A0,PCWREP         . YES, TELRF
)@@G@@L USER COULD NOT LINK   @C@@@@          ER        PRINT$            . PRRG
)@@G@@INT   @E@@@@          L,H2      A0,LNKERR         . GET RETURN ADDRESS  RH
)@@G@@@G@@@@          J         1,A0              . RETURN AS IF NOTHING HAPPERI
)@@G@@NED   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@MREP      'ATTEMPT TO ER LINK$ TO ERROR$ REP FAIRJ
)@@G@@LED' .@E@@@@PCWREP    +         0100+$-MREP,MREP  . PRINT CONTROL WORD  RK
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@$(1). @D@@@@. THIS ROUTINE SIMULATES AN I$ALL ERROR FORL
)@@G@@R I/O ERRORS@D@@@@. WHICH ARE NOT CONTINGENCIES I.E. I/O ERRORS 1-20    RM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@. CALLED    @B@@@@.         L,U       A0,PACKET ADDRESRN
)@@G@@S     @^@@@@.         LMJ X11,I$OERR@#@@@@.         <RETURN>@[@@@@.     RO
)@@G@@@]@@@@I$OERR*.    @D@@@@          DS        A0,A0A1$          . SAVE REGRP
)@@G@@ISTERS@I@@@@          LXI,U     A1,,X11           . TAKE CONTINGENCY ADDRQ
)@@G@@RESS AS CALL ADDRESS    @E@@@@          LXM,U     A1,,A0            . GERR
)@@G@@T PACKET ADDRESS  @D@@@@          L,S1      A0,3,A0           . GET I/O RS
)@@G@@STATUS@D@@@@          LSSL      A0,6              . SHIFT IN PLACE@E@@@@RT
)@@G@@          A,U       A0,010012         . ADD CONTINGENCY BITS@C@@@@      RU
)@@G@@    LDSL      A0,18             . SHIFT   @C@@@@          SSL       A1,1RV
)@@G@@8             . RESET A1@F@@@@          DS        A0,I$PKT          . STRW
)@@G@@ORE IN CONTINGENCY CELLS@D@@@@          J         I$CAL             . FARX
)@@G@@KE INTERRUPT@B@@@@          END                         .   ___     . = RY
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@          DEF     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE: FUNCTIONS RZ
)@@G@@WHOSE NAMES ARE THE SAME AS VARIABLE NAMES *MUST*     @D@@@@. BE DEFINEDSA
)@@G@@ PRIOR TO THE EQU'S FOR THE VARIABLES     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@SB
)@@G@@. ------ FUNCTION TO CONSTUCT IMMEDIATE VALUES  @G@@@@.        NOTE: FULSC
)@@G@@LWORD NEGATIVE VALUES WILL AUTOMATICALLY GET SIGN     @G@@@@.           SD
)@@G@@   EXTENSION, BUT HALFWDS WHOSE LEFTMOST BIT HAPPENS TO BE  @G@@@@.     SE
)@@G@@         ON WILL NOT. HENCETHERE IS NO NEED FOR AN XU(...) FUNC.  @[@@@@SF
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@F         FUNC    @^@@@@U*        NAME      016 @^@@@@XU*   SG
)@@G@@    NAME      017 @E@@@@ DO F=3 , GO G$$FMU                   . TEST FORSH
)@@G@@ FLAGGED    @D@@@@MASM      EQU       0=0=0             . ON IF MASM    SI
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ON        MASM=0            . BEGIN ASM STUFF     @F@@@@SJ
)@@G@@ DO 1-(&(F(1))=-2) , GO G$$FMU        . TEST FOR F(1) RELOCATABLE @E@@@@SK
)@@G@@ DO 1= +(I$ 0,1++F(1)**1,0,0,0,0) , GO G$$FMU . OR HAS FORM @E@@@@      SL
)@@G@@    OFF                         . END OF ASM STUFF    @E@@@@          ONSM
)@@G@@        MASM              . BEGIN MASM STUFF    @H@@@@ DO F=1 , END +F(0SN
)@@G@@)                   . IF NO ARGS ('U') THEN OUTPUT VALUE    @G@@@@ DO $BSO
)@@G@@A(F(1))>0 , GO G$$FMU           . IF NOT 0, THEN FORM OR RELOC    @D@@@@SP
)@@G@@          OFF                         . END OF MASM   @F@@@@. AT THIS POSQ
)@@G@@INT, F(1) IS A LEGITIMATE FORMLESS CONSTANT VALUE     @G@@@@ DO (F(1)>07SR
)@@G@@77777)++(F(1)<-131071) , END (+F(1)) . TOO BIG? GEN LITERAL.@A@@@@IBIT  SS
)@@G@@    EQU     0<(F(1)**0200000) @A@@@@HBIT      EQU     0<(F(1)**0400000) ST
)@@G@@@G@@@@J         EQU       017-(F(0)=016)*(F(1)>-0) . IF NOT 'XU', GEN EISU
)@@G@@THER  @E@@@@ DO 1 ,   END     +(I$ 0,J,0,0,2*HBIT+IBIT,F(1)**0177777)   SV
)@@G@@@F@@@@. COME HERE IF ARG F(1) IS RELOCATABLE, TAGGED, OR HAS FORM...    SW
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$FMU*   NAME    @E@@@@          END       +(I$ 0,F(0),0,F(2),2*FSX
)@@G@@(*2)+F(*1),F(1))  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. HARDWARE MODE INDEPENDENT FUNCS TOSY
)@@G@@ SIGNIFY EXTRACTION OF A PARTIAL WORD     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@F         FUSZ
)@@G@@NC    @C@@@@W*        NAME      0                 . FULLWORD@^@@@@H1*   TA
)@@G@@    NAME      2   @^@@@@H2*       NAME      1   @^@@@@XH2*      NAME    TB
)@@G@@  3   @^@@@@S1*       NAME      015 @^@@@@S2*       NAME      014 @^@@@@TC
)@@G@@S3*       NAME      013 @^@@@@S4*       NAME      012 @^@@@@S5*       NATD
)@@G@@ME      011 @^@@@@S6*       NAME      010 @F@@@@ DO (0=0=0)**(F=1) , ENDTE
)@@G@@ +(F(0))      . NO ARGS +> OUTPUT VALUE   @E@@@@          END       +(I$TF
)@@G@@ 0,F(0),,F(2),2*F(*2)+F(*1),F(1))   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. HARDWARE MODE DETG
)@@G@@PENDENT PARTIAL WORD EXTRACTION FUNCS     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$PWMD(1) EQTH
)@@G@@U       -1                . SET PARTIAL WORD MODE UNDEFINED @[@@@@.     TI
)@@G@@@G@@@@F         FUNC                        . THIRD WORD DEPENDENT PARTITJ
)@@G@@AL WDS@^@@@@XH1*      NAME      4   @^@@@@T1*       NAME      7   @^@@@@TK
)@@G@@T2*       NAME      6   @^@@@@T3*       NAME      5   @G@@@@          ONTL
)@@G@@        0                 . TURN OFF PSR CHECK (FOR NOW)    @G@@@@ DO G$TM
)@@G@@PWMD(1)=1                       ; IF PARTWD MODE SET TO QUARTER   @E@@@@TN
)@@G@@   , END +(I$ 077,020,020,020,4,010000000) . FORCE A T-FLAG @F@@@@G$PWMDTO
)@@G@@*(1) EQU      0                 . ELSE DEFINE THIRDWD MODE  @B@@@@      TP
)@@G@@    OFF                         .   @F@@@@ DO (0=0=0)**(F=1) , END +(F(0TQ
)@@G@@))      . NO ARGS +> OUTPUT VALUE   @E@@@@          END       +(I$ 0,F(0TR
)@@G@@),,F(2),2*F(*2)+F(*1),F(1))   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@F         FUNC          TS
)@@G@@              . QUARTER WD DEPENDENT PARTIAL WDS@^@@@@Q2*       NAME    TT
)@@G@@  4   @^@@@@Q1*       NAME      7   @^@@@@Q3*       NAME      6   @^@@@@TU
)@@G@@Q4*       NAME      5   @G@@@@          ON        0                 . TUTV
)@@G@@RN OFF PSR CHECK (FOR NOW)    @G@@@@ DO G$PWMD(1)=0                     TW
)@@G@@  ; IF PARTWD MODE SET TO THIRD     @E@@@@   , END +(I$ 077,020,020,020,TX
)@@G@@4,010000000) . FORCE A T-FLAG @F@@@@G$PWMD*(1) EQU      1               TY
)@@G@@  . ELSE DEFINE QUARTERWD MODE@B@@@@          OFF                       TZ
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@ DO (0=0=0)**(F=1) , END +(F(0))      . NO ARGS +> OUTPUT VAUA
)@@G@@LUE   @E@@@@          END       +(I$ 0,F(0),,F(2),2*F(*2)+F(*1),F(1))   UB
)@@G@@@F@@@@/. DEFINITIONS WHICH REPLACE THE NEED FOR AXR$. BY DOING THIS, WE UC
)@@G@@@F@@@@. PREVENT ERRORS IN DEFINITION WHICH MIGHT OCCUR IF THE PROGRAMMERUD
)@@G@@@F@@@@. PUT HIS OWN AXR$ IN AND IT ACCIDENTALLY PRECEDED THE FUNCTION   UE
)@@G@@@B@@@@. DEFINITIONS CONTAINED IN THIS ELEMENT.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@X1    UF

)@@G@@    EQU       R9  @A@@@@. PARTIAL WORD DESIGNATORS FOLLOW   @[@@@@.     VA
)@@G@@@G@@@@. WELL, THEY USED TO, BUT HAVE BEEN REMOVED FOR REASONS GIVEN ABOVVB

)@@G@@OC    *0    @#@@@@SAXR$*    NAME    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF NOT @MASM, DEVF

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND EDIT$ PROCS@F@@@@TL
)@@G@@. MODIFIED BY JEFF JEWETT FROM THE ORIGINAL CLASSIC BY D. ZAVE.   @[@@@@TM
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@. REASONS FOR MODIFICATIONS:  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. 1) TO ALLOTN
)@@G@@W 18 BIT UFIELDS. E.G.  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         E$FD1     'RES',,U  TO
)@@G@@        . I$ OR BUST    @C@@@@.   GENERATES A 'T' FLAG WHEN USING STOCK TP
)@@G@@EDIT$P@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. 2) TO ALLOW EQUF'D J-DESIGNATOR. E.G.   @[@@@@TQ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.   A     EQUF      BLIP,,S3  @B@@@@.         E$COL     BLIPTR
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   STOCK EDIT$P GENERATES A 'T' FLATS
)@@G@@G. SOUND INCREDIBLE, BUT IT'S @G@@@@.   TRUE. WHAT PAIN EXISTS IS DUE ALTT
)@@G@@MOST ENTIRELY TO THE ILL-CONSIDERED @G@@@@.   (SORRY, DAREK) 'U' DEFAULTTU
)@@G@@ J-DESIGNATOR. IN THE ABOVE EXAMPLE THE   @F@@@@.   STOCK EDIT$P 'SEES' TV
)@@G@@NO EXPLICIT J-DESIG (E.G. BLIP,,J) AND SO @ @@@@.   TRIES TO FORCE A 'U'TW
)@@G@@ IN.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. 3) EXTENSIONS TO HANDLE OUR ADDITIONAL ROUTINETX
)@@G@@S AND PACKET FIELDS.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE THAT MODIFICATIONS (1) TY
)@@G@@AND (3) ARE REFLECTED IN A SIGNIFICANTLY  @F@@@@. LARGER E$AD. IF THE STTZ
)@@G@@OCK ASSEMBLER ALLOWED ONE TO 'OR' OFF     @H@@@@. NON-RELOCATABLE FIELDSUA
)@@G@@ (A PERFECTLY REASONABLE REQUEST, WE THINK), THEN     @B@@@@. THE PROC WUB
)@@G@@OULD BE SUBSTANTIALLY SMALLER.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOTE: WE BELIEVE THAT UC
)@@G@@THIS PROC IS COMPATIBLE WITH STOCK UNIVAC @F@@@@. ASM AND MASM. WE MIGHTUD
)@@G@@ BE WRONG. ANY COMPLAINTS, SUGGESTIONS, OR@E@@@@. EFFUSIVE DEMOSTRATIONSUE
)@@G@@ OF PRAISE SHOULD BE FORWARDED TO:  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         JEFF JEWUF

)@@G@@D                         .   @[@@@@/.    @^@@@@.   THE UOM EDIT$ PACKETWI

)@@G@@ER-DEFINED  @F@@@@.    PARAMETERS, AND INTERNAL FLAGS USED BY THE EDIT$ WK
)@@G@@ROUTINES.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    EDIT$ USES THE FOLLOWING PACKET. WORDWL
)@@G@@S 6 THROUGH 9 ARE NEEDED@G@@@@.    BY THE FLOATING POINT ROUTINES. WORDSWM
)@@G@@ 6 THROUGH 12 ARE REQUIRED    @E@@@@.    FOR ASCII CAPABILITIES. EXTENDEWN

)@@G@@LY BY EDIT$.@[@@@@.     @[@@@@/.    @G@@@@.   EXTERNAL DEFINITIONS  (FORXT
)@@G@@ JOE USER). JOE SUPPLIES PACKET ADDRESS.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P$        PRXU

)@@G@@,1),P$(1,2)   . DEFINE STUFF  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@QT        EQU       05  XX

)@@G@@@G@@@@FPS*      EQUF      PKT+2,,13           SCALE FOR FLOATING POINT EYB

)@@G@@/.    @F@@@@. ORIGINAL GENERALIZED ADDRESSING PROC, INCLUDED FOR COMPLETYY
)@@G@@ENESS.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.  +(E$AD S,T U) SCANS P$(S,T) FOR UFIELD, P$(S,YZ
)@@G@@T+1) FOR EXPLICIT XREG, @G@@@@.         P$(S,T+2) FOR EXPLICIT J-DESIGNAZA
)@@G@@TOR. UFIELD MAY BE EQUFFED. IF@D@@@@.         NO J-DESIG FOUND, THEN DEFZB
)@@G@@AULT U IS USED.   @F@@@@.  +(E$AD0 S,T U) PERFORMS AS ABOVE, BUT ONLY P$ZC
)@@G@@(S,T) IS SCANNED. @E@@@@.         THERE ARE NO EXPLICIT XREG OR J-DESIG ZD
)@@G@@FIELDS.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DECODE A U-FIELD INTO ITS CONSTITUENT ELZE
)@@G@@EMENTS. THIS PROC USES  @G@@@@. SUBTRACTION TO AVOID SPURIOUS R-FLAGS WHZF
)@@G@@ICH MIGHT OTHERWISE ARISE.    @F@@@@. IN ADDITION, IT DOES NOT ALTER THEZG
)@@G@@ FORM OF THE ORIGINAL U-FIELD,@F@@@@. SINCE IT IS UNKNOWN WHETHER THE U ZH
)@@G@@FIELD ALREADY HAS FORM OR NOT.@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. I HAVE NO SCRUPLES, SOZI
)@@G@@ MUCH OF THIS PROC WAS SNARFED FROM @^@@@@. PAT HAGERTY'S STRUC$. @[@@@@ZJ
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@        DEF @E@@@@G$JBIT(1) EQU 1*/29                   . J-ZK
)@@G@@DESIGNATOR BITS   @^@@@@G$JBIT(2) EQU 1*/28     @^@@@@G$JBIT(3) EQU 1*/2ZL
)@@G@@7     @^@@@@G$JBIT(4) EQU 1*/26     @D@@@@G$XBIT(1) EQU 1*/21           ZM
)@@G@@        . XREG BITS     @^@@@@G$XBIT(2) EQU 1*/20     @^@@@@G$XBIT(3) EQZN
)@@G@@U 1*/19     @^@@@@G$XBIT(4) EQU 1*/18     @C@@@@G$HIBI(1) EQU 1*/17     ZO
)@@G@@              . HBIT    @C@@@@G$HIBI(2) EQU 1*/16                   . IBZP
)@@G@@IT    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Q         PROC      *2,0            ZQ
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@E$AD*     NAME      1                 . COMPUTE GENERALIZED ZR
)@@G@@ADDRESS     @F@@@@E$AD0*    NAME      0                 . PROCESS ONE FIZS
)@@G@@ELD ONLY    @F@@@@MF   EQU  Q(0,0)                      . TRUE IF MANY-SZT
)@@G@@UBFIELDS    @C@@@@S    EQU  Q(1,1)                      . FIELD   @C@@@@ZU
)@@G@@T    EQU  Q(1,2)                      . SUBFIELD@H@@@@HBIT EQU P$(S,*T+1ZV
)@@G@@)*MF                . ON IF UFIELD,*XREG : ZERO IF E$AD0    @H@@@@IBIT EZW
)@@G@@QU P$(S,*T)*MF                  . ON IF *UFIELD      : ZERO IF E$AD0    ZX
)@@G@@@G@@@@. NOTE THAT WE CAN'T PROCESS THE NEXT 4 LINES AS P$(S,T+1)*(EXISTEZY
)@@G@@NCE=1)@G@@@@. BECAUSE OF PROPAGATION OF FORMS. E.G. A*0 => ZERO WITH FORZZ
)@@G@@M OF C.     @#@@@@. UGLY BUT TRUE.  @E@@@@ DO MF=0 ,XREG EQU  0         AA
)@@G@@        . EXPLICIT XREG SET 0 @F@@@@ DO MF=0 ,EXPJ EQU  0               AB
)@@G@@  . EXPLICIT J-DESIG SET 0    @H@@@@ DO MF ,XREG EQU  P$(S,T+1)         AC
)@@G@@  . IF NOT E$$A0 ,FETCH EXPLICIT XREG     @H@@@@ DO MF ,EXPJ EQU  P$(S,TAD
)@@G@@+2)           . IF NOT E$$A0 ,FETCH EXPLICIT J-DESIG  @C@@@@. OBTAIN MANAE
)@@G@@IPULATABLE UFIELD FROM ASM OR MASM. @D@@@@     ON   1-(+3>2>1)          AF
)@@G@@        . ON IF @ASM    @D@@@@IV(1) EQU +(P$(S,T))                  . NOAG
)@@G@@ *'S, PLEASE@D@@@@     OFF                              . END OF @ASM   AH
)@@G@@@D@@@@     ON   +3>2>1                      . ON IF @MASM   @F@@@@IV(1) AI
)@@G@@EQU $AP(P$(S,T))                . ONLY THE NON-REL PART     @D@@@@     OAJ
)@@G@@FF                              . END OF @MASM  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@JAY(1)AK
)@@G@@  EQU     0                     . ASSUME NO EQUF'D J-SPEC   @F@@@@ DO IVAL
)@@G@@(1)>0377777777                  ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D J     @D@@@@  ,K DAM
)@@G@@O 4                             ; FOR ALL J-BITS@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-JAAN
)@@G@@Y(1))>(G$JBIT(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,JAY(1) EQU JAY(1AO
)@@G@@)++G$JBIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-JAY(1)  AP
)@@G@@        . STRIP EQUF'D J FROM OPERAND     @E@@@@JAY(2)  EQU     EXPJ++JAAQ
)@@G@@Y(1)*/-26     . GET COMPLETE J-SPEC @F@@@@XRG(1)  EQU     0             AR
)@@G@@        . ASSUME NO EQUF'D X-SPEC   @F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0777777             AS
)@@G@@        ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D X     @D@@@@  ,K DO 4                     AT
)@@G@@        ; FOR ALL X-BITS@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-XRG(1))>(G$XBIT(K)-1) ; IFAU
)@@G@@ CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,XRG(1) EQU XRG(1)++G$XBIT(K)  . FOLD INTAV
)@@G@@O RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-XRG(1)          . STRIP EQUF'D XAW
)@@G@@ FROM OPERAND     @E@@@@XRG(2)  EQU     XREG++XRG(1)*/-18     . GET COMPAX
)@@G@@LETE X-SPEC @G@@@@ DO MF=1 , DO (JAY(2)=0)**(P$(S)<(T+2)) ,JAY(2) EQU Q(AY
)@@G@@2,1) . SET DEFALT @G@@@@ DO MF=0 , DO JAY(2)=0                  ,JAY(2) AZ
)@@G@@EQU Q(2,1) . SET DEFALT @F@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     0                     . ASBA
)@@G@@SUME NO EQUF'D H/I BITS @F@@@@ DO  IV(1)>0177777                    ; IFBB
)@@G@@ VALUE HAS EQUF'D H OR I@G@@@@  ,K DO 2                             ; FOBC
)@@G@@R BOTH BITS (OF I$ FORM INSTR)@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-HIB(1))>(G$HIBI(K)-1BD
)@@G@@) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,HIB(1) EQU HIB(1)++G$HIBI(K)  . FOBE
)@@G@@LD INTO RESULT    @F@@@@UF EQU +(P$(S,T))-HIB(1)-XRG(1)-JAY(1) . STRIP OBF
)@@G@@FF J,X,HI BITS    @F@@@@HIB(1) EQU (HBIT*2)++IBIT++(HIB(1)*/-16) . ALIGNBG
)@@G@@ H AND I BITS     @G@@@@ DO IV(1)<0 ,HIB(1) EQU 3             . IF UFIELBH
)@@G@@D IS NEG, H,I ARE BOTH 1@[@@@@.     @F@@@@  I$  0,JAY(2),0,XRG(2),HIB(1)BI
)@@G@@,UF . GENERATE THE EFFECTIVE UFIELD @D@@@@          END                 BJ
)@@G@@        . END OF E$AD   @[@@@@/.    @#@@@@. BEGIN USER PROCS@[@@@@.     BK
)@@G@@@B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @C@@@@E$APRT*   NAME    BL
)@@G@@  EAPRT$            . APRINT$ @E@@@@E$PRTG*   NAME      EPRTG$          BM
)@@G@@  . PRINT$ OR APRINT$   @F@@@@E$PRTGA*  NAME      EPRTGA$           . ASBN
)@@G@@CII OR FIELDATA PRINT$  @D@@@@E$PRTA*   NAME      EPRTA$            . ASBO
)@@G@@CII PRINT$  @G@@@@E$PRT*    NAME      EPRT$             . PRODUCE LITERABP
)@@G@@L, PRINT, CLEAR   @C@@@@E$PRTI*   NAME      EPRTI$            . PRINT   BQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@E$APRTI*  NAME      EAPRTI$           . ASCII PRINT   @D@@@@E$CSF*BR
)@@G@@    NAME      ECSF$             . CSF$ THINGIE  @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA  BS
)@@G@@  12,+(E$AD 1,2 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1,4)   @E@@@@ DO P$BT
)@@G@@(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LA,U  A1,P$(1,1)   @B@@@@          LMBU
)@@G@@J       11,P$(0,0)        .   @B@@@@          END                       BV
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *0,1            BW
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@E$DITX*   NAME      0                 . CLOSE EDIT$ PACKET  BX
)@@G@@@F@@@@E$COLN*   NAME      1                 . RETURN WITH COL NUM IN A0 BY
)@@G@@@F@@@@E$WRDN*   NAME      2                 . RETURN WITH WORD NUM IN A0BZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@E$MSGR*   NAME      3                 . REENTER MESSAGE EDITOR    CA
)@@G@@@H@@@@E$CLEAR*  NAME      4                 . CLEAR OUTPUT BUFFER, SET CCB
)@@G@@OL TO 0     @D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESSCC
)@@G@@@B@@@@ DO J=0 , LMJ       11,EDITX$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMJ     CD
)@@G@@  11,ECOLN$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=2 , LMJ       11,EWRDN$         .   CE
)@@G@@@B@@@@ DO J=3 , LMJ       11,EMSGR$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=4 , LMJ     CF
)@@G@@  11,ECLEAR$        .   @B@@@@          END                         .   CG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2                .   CH
)@@G@@@E@@@@E$PAD*    NAME      0                 . PAD OUT CHARACTERS  @H@@@@CI
)@@G@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2),P$(1CJ
)@@G@@,3)   @H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD 2,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$(2,1),CK
)@@G@@P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,EPAD$          .   @B@@@@CL
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@CM
)@@G@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @G@@@@E$DIT*    NAME      1   CN
)@@G@@              . ENTER AND OPEN EDIT$ PACKET     @H@@@@E$DITR*   NAME    CO
)@@G@@  2                 . REENTER EDIT$ PACKET AFTER E$DITX     @E@@@@E$CHARCP
)@@G@@*   NAME      3                 . INSERT 1 CHARACTER  @F@@@@E$COL*    NACQ
)@@G@@ME      4                 . MOVE TO SPECIFIED COL     @F@@@@E$SKIP*   NACR
)@@G@@ME      5                 . SKIP SPECIFIED NUM OF COLS@E@@@@E$MSG*    NACS
)@@G@@ME      6                 . ENTER MESSAGE EDITOR@E@@@@E$MSKP*   NAME    CT
)@@G@@  7                 . SKIP MSG FIELDS     @B@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    12,+CU
)@@G@@(E$AD 1,1 15) .   @D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ACV
)@@G@@DDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMJ       11,EDIT$          .   @B@@@@ DO J=2 , LMCW
)@@G@@J       11,EDITR$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=3 , LMJ       11,ECHAR$       CX
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@ DO J=4 , LMJ       11,ECOL$          .   @B@@@@ DO J=5 , LMCY
)@@G@@J       11,ESKIP$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=6 , LMJ       11,EMSG$        CZ
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@ DO J=7 , LMJ       11,EMSKP$         .   @B@@@@          ENDA
)@@G@@D                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PRDB
)@@G@@OC      *1                .   @D@@@@E$RASE*   NAME      0               DC
)@@G@@  . CLEAR BUFFER  @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD 1,1 15) . LA[,XU] DD
)@@G@@ A1,P$(1,1),P$(1,2),P$(1,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,ERASE$       DE
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@DF
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @D@@@@E$FD3*    NADG
)@@G@@ME      0                 . INSERT 3 WORDS@H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA  14,+(EDH
)@@G@@$AD 1,1)+2    . LA       A2,P$(1,1)+2,P$(1,2),P$(1,3) @E@@@@E$FD2*    NADI
)@@G@@ME      1                 . INSERT TWO WORDS    @G@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , DL  DJ
)@@G@@  12,+(E$AD 1,1)    . DL       A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2)     @D@@@@J         EQDK
)@@G@@U       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=0 , LMJ       11,EDL
)@@G@@FD3$          .   @B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMJ       11,EFD2$          .   @B@@@@DM
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@DN
)@@G@@P$        PROC      *2                .   @C@@@@E$PACKC*  NAME      0   DO
)@@G@@              . PACK    @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2 15) . LADP
)@@G@@[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1,4)   @F@@@@ DO P$(0)>1 , LXI   12,+(E$AD0DQ
)@@G@@ 0,1 15) . LXI[,XU]  A0,P$(0,1)     @E@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0DR
)@@G@@ 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1)@H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    14,+(E$AD 2,1 15DS
)@@G@@) . LA[,XU]  A2,P$(2,1),P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,EDT
)@@G@@PACKC$        .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@DU
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @D@@@@DV
)@@G@@E$COPY*   NAME      1                 . STRING COPY   @F@@@@E$PACK*   NADW
)@@G@@ME      2                 . STRING COPY WITH PACKING  @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 DX
)@@G@@, LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1,4)   @F@@@@DY
)@@G@@ DO P$(0)>1 , LXI   12,+(E$AD0 0,1 15) . LXI[,XU]  A0,P$(0,1)     @E@@@@DZ
)@@G@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1)@D@@@@J     EA
)@@G@@    EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMJ     EB
)@@G@@  11,ECOPY$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=2 , LMJ       11,EPACK$         .   EC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     ED
)@@G@@@B@@@@P$        PROC      *1,1              .   @D@@@@E$FW*     NAME    EE
)@@G@@  0                 . EFORM$ WORD   @F@@@@I         DO        P$(1) ,P$(EF
)@@G@@0,0) EQU (P$(0,0)*/P$(1,I))++1 .    @B@@@@          +         P$(0,0)   EG
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     EH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @D@@@@E$MSKPEI

)@@G@@  12,+(E$AD 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2),P$(1,3)   @D@@@@      EK
)@@G@@    LMJ       11,EMSKP$         . SKIP MSG FIELD@C@@@@          LMJ     EL
)@@G@@  11,EMSGR$         . AND COPY@B@@@@          END                       EM
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2              EN
)@@G@@  .   @G@@@@E$DECFL*  NAME      0                 . LEADING CHARS - FIXEEO
)@@G@@D FORMAT    @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA 12,+(E$AD 1,2)     . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1EP
)@@G@@,1+I),P$(1,2+I),P$(1,3+I@E@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LEQ
)@@G@@A[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1)@H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    14,+(E$AD 2,1 15) . LA[,XU] ER
)@@G@@ A2,P$(2,1),P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,EDECFL$      ES
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@ET
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @E@@@@E$OCTF*   NAEU
)@@G@@ME      1                 . FIXED FORMAT OCTAL  @E@@@@E$DECF*   NAME    EV
)@@G@@  2                 . FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL@F@@@@E$HEXF*   NAME      3   EW
)@@G@@              . FIXED FORMAT HEXADECIMAL  @H@@@@E$DECFZ*  NAME      4   EX
)@@G@@              . FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL-LEADING ZEROES   @H@@@@E$DCFZ*   NAEY
)@@G@@ME      4                 . FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL-LEADING ZEROES   @H@@@@EZ
)@@G@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2)    . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1FA

)@@G@@4 , LMJ       11,EDECFZ$        .   @B@@@@          END                 FF
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1        FG

)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2  FQ
)@@G@@              .   @G@@@@E$FORMC*  NAME      EFORMC$           . FORM EDIFR

)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P$        PROC      *1  @H@@@@E$FLS1*   NAME    GO

)@@G@@NT FORMAT   @E@@@@P$(9)     EQU       1                 . INSTRUCTION FLGS
)@@G@@AG    @H@@@@E$FLS2*   NAME      EFLS2$            . DOUBLE PRECISION SCIGT
