)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@F(']')    EQU       0135              .   @B@@@@GJ
)@@G@@F('#')    EQU       0043              .   @B@@@@F('^')    EQU       0136GK
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@F(' ')    EQU       0040              .   @C@@@@GL
)@@G@@I DO 26 ,F(5+I)  EQU  0100+I          . LETTERS @B@@@@F(')')    EQU     GM
)@@G@@  0051              .   @B@@@@F('-')    EQU       0055              .   GN
)@@G@@@B@@@@F('+')    EQU       0053              .   @C@@@@I DO 3 ,F(042+I)  GO
)@@G@@EQU  073+I          . <=>     @B@@@@F('&')    EQU       0046            GP
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@F('$')    EQU       0044              .   @B@@@@F('*')    EQGQ
)@@G@@U       0052              .   @B@@@@F('(')    EQU       0050            GR
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@F('%')    EQU       0045              .   @B@@@@F(':')    EQGS
)@@G@@U       0072              .   @B@@@@F('?')    EQU       0077            GT
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@F('!')    EQU       0041              .   @B@@@@F(',')    EQGU
)@@G@@U       0054              .   @B@@@@F('\')    EQU       0134            GV
)@@G@@  .   @C@@@@I DO 10 ,F(057+I) EQU 057+I           . DIGITS  @B@@@@F(072)GW
)@@G@@    EQU       0047              .   @B@@@@F(';')    EQU       0073      GX
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@F('/')    EQU       0057              .   @B@@@@F('.')GY
)@@G@@    EQU       0056              .   @B@@@@F('"')    EQU       0042      GZ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@F(077)    EQU       0137              .   @B@@@@ DO P$HA
)@@G@@(0,0) ,I DO 64 ,F(I+63) EQU 0   .   @[@@@@/.    @^@@@@.   ASCII TO FIELDHB
)@@G@@ATA   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@I DO 040 ,A(I-1)  EQU  '?'            . CHARACTEHC
)@@G@@RS    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@A(040)    EQU       ' '               .   @B@@@@HD
)@@G@@A(041)    EQU       '!'               .   @B@@@@A(042)    EQU       '"' HE
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(043)    EQU       '#'               .   @B@@@@HF
)@@G@@A(044)    EQU       '$'               .   @B@@@@A(045)    EQU       '%' HG
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(046)    EQU       '&'               .   @B@@@@HH
)@@G@@A(047)    EQU       ''''              .   @B@@@@A(050)    EQU       '(' HI
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(051)    EQU       ')'               .   @B@@@@HJ
)@@G@@A(052)    EQU       '*'               .   @B@@@@A(053)    EQU       '+' HK
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(054)    EQU       ','               .   @B@@@@HL
)@@G@@A(055)    EQU       '-'               .   @B@@@@A(056)    EQU       '.' HM
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(057)    EQU       '/'               .   @C@@@@HN
)@@G@@I DO 10 ,A(057+I) EQU 057+I           . DIGITS  @B@@@@A(072)    EQU     HO
)@@G@@  ':'               .   @B@@@@A(073)    EQU       ';'               .   HP
)@@G@@@B@@@@A(074)    EQU       '<'               .   @B@@@@A(075)    EQU     HQ
)@@G@@  '='               .   @B@@@@A(076)    EQU       '>'               .   HR
)@@G@@@B@@@@A(077)    EQU       '?'               .   @B@@@@A(0100)   EQU     HS
)@@G@@  '@'               .   @C@@@@I DO 26 ,A(0100+I) EQU 5+I            . LEHT
)@@G@@TTERS @B@@@@A(0133)   EQU       '['               .   @B@@@@A(0134)   EQHU
)@@G@@U       '\'               .   @B@@@@A(0135)   EQU       ']'             HV
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@A(0136)   EQU       '^'               .   @B@@@@A(0137)   EQHW
)@@G@@U       077               .   @D@@@@I DO 040 ,A(0137+I) EQU A(077+I)    HX
)@@G@@  . FOLD OVER     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.   PROC TO INSERT NEW CONVERSION VAHY
)@@G@@LUES  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Q$        PROC      *1,0              .   @B@@@@HZ
)@@G@@GETIT*    NAME                        .   @G@@@@ DO        Q$(1,1)='FD' IA
)@@G@@,J DO P$(I)/2 ,F*(P$(I,J*2)) EQU P$(I,J*2+1) .  @G@@@@ DO        Q$(1,1)IB
)@@G@@='AS' ,J DO P$(I)/2 ,A*(P$(I,J*2)) EQU P$(I,J*2+1) .  @B@@@@          ENIC
)@@G@@D                         .   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.   GENERATE TABLE@[@@@@ID
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@I         DO        P$-1 ,  GETIT  P$(I,1) .    @B@@@@FR    IE
)@@G@@    FORM      6,6,6,9,9         .   @E@@@@ DO P$(0,0)=0 ,I DO 64 , FR  AIF
)@@G@@(I-1),A(I+63),0,0,F(I-1) .    @D@@@@ DO P$(0,0) ,I DO   128 , FR A(I-1),IG
)@@G@@0,0,0,F(I-1) .    @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@IH
)@@G@@/.    @ @@@@.   INTERNAL CHARACTER LINKS  @F@@@@.   THESE DEFINE THE CELII
)@@G@@LS SETUP BY THE GENCHARS PROC. WE KEEP    @C@@@@.   THEM TOGETHER FOR THIJ
)@@G@@E SAKE OF MANAGEABILITY.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          DEF                 IK
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@@QT        EQU       Q4                . ALSO T3 @D@@@@IL
)@@G@@XTRA      EQUF      E$CHAR$+0,,S1     . INITIAL FUDGE @C@@@@SLASH     EQIM
)@@G@@UF      E$CHAR$+2,,S2     . '/'     @E@@@@FSHIFT    EQUF      E$CHAR$+2,IN
)@@G@@,S3     . DEC FRAC SHIFT COUNT@C@@@@PERIOD    EQUF      E$CHAR$+2,,S4   IO
)@@G@@  . '.'     @E@@@@SHFT      EQUF      E$CHAR$+2,,QT     . 72 - CHARS PERIP
)@@G@@ WORD @D@@@@MASK      EQUF      E$CHAR$+3,,QT     . 077 OR 0777   @C@@@@IQ
)@@G@@MINUS     EQUF      E$CHAR$+4,,S2     . '-'     @C@@@@COLON     EQUF    IR
)@@G@@  E$CHAR$+4,,S4     . ':'     @C@@@@. ATSIGN  EQUF      E$CHAR$+5,,QT   IS
)@@G@@  . '@'     @C@@@@PLUS      EQUF      E$CHAR$+6,,S2     . '+'     @C@@@@IT
)@@G@@COMMA     EQUF      E$CHAR$+6,,S4     . ','     @D@@@@MODINV    EQUF    IU
)@@G@@  E$CHAR$+6,,S5     . INVERSE MODE  @E@@@@SCNT1     EQUF      E$CHAR$+8,IV
)@@G@@,S2     . CHARS PER WORD -1   @D@@@@SCNT      EQUF      E$CHAR$+8,,S4   IW
)@@G@@  . CHARS PER WORD@F@@@@DCNT      EQUF      E$CHAR$+8,,S5     . CHARS PEIX
)@@G@@R DOUBLE WORD     @F@@@@DCNT1     EQUF      E$CHAR$+10,,S2    . CHARS PEIY
)@@G@@R DOUBLE WORD -1  @E@@@@E$PTRS$   EQUF      E$CHAR$+10,,01    . XQT TABLIZ
)@@G@@E POINTERS  @C@@@@BLANKS    EQU       E$CHAR$+13        . SPACES  @C@@@@JA
)@@G@@BLANK     EQUF      BLANKS,,8         . ONLY ONE@C@@@@EZERO     EQU     JB
)@@G@@  E$CHAR$           . ZERO    @D@@@@FUDGE     EQU       E$CHAR$         JC
)@@G@@  . FINAL FUDGE   @C@@@@ONEZERO   EQU       E$CHAR$+12        . (1,0)   JD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     ADRASCX JUMP TABLE INDICES    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@JE
)@@G@@ECNVT     EQU       0                 . CONVERT - SET UP ASCII XLATION  JF
)@@G@@@E@@@@EADAY3    EQU       1                 . EDAY3$ ASCII CODE   @F@@@@JG
)@@G@@EQWM      EQU       2                 . CHECK FOR QUARTERWORD MODE@E@@@@JH
)@@G@@EAMNTH    EQU       3                 . ASCII MONTH TABLE   @F@@@@EXLATEJI
)@@G@@    EQU       4                 . TRANSLATE 1 CHARACTER     @[@@@@.     JJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@EDIT$PROC* PROC                       . LINKS   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@JK
)@@G@@.   TRANSLATE CHARACTER @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1        JL
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@XLATE**   NAME      01                .   @F@@@@ DO P$JM
)@@G@@(1)>0 , DO 1-(P$(1,1)=14) , LA 14,P$(1,1),P$(1,2),P$(1,3) . @G@@@@      JN
)@@G@@    LA        15,ADRASCX        . 15 HAS ASCII CODE BASE ADDRESS  @B@@@@JO
)@@G@@          UNLIST                      .   @D@@@@          TZ        EASCJP
)@@G@@II            . ASCII ANYTHING@D@@@@          LMJ       15,EXLATE,15    JQ
)@@G@@  . YES, PROCESS  @C@@@@          LM,15     14,,14            . BE SAFE JR
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LIST                        .   @B@@@@          END     JS
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.   ASCII, FIELDATA CHARS, SHIJT
)@@G@@FT COUNTS, MASKS, ETC.  @B@@@@.   DEFINED AND GENERATED BY EDIT$PROC.   JU
)@@G@@@B@@@@P$        PROC                        .   @B@@@@GENCHARS** NAME   JV
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@@R         FORM      6,6,6,6,12        .   JW
)@@G@@@B@@@@RR        FORM      6,6,6,18          .   @D@@@@          +       JX
)@@G@@  07777D            . ROUNDING UP   @E@@@@          R         0,'/',34,'JY
)@@G@@.',72-6 . SLASH,PERIOD,SHFT   @B@@@@          R         0,057,31,056,72-JZ
)@@G@@9 .   @D@@@@          R         1,'-',28,':',0777 . MINUS,COLON   @C@@@@KA
)@@G@@          R         1,055,24,072,'@'  . ATSIGN  @E@@@@          +       KB
)@@G@@  1,'+',21,',',1,0  . PLUS,COMMA,MODINV   @B@@@@          +         1,05KC
)@@G@@3,18,054,0,0  .   @D@@@@          +         1,6-1,14,6,12,0   . SCNT1,CNKD
)@@G@@T,DCNT@B@@@@          +         1,4-1,11,4,8,0    .   @D@@@@          RRKE
)@@G@@        0,12-1,8,EDIT$T   . DCNT,E$PTRS$  @B@@@@          RR        0,8-KF
)@@G@@1,4,EDIT$TA   .   @C@@@@          +         1,0               . ONEZERO KG
)@@G@@@C@@@@          +         '      '          . BLANKS  @D@@@@          + KH
)@@G@@        040,040,040,040   . ASCII BLANKS  @B@@@@          END           KI
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@KJ
)@@G@@/.    @G@@@@.   EXTERNAL DEFINITIONS  (FOR JOE USER). JOE SUPPLIES PACKEKK
)@@G@@T ADDRESS.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P$        PROC      *1                . FIKL
)@@G@@ELD IS ADDR OF PACKET   @B@@@@A$EFIELDS* NAME                       .   KM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@PKT       EQUF      P$(1,1),P$(1,2)   . DEFINE STUFF  KN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@QT        EQU       05                . 05 OR T3@D@@@@KO
)@@G@@IL*       EQUF      PKT,,11             IMAGE LENGTH  @D@@@@ILOC*     EQKP
)@@G@@UF      PKT,,01             IMAGE LOCATION@G@@@@FPS*      EQUF      PKT+KQ
)@@G@@2,,13           SCALE FOR FLOATING POINT EDIT   @G@@@@FPR*      EQUF    KR
)@@G@@  PKT+2,,12           FLOATING POINT ROUNDING OPTION  @G@@@@AEMSGC*   EQKS
)@@G@@UF      PKT+6,,QT         . EMSG$ ASCII SIGNAL CHARACTER    @I@@@@DPC*  KT
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+10,,Q1        . ASCII CHARACTER FOR DOUBLE PRECISION SKU
)@@G@@C     @I@@@@SPC*      EQUF      PKT+10,,Q2        . ASCII CHARACTER FOR KV
)@@G@@SINGLE PRECISION SC     @D@@@@          END                         . ALKW
)@@G@@L FOR YOU   _@@@@@              .   @B@@@@XLATE**[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@      KX
)@@G@@  DEF @^@@@@PF      FORM    12,6,18 @F@@@@. PARAMETERS FOR DEFINITION OFKY
)@@G@@ ERROR$ LINKAGE AND CONTROL PACKETS @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. ***** NOTE TO NOKZ
)@@G@@N-UOM SITES ***** @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LIJON = 1 : ERROR$ REP IS CONFIGURLA
)@@G@@ED AS A SYSTEM COMMON BANK    @F@@@@.         AND MAY THEREFORE BY CALLELB
)@@G@@D VIA AN LIJ. THE ENTRY POINT @F@@@@.         ('ERROR$$') IS PRESENTLY DLC
)@@G@@EFINED IN UOM-ERU$ AS 01001.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.       = 0 : ERROR$ IS LD
)@@G@@NOT CONFIGURED BUT RESIDES IN LIB$ OR IN THE    @F@@@@.         FILE FROLE
)@@G@@M WHICH THE PROGRAM IS EXECUTING. CONTROL IS VIA@F@@@@.         RLIST$-LLF
)@@G@@INK$. THIS WILL NOT WORK ON EXEC LEVELS > 33.   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. ****LG
)@@G@@*     @B@@@@LIJON   EQU    1    . WE MAY LIJ TO ERROR$@[@@@@.     @D@@@@LH
)@@G@@ERROR$BDI EQU       E$RROR$           . UOM STANDARD  @G@@@@. ERROR$BDI LI
)@@G@@EQU       UOM$ERROR$        . FUNKY VERSION FOR OUR FRIENDS @[@@@@.     LJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@/.                   H$MONITOR - ERROR$   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     LK
)@@G@@ THE  UNIVERSITY  OF  MARYLAND  FORTRAN  CONTINGENCY MONITOR IS   @G@@@@LL
)@@G@@.  COMPOSED OF A  GROUP  OF  ELEMENTS  COLLECTIVELY  REFERRED  TO  AS   LM
)@@G@@@G@@@@.  H$MONITOR.  TO  REDUCE  STORAGE  REQUIREMENTS,  MUCH  OF THE ERLN
)@@G@@ROR   @G@@@@.  ANALYSIS CODE AND MOST OF THE ERROR MESSAGES RESIDE IN  ALO
)@@G@@  DYNAMIC   @G@@@@.  COMMON  BANK  NAMED  ERROR$,  WHICH  IS CALLED BY HLP
)@@G@@$MONITOR IN THE   @ @@@@.  EVENT OF A HARDWARE ERROR. @[@@@@.     @G@@@@LQ
)@@G@@.     THERE ARE FOUR WAYS THAT H$MONITOR MAY  CALL  THE  ERROR$  BANK   LR
)@@G@@@G@@@@.  (ONE WAY USING RLIST$-LINK$, AND THREE USING THE LIJ INSTRUCTIOLS
)@@G@@N).   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.  1) ER LINK$    @G@@@@.     THIS PROCEDURE IS LT
)@@G@@THE MOST CONVENIENT, AND HENCE WILL NOT  WORK   @G@@@@.  ON  EXEC  LEVELLU
)@@G@@S GREATER THAN 33. THIS METHOD IS CONFIGURED IN THE   @G@@@@.  UOM-RLIB$LV
)@@G@@ FILE PROVIDED ON THE UOM DISTRIBUTION TAPES.  TO PRODUCE   @^@@@@.  A LLW
)@@G@@INK$ H$MONITOR:   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.     @COPY UOMRLIB$.,              LX
)@@G@@. COPY RLIB$ INTO TPF$. @F@@@@.     @ED H$TAGS/UOM                . EDITLY
)@@G@@ THE H$MONITOR PROC     @E@@@@.     F LIJON                       . FINDLZ
)@@G@@ THE LINK$-LIJ TAG@F@@@@.     R LIJON EQU 0                 . SAY: WE MAMA
)@@G@@Y LINK$ TO ERROR$ @A@@@@.     @PDP,L H$TAGS/UOM,H$TAGS/UOM  @F@@@@.     MB
)@@G@@@MASM,SE ERROR$LINK,ERROR$LINK/H$MONITOR . @ASM MAY BE USED @B@@@@.     MC
)@@G@@@MASM,SE RUN$ERR,RUN$ERR/H$MONITOR  @]@@@@.     @PACK @]@@@@.     @PREP MD
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     @COPY ,UOMRLIB$.              . BACK TO THE FILE@[@@@@.     ME
)@@G@@@G@@@@.     THE PRECEEDING DISCRIPTION IS PROVIDED ONLY IN THE INTEREST MF
)@@G@@ OF   @G@@@@.  COMPLETENESS,  AS  A  LINK$  UOM-RLIB$ IS PROVIDED ON THEMG
)@@G@@ DISTAPE.   @G@@@@.  NOTE THAT NO SPECIAL @MAP PROCEDURES ARE REQUIRED WMH
)@@G@@HEN  COLLECTING   @G@@@@.  A  FORTRAN  PROGRAM USING H$MONITOR, BUT ERROMI
)@@G@@R$ MUST RESIDE EITHER   @G@@@@.  IN SYS$*LIB$ OR IN THE FILE  FROM  WHICMJ
)@@G@@H  THE  ABSOLUTE  IS  BEING   @]@@@@.  EXECUTED.@[@@@@.     @^@@@@.  2) MK
)@@G@@LIJ CONFIGURATIONS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     THE THREE POSSIBLE LIJ PROCEDUML
)@@G@@RES MAY REQUIRE CHANGES EITHER TO   @G@@@@.  SYS$*LIB$ OR TO  THE  EXEC MM
)@@G@@ CONFIG,  AND  MAY  REQUIRE  A  SPECIAL   @G@@@@.  COLLECTION (@MAP) WHEMN
)@@G@@N CREATING A FORTRAN ABSOLUTE.  TO PRODUCE AN   @C@@@@.  H$MONITOR WHICHMO
)@@G@@ WILL LIJ TO ERROR$, ONE DOES:@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     @ED H$TAGS/UOM,H$TMP
)@@G@@AGS/UOM     @#@@@@.     F LIJON     @D@@@@.     R LIJON EQU 1           MQ
)@@G@@      . LIJ TO ERROR$   @]@@@@.     @EOF  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.  IF  ONE  MR
)@@G@@WISHES  TO  REFERENCE ERROR$ BY A SYMBOLIC BDI OTHER THAN   @G@@@@.  'E$MS
)@@G@@RROR$' (THE UOM STANDARD), A FURTHER  CORRECTION  IS  REQUIRED.   @G@@@@MT
)@@G@@.  FOR  EXAMPLE,  IF  IT  IS  DESIRED  TO REFERENCE ERROR$ BY THE BDI   MU
)@@G@@@]@@@@.  'SNORT$':@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.     @ED H$TAGS/UOM,H$TAGS/UOM     MV
)@@G@@@#@@@@.     F ERROR$BDI @G@@@@.     R ERROR$BDI EQU SNORT$        . 'SNOMW
)@@G@@RT$' IS NOW THE ERROR$ BDI    @G@@@@.     @PDP,L H$TAGS/UOM,H$TAGS/UOM  MX
)@@G@@. NOW PROCESS THE H$MONITOR PROC    @F@@@@.     @MASM,SE ERROR$LINK,ERROMY
)@@G@@R$LINK/H$MONITOR . @ASM MAY BE USED @B@@@@.     @MASM,SE RUN$ERR,RUN$ERRMZ
)@@G@@/H$MONITOR  @]@@@@.     @PACK @]@@@@.     @PREP @D@@@@.     @COPY ,UOMRLNA
)@@G@@IB$.              . BACK TO THE FILE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     AFTER CREATINB
)@@G@@NG THE LIJ H$MONITOR, THERE ARE THREE POSSIBLE WAYS   @#@@@@.  TO CALL ENC
)@@G@@RROR$.@[@@@@/.    @^@@@@.  2A) USER DEFINED BANK@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     ND
)@@G@@ THIS  METHOD REQUIRES NO MODIFICATION EITHER TO THE EXEC OR TO   @G@@@@NE
)@@G@@.  SYS$*LIB$, BUT DOES REQUIRE A SPECIAL  COLLECTION  PROCEDURE  WHEN   NF
)@@G@@@ @@@@.  CREATING FORTRAN PROGRAMS. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     @MAP,S ,ABS NG
)@@G@@                  . BEGIN COLLECTION@C@@@@.     LIB UOMRLIB(I1/$ODD,D1/$NH
)@@G@@EVEN) . SEE BELOW @#@@@@.     IBANK I1    @#@@@@.     IN TPF$.    @#@@@@NI
)@@G@@.     DBANK D1    @#@@@@.     IN TPF$.    @E@@@@.     IBANK,R E$RROR$,01NJ
)@@G@@000         . OR: IBANK,R SNORT$    @F@@@@.     IN UOMRLIB.ERROR$BANK/SYNK
)@@G@@S     . BANK MUST START AT 01000    @]@@@@.     END   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NL
)@@G@@.      THE  BIZARRE  'LIB' STATEMENT IS NECESSARY IN ORDER TO PREVENT   NM
)@@G@@@G@@@@.  ALL THE LOCATION COUNTERS OF ALL THE IMPLICITLY INCLUDED  ELEMENN
)@@G@@NTS   @G@@@@.  FROM  BEING PLACED IN THE MAIN DBANK. DON'T LOOK AT ME THNO
)@@G@@AT WAY, I   @#@@@@.  JUST WORK HERE.@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.  2B) COMMON BANKNP
)@@G@@ (CONFIGURED)     @G@@@@.      THIS  METHOD  REQUIRES  NO  SPECIAL  @MAPNQ
)@@G@@ COLLECTION, BUT DOES   @C@@@@.  DEMAND THE FOLLOWING EXEC CONFIG CHANGENR
)@@G@@S:    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.     LEVEL 33:   @C@@@@.               REPROG,WNS
)@@G@@+D+PE 'ERROR$',E$RROR$  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.     LEVEL 36:   @E@@@@.     NT
)@@G@@          REPROG BANKS,W+D+PE ARE 'ERROR$',E$RROR$    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@NU
)@@G@@.     ERROR$ MUST RESIDE IN SYS$*LIB$.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.  2C) COMMONV
)@@G@@N BANK (NON-CONFIGURED) : LEVEL 36 AND ABOVE    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.     NW
)@@G@@THIS  METHOD  REQUIRES  AN  EXEC  CONFIG  CHANGE,   A   SPECIAL   @D@@@@NX
)@@G@@.  COLLECTION PROCEDURE, BUT NO CHANGE TO SYS$*LIB$.  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@NY
)@@G@@.     EXEC CONFIG:@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.          REPROG BANKS,W+D+PE ARE 'NZ
)@@G@@ERROR$',E$RROR$   @ @@@@.          CBANKF 'TESTFILE'  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@OA
)@@G@@.     ERROR$ IS PLACED IN THE FILE  SYS$*TESTFILE , WHEREIN LURK  ALL   OB
)@@G@@@G@@@@.  SUCH NCCB'S. AFTER THE FIRST INITIAL LOAD, THE BANK WILL RESIDEOC
)@@G@@ IN   @G@@@@.  THE SWAPFILE. TO COLLECT AN ABSOLUTE CONTAINING THE LIJ-HOD
)@@G@@$MONITOR:   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.     @MAP,S ,ABS @A@@@@.     LIB UOMRLIB(OE
)@@G@@I1/$ODD,D1/$EVEN) @#@@@@.     IBANK I1    @#@@@@.     IN TPF$.    @#@@@@OF
)@@G@@.     DBANK D1    @#@@@@.     IN TPF$.    @G@@@@.     IBANK,S SNORT$    OG
)@@G@@            . NULL BANK (EMPTY): 'S' OPTION     @]@@@@.     END   @[@@@@OH
)@@G@@/.    @G@@@@.      WORK IS PROGRESSING ON SYSTEM LEVEL 74 AND FORTRAN  LOI
)@@G@@EVEL  E4.   @G@@@@.  ALL  SUGGESTIONS AND COMPLAINTS SHOULD BE BROUGHT TOJ
)@@G@@O THE ATTENTION   @]@@@@.  OF :     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.           JEFF JOK
)@@G@@EWETT @B@@@@.           SYSTEMS PROGRAMMING GROUP     @A@@@@.           OL
)@@G@@COMPUTER SCIENCE CENTER @A@@@@.           UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND  @B@@@@OM
)@@G@@.           COLLEGE PARK, MARYLAND  20742 @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.           ON
)@@G@@PHONE: (301) 454-2946   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. ----- CONTINGENCOO
)@@G@@Y TYPES (SET IN S3 OF PACKET) @[@@@@.     @B@@@@IOPR      EQU       01  OP
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@IGDM      EQU       02                 .  @B@@@@OQ
)@@G@@IFOF      EQU       03                 .  @B@@@@IFUF      EQU       04  OR
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@IDOF      EQU       05                 .  @B@@@@OS
)@@G@@IRST      EQU       06                 .  @B@@@@IABT      EQU       07  OT
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@IINT      EQU       010                .  @B@@@@OU
)@@G@@ITS       EQU       011                .  @B@@@@IERR      EQU       012 OV
)@@G@@               .  @B@@@@IIAI      EQU       013                .  @B@@@@OW
)@@G@@IBRK      EQU       014                .  @B@@@@IGRS      EQU       015 OX
)@@G@@               .  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. FUNCTION TO GET CORRECT BIT SETTINOY
)@@G@@G     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@BIT$*     FUNC      .   @D@@@@N         EQU     OZ
)@@G@@  BIT$(1)-1          . SHIFT COUNT  @G@@@@          END       1*/N      PA
)@@G@@         . SHIFT BIT TO CORRECT PLACE     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. SPECIAL TAPB
)@@G@@GS INDICATING TYPES OF ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN@[@@@@.     @F@@@@H$      EQU PC
)@@G@@    0777776               . TAKE H$MONITOR ACTION     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PD
)@@G@@. PRIMARY JUMPTARGETS FOR H$MONITOR DEFAULT ACTIONS   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@PE
)@@G@@C$DFLT(H$,IOPR) EQU H$EZAP    @ @@@@C$DFLT(H$,IGDM) EQU H$IGDM    @ @@@@PF
)@@G@@C$DFLT(H$,IFOF) EQU H$IFOF    @ @@@@C$DFLT(H$,IFUF) EQU H$IFUF    @ @@@@PG

)@@G@@@E@@@@. INITIALIZE CONTROL PARAMETERS USED BY GENERATING PROCS    @[@@@@PK
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@C$MINC(1) EQU 999999                  . MIN CONTING VALUE REPL

)@@G@@NK DUM@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ERRFRM FORM    6,6,6,6,6,6,6,6,6,6,12 . ERROR$ CPP

)@@G@@,,,0)     . RETURN IS S5 OF WD@[@@@@.     @^@@@@IALL$   EQU     0101    QH
)@@G@@@^@@@@CSF$    EQU     0017    @^@@@@MSCON$  EQU     0125    @^@@@@RFLAG$QI
)@@G@@(IALL$) EQU 1     @#@@@@RFLAG$(CSF$) EQU 2@^@@@@RFLAG$(MSCON$) EQU 15   QJ
)@@G@@@]@@@@F       FUNC@]@@@@ERRTYP* NAME@G@@@@        END  +(ERRFRM 0,,,,,RFQK
)@@G@@LAG$(F(1)),,,,,0)  . TYPE IS S6 OF WORD 1 @[@@@@ .    @C@@@@. SNAP BITS QL
)@@G@@(S1 OF WORD 2 OF ANALYSIS PACKET)   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@SNAPR   EQU     1 QM

)@@G@@.     @C@@@@/. PROC TO BUILD PRIMARY JUMP TABLE AND MASK    @[@@@@.     RL
)@@G@@@G@@@@P       PROC    *999                  . ARGS: TYPE,JUMPADR  TYPE,JRM
)@@G@@UMPADR@G@@@@C$TYPE**        NAME                  . DECLARE BY CONTINGENRN
)@@G@@CY TYPE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CHECK FOR AND PROCESS GLOBAL DEFAULTS   RO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@PP(1)     EQU       P                 . ASSUME  @G@@@@RP
)@@G@@ DO P(1)>0 , GO C$0001                . DEFAULT ONLY IF NO SPECS AT ALL RQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@DTYP    EQU     P(0,1)                . DEFAULT TYPE IS SUBFIELD ORR
)@@G@@N OPCO@G@@@@NREG    EQU     C$DFLT(DTYP)          . NO OF CONTIGENCIES TRS
)@@G@@O DEFAULT   @D@@@@K DO NREG ,P(K,1) EQU K               . SET THE TYPES RT
)@@G@@@F@@@@K DO NREG ,P(K,2) EQU DTYP            . AND DEFAULT ACTION FLAGS  RU
)@@G@@@F@@@@PP(1)   EQU     NREG+1                . MAKE SURE COUNT IS CORRECTRV
)@@G@@@]@@@@C$0001  NAME@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CHECK FOR AND PROCESS LOCAL DEFAULRW
)@@G@@TS    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@K DO PP(1)-1 , DO P(K,2)=H$ ,P(K,2) EQU C$DFLT(HRX
)@@G@@$,P(K,1)) . SET H$MON DEFAUL  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. FOLD SPECIFICATIONS INRY
)@@G@@TO MASK AND TABLE ENTRIES     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@K DO PP(1)-1 ,C$MASK*(1)RZ
)@@G@@ EQU C$MASK(1)++BIT$(P(K,1)) . BUILD CONTING MASK     @H@@@@K DO PP(1)-1SA
)@@G@@ , DO C$MINC(1)>P(K,1) ,C$MINC*(1) EQU P(K,1) . UPDATE MINVAL     @H@@@@SB
)@@G@@K DO PP(1)-1 , DO C$MAXC(1)<P(K,1) ,C$MAXC*(1) EQU P(K,1) . UPDATE MAXVASC
)@@G@@L     @G@@@@K DO PP(1)-1 ,C$JUMP*(P(K,1)) EQU P(K,2)      . TABULATE JUMSD
)@@G@@PTARGETS    @A@@@@        END     . END OF C$TYPE     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@SE
)@@G@@. PROC TO ACTUALLY GENERATE THE SPECIFIED TABLES@[@@@@.     @^@@@@P     SF
)@@G@@  PROC      *999  @#@@@@C$TGEN** NAME     @F@@@@*       EQU     $-C$MINCSG
)@@G@@(1)              . DEFINE TABLE BASE ADDR @B@@@@SPAN    EQU     C$MAXC(1SH
)@@G@@)-C$MINC(1)+1     @G@@@@K DO SPAN , +0,C$JUMP(C$MINC(1)-1+K)        . GESI
)@@G@@NERATE TABLE ENTRIES    @]@@@@        END @C@@@@/. PROC TO DEFINE ERROR$SJ
)@@G@@ ANALYSIS CONTROL PACKET@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC    *1@#@@@@ERR$CTSK
)@@G@@L** NAME    @B@@@@MASK(1) EQU     +(ERRFRM 0,,,,,,,,,,0)    @B@@@@K DO PSL
)@@G@@(1) ,MASK(1) EQU MASK(1)++P(1,K)    @^@@@@        ERRFRM MASK(1)  @]@@@@SM
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @A@@@@        END     . END OF H$TAGS     _@@@@@SN
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROC DOES A PCT$, AND RETURNS A0=CPSO
)@@G@@U TIME, A1=MEM TIME.    @F@@@@. PLACE ACCESS WORD FOR PCT$ IN A0, WHICH SP
)@@G@@MUST BE AT LEAST THE    @D@@@@. SIZE DESCRIBED BELOW.  TRASHES A0,A1,A3,SQ
)@@G@@ AND A4 .   @F@@@@. NOTE- CALLING ROUTINES RELY ON THE FACT THAT A2 IS PSR
)@@G@@RESERVED    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE FIRST PARAMETER FIELD INDICATES UNDESS
)@@G@@R WHICH LEVEL OF EXEC 8 @F@@@@. THIS PROC SHOULD WORK.  MORE THAN ONE LEST
)@@G@@VEL MAY BE SPECIFIED    @E@@@@. (I.E. M$TIME 27,31), IN WHICH CASE THE GSU
)@@G@@ENERATED CODE WILL@E@@@@. DETERMINE AT EXECUTION TIME WHICH LEVEL OF THESV
)@@G@@ EXEC IT IS @F@@@@. ACTUALLY RUNNING UNDER.  IF NO LEVEL IS SPECIFIED, TSW
)@@G@@HE CURRENT  @F@@@@. EXEC LEVEL IS ASSUMED. (31 AT THE TIME, BUT THAT MAYSX
)@@G@@ CHANGE).   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ENTRY 'M$TIMX' GENERATES ABBREVIATEDSY
)@@G@@ CODE FOR PEOPLE WHO    @F@@@@. HAVE ALREADY GOTTEN THE PCT.  REGISTER CSZ
)@@G@@ONTENTS MUST BE: A0=PCT @F@@@@. ADDR, A1=RESULT OF TIME$ DONE JUST BEFORTA
)@@G@@E ER PCT$ (27 AND 27/31 @F@@@@. ONLY), A4=POSITIVE FOR LEVEL 27, NEGATIVTB
)@@G@@E FOR LEVEL 31 (27/31   @#@@@@. VERSION ONLY).  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE TC
)@@G@@ARRAY MTIMESIZE STATES HOW LARGE THE PCT BUFFER HAS TO BE   @E@@@@. FOR TD
)@@G@@THE VARIOUS LEVELS, MTIMESIZE(0) CONTAINS THE PCT SIZE@B@@@@. NECESSARY TE
)@@G@@FOR THE CURRENT EXEC LEVEL.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE FOLLOWING LEVELS ATF
)@@G@@ND COMBINATIONS ARE CURRENTLY IMPLEMENTED:@^@@@@. 27, 31, 27/31, 32, 33 TG
)@@G@@@A@@@@. LEVEL 32 IS SUPPORTED AS LEVEL31  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          DETH
)@@G@@F     @^@@@@MTIMESIZE(0)  EQU   027 @^@@@@MTIMESIZE(27) EQU   0110@^@@@@TI
)@@G@@MTIMESIZE(31) EQU   027 @B@@@@MTIMESIZE(32) EQU   MTIMESIZE(31)     .   TJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@MTIMESIZE(33) EQU   MTIMESIZE(31)     .   @^@@@@P         PROC    TK
)@@G@@  1   @^@@@@M$TIME*   NAME      1   @D@@@@M$TIMX*   NAME      0         TL
)@@G@@ . ABBREVIATED ENTRY    @F@@@@PCT       EQUF      0,A0       . PCT ACCESTM
)@@G@@S WD IS USED AS INDEX   @D@@@@  DO  P(1)=0  ,P(1,1)  EQU  33  . ASSUMED TN
)@@G@@EXEC LEVEL  @A@@@@I DO P(1) ,GENFLG(P(1,I)) EQU 1     @ @@@@   DO  P(0,0TO
)@@G@@)=0  ,  GO M$TIMY @D@@@@      ON        GENFLG(27)        . LEVEL 27 CODTP
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@      LA        A1,A0             . PRESERVE PCT ACCESS WORDTQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@         ON        GENFLG(31)        . LEVEL 27/31 ONLY     @G@@@@TR
)@@G@@         SZ        0,A0              . CLEAR 1ST WORD OF PCT BUFFER     TS
)@@G@@@G@@@@         ER        MSCON$            . DO MSCON$ WITH INVALID FUNCTT
)@@G@@T (0) @G@@@@         LSSL      A0,1              . ALIGN STATUS TO SEE ITU
)@@G@@F S1=020    @E@@@@         SA        A0,A4             . AND STASH THE PTV
)@@G@@1 BIT @ @@@@         OFF       GENFLG(31) @F@@@@      ER        TIME$   TW
)@@G@@          . FIND OUT WHAT TIME IT IS NOW  @F@@@@      LDSC      A0,36   TX
)@@G@@          . RECOVER PCT ACW, HIDE TIME$   @ @@@@      OFF       GENFLG(2TY
)@@G@@7)    @E@@@@          ON        1-GENFLG(33)      . IF NOT LEVEL 33     TZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@   ER        PCT$              . THEN GLOMB UP THE PCT@E@@@@      UA
)@@G@@    OFF       1-GENFLG(33)      . END OF NON-33 CODE  @^@@@@M$TIMY    NAUB
)@@G@@ME      .   @D@@@@      ON        GENFLG(27)        . LEVEL 27 CODE     UC
)@@G@@@D@@@@      .         COMPUTE ACCURATE LEVEL 27 MEMORY TIME @E@@@@      UD
)@@G@@LA        A3,PCT+030        . GET CURRENT CORE SIZE   @E@@@@         ON UE
)@@G@@       GENFLG(31)        . LEVEL 27/31 ONLY     @F@@@@         TP       UF
)@@G@@ A4                . IS THIS REALLY LEVEL 27    @G@@@@         LA,U     UG
)@@G@@ A3,0              . NO, 31. MAKE CALCULATION VACUOUS @ @@@@         OFFUH
)@@G@@       GENFLG(31) @E@@@@      AND,U     A3,07777          . ACTUAL SIZE UI
)@@G@@IS IN T3    @G@@@@      MSI,U     A1,5              . CONVERT TIME (MSECUJ
)@@G@@) TO CLOCK TICKS  @F@@@@      ANA       A1,PCT+0107       . LESS TIME OFUK
)@@G@@ LAST PCT UPDATE  @D@@@@      LA,H1     A3,PCT+025        . GET QUANTUM UL
)@@G@@USED  @E@@@@      TN        A1                . WAS PCT UP-TO-DATE?     UM
)@@G@@@F@@@@      AA        A3,A1             . NO, BUMP BY TIME SINCE UPDATE UN
)@@G@@@F@@@@      MSI       A3,A4             . QUANTUM (A3) BY CORE SIZE (A4)UO
)@@G@@@ @@@@      OFF       GENFLG(27)    @E@@@@          ON        1-GENFLG(3UP
)@@G@@3)      . IF NOT LEVEL 33     @F@@@@   LA        A1,PCT+014        . PLUUQ
)@@G@@S RUN ACCUMULATION SO FAR     @D@@@@      ON        GENFLG(27)        . UR
)@@G@@LEVEL 27 CODE     @D@@@@      AA        A1,A3             . PUT IN EXIT US
)@@G@@REG   @ @@@@      OFF       GENFLG(27)    @G@@@@. NOTE: EXEC8 KEEPS TIMEUT
)@@G@@ NORMALIZED TO CORE BLOCKS. TO GET IN UNITS     @G@@@@. USED FOR UOM ACCUU
)@@G@@OUNTING (32K) SHIFT RESULT RIGHT 6 BITS (DIV BY 64)   @E@@@@   LA       UV
)@@G@@ A0,PCT+026        . FOR GOOD LUCK, GET CPU TIME@E@@@@          OFF     UW
)@@G@@  1-GENFLG(33)      . END OF NON-33 CODE  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. FOR LEVEL UX
)@@G@@33, WE TEST FOR OPERATION ON 1110-TYPE MACHINE  @E@@@@. VIA THE HIGHLY UUY
)@@G@@SEFUL TSS INSTRUCTION AND COMPUTE THE CPU @E@@@@. TIME FROM THE SRC'S. EUZ
)@@G@@LSE WE FETCH CPU TIME FROM PCT+026. @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          ON      VA
)@@G@@  GENFLG(33)        . BEGIN LEVEL 33 CODE @F@@@@          SZ        A3  VB
)@@G@@              . SET MACHINE FLAG (1=>1108)@H@@@@          SZ        PCT VC
)@@G@@              . CLEAR TEST-SET CELL IN PCT BUFFER     @G@@@@          TSVD
)@@G@@S       PCT               . IF 1110, SKIP NEXT INSTRUCTION  @F@@@@      VE
)@@G@@    J         A(1108)           . IF HERE, WE ARE ON 1108   @[@@@@.     VF
)@@G@@@^@@@@. BEGIN 1140/1110 CODE. @G@@@@. CPU TIME IS COMPUTED DIRECTLY FROMVG
)@@G@@ THE SRC'S BY THE FOLLOWING FORMULA:@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         CPU (200VH
)@@G@@ USECS) = (TOTAL SRC'S)*(AVE. INSTRUCTION/1.6 SRC)    @G@@@@.           VI
)@@G@@                 *(700NS/AVE.INSTRUCTION)*(SUP/200USECS)    @[@@@@.     VJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                         = (TOTAL SRC'S)*(7/3200)    @[@@@@.     VK
)@@G@@@G@@@@. UOM MOD EFFECTIVE 7/1/78. TO EQUALIZE CPU TIME (AND HENCE CB-SUBVL
)@@G@@S)    @E@@@@. ON OUR 1108 AND 1140 (WELL, AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE), WE HAVE VM
)@@G@@@D@@@@. DOUBLED THE CPU CALCULATION. E.G. CPU=SRC(14/3200)  @[@@@@.     VN
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LA        A3,A0             . WE ARE 1110. SAVE USERS PCVO
)@@G@@T ACW @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,PCT            . CLEAR INCREMENT OF AVP
)@@G@@0     @G@@@@          LA        A1,(4,0223)       . GET SRC'S (***NOTE: VQ
)@@G@@A LITERAL**)@H@@@@          ER        PCT$              . SRC'S INTO PCTVR
)@@G@@ BUFFER (2 DBLWORDS)    @F@@@@          LA        A0,A3             . REVS
)@@G@@LOAD USER'S PCT ACW     @E@@@@          DL        A3,PCT            . LOVT
)@@G@@AD SRC/PRIMARY    @G@@@@          DA        A3,PCT+2          . ADD SRC/VU
)@@G@@EXTENDED. SUM IN A3     @E@@@@          DS        A3,PCT+0          . SAVV
)@@G@@VE SUM IN PCT     @E@@@@          LDSL      A3,3              . MULTIPLYVW
)@@G@@ SUM BY 8   @H@@@@          DAN       A3,PCT+0          . MINUS 1*SUM = VX
)@@G@@7*SUM (DBLWORD MULTIPLY)@F@@@@          LDSL      A3,1              . UOVY
)@@G@@MMOD. TIMES TWO = 14*SUM@E@@@@          DI,U      A3,3200           . DIVZ
)@@G@@VIDE MEMTIME BY 64@A@@@@A(1108) . COME HERE FOR 1108 CODE   @E@@@@      WA
)@@G@@    ER        PCT$              . LOAD 027 WORD BUFFER@E@@@@          LAWB
)@@G@@        A1,PCT+014        . LOAD MEMTIME INTO A1@F@@@@          LA      WC
)@@G@@  A0,PCT+026        . LOAD A0 WITH 1108 CPU TIME@F@@@@          JZ      WD
)@@G@@  A3,$+2            . BUT IF A3 IS NONZ, THEN   @F@@@@          LA      WE
)@@G@@  A0,A3             . IT CONTAINS 1140 CPU TIME @E@@@@          OFF     WF
)@@G@@  GENFLG(33)        . END OF LEVEL 33 CODE@#@@@@   END       .    _@@@@@WG
)@@G@@64)   @E@@@@   LA        A0,PCT+026        . FOR GOOD LUCK, GET CPU TIMEWH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURES TO CALL FIASG$ AND FIFREE$ ROWI
)@@G@@UTINES.     @A@@@@. FIBITS WRITTEN BY MIKE MCAMIS     @A@@@@. FIASG  WRIWJ
)@@G@@TTEN BY ALAN STEBBENS   @A@@@@. FIFREE WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @A@@@@WK
)@@G@@. FIPFIL WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTON    @A@@@@. FIPELT WRITTEN BY BEN CRANSTWL
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. FIASG UPDATED TO WORK IN ASCII OR FIELDATA - 2WM
)@@G@@/11/76, AKS.@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         DEFINE BITS FOR FIASG$    @[@@@@WN
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          DEF                         .   @D@@@@FBIT      EQWO
)@@G@@U       001               . FORCE USE NAME@D@@@@UBIT      EQU       002 WP
)@@G@@              . USE NAME GIVEN@D@@@@XBIT      EQU       004             WQ
)@@G@@  . GET ASG,AX    @E@@@@RBIT      EQU       010               . GET READWR
)@@G@@ PERMISSION @E@@@@WBIT      EQU       020               . GET WRITE PERMWS
)@@G@@ISSION@D@@@@OBIT      EQU       040               . OPTIONS IN A3 @B@@@@WT
)@@G@@FIBITS*   PROC      0,0               .   @B@@@@          END           WU
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. TO ASSIGN A FILE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@WV
)@@G@@.         FIASG,'OPTS' PACKET,BITS NAME   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PRWW
)@@G@@OC      *2                .   @B@@@@FIASG*    NAME                      WX
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@N         EQU       6+3*(' '=040)     . # OF BITS PER CHAR  WY
)@@G@@@E@@@@C         EQU       077+0700*(N=9)    . SET PROPER MASK     @D@@@@WZ
)@@G@@          ON        P(1)>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@XA
)@@G@@. FUNCTION TO GET BIT FOR 'BITS' LETTER.  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@F         FUXB
)@@G@@NC      *                 .   @B@@@@PBIT*     NAME                      XC
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@I         DO      6 , DO M(0)*/(N-N*I)**C=F(1) , END F(2)   XD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          END       +0                . STRANGE BITS  @[@@@@.     XE
)@@G@@@E@@@@M(0)      EQU       P(1,2)+0D         . PICK UP MODE LETTERS@F@@@@XF
)@@G@@B(0)      EQU       PBIT('F',1)+PBIT('U',2)+PBIT('X',4)+; F,U,X   @F@@@@XG
)@@G@@                    PBIT('R',8)+PBIT('W',16)+PBIT('O',32)++; R,W,O@G@@@@XH
)@@G@@                    2*(P(2)>0)+32*(P(0)>1) . FORCE BITS IF NECESSARY    XI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@. NOW GENERATE CODE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          LAXJ
)@@G@@,U      A0,P(1,1)         .   @B@@@@          DO (B(0)=0)=0 , LXI,U A0,BXK
)@@G@@(0) . @D@@@@          OFF       P(1)>0            . ANY SPEC1 ?   @[@@@@XL
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(2)>0 , DL A1,P(2,1),P(2,2)      . GET FILENAME  @[@@@@XM
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@          ON        P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @E@@@@XN
)@@G@@          ON        P(0,1)=0=0        . SOMETHING THERE?    @E@@@@      XO
)@@G@@    ON        N=9               . ASCII CHARACTERSET? @G@@@@F         FUXP
)@@G@@NC      *                 . ASCII TO FIELDATA MAPPING FUNC  @B@@@@ATOF* XQ
)@@G@@    NAME                        .   @D@@@@        DO (F(1)=' ')++(F(1)=0XR
)@@G@@) , END +0 . ABLANK     @F@@@@          DO        (F(1)<'A')++(F(1)>'Z')XS
)@@G@@ , END +09) . BAD NEWS  @F@@@@          END       F(1)-'A'+6        . CHXT
)@@G@@ANGE TO FIELDATA   A    @E@@@@I         DO        6 ,;                MAXU
)@@G@@XIMUM OF 6 CHARS  @I@@@@P(0,1)    EQU       (P(0,1)**-(C*/(I*9-9)))+ATOFXV
)@@G@@(P(0,1)*/(9-9*I)**C)*/(I*6-6) .     @E@@@@          OFF       N=9       XW
)@@G@@        . ASCII CHARACTERSET? @G@@@@I DO 6 , DO P(0,1)**C*/30=0 ,P(0,1) XX
)@@G@@EQU P(0,1)*/6+5 . FILL THE FIELDATA @F@@@@G         FORM      36        XY
)@@G@@        . WE WANT ONLY ONE WORD     @D@@@@          L         A3,(G P(0,XZ
)@@G@@1))       . LOAD LITERAL@B@@@@          OFF       P(0,1)=0=0        .   YA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DO        P(0,1)=0 , LA,U   A3,0 . CLEAR OPTIONS REG    YB
)@@G@@@D@@@@          OFF       P(0)>1            . ANY OPTIONS ? @[@@@@.     YC
)@@G@@@ @@@@. FINALLY, CALL SUBROUTINE    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LMJ     YD
)@@G@@  X11,FIASG$        . ASSIGN FILE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END     YE
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS USED TO CAYF
)@@G@@LL THE DIAGNOSTIC ROUTINE FIDIAG$   @F@@@@. IF A CSF$ ERROR IS DETECTED YG
)@@G@@THE ERROR$ REP IS CALLED.  IF THE   @D@@@@. ERROR IS PERMISSIONS FIDIAG YH
)@@G@@PRINTS THE MESSAGE.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *0,1      YI
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@FIDIAG*   NAME      FIDIAG$           .   @D@@@@      YJ
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,P(0,0)        . CALL ROUTINE  @B@@@@          END     YK
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO YL
)@@G@@FREE A FILE WHICH HAS BEEN ASSIGNED @ @@@@. VIA FIASG$. THE CALL IS:    YM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         FIFREE    NAME FREECODE   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@YN
)@@G@@P         PROC      *2                .   @D@@@@FIFREE*   NAME      FIFRYO
)@@G@@EE$           . NORMAL FREE   @E@@@@FIFRIM*   NAME      FIFRIM$         YP
)@@G@@  . RETURN FREE IMAGE   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , DL A1,P(1,1),P(1,YQ
)@@G@@2)      . GET FILE NAME @E@@@@ DO P(2)>0 , L  A0,P(2,1),P(2,2),P(2,3) . YR
)@@G@@GET FREE CODE     @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,P(0,0)        . CALL SELYS
)@@G@@ECTED ROUTINE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          END                       YT
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. GENERATE FIASG$ PACKET.  THE CALLS ARE: @[@@@@YU
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.         FIPFIL    'Q','QUAL' 'F','FILE' ....  @[@@@@.     YV
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THE FIRST SUBFIELD OF EACH FIELD IS A CODE LETTER, IN QUOTES :  YW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         'Q' - QUALIFIER     @^@@@@.         'F' - FIYX
)@@G@@LENAME@^@@@@.         'R' - READKEY @^@@@@.         'W' - WRITEKEY@ @@@@YY
)@@G@@.         'C' - FILECYCLE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF THE PROCEDURE FIPELYZ
)@@G@@T IS CALLED THE FULL 14 WORD ELT$ PACKET  @F@@@@. IS GENERATED AND THE FZA
)@@G@@OLLOWING ADDITION FIELDS ARE ALLOWED.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         'EZB
)@@G@@' - ELEMENT NAME  @ @@@@.         'V' - VERSION NAME  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ZC
)@@G@@. THE SECOND SUBFIELD OF EACH FIELD IS A STRING OF NOT MORE THAN  @F@@@@ZD
)@@G@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENDING ON THE NORMAL LENGTH OF THAT FIELD)  @ @@@@ZE
)@@G@@. ENCLOSED IN QUOTATION MARKS.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P         PROC      *8  ZF
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@FIPFIL*   NAME      0                 . ONLY FILZG
)@@G@@E PORTION   @G@@@@FIPELT*   NAME      1                 . BOTH FILE AND ZH
)@@G@@ELEMENT PORTIONS  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@B(1)      EQU       0D              ZI
)@@G@@  . PRESENCE BITS (2 WORDS)   @D@@@@Q(1)      EQU       0D              ZJ
)@@G@@  . QUALIFIER (2) @D@@@@F(1)      EQU       0D                . FILENAMEZK
)@@G@@ (2)  @D@@@@R(1)      EQU       0                 . READKEY (1)   @D@@@@ZL
)@@G@@W(1)      EQU       0                 . WRITEKEY (1)  @D@@@@C(1)      EQZM
)@@G@@U       0                 . CYCLE (1)     @E@@@@E(1)      EQU       0D  ZN
)@@G@@              . ELEMENT NAME (2)    @E@@@@V(1)      EQU       0D        ZO
)@@G@@        . VERSION NAME(2)     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@I DO P-1 , FISCAN   .   ZP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@          +         B(1)              .   @B@@@@      ZQ
)@@G@@    +         Q(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         F(1)      ZR
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         C(1)              .   @B@@@@      ZS
)@@G@@    +         R(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         W(1)      ZT
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          ON        P(0,0)            .   @B@@@@      ZU
)@@G@@    +         E(1)              .   @B@@@@          +         V(1)      ZV
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          +         0                 .   @B@@@@      ZW
)@@G@@    OFF       P(0,0)            .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          END     ZX
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. PROCEDURE TO PROCESS EACH FIELD.  @[@@@@.     ZY
)@@G@@@F@@@@FISCAN*   PROC      *0,0              . SECOND GLOBAL PASS ONLY   ZZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='Q' ,Q*(1) FIW2 66 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='AA
)@@G@@F' ,F*(1) FIW2 60 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='C' ,C*(1) FIW1 54 .     @A@@@@AB
)@@G@@ DO P(I,1)='R' ,R*(1) FIW1 48 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='W' ,W*(1) FIW1 42 AC
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@          ON        P(0,0)            .   @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='AD
)@@G@@E' ,E*(1) FIW2 30 .     @A@@@@ DO P(I,1)='V' ,V*(1) FIW2 24 .     @B@@@@AE
)@@G@@          OFF       P(0,0)            .   @B@@@@ DO FOUND(1)=0 , +09    AF
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@AG
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@. PROCEDURE TO LEFT JUSTIFY AND STORE THE COMPONENT.  @[@@@@AH
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@Z         PROC      *1,0              .   @B@@@@FIW2*     NAAI
)@@G@@ME                        .   @B@@@@P**(I,2)  EQU       P(I,2)++0D      AJ
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@ DO 12 , DO (P(I,2)*/-66)**077=0 ,P**(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 AK
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@FIW1*     NAME                        .   @F@@@@ DO 06 , DO AL
)@@G@@(P(I,2)*/-30)**077=0 ,P**(I,2) EQU P(I,2)*/6+05 .     @B@@@@*         EQAM
)@@G@@U       P(I,2)            .   @B@@@@B**(1)    EQU       B(1)++1D*/Z(1,1)AN
)@@G@@   .  @B@@@@FOUND*(1) EQU       1                 .   @^@@@@          ENAO
)@@G@@D       .   _@@@@@@F@@@@. 6 OR 12 LETTERS (DEPENDING ON THE NORMAL LENGTAP
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@          DEF     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE: FUNCTIONS AQ
)@@G@@WHOSE NAMES ARE THE SAME AS VARIABLE NAMES *MUST*     @D@@@@. BE DEFINEDAR
)@@G@@ PRIOR TO THE EQU'S FOR THE VARIABLES     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@AS
)@@G@@. ------ FUNCTION TO CONSTUCT IMMEDIATE VALUES  @G@@@@.        NOTE: FULAT
)@@G@@LWORD NEGATIVE VALUES WILL AUTOMATICALLY GET SIGN     @G@@@@.           AU
)@@G@@   EXTENSION, BUT HALFWDS WHOSE LEFTMOST BIT HAPPENS TO BE  @G@@@@.     AV
)@@G@@         ON WILL NOT. HENCETHERE IS NO NEED FOR AN XU(...) FUNC.  @[@@@@AW
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@F         FUNC    @^@@@@U*        NAME      016 @^@@@@XU*   AX
)@@G@@    NAME      017 @E@@@@ DO F=3 , GO G$$FMU                   . TEST FORAY
)@@G@@ FLAGGED    @D@@@@MASM      EQU       0=0=0             . ON IF MASM    AZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ON        MASM=0            . BEGIN ASM STUFF     @F@@@@BA
)@@G@@ DO 1-(&(F(1))=-2) , GO G$$FMU        . TEST FOR F(1) RELOCATABLE @E@@@@BB
)@@G@@ DO 1= +(I$ 0,1++F(1)**1,0,0,0,0) , GO G$$FMU . OR HAS FORM @E@@@@      BC
)@@G@@    OFF                         . END OF ASM STUFF    @E@@@@          ONBD
)@@G@@        MASM              . BEGIN MASM STUFF    @H@@@@ DO F=1 , END +F(0BE
)@@G@@)                   . IF NO ARGS ('U') THEN OUTPUT VALUE    @G@@@@ DO $BBF
)@@G@@A(F(1))>0 , GO G$$FMU           . IF NOT 0, THEN FORM OR RELOC    @D@@@@BG
)@@G@@          OFF                         . END OF MASM   @F@@@@. AT THIS POBH
)@@G@@INT, F(1) IS A LEGITIMATE FORMLESS CONSTANT VALUE     @G@@@@ DO (F(1)>07BI
)@@G@@77777)++(F(1)<-131071) , END (+F(1)) . TOO BIG? GEN LITERAL.@A@@@@IBIT  BJ
)@@G@@    EQU     0<(F(1)**0200000) @A@@@@HBIT      EQU     0<(F(1)**0400000) BK
)@@G@@@G@@@@J         EQU       017-(F(0)=016)*(F(1)>-0) . IF NOT 'XU', GEN EIBL
)@@G@@THER  @E@@@@ DO 1 ,   END     +(I$ 0,J,0,0,2*HBIT+IBIT,F(1)**0177777)   BM
)@@G@@@F@@@@. COME HERE IF ARG F(1) IS RELOCATABLE, TAGGED, OR HAS FORM...    BN
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$FMU*   NAME    @E@@@@          END       +(I$ 0,F(0),0,F(2),2*FBO
)@@G@@(*2)+F(*1),F(1))  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. HARDWARE MODE INDEPENDENT FUNCS TOBP
)@@G@@ SIGNIFY EXTRACTION OF A PARTIAL WORD     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@F         FUBQ
)@@G@@NC    @C@@@@W*        NAME      0                 . FULLWORD@^@@@@H1*   BR
)@@G@@    NAME      2   @^@@@@H2*       NAME      1   @^@@@@XH2*      NAME    BS
)@@G@@  3   @^@@@@S1*       NAME      015 @^@@@@S2*       NAME      014 @^@@@@BT
)@@G@@S3*       NAME      013 @^@@@@S4*       NAME      012 @^@@@@S5*       NABU
)@@G@@ME      011 @^@@@@S6*       NAME      010 @F@@@@ DO (0=0=0)**(F=1) , ENDBV
)@@G@@ +(F(0))      . NO ARGS +> OUTPUT VALUE   @E@@@@          END       +(I$BW
)@@G@@ 0,F(0),,F(2),2*F(*2)+F(*1),F(1))   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. HARDWARE MODE DEBX
)@@G@@PENDENT PARTIAL WORD EXTRACTION FUNCS     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$PWMD(1) EQBY
)@@G@@U       -1                . SET PARTIAL WORD MODE UNDEFINED @[@@@@.     BZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@F         FUNC                        . THIRD WORD DEPENDENT PARTICA
)@@G@@AL WDS@^@@@@XH1*      NAME      4   @^@@@@T1*       NAME      7   @^@@@@CB
)@@G@@T2*       NAME      6   @^@@@@T3*       NAME      5   @G@@@@          ONCC
)@@G@@        0                 . TURN OFF PSR CHECK (FOR NOW)    @G@@@@ DO G$CD
)@@G@@PWMD(1)=1                       ; IF PARTWD MODE SET TO QUARTER   @E@@@@CE
)@@G@@   , END +(I$ 077,020,020,020,4,010000000) . FORCE A T-FLAG @F@@@@G$PWMDCF
)@@G@@*(1) EQU      0                 . ELSE DEFINE THIRDWD MODE  @B@@@@      CG
)@@G@@    OFF                         .   @F@@@@ DO (0=0=0)**(F=1) , END +(F(0CH
)@@G@@))      . NO ARGS +> OUTPUT VALUE   @E@@@@          END       +(I$ 0,F(0CI
)@@G@@),,F(2),2*F(*2)+F(*1),F(1))   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@F         FUNC          CJ
)@@G@@              . QUARTER WD DEPENDENT PARTIAL WDS@^@@@@Q2*       NAME    CK
)@@G@@  4   @^@@@@Q1*       NAME      7   @^@@@@Q3*       NAME      6   @^@@@@CL
)@@G@@Q4*       NAME      5   @G@@@@          ON        0                 . TUCM
)@@G@@RN OFF PSR CHECK (FOR NOW)    @G@@@@ DO G$PWMD(1)=0                     CN
)@@G@@  ; IF PARTWD MODE SET TO THIRD     @E@@@@   , END +(I$ 077,020,020,020,CO
)@@G@@4,010000000) . FORCE A T-FLAG @F@@@@G$PWMD*(1) EQU      1               CP
)@@G@@  . ELSE DEFINE QUARTERWD MODE@B@@@@          OFF                       CQ
)@@G@@  .   @F@@@@ DO (0=0=0)**(F=1) , END +(F(0))      . NO ARGS +> OUTPUT VACR
)@@G@@LUE   @E@@@@          END       +(I$ 0,F(0),,F(2),2*F(*2)+F(*1),F(1))   CS
)@@G@@@F@@@@/. DEFINITIONS WHICH REPLACE THE NEED FOR AXR$. BY DOING THIS, WE CT
)@@G@@@F@@@@. PREVENT ERRORS IN DEFINITION WHICH MIGHT OCCUR IF THE PROGRAMMERCU
)@@G@@@F@@@@. PUT HIS OWN AXR$ IN AND IT ACCIDENTALLY PRECEDED THE FUNCTION   CV
)@@G@@@B@@@@. DEFINITIONS CONTAINED IN THIS ELEMENT.  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@X1    CW
)@@G@@    EQU       1   @^@@@@X2        EQU       2   @^@@@@X3        EQU     CX
)@@G@@  3   @^@@@@X4        EQU       4   @^@@@@X5        EQU       5   @^@@@@CY
)@@G@@X6        EQU       6   @^@@@@X7        EQU       7   @^@@@@X8        EQCZ
)@@G@@U       010 @^@@@@X9        EQU       011 @^@@@@X10       EQU       012 DA
)@@G@@@^@@@@X11       EQU       013 @^@@@@A0        EQU       014 @^@@@@A1    DB
)@@G@@    EQU       015 @^@@@@A2        EQU       016 @^@@@@A3        EQU     DC
)@@G@@  017 @^@@@@A4        EQU       020 @^@@@@A5        EQU       021 @^@@@@DD
)@@G@@A6        EQU       022 @^@@@@A7        EQU       023 @^@@@@A8        EQDE
)@@G@@U       024 @^@@@@A9        EQU       025 @^@@@@A10       EQU       026 DF
)@@G@@@^@@@@A11       EQU       027 @^@@@@A12       EQU       030 @^@@@@A13   DG
)@@G@@    EQU       031 @^@@@@A14       EQU       032 @^@@@@A15       EQU     DH
)@@G@@  033 @^@@@@R1        EQU       0101@^@@@@R2        EQU       0102@^@@@@DI
)@@G@@R3        EQU       0103@^@@@@R4        EQU       0104@^@@@@R5        EQDJ
)@@G@@U       0105@^@@@@R6        EQU       0106@^@@@@R7        EQU       0107DK
)@@G@@@^@@@@R8        EQU       0110@^@@@@R9        EQU       0111@^@@@@R10   DL
)@@G@@    EQU       0112@^@@@@R11       EQU       0113@^@@@@R12       EQU     DM
)@@G@@  0114@^@@@@R13       EQU       0115@^@@@@R14       EQU       0116@^@@@@DN
)@@G@@R15       EQU       0117@^@@@@SR1       EQU       R3  @^@@@@SR2       EQDO
)@@G@@U       R4  @^@@@@SR3       EQU       R5  @^@@@@J0        EQU       R6  DP
)@@G@@@^@@@@J1        EQU       R7  @^@@@@J2        EQU       R8  @^@@@@J3    DQ
)@@G@@    EQU       R9  @A@@@@. PARTIAL WORD DESIGNATORS FOLLOW   @[@@@@.     DR
)@@G@@@G@@@@. WELL, THEY USED TO, BUT HAVE BEEN REMOVED FOR REASONS GIVEN ABOVDS
)@@G@@E.    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P         PROC    *0    @#@@@@SAXR$*DT
)@@G@@    NAME    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. IF NOT @MASM, DEFINE THE PARTIALWORD DESDU
)@@G@@IGS HERE. IF @MASM, THE @B@@@@. VALUES ARE DEFINED BY THE FUNCTIONS.    DV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@          ON        0=0=1             . 1 IF @ASM, 0 IDW
)@@G@@F @MASM     @^@@@@W*        EQU       0   @^@@@@H2*       EQU       1   DX
)@@G@@@^@@@@H1*       EQU       2   @^@@@@XH2*      EQU       3   @^@@@@XH1*  DY
)@@G@@    EQU       4   @^@@@@T3*       EQU       5   @^@@@@T2*       EQU     DZ
)@@G@@  6   @^@@@@T1*       EQU       7   @^@@@@S6*       EQU       010 @^@@@@EA
)@@G@@S5*       EQU       011 @^@@@@S4*       EQU       012 @^@@@@S3*       EQEB
)@@G@@U       013 @^@@@@S2*       EQU       014 @^@@@@S1*       EQU       015 EC
)@@G@@@^@@@@U*        EQU       016 @^@@@@XU*       EQU       017 @^@@@@Q2*   ED
)@@G@@    EQU       4   @^@@@@Q4*       EQU       5   @^@@@@Q3*       EQU     EE
)@@G@@  6   @^@@@@Q1*       EQU       7   @B@@@@          OFF                 EF
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          END     _@@@@@D IT ACCIDENTALLY EG
)@@G@@PRECEDED THE FUNCTION   @B@@@@. DEFINITIONS CONT*[S@@@*SDFF*@C@@@@. AVAIEH
)@@G@@LABLE PREFIXES ARE G$ J$ M$ Q$ V$ W$ Z$   @H@@@@        DEF . IF @MASM-OEI
)@@G@@MN, REPLACE THIS LINE WITH: $DEF,$LEVEL, AND G$OMN=1  @G@@@@G$OMN     EQEJ
)@@G@@U       0                 . 0 IF PDP, 1 IF MASM OMNIBUS     @E@@@@. ** WEK
)@@G@@HEN GENERATING AN @MASM OMNIBUS, PERUSE, AND THEN     @D@@@@. ** OBEY THEL
)@@G@@E INSTRUCTIONS IN TCF-TO-MAKE/OMNIBUS.    @F@@@@STRUC$OMN* PROC     *0  EM
)@@G@@              . IF @MASM, DEFINE G$OMN    @F@@@@ DO G$OMN=0 , $INCLUDE 'EN
)@@G@@STRUC$'       . IF READING PDP, GET OMN.  @E@@@@          END           EO
)@@G@@              . END OF STRUC$OMN    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@          DEF     EP
)@@G@@                    . FOR @ASM, BEGIN DEF FOR STRUC$DEF     @H@@@@G$UOM EQ
)@@G@@    EQU       1                 . IF 1, THIS IS UOM ASM OR MASM, SO     ER
)@@G@@@I@@@@                                      .    ASSUME EXISTENCE OF BRIES
)@@G@@EF AND RESUME     @G@@@@                                      . IF 0, FAET
)@@G@@KE IT WITH DUMMY PROCS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. KEYWORDS WHICH DETERMINE STREU
)@@G@@UCTURE OF THE HEADER LINE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. NOTE THAT THESE KEYWOREV
)@@G@@DS ARE NEGATIVE TO AVOID CONFUSION  @F@@@@. WITH USER SUPPLIED REGISTER EW
)@@G@@AND J-DESIGNATOR SPECIFICATIONS     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@IN      EQU    - 1EX
)@@G@@@#@@@@IS      EQU    - 2@#@@@@THEN    EQU    - 3@#@@@@AND     EQU    - 4EY
)@@G@@@#@@@@OR      EQU    - 5@#@@@@WHILE   EQU    - 6@#@@@@UNTIL   EQU    - 7EZ
)@@G@@@H@@@@. NOTE: KEYWORDS VARY THRU LOOKFOR MUST BE IN ORDER, RANGE TESTS AFA
)@@G@@RE USED     @#@@@@VARY    EQU    - 8@#@@@@JGD     EQU    - 9@^@@@@TLEM  FB
)@@G@@  EQU    - 10     @^@@@@JMGI    EQU    - 11     @^@@@@LOOKFOR EQU    - 1FC
)@@G@@2     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@TO      EQU    - 13     @^@@@@BY      EQU    - 1FD
)@@G@@4     @^@@@@FOR     EQU    - 15     @^@@@@UP      EQU    - 16     @^@@@@FE
)@@G@@DOWN    EQU    - 17     @^@@@@WHEN    EQU    - 18     @^@@@@FROM    EQU FF
)@@G@@   - 19     @^@@@@MASKED  EQU    - 20     @^@@@@SUBROUTINE EQU - 21     FG
)@@G@@@^@@@@MAINPROGRAM EQU - 22    @^@@@@CONTINGENCY EQU - 23    @^@@@@CYCLICFH
)@@G@@    EQU       -24 @^@@@@POINTER EQU    - 25     @^@@@@SIGNAL  EQU    - 2FI
)@@G@@6     @^@@@@STACK   EQU    - 27     @^@@@@SAVE    EQU    - 28     @^@@@@FJ
)@@G@@OFFSET  EQU    - 29     @^@@@@CHANNEL EQU    - 30     @^@@@@STARTIO EQU FK
)@@G@@   - 31     @^@@@@NOT       EQU       -32 @^@@@@NOSAVE    EQU       -33 FL
)@@G@@@^@@@@EXECSUB   EQU       -34 @^@@@@CALLING EQU         -35 @^@@@@BASINGFM
)@@G@@     EQU      -36 @^@@@@IBANK      EQU      -37 @^@@@@DBANK      EQU    FN
)@@G@@  -38 @^@@@@LIJSUB     EQU      -39 @^@@@@LDJSUB     EQU      -40 @^@@@@FO
)@@G@@REMOTESUB  EQU      -41 @^@@@@VIA        EQU      -42 @^@@@@NOFINDEXIT EFP
)@@G@@QU      -43 @^@@@@NOCHECKING EQU      -44 @C@@@@/. TABLES FOR GENERATIONFQ
)@@G@@ OF TYPE 1 TESTS, FORM: @C@@@@.                 <AREG>,<KEYWORD>,<U-SPECFR
)@@G@@>     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@. KEYWORDS-----   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@EQ      EQU FS
)@@G@@   1  @D@@@@NE      EQU    2                      . PREFERRED     @F@@@@FT
)@@G@@NEQ     EQU    NE                     . ALTERNATE (MAY BE REMOVED)@#@@@@FU
)@@G@@LT      EQU    3  @G@@@@LTE     EQU     LT                    . MNEMONICFV
)@@G@@ FOR DON'T CARE EQUALS  @E@@@@GE      EQU    4                      . PRFW
)@@G@@EFERRED KEYWORD   @F@@@@GEQ     EQU    GE                     . SUPERCEDFX
)@@G@@ED BY THE ABOVE   @G@@@@GTE     EQU     GE                    . DON'T CAFY
)@@G@@RE (ABOUT EQUALITY) MNEM@#@@@@GT      EQU    5  @E@@@@LE        EQU     FZ
)@@G@@  6                 . THIS IS PREFERRED   @F@@@@LEQ       EQU       LE  GA
)@@G@@              . THIS HAS BEEN SUPERCEDED  @#@@@@SPANS   EQU    7  @#@@@@GB
)@@G@@NOSPAN  EQU    8  @#@@@@EVENP   EQU    9  @#@@@@ODDP    EQU    10 @#@@@@GC
)@@G@@DEQ     EQU    11 @D@@@@DNE     EQU    12                     . PREFERREGD
)@@G@@D     @F@@@@DNEQ    EQU    DNE                    . ALTERNATE (MAY BE REGE
)@@G@@MOVED)@I@@@@AGE     EQU    13                     . PREFERRED: SPECIAL FGF
)@@G@@OR MASKED ALFA SEARC    @#@@@@AGEQ    EQU    AGE@#@@@@ALT     EQU    14 GG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. WAITING STATUS=2 INDICATES  CONDITION AFTER TEST IS GH
)@@G@@ FALSE,TRUE @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$WS(1,EQ)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,NE)  GI
)@@G@@      EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,GT)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,LE)        EQU  3GJ
)@@G@@@^@@@@G$WS(1,LT)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1,GE)        EQU  2@^@@@@G$WS(1GK

)@@G@@OF TOTAL NO BLOX (ALL KINDS EXCEPT BEGIN) @A@@@@.       2 = GLOBAL ADDREML
)@@G@@SS FLOAT    @A@@@@.       3 = ARG PUSHDOWN COUNTER    @C@@@@.       4 = MM

)@@G@@@D@@@@.       7 = LOGICAL FOR GLOBAL PASS: TRUE ON PASS 2   @[@@@@.     MP
)@@G@@@D@@@@K DO     5 ,G$CTR*(K) EQU 0           . CLEAR COUNTERS@[@@@@.     MQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@. NOW DEFINE SPECIAL THINGS DEPENDENT UPON WHICH ASSEMBLER PASS THMR
)@@G@@IS IS @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*(6) EQU 1-G$CTR(6)            . SET FLAG: MS

)@@G@@GNOSTICS *****    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. FIELDS IN ERROR MESSAGNK
)@@G@@E FORM ARE: @C@@@@.    FIELD 1: TYPE OF CURRENTLY ACTIVE BLOCK    @E@@@@NL
)@@G@@.             TYPES ARE 1=>BEGIN, 2=>IF, 3=>CASE, 4=>REPEAT @A@@@@.     NM
)@@G@@     2: CURRENT NESTING DEPTH @F@@@@.          3: MESSAGE CLASS (0=LOCN NN
)@@G@@CTR, 1=SYNTAX, 2=STRUCTURE)   @^@@@@.          4: ERROR TYPE@ @@@@.     NO
)@@G@@     5: ERROR SUBTYPE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. LOCATION COUNTER ERRORS (MESNP
)@@G@@SAGE CLASS=0) ARE SIGNALLED WHEN    @E@@@@. SOME CODE PREVIOUS TO THE PONQ
)@@G@@INT OF THE MESSAGE GENERATES  @F@@@@. A DIFFERENT NUMBER OF INSTRUCTIONSNR
)@@G@@ ON ASSEMBLER PASSES ONE AND  @F@@@@. TWO (ASSEMBLER D-FLAG). AT THE POINS
)@@G@@NT OF DETECTION, STRUC$ WILL  @F@@@@. ATTEMPT TO FORESTALL SPURIOUS ERRONT
)@@G@@RS OF THIS TYPE IN THE CODE   @G@@@@. WHICH FOLLOWS BY FORCING THE LOCATNU
)@@G@@ION COUNTER TO WHAT IT BELIEVES     @F@@@@. THE CORRECT VALUE SHOULD BE.NV
)@@G@@ THE ERROR TYPE AND SUBTYPE FIELDS  @F@@@@. ARE INTERNAL SERIAL NUMBERS,NW
)@@G@@ AND HAVE NO SPECIAL SIGNIFICANCE.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR SYNTAX ERRORNX
)@@G@@S (MESSAGE CLASS=1), ERROR TYPES AND SUBTYPES ARE:    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@NY
)@@G@@.    1,X => ERROR IN SPECIFICATION OF TEST@C@@@@.     ,01      UNRECOGNINZ
)@@G@@ZEABLE TYPE OF TEST     @B@@@@.     ,02      UNRECOGNIZEABLE KEYWORD    OA
)@@G@@@B@@@@.    2,X => ERROR IN <VARY> SPECIFICATION @C@@@@.     ,01      OFFOB
)@@G@@SET REQUIRES IMMEDIATE 'BY'   @E@@@@.     ,02      LOOKFOR FORMAT REQUIROC
)@@G@@ES 'BY' SPECIFICATION   @D@@@@.     ,03      REQUIRED FROM, TO, OR BY SPOD
)@@G@@EC MISSING  @E@@@@.     ,04      LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE PASSES THROUGH ZEOE
)@@G@@RO    @E@@@@.     ,05      SIGN OF BY CONFLICTS WITH SIGN OF TO-FROM    OF
)@@G@@@F@@@@.     ,06      EXPLICIT SENSE (UP/DOWN) CONFLICTS WITH BY, TO-FROMOG
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     ,07      REQUIRED 'BY' SPECIFICATION NOT GIVEN  @C@@@@.     OH
)@@G@@,010     BAD KEYWORD FOLLOWING 'LOOKFOR'  @G@@@@.     ,011     SPECIFIC OI
)@@G@@LOOP INSTR CONFLICTS WITH TO/FROM/BY/FOR SPEC   @ @@@@.    3,X => PARAMEOJ
)@@G@@TER ERROR   @D@@@@.     ,01      CASEREGISTER NOT OVERLAPPED (A0-A3)    OK
)@@G@@@D@@@@.     ,02      REQUIRED REGISTER SPECIFICATION MISSING@D@@@@.     OL
)@@G@@,03      INCORRECT NUMBER OF FIELDS ON 'IF'     @D@@@@.     ,04      MISOM
)@@G@@SING 'WHEN' ON ESCAPE STATEMENT     @F@@@@.     ,05      MINIMUM SPECIFION
)@@G@@ED CASE NOT ZERO (CALLING OPTION)   @F@@@@.     ,06      ALL CASE VALUESOO
)@@G@@ NOT SPECIFIED (CALLING OPTION)     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FOR STRUCTURE EROP
)@@G@@RORS (MESSAGE CLASS=2) , TYPES AND SUBTYPES ARE:@[@@@@.     @ @@@@.    1OQ
)@@G@@,X => NESTING ERROR     @F@@@@.     ,01      TOO MANY OR TOO FEW END STAOR
)@@G@@TMENTS IN PREVIOUS BLOCK@F@@@@.     ,02      MISSING END IN PREVIOUS BLOOS
)@@G@@CK MAY CAUSE D-FLAGS    @E@@@@.     ,03      STATEMENT CANNOT APPEAR IN OT
)@@G@@CURRENT BLOCK TYPE@F@@@@.              EITHER THE END STATEMENT FOR THE OU
)@@G@@PREVIOUS BLOCK OR @G@@@@.              THE START STATEMENT FOR THE CURREOV
)@@G@@NT BLOCK IS MISSING     @D@@@@.    2,X => INCONSISTENT LOGIC (STATEMENTSOW
)@@G@@ OR FIELDS) @G@@@@.     ,01      ESCAPE INVALID IF BOTH WHILE/LOOKFOR ANOX
)@@G@@D UNTIL ARE GIVEN @E@@@@.     ,02      OTHERWISE STMNT MEANINGLESS, NO EOY
)@@G@@SCAPE GIVEN @F@@@@.     ,03      ATEND UNREACHABLE, NO TESTS APPEARED ONOZ
)@@G@@ REPEAT     @F@@@@.     ,05      NOFIND CODE ILLEGAL WITH CALLING OPTIONPA
)@@G@@ (CASE)     @C@@@@.     ,06      REMOTE CALL TO NON-REMOTE BLOCK  @ @@@@PB
)@@G@@.    3,X => MISCELLANEOUS     @E@@@@.     ,01      ATTEMPT TO CHANGE LOCPC
)@@G@@ATION COUNTERS WITHIN   @F@@@@.              A BLOCK. BLOCKS MUST BE WHOPD
)@@G@@LLY CONTAINED WITHIN    @F@@@@.              A SINGLE BANK. SWITCHING BEPE
)@@G@@TWEEN BANKS MUST BE     @D@@@@.              ACCOMPLISHED VIA A SUBROUTIPF
)@@G@@NE CALL     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@          DEF     @H@@@@G$ERFO    FORM    PG
)@@G@@  3,6,3,12,12     . A DISTINCTIVE FORM FOR ERROR MESSAGES   @#@@@@P     PH
)@@G@@  PROC   *2 @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$GFL*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PI
)@@G@@. FORCE DEFINITION OF PROC NEEDED TO FORCE G-FLAGS    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@PJ
)@@G@@          PROC    @#@@@@G$$FRG**  NAME    @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @#@@@@      PK
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. NOW G-FLAG GENERATOR ACTUALLY DOES ITS TPL
)@@G@@HING  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ GO G$$FRG          . LEAP TO OTHER PROC, WHICH PM
)@@G@@LEAPS TO G$$DIA   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$IFL*  NAME       3   PN
)@@G@@              . THIS ENTRY FOR TRULY INVALID INSTRUCTION    @H@@@@      PO
)@@G@@    RES       1                 . WHICH ACTUALLY TAKES SPACE IN THE CODEPP
)@@G@@@C@@@@ GO G$$DIA          . GO DISPLAY THE MESSAGE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PQ
)@@G@@G$$EFL*  NAME       1                 . GENERATE AN E-FLAG  @#@@@@A     PR
)@@G@@  EQU    +) @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$$DFL*  NAME       0   PS
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$DFLG****                      . GENERATE A GLOBAL D-FLAG  @B@@@@PT
)@@G@@G$DFLG****          EQU               0 . @G@@@@ DO P(1)>0 , RES P(1,1)-PU
)@@G@@$             . THEN FORCE LC BACK INTO PHASE   @]@@@@ GO G$$DIA  @[@@@@PV
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@G$$TFL*  NAME       4                 . GENERATE A T-FLAG   PW
)@@G@@@A@@@@A       EQU    + (I$ 0,0,0,0,077,0) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. NOW WE GENPX
)@@G@@ERATE THE MESSAGES. TO AVOID EXTRANEOUS D-FLAGS ON    @E@@@@. THE USER'SPY
)@@G@@ LISTING, NEGATIVE RES'S ARE USED TO INSURE THAT@F@@@@. THE MESSAGES DO PZ
)@@G@@NOT OCCUPY ANY SPACE IN THE PROGRAM'S ADDRESS   @F@@@@. SPACE. TO INSUREQA
)@@G@@ THAT THE MESSAGE DOES NOT GO UNNOTICED, WE     @G@@@@. TRASH ON THE LASQB
)@@G@@T WORD OF GENERATED USER CODE, MAKING IT AN IOPR.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@QC
)@@G@@. TO AVOID SURPRESSION IF BRIEF MODE IS ON, THE DIAGNOSTIC  @D@@@@. MESSQD
)@@G@@AGE SENTINAL WORD IS THE 1ST ONE GENERATED.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$DIAQE
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . DIAGNOSTIC PRINTOUT STARTS HERE @H@@@@QF
)@@G@@          RES       -1                . GET RID OF USER'S LAST INSTRUCTIQG
)@@G@@ON    @F@@@@K         EQU       1+(P(0,0)=0)      . SPEC TO FIND FLAGS IQH
)@@G@@N     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . CURRENT NESTING LEVEQI
)@@G@@L     @D@@@@          G$ERFO    G$TYPE(M),M,P(0,0),P(K,1),P(K,2)  @#@@@@QJ
)@@G@@          UNLIST  @F@@@@          G$$IFLAG                    . MARK THIQK
)@@G@@S ELEMENT IN ERROR@G@@@@          RES       -2                . PURGE SEQL
)@@G@@NTINAL AND IFLAG WORD   @H@@@@          +0                          . FOQM
)@@G@@RCE PROG TO IOPR IF ITS EXECUTED    @#@@@@          LIST    @E@@@@      QN
)@@G@@    END                         . OF DIAGNOSTIC PROCS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@QO
)@@G@@. THIS PROC DISPLAYS DEBUGGING INFORMATION WITHOUT AFFECTING@F@@@@. THE QP
)@@G@@GENERATED CODE. IT IS USED FOR DEBUGGING STRUC$ ITSELF.     @[@@@@.     QQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@P          PROC     *999,0    @#@@@@G$DBUG*    NAME   @B@@@@I(1)  QR
)@@G@@     EQU      I(1)+1            .   @^@@@@ DO P(I(1))=0 , END     @ @@@@QS
)@@G@@ DO P(I(1))=1 , +P(I(1),1)    @A@@@@ DO P(I(1))=2 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2)QT
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO P(I(1))=3 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3)  @E@@@@ DO P(I(1))=QU
)@@G@@4 , +P(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3),P(I(1),4)    @H@@@@ DO P(I(1))>4 , +PQV
)@@G@@(I(1),1),P(I(1),2),P(I(1),3),P(I(1),4),P(I(1),5),P(I(1),6)  @^@@@@      QW
)@@G@@     RES      -1  @B@@@@ DO I(1)<P , GO G$DBUG                  . @#@@@@QX
)@@G@@           END    @C@@@@/.    ******** PROGRAM DEFINITION GROUP ********QY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ARRAY USAGE BY BEGIN BLOCKS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    GQZ
)@@G@@$LABL(K,1) ENTRY POINT TO BLOCK (=PKT ADDR IF CONTINGENCY)  @B@@@@.     RA
)@@G@@        2) EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK    @E@@@@.             3) ADDR OF GENERRB
)@@G@@ATED REG SAVE AREA (IF ANY)   @E@@@@.             4) ADDR OF SIGNAL CELLRC
)@@G@@ OR RETURN TARGET ADDR  @G@@@@.             5) ADDR OF BLOK EXIT INSTR (RD
)@@G@@AFTER REG RESTORE INSTRS)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    G$FLAG(K,1) XREG USRE
)@@G@@ED FOR SIGNALLING, ZERO IF NONE     @B@@@@.             2) NUMBER OF SAVRF
)@@G@@ED REGISTERS@C@@@@.             2,N) AXR$ VALUE OF N'TH SAVED REG @C@@@@RG
)@@G@@.             3) BLOCK TYPE (MAINPROG, ETC.)    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    GRH
)@@G@@$BSEQ(<X>) BLOK SEQ NO (I.E., K) WHERE <X> IS START ADDR    @[@@@@.     RI
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           RJ
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *           BERK
)@@G@@GIN             * @C@@@@.               *                             * RL
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@RM
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@           DEF    @H@@@@F          FUNC         RN
)@@G@@              . ----- UTILITY FUNC USED IN SORTING    @#@@@@G$$INC*    NRO
)@@G@@AME   @D@@@@III*(1)    EQU              III(1)+1  . BUMP COUNTER  @E@@@@RP
)@@G@@           END              III(1)    . RETURN NEW VALUE    @[@@@@.     RQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *3 @]@@@@BEGIN*  NAME@G@@@@ DO (G$CTR(5RR
)@@G@@)=0)=0 , G$$GFL 1,1             . REQUIRE NESTING DEPTH ZERO@F@@@@M     RS
)@@G@@    EQU       1                 . FORCE NEW NESTING DEPTH   @D@@@@G$CTR*RT
)@@G@@(5) EQU  M                      . THEN SAVE IT  @F@@@@ DO (G$CTR(2)=0)=0RU
)@@G@@ , G$$GFL 1,2             . REQUIRE NO FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@K     RV
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SERIAL NUMBER   @D@@@@G$CTR*RW
)@@G@@(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @D@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU    RX
)@@G@@  1                 . SET BLOCK TYPE@E@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K         RY
)@@G@@        . SAVE SERIAL NUMBER  @F@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,G$BSEQ*($) EQU      K RZ
)@@G@@  . SERIAL # INDEXED BY STARTA@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,G$BSEQ*($AP($)) EQU K SA
)@@G@@  . SERIAL # INDEXED BY STARTADR    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@T         EQU  P(1SB
)@@G@@,1)+(P(1)=0)*MAINPROGRAM . GET PROG TYPE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU T      SC
)@@G@@               . AND REMEMBER IT    @E@@@@ISSUB      EQU      (T=SUBROUTSD
)@@G@@INE)++(T=LIJSUB)++(T=LDJSUB)  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. ALLOW 'NOSAVE' TO DEFASE
)@@G@@ULT TO SUBFIELD 2 @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NOSDEF    EQU       ISSUB**(P(1)=2)*SF
)@@G@@*(P(1,2)=NOSAVE) . NOSAVE DEFAULT   @E@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE SG
)@@G@@        . FORCE THIRD FIELD   @D@@@@ DO NOSDEF ,P(1,2) EQU 0            SH
)@@G@@  . CLEAR REGISTER@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO NOSDEF ,P(1)   EQU 3 . NOW NOTSI
)@@G@@E THERE ARE 3 SUBFIELDS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,1)SJ
)@@G@@=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $           . SASK
)@@G@@VE ENTRY POINT TO BLOK  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       G$CTR(6)  SL
)@@G@@        . ALLOW ZERO AS A FLAG@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0-G$CTR(7)      SM
)@@G@@  . SET GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO T=CYCLIC , END            SN
)@@G@@     . SINCE CYCLICS NEVER EXIT, WE'RE DONE     @G@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY SO
)@@G@@, +0D               . IF CONTING, GENERATE PACKET     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SP
)@@G@@.              HANDLE EXITS WHICH SIGNAL THE EXEC (MAIN/CONTINGENCY)    SQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@GI      EQU    (P(1,1)=SIGNAL)+2*(P(2,1)=SIGNAL)+3*(P(SR
)@@G@@3,1)=SIGNAL)@F@@@@. SIGNAL XREG IS FLAG, IF NONE (<0), THEN EXIT WILL BESS
)@@G@@ 'NORMAL'   @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU (GI>0)*(P(1,2)+(P(1)<2)*A0)-(GI=0) . ST
)@@G@@SET SIGNAL XREG   @F@@@@ DO (T=REMOTESUB)=0                     ; IF NOTSU
)@@G@@ A REMOTE SUB     @F@@@@   ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU                  ; DEFAULT SV
)@@G@@RETURN JUMPTARGET @G@@@@      (T=CONTINGENCY)*G$LABL(K,1)-ISSUB . TO PACSW
)@@G@@KET OR -1 FLAG VALUE    @G@@@@ DO (T=EXECSUB)**(P(1)=1)             ; IFSX
)@@G@@ EXECSUB BUT NO RETURN ADDR   @F@@@@   ,P(1,2) EQU DISP                 SY
)@@G@@  . FORCE STD RETURN ADDR     @G@@@@ DO T=EXECSUB ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU P(1,SZ
)@@G@@2) . JUMPTARGET FOR EXEC ROUTINES   @G@@@@ DO GI>0 , DO P(GI)>1 ,G$LABL*TA
)@@G@@(K,4) EQU ;  UNLESS USER PROVIDED A USPEC @G@@@@        +      (I$ 0,P(GTB
)@@G@@I,4),,P(GI,3),2*P(GI,*3)+P(GI,*2),P(GI,2) )     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.     TC
)@@G@@         HANDLE REGISTER SAVE REQUESTS    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO ISSUB**(TD
)@@G@@P(1,2)=0) ,P(1,2) EQU X11 . DEFAULT LINKREG TO X11    @H@@@@SII     EQU TE
)@@G@@   ((P(1,1)=STACK)++(P(1,1)=SAVE))+; FIND REG SAVE CONTROL FIELD  @G@@@@TF
)@@G@@2*((P(2,1)=STACK)++(P(2,1)=SAVE))+3*((P(3,1)=STACK)++(P(3,1)=SAVE))     TG
)@@G@@@F@@@@SI      EQU    SII+(SII=0)*ISSUB      . IF NONE**SUBROUTINE, SET 1TH
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO SI=0 ,  END                       . IF NONE, WE'RE DONE @[@@@@TI
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@ST      EQU    P(SI,1)                . ELSE GET TYPE (SAVE/TJ
)@@G@@STACK/SUBRTNE)    @H@@@@ DO ISSUB=0                           ; IF NOT ATK
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE TO START WITH     @G@@@@    ,P(1,3) EQU NOSAVE              TL
)@@G@@  . OBVIOUSLY NO LINKREG TO BE SAVED@D@@@@I DO 3 ,Q(I) EQU P(I)         TM
)@@G@@        . COPY LEAVES   @G@@@@NOLINK    EQU       P(1,3)=NOSAVE     . ONTN
)@@G@@=> INHIBIT SAVE OF LINKREG    @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,P(1,2) EQU -P(1,2)      TO
)@@G@@  . IF NOT SAVING, JUST REMEMBER IT @G@@@@ DO NOLINK ,Q(1) EQU +2       TP
)@@G@@        . AND FORCE THE NOSAVE SPEC AWAY  @H@@@@KLX     EQU    Q(SI)-2*(TQ
)@@G@@ST=STACK)     . INDEX OF LAST REG TO EXPLICITLY SAVE  @H@@@@I DO KLX ,RSTR
)@@G@@AV(P(SI,I+1)**0777777) EQU 1 . MARK ALL REGS REQUESTED EXPLICITLY @H@@@@TS
)@@G@@III(1)     EQU      1       . INIT INCREMENTATION CTR: 1ST SUBFIELD WILLTT
)@@G@@ BE 2 @F@@@@I DO 128 , DO RSAV(I) ,P(SI,G$$INC(1)) EQU I . SORT EXPLICITTU
)@@G@@ REGS @H@@@@ DO KLX<Q(SI) , DO (P(SI,KLX+1)=POINTER)=0 , G$$EFL 3,2 . RETV
)@@G@@QUIRE REG SPEC    @H@@@@SEX        EQU      (ST=SUBROUTINE)++(ST=LIJSUB)TW
)@@G@@++(ST=LDJSUB)=0 . ON IF SAVE G@H@@@@SLI        EQU      ISSUB           TX
)@@G@@  . ON IF LINKREG SHOULD BE REMEMBERED    @G@@@@ DO SEX**SLI ,P(SI,KLX+1TY
)@@G@@) EQU P(1,2)  . FORCE LINKREG INTO SAVE LIST    @G@@@@KLR     EQU    KLXTZ
)@@G@@+(SEX**SLI)         . INDEX OF LAST REG TO REMEMBER   @H@@@@I DO     KLRUA
)@@G@@-1 ,G$FLAG*(K,2,I) EQU +P(SI,I+1) . REMEMBER WHATS BEING SAVED    @I@@@@UB
)@@G@@KL        EQU       KLR-(NOLINK*(1-(T=EXECSUB))) . NUMBER TO ACTUALLY PUUC
)@@G@@T IN COR    @I@@@@I DO KL-1 ,FNC(I) EQU 1+5*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+3*(G$FLAGUD
)@@G@@(K,2,I)>A15) . SA, SX, SR     @G@@@@I DO KL-1 ,AFL(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-UE
)@@G@@A0*(FNC(I)=1)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=4)     @H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)=1 ,FNC(IUF
)@@G@@) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE STORE A'S    @F@@@@  (070*(AFL(I+1)=AUG
)@@G@@FL(I)+1)+1) . DOUBLE STORE CONTIGUOUS AREGS     @G@@@@ DO ST=STACK , GO UH
)@@G@@G$$B10              . IF STACKING, GO DO SPECIAL STUFF@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0UI
)@@G@@ ,IC      EQU    &        . PRESERVE USER'S LOCATION COUNTER@G@@@@ DO G$UJ
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,IC      EQU    $LCN     . IC IS CURRENT LOCATION COUNTER  @F@@@@UK
)@@G@@$(G$LCTR(1))                          . AND ESTABLISH OUR OWN     @G@@@@UL
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&=IC)**(KL>1) , J $+KL    . IF =, LEAP AROUND THE RESUM
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($LCN=IC)**(KL>1) , J $+KL . IF =, LEAP AROUND TUN
)@@G@@HE RES@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU    $                 . START OF REG SAVE ARUO
)@@G@@EA (IF ANY) @E@@@@             RES    KL-1              . SET ASIDE SAVEUP
)@@G@@ SPACE@E@@@@$(IC)                                 . RESTORE USER'S IC   UQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@I DO KL-1 , DO FNC(I)>0 , I$ FNC(I),012*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LAUR
)@@G@@BL(K,3)+I-1 @G@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . IF NOT STACKINUS
)@@G@@G, WE'RE DONE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$$B10* NAME                        UT
)@@G@@  . HANDLE STACKING HERE@F@@@@OI      EQU    P(SI+1,1)=OFFSET       . ONUU
)@@G@@ IF OFFSET SPECIFIED    @H@@@@AI      EQU    P(SI,*KLX+2)           . ONUV
)@@G@@ TO AUTO-INCREMENT STACK POINTER    @G@@@@OSV     EQU    + (I$ 0,OI*P(SIUW
)@@G@@+1,3),0,P(SI,KLX+2),2*AI,OI*P(SI+1,2))    @C@@@@I DO  KL-1 , S G$FLAG(K,UX
)@@G@@2,I),OSV+(1-AI)*(I-1)   @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU 0-OSV                  . UY
)@@G@@REMEMBER OFFSET FLAGS   @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@UZ
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * VA
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *          ENDBEG   VB
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@VC
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     VD
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@ENDBEG*  NAME     @G@@@@M         EQU     VE
)@@G@@  G$CTR(5)          . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @H@@@@K         EQVF
)@@G@@U       G$SEQN(M)         . GET OVERALL BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER     @F@@@@VG
)@@G@@ DO (M=1)=0 , G$$GFL 1,1         . BE SURE NESTING LEVEL IS OK    @D@@@@VH
)@@G@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=1)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . AND BLOCK TYPE     @I@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQVI
)@@G@@U       0                 . FORCE NESTING LEVEL FOR SUBSEQUENT CODE     VJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO (G$CTR(2)=(0-G$CTR(7)))=0 , G$$GFL 1,2 . DIAGNOSE BAD FLOAT   VK
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       0                 . AND FORCE IT CORRECT@E@@@@VL
)@@G@@T         EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)       . GET BEGIN BLOCK TYPE@[@@@@.     VM
)@@G@@@E@@@@          RES       0-G$CTR(6)        . FIXUP FOR FLAGS     @E@@@@VN
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,2)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,2)    @D@@@@G$LABLVO
)@@G@@*(K,2)  EQU   $           . MARK END OF BLOCK   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO T=VP
)@@G@@CYCLIC , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . IF CYCLIC, LOOP BACK    @D@@@@ DO T=VQ
)@@G@@CYCLIC , END                 . AND THAT'S ALL   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. IF AVR
)@@G@@NY REGS WERE SAVED, RESTORE THEM    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)=0 VS
)@@G@@, GO G$$X01 @H@@@@NRR     EQU    +G$FLAG(K,2)              . GET NO OF RVT
)@@G@@EGISTERS REMEMBERED     @G@@@@LINK(1)   EQU       G$FLAG(K,2,NRR)   . LIVU
)@@G@@NK IS ALWAYS THE LAST ONE     @H@@@@NR        EQU       NRR-(LINK(1)<0) VV
)@@G@@  . FUDGE IN CASE WE DIDN'T SAVE LINK     @G@@@@ DO NRR>NR ,LINK(1) EQU VW
)@@G@@-LINK(1)      . THEN GET REAL VALUE OF LINK     @G@@@@I DO NR ,FNC(I) EQVX
)@@G@@U 010+017*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)<A0)+013*(G$FLAG(K,2,I)>A15)  @G@@@@I DO NR ,AFLVY
)@@G@@(I) EQU G$FLAG(K,2,I)-A0*(FNC(I)=010)-(R1-1)*(FNC(I)=023)   @H@@@@I DO NVZ
)@@G@@R , DO FNC(I)=010 ,FNC(I) EQU (FNC(I-1)<071)* ; FOR SINGLE LOAD A'S     WA
)@@G@@@F@@@@  (061*(AFL(I+1)=AFL(I)+1)+010) . DOUBLE LOAD CONTIGUOUS AREGS    WB
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,SR      EQU    0-G$LABL(K,3) . GET STACKREG/SAVE FLAWC
)@@G@@G     @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,SR      EQU    $AP(0-G$LABL(K,3)) . GET STACKRWD
)@@G@@EG/SAVE FLAG@ @@@@ DO (SR>0)=0 ,I DO NR , ;     @G@@@@  DO FNC(I)>0 , I$WE
)@@G@@ FNC(I),013*(FNC(I)=071),AFL(I),,,G$LABL(K,3)+I-1     @F@@@@ DO (SR>0)=0WF
)@@G@@ , GO G$$X01              . IF NOT STACKED, WE'RE DONE@#@@@@. HANDLE STAWG
)@@G@@CKING @F@@@@INC     EQU    SR**0400000            . ISOLATE AUTO-INCREMEWH
)@@G@@NT BIT@F@@@@XSR     EQU    (017000000**SR)*/4     . MOVE XREG INTO AREG WI
)@@G@@FIELD @F@@@@ DO INC>0 , ANX,U 0,NR+(017000000**SR)*/4 . BACK UP STACK POWJ
)@@G@@INTER @F@@@@I DO     NR , L G$FLAG(K,2,I),(SR**007777177777)+I-1 . AND UWK
)@@G@@NSTACK@F@@@@G$$X01* NAME                          . END OF REG RESTORATIWL
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $                 . MARK POSWM
)@@G@@N OF EXIT INSTR   @F@@@@ DO T=LIJSUB , I$ 07,013,LINK(1),LINK(1),,0 . LIWN
)@@G@@J LINK,0,LINK     @F@@@@ DO T=LDJSUB , I$ 07,012,LINK(1),LINK(1),,0 . LDWO
)@@G@@J LINK,0,LINK     @ @@@@ DO T=SUBROUTINE , J 0,LINK(1)@C@@@@ DO (T=EXECSWP
)@@G@@UB)++(T=REMOTESUB) , J G$LABL(K,4)  @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,5) , END       WQ
)@@G@@        . QUIT IF ANY OF THE ABOVE  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. PROCESS MAINPROGWR
)@@G@@S AND CONTINGENCIES     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@XREG    EQU    G$FLAG(K,1)    WS
)@@G@@        . GET EXIT TYPE (NORMAL OR SIGNAL)@G@@@@ DO XREG>0 , GO G$$X02  WT
)@@G@@              . IF EXCEPTION, GO PROCESS IT     @G@@@@ DO T=MAINPROGRAM WU
)@@G@@, ER EXIT$          . NORMAL MAINPROGRAM EXIT IS EXIT$@E@@@@ DO T=CONTINWV
)@@G@@GENCY , SZ,H1 G$LABL(K,4) . CLEAR PACKET UPPER  @F@@@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY WW
)@@G@@, I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . AND JUMP THRU PKT @G@@@@ DO 1 , END       WX
)@@G@@                    . THAT'S ALL FOR NORMAL EXITS     @H@@@@G$$X02* NAMEWY
)@@G@@                          . HERE TO HANDLE EXITS WITH SIGNALLING  @F@@@@WZ
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 051,H1,,,,G$LABL(K,4) . IS UPPER (H1) ZERO @G@@@@XA
)@@G@@ DO T=CONTINGENCY , I$ 074,04,,,1,G$LABL(K,4) . YES, EXIT THRU PACKET   XB
)@@G@@@I@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (G$LABL(K,4)<0)=0 , LX XREG,G$LABL(K,4) . LOAD FXC
)@@G@@ROM SIGNALLOC     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM , DO $AP(G$LABL(K,4))>=0 , LX XREG,G$XD
)@@G@@LABL(K,4) . LOAD FROM SIGNALLOC     @F@@@@        I$     074,04,,XREG,,$XE
)@@G@@+1      . JUMP INTO FOLLOWING TABLE @C@@@@        ER     011            XF
)@@G@@        . 0=EXIT$ @C@@@@        ER     040                    . 1=ERR$  XG
)@@G@@@C@@@@        ER     026                    . 2=EABT$ @C@@@@        ER  XH
)@@G@@   012                    . 3=ABORT$@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@XI
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     XJ
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       XK
)@@G@@  SWITCHTO            * @C@@@@.               *                         XL
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     XM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@SWITCHTO*  NAME   @[@@@@.     XN
)@@G@@@D@@@@. NOTE: THIS FEATURE IS NO LONGER AVAILABLE BECAUSE OF@E@@@@. OPTIXO
)@@G@@MIZATION TECHNIQUES FOR THE OBJECT CODE. ANY BLOCK    @E@@@@. MUST BE WHXP
)@@G@@OLLY GENERATED UNDER A SINGLE LOCATION COUNTER. @F@@@@. CONTINGENCY PROCXQ
)@@G@@ESSING IN A SEPERATE BANK MUST BE ACCOMPLISHED  @D@@@@. BY MEANS OF A SUXR
)@@G@@BROUTINE CALL TO THE OTHER BANK.    @[@@@@.     @I@@@@          RES     XS
)@@G@@  1                 . SPACE SO DIAGNOSTIC DOESN'T CREAM OLD US    @D@@@@XT
)@@G@@          G$$GFL    3,1               . GIVE A WARNING@H@@@@          REXU
)@@G@@S       -1                . ZAP THE IOPR SO THE PROGRAM WORKS     @G@@@@XV
)@@G@@. NOTE THAT WE SIMPLY IGNORE THE REQUEST FOR A LOCATION COUNTER CHANGE  XW
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********XX
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         XY
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           BASE              * @C@@@@.     XZ
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********YA
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@P          PROC   YB
)@@G@@  *1                .  SPECS:  IBANK\DBANK(,<USPEC FOR BDI>)@E@@@@BASE* YC
)@@G@@     NAME                       . MAKE A BANK VISIBLE @F@@@@XREG       EYD
)@@G@@QU      P(0,1)+X11*(P(0,1)=0) . XREG USED FOR LINKAGE @E@@@@. THE FOLLOWYE
)@@G@@ING THREE LINES ARE COURTESY OF ISAAC BORNSTEIN.@E@@@@. THEY FIX A BUG IYF
)@@G@@NVOLVING THE LOAD OF THE BDI (LXI,LDJ)    @F@@@@          DO P(1)<2 , GOYG
)@@G@@ NOLXI . IF ONLY 1 PARAM, NO LXI IS NEEDED@H@@@@ DO P(1,4)<016 , I$ 046,YH
)@@G@@P(1,4),XREG,P(1,3),2*P(1,*3)+P(1,*2),P(1,2) . LXI BDI @G@@@@ DO P(1,4)>0YI
)@@G@@15 , G$$IMU 046,P(1,4),XREG,P(1,3),P(1,2) . LXI,U/XU BDI    @^@@@@NOLXI YJ
)@@G@@    NAME      .   @F@@@@           I$       07,012+(P(1,1)=IBANK),XREG,,YK
)@@G@@,$+1 . DO LIJ/LDJ @#@@@@           END    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@YL
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * YM
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *            CALL   YN
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@YO
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     YP
)@@G@@@G@@@@          PROC      *0                . PROC TO DECLARE THE 'CALL'YQ
)@@G@@ PROC @E@@@@. PREVENTS RLIB$ ENTRY POINT CONFLICTS WITH COBOL'S 'CALL'  YR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@G$$CLD*   NAME                        .   @[@@@@.     YS
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @B@@@@CALL*** NAME                          .   YT
)@@G@@@G@@@@RAD(1)    EQU       +(0,-1)           . ASSUME NOT CALLING RMT BLOYU
)@@G@@K     @F@@@@P11       EQU       P(1,1)            . P11 IS ADDRESS OF TAYV
)@@G@@RGET  @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P11 EQU $AP(P11)        . IF MASM, USE ONLY ABYW
)@@G@@SOLUTE PART @E@@@@ DO P(1)=1                            ; IF ONLY ONE FIYX
)@@G@@ELD   @E@@@@   , DO P11<0400000                   ; AND IT ISN'T EQUF'D YY
)@@G@@@E@@@@      ,RAD(1) EQU P11                 . GET ITS ACTUAL ADDR @F@@@@YZ
)@@G@@K          EQU      G$BSEQ(RAD(1))    . GET SEQUENCE NO OF BLOK   @G@@@@ZA
)@@G@@ DO K>0                               ; IF BLOCK HAS BEEN PROCESSED...  ZB
)@@G@@@E@@@@   , DO G$FLAG(K,3)=REMOTESUB         ; AND IT'S REMOTE     @F@@@@ZC
)@@G@@      , GO G$$CL1                     . GO TREAT IT SPECIALLY     @[@@@@ZD
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@XREG    EQU    P(0,1)+(P(0,1)=0)*X11  . DEFAULT LINKREG TO XZE
)@@G@@11    @G@@@@BANKSW     EQU      P(2,1)=BASING     . ON IF WE SHOULD SWITZF
)@@G@@CH BANKS    @G@@@@K DO P(2)*(1-BANKSW) , SZ P(2,K) . CLEAR ALT EXIT SENTZG
)@@G@@INALS, IF ANY     @E@@@@. THE FOLLOWING THREE LINES ARE COURTESY OF ISAAZH
)@@G@@C BORNSTEIN.@E@@@@. THEY FIX A BUG INVOLVING THE LOAD OF THE BDI (LXI,LDZI
)@@G@@J)    @I@@@@          DO 1-(BANKSW**(P(2)>2)) , GO NOLXI . IF ONLY 1 PARZJ
)@@G@@AM, NO LXI IS NEEDED    @H@@@@ DO P(2,5)<016 , I$ 046,P(2,5),XREG,P(2,4)ZK
)@@G@@,2*P(2,*4)+P(2,*3),P(2,3) . LXI BDI @G@@@@ DO P(2,5)>015 , G$$IMU 046,P(ZL
)@@G@@2,5),XREG,P(2,4),P(2,3) . LXI,U/XU BDI    @^@@@@NOLXI     NAME      .   ZM
)@@G@@@D@@@@FUN        EQU      074-BANKSW*065    . LMJ OR LIJ/LDJ@H@@@@JAY   ZN
)@@G@@     EQU      013-BANKSW*(P(2,2)=DBANK) . 013 UNLESS LDJ (THEN 012)     ZO
)@@G@@@F@@@@           I$       FUN,JAY,XREG,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) .ZP
)@@G@@@I@@@@K DO     P(2)*(1-BANKSW) , SX XREG,P(2,K)        . SET ALT EXIT SEZQ
)@@G@@NTINALS, IF ANY   @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$CL1***  NAME   ZR
)@@G@@                    . HERE FOR CALLS TO REMOTE BLOX   @F@@@@           JZS
)@@G@@        P(1,1)            . FLYING LEAP TO THE BLOCK  @F@@@@           GZT
)@@G@@$$PRB   K,$               . PATCH ITS RETURN ADDR     @H@@@@          ENZU
)@@G@@D                         . END OF THE ACTUAL 'CALL' PROC DEFN    @G@@@@ZV
)@@G@@          END                         . END OF PROC WHICH DEFINES 'CALL'ZW
)@@G@@@C@@@@/.           ******    IF   GROUP    *******    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@ZX
)@@G@@. USE OF LABELS AND FLAGS --  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.       G$FLZY
)@@G@@AG(K,1) EXPLICIT NOT FLAG     @E@@@@.                2) SIDE EFFECT AND ZZ
)@@G@@'IF' TEST INVERSION FLAG@B@@@@.                3) IMPLIED LINEITEM FLAG AA
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                4) FLOAT ADJUSTMENT CAUSED BY 'ELSE' @F@@@@.     AB
)@@G@@           5) FLOAT CAUSED BY OPTIMIZATION OF 'IF' TEST     @B@@@@.     AC
)@@G@@           6) COMPLEX CONDITION FLAG@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1AD
)@@G@@) START ADDR OF TESTS AT 'IF' @E@@@@.                2) START ADDR OF USAE
)@@G@@ER CODE IN 'IF' BLOCK   @D@@@@.                3) END ADDR OF CODE IN 'IAF
)@@G@@F' BLOCK    @D@@@@.                4) START ADDR OF CODE IN 'ELSE' BLOCKAG
)@@G@@@D@@@@.                5) TARGET ADDR FOR EXIT FROM BLOCK   @[@@@@.     AH
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.           AI
)@@G@@    *                             * @C@@@@.               *            IAJ
