)@@G@@F               * @C@@@@.               *                             * AK
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@AL
)@@G@@P       PROC   *6 @]@@@@IF*     NAME@[@@@@.     @H@@@@LOOF      EQU     AM
)@@G@@  (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=LOOKFOR) . CHECK FOR TABLE SEARCH FORMAT@^@@@@ DO LOAN
)@@G@@OF , GO G$$I05    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ANALYZE SYNTAX SO WE KNOW IF THIS AO
)@@G@@IS LINEITEM OR A BLOCK  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@L       EQU    P-1@B@@@@L1    AP
)@@G@@  EQU    (P(L)=1)**(P(L,1)=THEN)    @B@@@@L2      EQU    (P(L-1)=1)**(P(AQ
)@@G@@L-1,1)=THEN)@E@@@@FLT     EQU    L1*L+L2*(L-1)  . FIELD OF 'THEN' OR ZERAR
)@@G@@O     @E@@@@THF     EQU    FLT+(FLT=0)*P  . IF NOT GIVEN, ASSUME IT     AS
)@@G@@@F@@@@IFNOT     EQU       (P(1)=1)**(P(1,1)=NOT) . SET EXPLICIT NOT FLAGAT
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO (THF=IFNOT+2)++(THF=IFNOT+4)=0 , G$$EFL 3,3 . CHECK NO OF FIELAU
)@@G@@DS    @F@@@@CXF       EQU       THF=IFNOT+4     . SET COMPLEX CONDITION AV
)@@G@@FLAG  @E@@@@ DO P<THF+2 , GO G$$I05               . GO DO NORMAL FORMAT AW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. LINEITEM FORMAT DOES NOT UPDATE NESTING ARRAYS- GETSAX
)@@G@@ SPECIAL HANDLING @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$TST    1+IFNOT,CXF,IFNOAY
)@@G@@T . GENERATE THE TEST   @E@@@@          +P(THF+1,1)                 . THAZ
)@@G@@EN THE LINEITEM   @A@@@@   DO 1 , END       . AND THEN QUIT @[@@@@.     BA
)@@G@@@B@@@@. PROCESS NORMAL (NOT LINEITEM) IF --     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I05BB
)@@G@@*   NAME    @H@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUBC
)@@G@@ENCE NO FOR THIS BLOCK  @F@@@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . ANBD
)@@G@@D UPDATE BLOCK COUNTER  @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUBE
)@@G@@MP CURRENT BLOCK NESTING LEVEL@G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        BF
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@G$TYPE*(M)          EQU       BG
)@@G@@        2 . SET CURRENT BLOCKTYPE TO IF   @H@@@@G$SEQN*(M)          EQU BH
)@@G@@              K . AND REMEMBER ITS SEQUENCE NUMBER    @[@@@@.     @ @@@@BI
)@@G@@. ADJUST ALL LABELS FOR FLOAT @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,1) EQU G$LABL(BJ
)@@G@@K,1)+G$CTR(2) . GLOBAL FLOAT  @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(BK
)@@G@@K,5) . APPLY 'IF' FLOAT @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQU G$LABL(K,N+1)+GBL
)@@G@@$CTR(2) . GLOBAL+IF     @F@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N+3) EQU G$LABL(K,N+3)+GBM
)@@G@@$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,4)     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@  DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,1BN
)@@G@@)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,1)   @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $        . REMEMBO
)@@G@@BER START ADDR FOR OPTIMIZATION     @H@@@@ DO LOOF , GO G$$I10          BP
)@@G@@        . LOOKFOR TESTS GET SPECIAL HANDLING    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@NOGEN BQ
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(7)*(G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,1)) . ON TO SURPRESS ALL   BR
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU G$CTR(4)+NOGEN           . KEEP G$$TST'S COUNTER IN BS
)@@G@@PHASE @A@@@@ DO NOGEN , END     . STOP IF NO MO @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAGBT
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU IFNOT            . SAVE NOT FLAG FOR OPTIMIZER   @E@@@@G$FLAGBU
)@@G@@*(K,6) EQU CXF              . AND ALSO COMPLEX FLAG   @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)BV
)@@G@@ , G$$SVA              . PASS 1: SAVE ARGS FOR RECALL AT ENDIF    @[@@@@BW
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL REVERSABX
)@@G@@L FLAG@F@@@@LIG       EQU       G$FLAG(K,3)     . SET IMPLIED LINEITEM FBY
)@@G@@LAG   @G@@@@ DO 1-LIG ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF G$LABL(K,4)  . GENERATEBZ
)@@G@@ THE TEST   @H@@@@ DO LIG  ,  G$$TST  1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      . GENERATE LICA
)@@G@@NE ITEM FORMAT TEST(S)  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU SIDE(1)               . RCB
)@@G@@EMEMBER IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         CC
)@@G@@. REMEMBER START OF USER CODE FOR OPTIMIZA@#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@CD
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE 'LOOKFOR' TESTS, WHICH GENERATE 1100 SERIES SEARCH CE
)@@G@@INSTRUCTIONS@[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I10*   NAME    @A@@@@ DO (P(3,1)=VARY)=CF
)@@G@@0 , G$$EFL 2,010 .@I@@@@VI        EQU       3                 . 'VARY' SCG
)@@G@@PECIFICATION MUST FOLLOW 'LOOKFO    @E@@@@P(3,1)    EQU       LOOKFOR   CH
)@@G@@        . FORCE THE KEYWORD   @G@@@@KW(1)     EQU       LOOKFOR         CI
)@@G@@  . IN ALL PLACES ITS EXPECTED TO BE@G@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         CJ
)@@G@@         . GUARANTEE NON-EMPTY 'IF' CLAUSE@H@@@@          G$$LAN        CK
)@@G@@              . ANALYZE SPECS, LOAD REGS IF NECESSARY @G@@@@          G$CL
)@@G@@$LGE    3,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,4),1 . GEN CODE FOR SEARCH   @F@@@@G$CTR*CM
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)+G$CTR(6)       . PRETEND WE SAVED THE ARGS @[@@@@.     CN
)@@G@@@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ********CO
)@@G@@*********************** @C@@@@.               *                         CP
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               *           ELSE              * @C@@@@.     CQ
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               ********CR
)@@G@@*********************** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@        PROC   *0 @]@@@@ELSE* CS
)@@G@@  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING CT
)@@G@@LEVEL @F@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GET SEQ NUM FOR THISCU
)@@G@@ BLOCK@F@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=2)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3        . CATCH NESTING ERROCV
)@@G@@RS    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,3)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LCW
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) .  @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU   $                       . MARK ENDCX
)@@G@@ OF 'IF' CLAUSE   @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)=$ , END . EMPTY 'IF' => IGNORE ECY
)@@G@@LSE COMPLETELY    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@     DO G$FLAG(K,4)=0 , I$     074,0CZ
)@@G@@4,,,,G$LABL(K,5) . LEAP TO ENDI     @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(DA
)@@G@@K,4) . SET ELSE FLOAT FOR CODE BELOW@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)  EQU   $ . MARK SDB
)@@G@@TART OF 'ELSE' USER CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@DC
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * DD
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           ENDIF   DE
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@DF
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @#@@@@      DG
)@@G@@  PROC   *0 @]@@@@ENDIF*  NAME@F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        DH
)@@G@@  . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)       DI
)@@G@@  . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @F@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=2)=0 , G$$GFL 1DJ
)@@G@@,3          . CATCH NESTING ERRORS  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO DK
)@@G@@(G$LABL(K,5)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,5)    @D@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $   DL
)@@G@@      . MARK END OF BLOCK     @G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M-1             DM
)@@G@@  . STEP NESTING BACK ONE LEVEL     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. RESTORE GLOBAL FDN
)@@G@@LOAT FOR FOLLOWING BLOX (EFFECTIVE ON PASS 2 ONLY)    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@DO
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU G$CTR(7)*(G$CTR(2)-G$FLAG(K,5)-G$FLAG(K,4)) . @E@@@@ DO G$DP
)@@G@@CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE AT THIS POINT    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@DQ
)@@G@@.   ***** PASS 1 ONLY BEYOND THIS POINT *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$CTR*DR
)@@G@@(3) EQU G$CTR(3)-1              . ADJUST ARGSAVE STACK POINTER    @[@@@@DS
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. TABULATE FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED ELSE, IF ANY    @[@@@@.     DT
)@@G@@@H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU 0-((G$LABL(K,3)>0)**(G$LABL(K,4)=$)) . 'ELSE' FLODU
)@@G@@AT (NO -0!!)@G@@@@          RES       G$FLAG(K,4)     . APPLY ELSFLOAT FDV
)@@G@@OR SUCCEEDING CODE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CHECK FOR SURPRESSION OF EVERYTHINDW
)@@G@@G (NO CODE AND NO SIDE EFFECTS)     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO ($>G$LABL(K,2)DX
)@@G@@)++G$FLAG(K,2) , GO G$$I20 . IF NOT, GO CHECK OPTIMIZATION  @E@@@@G$FLAGDY
)@@G@@*(K,5) EQU G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2) . TURN OFF 'IF'    @F@@@@          REDZ
)@@G@@S       G$LABL(K,1)-$   . ADJUST L.C. APPROPRIATELY   @C@@@@  DO 1 , ENDEA
)@@G@@        . AND TERMINATE GRACEFULLY  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. CHECK FOR POSSIBEB
)@@G@@LE OPTIMIZATION OF THE INITIAL TEST @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$I20*   NAME    EC
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,4)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU $ . IF NO ELSE, PUT IT HERE   ED
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU G$LABL(K,3)=G$LABL(K,2) . NO 'IF' CLAEE
)@@G@@USE =>INVERT@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU    $-G$LABL(K,2)=1   . IMPLIED LINEITEF
)@@G@@EM    @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,2)++G$FLAG(K,3)=0 , END . DONE IF NO OPTIMIZATIEG
)@@G@@ON    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WE'RE GOING TO OPTIMIZE THE JUMP WHEN WE GET BEH
)@@G@@ACK THERE ON PASS 2     @F@@@@. TO INSURE THAT LABELS BELOW THIS POINT AEI
)@@G@@RE OK, WE MUST PERFORCE @E@@@@. DO A TRIAL GENERATION OF THE MODIFIED TEEJ
)@@G@@ST SO WE KNOW     @G@@@@. HOW MANY INSTRUCTIONS IT WILL TAKE WHEN WE GENEK
)@@G@@ IT BACK AT THE TOP     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@KK        EQU       G$CTR(3)+1EL
)@@G@@        . GET ARGSAVE INDEX OF MATCHING 'IF'    @F@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,JEM
)@@G@@ DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +G$ARGS(KK,I,J)    @E@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,JEN
)@@G@@ DO G$ARGS(KK,I)    ; FOR ALL SUBFIELDS   @F@@@@  , DO G$ARGS(KK,I,*J) ,EO
)@@G@@P(I,J) EQU *P(I,J) . PRESERVE ASTERISKS   @A@@@@IFNOT     EQU       G$FLEP
)@@G@@AG(K,1)     @F@@@@CXF       EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)   . RETRIEVE COMPLEX CEQ
)@@G@@ONDN FLAG   @F@@@@RVF       EQU       IFNOT--G$FLAG(K,2) . SET OVERALL RER
)@@G@@EVERSAL FLAG@E@@@@START                 . REMEMBER WHERE BEGINNING OF TEES
)@@G@@ST WAS@D@@@@ DO 1-G$FLAG(K,3) , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF $+10 .     @D@@@@ET
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)   , G$$TST 1+IFNOT,CXF,RVF      .     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQEU
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(4)-1        . RESTORE INTERNAL CTR USED BY G$$TST   @[@@@@EV
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. NOW SET ADDRESS ADJUSTMENT FLAGS SO PASS 2 WILL GEN PROPEREW
)@@G@@ CODE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@SIZE      EQU       G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . SIEX
)@@G@@ZE OF ORIGINAL TEST     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU $-START-SIZE       . COMPEY
)@@G@@UTE PASS 2 FLOAT  @H@@@@          RES      0-SIZE            . COMPENSATEZ
)@@G@@E L.C. FOR CODE WHICH FOLLOWS @]@@@@        END @B@@@@/.          ******FA
)@@G@@** CASE GROUP  *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. ARRAY USAGE IS -FB
)@@G@@-     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$FLAG(K,1) TOTAL NUMBER OF CASE VALUES FC
)@@G@@GIVEN @G@@@@.         ...    2) RUNNING TALLY: NUMBER OF VALUES ON PREVIFD
)@@G@@OUS CASE    @C@@@@.         ...    3) INHIBIT/CALL OPTION FLAG    @E@@@@FE
)@@G@@.         ...    4,X) VALUE OF X'TH SPECIFIED CASEVALUE     @C@@@@.     FF
)@@G@@    ...    5) # OF REMOTE CASES PROCESSED @D@@@@.         ...    6) FLAGFG
)@@G@@ SET 1 IF NOCHECKING IS ON    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       G$LABL(K,1) STARFH
)@@G@@T ADDR OF USER NOFIND CODE    @C@@@@.         ...    2) END ADDR OF USERFI
)@@G@@ NOFIND CODE@D@@@@.         ...    3) ULTIMATE EXIT ADDR FROM BLOCK     FJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@.         ...    4,X) JUMPTARGET ADDR FOR X'TH CASEVALUE    @E@@@@FK
)@@G@@.         ...    5) RUNNING LABEL: LAST JUMP TO CLOSE A CASE@E@@@@.     FL
)@@G@@    ...    6) BASE ADDR FOR OFFSET INTO JUMP TABLE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@FM
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.     FN
)@@G@@          *                             * @C@@@@.               *       FO
)@@G@@   CASENTRY           * @C@@@@.               *                         FP
)@@G@@    * @C@@@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     FQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@. SYNTAX--     CASENTRY <AXREG>    OR...  @D@@@@.              CASFR
)@@G@@ENTRY CALLING(,<LINK>) NAME(,<TAG>) @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P     FS
)@@G@@  PROC   *6 @B@@@@CASENTRY*  NAME                       .   @F@@@@K     FT
)@@G@@    EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . GET BLOCK SEQUENCE NUM    @D@@@@G$CTR*FU
)@@G@@(1) EQU       K                 . AND UPDATE IT @G@@@@M         EQU     FV
)@@G@@  G$CTR(5)+1        . NESTING LEVEL FOR THIS BLOCK    @E@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQFW
)@@G@@U       M                 . UPDATE THAT, TOO    @G@@@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU    FX
)@@G@@  K                 . REMEMBER BLOCK SEQUENCE NUMBER  @F@@@@G$TYPE*(M) EFY
)@@G@@QU      3                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO CASE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@FZ
)@@G@@. DO PRELIMINARY PARSING@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CALOPT     EQU      P(1,1)=CALGA
)@@G@@LING    . ON TO CALL SUBROUTINE     @G@@@@N DO (P-2)*(P>2)              GB
)@@G@@        ; SEARCH ALL BUT 0TH AND 1ST FIELD@F@@@@  , DO P(N+1)=1         GC
)@@G@@              ; IF ONLY ONE SUBFIELD...   @G@@@@    , DO P(N+1,1)=NOCHECGD
)@@G@@KING          ; AND ITS THE NOCHECKING KEYWORD  @H@@@@       ,G$FLAG*(K,GE
)@@G@@6) EQU 1            . SET GLOBAL FLAG FOR ENDCASE FLOAT     @G@@@@N DO (GF
)@@G@@P-2)*(P>2)                      ; SEARCH ALL BUT 0TH AND 1ST FIELD@G@@@@GG
)@@G@@  , DO P(N+1,1)=NOFINDEXIT            ; AND ITS THE NOFIND EXIT SPEC    GH
)@@G@@@F@@@@     ,NFI(1) EQU N+1                  . REMEMBER WHERE IT APPEAREDGI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO CALOPT=0 , GO G$$C05              . SKIP THIS IF NGJ
)@@G@@ORMAL CASENTRY    @G@@@@BANKSW     EQU      P(3,1)=BASING     . ON IF WEGK
)@@G@@ SHOULD SWITCH BANKS    @G@@@@XREG       EQU      P(1,2)+X11*(P(1,2)=0) GL
)@@G@@. LINK REG, DEFAULT => X11    @I@@@@ DO BANKSW**(P(3)>2) , I$ 046,P(3,5)GM
)@@G@@,XREG,P(3,4),3*P(3,*4)+P(3,*3),P(3,3) . LXI     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C05GN
)@@G@@*    NAME   @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,0) EQU    G$LABL(K,0)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY GLOBAGO
)@@G@@L FLOAT     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,0)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,GP
)@@G@@0)    @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,0)  EQU   $                 . MARK START IN CASE WGQ
)@@G@@E'LL INHIBIT@[@@@@.     @E@@@@          RES       CALOPT*G$CTR(6) . ACCOGR
)@@G@@UNT FOR THE LMJ   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C10*   NAME    @F@@@@ DO G$CTR(6)GS
)@@G@@ , GO G$$C40           . ON PASS 1, SKIP THIS STUFF   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@GT
)@@G@@. ***** PASS 2 ONLY-- GENERATE CHECKING AND THE JUMPTABLE   @[@@@@.     GU
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO 1-CALOPT , ; IF NOT A SUBROUTINE CALL BLOCK @F@@@@ DO (P(1,1)<GV
)@@G@@A0)++(P(1,1)>A3) , G$$EFL 3,1 . DIE IF NOT OVERLAP REG@[@@@@.     @B@@@@GW
)@@G@@. COMPUTE CHARACTERISTICS OF THE TABLE    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NUMCA     EQGX
)@@G@@U       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@CMAX(1)   EQGY
)@@G@@U       -34359738367      . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUMBER  @H@@@@GZ
)@@G@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MHA
)@@G@@AX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MIN TO LARGEST HB
)@@G@@POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1) ,CMIN(1) EHC
)@@G@@QU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @D@@@@OFF     EQU    1-CMIN(1)            HD
)@@G@@  . SET OFFSET    @G@@@@JTSIZ   EQU    CMAX(1)+OFF            . SET TOT HE
)@@G@@TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL @F@@@@JTL       EQU       JTSIZ-(G$FLAG(K,3)=-1)HF
)@@G@@*(G$FLAG(K,4,1)=CMAX(1))@F@@@@ DO CALOPT , DO (CMIN(1)=0)=0 , G$$EFL 3,5HG
)@@G@@ . MIN VAL NOT ZERO     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS BELONHH
)@@G@@GING TO THIS BLOCK, SET GLOBAL FLOAT@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3) EQU  HI
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,3)+G$CTR(2) . LAST LBL GETS ONLY GLOBAL FLOAT    @G@@@@PRSIZ HJ
)@@G@@    EQU       (CALOPT=0)*(4-3*G$FLAG(K,6)) . SIZE OF PREAMBLE     @G@@@@HK
)@@G@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+(G$FLAG(K,3)<1)*(PRSIZ+JTL)  . SET FLOAT   HL
)@@G@@@E@@@@N DO 2 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,N)+G$CTR(2) . APPLY IT    @G@@@@HM
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END                 . IF OPTIMIZED AWAY, QUIT HERE  HN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE CROSS REFERENCES NEEDED TO GENERATE THE JUMPHO
)@@G@@ TABLE@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ISNF      EQU       G$LABL(K,2)>G$LABL(K,1) . ONHP
)@@G@@=> USER GAVE NOFIND CODE@H@@@@ DO (NFI(1)>0)**ISNF , G$$EFL 3,07    . NOHQ
)@@G@@FIND EXIT FORBIDS NOFIND USER CODE  @G@@@@NFA(1)    EQU       G$LABL(K,3HR
)@@G@@-2*ISNF) . NOFIND ADDR <= ENDCASE/USERCODE@G@@@@ DO NFI(1)>0            HS
)@@G@@              ; IF EXPLICIT NOFIND TARGET GIVEN @E@@@@  ,NFA(1) EQU P(NFHT
)@@G@@I(1),2)             . SET JUMPTARGET TO IT@F@@@@ DO CALOPT              HU
)@@G@@              ; IF WE'RE CALLING A SUBRTNE@G@@@@  ,NFA(1) EQU -1        HV
)@@G@@              . SET MISSING CASE DETECTION FLAG @F@@@@N DO JTSIZ        HW
)@@G@@                    ; FOR ALL JUMPTABLE ENTRIES @G@@@@  ,JT(N) EQU NFA(1HX
)@@G@@)                   . INITIALIZE TARGET ADDR TO NOFIND@F@@@@N DO NUMCA  HY
)@@G@@                          ; FOR ALL CASEVALUES GIVEN  @G@@@@  ,JT(G$FLAGHZ
)@@G@@(K,4,N)+OFF)              ; SET JMPTBL ADDR FOR N'TH VALUE  @G@@@@     EIA
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,4,N)+G$CTR(2)       . TO FLOATED ADDR OF TARGET BLOK  @E@@@@IB
)@@G@@N DO JTSIZ                            ; FOR ALL CASE VALUES @F@@@@  , DOIC
)@@G@@ JT(N)=G$CTR(2)                 ; IF TARGET BLOCK IS EMPTY  @G@@@@     ,ID
)@@G@@JT(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3)           . JUMP DIRECTLY TO THE ENDCASE    @G@@@@IE
)@@G@@N DO CALOPT*JTSIZ                     ; FOR ALL CASEVALS OF CALL OPTION IF
)@@G@@@G@@@@  , DO JT(N)=-1                       ; IF NO ACTION GIVEN FOR N'TIG
)@@G@@H EXIT@G@@@@     , G$$EFL 3,6                     . GIVE MISSING CASE DIIH
)@@G@@AGNOSTIC    @G@@@@. NOW FIXUP FOR LAST CASE OPTIMIZED OUT FROM UNDER EMPII
)@@G@@TY CASES BEFORE IT@F@@@@OSADR     EQU       G$LABL(K,3)+1     . OVERSHOOIJ
)@@G@@T TARGET ADDR     @F@@@@N DO JTSIZ                            ; FOR ALL IK
)@@G@@CASE VALUES GIVEN @G@@@@  , DO JT(N)=OSADR                    ; IF EMPTYIL
)@@G@@ CASE CAUSED OVERSHOOT  @H@@@@    ,JT(N) EQU G$LABL(K,3)            . PAIM
)@@G@@TCH UP EXIT TO REAL ENDBEG LOCN     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GEN PREAMBLE TO IN
)@@G@@JUMP TABLE, I.E., CHECKING CODE AND JUMP OR CALL@[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO CAIO
)@@G@@LOPT , GO G$$C26                . CALLING OPTION GETS NO PREAMBLE @G@@@@IP
)@@G@@    DO G$FLAG(K,6)>0 , GO G$$C25      . CHECKS INHIBITED GETS ONLY JUMP IQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TLE,XU    P(1,1),CMAX(1)+1  . TEST AGAINST MAX RANGE    IR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TLE,XU    P(1,1),CMIN(1)    . AND AGAINST THE MIN @G@@@@IS
)@@G@@          J         NFA(1)            . NOFIND EXIT IF OUT AT EITHER ENDIT
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$C25*   NAME    @E@@@@          J         $+OFF,P(1,1)      . JUIU
)@@G@@MP THRU TABLE     @#@@@@    GO G$$C29     @E@@@@G$$C26*   NAME          IV
)@@G@@              . HERE FOR CALLING    @F@@@@FUN       EQU       074-BANKSWIW
)@@G@@*065    . FUNC CODE, LMJ/LIJ/LDJ    @G@@@@JAY       EQU       013-BANKSWIX
)@@G@@*(P(3,2)=DBANK) . J-DES IS PART OF OPCODE @B@@@@HI        EQU       2*P(IY
)@@G@@2,*2)+P(2,*1)     @D@@@@          I$        FUN,JAY,XREG,P(2,2),HI,P(2,1IZ
)@@G@@) .   @F@@@@G$$C29*   NAME                        . END OF PREAMBLE GENEJA
)@@G@@RATION@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. NOW ACTUALLY GENERATE THE JUMP TABLE    @[@@@@JB
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@G$LABL*(K,6) EQU    $-CMIN(1)         . ESTABLISH ANCHOR ADDJC
)@@G@@R FOR JMPTBL@G@@@@N DO JTL                              ; FOR ALL ENTRIEJD
)@@G@@S IN THE TABLE    @G@@@@  , J JT(N)                           . TAKE PROJE
)@@G@@VERBIAL FLYING LEAP     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. ***** PASS 1 LEAPS DIRECTLY JF
)@@G@@HERE  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$C40*   NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU 0-CALOPJG
)@@G@@T             . REMEMBER CALL OPTION, IF ANY    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU JH
)@@G@@  $                 . MARK START OF NOFIND CODE, IF ANY     @F@@@@G$FLAGJI
)@@G@@*(K,1) EQU 0                    . NO CASE STMNTS SEEN YET   @G@@@@G$LABLJJ
)@@G@@*(K,4,0) EQU  $                 . INITIALIZE LOCAL OPTIMIZATION   @I@@@@JK
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU 0                    . NO VALUES ON NON-EXISTENT PREVIOJL
)@@G@@US CASE     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@JM
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * JN
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           CASE    JO
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@JP
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     JQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *2 @F@@@@CASE*   NAME                          . SPJR
)@@G@@ECS--  <VALUE-LIST>     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GEJS
)@@G@@T CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . GEJT
)@@G@@T SEQUENCE NUM OF THIS BLOCK  @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=3)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3    JU
)@@G@@  . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)>0 , END                 . JV
)@@G@@DONE IF OPTIMIZED AWAY  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@JJ      EQU    +G$FLAG(K,1)   JW
)@@G@@        . GET # OF CASEVALS SO FAR IN THIS GRP  @G@@@@ DO JJ=0 ,G$LABL*(JX
)@@G@@K,2)  EQU   $       . MARK END OF USER NOFIND CODE    @B@@@@ DO (JJ>0)++JY
)@@G@@(G$FLAG(K,3)>-1) , GO G$$C60 .@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. SPECIAL STUFF FOR 1ST JZ
)@@G@@CASE WITH CALLING OPTION@G@@@@.    THE MAX VAL IS MOVED TO THE 1ST POSN KA
)@@G@@SO THAT WE CAN EASILY CHECK   @G@@@@. LATER WHETHER IT IS THE GLOBAL MAXKB
)@@G@@.  IF SO, AND IF THE 1ST BLOCK HAS  @G@@@@. CODE, THEN THE LAST JUMPTBL KC
)@@G@@ENTRY CAN BE OMITTED AND WE CAN INSTEAD   @B@@@@. SIMPLY FALL INTO THE CKD
)@@G@@ODE FOR THIS CASE.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO $>G$LABL(K,1) , G$$GFL 2,5 . NO KE
)@@G@@NOFIND ALLOWED FOR CALL OPTION@E@@@@MAX(1)    EQU       P(1,1)          KF
)@@G@@    . INITIALIZE MAX    @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)>MAX(1) ,MAX(1) EQU PKG
)@@G@@(1,N) . FIND MAX VALUE  @F@@@@IMAX(1)   EQU       1                 . INKH
)@@G@@ITIALIZE POSN OF MAXVAL @F@@@@N DO P(1) , DO P(1,N)=MAX(1) ,IMAX(1) EQU KI
)@@G@@N . FIND POSN OF MAXVAL @E@@@@MTEMP     EQU       P(1,1)            . TEKJ
)@@G@@MP SAVE 1ST VALUE @E@@@@P(1,1)    EQU       MAX(1)            . FORCE ITKK
)@@G@@ TO MAX     @G@@@@P(1,IMAX(1)) EQU    MTEMP             . EXCHANGE WITH KL
)@@G@@PREVIOUS VALUE    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. CLOSE PREVIOUS CASE   @[@@@@.     KM
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$C60*   NAME    @H@@@@REDUN     EQU       $=G$LABL(K,3)     . ONKN
)@@G@@=> CLOSURE HERE WOULD BE REDUNDANT  @G@@@@GOTSOM EQU $>G$LABL(K,4,JJ)   KO
)@@G@@        . ON IF PRECEDING CASE HAD CODE   @G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,3)<0)**(JJKP
)@@G@@=1)           ; IF 2ND CASE OF CALLING OPTION...@F@@@@    ,G$FLAG*(K,3) KQ
)@@G@@EQU GOTSOM-2        . SET FLAG IF 1ST CASE EMPTY@F@@@@ DO GOTSOM**1-REDUKR
)@@G@@N , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,3) . CLOSE LAST CASE  @H@@@@ DO GOTSOM ,G$LABLKS
)@@G@@*(K,5)   EQU  $     . MARK START USERCODE FOR THIS CASE     @G@@@@G$CTR*KT
)@@G@@(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-REDUN*GOTSOM    . IF SURPRESSED, NOTE FLOAT@D@@@@KU
)@@G@@N DO (1-GOTSOM)*G$FLAG(K,2) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+1-N) EQU 0@[@@@@.     @B@@@@KV
)@@G@@. TABULATE PARAMETERS FOR THE PRESENT CASE@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1)KW
)@@G@@ EQU JJ+P(1)              . UPDATE CASEVAL COUNT@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU +KX
)@@G@@P(1)                . REMEMBER HOW MANY TBL ENTRIES WE'RE USI     @F@@@@KY
)@@G@@N DO P(1) ,G$FLAG*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU +(P(1,N)) . SAVE CASE VALUE(S)   @G@@@@KZ
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)=0)=0 , ; IF NOT OPTIMIZED AWAY ...  LA
)@@G@@@G@@@@  DO (G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CTR(2)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,4,JJ+1)+G$CLB
)@@G@@TR(2) @H@@@@N DO     P(1) ,G$LABL*(K,4,JJ+N) EQU $ . SET OUR OWN JUMPTARLC
)@@G@@GET ADDRESSES     @G@@@@ DO (P(2,1)=REMOTESUB)=0 , END          . QUIT ULD
)@@G@@NLESS REMOTESUB CALL    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    G$FLAG(K,5LE
)@@G@@)+G$CTR(6) . ON PASS 1,  COUNT REMOTE CALLS     @D@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) , ENDLF
)@@G@@                    . AND THAT'S ALL@F@@@@          G$$PRA    P(2,2),G$LLG
)@@G@@ABL(K,3) . PATCH UP BLOCK EXIT INSTR@E@@@@ DO P(2,3)=VIA ,P(2,2) EQU P(2LH
)@@G@@,4)     . SET XFER TARGET ADDR@F@@@@HERE                                LI
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WHERE WE ARE     @G@@@@N DO P(1)                           LJ
)@@G@@  ; FOR ALL VALUES IN THIS CASE     @G@@@@  , G$$PJT G$LABL(K,6)+P(1,N),LK
)@@G@@P(2,2)  . MAKE JMPTBL POINT TO TARGET     @E@@@@          RES       HERELL
)@@G@@-$            . RESTORE THE L.C.    @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LM
)@@G@@P         PROC      *1,0              . DO NOTHING ON PASS 1@E@@@@G$$PJTLN
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . PATCH UP JUMP TABLE @F@@@@          RELO
)@@G@@S       P(1,1)-$          . GO BACK TO JUMPTBL ENTRY  @G@@@@          J LP
)@@G@@        P(1,2)            . AND OVERLAY IT WITH NEW TARGET  @#@@@@      LQ
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **LR
)@@G@@***************************** @C@@@@.               *                   LS
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *          ENDCASE            * @C@@@@LT
)@@G@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.               **LU
)@@G@@***************************** @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROCLV
)@@G@@   *0 @#@@@@ENDCASE*  NAME    @G@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)        LW
)@@G@@  . GET NESTING LEVEL OF THIS BLOCK @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M) LX
)@@G@@        . GET SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=3)=0 , G$LY
)@@G@@$GFL 1,3      . DIAGNOSE BAD NESTING@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE TABLE SILZ
)@@G@@ZE SO WE KNOW HOW MUCH FLOAT TO APPLY     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@CALOPT    EQMA
)@@G@@U       G$FLAG(K,3)<0     . SET IF CASENTRY WITH CALLING OPTION   @F@@@@MB
)@@G@@NUMCA     EQU       +G$FLAG(K,1)      . NUMBER OF CASES GIVEN     @H@@@@MC
)@@G@@CMAX(1)   EQU       -34359738367      . INIT MAX TO SMALLEST POSSIBLE NUMD
)@@G@@MBER  @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)>CMAX(1) ,CMAX(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,ME
)@@G@@4,L) . GET MAX    @H@@@@CMIN(1)   EQU       0377777777777     . INIT MINMF
)@@G@@ TO LARGEST POSSIBLE NUMBER   @H@@@@L DO NUMCA , DO G$FLAG(K,4,L)<CMIN(1MG
)@@G@@) ,CMIN(1) EQU G$FLAG(K,4,L) . GET MIN    @G@@@@JTS(1)   EQU    CMAX(1)-MH
)@@G@@CMIN(1)+1      . SET TOT TABLE SIZE=RANGE OF VAL@F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,3)=-1MI
)@@G@@ ,JTS(1) EQU JTS(1)-(CMAX(1)=G$FLAG(K,4,1))     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$MJ
)@@G@@LABL(K,0)=$                     ; IF NO CODE IN ANY CASE BLOK     @G@@@@MK
)@@G@@  , DO G$FLAG(K,5)=0                  ; AND NO REMOTE BLOX EITHER...    ML
)@@G@@@F@@@@    ,G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU 1               . TURN OFF CODE GENERATION  MM
)@@G@@@G@@@@REDUN     EQU       G$LABL(K,5)=$     . ON=> LAST CASE CLOSURE REDMN
)@@G@@UNDANT@G@@@@PRSIZ     EQU       (CALOPT=0)*(4-3*G$FLAG(K,6)) . GET PREAMMO
)@@G@@BLE SIZE    @H@@@@FLOAT     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,3)<1)*(PRSIZ+JTS(1)-REDUMP
)@@G@@N) . FLOAT FOR TABL     @G@@@@          RES       FLOAT*G$CTR(6)    . ONMQ
)@@G@@ PASS 1, APPLY FLOAT TO L.C.  @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)-FLOAT*GMR
)@@G@@$CTR(7) . ON P2, APPLY TO GLOBAL FLOAT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7)MS
)@@G@@ , DO (G$LABL(K,3)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @H@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU MT
)@@G@@  $                 . MARK ULTIMATE EXIT POINT FROM BLOCK   @G@@@@G$CTR*MU
)@@G@@(5) EQU       M-1               . UPDATE GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL     @[@@@@MV
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@        END @B@@@@/.       ********* REPEAT GROUP ********* MW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$FLAG(K,X) IS USED TO KEEPMX
)@@G@@ FLAGS THROUGOUT  @E@@@@.    THE SCOPE OF THE REPEAT BLOCK. FOR EACH X, MY
)@@G@@THE FLAG IS:@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.       1      INDEX OF 'VARY' FIELD ON SOMZ
)@@G@@URCE 'REPEAT' IMAGE     @F@@@@.       2      ON IF THERE IS <LOOP CTL> CNA
)@@G@@ODE WHICH MUST APPEAR   @D@@@@.              AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF TNB
)@@G@@HE LOOP     @E@@@@.       3      INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD IN SOURCE 'REPEAT' NC
)@@G@@IMAGE @F@@@@.       4      INDEX OF 'WHILE' FIELD ON SOURCE 'REPEAT IMAGND
)@@G@@E     @B@@@@.       5      FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL @C@@@@.       6   NE
)@@G@@   INDEX OF 'UNTIL' ON SOURCE IMAGE @B@@@@.       7      SURPRESS EVERYTNF
)@@G@@HING FLAG   @A@@@@.       8      ON=> 'LOOKFOR' FORMAT@C@@@@.       9   NG
)@@G@@   ON=> BOTTOM OF LOOP CHECKING DONE@E@@@@.       .      FLAGS USED TO CNH
)@@G@@ONTROL POSITIONING AND FLOAT: @D@@@@.      10      ON=> ENTRY CONDITION NI
)@@G@@IS JUMP TO WHILE  @B@@@@.      11      ON => SURPRESS WHILE AT TOP@B@@@@NJ
)@@G@@.      12      ON=> INVERT ESCAPE TEST    @E@@@@.      13      ON=> CLOSNK
)@@G@@E ESCAPE CLAUSE (WITH JUMP TO EXIT) @G@@@@.      14      ON=> CLOSE OTHENL
)@@G@@RWISE/UNTIL CLAUSE (WITH JUMP TO LOOP)    @C@@@@.      15      ON=> SURPNM
)@@G@@RESS WHILE AT BOTTOM    @C@@@@.      16      FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED NN
)@@G@@AT TOP@B@@@@.      17      FLOAT FOR INVERTED ESCAPE  @D@@@@.      18   NO
)@@G@@   FLOAT FOR WHILE SURPRESSED AT BOTTOM   @E@@@@.      19      ON=> CODENP
)@@G@@ IN LOOP WILL APPEAR BELOW ESCAPE   @C@@@@.      20      GLOBAL FLOAT ATNQ
)@@G@@ ENTRY TO BLOCK   @E@@@@.      21      1+FLOAT FOR INITIAL JUMP FALLTHRUNR
)@@G@@ (0=>NONE)  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.    THE ARRAY G$LABL(K,X) IS USED TO LABENS
)@@G@@L VARIOUS CONTROL @D@@@@.    POINTS IN THE GENERATED CODE.  VALUES OF X NT
)@@G@@ARE:  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.       1      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP WHILE TESNU
)@@G@@T     @D@@@@.       2      LOCATION OF TOP-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE    @F@@@@NV
)@@G@@.       3      START USER-SPECIFIED REPEATED CODE (TOP OF LOOP)   @G@@@@NW
)@@G@@.       4      LOCATION OF CONDITION TEST AT ESCAPE (0=>NO ESCAPE STMNT)NX
)@@G@@@D@@@@.       5      START USER-SPECIFIED ESCAPE CLAUSE     @D@@@@.     NY
)@@G@@  6      START USER-SPECIFIED OTHERWISE CODE    @D@@@@.       7      LOCNZ
)@@G@@ATION OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE TEST  @D@@@@.       8      LOCATION OF BOTOA
)@@G@@TOM-OF-LOOP <VARY> CODE @C@@@@.       9      START USER-SPECIFIED ATEND OB
)@@G@@CODE  @C@@@@.      10      ULTIMATE BLOCK EXIT TARGET ADDR  @[@@@@.     OC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE FOLLOWING ARCANE RULES ARE FOLLOWED IN POSITIONIOD
)@@G@@NG THE VARIOUS    @ @@@@. CODE GENERATED FOR A LOOP:  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@OE
)@@G@@. 1) <UNTIL> CODE ALWAYS APPEARS AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE LOOP     OF
)@@G@@@F@@@@.            SO WE CAN AVOID JUMPING AROUND IT AT LOOP ENTRY.     OG
)@@G@@@B@@@@. 2) <VARY>  CODE MOVES AROUND AS FOLLOWS:@G@@@@.        A)  IF THOH
)@@G@@E SENSE (UP/DOWN) IS KNOWN, THEN THE CODE IS PLACED   @G@@@@.           OI
)@@G@@ ACCORDING TO THE PREFERENCE OF THE LOOP INSTRUCTION, E.G.  @D@@@@.     OJ
)@@G@@       JGD AT THE BOTTOM, SEARCHES AT THE TOP.  @G@@@@.        B)  IF THOK
)@@G@@E SENSE IS UNKNOWN, THE CODE APPEARS AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@.           OL
)@@G@@ BOTTOM, WITH THE BRANCH SENSE APPROPRIATELY INVERTED.@G@@@@.           OM
)@@G@@ IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE PRIMARY CODE (BOTTOM), A SIGN TEST  @G@@@@.     ON
)@@G@@       IS INSERTED WHICH DETERMINES WHICH OF THE TWO VARIATIONS   @ @@@@OO
)@@G@@.            WILL BE EXECUTED.@G@@@@. 3) <WHILE> CODE ALSO MOVES AROUND.OP
)@@G@@ WE DEFINE A <WHILE> TEST WHICH IS  @G@@@@.            PERFORMED IN A SIOQ
)@@G@@NGLE INSTRUCTION WHICH HAS AN INVERSE     @G@@@@.            (I.E. A CONOR
)@@G@@DITIONAL JUMP) AS 'OPTIMIZEABLE'. POSITIONING   @E@@@@.            THEN OS
)@@G@@DEPENDS UPON OTHER CONDITIONS AS FOLLOWS- @G@@@@.            NORMAL POSIOT
)@@G@@TIONING IS AT THE BOTTOM, WITH A (ONE TIME) JUMP@H@@@@.            TO THOU
)@@G@@E WHILE TEST INSERTED AT THE TOP. IF THERE IS AN ESCAPE     @G@@@@.     OV
)@@G@@       CONDITION WHICH WOULD OTHERWISE FALL THROUGH, HOWEVER, THE @H@@@@OW
)@@G@@.            JUMP AROUND THE WHILE IS AVOIDED BY PUTTING IT AT THE TOP AOX
)@@G@@ND    @H@@@@.            INVERTING THE ESCAPE TEST ACCORDINGLY. IF THEREOY
)@@G@@ IS NO <VARY>     @G@@@@.            CODE AT THE PHYSICAL BOTTOM OF THE OZ
)@@G@@LOOP, AND THE WHILE     @G@@@@.            TEST IS OPTIMIZEABLE, THEN THPA
)@@G@@E INITIAL JUMP TO THE WHILE   @G@@@@.            TEST IS REPLACED BY THEPB
)@@G@@ TEST ITSELF. IN THIS CASE, THE     @G@@@@.            TEST WILL APPEAR PC
)@@G@@AT BOTH THE TOP AND BOTTOM OF THE LOOP.   @E@@@@. 4) ESCAPE  AN ESCAPE TPD
)@@G@@EST CAN BE MODIFIED BOTH BECAUSE OF @G@@@@.            THE ABOVE, OR BECPE
)@@G@@AUSE THE CLAUSE IS EMPTY. IF THE CODE     @F@@@@.            FOLLOWING TPF
)@@G@@HE TEST IS NOT IN THE LOOP (I.E. IS A NON-@F@@@@.            VACUOUS ESCPG
)@@G@@APE CLAUSE OR IS THE END OF THE LOOP),    @F@@@@.            THE ESCAPE PH
)@@G@@TEST BRANCHES TO STAY IN THE LOOP. IF     @G@@@@.            THE FOLLOWIPI
)@@G@@NG CODE IS IN THE LOOP (I.E. VACUOUS ESCAPE     @G@@@@.            AND NPJ
)@@G@@ON-VACUOUS OTHERWISE), THEN THE SENSE IS REVERSED     @F@@@@.           PK
)@@G@@ SO THAT THE BRANCH CONDITION GOES COMPLETELY OUT OF  @^@@@@.           PL
)@@G@@ THE BLOCK. @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               **************************PM
)@@G@@***** @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.     PN
)@@G@@          *           REPEAT            * @C@@@@.               *       PO
)@@G@@                      * @C@@@@.               **************************PP
)@@G@@***** @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *12@]@@@@REPEAT* NAME@[@@@@.     PQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(1)+1        . BUMP BLOCK COUNTER  @F@@@@PR
)@@G@@G$CTR*(1) EQU       K                 . SAVE UPDATED BLOCK COUNT  @F@@@@PS
)@@G@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)+1        . BUMP GLOBAL NESTING LEVEL @F@@@@PT
)@@G@@G$CTR*(5) EQU       M                 . SAVE NEW NESTING LEVEL    @F@@@@PU
)@@G@@G$SEQN*(M) EQU      K                 . SAVE SEQ NO OF THIS BLOCK @F@@@@PV
)@@G@@G$TYPE*(M) EQU      4                 . SET BLOCK TYPE TO REPEAT  @[@@@@PW
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. APPLY FLOATS TO LABELS IN THIS BLOCK    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@PX
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(6) , GO G$$R10           . ON PASS 1, FLOAT MEANS NOTHING     PY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,20) EQU   G$CTR(2)          . SAVE INITIAL FPZ
)@@G@@LOAT  @H@@@@ESCF      EQU       G$LABL(K,4)       . REMEMBER ENTRY VALUEQA
)@@G@@ OF ESCAPE FLAG   @H@@@@FALLF     EQU       (G$FLAG(K,21)>0)*(1-G$FLAG(KQB
)@@G@@,21)) . GET FALLTHRU FLOAT    @H@@@@N DO 10 ,G$LABL*(K,N) EQU G$LABL(K,NQC
)@@G@@)+G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . GLOBAL, JUMPENTR@I@@@@N DO 9 ,G$LABL*(K,N+1) EQD
)@@G@@QU G$LABL(K,N+1)+G$FLAG(K,16)+FALLF . SURPRESS TOP WHILE    @G@@@@N DO 6QE
)@@G@@ ,G$LABL*(K,N+4) EQU G$LABL(K,N+4)+G$FLAG(K,17) . ESCAPE INVERSION@G@@@@QF
)@@G@@N DO 5 ,G$LABL*(K,N+5) EQU G$LABL(K,N+5)+G$FLAG(K,13) . ESCAPE CLOSURE  QG
)@@G@@@I@@@@N DO 4 ,G$LABL*(K,N+6) EQU G$LABL(K,N+6)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,5) QH
)@@G@@. OTHER/UNTIL     @G@@@@N DO 3 ,G$LABL*(K,N+7) EQU G$LABL(K,N+7)+G$FLAG(QI
)@@G@@K,18) . BOTTOM WHILE    @E@@@@ DO ESCF=0 ,G$LABL*(K,4) EQU 0 . IF NO ESCQJ
)@@G@@APE, RESTORE FLAG @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. ***** SYNTAX ANALYSIS ***** @[@@@@QK
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$R10*   NAME    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@C(1)      EQQL
)@@G@@U  1                      . INITIALIZE CURRENT FIELD COUNTER@G@@@@KW(1) QM
)@@G@@    EQU  P(1,1)                 . AND CURRENT LEADING KEYWORD     @[@@@@QN
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.               EXAMINE 'WHILE' FIELD     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@QO
)@@G@@G$$R50* NAME                          . MARK START OF WHILE TEST  @G@@@@QP
)@@G@@WI      EQU    KW(1)=WHILE            . FIELD INDEX OF 'WHILE' OR ZERO  QQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,4) EQU WI                 . REMEMBER INDEX IN CASE DEFERQR
)@@G@@RED   @C@@@@ DO WI=0 , GO G$$R59 . IF NO 'WHILE', WE'RE DONE@C@@@@WYNOT QS
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) .    @H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(QT
)@@G@@3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))**(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @F@@@@C(1)    EQU QU
)@@G@@   3+WYNOT+2*WC                 . UPDATE FIELD POINTER@F@@@@KW(1)   EQU QV
)@@G@@   P(C(1),1)              . KEYWORD FOR NEXT FIELD    @H@@@@G$$R59* NAMEQW
)@@G@@                          . END PROCESSING OF 'WHILE' CONDITION   @[@@@@QX
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@.       EXAMINE <LOOP CTL> FIELD, LOADING REGS IF NECESSARY QY
)@@G@@@D@@@@. NOTE: THE <LOOP CONTROL> ANALYSIS SUBROUTINE G$$LAN @E@@@@. SETSQZ
)@@G@@ THE FLAGS FI(X) USED BELOW.  FOR THEIR DEFINITIONS,  @ @@@@. SEE THE CORA
)@@G@@DE FOR G$$LAN     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.       SEE IF THIS IS A HARDWARE SERB
)@@G@@ARCH SPEC   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$R60* NAME                          . MARC
)@@G@@RK START PROCESSING OF <LOOP CNTRL> SP    @F@@@@ DO (KW(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , RD
)@@G@@GO G$$R61 . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO TRY 'VARY' @I@@@@VI      EQU    C(1)+2   RE
)@@G@@              . IN THIS FMT, 'VARY' FOLLOWS LOOKFOR AND     @F@@@@ DO (PRF
)@@G@@(VI,1)>VARY)++(P(VI,1)<LOOKFOR) , G$$EFL 2,010 . CHECK IT   @G@@@@P(VI,1RG
)@@G@@) EQU    LOOKFOR                . FORCE KEYWORD FOR USE BY G$$LAN @H@@@@RH
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,8) EQU 1                 . SET FLAG ALLOWING UNCONDITIONAL ESCRI
)@@G@@APE   @A@@@@ GO G$$R62 . THEN GO PROCESS IT     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$$R61RJ
)@@G@@* NAME                          . TRY A NORMAL 'VARY' FIELD @F@@@@VI    RK
)@@G@@  EQU    C(1)*((KW(1)>JMGI-1)**(KW(1)<VARY+1)) . FIELD INDEX@D@@@@ DO VIRL
)@@G@@=0 , GO G$$R69 . SKIP THIS IF FIELD NOT GIVEN   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R62RM
)@@G@@* NAME@E@@@@        G$$LAN                . ANALYZE THE LOOP CTL FIELD  RN
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,2) EQU FI(5)              . REMEMBER IF IT HAS DEFERRED RO
)@@G@@CODE  @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,3) EQU FI(3)              . NOTE FIELD IN WHICH 'TRP
)@@G@@O' SPEC APPEARS   @H@@@@C(1)    EQU    FI(7)+1                . SET FIELRQ
)@@G@@D OF NEXT (I.E. UNTIL) GROUP  @F@@@@KW(1)   EQU    P(C(1),1)            RR
)@@G@@  . AND ITS FUNCT FLAG WORD   @]@@@@G$$R69* NAME@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,1) EQU VRS
)@@G@@I                 . SAVE INDEX OF VARY FIELD, IF ANY  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@RT
)@@G@@.              SCAN 'UNTIL' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,6) EQU  RU
)@@G@@  C(1)*(KW(1)=UNTIL). EXTERNALIZE SO WE KNOW IT WAS GIVEN   @[@@@@.     RV
)@@G@@@A@@@@.     ***** CODE GENERATION *****   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$R80* NAMERW
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,10) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,7) . ENTER WITH JUMP TO WRX
)@@G@@HILE/VARY   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,10) . APPLY FLOARY
)@@G@@T, IF ANY   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,1)  EQU   $        . MARK START RZ
)@@G@@OF WHILE TEST     @H@@@@ DO (WI>0)**1-G$FLAG(K,11) , G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,WSA
)@@G@@YNOT G$LABL(K,9) . GEN IT     @D@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+((WI>0)SB
)@@G@@**G$FLAG(K,11)) . @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,16) . AND SC
)@@G@@APPLY THE FLOAT   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. GENERATE LOOP <VARY> CODE, IF ANY SD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,2)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF 2NDARY LSE
)@@G@@OOP CHECK   @C@@@@ DO VI>0 , ; IF THERE IS LOOP VARIATION CODE    @G@@@@SF
)@@G@@ DO (P(VI,1)=LOOKFOR)++((FI(5)=FI(6))=0) , ; AND SOME OR ALL IS HERE    SG
)@@G@@@E@@@@        G$$LGE VI,FI(3),FI(4) G$LABL(K,9),1 . GENERATE IT   @F@@@@SH
)@@G@@ DO G$LABL(K,2)<$ ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0 . IF ANY, CAN'T FALL THRU  @[@@@@SI
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. FINAL CLEANUP   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          G$$SVA        SJ
)@@G@@              . SAVE ARGS FOR LATER @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 0            SK
)@@G@@     . CLEAR ENDCHECK DONE FLAG     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,3)SL
)@@G@@=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,3)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,3)  EQU   $         . MARKSM
)@@G@@ START OF USER'S CODE   @[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@SN
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.               ******************************* SO
)@@G@@@C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@.           SP
)@@G@@    *           ESCAPE            * @C@@@@.               *             SQ
)@@G@@                * @C@@@@.               ******************************* SR
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@P       PROC   *4 @#@@@@ESCAPE*  NAME     SS
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQU       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NEST
)@@G@@STING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQU       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NSU
)@@G@@O OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (G$TYPE(M)=4)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTINGSV
)@@G@@ ERRORS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,4)=$)=0 , G$$DSW
)@@G@@FL G$LABL(K,4)    @E@@@@G$LABL*(K,4)  EQU   $        . MARK START OF ESCSX
)@@G@@APE TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@TBOT      EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)>0     . ONSY
)@@G@@ => TEST AT LOGICAL BOTTOM (UNTIL)  @H@@@@TTOP      EQU       (G$FLAG(K,SZ
)@@G@@1)>0)++(G$FLAG(K,4)>0) . ON => TESTS AT LGL TOP @H@@@@ DO TTOP**TBOT , GTA
)@@G@@$$GFL 2,1               . CAN'T HAVE CAKE AND EAT IT TOO    @G@@@@G$FLAGTB
)@@G@@*(K,8) EQU G$FLAG(K,8)**(P(1)=0) . UNCONDITIONAL (LOOKFOR) FLAG   @G@@@@TC
)@@G@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . UNCONDITIONAL => LEAP OUT TD
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,8) , GO G$$E10 . THEN GO CLEAN UP  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@TE
)@@G@@ DO (P(1,1)=WHEN)=0 , G$$EFL 3,4 . SYNTAX ERROR IF NO 'WHEN'@F@@@@WHENOTTF
)@@G@@    EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1)=NOT) . ON FOR NOT CONDITION @H@@@@CFLG  TG
)@@G@@  EQU    P>3+WHENOT                      . ON FOR COMPOUND CONDITION    TH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. ON PASS 1, BOTH SENSES OF THE TEST ARE GENERATED, SOTI
)@@G@@ WE CAN     @F@@@@. DETERMINE THE FLOAT TO USE IF REVERSAL OCCURS. ON PATJ
)@@G@@SS 2, ONLY  @A@@@@. THE DESIRED SENSE IS GENERATED    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@TK
)@@G@@ DO G$CTR(6)++G$FLAG(K,12) , ; PASS 1 ALWAYS, PASS 2 IF REVERSED  @I@@@@TL
)@@G@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,WHENOT G$LABL(K,1+5*G$FLAG(K,19)) . JUMP=> KEEPTM
)@@G@@ LOOPIN     @F@@@@SIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(K,4)     . LENGTH OF REVETN
)@@G@@RSED TEST   @E@@@@          RES      0-G$CTR(6)*SIZE . THEN RES TEST AWATO
)@@G@@Y     @H@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$CTR(7)+G$FLAG(K,7) . KEEP G$$TP
)@@G@@TST CTR IN PHASE  @H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,12)++G$FLAG(K,7)=0 , ; PASS1 ALWAYSTQ
)@@G@@, 2 IF NOT REVERSED/SURPRESSED@G@@@@    G$$TST 2+WHENOT,CFLG,1-WHENOT G$TR
)@@G@@LABL(K,10) . JUMP=> EXIT FROM LOOP  @E@@@@WIZE      EQU       $-G$LABL(KTS
)@@G@@,4)     . SIZE OF 2ND TEST    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,TT
)@@G@@7) EQU    SIDE(1)           . PASS 1: SET SIDE EFFECT @H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQTU
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,17) . PASS2: APPLY FLOAT FOR ENCLOSED BL@E@@@@TV
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU  SIZE-WIZE . PASS 1: GET FLOAT, 2=>NOISE  @[@@@@.     TW
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$E10*   NAME    @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,5)  EQU   $           . MARK STATX
)@@G@@RT OF USER'S ESCAPE CODE@]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@TY
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * TZ
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *         OTHERWISE UA
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@UB
)@@G@@.               *           ATEND             * @C@@@@.               * UC
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *           ENDREP  UD
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@UE
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     UF
)@@G@@@#@@@@Y       PROC   *1 @^@@@@OTHERWISE* NAME     0   @^@@@@ATEND*    NAUG
)@@G@@ME      1   @^@@@@ENDREP*   NAME      2   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@M         EQUH
)@@G@@U       G$CTR(5)          . GET CURRENT NESTING LEVEL @G@@@@K         EQUI
)@@G@@U       G$SEQN(M)         . AND SEQUENCE NO OF THIS BLOCK   @E@@@@ DO (GUJ
)@@G@@$TYPE(M)=4)=0 , G$$GFL 1,3 . CATCH NESTING ERRORS     @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(KUK
)@@G@@,5)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,5) EQU $ . FIXUP FOR MISSING ESCAPE  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@UL
)@@G@@. CLOSE DANGLING ESCAPE, IF REQUIRED@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,13) ,UM
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,10) . PASS2: LEAP OUT    @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU     UN
)@@G@@  G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,13) . APPLY CLOSURE FLOAT   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU UO
)@@G@@  0                 . REMEMBER WE'VE DONE THIS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. ****UP
)@@G@@ OTHERWISE GETS OFF THE TRAIN HERE ...    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO Y(0,0)>0UQ
)@@G@@ , GO G$$Z10              . IF ATEND OR ENDREP, KEEP MOVING @H@@@@ DO G$UR
)@@G@@LABL(K,4)=0 , G$$GFL 2,2            . OTHERWISE INVALID IF NO ESCAPE    US
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,6)=$)=0 , G$$DFL G$LABL(K,6) 1  @F@@@@UT
)@@G@@G$LABL*(K,6)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF 'OTHERWISE' CODE    @B@@@@UU
)@@G@@ DO 1 , END         . THAT'S ALL FOLKS    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. **** ATENDUV
)@@G@@/ENDREP LUMBER ONWARD...@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         CLOSE LOOP: GEN CTL UW
)@@G@@CODE WHICH PREFERS PHYSICAL BOTTOM  @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z10*   NAME    UX
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,9) , GO G$$Z50          . IF ITS TUESDAY, THIS MUST BUY
)@@G@@E ENDREP    @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,9) EQU 1                 . REMEMBER WE'VE BEUZ
)@@G@@EN HERE     @F@@@@ DO G$LABL(K,6)=0 ,G$LABL*(K,6) EQU $ . DEFAULT START VA
)@@G@@OF OTHERWISE@G@@@@KK        EQU       G$CTR(3)          . GET POINTER INVB
)@@G@@TO ARGSAVE STACK  @H@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I) ,P(I,J) EQU +VC
)@@G@@G$ARGS(KK,I,J) . GET ARGS     @E@@@@I DO G$ARGS(KK) ,J DO G$ARGS(KK,I)  VD
)@@G@@  ; FOR ALL SUBFIELDS   @F@@@@  , DO G$ARGS(KK,I,*J) ,P(I,J) EQU *P(I,J)VE
)@@G@@ . PRESERVE ASTERISKS   @G@@@@G$CTR*(3) EQU       KK-1              . THVF
)@@G@@EN MOVE STACK POINTER BACK    @I@@@@ DO (Y(0,0)=1)**(G$ARGS(KK)=0) , G$$VG
)@@G@@GFL 2,3        . ATEND UNREACHABLE IF NO ARG    @G@@@@LL      EQU    G$FVH
)@@G@@LAG(K,2)          . ON IF ANY <VARY> CODE WAS DEFERRED@H@@@@DFER      EQVI
)@@G@@U       LL++(G$FLAG(K,4)>0) . ON IF DEFFERED CODE OF ANY TYPE     @[@@@@VJ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE UNTIL CONDITIONS. THEY CAN HAVE EITHER BRANCH SENSEVK
)@@G@@:     @G@@@@.   A) IF WHILE/VARY CODE WILL FOLLOW, UNTIL SUCCESS LEAPS TVL
)@@G@@O ATEND     @E@@@@.   B) IF NOT (A), THEN UNTIL FAILURE LEAPS TO TOP OF VM
)@@G@@LOOP  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@UNORG                                 . MARK ORIVN
)@@G@@GIN OF UNTIL TESTS, IF ANY    @G@@@@UN        EQU       G$FLAG(K,6)     VO
)@@G@@. GET INDEX INTO P OF UNTIL SPECS   @B@@@@ DO UN=0 , GO G$$Z30          VP
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@KILL      EQU       G$CTR(7)**G$FLAG(K,7) . ON IF SURPVQ
)@@G@@RESSING ALL CODE  @G@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,5) . APPLYVR
)@@G@@ UNTIL SURPRESS FLOAT   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+KILL     . COVS
)@@G@@UNT SURPRESSED UNTIL    @E@@@@ DO KILL , GO G$$Z30                   . AVT
)@@G@@ND FORGET THE REST@F@@@@UNN       EQU       (P(UN+1)=1)**(P(UN+1,1)=NOT)VU
)@@G@@ . SET NOT FLAG   @I@@@@UNC       EQU       (P(UN+UNN+2)=1)**((P(UN+UNN+VV
)@@G@@2,1)=OR)++(P(UN+UNN+2,1)=AND)) .    @D@@@@  G$$TST UN+UNN+1,UNC,DFER--UNVW
)@@G@@N G$LABL(K,1+9*DFER)    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. CLOSE DANGLING OTHERWISE/UNTVX
)@@G@@IL    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$Z30*   NAME    @G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU    UNORVY
)@@G@@G-$           . GET FLOAT FOR SURPRESSED UNTIL  @E@@@@ DO G$FLAG(K,14) ,VZ
)@@G@@ I$ 074,04,,,,G$LABL(K,1) . JUMP TO TOP   @F@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTWA
)@@G@@R(2)+G$FLAG(K,14) . FLOAT FOLLOWING CODE  @E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   0   WB
)@@G@@              . REMEMBER WE DID THIS@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. HANDLE WHILE CONWC
)@@G@@DITIONS.  THESE CAN BE SURPRESSED OR CAN BRANCH TWO   @F@@@@. WAYS; FORTWD
)@@G@@UNATELY, THE BRANCH SENSE IS KNOWN ON PASS 1 (LL):    @F@@@@.  A) IF <VAWE
)@@G@@RY> CODE FOLLOWS, THEN WHILE FAILURE JUMPS TO ATEND   @D@@@@.  B) IF NOTWF
)@@G@@ (A), WHILE SUCCESS JUMPS TO TOP OF LOOP  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,7)WG
)@@G@@  EQU   $        . MARK START OF BOTTOM-OF-LOOP WHILE @B@@@@. NOTE: IF WWH
)@@G@@HILE EXISTS, ITS ALWAYS SPEC 1@B@@@@WYNOT     EQU       (P(2)=1)**(P(2,1WI
)@@G@@)=NOT)@H@@@@WC        EQU       ((P(3+WYNOT,1)=OR)++(P(3+WYNOT,1)=AND))*WJ
)@@G@@*(P(3+WYNOT)=1)   @G@@@@ DO (G$FLAG(K,4)>0)**1-G$FLAG(K,15) , ; IF EXISTWK
)@@G@@S AND NOT SURPRESSED-   @D@@@@        G$$TST 2+WYNOT,WC,LL=WYNOT G$LABL(WL
)@@G@@K,2+7*LL)   @F@@@@G$CTR*(4) EQU       G$CTR(4)+G$FLAG(K,15) . COUNT SURPWM
)@@G@@RESSED WHILE@H@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$CTR(2)+G$FLAG(K,18) . APPLY WHILWN
)@@G@@E SURPRESSION FLOAT     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. GENERATE <VARY> CODE  @[@@@@WO
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,8)  EQU   $        . MARK START OF BOTTOM OF LOOP WP
)@@G@@VARY  @H@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++(G$FLAG(K,1)>0) WQ
)@@G@@. NOTE SIDE EFFEC @D@@@@ DO LL , G$$LGE G$FLAG(K,1),G$FLAG(K,3) G$LABL(KWR
)@@G@@,3)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO G$CTR(6) ,G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU G$FLAG(K,7)++SIDEWS
)@@G@@(1) . NOTE SIDE EFFECTS @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,9)=$)=0 , G$$DWT
)@@G@@FL G$LABL(K,9) 2  @F@@@@G$LABL*(K,9)  EQU   $         . MARK START OF USWU
)@@G@@ER ATEND CODE     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. END PROCESSING OF LOOP TERMINATIONWV
)@@G@@ CONDITIONS @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO Y(0,0)=1 , END  . ATEND STATEMENT FINIWW
)@@G@@SHES UP HERE@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. CLEANUP FOR ENDREP STATEMENT@[@@@@.     WX
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$Z50*   NAME    @E@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , DO (G$LABL(K,10)=$)=0 , G$$WY
)@@G@@DFL G$LABL(K,10) 3@D@@@@G$LABL*(K,10) EQU   $          . SET BLOCK EXIT WZ
)@@G@@LABEL @E@@@@G$CTR*(2) EQU       G$FLAG(K,20)      . RESTORE GLOBAL FLOATXA
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$CTR*(5) EQU  M-1                    . DECREMENT GLOBAL NESTING LXB
)@@G@@EVEL  @C@@@@ DO G$CTR(7) , END . ON PASS 2, WE'RE DONE HERE @[@@@@.     XC
)@@G@@@E@@@@. ***** PASS 1 ONLY: DETERMINE POSITIONING AND OPTIMIZATIONS@[@@@@XD
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAGS INDICATING WHETHER USER PUT ANY CODEXE
)@@G@@ IN SPECIFIC CLAUSES    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ESCAPP    EQU       G$LABL(K,4XF
)@@G@@)>0     . ON=>ESCAPE STMNT APPEARED @H@@@@RVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,3XG
)@@G@@)=G$LABL(K,5-ESCAPP) . ON=> NOTHING AFTER REPEAT@H@@@@EVAC      EQU     XH
)@@G@@  G$LABL(K,5)=G$LABL(K,6) . ON=> USER ESCAPE CLAUSE VACUOUS @H@@@@UOVAC XI
)@@G@@    EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7)+G$FLAG(K,5) . ON=> NO USER 'OTHER XJ
)@@G@@@I@@@@OVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,6)=G$LABL(K,7) . ON=> EMPTY OTHERWISEXK
)@@G@@/UNTIL CLAUSE     @H@@@@AVAC      EQU       G$LABL(K,9)=G$LABL(K,10) . OXL
)@@G@@N=> USER ATEND CLAUSE VACUOUS @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NOKILL    EQU       G$FLXM
)@@G@@AG(K,7)++1-(RVAC**EVAC**UOVAC**AVAC) .    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@VATBOT    EQXN
)@@G@@U       G$FLAG(K,2)       . ON=> SOME (OR ALL) <VARY> AT BOTTOM   @H@@@@XO
)@@G@@LOOBOT    EQU       VATBOT++1-OVAC  . ON=> SOME LOOP CODE WILL BE AT BOTXP
)@@G@@TOM   @G@@@@EFOLLO    EQU       LOOBOT++1-AVAC  . ON=> SOMETHING WILL FOXQ
)@@G@@LLOW ESCAPE @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. COMPUTE OPTIMUM POSITIONING OF WHILE (CAXR
)@@G@@N BE TOP, BOTTOM, OR BOTH)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@WHSPEC    EQU       G$FLXS
)@@G@@AG(K,4)>0     . ON IF WHILE SPECIFICATION GIVEN @H@@@@WONET     EQU     XT
)@@G@@  1=G$LABL(K,2)-G$LABL(K,1) . ON => WHILE IS ONE INST AT T  @G@@@@WONEB XU
)@@G@@    EQU       1=G$LABL(K,8)-G$LABL(K,7) . ON => ONE INSTR AT BOT  @[@@@@XV
)@@G@@.     @H@@@@WHIBOT    EQU       (EFOLLO++1-ESCAPP)**NOKILL . ON=> IF WHIXW
)@@G@@LE, ALLOW AT BOTTO@I@@@@WHISBO    EQU       WHSPEC**WHIBOT    . ON => WHXX
)@@G@@ILE WILL REALLY APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @H@@@@WHITOP    EQU       (WONET**WOXY
)@@G@@NEB**1-VATBOT++1-WHIBOT)**NOKILL . 0N=>ALLOW    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SET XZ
)@@G@@GLOBAL SURPRESS FLAGS AND FLOATS FOR WHILE OPTIMIZATION     @[@@@@.     YA
)@@G@@@E@@@@G$FLAG*(K,11) EQU   WHSPEC**1-WHITOP . ON => SURPRESS AT TOP@H@@@@YB
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,16) EQU   (G$LABL(K,1)-G$LABL(K,2))*G$FLAG(K,11) . TOP SURPRESYC
)@@G@@S FLOA@F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,15) EQU   WHSPEC**1-WHIBOT . ON=> SURPRESS AT BOTTYD
)@@G@@OM    @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,18) EQU   (G$LABL(K,7)-G$LABL(K,8))*G$FLAG(K,15) .YE
)@@G@@ BOT SURPRESS FLOA@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. COMPUTE VARIOUS FLAGS FOR ESCAPE OYF
)@@G@@PTIMIZATION AND CLOSURE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,19) EQU   LOOBOT++WHYG
)@@G@@ISBO    . ON=>LOOP CODE FOLLOWS     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,12) EQU   (G$FLAG(K,YH
)@@G@@19)**EVAC=0)**NOKILL . ON=>JUMP TO KEEP GOING   @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,17) EQU YI
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,17)*G$FLAG(K,12) . SET FLOAT TO USE  @F@@@@ DO 1-NOKILL ,G$FLYJ
)@@G@@AG*(K,17) EQU ESCAPP*(G$LABL(K,4)-G$LABL(K,5)) .@I@@@@G$FLAG*(K,13) EQU YK
)@@G@@  NOKILL**ESCAPP**G$FLAG(K,12)**(EFOLLO++WHISBO) . CLOSURE FLAG   @[@@@@YL
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. SET FLAG FOR GENERATION OF JUMP TO WHILE/VARY AT TOP (INITYM
)@@G@@IAL ENTRY)  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU   (VATBOT++1-WHITOP**WHSYN
)@@G@@PEC)**NOKILL . ON=> GEN ENTRY JUMP  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. FOR IMMEDIATE JGYO
)@@G@@D LOOPS WE WON'T JUMP. FOR NOW, WE WON'T CHECK FOR    @G@@@@. PRESENCE OYP
)@@G@@F WHILE AT TOP, BUT WILL TURN OFF THIS OPTIMIZATION IF THERE@G@@@@. IS AYQ
)@@G@@NY WHILE AT ALL. IN ADDITION, ONLY JGD'S NOW SET THE OPTIMIZATION @G@@@@YR
)@@G@@. FLAG, SO THERE WILL BE NO FLOATING. WHEN TLEM'S AND JMGI'S ARE DONE,  YS
)@@G@@@G@@@@. SURPRESSION OF SOME REGISTER LOAD CODE WILL CAUSE FLOAT WHICH WIYT
)@@G@@LL    @C@@@@. NEED TO BE COMPENSATED FOR AT THIS POINT.     @[@@@@.     YU
)@@G@@@G@@@@CANFAL    EQU       1-WHSPEC**(G$FLAG(K,21)>0) . ON => WE CAN FALLYV
)@@G@@ THRU @H@@@@ DO CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,10) EQU 0       . SO FORGET ABOUT JUMPYW
)@@G@@ING TO BOTTOM     @G@@@@ DO 1-CANFAL ,G$FLAG*(K,21) EQU 0     . CLEAR FLYX
)@@G@@AG IF WE CAN'T FALL THRU@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. CLOSE OTHERWISE/UNTIL WITH JYY
)@@G@@UMP IF NOT FOLLOWED BY TESTS WHICH DO IT  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@UNTOP     EQYZ
)@@G@@U       (G$FLAG(K,6)>0)**(VATBOT++WHSPEC=0) . UNTIL JUMPS TO TOP  @G@@@@ZA
)@@G@@G$FLAG*(K,14) EQU   (OVAC**ESCAPP++WHISBO++VATBOT++UNTOP=0)**NOKILL .   ZB
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG*(K,5) EQU G$FLAG(K,5)*(1-NOKILL) . ADJUST UNTIL SURPRESSIONZC
)@@G@@ FLOAT@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. SET LC TO REFLECT WHAT IT WILL BE ON PASS 2 BYZD
)@@G@@ APPLYING FLOATS TO IT  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@G$FLAG*(K,7) EQU    1-NOKILL  ZE
)@@G@@        . SET FLAG TO KILL ALL CODE @H@@@@          RES       G$FLAG(K,5ZF
)@@G@@)+G$FLAG(K,10)+G$FLAG(K,16)+G$FLAG(K,17)+ ;     @E@@@@                  ZG
)@@G@@  G$FLAG(K,13)+G$FLAG(K,14)+G$FLAG(K,18)  @]@@@@        END @C@@@@/.    ZH
)@@G@@     ******** EXEC REQUEST GROUP *********@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @C@@@@ZI
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @C@@@@.               * ZJ
)@@G@@                            * @C@@@@.               *          -READ-$  ZK
)@@G@@          * @C@@@@.               *                             * @C@@@@ZL
)@@G@@.               ******************************* @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     ZM
)@@G@@@#@@@@P       PROC   *1 @#@@@@READ$*  NAME   015@#@@@@READA$*  NAME  042ZN
)@@G@@@^@@@@TREAD$*  NAME  0102     @^@@@@AREAD$*  NAME  0166     @^@@@@AREADAZO
)@@G@@$*  NAME 0167     @^@@@@ATREAD$*  NAME 0170     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (PZP
)@@G@@(0,0)=015)++(P(0,0)=0166) , GO G$$D20 . NO PKT IF READ$,AREAD$    @G@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@PKTOFF  EQU    (P(0,0)=0102)++(P(0,0)=0170) . OFFSET FOR TREAD$ PACKETS ZR
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO P(1)=0 , GO G$$D10                . IF PKT ADDR NOT GIVEN, GO ZS
)@@G@@KLUDGE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. GENERATE CODE FOR CASE WHERE PACKET ADDR EXPLIZT
)@@G@@CITLY GIVEN---    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@        LA,U   A0,$+5               ZU
)@@G@@  . GET EOF ADDR (SKIP AFTER READ$) @H@@@@        I$     06,H1,A0,P(1,2)ZV
)@@G@@,P(1,*1),P(1,1)+PKTOFF . STASH IN PACKET (FIELD @G@@@@        I$     026ZW
)@@G@@,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM PKT ADR   @E@@@@ GO G$$D99  ZX
)@@G@@                          . GO GENERATE THE READ@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. IF PZY
)@@G@@ACKET ADDR CAN VARY AT XQT TIME, WE MUST FARBLE A BIT @[@@@@.     @]@@@@ZZ
)@@G@@G$$D10* NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,0,A1                . TEMP SAVE A1 LAA
)@@G@@OWER IN A0 UPPER  @F@@@@        LXM,U  A1,$+7                 . GET ADDRAB
)@@G@@ OF EOF RETURN    @E@@@@        SA,H1  A1,PKTOFF,A0           . EOF ADDRAC
)@@G@@ TO PACKET  @G@@@@        LSSC   A0,18                  . ALIGN OLD A1 LAD
)@@G@@OWER IN A0 LOWER  @E@@@@        LXM,U  A1,0,A0                . RESTORE AE
)@@G@@A1 LOWER    @E@@@@        SSL    A0,18                  . REALIGN PACKETAF
)@@G@@ ADDR @E@@@@ GO G$$D99                            . THEN GO DO THE ER   AG
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. GENERATE CALL FOR IO FUNCTS WHICH DO NOT USE PACKETSAH
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D20* NAME@G@@@@        LXI,U  A0,$+(P(1)>0)+3      AI
)@@G@@  . SET EOF TO SKIP AFTER READ$     @H@@@@ DO P(1)>0 ,         I$     02AJ
)@@G@@6,U,A0,P(1,2),2*P(1,*2)+P(1,*1),P(1,1) . LXM BUF@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$D99AK
)@@G@@* NAME@D@@@@        ER     P(0,0)                 . DO THE FUNC   @E@@@@AL
)@@G@@        I$     074,04,,,,$+2          . NORMAL EXIT HERE    @G@@@@      AM
)@@G@@  AA,U   A0,0400000             . IF EOF, SET LOWORDER SIGN BIT   @]@@@@AN
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @D@@@@/.   ****** UTILITIES FOR CONDITION TESTINAO
)@@G@@G *******   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************************AP
)@@G@@********************    @F@@@@.     *                                   AQ
)@@G@@                   *    @F@@@@.     *       G$$CAN : ANALYZE A SIMPLE COAR
)@@G@@NDITION FIELD      *    @F@@@@.     *                                   AS
)@@G@@                   *    @F@@@@.     ************************************AT
)@@G@@********************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@. DEFINE ARRAYS FOAU
)@@G@@R OPTIMIZATION OF TYPE 1 TESTS ON REGISTERS INTO TYPE 3     @[@@@@.     AV
)@@G@@@#@@@@          DEF     @F@@@@G$ALTT(NE)  EQU     NONZ              . NOAW
)@@G@@T EQUAL ZERO IS NONZERO @E@@@@G$ALTT(EQ)  EQU     ZERO              . EQAX
)@@G@@UAL ZERO IS ZERO  @ @@@@G$ALTT(DNE) EQU     DNONZ     @ @@@@G$ALTT(DEQ) AY
)@@G@@EQU     DZERO     @F@@@@G$ALTT(LT)  EQU     NEG               . LESS THAAZ
)@@G@@N ZERO IS NEGATIVE@G@@@@G$ALTT(GE)  EQU     POS               . GTR OR EBA
)@@G@@QUAL ZERO IS POSITIVE   @#@@@@Z       PROC   *1 @#@@@@G$$CAN*  NAME     BB
)@@G@@@H@@@@I       EQU    Z(1,1)                 . GET INDEX TO FIELD BEING ABC
)@@G@@NALYZED     @F@@@@K       EQU    Z(1,2)                 . GET ITS ORDER BD
)@@G@@IN THE TEST @ @@@@. DETERMINE TYPE OF CONDITION @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)>0  ,N(1BE
)@@G@@) EQU 1     @ @@@@ DO P(I,2)=IN ,N(1) EQU 2     @A@@@@ DO P(I,2)=IS ,N(1BF
)@@G@@) EQU 3+2*(P(I)=4)@ @@@@ DO P(I)=1    ,N(1) EQU 4     @ @@@@ DO P(I,1)=CBG
)@@G@@HANNEL ,N(1) EQU 6@F@@@@ DO N(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,1               . E-FLAG IBH
)@@G@@F UNKNOWN TYPE    @F@@@@ DO N(1)<3 , G$$DCU,2 I,3             . DECODE EBI
)@@G@@QUF'D U-SPECS     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. TRY TO CHANGE TEST TO A MORE OPTIMBJ
)@@G@@AL ONE THAN SPECIFIED   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (N(1)=2)**G$AMPR , GO G$$ABK
)@@G@@10      . REG STATUS NEEDS RELOCATION FUNC &(X) @E@@@@U16     EQU     (PBL
)@@G@@(I,5)<016)++(P(I,4)>0)++P(I,*3)++P(I,*4)  @E@@@@ DO (N(1)>1)++U16 , GO GBM
)@@G@@$$A30 . VALUE TESTS NEED IMMEDIATES @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. IMMEDIATE LE OR BN
)@@G@@GT CAN BE ALTERED TO LT OR GE...    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PI3       EQU     BO
)@@G@@  P(I,3)            . PI3 IS UFIELD @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,PI3 EQU $AP(PI3)BP
)@@G@@        . IF MASM, REMOVE RELOCATABLE PART@C@@@@NEGEQU    EQU       (P(IBQ
)@@G@@,5)=017)**(PI3>0377777) @E@@@@OFVAL     EQU       0377777+0400000*((P(I,BR
)@@G@@5)=016)++NEGEQU)  @F@@@@FUDGE     EQU       ((LT-LE)*(P(I,2)=LE)+(GE-GT)BS
)@@G@@*(P(I,2)=GT))* ;  @F@@@@                    (PI3<OFVAL) . DON'T OVERFLOWBT
)@@G@@ OR CHANGE SIGN   @D@@@@P**(I,2) EQU        P(I,2)+FUDGE      . ADJUST KBU
)@@G@@EYWORD@F@@@@P**(I,3) EQU        P(I,3)+1-(FUDGE=0) . ADJUST IMMEDIATE VABV
)@@G@@LUE   @F@@@@ DO ((P(I,3)=0)**(P(I,4)=0)=0)++(G$ALTT(P(I,2))=0) , GO G$$ABW
)@@G@@30 .  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. REGISTER TESTS AGAINST IMMEDIATE ZEROES CAN BEBX
)@@G@@COME CONDITIONAL JUMPS  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. BE CAREFUL NOT TO OVEROPTIMIBY
)@@G@@ZE IMMEDIATES     @F@@@@ DO 1-G$AMPR , GO G$$A30 . CANNOT OPTIMIZE WITHOBZ
)@@G@@UT & FUNCTION     @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&(P(I,3))=-2)=0 , GO G$$A30 .CA
)@@G@@ ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE  @G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($BA(P(I,3))=0)=0 , GO GCB
)@@G@@$$A30 . ZERO MUST BE ABSOLUTE @F@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       G$ALTT(P(I,2))  CC
)@@G@@  . GET ALTERNATE KEYWORD     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 ,P**(I) EQU 3          CD
)@@G@@    . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWAY ,,U)     @I@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P**(CE
)@@G@@I,4) $DELETE          . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWAY ,,U)     @I@@@@CF
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P**(I,5) $DELETE          . FORCE NUMBER OF ARGS (PRUNE AWCG
)@@G@@AY ,,U)     @C@@@@ GO G$$A20          . GO FINISH UP THE FARBLING @[@@@@CH
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. TYPE 2 CONDITION TESTS ON A-REGS CAN BECOME CONDITIONAL JUCI
)@@G@@MPS, TOO.   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$A10*   NAME    @G@@@@ DO P(I)>3 , GO G$CJ
)@@G@@$A30                . DON'T OPTIMIZE EQUF'D CORE LOCNS@I@@@@REG       EQCK
)@@G@@U       P(I,3)            . GET REG FROM  <KEYWORD>,IN,<REG> FORMAT     CL
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($BA(REG)=0)=0 , GO G$$A30 . MUST BE AN ABSOLUTECM
)@@G@@ VALUE@G@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (&(REG)=-2)=0 , GO G$$A30  . MUST BE AN ABCN
)@@G@@SOLUTE VALUE@G@@@@ DO (REG<A0)++(REG>A15) , GO G$$A30   . MAKE SURE ITS CO
)@@G@@WITHIN AREG RANGE @H@@@@P**(I,3)  EQU       P(I,1)            . FORCE COCP
)@@G@@NDITION KEYWORD INTO SPEC3    @F@@@@P**(I,1)  EQU       REG             CQ
)@@G@@  . THEN MOVE REG INTO SPEC1  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$A20*   NAME          CR
)@@G@@              . FINISH FUDGING  <AREG>,IS,<KEYWORD> TEST    @E@@@@P**(I,CS
)@@G@@2)  EQU       IS                . CRAM IN THE KEYWORD @G@@@@N(1)      EQCT
)@@G@@U       3                 . AND MARK THIS AS A TYPE 3 TEST  @[@@@@.     CU
)@@G@@@#@@@@G$$A30*   NAME    @F@@@@J(1)    EQU    P(I,G$KSF(N(1)))       . GECV
)@@G@@T FUNC KEYWORD VALUE    @H@@@@ DO DTH ,J(1) EQU G$IV(N(1),J(1))     . FLCW
)@@G@@IP IF DEMORGAN'S THEOREM IN EFFECT  @F@@@@ DO J(1)<1 , G$$EFL 1,2       CX
)@@G@@        . E-FLAG IF UNKNOWN KEYWORD @F@@@@NI$*(K) EQU    G$FJ(N(1),J(1))CY
)@@G@@        . NO OF INSTRS GENERATED    @D@@@@WA$*(K) EQU    G$WS(N(1),J(1))CZ
)@@G@@        . WAITING STATUS@G@@@@KE$*(K) EQU    J(1)                   . EXDA
)@@G@@TERNALIZE FUNC KEYWORD VAL    @F@@@@TP$*(K) EQU    N(1)                 DB
)@@G@@  . EXTERNALIZE TYPE OF TEST  @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     DC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************************************DD
)@@G@@********    @F@@@@.     *                                               DE
)@@G@@       *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$COD : GENERATE CODE FOR A SIMPLE CONDITIONDF
)@@G@@ TEST  *    @F@@@@.     *                                               DG
)@@G@@       *    @F@@@@.     ************************************************DH
)@@G@@********    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@Q       PROC   *2 @I@@@@G$$CODDI
)@@G@@*  NAME                         . PF'S: FIELD-INDEX,TEST-INDEX,WAIT-VAL DJ
)@@G@@FA    @F@@@@I       EQU    Q(1,1)                 . GET FIELD WE'RE SCANDK
)@@G@@NING  @F@@@@NN      EQU    Q(1,2)                 . GET DECODED DATA INDDL
)@@G@@EX    @E@@@@N       EQU    TP$(NN)                . GET CONDITION TYPE  DM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@CGISF   EQU    G$FCF(N)=0             . TRUE IF G$FJ=FDN
)@@G@@UNC CODE (ELSE J-S@E@@@@JI(1)   EQU    KE$(NN)                . GET KEYWDO
)@@G@@ORD FUNCTION@F@@@@JI(2)   EQU    G$IV(N,JI(1))          . AND KEYWORD OFDP
)@@G@@ THE INVERSE@F@@@@WOK     EQU    Q(1,3)=G$WS(N,JI(1))   . ON IF WAITING DQ
)@@G@@STATUS OK   @A@@@@.     ---- DECODE OPERAND FIELDS    @G@@@@AAA     EQU DR
)@@G@@   0+(G$ASF(N)>0)*(P(I,G$ASF(N))-A0) . WATCH OUT FOR -0!!!!!@D@@@@JJJ   DS
)@@G@@  EQU     CGISF*P(I,5)          . J DESIGNATOR  @ @@@@XXX     EQU     CGDT
)@@G@@ISF*P(I,4)  @C@@@@HI      EQU     CGISF*(2*P(I,*4)+P(I,*3)) .     @G@@@@DU
)@@G@@U18     EQU     (JJJ>015)**(XXX=0)**(N<3)**(HI=0) . ON=>18 BIT U-FIELD  DV
)@@G@@@C@@@@UUU     EQU    CGISF*P(I,3)+(1-CGISF)*Q(2,1)    @G@@@@SIDE**(1) EQDW
)@@G@@U SIDE(1)++(N=5)++(HI>0)  . ON IF TEST HAS SIDE EFFECTS     @G@@@@ DO G$DX
)@@G@@FJ(N,JI(1),1)>077 , GO G$$G10   . CHECK FOR ASYMMETRIC INSTRUCTION@[@@@@DY
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@. PROCESS SYMMETRIC TESTS (FOR WHICH AN INVERSE MACHINE INSTDZ
)@@G@@R EXISTS)   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@JIU     EQU    JI(2-WOK)              . GEEA
)@@G@@T INDEX OF OPCODE WE'LL USE   @G@@@@NUMINS  EQU    G$FJ(N,JIU)          EB
)@@G@@  . GET NO OF INSTRS TO GENERATE    @E@@@@K DO     NUMINS ,FUN(K) EQU G$EC
)@@G@@FCF(N)+CGISF*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)    @E@@@@K DO     NUMINS ,JAY(K) EQU JJJ+(1-CED
)@@G@@GISF)*G$FJ(N,JIU,K)     @G@@@@K DO     NUMINS*(1-U18) , I$ FUN(K),JAY(K)EE
)@@G@@,AAA,XXX,HI,UUU . GENERATE    @F@@@@K DO     NUMINS*U18 , G$$IMU FUN(K),EF
)@@G@@JAY(K),AAA,XXX,UUU . IMMEDIAT @F@@@@REVER**(1) EQU G$FJ(N,JI(1))*G$FJ(N,EG
)@@G@@JI(2))=1 . SET REVERSIBLE FLAG@G@@@@ DO REVER(1)++WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,$EH
)@@G@@+2 . WATCHOUT FOR NON-REVERSIBLES   @H@@@@ DO 1 , END                   EI
)@@G@@        . FOR STANDARD INSTRS, ITS ALL OVER HERE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. PROCEJ
)@@G@@ESS ASYMMETRIC INSTRS (FOR WHICH NO SINGLE INVERSE EXISTS)  @[@@@@.     EK
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$G10* NAME@F@@@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(N,JI(1),1)        . GET FUNCEL
)@@G@@T-JDESIG VALUE    @E@@@@ DO FUN=01637 , GO G$$G20             . TEST FOREM
)@@G@@ DTE INSTR  @D@@@@. IF NOT A DTE, THEN INSTRUCTION IS A JUMP OF SORTS   EN
)@@G@@@B@@@@. (EITHER DJZ OR AN I/O CHANNEL TEST)     @H@@@@AREG    EQU    AAAEO
)@@G@@+A0*(FUN>01700)     . FOR CHANNEL INSTRS, USE GIVEN AVALUE  @G@@@@      EP
)@@G@@     I$       FUN*/-4,FUN**017,AREG,,,WOK*UUU+(WOK=0)*($+2) .     @ @@@@EQ
)@@G@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,UUU  @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @B@@@@. HERE WE HANDLE TER
)@@G@@HE DOUBLE TEST EQUAL -  @]@@@@G$$G20* NAME@D@@@@           I$       FUN*ES
)@@G@@/-4,FUN**017,AAA,XXX,HI,UUU . @ @@@@ DO WOK=0 , I$ 074,04,,,,$+2  @]@@@@ET
)@@G@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************EU
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       EV
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *  G$$TST : DRIVER FOR SEW

)@@G@@  PROC   *2 @H@@@@G$$TST*  NAME                         . PF'S: FIELD-INFA
)@@G@@-P,COMPOUND-FLAG,INVERT @I@@@@                              . IF NO JUMPFB
)@@G@@-EXIT GIVEN, G$TLBL(TTL)+1 IS USED (LINE I@H@@@@TTL     EQU    G$CTR(4)+FC
)@@G@@1             . COUNT THIS REFERENCE TO THIS PROCEDURE@F@@@@ORIG        FD

)@@G@@QU  TTL                   . BUMP NO OF CALLS TO THIS PROC   @D@@@@G$TLBLFF

)@@G@@)=0                 . ON IF LINEITEM FORMAT     @E@@@@FA(1)   EQU    R(2FH
)@@G@@,1)+LIF*(G$TLBL(TTL)+1) . SET FALSE EXIT  @G@@@@DTH     EQU    R(1,3)   FI
)@@G@@              . ON => USE DEMORGAN'S THEOREM FOR@I@@@@                  FJ
)@@G@@                    . WHICH CAUSES G$$CAN TO INVERT THE SENSE     @[@@@@FK
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@ DO R(1,2) , GO G$$T10                . GO DO COMPOUND CONDIFL
)@@G@@TION  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CODE GENERATION FOR SIMPLE CONDITIONS   @[@@@@FM
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@        G$$CAN R(1,1),1               . ANALYZE THE (SINGLE)FN
)@@G@@ FIELD@H@@@@ DO WA$(1)>1 , GO G$$T01              . CHECK FOR TEST INSTRFO
)@@G@@ TO GE GENN'D     @D@@@@        G$$COD R(1,1),1,0 FA(1)       . JUMP TO FP
)@@G@@FALSE @C@@@@ GO G$$T99                            . AND QUIT@[@@@@.     FQ

)@@G@@S A TEST    @I@@@@        G$$COD R(1,1),1,2+LIF         . SKIP IF: TRUE FS

)@@G@@  . JUMP TO FALSE (IF-ELSE)   @]@@@@ GO G$$T99  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     FU

)@@G@@$(1)>1)+(WA$(2)>1)  . DETERMINE OVERALL WAIT TYPE     @G@@@@ DO (P(R(1,1GB
)@@G@@)+1,1)=AND)=1-DTH , GO G$$T20 . IF AND-CONDITION, GO DO IT  @[@@@@.     GC

)@@G@@1)<0100) , GO G$$T12    @ @@@@. OOPS, WE'RE IN HOT WATER--  @E@@@@      GM
