)@@G@@R GENERATION OF LOOP CONTROLS ******@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SELEIQ
)@@G@@CTION OF THE INSTRUCTION TO BE USED TO CONTROL THE LOOP IS: @E@@@@.    1IR
)@@G@@) JGD    IF LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS -1, OR   @E@@@@.           IS
)@@G@@   LOOP IS FOR A SPECIFIED NUMBER OF TIMES.     @E@@@@.    2) JMGI   IF IT
)@@G@@LOOP TERMINATES AT 0 AND STEP IS NOT -1.  @D@@@@.    3) TLEM   IF LOOP TIU
)@@G@@ERMINATES AT OTHER THAN ZERO. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. POSITIONING OF THE LOOIV
)@@G@@P CONTROL INSTRUCTION IS:     @A@@@@.    1) JGD    ALWAYS AT THE BOTTOM IW
)@@G@@@F@@@@.    2) JMGI   AT BOTTOM (SO JUMP DESTINATION CONTINUES IN THE    IX
)@@G@@@F@@@@.              LOOP), IF INCREMENT NEGATIVE (LOOP SENSE DOWN),    IY
)@@G@@@E@@@@.              I.E. VALUES OF LOOP CONTROL VARIABLE ARE >0 .@A@@@@IZ
)@@G@@.              AT TOP OTHERWISE     @F@@@@.    3) TLEM   AT BOTTOM (SO SJA
)@@G@@KIP CAUSES EXIT FROM LOOP) WHEN     @E@@@@.              INCREMENT IS POJB
)@@G@@SITIVE (LOOP SENSE UP), I.E.  @F@@@@.              TERMINATION CONDITIONJC
)@@G@@ IS APPROACHED FROM BELOW.    @F@@@@.              BECAUSE OF LACK OF SIJD
)@@G@@GN EXTENSION, THIS HOLDS RE-  @F@@@@.              GARDLESS OF THE SIGN JE
)@@G@@OF THE LOOP VARIABLE ITSELF.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE: IF THE SIGN OF TJF
)@@G@@HE INCREMENT IS UNKNOWN (JMGI/TLEM), THE CODE   @G@@@@. TO VARY THE LOOPJG
)@@G@@ CONTROL VARIABLE WILL BE DUPLICATED AT BOTH TOP AND  @F@@@@. BOTTOM, WIJH
)@@G@@TH AN EXECUTE-TIME TEST (SIGN JUMP) AT THE BOTTOM TO  @A@@@@. DETERMINE JI
)@@G@@WHICH IS TO BE USED.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. TO ENFORCE THE REQUIREMENT TJJ
)@@G@@HAT THE LOOP CONTROL REGISTER CONTAIN     @F@@@@. THE FROM/TO VALUES ON JK
)@@G@@THE FIRST AND LAST TIMES THROUGH THE LOOP,@D@@@@. TLEM TESTS AT THE TOP JL
)@@G@@ARE SURROUNDED BY AX AND ANX  @F@@@@. OF THE INCREMENT. IN THE GENERAL CJM
)@@G@@ASE, THERE IS NO WAY TO AVOID @G@@@@. THIS. IN THE FUTURE, WE WILL ALLOWJN
)@@G@@ THE USER TO SURPRESS IT, AND/OR    @G@@@@. IN THE CASE WHERE THE CONTROJO
)@@G@@L FIELDS ARE IMMEDIATE, GENERATE SLIGHTLY @C@@@@. DIFFERENT CODE WHICH WJP
)@@G@@ILL MAKE IT UNNECESSARY.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************************JQ
)@@G@@********************************    @F@@@@.     *                       JR
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LAN : ANALYZE A <JS
)@@G@@LOOP CONTROL> SPECIFICATION    *    @F@@@@.     *                       JT
)@@G@@                               *    @F@@@@.     ************************JU
)@@G@@********************************    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.    FLAGS SET BY JV
)@@G@@THIS SUBROUTINE ARE USED BY CALLING ROUTINE (REPEAT)  @^@@@@.    THEIR MJW
)@@G@@EANINGS ARE:@D@@@@.       FI(1)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FOR' SPECIFICATION  JX
)@@G@@@C@@@@.       FI(2)  INDEX IN IMAGE OF 'FROM' SPEC    @G@@@@.       FI(3JY
)@@G@@)  INDEX OF 'TO' SPEC ('VARY'), OR 'MASKED' SPEC ('LOOKFOR')@G@@@@.     JZ
)@@G@@  FI(4)  INDEX OF 'BY' SPEC. NOTE THAT IF USER DIDN'T GIVE ONE,   @C@@@@KA
)@@G@@.              WE FORCE IT BY STORING IN P(X,Y) @G@@@@.       FI(5)  ON KB
)@@G@@IF ANY LOOP CONTROL CODE IS TO APPEAR AT THE PHYSICAL @B@@@@.           KC
)@@G@@   BOTTOM OF THE LOOP CODE    @F@@@@.       FI(6)  ON IF SENSE OF LOOP CKD
)@@G@@TL VARIABLE (UP\DOWN) IS KNOWN@D@@@@.              ('VARY'), OR OFFSET VKE
)@@G@@ALUE ('LOOKFOR')  @F@@@@.       FI(7)  INDEX IN P OF LAST FIELD SCANNED KF
)@@G@@BY THIS ROUTINE   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE ARRAYS IM(K) AND IV(K) ARE USEKG
)@@G@@D INTERNALLY FOR THE ANALYZED @H@@@@. PARAMETERS OF THE LOOP SPECIFICATIKH
)@@G@@ON. IM IS ON IF THE VALUE IS IMMEDIATE,   @G@@@@. AND IV IS THE VALUE ITKI
)@@G@@SELF. K=1,2,3,4=> FORVAL, FROMVAL, TOVAL, BYVAL.@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     KJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@        PROC   *0                     . NOTE: ONE-PASS PROC FLAG RKK
)@@G@@EQUIRED     @#@@@@G$$LAN*  NAME     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@W(1)    EQU    KW(KL
)@@G@@1)                  . GET KEYWORD WHICH DESCRIBES FIELD     @[@@@@.     KM
)@@G@@@E@@@@.       ***** BREAK DOWN SOURCE IMAGE, SET DEFAULTS *****   @[@@@@KN
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. SCAN ALL FIELDS FOR DEFINING KEYWORDS   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@KO
)@@G@@K3      EQU    MASKED*(W(1)=LOOKFOR)+TO*((W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0)  @G@@@@FI*(1)KP
)@@G@@  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FOR)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FOR)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FOR)   @G@@@@KQ
)@@G@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=FROM)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=FROM)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=FROM)KR
)@@G@@@D@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=K3)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=K3)+;   @B@@@@      KS
)@@G@@  3*(P(VI+3,1)=K3)+4*(P(VI+4,1)=K3) @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    VI+(P(VI+1,1)=BKT
)@@G@@Y)+2*(P(VI+2,1)=BY)+3*(P(VI+3,1)=BY)@G@@@@FI*(7)  EQU    FI(4)          KU
)@@G@@        . INITIALIZE LAST FIELD POINTER   @H@@@@I DO     3 , DO FI(I)>FIKV
)@@G@@(7) ,FI*(7) EQU FI(I) . FIND LAST FIELD USER GAVE US  @I@@@@LF(1)   EQU KW
)@@G@@   0+P                    . SET INDEX OF LAST FIELD + 1 IN CASE OF D    KX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'TO' SPECIFICATION TO ZERO  @[@@@@KY
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@ DO (K3=MASKED)++(FI(3)>VI) , GO G$$L01 . IF 'TO' EXPLICIT, KZ
)@@G@@SKIP THIS   @H@@@@FI*(3)  EQU    LF(1)                  . FORCE IT INTO LA
)@@G@@THE NEXT AVAIL SUBFIELD @E@@@@P*(FI(3),1) EQU TO                    . SELB
)@@G@@T ITS KEYWORD     @F@@@@P*(FI(3),4) EQU XU                    . MAKE IT LC
)@@G@@AN IMMEDIATE ZERO @G@@@@LF(1)   EQU    LF(1)+1                . BUMP NEXLD
)@@G@@T USABLE FIELD POINTER  @G@@@@G$$L01* NAME                          . ENLE
)@@G@@D OF DEFAULT FOR 'TO' FIELD   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. 'BY' FIELD (IF GIVEN) LF
)@@G@@IS VARIABLE LENGTH. FORCE TO FIXED FORMAT @C@@@@. BY MOVING UP/DOWN/OFFSLG
)@@G@@ET TO THE FIFTH SUBFIELD@[@@@@.     @F@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , GO G$$L02      LH
)@@G@@        . IF 'BY' OMITTED, SKIP THIS@E@@@@ DO P(FI(4),4)=U ,P*(FI(4),4) LI
)@@G@@EQU XU . FORCE SIGN EXTENSION @F@@@@NB      EQU    0+P(FI(4))           LJ
)@@G@@  . NO OF SPECS IN 'BY' FIELD @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0 , DO (P(FI(4),NB)>0)++(LK
)@@G@@NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST     @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=1 , DO ($AP(PLL
)@@G@@(FI(4),NB))>0)++(NB=5) , GO G$$L02 . NOTHING TO ADJUST@G@@@@P*(FI(4),5) LM
)@@G@@EQU P(FI(4),NB)           . FORCE UP DOWN OFFSET TO FIELD 5 @F@@@@P*(FI(LN
)@@G@@4),NB) EQU 0                    . AND RESET WHEREVER IT WAS @H@@@@G$$L02LO
)@@G@@* NAME                          . END KEYWORD FARBLING FOR 'BY' FIELD   LP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTE:  THE CODE BELOW WILL GENERATE (USUALLY) SPURIOLQ
)@@G@@US R-FLAGS IF     @F@@@@. THE FIELDS BEING EXAMINED ARE EXTERNAL (I.E. ULR
)@@G@@-FLAGGED) EVEN    @F@@@@. THOUGH WE ARE STRIPPING OFF FIELDS WHICH HAVE LS
)@@G@@NO RELOCATION (THE@E@@@@. X AND J FIELDS), AND EVEN THOUGH THE PORTION OLT
)@@G@@F UV WHICH  @F@@@@. MAY CARRY RELOCATION (THE U-FIELD) IS NOT MASKED AT LU
)@@G@@THE POINT   @A@@@@. OF ITS USE. <EXPLETIVE DELETED>   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@LV
)@@G@@          ON        G$MASM=0          . BEGIN ASM CODE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@LW
)@@G@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@LX
)@@G@@I DO     4 , DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ LY
)@@G@@0,P(FI(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @[@@@@LZ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)>0777777 ; IF THE USER EQUF'D THE MA
)@@G@@SYMBOL@E@@@@        ,IM(I) EQU 07017000000**(G$NOFO UV(I))=07000000000  MB
)@@G@@@F@@@@I DO     4 , DO P(FI(I),2)<01000000 ; IF HE DIDN'T EQUF IT ..     MC
)@@G@@@H@@@@        ,IM(I) EQU (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=P(FI(I),4)**016) . CHECK FMD
)@@G@@OR EXPLICI  @E@@@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)<01000000) ; IF NOT ME
)@@G@@EQUF'D@F@@@@        ,IV(I) EQU P(FI(I),2)         . USE THE VALUE HE GAVMF
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@I DO     4 , DO IM(I)**(P(FI(I),2)>0777777) ; BUT IF HE EQUFMG
)@@G@@'D IT @G@@@@        ,IV(I) EQU + (G$NOFO UV(I)**G$UMSK) . PRAY ITS NOT EMH
)@@G@@XTERNAL     @H@@@@I DO     4 , DO IV(I)>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU IV(I)++077777MI
)@@G@@7000000 . SIGN EXTEND   @I@@@@I DO 2 ,APIV(I+1) EQU IV(I+1)         . FUMJ
)@@G@@DGE ABSOLUTE PART FOR LATER MASM TESTS    @E@@@@          OFF           MK
)@@G@@              . END OF ASM CODE     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          ON      ML
)@@G@@  G$MASM=1          . BEGIN MASM CODE     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@I         $RMM
)@@G@@EPEAT   4                 . DO ALL THIS FOR I=1,2,3,4 @G@@@@APU       EQMN
)@@G@@U       $AP(P(FI(I),2))   . STRIP U-FIELD OF RELOCATION     @[@@@@.     MO
)@@G@@@D@@@@. PUT ALL FIELDS IN STANDARD FORM TO HANDLE EQUF'S    @[@@@@.     MP
)@@G@@@C@@@@ DO FI(I)>VI ,UV(I) EQU ; COMBINE ALL FIELDS    @G@@@@ +(I$ 0,P(FIMQ
)@@G@@(I),4),0,P(FI(I),3),2*P(FI(I),*3)+P(FI(I),*2),P(FI(I),2))   @G@@@@APUV  MR
)@@G@@    EQU       $AP(UV(I))        . APUV IS ABSOLUTE PART OF UV(I)  @[@@@@MS
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@IM(I) EQU APU>0777777-> ; . IF THE USER EQUF'D THE SYMBOL   MT
)@@G@@@H@@@@ 07017000000**(G$NOFO APUV)=07000000000! ; THEN SET TRUE IF 'U' ANMU
)@@G@@D NO XDESIG @I@@@@ (P(FI(I),3)=0)**(016=P(FI(I),4)**016) . ELSE SET TRUEMV
)@@G@@ IF EXPLICIT 'U', NO XREG     @D@@@@IV(I) EQU IM(I)**(APU<01000000)-> ; MW
)@@G@@  . IF NOT EQUF'D @F@@@@       P(FI(I),2)! ;      . USE THE VALUE HE GAVMX
)@@G@@E IN SUBFIELD 2   @F@@@@    + (G$NOFO APUV**G$UMSK)           . ELSE PRAMY
)@@G@@Y ITS NOT EXTERNAL@H@@@@ DO $AP(IV(I))>0377777 ,IV(I) EQU -(0777777-IV(IMZ
)@@G@@)) . SIGN EXTEND (IF NEEDED)  @G@@@@APIV(I)   EQU       $AP(IV(I))      NA
)@@G@@  . NO RELOCATION FOR LATER TESTS.  @F@@@@          $ENDR               NB
)@@G@@        . END OF $REPEAT STRUCTURE  @E@@@@          OFF                 NC
)@@G@@        . END OF MASM CODE    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@. APIV(2) AND APIV(3) ARND
)@@G@@E NON-RELOCATABLE EQUIVALENTS OF    @D@@@@. IV(2...3) FOR USE BY MASM INNE
)@@G@@ COMPARISONS OF THE FORM@C@@@@. IV(2)>IV(3). WHEN USING @ASM, APIV(I)=IVNF
)@@G@@(I).  @E@@@@. ***NOTE*** WE ASSUME THAT IV(I) WILL NOT BE UPDATED PRIOR NG
)@@G@@@A@@@@. TO THE USE OF APIV(I), FOR I=2,3  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@NH
)@@G@@. DEFAULT A MISSING 'BY' SPECIFICATION TO +-1, DEPENDING UPON     @F@@@@NI
)@@G@@. THE SIGN OF TO-FROM, AND/OR THE USER'S UP/DOWN/OFFSET SPEC.     @[@@@@NJ
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO FI(4)>VI , GO G$$L03              . SKIP THINK
)@@G@@S IF USER GAVE THIS FIELD     @F@@@@FI*(4)  EQU    LF(1)                NL
)@@G@@  . REMEMBER WHERE ITS GOING  @H@@@@ DO (W(1)=VARY)++(W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , NM
)@@G@@GO G$$L03 . SKIP FOR SPECIFIC LOOP TYPE   @F@@@@IV(4)   EQU    1        NN
)@@G@@              . INITIAL ASSUMPTION IS +1  @G@@@@ DO ((W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0)**NO
)@@G@@IM(2)**IM(3)  ; UNLESS WE KNOW TO-FROM VALUES   @F@@@@        ,IV(4) EQUNP
)@@G@@ 1-2*(APIV(2)>APIV(3))  . THEN USE SIGN OF DIFF @G@@@@ DO (IV(4)=1)**(P(NQ
)@@G@@FI(4),5)=DOWN) ,IV(4) EQU -1 . MAKE IMPLICIT EXPLICIT @F@@@@P*(FI(4),2) NR
)@@G@@EQU     IV(4)             . SAVE FOR USE BY GENERATOR @D@@@@P*(FI(4),4) NS
)@@G@@EQU XU  . MAKE SURE HE KNOWS ITS IMMEDIATE@E@@@@UV(4)   EQUF   IV(4),,XUNT
)@@G@@              . MARK IT AS IMMEDIATE@G@@@@IM(4)   EQU    1              NU
)@@G@@        . AND TURN ON THE IMMEDIATE FLAG  @G@@@@G$$L03* NAME            NV
)@@G@@              . END DEFAULT PROCESSING OF 'BY'  @G@@@@ DO P(FI(4),5)=0 ,NW
)@@G@@P*(FI(4),5) EQU P(VI,3) . SET USER'S SIGN, IF ANY     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@NX
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@ DO (W(1)=LOOKFOR)=0 , GO G$$L30      . IF NOT LOOKFOR, GO DNY
)@@G@@O VARY@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.       ***** PROCESS 'LOOKFOR' LOOPNZ
)@@G@@ (I.E. SEARCH, MASKED SEARCH) ***** @[@@@@.     @H@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    0  OA
)@@G@@                    . FLAG NO CODE APPEARS AT THE BOTTOM    @[@@@@.     OB
)@@G@@@A@@@@. LOAD MASK AND REPEAT REGISTERS    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO (FI(3)>VOC
)@@G@@I)**(P(FI(3))>1) , I$ 023,,2,,,UV(3) . LOAD MASK REG (R2)   @F@@@@ DO FIOD
)@@G@@(1)>VI , I$ 023,,1,,,UV(1)      . AND REPEAT COUNT (R1)     @[@@@@.     OE
)@@G@@@A@@@@. INITIALIZE REG USED AS TABLE INDEX@[@@@@.     @H@@@@ DO (P(FI(4)OF
)@@G@@,5)=OFFSET)**1-IM(4) , G$$EFL 2,1 . OFFSET NEEDS IMMEDIATE BY     @F@@@@OG
)@@G@@OFV     EQU    IM(4)*(P(FI(4),5)=OFFSET)*IV(4) . SET OFFSET VALUE @H@@@@OH
)@@G@@FI*(6)  EQU    OFV                    . AND SAVE FOR USE BY CODE GENERATOI
)@@G@@OR    @E@@@@ DO FI(2)=VI , END                    . IF NO 'FROM', QUIT  OJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO FI(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,2                 . REQUIRE THAT A 'BY' SPOK
)@@G@@EC APPEARED @H@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(4) , GO G$$L21          . IF BOTH IMMEDIOL
)@@G@@ATE, GO USE CONSTANT    @D@@@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,UV(2)   . LXOM
)@@G@@ XN,FROM    @F@@@@ DO OFV=0 , I$ 046,,P(VI,2),,,UV(4)   . IF NO OFFSET, ON
)@@G@@LXI XN,BY   @C@@@@ DO OFV=0 , END                       . AND QUIT@G@@@@OO
)@@G@@ DO P(VI,2)>X11 , AH P(VI,2),(+OFV,-OFV) . IF OVERLAPPED, ADD OFFSET IN OP
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , ANX,U P(VI,2),OFV    . IF NONOVERLAPPED, USE BRUTOQ
)@@G@@E FORCE     @B@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , LXI,U P(VI,2),OFV    .   @D@@@@ DO 1 OR
)@@G@@, END                           . THEN GET OUT  @I@@@@G$$L21* NAME      OS
)@@G@@                    . COME HERE IF FROM AND BY BOTH IMMEDIATE     @G@@@@OT
)@@G@@        I$     027,,P(VI,2),,,(+IV(4),IV(2)-OFV) . LOAD XREG FROM CONS  OU
)@@G@@@]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.       ****** PROCESS 'VARY' (NORMAOV
)@@G@@L LOOP) SPECIFICATION *****   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@G$$L30* NAME            OW
)@@G@@              . MARK START OF VARY CHECKING     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@ORIGOPOX
)@@G@@     EQU      +W(1)             . REMEMBER ORIGINAL OPCODE  @[@@@@.     OY
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO FI(1)>VI , GO G$$L34              . IF 'FOR', ASSUME JGD IMMEDOZ
)@@G@@IATELY@F@@@@ DO IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4)=0 , GO G$$L35 . NO FUDGE IF ALL NOT PA
)@@G@@KNOWN @D@@@@ DO (APIV(2)>0)**(IV(3)=0)**(IV(4)=-1)=0 , GO G$$L35  @G@@@@PB
)@@G@@FI*(1)  EQU    FI(2)                  . PUT 'FOR' IN P WHERE 'FROM' WAS PC
)@@G@@@F@@@@FI*(2)  EQU    VI                     . AND INVALIDATE THE 'FROM' PD
)@@G@@@G@@@@IV(1)   EQU    IV(2)+1                . FORVAL IS ONE MORE THAN FRPE
)@@G@@OMVAL @G@@@@IM(1)   EQU    1                      . TURN ON IMMEDIATE 'FPF
)@@G@@OR' FLAG    @D@@@@UV(1)   EQUF   IV(1),,XU              . AND SET U-SPECPG
)@@G@@@D@@@@G$$L34* NAME                          . SET OPCODE JGD@G@@@@W(1)  PH
)@@G@@  EQU    0+JGD                  . ADD ZERO TO OVERRIDE OPCODE EQU @G@@@@PI
)@@G@@ GO G$$L39                            . THEN GO GLOBALIZE THE OPCODE    PJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@.                             OP CAN'T BE JGD, MUST BE TLEM\JMGI  PK
)@@G@@@]@@@@G$$L35* NAME@G@@@@ DO (VARY=ORIGOP)=0 , GO G$$L40       . SKIP IF PL
)@@G@@OPCODE EXPLICITLY GIVEN @G@@@@ DO (FI(2)=VI)++(FI(3)=VI)++(FI(4)=VI) , GPM
)@@G@@$$EFL 2,3 . REQUIRE ALL SPECS @D@@@@W(1)    EQU    0+TLEM               PN
)@@G@@  . ASSUME TLEM   @F@@@@ DO IM(3)**(IV(3)=0) ,W(1) EQU 0+JMGI . UNLESS TPO
)@@G@@O IMMEDIATE ZERO  @[@@@@.     @I@@@@G$$L39* NAME                        PP
)@@G@@  . END DETERMINATION OF INSTR SPECIFICATION    @F@@@@P*(VI,1) EQU   W(1PQ
)@@G@@)                   . FORCE OPCODE SPEC FIELD   @G@@@@ DO (VARY=ORIGOP)+PR
)@@G@@+(W(1)=ORIGOP)=0 , G$$EFL 2,011 . OPCODE MISMATCH     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@PS
)@@G@@.        SET LOOP SENSE AND FLAG IF CODE AT BOTTOM OF LOOP REQUIRED     PT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L40* NAME@F@@@@ DO (W(1)=JGD)=0 , GO G$$L41        PU
)@@G@@  . IF NOT JGD, WE MUST FARBLE@F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    1                    PV
)@@G@@  . ELSE MARK SENSE KNOWN     @I@@@@FI*(5)  EQU    1                    PW
)@@G@@  . SET FLAG THAT CODE WILL APPEAR AT BOTTOM    @D@@@@ GO G$$L49        PX
)@@G@@                    . AND WE'RE DONE@[@@@@.     @F@@@@. COMPUTE SIGN/SENPY
)@@G@@SE FOR JMGI, TLEM LOOPS, AND CHECK TERMINATION  @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L41PZ
)@@G@@* NAME                          . NOT JGD, DETERMINE SENSE THE HARD WAY QA
)@@G@@@H@@@@USS     EQU    (P(FI(4),5)=UP)-(P(FI(4),5)=DOWN) . SET USER SUPPLIQB
)@@G@@ED SIGN     @D@@@@BYS     EQU    IM(4)*(1-2*(IV(4)<0))  . SIGN FROM 'BY'QC
)@@G@@@G@@@@FTS     EQU    (IM(2)**IM(3))*(1-2*(APIV(2)>APIV(3))) . FROMTO SIGQD
)@@G@@N     @G@@@@ DO FTS*BYS=-1 , G$$EFL 2,5               . N.G. IF SIGNS DOQE
)@@G@@N'T AGREE   @E@@@@MYS     EQU    FTS+BYS                . GET MY OWN SIGQF
)@@G@@N FLAG@F@@@@ DO MYS*USS=-1 , G$$EFL 2,6               . BETTER AGREE WITQG
)@@G@@H HIS @F@@@@SIGN    EQU    MYS+USS                . GET THE SIGN WE'LL UQH
)@@G@@SE    @F@@@@FI*(6)  EQU    (SIGN=0)=0             . ON IF WE KNOW LOOP SQI
)@@G@@ENSE  @H@@@@P*(VI,3) EQU   SIGN                   . REMEMBER FOR BOTTOM QJ
)@@G@@OF LOOP USAGE     @F@@@@FI*(5) EQU (SIGN=0)++(W(1)=TLEM)**(SIGN>0)++(W(1QK
)@@G@@)=JMGI)**(SIGN<0) @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. WATCH OUT FOR AX/ANX: TERMINATION QL
)@@G@@CONDITION MAY NOT PASS THRU ZERO    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO 1-((W(1)=TLEM)QM
)@@G@@**IM(2)**IM(3)**IM(4)) ; UNLESS TLEM AND IMMEDIATE... @E@@@@    , GO G$$QN
)@@G@@L49                       . DON'T DO THIS TEST  @E@@@@VV(1)      EQU    QO
)@@G@@  IV(2)             . SET UP START VAL    @E@@@@VV(2)      EQU      IV(3QP
)@@G@@)+IV(4)       . AND TERMINATION VAL @D@@@@          ON        G$MASM=0  QQ
)@@G@@        . BEGIN ASM CODE@G@@@@  DO G$AMPR                           ; IFQR
)@@G@@ RELOCATION CAN BE DETERMINED @F@@@@    ,VK DO 2                        QS
)@@G@@  ; THEN FOR BOTH FROM AND TO @F@@@@      , DO 1-(&(VV(VK))=-2)         QT
)@@G@@  ; IF VALUE NOT ABSOLUTE     @F@@@@        ,VV(VK) EQU VV(VK)+01000    QU
)@@G@@  . FUDGE FOR ITS RELOCATION  @E@@@@VK DO 2                             QV
)@@G@@  ; FOR BOTH LIMITS...  @G@@@@  ,VV(VK) EQU (1-(VV(VK)=0))*(1-2*(VV(VK)<QW
)@@G@@0)) . SIGN FLAG => -1, 0, +1  @F@@@@ DO VV(1)*VV(2)<1 , G$$EFL 2,4      QX
)@@G@@  . LOOP PASSES TO/THRU ZERO  @E@@@@          OFF                       QY
)@@G@@  . END OF ASM CODE     @E@@@@          ON        G$MASM=1          . BEQZ
)@@G@@GIN MASM CODE     @G@@@@  DO G$AMPR                           ; IF RELOCRA
)@@G@@ATION CAN BE DETERMINED @F@@@@    ,VK DO 2                          ; THRB
)@@G@@EN FOR BOTH FROM AND TO @F@@@@      , DO 1-($BA(VV(VK))=0)          ; IFRC
)@@G@@ VALUE NOT ABSOLUTE     @F@@@@        ,VV(VK) EQU VV(VK)+01000      . FURD
)@@G@@DGE FOR ITS RELOCATION  @E@@@@VK DO 2                               ; FORE
)@@G@@R BOTH LIMITS...  @H@@@@  ,VV(VK) EQU (1-(VV(VK)=0))*(1-2*($AP(VV(VK))<0RF
)@@G@@)) . SIGN FLAG => -1, 0, +1   @G@@@@ DO $AP(VV(1))*$AP(VV(2))<1 , G$$EFLRG
)@@G@@ 2,4 . LOOP PASSES TO/THRU ZERO     @E@@@@          OFF                 RH
)@@G@@        . END OF MASM CODE    @[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L49*    NAME         RI
)@@G@@              . END SENSE/PREFERENCE DETERMINATION    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@RJ
)@@G@@. SIGN EXTEND NEGATIVE EQUFS TO GET 18-BIT NEGATIVE IMMEDIATES.   @[@@@@RK
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@I DO 3 , DO (IM(I+1)=1)**(IV(I+1)<0) ; . FOR 2,3,4    @G@@@@RL
)@@G@@ ,UV(I+1)   EQUF      *IV(I+1),*0,XU  . IF NEG IMMED, SET HI BITS=1     RM
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@. GENERATE REGISTER INITIAL LOAD CODE, IF ANY   @[@@@@RN
)@@G@@.     @I@@@@IMOP      EQU       G$FLAG(K,21)>0    . IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZE FRO
)@@G@@LAG (ZERO ON PASS 1)    @H@@@@ DO FI(1)=VI , GO G$$L51              . IFRP
)@@G@@ 'FOR' NOT GIVEN, GO DO FROM/BY     @G@@@@RR      EQU    027*(P(VI,2)<A4RQ
)@@G@@)+023*(P(VI,2)>R1-1) . OPCODE IF X/R REG  @B@@@@RA      EQU    077**(0+PRR
)@@G@@(VI,2)-(RR=0)*A0) @G@@@@        I$     RR+010*(RR=0),,RA,,,UV(1)-IMOP . RS
)@@G@@LOAD COUNT REGISTER     @G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,21) EQU IM(1)              . SERT
)@@G@@T IMMEDIATE OPTIMIZATION FLAG @F@@@@ DO 1 , END                         RU
)@@G@@  . END OF REG LOAD GENERATION@[@@@@.     @H@@@@G$$L51* NAME            RV
)@@G@@              . HERE TO LOAD REG USING FROM/BY SPECS  @G@@@@ DO FI(2)=VIRW
)@@G@@ , END                    . NO LOAD IF 'FROM' FIELD ABSENT  @G@@@@ DO FIRX
)@@G@@(4)=VI , G$$EFL 2,7                 . ERROR IF 'FROM' BUT NO 'BY' @[@@@@RY
)@@G@@.     @C@@@@. IF 'BY' NOT IMMEDIATE, GEN 3 INSTRUCTIONS:    @C@@@@.   LXRZ
)@@G@@ XR,FROM  ;  ANX XR,(BY)  ;  LXI XR,(BY)  @E@@@@. IF 'BY' AND 'FROM' ARESA
)@@G@@ IMMED, GEN:  LX XR,(BY,FROM-BY)    @D@@@@. IF 'BY' AND LOOP CNTRL REG ISB
)@@G@@S OVERLAPPED AREG, GEN: @F@@@@.   LX AR,(BY,BY)  ;  AH AR,(FROM)    . IFSC
)@@G@@ 'FROM' NOT IMMEDIATE   @H@@@@. NOTE: IF LOOP REG IS NON-OVERLAPPED REG SD
)@@G@@WE MUST GEN BRUTE FORCE (3 INSTRS)  @G@@@@. WE CANNOT GEN (AX XR,(FROM) SE
)@@G@@) BECAUSE OF OVERFLOW INTO INCREMENT,     @E@@@@. E.G. (1,-1) + (2) = (2SF
)@@G@@,0) , NOT (1,1). SURPRISE, CHIEF!   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@ DO IM(4)=0 , GO GSG
)@@G@@$$L52               . IF 'BY' NOT IMMEDIATE, CANT USE LITERAL     @H@@@@SH
)@@G@@ DO (W(1)=JMGI)**IM(2)**1-G$FLAG(K,4) ; IF IMMEDIATE JMGI WITHOUT 'WHILESI
)@@G@@'     @G@@@@ , DO IV(4)<0 , GO G$$L53             . AND DECREASING, GO OSJ
)@@G@@PTIMIZE     @G@@@@ DO IM(2) , LX P(VI,2),(+IV(4),0+IV(2)-IV(4)) . LX XR,SK
)@@G@@(STEP,FROM-STEP)  @H@@@@ DO IM(2) , END                       . IF 'FROMSL
)@@G@@' AND 'BY' ARE IMMED, DONE    @G@@@@ DO P(VI,2)<A0 , GO G$$L52          SM
)@@G@@  . IF NOT OVERLAP, BRUTE FORCE     @F@@@@        LX     P(VI,2),(+IV(4)SN
)@@G@@,0-IV(4)) . LX XR,(STEP,FROM-STEP)  @G@@@@        AH     P(VI,2),UV(2)  SO
)@@G@@        . AH FROMVAL (OVERLAP ONLY!!!)    @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @D@@@@G$$L52SP
)@@G@@*   NAME                        . BRUTE FORCE.  @E@@@@        LX     P(VSQ
)@@G@@I,2),UV(2)          . LX WITH FROMVAL     @H@@@@        ANX    P(VI,2),USR
)@@G@@V(4)          . ANX STEP TO COMPENSATE FOR INCR AT TOP@G@@@@        LXI SS
)@@G@@   P(VI,2),UV(4)          . LXI STEP TO SET UP INCREMENT    @F@@@@ DO 1 ST
)@@G@@, END                           . END OF REG INITIALIZATION @[@@@@.     SU
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$$L53* NAME                          . OPTIMIZE IMMEDIATE JMGI LOSV
)@@G@@OPS   @E@@@@        LX      P(VI,2),(+IV(4),IV(2)) . LOAD (+BY,FROM)    SW
)@@G@@@G@@@@G$FLAG**(K,21) EQU  1                   . TURN ON OPTIMIZATION FLASX
)@@G@@G     @]@@@@        END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.     ************SY
)@@G@@********************************************    @F@@@@.     *           SZ
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     *   G$$LGE :TA
)@@G@@ GENERATE CODE FOR <LOOP CONTROL> FIELDS   *    @F@@@@.     *           TB
)@@G@@                                           *    @F@@@@.     ************TC
)@@G@@********************************************    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     TD
)@@G@@@I@@@@Q       PROC   *2                     . PF'S: 'VARY','TO','BY'  JUTE
)@@G@@MPTARG,TOP/BOT    @#@@@@G$$LGE*  NAME     @G@@@@VI      EQU    Q(1,1)   TF
)@@G@@              . INDEX IN P OF VARY SPEC FIELD   @E@@@@TI      EQU    Q(1TG
)@@G@@,2)                 . INDEX OF 'TO' FIELD @E@@@@BI      EQU    Q(1,3)   TH
)@@G@@              . INDEX OF 'BY' FIELD @E@@@@F       EQU    P(VI,1)        TI
)@@G@@        . FUNCTION REQUESTED  @H@@@@ATTOP     EQU       Q(2,2)          TJ
)@@G@@  . ON IF BEING CALLED AT TOP OF LOOP     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO F=LOOKFOTK
)@@G@@R , GO G$$L80             . SPECIAL HANDLING FOR SEARCHING  @F@@@@ DO F=TL
)@@G@@JGD , G$$FJA 070,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . JUMP TO KEEP LOOPING    @G@@@@ DO F=TM
)@@G@@JGD , END                       . FOR JGD, THAT'S ALL THERE IS    @[@@@@TN
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. TLEM/JMGI ---   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@JMF     EQU    F=JMGI   TO
)@@G@@              . TRUE IF FUNC IS JMGI@G@@@@OLAP    EQU    P(VI,2)>X11    TP
)@@G@@        . ON IF LOOP CTL REG IS OVERLAPPED@G@@@@SENU    EQU    (P(VI,3)=TQ
)@@G@@0)**(ATTOP=0) . ON AT BOTTOM AND UNKNOWN SENSE  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@ DO SETR
)@@G@@NU**1-OLAP , I$ 060+JMF,,,,,P(VI,2) . TP(TLEM) TN(JMGI) ON REG    @H@@@@TS
)@@G@@ DO SENU , I$ 074,04-OLAP*(JMF+1),0+OLAP*(P(VI,2)-A0),,,G$LABL(K,2) . J TT
)@@G@@JN JP @[@@@@.     @C@@@@ DO JMF , GO G$$L70 . JMGI LOOPS ARE SIMPLE     TU
)@@G@@@E@@@@PTI2      EQU       P(TI,2)           . 'TO' FIELD UFIELD   @E@@@@TV
)@@G@@PBI2      EQU       P(BI,2)           . 'BY' FIELD UFIELD   @F@@@@ DO G$TW
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,PTI2 EQU $AP(PTI2)      . JUST THE ABSOLUTE PART    @F@@@@ DO G$TX
)@@G@@MASM=1 ,PBI2 EQU $AP(PBI2)      . JUST THE ABSOLUTE PART    @G@@@@TUHI  TY
)@@G@@  EQU    3*(PTI2<0)+2*P(TI,*3)+P(TI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON    @D@@@@TZ
)@@G@@TU      EQU    + (I$ 0,P(TI,4),,P(TI,3),TUHI,P(TI,2)) @G@@@@BUHI    EQU UA
)@@G@@   3*(PBI2<0)+2*P(BI,*3)+P(BI,*2) . T-FLAG IF ALL ARE ON    @D@@@@BU    UB
)@@G@@  EQU    + (I$ 0,P(BI,4),,P(BI,3),BUHI,P(BI,2)) @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 074UC
)@@G@@,06,0,P(VI,2),2,0   . AT TOP AX INCR WITH A NOP @E@@@@          I$      UD
)@@G@@  047,,P(VI,2),,,TU . TLEM ON 'TO' FIELD  @B@@@@        I$     074,04,,,UE
)@@G@@,Q(2,1) . JUMP    @G@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 025,,P(VI,2),,,BU      . UNDO FUDUF
)@@G@@GE WITH ANX OF INCR     @E@@@@ DO 1 , END                           . THUG
)@@G@@AT'S ALL FOR TLEM @[@@@@.     @C@@@@. HANDLE JMGI LOOPS (WHICH TERMINATEUH
)@@G@@ AT ZERO)   @[@@@@.     @#@@@@G$$L70*   NAME    @F@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 051UI
)@@G@@,017,0,P(VI,2),,0 . TNZ REG (LAST TIME CHECK)   @B@@@@ DO ATTOP , I$ 074UJ
)@@G@@,04,,,,Q(2,1)       .   @C@@@@        I$     074,012,P(VI,2),,,Q(2,1) . UK
)@@G@@JMGI  @#@@@@ DO 1 , END .     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. HANDLE SEARCH/MASKED SUL
)@@G@@EARCH. NOTE: SINCE THIS IS ALWAYS CALLED  @E@@@@. AT THE PHYSICAL TOP OFUM
)@@G@@ THE LOOP BY REPEAT, THE VALUES OF  @B@@@@. THE ARRAY FI(N) ARE ALWAYS AUN
)@@G@@VAILABLE    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@G$$L80* NAME@H@@@@IC      EQU    VI-1     UO
)@@G@@              . INDEX IN P OF CONDITION TEST FIELD    @H@@@@KWD     EQU UP
)@@G@@   P(IC,2)                . GET KEYWORD FROM CONDITION SPEC FIELD @F@@@@UQ
)@@G@@MSF     EQU    FI(3)>VI               . ON IF SEARCH IS MASKED    @G@@@@UR
)@@G@@FUN     EQU    G$FJ(1,KWD,1)+010*(1-MSF)-052*MSF . MODIFY TO A SEARCH   US
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO   MSF , I$ 071,FUN,P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(IC,3)+FI(6)UT
)@@G@@ . MS-@H@@@@ DO 1-MSF , I$ FUN,P(IC,5),P(IC,1)-A0,P(VI,2),2+P(IC,*3),P(IUU
)@@G@@C,3)+FI(6) . S-   @E@@@@        I$     074,04,,,,Q(2,1)  . AT NOFIND,  JUV
)@@G@@UMP TO ATEND@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        END @ @@@@/. *** MISCELLANEOUS UTIUW
)@@G@@LITIES@[@@@@.     @H@@@@. PROCS TO CONSERVE TABLE SPACE BY SAVING ARGUMEUX
)@@G@@NTS IN RE-USABLE ARRAY SPACE  @[@@@@.     @^@@@@          PROC      *0  UY
)@@G@@@I@@@@G$$SVA* NAME                          . SAVE ARRAY P IN STANDARD AUZ
)@@G@@RGUMENT ARRAY     @F@@@@K         EQU       G$CTR(3)+1        . BUMP ARGVA
)@@G@@ PUSHDOWN LEVEL   @D@@@@G$CTR**(3) EQU K                      . SAVE THEVB
)@@G@@ LEVEL@^@@@@G$ARGS**(K) EQU +P-1    @A@@@@N DO P-1 ,G$ARGS**(K,N) EQU +0VC
)@@G@@+P(N) @C@@@@N DO P-1 ,M DO P(N) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU +P(N,M)@F@@@@N DO PVD
)@@G@@-1 ,M DO P(N) , DO P(N,*M) ,G$ARGS**(K,N,M) EQU *0+P(N,M) . @#@@@@      VE
)@@G@@    END     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DECODE A U-FIELD INTO ITS COVF
)@@G@@NSTITUENT ELEMENTS. THIS PROC USES  @G@@@@. SUBTRACTION TO AVOID SPURIOUVG
)@@G@@S R-FLAGS WHICH MIGHT OTHERWISE ARISE.    @F@@@@. IN ADDITION, IT DOES NVH
)@@G@@OT ALTER THE FORM OF THE ORIGINAL U-FIELD,@F@@@@. SINCE IT IS UNKNOWN WHVI
)@@G@@ETHER THE U FIELD ALREADY HAS FORM OR NOT.@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        DEF VJ
)@@G@@@^@@@@G$JBIT(1) EQU 1*/29     @^@@@@G$JBIT(2) EQU 1*/28     @^@@@@G$JBITVK
)@@G@@(3) EQU 1*/27     @^@@@@G$JBIT(4) EQU 1*/26     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$XBITVL
)@@G@@(1) EQU 1*/21     @^@@@@G$XBIT(2) EQU 1*/20     @^@@@@G$XBIT(3) EQU 1*/1VM
)@@G@@9     @^@@@@G$XBIT(4) EQU 1*/18     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@G$HIBI(1) EQU 1*/1VN
)@@G@@7     @^@@@@G$HIBI(2) EQU 1*/16     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@G$JBITS EQU +(I$ 0VO
)@@G@@,017,,,,0)       . MASK FOR J-DESEG @D@@@@G$XBITS EQU +(I$ 0,,,017,,0)  VP
)@@G@@     . MASK FOR X-DESEG @D@@@@G$HBITS EQU +(I$ 0,,,,2,0)         . MASK VQ
)@@G@@FOR H-DESEG @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Q       PROC        *2                .   VR
)@@G@@@B@@@@G$$DCU* NAME                          .   @E@@@@I       EQU     Q(VS
)@@G@@1,1)                . GET FIELD TO SCAN   @G@@@@J       EQU     Q(1,2)  VT
)@@G@@              . AND STARTING SUBFIELD (U-SPEC)  @G@@@@N       EQU     Q(VU
)@@G@@0,1)                . LEVEL OF P (NO OF ASTERISKS)    @C@@@@. OBTAIN MANVV
)@@G@@IPULATABLE UFIELD FROM MASM OR ASM  @D@@@@. NOTE: IF IV(1)<0, THEN IT CAVW
)@@G@@N'T HAVE BEEN EQUF'D    @G@@@@ DO G$MASM , $GO G$$DCU1              . IFVX
)@@G@@ @MASM, SKIP ASM FUMBLING     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. BEGIN ASM PROCESSING  VY
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@JAY(1)  EQU     0   . ASSUME NO EQUF'D J-SPEC   @C@@@@VZ
)@@G@@XRG(1)  EQU     0   . ASSUME NO EQUF'D X-SPEC   @C@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     0 WA
)@@G@@  . ASSUME NO EQUF'D HISPEC   @E@@@@IV(1)   EQU     +P(I,J)             WB
)@@G@@  . GET INITIAL VALUE   @F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0377777777                  ; IFWC
)@@G@@ VALUE HAS EQUF'D J     @D@@@@  ,K DO 4                             ; FOWD
)@@G@@R ALL J-BITS@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-JAY(1))>(G$JBIT(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BITWE
)@@G@@ ON   @E@@@@       ,JAY(1) EQU JAY(1)++G$JBIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    WF
)@@G@@@G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-JAY(1)          . STRIP EQUF'D J FROM OPERANWG
)@@G@@D     @E@@@@JAY(1)  EQU     P(I,J+2)++JAY(1)*/-26 . GET COMPLETE J-SPEC WH
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0777777                     ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D X     WI
)@@G@@@D@@@@  ,K DO 4                             ; FOR ALL X-BITS@E@@@@    , WJ
)@@G@@DO (IV(1)-XRG(1))>(G$XBIT(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,XRG(WK
)@@G@@1) EQU XRG(1)++G$XBIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IVWL
)@@G@@(1)-XRG(1)          . STRIP EQUF'D X FROM OPERAND     @E@@@@XRG(1)  EQU WM
)@@G@@    P(I,J+1)++XRG(1)*/-18 . GET COMPLETE X-SPEC @F@@@@U16     EQU     (JWN
)@@G@@AY(1)<016)++(XRG(1)>0)++P(I,*J)++P(I,*J+1) .    @F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0177777 WO
)@@G@@                    ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D H OR I@G@@@@  ,K DO 2*U16     WP
)@@G@@                    ; FOR BOTH BITS (OF I$ FORM INSTR)@E@@@@    , DO (IVWQ
)@@G@@(1)-HIB(1))>(G$HIBI(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,HIB(1) EQUWR
)@@G@@ HIB(1)++G$HIBI(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @E@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-HIWS
)@@G@@B(1)          . STRIP H AND I BITS  @E@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     HIB(1)*/-16   WT
)@@G@@        . ALIGN H AND I BITS  @E@@@@HBIT    EQU     P(I,*J+1)++(HIB(1)*/WU
)@@G@@-1) . SET TRUE H-BIT    @D@@@@IBIT    EQU     P(I,*J)++(HIB(1)**1) . SETWV
)@@G@@ TRUE I-BIT @^@@@@. GLOBALIZE RESULTS     @F@@@@ DO N=2 , GO G$$DC1     WW
)@@G@@              . CHECK FOR 2 *'S NEEDED    @G@@@@P**(I)   EQU     J+2    WX
)@@G@@               . FORCE NUMBER OF SPECFIELDS     @A@@@@  DO 1-IBIT ,P**(IWY
)@@G@@,J) EQU IV(1)     @A@@@@  DO  IBIT  ,P**(I,J) EQU *IV(1)    @A@@@@  DO 1WZ
)@@G@@-HBIT ,P**(I,J+1) EQU XRG(1)  @A@@@@  DO  HBIT  ,P**(I,J+1) EQU *XRG(1) XA
)@@G@@@^@@@@P**(I,J+2) EQU   JAY(1) @]@@@@ DO 1 , END @F@@@@G$$DC1* NAME      XB
)@@G@@                     . HERE IF P IS 2 LEVELS OUT@F@@@@P***(I)  EQU     JXC
)@@G@@+2                  . FORCE NUMBER OF SPECFIELDS@A@@@@  DO 1-IBIT ,P***(XD
)@@G@@I,J) EQU IV(1)    @A@@@@  DO  IBIT  ,P***(I,J) EQU *IV(1)   @A@@@@  DO 1XE
)@@G@@-HBIT ,P***(I,J+1) EQU XRG(1) @A@@@@  DO  HBIT  ,P***(I,J+1) EQU *XRG(1)XF
)@@G@@@^@@@@P***(I,J+2) EQU   JAY(1)@]@@@@ DO 1 , END @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     XG
)@@G@@@^@@@@. BEGIN MASM PROCESSING @[@@@@.     @E@@@@G$$DCU1* $NAME          XH
)@@G@@              . BEGIN @MASM CODE    @G@@@@IV      EQU     $AP(P(I,J))   XI
)@@G@@        . GET INITIAL VALUE W/O RELOCATION@E@@@@JAY2    EQU     (IV>0)*(XJ
)@@G@@IV**G$JBITS)  . STRIP OFF J-DESEG   @E@@@@JAY1    EQU     P(I,J+2)++JAY2XK
)@@G@@*/-26   . GET COMPLETE J-SPEC @E@@@@XRG2    EQU     (IV>0)*(IV**G$XBITS)XL
)@@G@@  . STRIP OFF X-DESEG   @E@@@@XRG1    EQU     P(I,J+1)++XRG2*/-18   . GEXM
)@@G@@T COMPLETE X-SPEC @E@@@@U16     EQU     (JAY1<016)++(XRG1>0)++P(I,*J)++PXN
)@@G@@(I,*J+1) .  @D@@@@HIB1    EQU     U16*(IV**G$HBITS)  . STRIP OFF HIDESEGXO
)@@G@@@E@@@@HBIT    EQU     P(I,*J+1)++(HIB1*/-17) . SET TRUE H-BIT     @E@@@@XP
)@@G@@IBIT    EQU     P(I,*J)++((HIB1*/-16)**1) . SET TRUE I-BIT  @^@@@@. GLOBXQ
)@@G@@ALIZE RESULTS     @F@@@@          $LEVEL    0,N+1,0           . ADD N+1 XR
)@@G@@STARS TO LABELS   @D@@@@P(I,J)   EQU   [IBIT->'*'!'']P(I,J)-JAY2-XRG2-HIXS
)@@G@@B1  . @A@@@@P(I,J+1) EQU   [HBIT->'*'!'']XRG1 . @^@@@@P(I,J+2) EQU   JAYXT
)@@G@@1     @E@@@@          $LEVEL    0,1,0             . RESET PROPER LEVEL  XU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          END                         . END OF G$$DCU @[@@@@.     XV
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. ----- PATCH UP RETURN ADDR (EXIT INSTR) OF A REMOTE XW
)@@G@@BLOCK @B@@@@.       INVOKED BY 'CALL' AND REMOTE CASES@D@@@@.       SPECXX
)@@G@@S ARE: <BLOCKID>,<BLOK EXIT TARGET ADDR>  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@P          PXY
)@@G@@ROC     *1,0              . DO NOTHING ON PASS 1@G@@@@G$$PRA*    NAME   XZ
)@@G@@                    . HERE IF P(1,1) IS ADDR OF BLOK  @H@@@@ DO G$MASM=0YA
)@@G@@ ,P(1,1)   EQU      G$BSEQ(P(1,1)) . USE ITS SERIAL NUMBER INSTEAD@I@@@@YB
)@@G@@ DO G$MASM=1 ,P(1,1)   EQU    G$BSEQ($AP(P(1,1))) . USE ITS SERIAL NUMBEYC
)@@G@@R INSTEA    @#@@@@G$$PRB*    NAME   @F@@@@K          EQU      P(1,1)    YD
)@@G@@        . SERIAL NO OF TARGET BLOCK @G@@@@ISRB       EQU      (K>0)**(G$YE
)@@G@@FLAG(K,3)=REMOTESUB) . ON IF BLK IS REMOTE@G@@@@ DO ISRB=0 , G$$GFL 2,6 YF
)@@G@@              . ERROR IF BLOK NOT REALLY RMT    @F@@@@ DO ISRB=0 , END  YG
)@@G@@                    . DON'T CLOBBER SPURIOUSLY  @G@@@@G$LABL**(K,4) EQU YH
)@@G@@  P(1,2)            . ESTABLISH JUMPTARG FOR BLK EXIT @G@@@@ DO G$LABL(KYI
)@@G@@,1)>$                     ; IF BLOCK APPEARS AFTER THIS...  @F@@@@  , ENYJ
)@@G@@D                               . THEN NO NEED TO PATCH IT  @G@@@@. WHENYK
)@@G@@ BLOCK PRECEDED US, THE RETURN ADDR IT NEEDED WAS NOT DEFINED     @F@@@@YL
)@@G@@. AT THE TIME THE ENDBEG WAS ASSEMBLED, SO WE MUST PATCH IT UP.   @^@@@@YM
)@@G@@HERE       EQU      $   @F@@@@           RES      G$LABL(K,5)-$     . GOYN
)@@G@@ BACK TO THE ENDBEG     @F@@@@           J        P(1,2)            . FIYO
)@@G@@X UP ITS EXIT INSTR     @E@@@@           RES      HERE-$            . THYP
)@@G@@EN RESTORE IC     @#@@@@           END    @D@@@@/. THINGS TO ADD IN THE YQ
)@@G@@FUTURE-- (NOTES TO MYSELF)-   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.      ENDBEYR
)@@G@@G    SPAWNING AT,<LABEL> WITH IOXI$ (AND MAKE IOXI N.G.)    @G@@@@.     YS
)@@G@@              SINCE IOXI IS ANOTHER WAY OF TERMINATING AN ACTIVITY@[@@@@YT
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.      SPAWN AT,<LABEL> NAME,<NAME-STASH> @G@@@@.           YU
)@@G@@           FORK$ TO AN ACTIVITY AND ACQUIRE A NAME FOR IT   @G@@@@.     YV
)@@G@@                 NOTE THAT NAME IS OWNED BY SPAWNNER, NOT SPAWNEE @[@@@@YW
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@.      DEFINITIONS OF 'CRITICAL' BLOCKS, BOUNDED BY TS, CTS YX
)@@G@@ON DATA     @E@@@@.      AND/OR IMPLEMENTATION OF P/V OR TS QUEUEING USAYY
)@@G@@GE    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. FINISH FALLTHRU OPTIMIZATION FOR JYZ
)@@G@@MGI/TLEM LOOPS    @C@@@@. FLAG AND SURPRESS CODE FOR 0 EXECUTION LOOPS  ZA
)@@G@@@C@@@@. FLAG AND SURPRESS CODE FOR IMPOSSIBLE TESTS   @F@@@@. DO DOUBLE ZB
)@@G@@LINEITEM IF-ELSE: TEST/INST1/NOTEST/INST2, IF AND     @E@@@@.   ONLY IF ZC
)@@G@@NO SIDE EFFECTS AND INST1 DOES NOT ALTER CONTEXT@F@@@@. CASENTRY CALLINGZD
)@@G@@: NORMAL 1,X11 AND 1 INSTR 0,X11 SHOULD SKIP    @D@@@@. DO SPARSE CASES ZE
)@@G@@WITH TESTS INSTEAD OF JUMPTABLES    @B@@@@. OPTIMIZE JUMPS ACROSS BLOCK ZF
)@@G@@BOUNDARIES  @F@@@@          PROC                        . THIS IS A CHARZG
)@@G@@LIE MCCARTHY@E@@@@          END                         . AND A MORTIMERZH
)@@G@@ SNERD@D@@@@.         END                         . *****MASM*****_@@@@@ZI
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@PI     PROC @[@@@@C     @G@@@@C      THIS ELEMENT CONTZJ
)@@G@@AINS THOSE PROCEDURES DESCRIBED IN THE RALPH    @G@@@@C      MANUAL DESIZK
)@@G@@GNED FOR USE UNDER RALPH.  RESULTS ARE NOG GUARANTEED @F@@@@C      WHEN ZL
)@@G@@THEY ARE USED WITH ANY OTHER COMPILER, EVEN BRAND X   @[@@@@C     @E@@@@ZM
)@@G@@               PARAMETER PI = 200262207732504205506043KM3   @[@@@@ END  ZN
)@@G@@@]@@@@CONST  PROC @D@@@@           PARAMETER SQRT2=1.4142135623730950488ZO
)@@G@@0     @D@@@@           PARAMETER DEGREE=0.0174532925199432957     @C@@@@ZP
)@@G@@           PARAMETER E=2.71828182845904523536   @D@@@@           PARAMETZQ
)@@G@@ER SQRT3 =1.73205080756887729352    @C@@@@           PARAMETER LN10 =2.3ZR
)@@G@@025850929949456840@[@@@@ END  @]@@@@MKS    PROC @F@@@@           PARAMETZS
)@@G@@ER C=2.997925E8      @ SPEED OF LIGHT (M/SEC)   @F@@@@           PARAMETZT
)@@G@@ER ME =0.9108E-30    @ MASS OF ELECTRON (KG)    @G@@@@           PARAMETZU
)@@G@@ER EQ =1.6021E-19    @ CHARGE OF ELECTRON (COULOMBS)  @G@@@@           PZV
)@@G@@ARAMETER H=6.6237E-34      @ PLANCK'S CONSTANT (JOULE-SECS) @E@@@@      ZW
)@@G@@     PARAMETER HBAR =1.0540E-34  @ H/2PI (JOULE-SECS) @H@@@@           PZX
)@@G@@ARAMETER NZERO =6.02252E26 @ AVOGADRO'S CONSTANT (MOLEC/KG-MOLE)  @E@@@@ZY
)@@G@@           PARAMETER MP =1.67221E-27   @ MASS OF PROTON     @H@@@@      ZZ
)@@G@@     PARAMETER K=1.3802E-23      @ BOLTZMANN'S CONSTANT (JOULES/DEGREE) AA
)@@G@@@G@@@@           PARAMETER R=8.3143E3        @ GAS CONSTANT (1/(KG-MOLE)AB
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@ END  @]@@@@CGS    PROC @F@@@@           PARAMETER C=2.99792AC
)@@G@@5E10     @ SPEED OF LIGHT (CM/SEC)  @F@@@@           PARAMETER EQ = 4.80AD
)@@G@@298E-10  @ CHARGE OF ELECTRON (ESU) @G@@@@           PARAMETER ME =9.108AE
)@@G@@E-28     @ MASS OF AN ELECTRON (GRAMS)    @G@@@@           PARAMETER H =AF
)@@G@@6.6237E-27     @ PLANCK'S CONSTANT (ERG-SEC)    @E@@@@           PARAMETAG

)@@G@@RO =6.02252E23 @ MOLECULE/GM-MOLE)  @F@@@@           PARAMETER MP =1.672AI

)@@G@@.3143E7        @ GAS CONSTANT (ERG/DEG-MOLE)    @[@@@@ END  @^@@@@SYMMTXAL
)@@G@@         PROC     @A@@@@      DEFINE SYMDIM(K) = (K*K-K)/2+K@G@@@@      AM
)@@G@@DEFINE SYMM(X,I,J,K)=X(MAX(I,J)-MIN(I,J)+1+((2*(K+1)-MIN(I,J))*   @^@@@@AN
)@@G@@     1(MIN(I,J)-1))/2)  @[@@@@ END  @^@@@@PARTWD         PROC     @C@@@@AO
)@@G@@               DEFINE PARTSZ(I,J) = I//(36/J)   @G@@@@               DEFAP

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@AR
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@/.    @A@@@@.   TIDE$ PROCS TO HELP OUR FRIENDS.@[@@@@AS
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.   TIDE$ DOCUMENTATION IN ELEMENT TIDE$  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@AT
)@@G@@P$        PROC      *2                .   @B@@@@T$IDE*    NAME      TIDEAU
)@@G@@$             .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A1,2              .   @D@@@@AV
)@@G@@T$IDER*   NAME      TIDER$            . REOPEN PACKET @B@@@@          T$AW
)@@G@@AD      A0,1              .   @D@@@@T$IDEX*   NAME      TIDEX$          AX
)@@G@@  . CLOSE PACKET  @B@@@@          LMJ       X11,P$(0,0)       .   @B@@@@AY
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PRAZ
)@@G@@OC      *1                .   @E@@@@T$COL*    NAME      TCOL$           BA
)@@G@@  . SET COLUMN POINTER  @F@@@@T$COLN*   NAME      TCOLN$            . REBB
)@@G@@TURN WITH COLUMNUMBER   @D@@@@T$SKIP*   NAME      TSKIP$            . SKBC
)@@G@@IP COLUMNS  @B@@@@          T$AD      A0,1              .   @B@@@@      BD
)@@G@@    LMJ       X11,P$(0,0)       .   @B@@@@          END                 BE
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2                .   BF
)@@G@@@E@@@@T$OCTV*   NAME      TOCTV$            . SP FREE FIELD OCTAL @E@@@@BG
)@@G@@T$OCTF*   NAME      TOCTF$            . SP FIXED FIELD OCTAL@E@@@@T$OCTVBH
)@@G@@D*  NAME      TOCTVD$           . DP FREE FIELD OCTAL @E@@@@T$OCTFD*  NABI
)@@G@@ME      TOCTFD$           . DP FIXED FIELD OCTAL@F@@@@T$DECV*   NAME    BJ

)@@G@@  A0,1              .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A1,2              .   BO
)@@G@@@B@@@@          LMJ       X11,P$(0,0)       .   @B@@@@          END     BP
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2        BQ
)@@G@@        .   @F@@@@T$INTV*   NAME      TINTV$            . SP FREE FIELD BR

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          LMJ       X11,P$(0,0)       .   @B@@@@      BX
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC    BY
)@@G@@  *2                .   @F@@@@T$FLOV*   NAME      TFLOV$            . SPBZ
)@@G@@ FREE FIELD FLOATING    @F@@@@T$FLOF*   NAME      TFLOF$            . SPCA

)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @]@@@@.   MORE    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2  CG
)@@G@@              .   @F@@@@T$GENV*   NAME      TGENV$            . SP FREE CH
)@@G@@FIELD GENERAL     @F@@@@T$GENF*   NAME      TGENF$            . SP FIXEDCI
)@@G@@ FIELD GENERAL    @H@@@@T$GNRV*   NAME      TGNRV$            . SP FREE CJ

)@@G@@          T$AD      A1,1              .   @B@@@@          LMJ       X11,CW
)@@G@@TCLR$         .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@CX
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@.   MASK ROUTINE  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1  CY
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@T$MASK*   NAME      TMASK$            . UP TO 12CZ
)@@G@@ CHARS, RJZF@C@@@@          T$ADD     A0,1              . IF ANY  @B@@@@DA
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,TMASK$        .   @B@@@@          END           DB
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@/     @B@@@@          DEF                       DC
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.   INTERNAL PACKET DEFINITIONS     @[@@@@.     DD
)@@G@@@D@@@@XP        EQU       04                . PACKET POINTER@E@@@@XC    DE
)@@G@@    EQU       05                . CHARACTER POINTER   @D@@@@XW        EQDF
)@@G@@U       06                . WORD POINTER  @E@@@@XA        EQU       07  DG
)@@G@@              . ASCII PACKET POINTER@[@@@@.     @E@@@@TPKT      EQUF    DH
)@@G@@  0,XP              . PACKET LOCATION     @E@@@@IC        EQUF      0,XCDI
)@@G@@              . CHARACTER INDEX     @D@@@@IW        EQUF      0,XW      DJ
)@@G@@        . WORD INDEX    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@BLK       EQUF      TPKT,,S2  DK
)@@G@@        . USER DEFINED - HANDLE BLANKS    @D@@@@BUFLNG    EQUF      TPKTDL
)@@G@@,,S3          . BUFFER LENGTH @D@@@@BUFADR    EQUF      TPKT,,H2        DM
)@@G@@  . BUFFER ADDRESS@[@@@@.     @F@@@@MSK       EQU       TPKT+1          DN
)@@G@@  . 2 WORD BREAK CHAR MASK    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@FDA       EQUF      TPKTDO
)@@G@@+3,,H1        . ADDR OF ASCII TO FIELDATA TABLE @E@@@@BUFEND    EQUF    DP
)@@G@@  TPKT+3,,H2        . LAST WORD OF BUFFER @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SAVEX11   EQDQ
)@@G@@UF      TPKT+4,,H1        . SAVE AREA FOR X11   @E@@@@SXP       EQUF    DR
)@@G@@  TPKT+4,,H2        . SAVE AREA FOR XP    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@SXC       EQDS
)@@G@@U       TPKT+5            . SAVE AREA FOR XC    @E@@@@SXW       EQU     DT
)@@G@@  TPKT+6            . SAVE AREA FOR XW    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@FLAGS     EQDU
)@@G@@U       TPKT+7            . INITIAL CLEAR @E@@@@EXP       EQUF      FLAGDV
)@@G@@S,,S1         . EXPONENT CHARACTER  @E@@@@DIGITS    EQUF      FLAGS,,S2 DW
)@@G@@        . SEEN SOME DIGITS    @F@@@@SIGNIF    EQUF      FLAGS,,S3       DX
)@@G@@  . SIGNIFICANT DIGIT FLAG    @F@@@@XSIGNIF   EQUF      FLAGS,,S4       DY
)@@G@@  . EXCESSIGNIFICANCE FLAG    @G@@@@NPL       EQUF      FLAGS,,S5       DZ
)@@G@@  . DIGITS TO RIGHT OF DECIMAL POINT@E@@@@SIGN      EQUF      FLAGS,,S6 EA
)@@G@@        . SIGN OF MANTISSA    @[@@@@/.    @ @@@@.   MORE PACKET DEFINITIEB
)@@G@@ONS   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@OCTINT    EQUF      TPKT+8,,H1        . INTEGER EC
)@@G@@FLAGS @E@@@@GENINT    EQUF      TPKT+8,,S1        . GENERAL INTEGER SCANED
)@@G@@@D@@@@INTEGER   EQUF      TPKT+8,,S2        . INTEGER FLAG  @D@@@@OCTAL EE
)@@G@@    EQUF      TPKT+8,,S3        . OCTAL FLAG    @F@@@@RGENERAL  EQUF    EF
)@@G@@  TPKT+8,,XH2       . RESTRICTED GENERAL FLAG   @E@@@@GENERAL   EQUF    EG
)@@G@@  TPKT+8,,S4        . GENERAL SCAN FLAG   @E@@@@MODE      EQUF      TPKTEH
)@@G@@+8,,S5        . MODE OF VARIABLE    @E@@@@EXPSIGN   EQUF      TPKT+8,,S6EI
)@@G@@        . SIGN OF EXPONENT    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ALPHA     EQUF      TPKTEJ
)@@G@@+9,,S1        . CONTINUED ALPHA MODE@G@@@@DAL       EQUF      TPKT+9,,S2EK
)@@G@@        . USER DEFINED - DOUBLE ALPHA MODE@E@@@@EXPOCTAL  EQUF      TPKTEL
)@@G@@+9,,S3        . SAVED OCTAL MODE    @E@@@@DL1       EQUF      TPKT+9,,S4EM
)@@G@@        . 1ST USER DELIMITER  @E@@@@DL2       EQUF      TPKT+9,,S5      EN
)@@G@@  . 2ND USER DELIMITER  @F@@@@GOC       EQUF      TPKT+9,,S6        . GEEO
)@@G@@NERAL INTEGER OCTAL FLAG@[@@@@.     @E@@@@SAVEA6    EQU       TPKT+10   EP
)@@G@@        . SAVE AREA FOR A6,A7 @[@@@@.     @D@@@@EXPSAVE   EQU       TPKTEQ
)@@G@@+12           . SAVE MANTISSA @D@@@@OURDLM    EQU       TPKT+12         ER
)@@G@@  . FD DELIMITER  @F@@@@ALNEXT    EQU       TPKT+13           . NEXT CHAES
)@@G@@RACTER TO STORE   @D@@@@ASCNEXT   EQUF      ALNEXT,,H1        . ASCII CHET
)@@G@@AR    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@INTFRC    EQUF      TPKT+14,,S1       . FRACTIONEU
)@@G@@ FLAG @E@@@@NLG       EQUF      TPKT+14,,S2       . NAME CHAR COUNT     EV
)@@G@@@F@@@@DOUBLE    EQUF      TPKT+14,,S3       . DOUBLE PRECISION FLAG     EW
)@@G@@@E@@@@ASC       EQUF      TPKT+14,,S4       . IF 1 - IN ASCII MODE@F@@@@EX
)@@G@@ASO       EQUF      TPKT+14,,S5       . IF 1 - ASCII OUTPUT MODE  @D@@@@EY
)@@G@@REN       EQUF      TPKT+14,,S6       . REENTRY MASK  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@EZ
)@@G@@TEXIT1    EQU       TPKT+15           .   @E@@@@ENDXIT    EQUF      TEXIFA
)@@G@@T1,,H1        . ENDOFCARD RETURN    @D@@@@ERRXIT    EQUF      TEXIT1,,H2FB
)@@G@@        . ERRORETURN    @B@@@@TEXIT2    EQU       TPKT+16           .   FC
)@@G@@@E@@@@BRKXIT    EQUF      TEXIT2,,H1        . BREAKARACTER RETURN @D@@@@FD
)@@G@@RENXIT    EQUF      TEXIT2,,H2        . REENTRY RETURN@[@@@@.     @E@@@@FE
)@@G@@SXA       EQUF      TPKT+17           . SAVE AREA FOR XA    @[@@@@.     FF
)@@G@@@F@@@@SAVEA0    EQU       TPKT+18           . SAVE AREA FOR A0 (ENTIRE) FG
)@@G@@@D@@@@PTWD      EQUF      TPKT+18,,H1       . PARTWORD SAVE @E@@@@ADDR  FH
)@@G@@    EQUF      TPKT+18,,H2       . VARIABLE ADDRESS    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@FI
)@@G@@SAVEXW    EQUF      TPKT+19,,H1       . POINTER SAVES @F@@@@GENAME    EQFJ
)@@G@@U       TPKT+19,,H2       . LINK TO ALPHA ROUTINE     @C@@@@SAVER1    EQFK
)@@G@@UF      TPKT+20,,H1       . RESCANS @E@@@@SAVEXC    EQUF      TPKT+20,,HFL
)@@G@@2       . FOR DECIMAL RESCANS @[@@@@.     @E@@@@MK1       EQU       TPKTFM
)@@G@@+21           . GOOD NAME CHAR MASK @E@@@@MK2       EQU       TPKT+23   FN
)@@G@@        . GOOD NAME CHAR MASK @[@@@@.     @C@@@@T$DEF*    PROC      *0,0FO
)@@G@@              . FOR US  @G@@@@ DO 0=0=0 , $INFO     9 1,3             . FP
)@@G@@OUR GUARANTEE: NO IBANK STORES@B@@@@          END                       FQ
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@/.    @A@@@@.   EXTERNAL PACKET DEFINITIONS     @[@@@@.     FR
)@@G@@@F@@@@P$        PROC      *1,0              . GET ADDRESS OF PACKET     FS
)@@G@@@B@@@@T$FIELDS* NAME                        .   @[@@@@.     @H@@@@TPKT  FT
)@@G@@    EQUF      +(I$ 0,0,0,P$(1,2),P$(1,*1),P$(1,1)) . DEFINE ADDRESS     FU
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@BLK*      EQUF      TPKT,,S2          . USER DEFINED -FV
)@@G@@ HANDLE BLANKS    @D@@@@BUFLNG*   EQUF      TPKT,,S3          . BUFFER LFW
)@@G@@ENGTH @D@@@@BUFADR*   EQUF      TPKT,,H2          . BUFFER ADDRESS@F@@@@FX
)@@G@@MSK*      EQU       TPKT+1            . 2 WORD BREAK CHAR MASK    @G@@@@FY
)@@G@@FDA*      EQUF      TPKT+3,,H1        . ADDR OF ASCII TO FIELDATA TABLE FZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@DAL*      EQUF      TPKT+9,,S2        . USER DEFINED - DOUBLE ALPHGA
)@@G@@A MODE@E@@@@DL1*      EQUF      TPKT+9,,S4        . 1ST USER DELIMITER  GB
)@@G@@@E@@@@DL2*      EQUF      TPKT+9,,S5        . 2ND USER DELIMITER  @F@@@@GC
)@@G@@GOC*      EQUF      TPKT+9,,S6        . GENERAL INTEGER OCTAL FLAG@D@@@@GD
)@@G@@INTFRC*   EQUF      TPKT+14,,S1       . FRACTION FLAG @E@@@@NLG*      EQGE
)@@G@@UF      TPKT+14,,S2       . NAME CHAR COUNT     @E@@@@ASC*      EQUF    GF
)@@G@@  TPKT+14,,S4       . IF 1 - IN ASCII MODE@F@@@@ASO*      EQUF      TPKTGG
)@@G@@+14,,S5       . IF 1 - ASCII OUTPUT MODE  @D@@@@REN*      EQUF      TPKTGH
)@@G@@+14,,S6       . REENTRY MASK  @B@@@@TEXIT1    EQU       TPKT+15         GI
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@ENDXIT*   EQUF      TEXIT1,,H1        . ENDOFCARD RETURN    GJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@ERRXIT*   EQUF      TEXIT1,,H2        . ERRORETURN    @B@@@@TEXIT2GK
)@@G@@    EQU       TPKT+16           .   @E@@@@BRKXIT*   EQUF      TEXIT2,,H1GL
)@@G@@        . BREAKARACTER RETURN @D@@@@RENXIT*   EQUF      TEXIT2,,H2      GM
)@@G@@  . REENTRY RETURN@E@@@@MK1*      EQU       TPKT+21           . GOOD NAMGN
)@@G@@E CHAR MASK @E@@@@MK2*      EQU       TPKT+23           . GOOD NAME CHARGO
)@@G@@ MASK @ @@@@ DO P$(0,1)=0 , END . ALL DONE@E@@@@MODE*     EQUF      TPKTGP
)@@G@@+8,,S5        . MODE OF VARIABLE    @E@@@@ALPHA*    EQUF      TPKT+9,,S1GQ
)@@G@@        . CONTINUED ALPHA MODE@B@@@@          END                       GR
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@/     @B@@@@          DEF                         .   @[@@@@GS
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.   PROCS AND EQU'S USED BY TIDE$ ELEMENTS@[@@@@.     @]@@@@GT
)@@G@@.   MODES   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@SP        EQU       1                 . SIGU
)@@G@@NGLE PRECISION FLOATING @F@@@@DP        EQU       2                 . DOGV
)@@G@@UBLE PRECISION FLOATING @E@@@@DEC       EQU       3                 . SPGW
)@@G@@ DECIMAL INTEGER  @E@@@@DDEC      EQU       4                 . DP DECIMGX
)@@G@@AL INTEGER  @E@@@@OCT       EQU       5                 . SP OCTAL INTEGGY
)@@G@@ER    @E@@@@DOCT      EQU       6                 . DP OCTAL INTEGER    GZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ALPH      EQU       7                 . SP INTEGER ALPHANUMERIC   HA
)@@G@@@F@@@@DALPH     EQU       8                 . DP INTEGER ALPHANUMERIC   HB
)@@G@@@G@@@@ASALPH    EQU       9                 . SP INTEGER ALPHANUMERIC (AHC
)@@G@@SCII) @G@@@@ASDALPH   EQU       10                . DP INTEGER ALPHANUMEHD
)@@G@@RIC (ASCII) @F@@@@NAME      EQU       11                . GENERAL MODE NHE
)@@G@@AME-LABEL   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.   ALLOWABLE RANGES OF MAGNITUDE AND SIGNHF
)@@G@@IFICANCE    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@LO(SP)    EQU       -37               . 10HG
)@@G@@**-38 + 1   @F@@@@DG(SP)    EQU       8                 . 8 DIGITS OF SIHH
)@@G@@GNIFICANCE  @D@@@@HI(SP)    EQU       38                . 10**+37 + 1   HI
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@LO(DP)    EQU       -307              .   @B@@@@DG(DP)HJ
)@@G@@    EQU       20                .   @B@@@@HI(DP)    EQU       308       HK
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@LO(DEC)   EQU       0                 .   HL
)@@G@@@B@@@@DG(DEC)   EQU       11                .   @B@@@@HI(DEC)   EQU     HM
)@@G@@  11                .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@LO(DDEC)  EQU       0         HN
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@DG(DDEC)  EQU       20                .   @B@@@@HI(DDEHO
)@@G@@C)  EQU       20                .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@LO(OCT)   EQU     HP
)@@G@@  0                 .   @B@@@@DG(OCT)   EQU       12                .   HQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@HI(OCT)   EQU       12                .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@LO(DOCHR
)@@G@@T)  EQU       0                 .   @B@@@@DG(DOCT)  EQU       24        HS
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@HI(DOCT)  EQU       24                .   @[@@@@/.    HT
)@@G@@@ @@@@.   ERROR TYPES - FOUND IN A1 @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ERRCHAR   EQU     HU
)@@G@@  1                 . ILLEGAL CHARACTER   @E@@@@ERROCT    EQU       2   HV
)@@G@@              . ILLEGAL OCTAL DIGIT @E@@@@ERRINT    EQU       3         HW
)@@G@@        . INTEGER OVERFLOW    @D@@@@ERRSPO    EQU       4               HX
)@@G@@  . S.P. OVERFLOW @D@@@@ERRSPU    EQU       5                 . S.P. UNDHY
)@@G@@ERFLOW@D@@@@ERRDPO    EQU       6                 . D.P. OVERFLOW @D@@@@HZ
)@@G@@ERRDPU    EQU       7                 . D.P. UNDERFLOW@G@@@@ERRALPH   EQIA
)@@G@@U       8                 . ALPHANUMERICONFUSION (DELIMETER)@G@@@@ERRALCIB
)@@G@@ONT EQU       9                 . BAD MODE FOR CONTINUED ALPHA    @[@@@@IC
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@INDEX     EQU       T$INDEX$          .   @C@@@@ONEZERO   EQID
)@@G@@U       INDEX             . (1,0)   @C@@@@ONEPUT    EQU       INDEX+1   IE
)@@G@@        . (1,PUT) @C@@@@ONEGET    EQU       INDEX+3           . (1,GET) IF
)@@G@@@D@@@@ZEROCNT   EQUF      INDEX+5,,H1       . POINTER STUFF @B@@@@ACOUNTIG
)@@G@@    EQUF      INDEX+5,,H2       .   @B@@@@ZERO      EQU       INDEX+7   IH
)@@G@@        .   @D@@@@T$PROC*   PROC                        . THE GOOD STUFFII
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.   SOME PROCS FOR US   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@IJ
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@.   R3 CONTAINS 1. STORE IT   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PRIK
)@@G@@OC      *1,1              .   @C@@@@SNZ**     NAME      0               IL
)@@G@@  . ENTRY   @H@@@@          SR,P$(1,3)  R3,+(I$ 0,0,0,P$(1,2),2*P$(1,*2)IM
)@@G@@+P$(1,*1),P$(1,1))  .   @B@@@@          END                         .   IN
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@.   GRAB A MASK, SEE IF A3 IS A BREAK CHARACTER.@[@@@@IO
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1,3              .   @C@@@@NBREAK**  NAIP
)@@G@@ME      010               . JNB     @B@@@@BREAK**   NAME      011       IQ
)@@G@@        . JB@C@@@@          DL        P$(1,1),P$(1,2)   . GET MASK@E@@@@IR
)@@G@@          DSL       P$(1,1),0,A3      . GET CHARACTER BIT   @F@@@@      IS
)@@G@@    I$        074,P$(0,0),P$(1,1)-11,P$(1,4),0,P$(1,3) .    @B@@@@      IT
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.   GENERATE A JUMIU
)@@G@@P TABLE     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *72,36            .   IV
)@@G@@@B@@@@GENTBL**  NAME      0                 .   @D@@@@I DO 72 ,NYERP(I) IW
)@@G@@EQU P$(0,1)         . INITIALIZE    @F@@@@I DO P$-1 ,J DO P$(I)-1 ,NYERPIX
)@@G@@(P$(I,J)+1) EQU P$(I,P$(I)) . FILL  @D@@@@I DO 36 , + NYERP(I),NYERP(I+3IY
)@@G@@6)      . BUILD TABLE   @B@@@@          END                         .   IZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @A@@@@.   GRAB A CHARACTER FROM THE BUFFER@[@@@@.     @B@@@@JA
)@@G@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @B@@@@GRAB**    NAME      0   JB
)@@G@@              .   @D@@@@          EX        0,*XC             . GET CHARJC
)@@G@@ACTER @D@@@@  DO P$>1 , JN  A3,+(E$AD 1,1)        . EOCARD RETURN @F@@@@JD
)@@G@@          AX        X11,ONEZERO       . INCREMENT CHAR COUNTER    @B@@@@JE
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.   STORE A JF
)@@G@@CHARACTER (ALPHANUMERICALLY)  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *0,1JG
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@STUFF**   NAME      0                 .   @E@@@@JH
)@@G@@          EX        0,*A1             . INSERT CHARACTER    @B@@@@      JI
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.   ERROR PROC. JUJJ
)@@G@@MP TO RIGHT STUFF @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1,1            JK
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@ERR**     NAME      0                 .   @G@@@@          I$JL
)@@G@@        072,010,P$(1,1),0,0,T$ERROR$ . EX (LMJ A1,ERROR)    @B@@@@      JM
)@@G@@    END                         .   @B@@@@          END                 JN
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.   TIDE$N ENTRY POINTS USED BY OTHER TIDEJO
)@@G@@$ ELEMENTS  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          DEF                         .   JP
)@@G@@@B@@@@SETUP     EQU       T$SETUP$          .   @B@@@@SETUP1    EQU     JQ
)@@G@@  T$SETUP1$         .   @B@@@@SCAN      EQU       T$SCAN$           .   JR
)@@G@@@B@@@@SCAN1     EQU       T$SCAN1$          .   @B@@@@RETURN    EQU     JS
)@@G@@  T$RETURN$         .   @B@@@@RETURN0   EQU       T$RETURN0$        .   JT
)@@G@@@B@@@@RETURN1   EQU       T$RETURN1$        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@T$ENTRJU
)@@G@@Y*  PROC      *0,0              .   @B@@@@          END                 JV
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.   PACKET GENERATION   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@JW
)@@G@@P$        PROC      *18               .   @F@@@@T$PKTGN*  NAME      2   JX
)@@G@@              . GENERAL MODE WITH NAMES   @D@@@@GENAME    EQU       T$TSJY
)@@G@@CAN0$         . HOT STUFF!!!  @D@@@@T$PKTG*   NAME      1               JZ
)@@G@@  . GENERAL MODE  @C@@@@T$PKT*    NAME      0                 . ALL ELSEKA
)@@G@@@D@@@@ DO P$(0,0)<2 ,GENAME EQU 0           . WHEEZE...     @[@@@@/.    KB
)@@G@@@ @@@@.   MORE PACKET GENERATION    @[@@@@.     @D@@@@A('BLK')  EQU     KC
)@@G@@  1                 . BLANK FLAG    @D@@@@A('MSK')  EQU       1D*/','   KD
)@@G@@        . COMMA ONLY    @D@@@@A('DAL')  EQU       0                 . DAKE
)@@G@@LPHA FLAG   @D@@@@A('DL1')  EQU       ''''              . 1ST DELIM     KF
)@@G@@@C@@@@A('DL2')  EQU       '$'               . 2ND     @E@@@@A('GOC')  EQKG
)@@G@@U       0                 . GENINT OCTAL FLAG   @D@@@@A('FRC')  EQU     KH
)@@G@@  0                 . FRACTION FLAG @D@@@@A('NLG')  EQU       12        KI
)@@G@@        . MAX LABELENGTH@E@@@@A('ASC')  EQU       0                 . ASKJ
)@@G@@CII MODE FLAG     @E@@@@A('ASO')  EQU       0                 . ASCII OUKK
)@@G@@TPUT FLAG   @E@@@@A('REN')  EQU       0                 . ASCII REENTER KL
)@@G@@FLAG  @C@@@@A('END')  EQU       0                 . ENDXIT  @C@@@@A('ERRKM
)@@G@@')  EQU       0                 . ERRXIT  @C@@@@A('BRX')  EQU       0   KN
)@@G@@              . BRKXIT  @C@@@@A('RNX')  EQU       0                 . REKO
)@@G@@NXIT  @D@@@@A('FDA')  EQU       0                 . TABLE ADDR    @E@@@@KP
)@@G@@A('MK1')  EQU       000000000037777777700D . 1ST NAME MASK  @E@@@@A('MK2KQ
)@@G@@')  EQU       017770010037777777700D . 2ND NAME MASK  @D@@@@I DO P$-1 ,AKR
)@@G@@(P$(I,1)) EQU P$(I,2)     . FILL FLAGS    @B@@@@F4        FORM      6,6,KS
)@@G@@6,18          .   @G@@@@          F4        0,A('BLK'),P$(1,1),P$(1,2) .KT
)@@G@@ TS,BLANKS,BUFLNG,BUFADR@D@@@@          +         A('MSK')          . BRKU
)@@G@@EAKMASK     @E@@@@          +         A('FDA'),0        . TABLE-ADDR,BUFKV
)@@G@@END   @D@@@@          +         0,0               . SAVX11,SXP    @C@@@@KW
)@@G@@          +         0                 . SXC     @C@@@@          +       KX
)@@G@@  0                 . SXW     @E@@@@          +         0,0,0,0,0,0     KY
)@@G@@  . EXP,EXPOCTAL,EXPSIGN@E@@@@                                      . SIKZ
)@@G@@GN,DOUBLE,GENERAL @E@@@@          +         0,0,0,0,0,0       . GENINT,ILA
)@@G@@NTEGER,OCTAL@H@@@@          +         0,A('DAL'),0,A('DL1'),A('DL2'),A('LB
)@@G@@GOC') . ALPHA,DAL,MODE  @D@@@@                                      . DLLC
)@@G@@1,DL2,GOC   @E@@@@          +         0                 . SAVE AREA FOR LD
)@@G@@A6    @E@@@@          +         0                 . SAVE AREA FOR A7    LE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          +         0,0               . EXPSAVE (OURDLM)    @C@@@@LF
)@@G@@          +         0,0               . ALNEXT  @E@@@@NLG       EQU     LG
)@@G@@  A('NLG')*(P$(0,0)=2) . NLG NEEDS T$PKTGN@F@@@@          +         A('FLH
)@@G@@RC'),NLG,0,A('ASC'),A('ASO'),A('REN') .   @D@@@@          +         A('ELI
)@@G@@ND'),A('ERR') . ENDXIT,ERRXIT @D@@@@          +         A('BRX'),A('RNX'LJ
)@@G@@) . BRKXIT,RENXIT @C@@@@          +         0                 . SXA     LK
)@@G@@@D@@@@          +         0,0               . PTWD,ADDR     @B@@@@ DO P$LL
)@@G@@(0,0)=0 ,     END               .   @D@@@@          +         0,GENAME  LM
)@@G@@        . SAVEXW,GENAME @E@@@@          +         0,0               . GELN
)@@G@@NERAL GOODIES     @B@@@@ DO P$(0,0)=1 ,     END               .   @C@@@@LO
)@@G@@          +         A('MK1')          . MASK    @C@@@@          +       LP
)@@G@@  A('MK2')          . MASK    @B@@@@          END                       LQ
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@/.    @^@@@@.   SCANNING ROUTINES   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$    LR
)@@G@@    PROC      *4                .   @D@@@@T$SCANV*  NAME      TSCANV$   LS
)@@G@@        . FREE FIELD    @C@@@@T$SCANF*  NAME      TSCANF$           . FILT
)@@G@@XED   @C@@@@T$NBRKV*  NAME      TNBRKV$           . FREE    @C@@@@T$NBRKLU
)@@G@@F*  NAME      TNBRKF$           . FIXED   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          T$LV
)@@G@@AD      A0,1              . VARIABLE ADDRESS    @C@@@@          T$AH1   LW
)@@G@@  A0,0              . PARTWD? @C@@@@          T$ADD     A2,2            LX
)@@G@@  . MASK    @C@@@@          T$AD      A1,3              . LENGTH  @C@@@@LY
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,P$(0,0)       . GO DO IT@B@@@@          END     LZ
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.   ADDRESSINGOODIES    @[@@@@MA
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@J$        PROC      *1                .   @E@@@@T$AD*     NAMB
)@@G@@ME      0                 . SINGLE PRECISION    @E@@@@T$ADD*    NAME    MC
)@@G@@  1                 . DOUBLE PRECISION    @D@@@@T$AH1*    NAME      2   MD
)@@G@@              . XI PART OF A  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.   GENERALIZED ADDRESSIME
)@@G@@NG THING    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@J$AD*     PROC                        .   MF
)@@G@@@G@@@@ DO P$(F)>1 , I$    0,0,0,P$(F,2),2*P$(F,*2)+P$(F,*1),P$(F,1) . DOMG
)@@G@@ IT   @C@@@@ DO P$(F)=1 , + 0,P$(F,1)             . SHORT   @B@@@@      MH
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@F         EQU     MI
)@@G@@  J$(1,2)           . FIELD   @B@@@@ DO P$<F+1 , END                    MJ
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@@A         EQU       J$(1,1)           . A REGISTER    @D@@@@MK
)@@G@@J         EQU       P$(F,3)           . J DESIGNATOR  @E@@@@NOJAY     EQML
)@@G@@U       P$(F)<3           . IS THERE A J-FIELD? @C@@@@ DO J$(0,0)=0 , L,MM
)@@G@@XU*NOJAY+J  A,+(J$AD 1) .     @A@@@@ DO J$(0,0)=1 , DL  A,+(J$AD 1)  .  MN
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO J$(0,0)=2 , DO P$(0)>1 , LXI,XU*NOJAY+J  A,+(J$AD 1) .  @B@@@@MO
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@/.    @B@@@@.   EXTRA TIMP
)@@G@@DE$ PROCS TO EASE THE PAIN    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.   TO GRAB THE NEXT CHAMQ
)@@G@@RACTER:     @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.   T$CHAR          EOC-RETURN        . MOMR
)@@G@@VES THE POINTER TO NEXT CHARACTER   @[@@@@.     @I@@@@.   T$CHARN       MS
)@@G@@  EOC-RETURN        . LEAVES POINTER AT CHARACTER JUST GRABBED    @[@@@@MT
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@.         CHARACTER RETURNS IN A3.  @E@@@@.         IF A3 ISMU
)@@G@@ NEGATIVE, END OF CARD WAS ENCOUNTERED    @A@@@@.         EOC-RETURN IS MV
)@@G@@OPTIONAL    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   ASCII CHARACTER (IF ANY) IN A2 AND INCMW
)@@G@@REMENT PORTION OF A3.   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC    MX
)@@G@@  *1                .   @E@@@@T$CHAR*   NAME      2                 . INMY
)@@G@@CREMENT POINTER   @C@@@@T$CHARN*  NAME      0                 . DON'T   MZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@XC        EQU       X5                . CHARACTER POINTER   @H@@@@NA
)@@G@@          I$        072,010,0,XC,P$(0,0),0+((P$(0,0)=0)*T$CHARNL$) . GRANB
)@@G@@B IT  @B@@@@ DO P$>1 , JN       A3,+(E$AD 1,1)    .   @B@@@@          ENNC
)@@G@@D                         .   @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.   FIND THE NEXT (NON) ND
)@@G@@CHARACTER   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2                .   NE
)@@G@@@B@@@@T$FINDA*  NAME      062               .   @B@@@@T$NFINDA* NAME    NF
)@@G@@  063               .   @B@@@@T$FIND*   NAME      052               .   NG
)@@G@@@B@@@@T$NFIND*  NAME      053               .   @B@@@@A         EQU     NH
)@@G@@  P$(0,0)>055       .   @B@@@@F         EQU       P$(0,0)-(010*A)   .   NI
)@@G@@@E@@@@XC        EQU       X5                . CHARACTER POINTER   @E@@@@NJ
)@@G@@TPKT      EQUF      0,X4              . PACKET LOCATION     @E@@@@ENDXITNK
)@@G@@    EQUF      TPKT+15,,H1       . ENDOF CARD RETURN   @C@@@@ DO P$<3 , LNL
)@@G@@X       X11,ENDXIT        . DEFAULT @B@@@@GLOM      EX        0,*XC     NM
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@@          JN        A3,+(E$AD 2,1),(P$<3)*X11 . @C@@@@NN
)@@G@@ DO A ,   LA,U      A3,,A3            . FD PART @F@@@@          I$      NO
)@@G@@  F,U*(P$(1)<3)+P$(1,3),A3-A0,0,0,0+(E$AD 1,1) .@B@@@@          J       NP
)@@G@@  GLOM              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   NQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @^@@@@.   MASK GENERATING PROC@E@@@@.   IDEA SORT OF STOLEN NR
)@@G@@FROM KERN SIBBALD AND BERT HYMAN.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.   THIS PROC GENENS
)@@G@@RATES A LEFT OR RIGHT JUSTIFIED BIT MASK  @B@@@@.   CORRESPONDING TO THENT
)@@G@@ FIELDATA CODE.   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         T$MASKR   'THINGS TO SET' NU
)@@G@@  . (RIGHT JUSTIFIES)   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         T$MASKL   'THINGS TONV
)@@G@@ SET'   . (LEFT JUSTIFIES)    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.   THINGS TO SET ARE 'ANW
)@@G@@' 'B' ETC. ONE MAY ALSO SPECIFY:    @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         'NUM' SENX
)@@G@@TS ALL DIGITS     @A@@@@.         'LET' SETS ALL LETTERS    @A@@@@.     NY
)@@G@@    'SP' SETS EVERYTHING ELSE @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   IF A FIELD IS PRECEENZ
)@@G@@DED BY A * , THAT BIT IS CLEARED. THUSLY, @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         T$OA
)@@G@@MASKR   'LET'  *'Q'     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.   SETS ALL LETTERS EXCEPT Q OB
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   REMEMBER: TIDE$ PROCS USE T$MASKR TO JUSTIFY THEIROC
)@@G@@ RESULTS.   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *80,2             .   OD
)@@G@@@D@@@@T$MASKR*  NAME      1                 . RIGHT JUSTIFY @D@@@@T$MASKOE
)@@G@@L*  NAME      0                 . LEFT JUSTIFY  @F@@@@NUM(1)    EQU     OF
)@@G@@  000017770000000000000000D . NUMBERS RIGHT     @E@@@@NUM(0)    EQU     OG
)@@G@@  000000000000000077740000D . NUMBERS LEFT@F@@@@LET(1)    EQU       0000OH
)@@G@@00000000037777777700D . LETTERS RIGHT     @E@@@@LET(0)    EQU       0077OI
)@@G@@77777760000000000000D . LETTERS LEFT@F@@@@SP(1)     EQU       -(NUM(1)++OJ
)@@G@@LET(1)) . SPECIAL CHARACTERS RIGHT  @F@@@@SP(0)     EQU       -(NUM(0)++OK
)@@G@@LET(0)) . SPECIAL CHARACTERS LEFT   @E@@@@O(1)      EQU       1D        OL
)@@G@@        . A DOUBLE BIT RIGHT  @E@@@@O(0)      EQU       1D*/71          OM
)@@G@@  . A DOUBLE BIT LEFT   @D@@@@SHIFT(1)  EQU       1                 . LEON
)@@G@@FT SHIFT    @D@@@@SHIFT(0)  EQU       -1                . RIGHT SHIFT   OO
)@@G@@@E@@@@P         EQU       P$(0,0)           . WHICH WAY TO SHIFT  @C@@@@OP
)@@G@@ONE       EQU       O(P)              . OURS    @C@@@@F(1)      EQU     OQ
)@@G@@  0D                . ON FLAG @C@@@@G(1)      EQU       0D              OR
)@@G@@  . OFF FLAG@[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @C@@@@I DO P$-1 ,Q(P$(I,1)) EQU 1   OS
)@@G@@        . TURN ON @C@@@@I DO P$-1 ,N(P$(I,1)) EQU P$(I,*1)    . TURN OFFOT
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO Q('NUM') ,F(1) EQU F(1)++NUM(P)   . NUMBERS ON    OU
)@@G@@@D@@@@ DO Q('LET') ,F(1) EQU F(1)++LET(P)   . LETTERS ON    @D@@@@ DO Q(OV
)@@G@@'SP') ,F(1) EQU F(1)++SP(P)     . SPECIALS ON   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@ DO N(OW
)@@G@@'NUM') ,G(1) EQU G(1)++NUM(P)   . NUMBERS OFF   @D@@@@ DO N('LET') ,G(1)OX
)@@G@@ EQU G(1)++LET(P)   . LETTERS OFF   @D@@@@ DO N('SP') ,G(1) EQU G(1)++SPOY
)@@G@@(P)     . SPECIALS OFF  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@I DO 72 , DO Q(I-1) ,F(1) EQU OZ
)@@G@@F(1)++(ONE*/(SHIFT(P)*(I-1))) . CHAR ON   @G@@@@I DO 72 , DO N(I-1) ,G(1PA
)@@G@@) EQU G(1)++(ONE*/(SHIFT(P)*(I-1))) . CHAR OFF  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@FF(1) PB
)@@G@@    EQU       F(1)--G(1)        .   @C@@@@          +         FF(1)     PC
)@@G@@        . GENERATE@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@PD
)@@G@@/.    @G@@@@.   THIS PROC GENERATES AN ASCII TO FIELDATA CONVERSION TABLPE
)@@G@@E. EACH     @G@@@@.   ASCII CHAR IS MAPPED TO EITHER A FIELDATA CHAR (0-PF
)@@G@@63), OR ONE OF    @B@@@@.   SEVERAL FIELDATA FUNNY CHARS (64-71). @F@@@@PG
)@@G@@.   IN TIDE$ NUMERIC SCANS, THE FUNNY CHARS (SUPERCHARGED) ARE:   @[@@@@PH
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@.         64 - NULL. IGNORE THIS COMPLETELY (EXCEPT IN ALPHAPI
)@@G@@ MODE)@C@@@@.         65 - ERROR CHARACTER (ERR ERCHAR)     @C@@@@.     PJ
)@@G@@    66 - BREAKARACTER. TERMINATE FIELD    @F@@@@.         67 - ASCII ALPPK
)@@G@@HA DELIMITER (TRANSFER ASCII CHARACTERS)  @E@@@@.         68 - SUPER BREPL
)@@G@@AKARACTER, TERMINATE FIELD AND LINE.@G@@@@.         69-71 - ARE NORMALLYPM
)@@G@@ TREATED AS ERROR CHARACTERS, BUT CAN     @F@@@@.                 BE TRAPN
)@@G@@NSFORMED INTO BREAKARACTERS BY SETTING THE@D@@@@.                 APPROPPO
)@@G@@RIATE BITS OF THE BREAK MASK. @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         T$ATBL    A(1)PP
)@@G@@,F(I)  A(2),F(2)    A(N),F(N) @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.   A(I) ARE ASCII, AND PQ
)@@G@@F(I) THEIR FIELDATA COUNTERPARTS    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   DEFAULT CONDITPR
)@@G@@IONS - ALL ASCII MAP TO POSSIBLE FD EQUIVALENTS @E@@@@.   (LETTERS TO LEPS
)@@G@@TTERS, NUMBERS TO NUMBERS, ETC), AND ALL  @F@@@@.   ASCII SPECIAL CHARS PT
)@@G@@(0-037) MAP TO '?', WITH THE EXCEPTIONS   @G@@@@.   OF 015(CR), 017(SI),PU
)@@G@@ AND 023(XOFF), WHICH GO TO 68 (SUPERBREAK).    @D@@@@.         016(SO) PV
)@@G@@AND 000(NUL) ARE SET TO 64 (IGNORE).@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC    PW
)@@G@@  *64,32            .   @B@@@@T$ATBL*   NAME                        .   PX
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@A(0)      EQU       64                . NUL     @B@@@@PY
)@@G@@A(015)    EQU       68                . CR@B@@@@A(016)    EQU       64  PZ
)@@G@@              . SO@B@@@@A(017)    EQU       68                . SI@C@@@@QA
)@@G@@A(023)    EQU       68                . XOFF    @C@@@@I DO 014 ,A(I) EQUQB
)@@G@@  '?'               . SPECIAL @B@@@@I DO 3   ,A(I+017) EQU '?'          QC
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@I DO 12  ,A(I+023) EQU '?'            .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@QD
)@@G@@A(040)    EQU       ' '               .   @B@@@@A(041)    EQU       '!' QE
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(042)    EQU       '"'               .   @B@@@@QF
)@@G@@A(043)    EQU       '#'               .   @B@@@@A(044)    EQU       '$' QG
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(045)    EQU       '%'               .   @B@@@@QH
)@@G@@A(046)    EQU       '&'               .   @B@@@@A(047)    EQU       ''''QI
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(050)    EQU       '('               .   @B@@@@QJ
)@@G@@A(051)    EQU       ')'               .   @B@@@@A(052)    EQU       '*' QK
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(053)    EQU       '+'               .   @B@@@@QL
)@@G@@A(054)    EQU       ','               .   @B@@@@A(055)    EQU       '-' QM
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(056)    EQU       '.'               .   @B@@@@QN
)@@G@@A(057)    EQU       '/'               .   @[@@@@/.    @]@@@@.   MORE    QO
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @C@@@@I DO 10 ,A(057+I) EQU 057+I           . DIGITS  @B@@@@QP
)@@G@@A(072)    EQU       ':'               .   @B@@@@A(073)    EQU       ';' QQ
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(074)    EQU       '<'               .   @B@@@@QR
)@@G@@A(075)    EQU       '='               .   @B@@@@A(076)    EQU       '>' QS
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@A(077)    EQU       '?'               .   @B@@@@QT
)@@G@@A(0100)   EQU       '@'               .   @C@@@@I DO 26 ,A(0100+I) EQU 5QU
)@@G@@+I            . LETTERS @B@@@@A(0133)   EQU       '['               .   QV
)@@G@@@B@@@@A(0134)   EQU       '\'               .   @B@@@@A(0135)   EQU     QW
)@@G@@  ']'               .   @B@@@@A(0136)   EQU       '^'               .   QX
)@@G@@@B@@@@A(0137)   EQU       077               .   @D@@@@I DO 040 ,A(0137+IQY
)@@G@@) EQU A(077+I)      . FOLD OVER     @G@@@@I DO P$-1 ,J DO P$(I)-1 ,A(P$(QZ
)@@G@@I,J)) EQU P$(I,P$(I)) . GET NEW STUFF     @E@@@@I DO 32 , + A(4*I-4),A(4RA
)@@G@@*I-3),A(4*I-2),A(4*I-1) . GENERATE  @B@@@@          END                 RB
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.   MORE ASCII PROCS    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@RC
)@@G@@.   READ CARD, SET FLAGS@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2        RD
)@@G@@        .   @C@@@@T$TRD*    NAME      1                 . TREAD$  @C@@@@RE
)@@G@@T$RD*     NAME      0                 . READ$   @B@@@@Q(1)      EQU     RF
)@@G@@  TTRD$             .   @B@@@@Q(0)      EQU       TRD$              .   RG
)@@G@@@D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)*U*(P$(1)<3)+P$(1,3) .     @B@@@@ DO P$RH
)@@G@@>1 , LA,J     A0,+(E$AD 1,1)    .   @D@@@@          T$AD      A1,2      RI
)@@G@@        . PACKET ADDRESS@B@@@@          LMJ       X11,Q(P$(0,0))    .   RJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.   CLRK
)@@G@@EAN UP ASCII IMAGES. DYNAMICALLY INSERT INTO TABLE.   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@RL
)@@G@@P$        PROC      *6                .   @B@@@@T$CLN*    NAME      1   RM
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@T$BLIN*   NAME      0                 .   @B@@@@RN
)@@G@@Q(1)      EQU       TCLN$             .   @B@@@@Q(0)      EQU       TBLIRO
)@@G@@N$            .   @B@@@@R0        EQU       0100              .   @B@@@@RP
)@@G@@          T$AD      A2,3              .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A0,1RQ
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A1,2              .   @B@@@@RR
)@@G@@ DO P$(0,0) ,I DO 3 , T$AD R0+I,I+3   .   @B@@@@          LMJ       X11,RS
)@@G@@Q(P$(0,0))    .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@RT
)@@G@@/.    @A@@@@.   REENTER TCLN$ FROM ESCAPE RETURN@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$    RU
)@@G@@    PROC      *1                .   @B@@@@T$CLNESC* NAME                RV
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A4,1              .   @B@@@@      RW
)@@G@@    J         TCLNESC$          .   @B@@@@          END                 RX
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @C@@@@.   INSERT CHARACTER IN A4 INTO TCLN$ BUFFRY
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @B@@@@RZ
)@@G@@T$CLNADD* NAME                        .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A4,1SA
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          EX        0,*A3             .   @B@@@@SB
)@@G@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.   OPEN PACSC
)@@G@@KET OR REENTER TCLN$ FROM FULL BUFFERETURN@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PRSD
)@@G@@OC      *2                .   @B@@@@T$CLNFUL* NAME      0               SE
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          T$AD      A1,2              .   @B@@@@          T$SF
)@@G@@AD      A0,1              .   @B@@@@          J         TCLNFUL$        SG
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @^@@@@SH
